{["next"]={215},zone="The Misty Mountains",area="Northern High Pass",money={{val="38s 64c"}},d="Thorkell has an important shipment of worm-scales that he has promised to the Elves of Rivendell as they prepare for the possibility of war with Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"24.55S, 7.04E"},name="Thorgest"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=463,scope="n/a",name="Business Before Vengeance",arcs="Scales of Vengeance",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Thorgest",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe worm-caves are to the south-east of Thorgest's dwelling.\nThorgest has asked you to help him collect Fissure-worm scales to make ready a shipment for the armourers of Rivendell.\n* Bring the Fissure-worm Scales to Thorgest\n* Turn in Fissure-worm Scale",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Egladil",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Maliriel has asked you to help her companions complete preparations for the upcoming banquet.",mobs={{locations={"18.60S, 63.85W"},name="Aesbrennil"}},category="Lothlórien",id=464,scope="n/a",name="Buttons and Berries",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,pois={{locations={"17.55S, 64.88W","17.22S, 64.62W","17.14S, 65.48W","17.38S, 64.53W","17.65S, 64.23W","17.72S, 64.50W","16.15S, 66.04W","16.26S, 66.19W","17.79S, 64.05W","16.85S, 65.61W","17.16S, 65.07W","17.29S, 65.21W","16.80S, 65.75W"},name="Button Mushroom"},{locations={"15.89S, 65.03W","16.20S, 63.89W","15.81S, 64.68W","16.72S, 65.05W","16.95S, 64.75W","16.58S, 64.76W","16.27S, 64.17W","15.78S, 64.30W","15.98S, 64.13W","16.56S, 64.57W","16.19S, 64.69W","16.14S, 65.16W","16.01S, 63.83W","16.84S, 64.95W","16.08S, 64.97W"},name="Berry-bearing bush"}},minlevel=55,b="Aesbrennil",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMushrooms can be found along the bank of the stream that borders Imlad Lalaith. Berries can be found in the forest north of Imlad Lalaith.\nAesbrennil would like you to gather berries and button-like mushrooms for the meal she is preparing for the evening festivities.\n* Use Berry-bearing bush\n* Use Button Mushroom\nObj 2:\nAesbrennil is at the Vinyards of Lórien, south of Imlad Lalaith.\nYou should bring the mushrooms and berries back to Aesbrennil.\n* Talk to Aesbrennil\n* Turn in Berries\n* Turn in Mushroom (Level 1)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nen Harn",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+500 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="5s 50c"}},d="The woods of Bree-land can be dark and mysterious. Some places are darker than others....",mobs={{locations={"22.34S, 43.98W"},name="Walt Whitrose"},{locations={"22.12S, 52.06W"},name="Gil Sandheaver"}},selectoneof={{val="Crusher of Tarbúrz",id="7000910B"},{val="Tarbúrz's End",id="7000910D"},{val="Menedhdail",id="700090F7"}},category="Bree-land",id=465,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1280},name="By Axe and Fire",arcs="Into the Woods",level=21,minlevel=16,b="Walt Whitrose",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWalt Whitrose mentioned that Gil Sandheaver had come from the north and east, where the lake meets the woodland.\nWalt Whitrose believes it is worth looking into Gil Sandheaver's claims that trees were walking near Nen Harn, if for no other reason that Gil's peace of mind.\n* Find Gil Sandheaver's walking tree\nObj 2:\nWalt Whitrose is at his camp on the western edge of Nen Harn.\nYour discovery should be explained to Walt Whitrose at his camp, if only to warn him that such things exist out here in the northernmost parts of Bree-land.\n* Talk to Walt Whitrose in Nen Harn\nObj 3:\nGil Sandheaver is at the Hengstacer Farm, west of Walt Whitrose's camp at Nen Harn and north of Bree-town.\nWalt Whitrose told you to take news of your victory to Gil Sandheaver, with the reassurance that he may once again walk the woods in peace.\n* Talk to Gil Sandheaver at the Hengstacer Farm"},
{area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="7s"}},d="Some of the guests within The Forsaken Inn have developed a taste for Arinora's pork dishes.",mobs={{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Arinora"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Simple Athelas Essence",id=70001346},{q="(x2)",val="Simple Celebrant Salve",id=70001049}},category="Lone-lands",id=466,scope="n/a",name="By Hoof and Crook",arcs="Inn Troubles",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Forsaken Ale",id="700007CB"}},level=22,minlevel=17,b="Arinora",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBoars can be found in the area surrounding The Forsaken Inn and north-east among the Weather Hills.\nArinora asked you to collect boar-feet and leg-bones for a dish she serves at The Forsaken Inn.\n* Bring boar-bones and boar-feet to Arinora\n* Turn in Boar Leg-bone\n* Turn in Boar-foot"},
{["next"]={896},area="The Hill",zone="The Shire",d="Lobelia insists on fireworks for her birthday party. The only possible way to get them in time for her party is to recover the fireworks stolen from Hyacinth Took.",mobs={{locations={"33.60S, 71.13W","33.61S, 71.13W"},name="Thain Paladin Took II"},{locations={"31.35S, 71.13W"},name="Shirriff Robin Smallburrow"},{locations={"29.36S, 71.33W"},name="Lobelia Sackville-Baggins"}},category="Shire",id=467,scope="n/a",prev={433},name="By Hook or By Crook",arcs="Lobelia's Fireworks",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Lobelia Sackville-Baggins",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nShirriff Robin Smallburrow can be found inside the Ivy Bush in the centre of Hobbiton.\nSince it will be three months before Hyacinth Took can have more fireworks ready for Lobelia Sackville-Baggins, a month too late for her party, Lobelia instructed you to speak with Robin Smallburrow about recovering Hyacinth's stolen fireworks.\n* Talk to Shirriff Robin Smallburrow\nObj 2:\nThe Thain can be found at the Great Smials in Tuckborough, south of Hobbiton.\nLobelia Sackville-Baggins sent you to speak with Robin Smallburrow about Hyacinth Took's stolen fireworks, but Shirriff Smallburrow told you the matter was outside of his jurisdiction. He suggested you speak with Paladin Took, Thain of the Shire.\n* Talk to Thain Paladin Took II",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Culang has assigned you the task of finding a number of hidden supply caches scattered throughout Nan Laeglin. If you can uncover these caches, the Grey Company will be able to pass through the land swiftly without having to risk bartering with potentially hostile locals.",mobs={{locations={"69.39S, 13.75W"},name="Culang"}},category="Enedwaith",id=468,scope="n/a",name="Cache and Carry: Arrows",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"58.48S, 12.19W","60.77S, 13.06W","65.61S, 17.95W","70.57S, 16.50W","60.88S, 14.92W","66.57S, 15.85W","56.57S, 15.16W"},name="Wayfarer's Rune"},{locations={"56.54S, 15.43W","66.47S, 15.60W","66.27S, 17.98W","60.77S, 13.06W","57.79S, 12.02W","61.09S, 14.32W","70.66S, 16.92W"},name="Buried Cache"}},minlevel=60,b="Culang",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe cache is somewhere a short distance north-west of Lhanuch where you can see a small set of curious ruins. You should be able to find the Rangers' rune on an overlook above them.\nCulang has sent you to find a cache of arrows, which can be found sixty paces south of a Rangers' rune.\n* Use Wayfarer's Rune\n* Find the Rangers' rune hidden on an overlook above the curious ruins north-west of Lhanuch\nObj 2:\nThe cache of arrows is buried about sixty paces directly south of the Rangers' rune, along the base of a small cliff there.\nCulang asked you to find a hidden cache of arrows.\n* Use Buried Cache\n* Search for the cache about sixty paces south of the Rangers' rune at the base of a small cliff.\nObj 3:\nCulang is at his camp in Nan Laeglin, south-east of the cache.\nYou have discovered the Rangers' cache and dug up the arrows hidden there. Now you should return with them to Culang.\n* Talk to Culang\n* Turn in Spare Quiver",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Culang has assigned you the task of finding a number of hidden caches of supplies scattered throughout Nan Laeglin. If you can uncover these supplies, the Grey Company will be able to pass through swiftly without as having to resort to bartering with possibly hostile locals or stopping to hunt.",mobs={{locations={"69.39S, 13.75W"},name="Culang"}},category="Enedwaith",id=469,scope="n/a",name="Cache and Carry: Bandages",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"58.48S, 12.19W","60.77S, 13.06W","65.61S, 17.95W","70.57S, 16.50W","60.88S, 14.92W","66.57S, 15.85W","56.57S, 15.16W"},name="Wayfarer's Rune"},{locations={"56.54S, 15.43W","66.47S, 15.60W","66.27S, 17.98W","60.77S, 13.06W","57.79S, 12.02W","61.09S, 14.32W","70.66S, 16.92W"},name="Buried Cache"}},minlevel=60,b="Culang",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe cache of bandages he says is hidden east of Lhanuch. The rune-marker should be carved on a solitary tree somewhere directly east of the Lhanuch.\nCulang has sent you to retrieve a hidden cache of bandages.\n* Use Wayfarer's Rune\n* Find the Rangers' rune hidden on a solitary tree east of Lhanuch\nObj 2:\nThe cache of bandages is buried in a small copse of trees directly north-east of the rune.\nCulang asked you to retrieve a hidden cache of bandages.\n* Use Buried Cache\n* The cache should be buried in a small copse of trees north-east of the Rangers' rune\nObj 3:\nCulang is at his camp in Nan Laeglin, to the south of the cache.\nYou have discovered the Rangers' cache and dug up the bandages hidden there. Now you should return with them to Culang.\n* Talk to Culang\n* Turn in Infused Bandage",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Culang has assigned you the task of finding a number of hidden caches of supplies scattered throughout Nan Laeglin. If you can uncover these supplies, the Grey Company will be able to pass through swiftly without as having to resort to bartering with possibly hostile locals or stopping to hunt.",mobs={{locations={"69.39S, 13.75W"},name="Culang"}},category="Enedwaith",id=470,scope="n/a",name="Cache and Carry: Healing Draughts",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"58.48S, 12.19W","60.77S, 13.06W","65.61S, 17.95W","70.57S, 16.50W","60.88S, 14.92W","66.57S, 15.85W","56.57S, 15.16W"},name="Wayfarer's Rune"},{locations={"56.54S, 15.43W","66.47S, 15.60W","66.27S, 17.98W","60.77S, 13.06W","57.79S, 12.02W","61.09S, 14.32W","70.66S, 16.92W"},name="Buried Cache"}},minlevel=60,b="Culang",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe cache of healing draughts is hidden well to the south of Lhanuch, on the border of the Lich Bluffs. The Rangers' rune may be found atop a green hill with many trees upon it.\nCulang has sent you to retrieve a hidden cache of healing draughts.\n* Use Wayfarer's Rune\n* Find the  rune atop a green hill with several trees upon it\nObj 2:\nThe cache of potions would be buried around the base of a boulder some forty paces west into a stand of evergreens.\nCulang asked you to retrieve a hidden cache of healing draughts.\n* Use Buried Cache\n* Find the Rangers' cache forty paces west of the rune, buried around a boulder among a stand of evergreens\nObj 3:\nCulang is at his camp in Nan Laeglin, north-east of the cache.\nYou have discovered the Rangers' cache and dug up the healing draughts hidden there. Now you should return with them to Culang.\n* Talk to Culang\n* Turn in Curative Potion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={478,476,477},area="Fordirith",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Braigiar has assigned you the task of finding a number of hidden caches of supplies scattered throughout northern Enedwaith. If you can uncover these supplies, the Grey Company will be able to pass through swiftly without having to resort to bartering with hostile locals or stopping to hunt.",mobs={{locations={"58.69S, 14.58W"},name="Braigiar"}},category="Enedwaith",id=471,scope="n/a",name="Cache and Carry: Hidden Foodstuffs",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"58.48S, 12.19W","60.77S, 13.06W","65.61S, 17.95W","70.57S, 16.50W","60.88S, 14.92W","66.57S, 15.85W","56.57S, 15.16W"},name="Wayfarer's Rune"},{locations={"56.54S, 15.43W","66.47S, 15.60W","66.27S, 17.98W","60.77S, 13.06W","57.79S, 12.02W","61.09S, 14.32W","70.66S, 16.92W"},name="Buried Cache"}},minlevel=60,b="Braigiar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBraigiar has pointed you to a cache of foodstuffs he says is hidden in the northwestern area of Fordirith. He believes it should be buried about twenty paces west from a tree marked with the Ranger's rune.\n* Use Wayfarer's Rune\n* Find the hidden rune\nObj 2:\nBraigiar said the cache of foodstuffs would be buried about twenty paces west of the rune-marked tree.\n* Use Buried Cache\n* Find the Rangers' cache of foodstuffs\nObj 3:\nBraigiar is at Echad Dagoras in Fordirith.\nYou discovered the Rangers' cache and dug up the foodstuffs hidden there. Now you should return with them to Braigiar.\n* Take the food to Braigiar\n* Turn in Preserved Foodstuffs"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Grey Company"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Fordirith",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Amarion has told you of a particularly valuable hidden cache secreted within the Black Dens -- unfortunately this was before it was overrun by the deadly Shadow Wolves. If you can recover the Weapon-lore scrolls hidden away within, it would be a considerable boon to the Grey Company.",mobs={{locations={"58.69S, 14.56W"},name="Amarion"}},category="Enedwaith",id=472,scope="n/a",prev={198,475},name="Cache and Carry: Hidden Lore",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"58.48S, 12.19W","60.77S, 13.06W","65.61S, 17.95W","70.57S, 16.50W","60.88S, 14.92W","66.57S, 15.85W","56.57S, 15.16W"},name="Wayfarer's Rune"},{locations={"56.54S, 15.43W","66.47S, 15.60W","66.27S, 17.98W","60.77S, 13.06W","57.79S, 12.02W","61.09S, 14.32W","70.66S, 16.92W"},name="Buried Cache"}},minlevel=60,b="Amarion",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAmarion has pointed you to a cache of weapon-lore scrolls he says is hidden within the Black Dens, south-east of Echad Dagoras. He believes it should be buried about fifty paces west of the cavern floor marked with the Rangers' rune.\n* Use Wayfarer's Rune\n* Find the hidden rune\nObj 2:\nAmarion said the cache of weapon-lore scrolls would be buried about fifty paces west of the rune-marked cavern.\n* Use Buried Cache\n* Find the Rangers' cache of scrolls\nObj 3:\nAmarion is at Echad Dagoras, north-west of the Black Dens.\nYou have discovered the Rangers' cache and dug up the scrolls of lore hidden there. Now you should return with them to Amarion.\n* Take the scrolls to Amarion\n* Turn in Scroll of Weapon-lore",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Fordirith",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Braigiar has assigned you the task of finding a number of hidden caches of supplies scattered throughout northern Enedwaith. If you can uncover these supplies, the Grey Company will be able to pass through swiftly without as having to resort to bartering with hostile locals or stopping to hunt.",mobs={{locations={"58.69S, 14.58W"},name="Braigiar"}},category="Enedwaith",id=473,scope="n/a",prev={475},name="Cache and Carry: Hidden Medicine",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"58.48S, 12.19W","60.77S, 13.06W","65.61S, 17.95W","70.57S, 16.50W","60.88S, 14.92W","66.57S, 15.85W","56.57S, 15.16W"},name="Wayfarer's Rune"},{locations={"56.54S, 15.43W","66.47S, 15.60W","66.27S, 17.98W","60.77S, 13.06W","57.79S, 12.02W","61.09S, 14.32W","70.66S, 16.92W"},name="Buried Cache"}},minlevel=60,b="Braigiar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBraigiar has pointed you to a cache of herbs and poultices he says is hidden in the northeastern area of Fordirith. He believes it should be buried among a stand of pine trees eighty paces north of a boulder marked with the Rangers' rune.\n* Use Wayfarer's Rune\n* Find the hidden rune\nObj 2:\nBraigiar said the cache of medicines would be buried among a grove of pine trees roughly eighty paces north of a large rune-marked boulder.\n* Use Buried Cache\n* Find the Rangers' medicine cache\nObj 3:\nBraigiar is at Echad Dagoras, south-west of the medicine-cache.\nYou have discovered the Rangers' cache and dug up the medicines hidden there. Now you should return with them to Braigiar.\n* Take the medicines to Braigiar\n* Turn in Medicinal Herbs"},
{area="Fordirith",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Some among the northern Rangers have often made the trek through Dunland to Gondor, far to the South. During these prior journeys, they left cleverly hidden caches in case one of their number should be injured or in desperate need of supplies during their journies. Now with the Grey Company travelling into the south they have decided to collect these caches to ensure they are ready to deal with the dangers ahead.",mobs={{locations={"58.69S, 14.58W"},name="Braigiar"}},category="Enedwaith",id=474,scope="n/a",prev={475},name="Cache and Carry: Hidden Weapons",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"58.48S, 12.19W","60.77S, 13.06W","65.61S, 17.95W","70.57S, 16.50W","60.88S, 14.92W","66.57S, 15.85W","56.57S, 15.16W"},name="Wayfarer's Rune"},{locations={"56.54S, 15.43W","66.47S, 15.60W","66.27S, 17.98W","60.77S, 13.06W","57.79S, 12.02W","61.09S, 14.32W","70.66S, 16.92W"},name="Buried Cache"}},minlevel=60,b="Braigiar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBraigiar has pointed you to a cache he believes is hidden in the Southern area of Fordirith. First, you should find a marker rune atop a small rounded hill with several trees upon it.\n* Use Wayfarer's Rune\n* Find the hidden rune\nObj 2:\nBraigiar said the cache of weapons would be buried about sixty paces east of the rune marker, amid a jumble of large boulders.\n* Use Buried Cache\n* Find the Rangers' weapons-cache\nObj 3:\nBraigiar is at Echad Dagoras, north of the weapon-cache.\nYou have discovered the Rangers' cache and dug up the weapons hidden there. You should return with them to Braigiar.\n* Take the weapons to Braigiar\n* Turn in Sturdy Blade"},
{["next"]={562},area="Celondim",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Thinglaer's brother Calengil also seeks to restore the ancient Elf-ruins within Ered Luin and requires your aid.",mobs={{locations={"24.16S, 93.01W"},name="Calengil"},{locations={"27.90S, 92.22W"},name="Thinglaer"}},category="Ered Luin",id=475,scope="n/a",prev={1059},name="Calengil's Vigil",arcs="Hallowed Ground",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Thinglaer",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCalengil can be found in the Elf-refuge of Duillond to the north.\nThinglaer has asked you to seek out his brother Calengil and lend him what aid you may.\n* Talk to Calengil"},
{["next"]={1403},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="7s 42c"}},d="Aragorn has charged you with bringing word to the Ranger Calenglad that Narsil will be reforged.",mobs={{locations={"12.72S, 67.18W"},name="Calenglad"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Greater Celebrant Salve",id=70000856},{q="(x2)",val="Greater Athelas Essence",id=70000855}},category="Evendim",id=476,scope="n/a",prev={2329},name="Calenglad Remained",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Superior Steak and Kidney Pie",id="7000336E"}},level=32,minlevel=27,b="Aragorn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCalenglad is at Tinnudir, an island on the eastern shore of Lake Nenuial, in Evendim, far to the west of the Trollshaws.\nAragorn has given you a letter to present to Calenglad and advice concerning the nature of respect: that it cannot be bought, but must be earned. With the aid of Calenglad, Aragorn hopes that you can recover the Silithar needed to reforge Narsil.\n* Talk to Calenglad\n* Turn in Aragorn's Letter"},
{["next"]={1309},area="Nan Tornaeth",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="Calenthon has sent his falcon Malloval to scout the Rhudaur ruins in Nan Tornaeth a long while ago, but Malloval has not returned.",mobs={{locations={"28.16S, 15.29W"},name="Calenthon"}},category="Trollshaws",id=477,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={364},name="Calenthon and Malloval",arcs="Abominations",level=38,minlevel=33,b="Calenthon",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe slope south of Calenthon would be an ideal location at which to blow the whistle he gave you to summon Malloval.\nCalenthon gave you a whistle with which to summon his falcon, Malloval. He suggested you take friends for safety.\n* Use Calenthon's Whistle\nObj 2:\nAfter using Calenthon's whistle, you heard a falcon cry above the ruins near the bridge of Thoniant in Nan Tornaeth.\n* Locate Malloval\n* Use Calenthon's Whistle\nObj 3:\nCalenthon is south of the bridge of Thoniant, in Nan Tornaeth.\nCalenthon will be pleased to hear that you defended his falcon, Malloval, from the Hillmen of Rhudaur and waits for you to return with his whistle.\n* Talk to Calenthon\n* Turn in Calenthon's Whistle"},
{["next"]={2293},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",d="Since Lobelia Sackville-Baggins paid to acquire the ingredients for her fireworks, Hyacinth Took has recruited you to help her gather them.",mobs={{locations={"28.08S, 70.10W"},name="Hart Holeman"},{locations={"33.44S, 71.42W"},name="Hyacinth Took"}},category="Shire",id=478,scope="n/a",prev={3254},name="Calling for Charcoal",arcs="Lobelia's Fireworks",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Hyacinth Took",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHart Holeman is at his home in the centre of Overhill.\nHyacinth Took appreciated the saltpetre you brought back with you, though she chided you for letting Cam Puddifoot talk you into hunting wolves for him. Now she has asked you to speak with Hart Holeman about the charcoal she needs.\n* Talk to Hart Holeman",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1724},area="Northern Barrow-downs",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="3s 20c"}},d="Guides out of Bree fear for their charges as the terror of the Barrow-downs are now unleashed in the north. This unexpected course has forced them to drastic action.",mobs={{locations={"31.69S, 56.20W"},name="Reginald Sickleweed"}},category="Bree-land",id=479,scope="n/a",name="Calming the Wake",arcs="Calming the Wake",receive={{val="Grimbriar's Bracelet",id="7000910C"}},level=18,minlevel=13,b="Reginald Sickleweed",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWights can be found throughout the Barrow-downs, east and north of the guides' camp.\nThrough their own folly, the guides have become trapped. While here they wish to assist the Watchers of Bree by reducing the threat found in the Barrow-downs.\n* Defeat wights in the northern Barrow-downs (12)\nObj 2:\nYou will find Reginald Sickleweed at the makeshift camp between the Old Forest and the northern Barrow-downs.\nYou should now return to Reginald Sickleweed and tell him that you have begun to purge the wights from the Barrow-downs.\n* Talk to Reginald Sickleweed in the Barrow-downs"},
{["next"]={485},area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="7s"}},d="Lily Sandheaver, a well-to-do hobbit of Bree, collects pottery gathered from old ruins in the Lone-lands. She is waiting for her latest delivery, but it has not arrived.",mobs={{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Candac Brightwood"},{locations={"29.44S, 52.30W"},name="Lily Sandheaver"}},category="Bree-land",id=480,scope="n/a",name="Candac's Delay",arcs="Traders from Bree",receive={{val="Brightwood's Vest",id="70000C5E"}},level=22,minlevel=17,b="Lily Sandheaver",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCandac Brightwood is at the Forsaken Inn, east of the Midgewater Marshes along the Great East Road.\nCandac Brightwood supplies Lily Sandheaver with pottery and other collectibles from the ruins of the kingdom of Arnor. Lily gave you a letter for Candac and sent you to The Forsaken Inn to deliver it and inquire about the delay.\n* Deliver Lily's letter to Candac\n* Turn in Letter to Candac"},
{area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="8s 50c"}},d="Candac Brightwood buys pottery and other trinkets from the Munces at The Forsaken Inn, but they are having trouble gathering enough pieces with the goblins creeping into the Lone-lands.",mobs={{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Candac Brightwood"}},selectoneof={{val="Brightwood's Bracelet",id="7001D211"},{val="Candac's Salvation",id="7001D214"}},category="Lone-lands",id=481,scope="n/a",name="Candac's Obligation",arcs="Traders from Bree",level=23,minlevel=18,b="Candac Brightwood",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAncient bits of pottery may be found in the valley beneath the ruins of Minas Eriol, south-east of The Forsaken Inn. Candac Brightwood is at The Forsaken Inn.\nCandac Brightwood has asked you to search for bits of pottery with which he can continue his trade.\n* Use Ancient Pottery Shards\nObj 2:\nCandac Brightwood is at The Forsaken Inn.\nCandac Brightwood has asked you to search for bits of pottery with which he can continue his trade.\n* Talk to Candac Brightwood\n* Turn in Arnorian Pottery"},
{area="Dar-gazag",zone="Ettenmoors",d="At the head of the enemy forces stand the Captain-Generals. Their symbols garner great favour amongst Angmar's army, and presenting these to Mordirith will undoubtedly earn you favour with Lugbúrz.",category="Ettenmoors",id=482,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=2000}},name="Captain-Generals' Symbols",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Chieftain Durulkum",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nCaptain-Generals can only be found at locations where the enemy army holds power.\nChieftain Durulkum directed you to collect Captain-General symbols from enemy leaders and then return to him.\n* Return to Chieftain Durulkum at Dâr-gazag ()\n* Turn in Captain-General's Symbol",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="43s 40c"}},d="A legend of the Battle of Fornost mentioned a great captain of the armies of Fornost who led his men onto the field, only to betray his oath and lead them against King Arvedui instead.",mobs={{locations={"7.89S, 55.96W"},name="Emma Slee"}},selectoneof={{val="Riamul's Purger",id="70006B59"},{val="Swift-riders",id="70006B2B"},{val="Faervaib",id="70006A8D"},{val="Ronolf",id="70006BB8"}},category="Fornost",id=483,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={937},name="Captain Riamul",arcs="Free the Fallen",receive={{val="Silivrengil",id="700069DA"}},level=41,minlevel=36,b="Emma Slee",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRiamul is somewhere within Fornost.\nEmma Slee has asked you to seek the shade-captain, Riamul, and bring him word of his pardon. She hopes that his freedom will allow his men to follow.\n* Find Riamul and release his spirit\nObj 2:\nEmma Slee is at the Fornost camp.\nRiamul, loyal to Angmar even in death, refused his pardon, believing that the Witch-king would restore him. You should return to Emma Slee and let her know you had to defeat him to free his men.\n* Talk to Emma Slee"},
{["next"]={1604},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="30s 24c"}},d="A great host of Orcs spilled through Ram Dúath, driving the Men of the North Downs from their farms. Esteldín, home of the few remaining Dúnedain of the North, was spared discovery. It is from there that the Rangers begin to plan their counter-offensive against the black tide of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.63S, 41.42W"},name="Arohir"}},category="North Downs",id=484,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1978},name="Captains of the Black Tide",arcs="Shattering the Alliance",level=33,minlevel=28,b="Arohir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Ongbúrz captains Thorgal, Shum-batar, and Dombrî were last seen among the Warg-keepers in the Orc-camp in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\nArohir told you of the discovery of three captains of the Ongbúrz tribe who command the lower ranks of the Orc-host: Thorgal, Shum-batar, and Dombrî. He believes that their deaths will throw the lower ranks into confusion. He recommends you do not attempt this task alone.\n* Kill 1 Captain Shum-batar\n* Kill 1 Captain Thorgal\n* Kill 1 Captain Dombrî\nObj 2:\nArohir awaits word of your success at Esteldín.\nArohir provided you the names of three Blogmal captains amongst the Orcs in Dol Dínen where the Warg-keepers patrol. With these captains slain, you should report back to Arohir.\n* Talk to Arohir"},
{area="Nan Sirannon",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="You discovered the corpse of a slain Redhorn-goat, which Hjór took as a good sign that his friend may yet live, for the corpse was expertly skinned.",mobs={{locations={"50.48S, 7.80W"},name="Hjór"}},category="Eregion",id=485,scope="n/a",prev={65},name="Caradhras the Cruel",arcs="Caradhras the Cruel",receive={{val="Hjór's Grief",id="700160F9"}},level=50,c={"* The Frozen Dwarf-corpse is in the Redhorn Gate at [46.5, 2.9W]"},pois={{locations={"46.51S, 2.92W"},name="Frozen Dwarf-corpse"}},minlevel=45,b="Hjór",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThorlák entered the Redhorn Gate in search of Durin's Tower in the eastern parts of the pass, upon Zirakzigil.\nHjór hopes that Thorlák has found some shelter in the upper reaches of the Redhorn Gate.\n* Find Thorlák\nObj 2:\nHjór is in Echad Dúnann, south-west of the Redhorn Gate.\nYou should return to Hjór and inform him of Thorlák's death.\n* Talk to Hjór at Echad Dúnann"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="4s"}},d="The Barrow-downs were once a haven of the Rangers of Cardolan. They fell long ago and became of place of terror beneath the shadow of the Witch-king of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"31.82S, 51.41W"},name="Anglinn"}},category="Reputation",id=486,scope="n/a",name="Cardolan Trinket -- Introduction",level=20,minlevel=15,b="Anglinn",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarrows lie scattered across the Northern and Southern Barrow-downs. Anglinn is at the Bree Hunting Lodge in Bree-town, east of the Barrow-downs.\nThe Ranger Anglinn has asked you to banish the wights beneath the Northern and Southern Barrow-downs and bring him trinkets of ancient Cardolan which they might be carrying.\n* Bring the Cardolan trinket to Anglinn\n* Turn in Cardolan-trinket",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hithlad",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="The Angmarim within the city of Carn Dûm have a desire for the heartwood cut from the centre of the Leafcull-trees within the Grimwood. He has offered you a reward for collecting the heartwood.",category="Grimwood",id=487,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=750}},name="Carving Out Hearts",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Chieftain Torbok",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGrimwood-heartwood can be found on the Leafcull-trees, though you may possibly find it in the fallen logs as well.\nChieftain Torbok directed you to recover and return Grimwood-heartwood to him.\n* Return to Chieftain Torbok at the Grimwood Lumber-yamp ()\n* Turn in Grimwood Heartwood",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="Pynti-peldot is the primary source of cat-tusk scrimshaw in Forochel. The Lossoth carve the large tusks during the long winter nights, and sell them to south-landers.",mobs={{locations={"11.50N, 69.89W"},name="Kimmo"}},category="Forochel",id=488,scope="n/a",prev={1143,1045},name="Cat-tusk Scrimshaw",receive={{val="Scrimshaw's Fate",id="7000E6E6"}},level=46,c={"* Kill Kalpa-kitas around the camp and the enclave south of the camp"},minlevel=41,b="Kimmo",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKalpa-kita can be found in and around their den at Leijona-kotin, as well as roaming the rest of Itä-ma.\nKimmo has asked you to bring him some tusks from the kalpa-kita which roam Forochel.\n* Turn in Kalpa-kita Tusk\nObj 2:\nKimmo is at Pynti-peldot. You should return to him with the kalpa-kita tusks.\n* Talk to Kimmo\n* Turn in Kalpa-kita Tusk"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="You discovered a brooch of Lórien within the spiderwebs of the Water-works.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=489,scope="n/a",name="Caught in Clear Webs",receive={{val="Geirfast's Rejoice",id="700163AE"}},level=55,minlevel=50,b="Brooch of Lórien",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGeirfast is in the Twenty-first Hall.\nThe brooch of Lórien you found is marked with the name Geirfast.\n* Talk to Geirfast in the Twenty-First Hall\n* Turn in Brooch of Lórien",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Esteldín relied on the Earth-kin to aid in safeguarding the pass to Angmar in the north. Their recent corruption has forced the Rangers' hand and they must now strike down their former allies to ensure that the few remaining Earth-kin allies are safeguarded.",mobs={{locations={"9.44S, 39.93W"},name="Asikko"},{locations={"9.78S, 42.20W"},name="Elúr"}},category="North Downs",id=490,scope="n/a",prev={1799},name="Caught in the Wake",arcs="Stemming the Tide",receive={{val="Silver Locket",id="700069D8"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="Elúr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAsikko, chieftain of the Suuri-lehmä, can be found at the Earth-kin camp located along the hills north of the eastern entrance to Esteldín.\nWhen you returned with the stolen Earth-kin weapons, Elúr asked you for one final favour. He gave you a letter and sent you to find Asikko, the chieftain of the Earth-kin still loyal to the defence of Ram Dúath.\n* Talk to Asikko\n* Turn in Letter to the Earth-kin\nObj 2:\nElúr resides at Esteldín.\nElúr will be pleased to learn that Asikko, the Earth-kin chieftain, pledged that he and his people intend to honour their oaths and will fight against the Rauta-lehmä.\n* Talk to Elúr"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="9s 24c"}},d="Nora Strawley has given you unexpected, but joyful, tidings: her husband survived his encounter with the Gauredain.",mobs={{locations={"37.10S, 14.04W"},name="Tongannel"},{locations={"30.98S, 52.67W"},name="Nora Strawley"}},selectoneof={{val="Forest-walker",id="7000D2A8"},{val="Tongannel's Joy",id="7000D2E2"},{val="Tongannel's Shield",id="700161B6"},{val="Grove-tender's Gloves",id="7000D2AA"}},category="Trollshaws",id=491,scope="n/a",prev={496},name="Cause for Joy",arcs="An End to Enterprise",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Nora Strawley",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTongannel is at Echad Candelleth, the Elf-camp in Tâl Bruinen.\nNora Strawley has given you the happy news that her husband survived his ordeal and has asked you to bring one of the wooden figurines to Tongannel as a sign of friendship.\n* Talk to Tongannel\n* Turn in Wooden Figurine"},
{["next"]={495},area="Tâl Bruinen",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="9s 24c"}},d="Tongannel wants you to bring the sad news to Nora Strawley and to give her the wooden figurines you recovered.",mobs={{locations={"37.10S, 14.04W"},name="Tongannel"},{locations={"30.98S, 52.67W"},name="Nora Strawley"}},category="Trollshaws",id=492,scope="n/a",prev={253},name="Cause for Sorrow",arcs="An End to Enterprise",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Tongannel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNora Strawley lives somewhere in the town of Bree.\nTongannel has asked you to bring the wooden figurines to Nora Strawley in the hope that she will be able to sell them and make enough coin to live on for a time.\n* Talk to Nora Strawley\n* Turn in Wooden Figurine"},
{area="Rath Teraig",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="Tralli Hammerfist is concerned about the cave-claws burrowing beneath the barricades. Until recently, the barricades have been strong enough to withstand the goblin assaults, but the cave-claws have now weakened them.",mobs={{locations={"22.12S, 96.83W"},name="Tralli Hammerfist"}},category="Ered Luin",id=493,scope="n/a",name="Cave-claws in the Narrows",arcs="The Southern Road",level=12,minlevel=8,b="Tralli Hammerfist",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMilkeyes can be found beyond the barricades south of the dwarf-camp.\nTralli Hammerfist has asked you to enter Rath Teraig and kill off a number of Milkeyes, to prevent them from gnawing at the barricades.\n* Defeat Milkeyes within Rath Teraig  (9)\nObj 2:\nTralli Hammerfist is at his camp beyond the barricade at the northern entrance to Rath Teraig.\nYou should return to Tralli Hammerfist and let him know that you have done as he asked.\n* Talk to Tralli Hammerfist",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The priests and priestesses of the cult of Angmar have a strong influence over many of the Hillman-tribes.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Maerchiniath"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Pure Flask of Conhuith",id="7000C638"},{q="(x2)",val="Pure Healing Draught",id="7000C640"}},category="Angmar",id=494,scope="n/a",name="Cease and Desist",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Maerchiniath",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe priests and priestesses of Angmar can be found near the altars throughout the Bails of Himbar, which lie to the west of Gath Forthnír.\nMaerchiniath has instructed you to go forth and defeat the priests of Angmar, bringing him their staves as evidence of your success.\n* Turn in Angmarim Staff\nObj 2:\nGath Forthnír is to the east of Himbar.\nYou should return to Maerchiniath with the staves you took from the priests of Angmar.\n* Talk to Maerchiniath\n* Turn in Angmarim Staff"},
{area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+700 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="Behind the wights and fell spirits of Imlad Balchorth, there are even greater terrors.",mobs={{locations={"6.88N, 25.87W"},name="Sigar"}},category="Angmar",id=495,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Cease the Reign",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Sigar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGaunt-men can be found in western Imlad Balchorth, west of Myrkworth.\nSigar has asked you to destroy the Gaunt-men in Imlad Balchorth.\n* Defeat Gaunt-men in Imlad Balchorth (5)\nObj 2:\nSigar is at Myrkworth, east of Imlad Balchorth.\nHaving killed the Gaunt-men as asked, return to Sigar in Myrkworth and tell him the deed is done.\n* Talk to Sigar"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The Rangers of the North confer ceremonial blades upon the greatest of their heroes.",category="Reputation",id=496,scope="n/a",name="Ceremonial Blades -- Introduction",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Cannasgam",repeatable="No",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nCannasgam is at Tinnudir in Evendim.\nCannasgam has asked you to forge the ceremonial blades, which the Rangers of the North confer upon their greatest heroes.\n* Present your Ceremonial Blades to Cannasgam at Tinnudir\n* Turn in Ceremonial Blade"},
{area="",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="The Rangers of the North once sent their youths coming of age upon pilgrimages to notable sites of their forefathers, but war has necessitated a change.",category="Reputation",id=497,scope="n/a",name="Ceremonial Dagger -- Introduction",level=35,c={"* Craft 5 daggers and return to Cannasgam at Tinnudir in Evendim"},minlevel=30,b="Cannasgam",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCannasgam is at Tinnudir in Evendim.\nCannasgam has asked you to forge ceremonial daggers and bring them to her.\n* Present your Ceremonial Daggers to Cannasgam at Tinnudir\n* Turn in Ceremonial Dagger",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",d="Balhest is the Angmarim who has taken up residence within the ancient palace of Annuminas, claiming it for his fallen king.\nBalhest has great love for his sorceresses, and if he sees them all suitably weakened, he will intervene to save them. When he does, show them how weak their master is.",category="Annúminas",id=498,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Balhest",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nBalhest is in the throne room of Ost Elendil.\n* Reach Balhest\nObj 2:\nBalhest must be defeated while his sorceresses watch his demise.\nBalhest has great love for his sorceresses, and if he sees them all suitably weakened, he will intervene to save them. When he does, show them how weak their master is.\n* Defeat Balhest\nObj 3:\nWith Balhest defeated and their minds reeling, defeat the High Sorceresses and end their misery.\n* Defeat the High Sorceresses"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="In the Sword-hall of Dol Guldur, the fell champions of the arena train tirelessly to hone their prowess in battle. You have been challenged to prove your superior might by defeating all three champions of the Sword-hall at once.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=499,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=2000}},name="Challenge: Battle of the Sword-hall (Daily)",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Dol Guldur",id="7001D28D"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Sword-hall is at Dol Guldur, the enemy stronghold of Mirkwood.\nYou should endeavour to defeat all three champions of the Sword-hall at once -- a great challenge that will earn you much renown.\n* Engage and defeat all three champions at once",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="In the Water-works, ancient Caeryg rumble through the halls. Their presence is causing the Dwarves of Khazad-dûm great concern. They often fight in packs and are quite dangerous to those who attempt to disturb them.",category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=500,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Caeryg",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Lothlórien",id="7001D28C"}},level=60,minlevel=55,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nDeep in the Water-works, there are great Caeryg lurking. You should find them in the hidden rooms of the Water-works and banish them from Moria.\n* Defeat the Caeryg in the southern room\n* Defeat the Caeryg in the western room\nObj 2:\nIn the farthest depths of the Water-works, there is the greatest of Caeryg, Caerlug. Defeat him to claim your reward.\n* Defeat Caerlûg"},
{d="Chieftain Gûrsh is a foul uruk with a curious soft-spot in his blackened heart for craban.\nTo shatter the confidence of the invaders, defeat Gûrsh and all his Dark-wing Warders together. None of the Dark-wing Warders may be defeated before Gûrsh has returned to the Library.",category="Eregion",id=501,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Chieftain Gûrsh",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nChieftain Gûrsh is very fond of his craban-warders.\nTo shatter the confidence of the invaders, defeat Gûrsh and all his Dark-wing Warders together.\n* Call forth Chieftain Gûrsh\nObj 2:\nChieftain Gûrsh is very fond of his craban-warders.\nTo shatter the confidence of the invaders, defeat Gûrsh and all his Dark-wing Warders together.\n* Defeat Chieftain Gûrsh\n* Defeat the Dark-wing Warders"},
{d="Those most loyal to Ivar have been granted exceptional protections. A true hero will tackle this adversity, not avoid it.",category="In Their Absence",id=502,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Corrupted Champions",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nIvar is waiting deep within Ost Dunhoth.\n* Reach Ivar\nObj 2:\nIvar's champions draw power from dark corruptions. To show the gauntlord you fear no evil power defeat Ivar and his champions without removing any corruptions.\n* Defeat Ivar and his Champions"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+900 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="29s 68c"}},d="Not all who occupy Garth Agarwen are given over to corruption. Some are taken from their homes or the sites where they worked and brought to the ruins where they are enchanted and taught a new way of thought through foul magic. The Créoth warlord, Dúnlang, is possessed of the gifts of Angmar and captures members of the Eglain to corrupt and turn into mindles minions of the Red-maid.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=503,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Dúnlang",receive={{val="Eglain Token",id="7001E6E2"}},level=32,minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nDúnlang was given the power to enslave weaker minds, and many of the Eglain have gone missing over the years. He makes his home deep within the ruins of the Garth Agarwen Fortress and is in the process of converting members of the Eglain into devoted members of the Créoth clan. You should save them from the influence of this man, but not harm them in the process.\n* Defeat Dúnlang",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="High up in Zirakzigil, there lies a cave. This cave was a means to harness the light of the sun and bring it down to the depths of Moria. Years of neglect have brought this system to its knees, and now the cave is home to merrevail, Wargs, and other dark creatures.",category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=504,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Ergoth (Daily)",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Lothlórien",id="7001D28C"}},level=60,minlevel=55,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nYou should defeat the morroval-queen, Ergoth while she is at her strongest. If you weaken her first, you will not be able to claim the greatest of rewards.\n* Defeat Ergoth"},
{d="A true hero of Middle-earth never turns their backs, regardless of the terrors they are faced with.",category="In Their Absence",id=505,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Face Your Fears",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nConfront your fear. When the moment comes, do not turn your back on it.\n* Reach the fear boss\nObj 2:\nDo not turn your back on your fear.\n* Defeat Durin's Bane"},
{d="The School at Tham Mirdaín was renowned for it's knowledge and learning.\nThe forces here have learned all they can and are now burning the books to keep the information from the hands of the Free Peoples. The books must be saved.",category="Eregion",id=506,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Flames of Knowledge",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe greatest of the school's knowledge is kept within the north annex.\n* Reach the North Annex\nObj 2:\nThe School at Tham Mirdaín did not contain much of the knowledge that the library did, but there were several tomes of great import.\nThe forces here have learned all they can and are now burning the books to keep the information from the hands of the Free Peoples. The books must be saved.\n* Use Bookstand"},
{zone="Bree-land",area="Southern Barrow-downs",d="Ancient dead has arisen within the Great Barrow.\nGaerthel will come to his brothers aid if enough decayed have fallen in battle and none of the tomb-wights have been defeated. Once in battle, both brothers must meet their defeat before any tomb-wights do.",category="Great Barrows",id=507,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Gaerdring and Gaerthel",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nGaerdring and Gaerthel, ancient warrior brothers, have arisen deep within the maze of the Great Barrow.\n* Approach Gaerdring and Gaerthel\nObj 2:\nGaerthel will enter the battle early if sufficiently taunted.\n* Defeat Crawling Arms\nObj 3:\nDefeat the brothers together.\n* Defeat Gaerdring\n* Defeat Gaerthel"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Fil Gashan is the barracks and training grounds of the Orcs in Moria. Within those walls, a fearsome general has been readying his troops for an assault upon the Elves of Lothlórien to the east of Khazad-dûm. Brogur and Bósi's dwarves, wishing to reclaim Moria, intend to prevent this at any cost, for they would see the Elves and dwarves reinstate old alliances for the good of both.",category="Dungeons of Moria",id=508,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: General Talug (Daily)",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Moria",id="7001D28B"}},level=60,minlevel=55,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nFil Gashan is far to the south-west of the Twenty-first Hall, and General Talug can be found in the depths of that place.\nSigurd has challenged you to use stealth and wit to conquer General Talug, the leader of a great Orc-host, without defeating too many of his sentries.\n* Defeat General Talug"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="37s 10c"}},d="It may seem impossible that so small a creature can have so large an impact on the world, but it is the case that the small insects driven to madness by the caretaker of the woods of Agamaur are such creatures. Grimbark has long held control of the Arboretum at the behest of the Red-maid and with his corruption has driven all living denizens of the swamp mad.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=509,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Grimbark",receive={{val="Eglain Token",id="7001E6E2"}},level=32,c={"* For tactics on Grimbark, see Grimbark.\n* The fight will be harder on the Warden since the majority of the Fist Gambits are AoE taunt dots.  This means that the beehives might be accidentally affected with the taunt dots."},minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Huorn Grimbark is lost to the corruption that has long plagued this land. It is an unfortunate end for a once noble creature, but Grimbark cannot be redeemed.\nYou are tasked with destroying Grimbark, but you should avoid harming the bees under his dominion.\n* Defeat Grimbark, but do not destroy the beehives",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Helegrod",zone="The Misty Mountains",d="Any trace of Grisgart's influence must be destroyed.\nEvery drake egg and Ice-drake hatchling within Grisgart's chamber must be destroyed.",titles={{val="Drake Dropper"}},category="Helegrod",id=510,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Grisgart",receive={{val="Helegrod Mark",id="700216C0"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nEvery drake egg and Ice-drake hatchling within Grisgart's chamber must be destroyed.\n* Destroy all of the Ice-drake hatchlings",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="In the Dark Delvings, the most forsaken depths of Khazad-dûm, the Nameless hold sway over the bitter shadows. Like other creatures that hide in the Black Pit that is Moria, the Nameless dread light, but they will not turn aside from any opportunity to spread corruption and dismay.",category="Dungeons of Moria",id=511,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Gurvand (Daily)",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Moria",id="7001D28B"}},level=60,minlevel=55,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe region of the Dark Delvings is far to the south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nThe dwarf Sigurd has challenged you to make your way into the Dark Delvings and defeat the Gurvand without the help of runes, wishing you to prove your worth as the great warrior you are rumoured to be.\n* Defeat the Gurvand"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="No living Man, Elf, hobbit, or dwarf will want to set foot in Skûmfil, grave of the Orcs, feeding and breeding ground of vile kergrim and slavering gredbyg. There, the Orcs pile their dead, and there, disgusting creatures feast on rotten waste.",category="Dungeons of Moria",id=512,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Hwandrin (Daily)",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Moria",id="7001D28B"}},level=60,minlevel=55,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nHwandrin and her brood ever belch unwholesome filth upon the corpse-ridden halls of Skûmfil, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nSigurd has challenged you to defeat Hwandrin in Skûmfil as proof of your worth as a warrior. Her threat is great, yet few are wilful enough to withstand the menace of such an old and malevolent being.\n* Defeat Hwandrin"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Once a great and beautiful crossroads of Moria, the Grand Stair is a vile haven of many of the gathered tribes of Orcs. Igash, regarded as a leader by all of the varied groups, gathers tribute from every tribe to give to Mazog, the mightiest and greatest of Orcs in Khazad-dûm. The dwarves wish to unseat Igash's Orcs from this Grand Stair and stop Mazog from receiving valuable and unsavoury gifts.",category="Dungeons of Moria",id=513,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Igash (Daily)",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Moria",id="7001D28B"}},level=60,minlevel=55,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nMany tribes of Orcs prowl the Grand Stair, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nGeirr has asked you to defeat Igash in the Grand Stair without defeating any other members of the Moria Orc-tribes. In doing so, you will assist in efforts to reclaim that crossroads for the dwarves and prove your great worth to Sigurd.\n* Defeat Igash"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="37s 10c"}},d="Ivar the Blood-hand is a Gaunt-lord, a being of great and dark power, made in mockery of the Wizard Radagast the Brown. He is weakened at the moment, not only by his meddling with Radagast, but also as he continues to raise his army of Dead within the bounds of Garth Agarwen.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=514,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Ivar",receive={{val="Eglain Token",id="7001E6E2"}},level=32,c={"* Ivar's wight-banners do not move and have low Morale. These banners provide with buffs and makes the encounter more challenging. Move Ivar to a place away from the banners. Throughout the battle, additional wights will spawn from the two mounds on his left and right.\n* Tank - make sure to grab the adds and kill them before going back on Ivar.\n* DPS - make sure to kill the adds before going back to Ivar.\n* Failure on killing the adds will mean more adds will spawn in addition to the ones that aren't killed and will result in a wipe."},minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nIvar the Blood-hand must fall. His strength must fade, and he must become what he should have been all along: a memory of a bygone age. His strength is born of raising the Dead and returning those that have fallen back to battle.\nThis is his role, and stopping him from achieving this role, no matter how minutely, will see that the mark of his hand is removed from the land. To do this, you must ensure that his banners remain so that at his death his power is split between them.\n* Defeat Ivar the Blood-hand without destroying his banners",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="The Forges of Khazad-dûm, once a glorious smith-hall for the Dwarves of Moria, have fallen into evil hands. The Forges now serve the Orc-masters of Moria and are used to build all manner of weapons and war-machines for an assault against fair Lothlórien. Brogur and Bósi's dwarves, wishing to reclaim Moria, intend to prevent this at any cost, for they would see the Elves and dwarves reinstate old alliances for the good of both peoples.",category="Dungeons of Moria",id=515,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Kranklûk (Daily)",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Moria",id="7001D28B"}},level=60,minlevel=55,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe Forges of Khazad-dûm are to the south-west of the Twenty-first Hall.\nThe dwarf Sigurd has challenged you to fight your way to the Orc Kranklûk. Narkû, who stands between you and your intended quarry, will undoubtedly alert Kranklûk that you are coming. You will have a limited amount of time in which to accomplish your task after the warning goes out.\n* Defeat Narkû to alert Kranklûk of your presence\nObj 2:\nKranklûk is in the heart of the Forges of Khazad-Dûm.\nNarkû has been defeated, and Kranklûk is alerted to your presence. Sigurd believes that Kranklûk is the driving force in the Forges of Khazad-dûm; he wants you to defeat your foe to hinder the efforts of the Orcs.\n* Defeat Kranklûk before the time runs out"},
{d="Wounds cut deep and bleed long. Show Ivar you do not fear his power by completing the Wound Wing in hasty fashion.",category="In Their Absence",id=516,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Leader of the Pack",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nTo begin, you must open the path forward. Once open, be prepared to aggressively move forward.\n* Open the gates forward\nObj 2:\nThe mammoths must be brought to the end of the paths and then defeated. Do this as quickly as possible in order to show Gortheron you are a force to be reckoned with.\n* Defeat the Mammoth Riders"},
{area="Dol Guldur",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="The Wargs of Dol Guldur gain unusual strength from eating specially-prepared meat. You have been challenged to defeat the Wargs who have already consumed this vile feed, right down to the last morsel.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=517,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=2000}},name="Challenge: Meat for the Warg-pens (Daily)",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Medallion of Dol Guldur",id="7001D28D"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe slavering Wargs reside in the Warg-pens of Dol Guldur.\nYou must goad the Wargs to consume all the slabs of vile meat located throughout the encounter, then attempt to best them in their strengthened state.\n* Clear the pens of all meat-slabs"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="37s 10c"}},d="The Red-maid is lost -- or so it seems -- to the corruption wrought upon her land at the hands of corrupt Men. These Men stand before her, ready to sacrifice themselves for the Red-maid, and they deserve this fate. However, the nobility of your blood will be a greater reward for her, and when these Men fall before her willingly, she will see that the noble are attempting to destroy her and ignoble keeping her this way.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=518,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Naruhel",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Eglain Token",id="7001E6E2"}},level=32,minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Créoth will sacrifice themselves to the Red-maid to restore her strength and connexion to the corruption within the swamp. These Men deserve nothing better than death, and your presence in standing against the Red-maid may alert some part of her to the folly of her ways. You should let these Men die and strengthen the Red-maid, then defeat her. Perhaps a piece of her will understand that the corruption has grown too great, and she must return to the natural world which she was once part of.\n* Aid in the cleansing of the Red-maid",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",d="Nengon is a foul and ancient darkwater ruling over Glinghant, the ancient gardens of Annúminas.\nNengon and his darkwater brethren must all be defeated in rapid succession, lest they are allowed a chance to recover and reform. From the time the first falls, there is a small window of time in which all must fall as well.",category="Annúminas",id=519,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Nengon",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nNengon resides at the far end of the gardens.\n* Begin the battle with Nengon\nObj 2:\nNengon and his darkwater brethren must all be defeated in rapid succession, lest they are allowed a chance to recover and reform.\n* Defeat Nengon and his brethren\nObj 3:\nNengon and his darkwater brethren must all be defeated in rapid succession, lest they are allowed a chance to recover and reform.\n* Defeat Nengon and his brethren"},
{zone="Bree-land",area="Southern Barrow-downs",d="Ancient dead have arisen within the Great Barrow.\nSambrog's crypt must be disturbed before he is engaged. Once disturbed, you must simply survive the onslaught the Wight Lord will bring down upon you.",category="Great Barrows",id=520,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Sambrog",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nSambrog can be found in the greatest depths of the Great Barrow.\n* Find Sambrog\nObj 2:\nSambrog can be found in the greatest depths of the Great Barrow.\n* Use Crypt\nObj 3:\nSambrog hates those who disturb and defile his crypt.\n* Defeat Sambrog"},
{d="Disease has run rampant through the depths of Ost Dunhoth. Nature has been fouled by the poisoned waters. Once you have been marked with one of the diseases you must not change it.",category="In Their Absence",id=521,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Sticky Sap",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe poisoned waters must gather into a stagnant pool at some point.\n* Proceed to the stagnant pool\nObj 2:\nOnce a huorn has marked you with sap, do not replace it with the other huorn's sap.\n* Defeat the huorns"},
{area="Helegrod",zone="The Misty Mountains",d="Storvâgûn is capable of bringing down the very peak of Helegrod.\nStorvâgûn must be defeated without anyone being caught by the avalanche from the peak of Helegrod.",titles={{val="Diminisher of Giants"}},category="Helegrod",id=522,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Storvâgûn",receive={{val="Helegrod Mark",id="700216C0"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nStorvâgûn must be defeated without anyone being caught by the avalanche from the peak of Helegrod.\n* Defeat Storvâgûn",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Bree-land",area="Southern Barrow-downs",d="Ancient dead have arisen within the Great Barrow.\nEach time Thadúr calls forth his allies a brazier fills with oil. All three braziers must be burning before the Gauntlord falls.",category="Great Barrows",id=523,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Thadúr the Ravager",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThadúr the Ravager, an ancient Gaunt-lord, has arisen deep within the watery depths of the Great Barrow.\n* Approach Thadúr the Ravager\nObj 2:\nThadúr the Ravager, an ancient Gaunt-lord, has arisen deep within the watery depths of the Great Barrow.\n* Defeat Thadúr the Ravager\nObj 3:\nThadúr the Ravager, an ancient Gaunt-lord, has arisen deep within the watery depths of the Great Barrow.\nObj 4:\nThadúr the Ravager, an ancient Gaunt-lord, has arisen deep within the watery depths of the Great Barrow.\n* Defeat Thadúr the Ravager\nObj 5:\nThadúr the Ravager, an ancient Gaunt-lord, has arisen deep within the watery depths of the Great Barrow.\nObj 6:\nThadúr the Ravager, an ancient Gaunt-lord, has arisen deep within the watery depths of the Great Barrow.\n* Defeat Thardúr the Ravager\nObj 7:\nThadúr the Ravager, an ancient Gaunt-lord, has arisen deep within the watery depths of the Great Barrow.\nObj 8:\nThadúr the Ravager, an ancient Gaunt-lord, has arisen deep within the watery depths of the Great Barrow.\n* Defeat Thardúr the Ravager"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Once filled with the thunder of dwarf-hammers and smiths, the Halls of Crafting are now dominated by foul Orcs. Led by the evil Black Uruk, Thaguzg, they are building weapons for a massive assault upon Lothlórien itself.",category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=524,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Thaguzg (Daily)",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Lothlórien",id="7001D28C"}},level=60,minlevel=55,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nYou should defeat Thaguzg without his minions' assistance. They must not reach him, or great woe will befall your fellowship.\n* Defeat Thaguzg"},
{area="Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",d="Dithrik has given you the final task in your quest for advancement as a Guardian.",category="Guardian",id=525,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1893},name="Challenge the Darkness",arcs="The Path of the Defender of the Free",receive={{val="Jewel of the Sentinel",id=70018385},{val="Khuzdul Tablets",id="70017AC6"}},level=58,minlevel=58,b="Dithrik",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDefeat the World Eater in the Dark Delvings\n* Use Stone Slab\n* Defeat Nightshine\nObj 2:\nReturn to Dithrik in the Foundations of Stone\n* Talk to Dithrik\n* Turn in Rotten Slab of Meat"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Having discovered Drugoth's secret citadel, you must clear it of all threats.  An ancient glacier has been made into a breeding ground for the undead.\nThis quest will be cancelled if you leave the Glacier Fortress before completing it.",category="In Their Absence",id=526,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: The Glacier Fortress - Survival",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x5)",val="Medallion of the North-men",id=70025341}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nDrugoth the Death-monger has relocated from the Misty Mountains and made his new home in the largest glacier in Forochel Bay.  Now, his mad rambling mind is planning an attack on Annuminas down south.\nYou must stop this attack before it happens by killing all four of Drugoth's lieutenants.\n* Kill all four of Drugoth's Lieutenants\nObj 2:\nHaving killed Drugoth's lieutenants, you must advance to the top of the Glacier and defeat Drugoth and his two guardians.\n* Kill the 2 Guardians\n* Kill Drugoth"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="In Sammath Gûl, the chambers of the Necromancer, the most evil of spirits were summoned and sent forth to do Sauron's bidding. One such spirit still remains, locked behind the doors of Sammath Gûl.\nThis quest will be cancelled if you leave Sammath Gûl before completing it.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=527,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=2000}},name="Challenge: The Guardian of Sammath Gûl (Daily)",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Dol Guldur",id="7001D28D"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGorothúl lies deep within Sammath Gûl, a chamber of Dol Guldur.\nYou should defeat Gorothúl and attempt to unlock the doors behind which the spirit Demafaer resides.\n* Defeat Gorothúl\nObj 2:\nDemafaer stands guard within the chambers of the Necromancer.\nThe great doors are unlocked; you should defeat the great fell-spirit, Demafaer, servant of the Necromancer.\n* Defeat Demafaer",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Atop Barad Guldur stands the Lieutenant of Dol Guldur and his fell beast. You are challenged to defeat the Lieutenant before slaying his evil mount.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=528,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=2000}},name="Challenge: The Lieutenant and his Steed (Weekly)",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Dol Guldur",id="7001D28D"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Lieutenant of Dol Guldur stands at the top of Barad Guldur with the cruel fell beast he rides from tower to tower.\nYou should  endeavour to defeat the Lieutenant of Dol Guldur before defeating his evil steed, a fell beast of Mordor.\n* Defeat the Lieutenant of Dol Guldur before his fell beast steed falls",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="In the Sixteenth Hall, defilers and other Orcs, sworn to some dark power, poison their brethren with a fungal disease. The source of this evil lies far beneath the surface of this stronghold, once inhabited by the dwarves. The Dwarves in Moria wish only to drive the Orcs and the evil of the Sixteenth Hall away from their former realm.",category="Dungeons of Moria",id=529,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: The Lost One (Daily)",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Moria",id="7001D28B"}},level=60,minlevel=55,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe Lost One is below the Sixteenth Hall, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nYou have been challenged to prove your great worth by defeating the Lost One without making the battle easier by killing his summoned gredbyg.\n* Defeat the Lost One"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Destroy all of the infected corpses in Ferndúr's Chamber before defeating the Gaunt-lord himself.\nThis quest will be cancelled if you leave the Lost Temple before completing it.",category="In Their Absence",id=530,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: The Lost Temple - Clean Sweep",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x5)",val="Medallion of the North-men",id=70025341}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nFerndúr the Virulent has nearly completed his deadly experiments beneath the lost Rhudauran temple.\nThe plagues he has concocted are too deadly to be allowed to fester. You must destroy all the corpses within his chamber before the Gaunt-lord himself is defeated in order to ensure that every trace of them is obliterated.\n* Destroy all the corpses before defeating Ferndúr"},
{d="Gortheron is a master over life and death, reality and illusion. He is marshalling forth forces from all across Eriador to his banner.",category="In Their Absence",id=531,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: The Power of Gortheron",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nGortheron is at the highest tower of Ost Dunhoth. Once his found, be prepared to stand against his forces.\n* Find Gortheron\nObj 2:\nGortheron's forces are vast and varied. As Gortheron's army grows, so does he. Show Sauron you do not fear him by defeating Gortheron at his most potent.\n* Allow Gortheron to reach maximum power\nObj 3:\nGortheron's forces are vast and varied. As Gortheron's army grows, so does he. Show Sauron you do not fear him by defeating Gortheron at his most potent.\n* Defeat Gortheron"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Concealed within Barad Guldur is Durchest, accompanied by ten lesser guards. Each guard alone is a mighty foe, and they lend their strength and fealty to cruel Durchest. You have been challenged to defeat each of the ten foes before Durchest can be slain.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=532,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=2000}},name="Challenge: The Ten Guards (Weekly)",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Dol Guldur",id="7001D28D"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nDurchest and his ten guards loom within sinister Barad Guldur.\nYou must engage in battle with Durchest, defeat each of his ten guards, and finally muster your remaining strength to slay Durchest himself.\n* Defeat Durchest and all ten of his guards",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Defeat all of the bosses in Stoneheight, without removing their corruptions.\nThis quest will be cancelled if you leave Stoneheight before completing it.",category="In Their Absence",id=533,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: The Town of Stoneheight",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x5)",val="Medallion of the North-men",id=70025341}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nDefeat Gundúl\n* Defeat Gundúl\n* Defeat Búbhosh-grat\n* Defeat Dale Truitt"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="While attempting to destroy Úmheryn, the vile cauldron, you must not douse the fire that stands below the cauldron.\nThis quest will be cancelled if you leave the Northcotton Farms before completing it.",category="In Their Absence",id=534,scope="n/a",name="Challenge:  The Unquenched Flame",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{val="Eglain Token",id="7001E6E2"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nWithin the Northcotton Farms, there is an odor most foul in the air.  Discover the source of the foul odor.\n* Locate the source of the noxious fumes\nObj 2:\nThadúr the Ravager has nearly completed his fiendish experiments within the remenants of Northcotton Farms.\nThe virulent poison that he has concocted would be devistating to the Hobbits that dwelll below the farm. You must refrain from dousing the fire beneath the cauldron with the bucket  in order to ensure that every rememnant of the poison is destroyed.\n* Do not quench the fire  while defeating Úmheryn"},
{area="Dol Guldur",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="In the depths of Dol Guldur, prisoners languish in the stronghold's vile Dungeons, lost to those who care for them. Only the Dungeon's Warden knows their fate, but they cannot be freed as long as he stands guard.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=535,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=2000}},name="Challenge: The Warden of the Dungeons (Daily)",receive={{q="(x8)",val="Medallion of Dol Guldur",id="7001D28D"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMany prisoners are trapped deep within the Dungeons of Dol Guldur.\nYou should save as many prisoners as you can while you engage in battle with the Warden of the Dungeons.\n* Defeat the Warden of the Dungeons of Dol Guldur\n* Save most of the prisoners from the Warden"},
{area="Helegrod",zone="The Misty Mountains",d="The great dragon Thorog has arisen and returned!",titles={{val="De-animator of Thorog"}},category="Helegrod",id=536,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Thorog",receive={{val="Helegrod Mark",id="700216C0"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nTBD\n* Defeat Thorog",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{d="The source of the poisoned waters has several places of safety. Taunt the evil there by always having each location be occupied by a hero of the Free Peoples.",category="In Their Absence",id=537,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Toes in the Water",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nDeep beyond the diseased infestation lies the source of the poison waters. Once you find it, make sure each safe location is occupied by a hero of the Free Peoples.\n* Reach the source of the poisoned waters\nObj 2:\nContinue to occupy and defend each safe location with a hero of the Free Peoples. All safe locations must survive the battle.\n* Defeat Frothmar"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="The second level of Barad Guldur is guarded by the twin enemies of Fire and Shadow. They must both be defeated within ten seconds of one another to ensure that their powers are lost to the Enemy.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=538,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=2000}},name="Challenge: Two with One Blow (Weekly)",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Medallion of Dol Guldur",id="7001D28D"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe twin fiends of Fire and Shadow are in Barad Guldur.\nYou must successfully engage and defeat the twin enemies of Fire and Shadow within Barad Guldur within ten seconds of one another.\n* Defeat the twins of Fire and Shadow within ten seconds of one another",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",d="Dolvaethor is deep within the tombs of Annúminas attempting to bring forth one of the ancient kings as a wight.\nDolvaethor has brought Valandil back as a wight. If you are to be sure of their defeat, their demise must come in nearly the same moment.",category="Annúminas",id=539,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Valandil and Dolvaethor",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nDolvaethor is awaiting you at the ancient tomb of Haudh Valandil.\n* Engage Dolvaethor\nObj 2:\nDolvaethor has brought Valandil back as a wight. If you are to be sure of their defeat, their demise must come in nearly the same moment.\n* Defeat Valandil and Dolvaethor within 10 seconds of each other\n* Kill 1 Dolvaethor\nObj 3:\nDolvaethor has brought Valandil back as a wight. If you are to be sure of their defeat, their demise must come in nearly the same moment.\n* Defeat Valandil and Dolvaethor within 10 seconds of each other\n* Defeat Valandil and Dolvaethor within 10 seconds of each other"},
{area="Helegrod",zone="The Misty Mountains",d="Zaudru's brood has flourished beneath the peak of Helegrod.\nOnce a sufficient number of Grisgart's allies are defeated an opportunity will arise to burn several of Xaudru's cocoons. Once burned, the spider will become enraged and enter the battle. She must fall before the final four white silkspinners are defeated.",category="Helegrod",id=540,scope="n/a",name="Challenge: Zaudru",receive={{val="Superior Third Mark",id="700216CA"}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nBreosal and Zaudru are deep within the tunnels underneath Helegrod.\n* Approach Breosal and Zaudru\nObj 2:\nBreosal has brought many allies with her, they will need to be eliminated.\n* Defeat Breosal's Allies\nObj 3:\nLogs have started falling from the bonfires. They can be used to burn the cocoons and spider-nests surrounding this area.\n* Light the cocoons on fire\nObj 4:\nBurning the cocoons has angered Zaudru. She must now be vanquished.\n* Defeat Zaudru\n* Defeat the Angmarim Silkspinners"},
{["next"]={1431},area="Gabilshathur",zone="Angmar",money={{val="38s 64c"}},d="Hwati told you that to truly end the threat of Maethad, you must defeat its master, Khurrákh. However, this Gorthorog will only fight you if you can prove yourself worthy of his attention.",category="Angmar",id=541,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2284},name="Champion of Maethad",arcs="Master of the Maethad",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Hwati",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRonkûrz, the champion of Maethad, can be found training Uruks within the the Orc encampment of  Mor Maudhúl, north of Gabilshathûr, on the far side of the lake in Duvuinen.\nOnce you have claimed one of Ronkûrz's maces, bring it back to Hwati in Gabilshathûr.\n* Bring Ronkûrz's mace to Hwati\n* Turn in Ronkûrz's Mace (Level 1)"},
{["next"]={3230},area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="25s 20c"}},d="You caught up with one of the half-orcs who ransacked the Company's campsite, but the other had already continued southwards with their stolen prize.",mobs={{locations={"47.02S, 12.53W"},name="Golgallon"}},selectoneof={{val="Golgallon's Sword",id=70016107},{val="Ring of Sirannon",id="700163BA"},{val="Orc Out-runner",id="7001610F"}},category="Eregion",id=542,scope="n/a",prev={2595},name="Chasing Trouble",arcs="Footsteps of the Company",level=51,c={"* You will only have 30 min to find the Half-orc Rider\n* The Half-orc Rider is in the Nan Sirannon area [52.1S, 9.6W]"},minlevel=46,b="Golgallon",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe remaining half-orc might be found along the northern banks of the dry Sirannon river-bed, south-east of Echad Eregion.\nGolgallon suggests that there is a chance to stop the remaining half-orc when he stops to rest his horse.\n* Turn in Small Cooking-pot\nObj 2:\nGolgallon is at Echad Eregion, north-west of the Sirannon.\nYou should bring the pot you found back to Golgallon.\n* Talk to Golgallon\n* Turn in Small Cooking-pot"},
{["next"]={229},area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="Lengliel had you collect several White Hand banners and bring them to her. From them, she has been able to learn the identity of the half-orcs' leader.",mobs={{locations={"46.98S, 12.48W"},name="Lengliel"}},selectoneof={{val="Horngoth's End",id="7001608A"},{val="Lengliel's Earring",id="7001639E"}},category="Eregion",id=543,scope="n/a",prev={1290},name="Chief of the Invaders",arcs="Invaders of Barad Morlas",level=50,c={"* The Barad Morlas Mustering-horn is at [48.0S, 13.7W]"},pois={{locations={"47.96S, 13.71W"},name="Barad Morlas Mustering-horn"}},minlevel=45,b="Lengliel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe summoning horn is at the northern foot of a bridge in Barad Morlas, south-west of Echad Eregion.\nLengliel has asked you to use the summoning horn of Barad Morlas to challenge Horngoth, the leader of the half-orcs there.\n* Kill 1 Horngoth\n* Use Barad Morlas Mustering-horn\nObj 2:\nLengliel is at Echad Ergion, north-east of Barad Morlas.\nYou should return to Lengliel and tell her of your victory at Barad Morlas.\n* Talk to Lengliel at Echad Eregion"},
{money={{val="40s 32c"}},d="Scouts reported seeing a strange uruk, and overheard the Orc-overseers under his command calling out \\qChieftain Gûrsh\\q as he strode away toward the Library at Tham Mírdain. It appears that we have identified the leader of this war effort out of Angmar, and now we must do what we can to end this menace.\nI would ask you to enter the Library at Tham Mírdain and challenge Gûrsh to a battle. If you can draw him out and defeat him, we will have effectively eliminated the leader of the northern forces.\nWe must be careful, however, not to attract the attention of the Orcs and Dunlendings from the South, for we do not have the strength to combat north and south should they suddenly join forces. The more stealthy we are, the better our chances to best all foes. Gather no more than two companions for this assault, for our hope is in secrecy. Before you make your assault, you should speak with Maegamiel.",category="Eregion",id=544,scope="n/a",name="Chieftain Gûrsh",level=51,minlevel=46,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nChieftain Gûrsh, leader of the northern forces of Angmar, can be found in the Library at Tham Mírdain, just to the south-west of Echad Mirobel.\nOrnras of Echad Mirobel has asked you to take a small band of fighters and unseat Chieftan Gûrsh, which will hopefully weaken the enemy presence from the north without drawing the attention of the south. Enemies have been scavenging the Library for forgotten history that might be useful to their cause.\n* Defeat Chieftain Gûrsh"},
{d="Ancient dead has arisen within the Great Barrow.",category="Great Barrows",id=545,scope="n/a",name="Chilled Barrow-wights",receive={{val="Great Barrow Mark",id="700230A1"}},level=22,minlevel=17,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nChilled Barrow-wights can be found within the Flooded Wing of the Great Barrow.\n* Defeat Chilled Barrow-wights"},
{["next"]={2677},area="Northern High Pass",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Thorgest appears to have fallen terribly ill from the Gauredain's poisoned weapons.",mobs={{locations={"24.55S, 7.04E"},name="Thorgest"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=546,scope="n/a",prev={786},name="Chilled to the Bone",arcs="Gauradan Curse",level=47,pois={{locations={"29.23S, 8.76E","29.57S, 8.51E","29.33S, 9.29E","29.44S, 9.41E","29.41S, 8.68E"},name="Gauradan Basket"}},minlevel=42,b="Thorgest",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Gauradan-camps lie to the south of Thorgest's dwelling.\nThorgest has asked you to search through the camps of the Gauredain in the hopes of finding some cure for the affliction they have placed upon him.\n* Use Gauradan Basket\nObj 2:\nThorgest's dwelling is to the north of the Gauradan camps.\nYou should bring the Gauradan-relics you have collected to Thorgest to see if he can discover a cure among them.\n* Talk to Thorgest"},
{money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="All of the chores have been done to get the farm ready for the market.",category="Evendim",id=547,scope="n/a",prev={1646},name="Chores Done",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="Milo Longfurrow",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAlbin Northcotton is at the market area.\nAlbin Northcotton will want to know that all the chores are done and the farm is ready.\n* Talk to Albin Northcotton",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1885},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="The water-wheels of Moria were once instrumental in powering and cooling the great fires of the ancient forges.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=548,scope="n/a",name="Churning Froth",arcs="Churning Wheel",level=55,c={"* The Great Wheel is at [17.7S, 115.6W]"},minlevel=50,b="Ansurr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe water-wheels can be found at The Great Wheel, south-west of the Rotting Cellar.\nAnsurr challenged you to find a great water-wheel in the Water-works which is no longer working. Once found, he wants you to clear out some of the creatures nearby to secure it.\n* Find the ancient water-wheel\nObj 2:\nAnsurr is in the Rotting Cellar, north-east of The Great Wheel.\nAnsurr will be pleased to hear you located and secured the water-wheel.\n* Talk to Ansurr in the Rotting Cellar"},
{area="Egladil",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="There is an ancient tradition in Lothlórien, wherin one travels throughout the forest, visiting a series of stone glades and meditating within each.",mobs={{locations={"17.24S, 64.05W"},name="Galhíril"}},category="Lothlórien",id=549,scope="n/a",name="Circles of Silence",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,c={"* The Peaceful Glade is at [12.0S, 64.9W]\n* The Ring of Melbrethil is at [9.8S, 64.7W]\n* The Stone-grove is at [14.3S, 69.2W]\n* The Elder Circle is around [18.3S, 65.5W]"},minlevel=60,b="Galhíril",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Peaceful Glade lies north of Egladil.\nGalhíril suggested you meditate in the Peaceful Glade.\n* Perform /meditate\nObj 2:\nThe Peaceful Glade lies north of Egladil.\nGalhíril suggested you meditate in the Peaceful Glade.\nObj 3:\nThe Ring of Melbrethil lies to the north of the Peaceful Glade.\nGalhíril suggested that you meditate within the Ring of Melbrethil.\n* Perform /meditate\nObj 4:\nThe Ring of Melbrethil lies to the north of the Peaceful Glade.\nGalhíril suggested that you meditate within the Ring of Melbrethil.\nObj 5:\nThe Stone-grove lies well to the south-west of the Ring of Melbrethil.\nGalhíril suggested that you meditate within the Stone-grove.\n* Perform /meditate\nObj 6:\nThe Stone-grove lies far to the south-west of the Ring of Melbrethil.\nGalhíril suggested that you meditate within the Stone-grove.\nObj 7:\nThe Elder Circle lies to the south-east of the Stone-grove.\nGlahíril suggested that you meditate within the Elder Circle.\n* Perform /meditate\nObj 8:\nThe Elder Circle lies to the south-east of the Stone-grove.\nGlahíril suggested that you meditate within the Elder Circle.\nObj 9:\nGalhíril is in Egladil.\nYou should return to Galhiril and tell her of your meditations within the circles of Lothlórien.\n* Talk to Galhíril in Egladil",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Rivendell is nestled hidden in a valley in the West of the Trollshaws.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Evendim",id=550,scope="n/a",name="City of the Elves",level=40,minlevel=35,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou have been called to Rivendell, in the Trollshaws, for there is much to do there.\n* Talk to Elrond",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Caras Galadhon",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Trevadiel has welcomed you to Caras Galadhon and wants you to become familiar with the city.",mobs={{locations={"15.75S, 67.78W"},name="Randiron"},{locations={"15.81S, 67.79W"},name="Padril"},{locations={"15.81S, 67.74W"},name="Rainen"},{locations={"16.02S, 67.11W"},name="Trevadiel"}},category="Lothlórien",id=551,scope="n/a",name="City of the Golden Wood",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,c={"* Randiron can be found at [15.7S, 67.8W]\n* Rainen is at the first level of Telain Galadhrim [15.8S, 67.7W]"},minlevel=55,b="Trevadiel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nRandiron is in Telain Galadhrim, beneath the flet on which the trainers reside, down the western path and along the first right turn.\nTrevadiel told you to seek Randiron to learn more of the ways of Caras Galadhon.\n* Talk to Randiron near Telain Galadhrim\nObj 2:\nRainen is at Telain Galadhrim, the flet upon which the trainers reside, up the winding steps from Randiron.\nRandiron has told you to speak with his friend Rainen.\n* Talk to Rainen at Telain Galadhrim\nObj 3:\nPadril can be found at Telain Galadhrim, on the level above Rainen, reached by climbing the ladder.\nRainen has asked you to speak with her friend Padril.\n* Talk to Padril at Telain Galadhrim",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2733},area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Esko has told you that the Hylje-heimo may be swayed to side with the Free Peoples of the South if the Jewel of Ice can be recovered.",mobs={{locations={"11.45N, 69.70W"},name="Esko"}},category="Forochel",id=552,scope="n/a",prev={2524},name="Claiming the Jewel",level=49,c={"* Roibeard, who holds the Jewel of Ice, can be found deep into the Ironspan at [16.5N, 60.6W]"},minlevel=44,b="Esko",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRoibeard is at the Angmarim encampments near the Ironspan, north-east of Pynti-peldot.\nEsko has told you where the Angmarim are holding the Jewel of Ice. You must retrieve it before it can be returned to the vaults of Angmar.\n* Bring the Jewel of Ice to Esko at Pynti-peldot\n* Turn in Jewel of Ice"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="44s 80c"}},d="The Forges of Khazad-dûm were once the heart of smithing within Moria. Here, the mighty dwarf-smiths would work the mithril and forge their greastest wonders. In the time since its fall, the Forges of Khazad-dûm have been flooded with massive lava-floes and populated by the Orcs of Moria and their troll and goblin-labourers. Here the Orc war-host hammers away incessantly, as they built their weapons and siege-engines in preparation for their war against Lothlórien.",mobs={{locations={"13.44S, 108.07W"},name="Pálmar"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=553,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Claiming the Past",arcs="Forges of Khazad-dûm",level=59,minlevel=57,b="Pálmar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nRaf and Sigir are at Anazârmekhem.\nPálmar asked you to speak with Raf and Sigir and to assist them in clearing the Forges of Khazad-dûm.\n* Help Raf drive the Uruks out of the Forges\n* Assist Sigir in his reclamation efforts\n* Assist Sigir in his effort to recover stolen tools\nObj 2:\nPálmar is at Anazârmekhem, north-east of the Forges of Khazad-dûm.\nYou assisted both Raf and Sigir with their tasks and should now speak to Pálmar to obtain his favour with Narfi.\n* Talk to Pálmar at Anzârmekhem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Ram Dúath",zone="Angmar",money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Reko, the Earth-kin hunter, desires the beaks of Blade-beak Ravagers, though for what, the creature would not say.",mobs={{locations={"3.15S, 39.25W"},name="Reko"}},category="Angmar",id=554,scope="n/a",name="Claws of the Earth",receive={{val="Balanthol",id="70006AF5"}},level=40,c={"* The Hill-claws can be found along the road just to the east of the Earth-kin camp. They seem to share spawn locations with Spiders, so you may need to defeat some of those to get the Hill-claws to spawn."},minlevel=35,b="Reko",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBlade-beak Ravagers can be found throughout Ram Dúath.\nReko has asked you to collect the Blade-beak Ravager beaks he desires.\n* Bring the Blade-beak Ravager beaks to Reko at Lehmä-koti.\n* Turn in Ravager beak",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="The goblins of Moria have overtaken the platforms below the Dolven-view.",selectoneof={{val="Goblin-hewer",id="700160FE"},{val="Slagvi's Rune-stone",id=70016111}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=555,scope="n/a",name="Cleaning the Slate",arcs="Goblins of the Great Delving",receive={{val="Infused Garnet",id="700135D7"}},level=52,minlevel=47,b="Slagvi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are goblins in the parts of the Great Delving below the Dolven-view.\nSlagvi has asked you to help reclaim the city below the Dolven-view by defeating some of the goblins encamped there.\n* Defeat goblins around the Dolven-view (12)\nObj 2:\nSlagvi is at the Dolven-view camp above the Great Delving.\nYou have killed many goblins below the Dolven-view; however, it feels like endless hordes lie beyond the shadows. You should return to Slagvi and inform him that you have fulfilled his request.\n* Talk to Slagvi at the Dolven-view"},
{["next"]={564},area="Falathlorn",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Calengil has asked you to collect some herbs for him as part of a draught he is creating to cleanse a dark taint from the ruins near Duillond.",mobs={{locations={"24.16S, 93.01W"},name="Calengil"}},category="Ered Luin",id=556,scope="n/a",prev={479},name="Cleansing Draught",arcs="Hallowed Ground",level=9,c={"* There are some Damp Fragrant Herbs in Falathlorn around [23.0S, 92.1W]"},pois={{locations={"24.70S, 91.73W","23.29S, 92.14W","24.57S, 92.17W","24.44S, 91.85W","22.96S, 92.14W","23.46S, 92.17W","23.00S, 92.23W","23.19S, 92.23W","24.95S, 92.22W","24.78S, 92.17W","24.86S, 91.91W","24.56S, 91.78W"},name="Damp Fragrant Herb"}},minlevel=5,b="Calengil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe herbs can be found along the riverside beneath Duillond.\nCalengil has asked you to retrieve the herbs that he needs to complete the cleansing draught.\n* Collect damp fragrant herbs (3 Damp Fragrant Herb )\nObj 2:\nCalengil is at Duillond, north of Celondim.\nYou should return the herbs you collected to Calengil.\n* Talk to Calengil\n* Turn in Damp Fragrant Herb"},
{area="Coldfells",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Captain-General Tordúr explained that scouts near Tol Ascarnen have seen a number of Angmar's servants dumping the contents of barrels into the river. Drawing water from the river shows that the river is slowly being poisoned. If this is allowed to continue, then the hobbits at Hoarhallow will certainly perish.",category="Ettenmoors",id=557,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Cleansing the Hoarwell",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Captain-General Tordúr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe poison was introduced to the Hoarwell at the waterfall overlooking Tol Ascarnen, in the central area of the Ettenmoors. Northwest of Glán Vraig.\nCaptain-General Tordúr asked you to make your way to the top of the waterfall overlooking Tol Ascarnen to assist in cleansing the poison that the goblins of Angmar introduced into the Hoarwell River.\n* Use Cleansing Draught (Level 1)\n* The cleansing agent has been introduced to the Hoarwell\nObj 2:\nCaptain-General Tordúr is at Glân Vraig.\nYou should return to Captain-General Tordúr with news of your success.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1002},area="Falathlorn",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Calengil has prepared his draught and has offered you the honour of cleansing Dol Ringwest. The draught will in time encourage the growth of great vines that will entwine the ruins, tearing them down and returning them to pristine nature.",mobs={{locations={"24.16S, 93.01W"},name="Calengil"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Lesser Athelas Essence",id="70000D5D"},{q="(x5)",val="Lesser Celebrant Salve",id="700005B4"}},category="Ered Luin",id=558,scope="n/a",prev={562},name="Cleansing the Ruins",arcs="Hallowed Ground",level=9,c={"* This quest can be a bit confusing because there is nothing to click on or highlight with the mouse, you'll need to either open your bag or hotkey the potion when the notice is given that you should use your potion. Then click on the cleansing potion just as you would any other potion.\n* The first tower is in Dol Ringwest around [24.8S, 94.9W]\n* The second tower is in Dol Ringwest around [24.8S, 95.1W]"},minlevel=5,b="Calengil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDol Ringwest is west of Duillond.\nCalengil bade you pour the cleansing draught upon the ground at the base of two towers that remain standing in the ruins of Dol Ringwest.\n* Use Cleansing Draught\n* Find the first tower of Dol Ringwest\n* Use Cleansing Draught\n* Find the second tower of Dol Ringwest\nObj 2:\nCalengil is in Duillond, east of Dol Ringwest.\nYou should return to Calengil and inform him that your task in the ruins of Dol Ringwest is complete.\n* Talk to Calengil\n* Turn in Cleansing Draught"},
{["next"]={2037},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="The materials originally used to craft the dwarf-lamps have long since been used up. More must be found if the halls of Moria are to shine once more.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=559,scope="n/a",name="Clearly Problematic",arcs="Glass Spiders",level=55,minlevel=50,b="Thrand",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlass-spiders can be found to the west of the Rotting Cellar, near The Lost Palace.\nThrand wishes to repair some of the dwarf-lamps smashed by the goblins and speculates that glass-spider legs will make the best replacements for the crystals.\n* Turn in Glass-spider Leg\nObj 2:\nThrand is in the Rotting Cellar, east of The Lost Palace.\nThrand will be delighted to see the condition of the glass-spider legs you collected.\n* Talk to Thrand in the Rotting Cellar\n* Turn in Glass-spider Leg"},
{area="Vale of Thrain",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Vicious bears have grown numerous and bold north of Noglond along the road through the Vale of Thráin, making travel through the Vale unsafe.",mobs={{locations={"19.37S, 100.56W"},name="Ketill"}},selectoneof={{val="Furred Bear-Pelt Shirt",id="70019C39"},{val="Thick Bear-hide Tunic",id="70019C2E"}},category="Ered Luin",id=560,scope="n/a",name="Clear the Roads",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Ketill",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHunter's Notch can be found north of Noglond.\nKetill has asked you to hunt bears in Hunter's Notch and cull their numbers.\n* Defeat bears in the Vale of Thráin (8)\nObj 2:\nKetill is in Noglond, south of Thorin's Hall.\nYou should return to Ketill and report the results of your patrol.\n* Talk to Ketill"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="The water supply coming into Gondamon is still interrupted, despite your efforts to clear the canal.",mobs={{locations={"20.33S, 97.14W"},name="Otkell"}},category="Ered Luin",id=561,scope="n/a",prev={1579},name="Clear the Way",arcs="The Dwarf-canal",level=11,minlevel=7,b="Otkell",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe canal near Gondamon is to the west, past the hills.\nOtkell, the Chief Builder of Gondamon, informed you that goblins are responsible for the lack of fresh water. He asked you to go to the area west of the canal and remove the goblin threat.\n* Kill 3 Blue-crag Spoiler\n* Kill 3 Blue-crag Novice\n* Kill 1 Blue-crag Trapper\nObj 2:\nOtkell is at Gondamon to the east of the canal, beyond the hills.\nYou should return to Otkell and tell him about the goblins you defeated.\n* Talk to Otkell",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1587},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="The paths from the Dolven-view are clogged with debris and rubble, making travel difficult.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=562,scope="n/a",name="Clear Tunnels",arcs="Moria Reclamation",level=52,pois={{locations={"8.19S, 110.90W","7.77S, 110.68W","7.91S, 110.67W","7.84S, 110.63W","8.34S, 110.94W","7.97S, 110.71W","8.02S, 110.82W","7.93S, 110.78W"},name="Rubble"}},minlevel=47,b="Sót",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe rock-fall that Sót has asked you to clear can be found in the eastern side of the Great Delving, south of the gate leading to the Lonely Span.\nSót, the librarian of the Dolven-view expedition, has asked you to aid him by clearing the road leading to the Lonely Span of debris and rubble.\n* Use Rubble\nObj 2:\nSót is at the Dolven-view camp, south-west of the Lonely Span.\nThe rubble from the rock-fall has been cleared out. You should return to Sót and let him know.\n* Talk to Sót at the Dolven-view camp"},
{area="Talath Gaun",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="17s 50c"}},d="Within the ruins of Dol Vaeg, Northrim collects the last few items needed for Stanric's defence. Soon the Eglain hope to be prepared for the worst, a prolonged battle against encroaching darkness.",selectoneof={{val="Stanric's Iron Mace",id="70006B85"},{val="Stanric's Trousers",id="70006A77"},{val="Stanric's Javelin",id="700161D0"},{val="Stanric's Earring",id="700069F6"}},category="Lone-lands",id=563,scope="n/a",name="Clear Water",arcs="Well-prepared",level=29,c={"* pending"},minlevel=24,b="Northrim",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Last Bridge lies at the eastern end of the Great East Road.\nNorthrim gave you an empty, cured bladder and asked you to collect water from the Hoarwell on the northern side of the Last Bridge.\n* Use Empty Water-bladder\n* Fill the water-bladder at the Last Bridge\nObj 2:\nNorthrim awaits your return with clean water at Dol Vaeg, west of the Last Bridge.\nYou made your way to the Hoarwell's edge and collected water from the banks. You should return at once to Northrim.\n* Talk to Northrim\n* Turn in Full Water-bladder"},
{["next"]={849},area="Bridgefields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Odovacar Bolger has sent you to pursue the so-called Black Rider who has been stalking his pig sties by night.",mobs={{locations={"31.04S, 65.48W"},name="Odovacar Bolger"}},category="Shire",id=564,scope="n/a",prev={2030},name="Cloak of the Black Rider",arcs="Spectre of the Black Rider",level=10,pois={{locations={"31.07S, 63.99W"},name="Black Cloak"}},minlevel=6,b="Odovacar Bolger",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe \"Black Rider\" was seen in Cam Puddifoot's fields, east of Budgeford.\nOdovacar Bolger told you that one of his neighbours, Cam Puddifoot, reported the Black Rider on his land, being chased by wolves. Odovacar has asked you to go look for the horseless \"Rider\".\n* Use Black Cloak\nObj 2:\nOdovacar Bolger is at his home up the hill in the centre of Budgeford.\nOdovacar Bolger sent you to search Puddifoot's fields for signs of the Black Rider, but all you found was a ruined black cloak. You should bring the cloak back to Odovacar.\n* Talk to Odovacar Bolger\n* Turn in Black Cloak"},
{zone="Enedwaith",area="Thrór's Coomb",money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="From the myriad beasts you have defeated in Thrór's Coomb, you have manage to obtain a great trophy: Cloben's Fang.",mobs={{locations={"65.57S, 8.48W"},name="Frithgeir"}},category="Enedwaith",id=565,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Cloben's Fang",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Cloben's Fang",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFrithgeir is at Zudrugund, which lies within Nár's Peak, north of the river.\nThe fang you recovered will long serve as a symbol of the defeat of the gwiber that menaced Thrór's Coomb.\n* Talk to Frithgeir in Zudrugund",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="The shrew population near Michel Delving has increased tremendously recently, and Ruby Primstone wants the Bounders to do something about it.",mobs={{locations={"34.20S, 74.62W"},name="Ruby Primstone"}},selectoneof={{val="Primstone's Shield",id="700032D4"},{val="Primstone's Cloak",id="700032D3"}},category="Shire",id=566,scope="n/a",name="Close Up Their Burrows",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Ruby Primstone",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are shrew burrows to the east of Michel Delving, beyond the Delving Fields.\nRuby Primstone is upset by the ruination of the greenery caused by the shrews and wants you to close up some of their burrows.\n* Use Shrew Burrow\nObj 2:\nRuby Primstone is in Michel Delving, at her home south-east of the statue of Marcho and Blanco in the centre of town.\nRuby will be pleased to hear that you have closed some of the shrew burrows near the town.\n* Talk to Ruby Primstone",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nan Amlug East",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="The Earth-kin once believed the hides of the Wargs to be utterly useless, but have recently discovered a way to cure them.",mobs={{locations={"9.26S, 40.04W"},name="Mauno"}},selectoneof={{val="Stalking Cloak",id="70002FF6"},{val="Warg Hide Helm",id="70006AD3"}},category="North Downs",id=567,scope="n/a",prev={1726},name="Coat of Shadow",arcs="Warg Poachers",level=31,c={"* Collect Harrow Weed\n* [9.3S, 37.1W]\n* [9.7S, 36.9W]\n* [9.9S, 36.8W]\n* [9.8S, 36.4W]\n* [9.8S, 36.6W]\n* [9.4S, 36.8W]\n* [9.9S, 36.6W]\n* Collect Dire Warg hides:"},minlevel=26,b="Mauno",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBoth Dire Wargs and harrow weed can be found in the eastern plains of Nan Amlug.\nIn order to make armour for the Suuri-lehmä, Mauno has asked you to gather hides from Dire Wargs and some harrow weed.\n* Turn in Dire Warg-hide\n* Turn in Harrow-weed\nObj 2:\nMauno is at the camp of the Suuri-lehmä.\nYou have gathered enough Warg hides and the harrow weed that Mauno needs to cure them. You should take them to Mauno as soon as possible.\n* Talk to Mauno\n* Turn in Harrow-weed\n* Turn in Dire Warg-hide"},
{area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+900 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="Nicca has told you of the fell spirits which wander the glacier and the creature that draws them forth, entombing them within the frozen husks of Men to serve as dark warriors.",mobs={{locations={"12.30N, 79.41W"},name="Nicca"},{locations={"19.55N, 83.77W"},name="Arre"}},selectoneof={{val="Exile's Shoulder Guards",id="7000E5B0"},{val="Exile's Shoulder Pads",id="7000E5A7"},{val="Exile's Mantle",id="7000E5A8"}},category="Forochel",id=568,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={812},name="Cold as Death",level=50,c={"* Delucheleg can only be summoned by re-kindling the 3 braziers in Kibilzahar at the same time."},minlevel=45,b="Nicca",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKibilzahar lies to the north-west of Kuru-leiri.\nNicca told you that some evil power has trapped fell spirits within the bodies of wights in Kibilzahar. Only the warmth of fire can banish them. He has told you to re-kindle the ancient fires that the dwarves once used to heat the ancient fortress. He also warned you of an evil lord who haunts that place, and to be ready to face him with allies should you go there again.\n* Summon and defeat Delucheleg\nObj 2:\nArre is at Kuru-leiri, south-east of Kibilzahar.\nHaving defeated Delucheleg, the Gaunt-man responsible for raising the wights, you should return to Arre and tell him of your discoveries and battles.\n* Talk to Arre in Kuru-leiri"},
{["next"]={2485},area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You found a black collar marked with evil-looking runes upon the corpse of one of the Druggavar you slew.",mobs={{locations={"63.82S, 17.45W"},name="Saeradan"}},category="Enedwaith",id=569,scope="n/a",name="Collars of the Accursed",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Black Rune-marked Collar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSaeradan is at Echad Saeradan, south-west of Gavar Cadlus.\nYou should bring the collar you found to Saeradan for his examination.\n* Talk to Saeradan\n* Turn in Black Rune-marked Collar"},
{area="Northern Barrow-downs",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+1200 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="17s"}},d="Tobold Leafcutter learned of ancient relics which the Men of Cardolan buried with their dead in the Barrow-downs, suggesting they might be of some use in defending against creatures such as the barrow-wights.",mobs={{locations={"31.74S, 56.24W"},name="Tobold Leafcutter"}},selectoneof={{val="Golugor",id=70003406},{val="Leafcutter's Edge",id=70003405},{val="Skunkwood's Coat",id=70003404},{val="Urn Finder's Staff",id=70003403}},category="Great Barrows",id=570,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2737},name="Collecting History",arcs="History in the Barrow-downs",level=23,c={"* The chalices are inside the three Great Barrow instances: Thadúr, Maze, and Sambrog"},pois={{locations={"33.84S, 55.81W"},name="Ancient Chalice"}},minlevel=18,b="Tobold Leafcutter",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Great Barrow is at the heart of the Barrow-downs, beyond the Dead Man's Perch in the southern Barrow-downs.\nTobold Leafcutter has asked you to gather ancient chalices from the Great Barrow located in the heart of the Barrow-downs.\n* Bring the ancient chalices to Tobold Leafcutter\n* Collect ancient chalices (10 Ancient Chalice )"},
{["next"]={1959},area="Bullroarer's Sward",zone="Evendim",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Your discovery of wolves in his fields has upset Nibs Chubb.",mobs={{locations={"23.21S, 66.53W"},name="Nibs Chubb"},{locations={"23.03S, 67.24W"},name="Hal Gamgee"}},category="Evendim",id=571,scope="n/a",prev={848},name="Collecting the Bait",arcs="Farmer's Bane",level=30,minlevel=25,b="Nibs Chubb",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHal Gamgee can be found in Oatbarton centre.\nNibs Chubb has asked you to speak with Hal Gamgee about the wolves.\n* Talk to Hal Gamgee\nObj 2:\nYoung Greensward-hind can be found grazing in the old orchard just north of Oatbarton centre.\nHal Gamgee suggested you hunt some elk to provide bait for the wolves then return to him.\n* Bring the elk-meat to Hal Gamgee\n* Turn in Elk-meat"},
{["next"]={983,2301},area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Wargs of Gathbúrz are led by Athdurub, a Warg-rider with a reputation for cunning and viciousness.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 46.57W"},name="Rodelleth"}},category="Mirkwood",id=572,scope="n/a",prev={579},name="Commander Athdurub",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Rodelleth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAthdurub patrols the woods of Gathbúrz.\nRodelleth has asked you to hunt down and defeat the Warg-rider Athdurub, commander of the Wargs of Gathbúrz.\n* Defeat Commander Athdurub\nObj 2:\nRodelleth is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nYou should return to Rodelleth with tidings of Athdurub's defeat.\n* Talk to Rodelleth at Thangúlhad"},
{["next"]={2436,578},area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orc-garrison at Bûrzkala is commanded by a fearsome creature known as Fikthrug.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 46.57W"},name="Rodelleth"}},category="Mirkwood",id=573,scope="n/a",name="Commander Fikthrug",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Rodelleth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFikthrug is at Bûrzkala, directly north of Thangúlhad.\nRodelleth has asked you to find and defeat the Orc-commander Fikthrug.\n* Defeat Commander Fikthrug\nObj 2:\nRodelleth is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz, south of Búrzkala.\nYou should return to Rodelleth with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Rodelleth in Thangúlhad"},
{money={{val="41s 44c"}},d="Based on what we know of the White Hand's movements in this area, I have discerned that there is an intelligent uruk-hai at the head of the enemy forces here in Eregion.\nHe is currently commanding the effort to scour the ruins of the School at Tham Mírdain to the south-east of Echad Mirobel. He is a fearsome warrior by all accounts, and his name is Commander Târsh. I would have you enter the School at Tham Mírdain and face down this clever uruk-hai.\nIt is said that his ego is large, and that he fancies himself a warrior without equal. Perhaps we can use this against him. Take no more than two others into the School, for we do not want to attract the attention of our northern enemies as well. We have our hands full enough with our more aggressive manoeuvres against those foes, and it would be grievous indeed if they were to join forces.",category="Eregion",id=574,scope="n/a",name="Commander Târsh",level=53,minlevel=48,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nCommander Târsh can be found in the School of Tham Mírdain, south-east of the Elf-refuge of Echad Mirobel.\nCommander Târsh, a pride-filled uruk-hai, leads the forces of the White Hand in an attempt to gain information of old from the School in which he has established his host. Gelirwen wishes you to enter the School and face down this brute with the aid of a small fellowship.\n* Defeat Commander Târsh"},
{["next"]={200},area="Nan Amlug West",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+500 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Hornbori's cousin, Ragnarr Hornsounder, has journeyed to the camp of the Earth-kin in Nan Amlug. Hornbori is concerned because he has received no word from his cousin.",mobs={{locations={"9.31S, 39.91W"},name="Ragnarr Hornsounder"},{locations={"7.27S, 45.34W"},name="Hornbori"}},category="North Downs",id=575,scope="n/a",name="Common Blood",arcs="Common Blood",level=31,c={"* Ragnarr and the camp are at [9.3S, 39.9W]"},minlevel=26,b="Hornbori",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRagnarr Hornsounder is at the Earth-kin camp along the western mountains in eastern Nan Amlug, east of Othrikar.\nHornbori has asked you to find his cousin in the Earth-kin camp and make sure he is still safe.\n* Talk to Ragnarr Hornsounder"},
{["next"]={828},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",d="Falco's garden is failing for an unknown reason, causing distress among the people of Staddle.",mobs={{locations={"31.45S, 48.60W"},name="Falco Greenhand"},{locations={"30.97S, 48.18W"},name="Gammy Boggs"}},category="Bree-land",id=576,scope="n/a",name="Concern for a Friend",arcs="Falco's Garden",level=12,minlevel=8,b="Gammy Boggs",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFalco Greenhand's farm lies to the south-west of Gammy Boggs' farm.\nGammy Boggs, the local town gossip, has asked you to find out why Falco's garden is failing.\n* Talk to Falco Greenhand at his farm\nObj 2:\nGammy Boggs is at her farm, north-east of Falco Greenhand's farm.\nFalco Greenhand did not want to trouble you with his problems and asked you to tell Gammy Boggs to stop nosing about.\n* Talk to Gammy Boggs at her farm",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Northern High Pass",zone="The Misty Mountains",reputation={{val="+900 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="36s 96c"}},d="Eywind and Nogmeldir have formed a plan to use Gandalf's draught to wreak havoc upon the goblins.",mobs={{locations={"23.29S, 4.30E"},name="Eywind"}},selectoneof={{val="Eywind's Mace",id="7000D2CF"},{val="Eywind's Great Sword",id="7000D2D4"},{val="Túrin",id="7000D2BC"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=577,scope="n/a",prev={968},name="Conflagration",arcs="Goblin Fire",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Eywind",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe burning cauldron is in a tall wooden structure in Ghâshru to the north-east.\nEywind told you to pour Gandalf's draught into the cauldron which the goblins use to produce their fire-pots and tip it over so the mixture will ignite the materials throughout the encampment.\n* Use\n* Bring Gandalf's draught to the burning cauldron\nObj 2:\nTell Eywind of the destruction wrought by Gandalf's draught at the burning cauldron.\n* Talk to Eywind\n* Turn in Gandalf's Draught"},
{area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",d="Nothing you have done for Adelard Took has appeared to have any effect whatsoever on the \\qghost\\q in Adelard's library.",mobs={{locations={"33.60S, 71.13W","33.61S, 71.13W"},name="Adelard Took"}},selectoneof={{val="Sharpened Dagger",id="70000D41"},{val="Tookish Earring",id="70000D42"}},category="Shire",id=578,scope="n/a",prev={2452},name="Confront the Old Took",arcs="Ghost of the Old Took",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=9,minlevel=5,b="Adelard Took",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ghost's presence is strongest in the far corner of Adelard's library, near the small bookshelf.\nAfter all else failed, Adelard Took has asked you to enter his library and confront the ghost of the Old Took.\n* Confront the Old Took's ghost\nObj 2:\nAdelard Took is outside the library in the Great Smials.\nIn confronting the \"ghost\" in Adelard Took's library, you discovered that it was nothing more than a squirrel hiding behind the bookcase. You should tell Adelard that it is safe to return to his library.\n* Talk to Adelard Took"},
{area="Eryn Laer",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Bahanneth was so pleased with the success of your mission to destroy the Orcs' weapons that he would like you to continue your efforts.",mobs={{locations={"12.10S, 71.09W"},name="Bahanneth"}},category="Lothlórien",id=579,scope="n/a",prev={723},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Consistent Harassment",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,pois={{locations={"9.08S, 73.14W","8.17S, 73.01W","8.26S, 73.63W","8.38S, 72.58W","9.10S, 73.03W","8.36S, 73.45W","8.45S, 73.40W","8.25S, 73.37W","8.42S, 72.68W"},name="Weapon-store"}},minlevel=55,b="Bahanneth",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFanuidhol lies to the north-west of Talan Fanuidhol.\nBahanneth wants you to go into Fanuidhol and defeat some of the smiths there, as well as to destroy the stores of weapons they have forged.\n* Defeat Orc-smiths\n* Use Weapon-store\nObj 2:\nBahanneth is at Talan Fanuidhol, south-east of Fanuidhol.\nYou should return to Bahanneth with tidings of your success.\n* Talk to Bahanneth at Talan Fanuidhol"},
{zone="Bree-land",area="Southern Barrow-downs",d="Ancient dead has arisen within the Great Barrow.",category="Great Barrows",id=580,scope="n/a",name="Consuming Barrow-crawler",receive={{val="Great Barrow Mark",id="700230A1"}},level=24,minlevel=19,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nConsuming Barrow-crawlers can be found within the Flooded Wing of the Great Barrow.\n* Defeat Consuming Barrow-crawlers"},
{["next"]={404,991},d="Fungus-infested Orcs, called the Globsnaga by the Orcs of Moria, dwell throughout the Foundations of Stone.",category="Champion",id=581,scope="n/a",prev={3},name="Controlled Burn",arcs="The Path of the Martial Champion",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Valthor",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlobsnaga Orcs infest the Foundations of Stone.\nValthor has asked you to defeat Globsnaga Orcs to prove your might.\n* Defeat Globsnaga Orcs in the Foundations of Stone (12)\nObj 2:\nValthor is at the Shadowed Refuge in the northern region of the Foundations of Stone.\nYou should return to Valthor and tell him of your deeds.\n* Talk to Valthor at the Shadowed Refuge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",d="The Free Peoples will return to take Tol Ascarnen, and Angmar's defenders wish to strengthen the walls with deterents that will drive the foe away.",category="Tol Ascarnen",id=582,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Cooking Sauce",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Glat",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nOil can be found on the Free Peoples fighting throughout the Ettenmoors. The closest camp is over the southern bridge, though a larger group can be found at Ost Ringdyr, far to the east.\nAngmar's Army is shoring up the defences at Tol Ascarnen. Glat needs oil with which to douse the Free Peoples who attempt to assail the keep.\n* Deliver the oil to Soldier Glat at Tol Ascarnen ( )\n* Turn in Barrel of Oil",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={71},area="Southern Emyn Uial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="Gwindeth wants you to prove yourself worthy of recovering the Silithar by fighting the salamanders of Tyl Ruinen.",mobs={{locations={"13.67S, 76.01W"},name="Gwindeth"}},category="Evendim",id=583,scope="n/a",prev={112},name="Corrupted Beasts of Nenuial",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Gwindeth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe islands of Tyl Ruinen are located north-east of Rushingdale, near the middle of the lake, in Evendim.\nGwindeth has asked you to defeat the corrupted salamanders you find on Tyl Ruinen.\n* Defeat salamanders on Tyl Ruinen (10)\nObj 2:\nThe Blue Lady is in Gwindethrond, behind the waterfall at Rushingdale in western Emyn Uial, south-west of Tyl Ruinen.\nGwindeth is waiting to hear that you have dealt a blow to the salamanders of Tyl Ruinen.\n* Talk to Gwindeth"},
{["next"]={2067},area="Emyn Lûm",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Agorin revealed that the relics of Minas Gîl have been irreversibly corrupted by the sorcerers of Dol Guldur.",category="Mirkwood",id=584,scope="n/a",prev={3193},name="Corrupted Memories",arcs="The Grim Tower",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,pois={{locations={"15.07S, 48.61W","15.02S, 48.73W","14.99S, 48.80W","15.11S, 49.57W"},name="Corrupted Silvan Relic"}},minlevel=58,b="Agorin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe corrupted relics lie within Minas Gîl, east of Ost Galadh.\nAgorin has asked you to destroy the corrupted Silvan relics within Minas Gîl.\n* Use Corrupted Silvan Relic\nObj 2:\nAgorin is at Ost Galadh, west of Minas Gîl.\nYou should report your success to Agorin.\n* Talk to Agorin at Ost Galadh"},
{area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="13s"}},d="Agnes Martlet listened to the tale of your time in the Fields of Fornost and feels some pity for the creatures corrupted by its dark past.",category="North Downs",id=585,scope="n/a",prev={1486,2542},name="Corruption from Fornost",arcs="Agnes and the Bears",receive={{val="Agnes' Two-Handed Sword",id="70006B95"}},level=26,minlevel=21,b="Agnes Martlet",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarghests can be found all through the Fields of Fornost.\nAgnes Martlet has asked you to defeat some of the barghests on the Fields of Fornost in order to save the bears from their corruption.\n* Defeat barghests on the Fields of Fornost (14)\nObj 2:\nAgnes Martlet is in Amon Raith, south-east of the Fields of Fornost.\nAgnes will be glad that you have given freedom to the bears from the corruption of the barghests on the Fields of Fornost.\n* Talk to Agnes Martlet"},
{["next"]={678},area="Lich Bluffs",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="The ancient homes of the interred dead have been violated. Cairn-stones that once stood as markers for the honoured dead are now being corrupted towards a dark purpose.",mobs={{locations={"70.57S, 15.46W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Enedwaith",id=586,scope="n/a",prev={1956,1818},name="Corruption of Cairns",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"72.80S, 16.56W","73.73S, 16.86W","73.05S, 16.55W","73.11S, 16.77W","73.17S, 16.93W","73.49S, 16.89W","72.94S, 16.71W","73.46S, 16.54W","73.24S, 16.76W","72.85S, 16.80W","73.13S, 16.47W"},name="Corrupted Cairn Stone"}},minlevel=65,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe corrupted cairn-stones lie to the north of Trac-plas, south-west of Mincham's camp.\nMincham asked you to seek out corrupted cairn-stones, examine them, and report back with your findings.\n* Use Corrupted Cairn Stone\nObj 2:\nMincham's camp is north-east of Trac-plas.\nYou should return to Mincham and report that you discovered a strange liquid had been poured on the cairn-stones, and that several dark markings were engraved upon them as well.\n* Talk to Mincham in the Lich Bluffs"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",d="An overeager dwarf-warrior made his way to the camp south of Tol Ascarnen when Angmar captured the keep. This dwarf would call the Free Peoples to his banner and make an assault against the fortress on his own, if given leave to do so.",category="Tol Ascarnen",id=587,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=2000}},name="Counter Assault",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Paashum",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Free Peoples' encampment is south of Tol Ascarnen.\nPaashum sent you to the enemy encampment south of Tol Ascarnen to find and defeat First Marshal Án. You should not attempt this alone as Án is a powerful combatant.\n* Kill 1 First Marshal Án\nObj 2:\nThe Angmar-encampment is west of Tol Ascarnen.\nA successful assault against the Free Peoples' encampment resulted in the slaughter of the First Marshal and many of the forces located in the encampment south of Tol Ascarnen.\n* Return to Soldier Paashum at the encampment west of Tol Ascarnen ( )",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1794},area="The Flaming Deeps",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The dwarves saw Ghâsh-hai dragging a piece of the ancient statue into the Flaming Deeps.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=588,scope="n/a",prev={1976},name="Cradled in Flame",level=56,pois={{locations={"16.97S, 107.29W"},name="Statue Shoulder-piece"}},minlevel=51,b="Gúthi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe statue-piece is believed to be in Hurmulkezer, a Ghâsh-hai camp to the south of Anazârmekhem.\nGúthi saw the Ghâsh-hai drag a piece of one of Moria's beloved statues into the depths.\n* Use Statue Shoulder-piece\nObj 2:\nGúthi is in Anazârmekhem, north of Hurmulkezer.\nGúthi will want to know the statue's head is safe.\n* Talk to Gúthi in Anazârmekhem"},
{area="Celondim",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Mibrethil has suggested that you speak with his friend Gwaloth at a terrace overlooking the harbour of Celondim where useful and comely goods are made.",mobs={{locations={"28.31S, 92.46W"},name="Mibrethil"},{locations={"28.15S, 92.70W"},name="Gwaloth"}},category="Crafting",id=589,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: A Terrace in Celondim",level=6,minlevel=2,b="Mibrethil",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGwaloth is on a terrace overlooking Celondim, located south of the top of the stairs that wind up the hillside around which the city is constructed.\nThe Elf Mibrethil suggested that you speak with his friend Gwaloth if you are interested in learning a crafting trade.\n* Talk to Gwaloth",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Midgewater Marshes",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Barton Tyne has lost the glittering copper ring given to him by his wife Verity, and he is beside himself with worry about what she will do when she finds out he lost it.",mobs={{locations={"34.38S, 42.13W"},name="Barton Tyne"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Chunk of Tin Ore",id="7000394A"},{q="(x5)",val="Mushroom",id="700005C5"}},category="Crafting",id=590,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Barton Tyne Has Lost His Ring",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Copper Ingot",id="70001BFF"}},level=15,minlevel=11,b="Barton Tyne",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarton Tyne is on the road between the town of Bree and The Forsaken Inn.\nBarton Tyne has told you that he lost his wedding ring, and he is looking for the services of a jeweller to make a glittering copper ring to replace it. His wife Verity is sure to be furious if he returns without it.\n* Bring a glittering copper ring to Barton Tyne\n* Turn in Glittering Copper Ring (Level 11)"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Osur Stouthammer is concerned by what he feels to be the sad state of the armour worn by the guards of the town of Bree and wants to ease the situation.",mobs={{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Osur Stouthammer"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Log of Rowan Wood",id=70003975},{q="(x2)",val="Chunk of Copper Ore",id=70003949}},category="Crafting",id=591,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Bronze for Bree-town",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Bronze Plate",id="70001B3A"}},level=15,minlevel=11,b="Osur Stouthammer",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOsur Stouthammer is in the crafting hall near the Boar Fountain in the town of Bree.\nOsur Stouthammer is concerned by the low quality of the armour worn by the guards of the town of Bree and wants you to find a metalsmith willing to make some bronze armour and a bronze buckler he can give to the defenders.\n* Bring bronze armour and a bronze buckler to Osur Stouthammer\n* Turn in Bronze Buckler\n* Turn in Bronze Armour (Level 16)"},
{area="Bindbole Wood",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Crocus Stonybanks is trying to assemble some campfire materials so she can go camping with her friends.",mobs={{locations={"28.16S, 70.02W"},name="Crocus Stonybanks"}},selectoneof={{q="(x4)",val="Light Hide",id="70001DF7"},{q="(x2)",val="Chunk of Copper Ore",id=70003949}},category="Crafting",id=592,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Camping Preparations",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Plank of Treated Rowan",id="70001E8D"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Crocus Stonybanks",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCrocus Stonybanks is in Overhill.\nCrocus has asked you to bring her two rowan campfire kits so she can go camping with her friends.\n* Bring two rowan campfire kits to Crocus Stonybanks\n* Turn in Rowan Campfire Kit"},
{area="Celondim",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="The jeweller Guleneth has asked you to bring him polished agates he can use in the pieces he makes.",mobs={{locations={"27.88S, 92.77W"},name="Guleneth"}},selectoneof={{q="(x4)",val="Lump of Butter",id="700005CC"},{val="Early Third Age Relic",id="70001A98"}},category="Crafting",id=593,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Gems for Guleneth",receive={{val="Dull Edhelharn Token",id="70004A57"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Guleneth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGuleneth is at Celondim in Ered Luin.\nJeweller Guleneth has asked you to acquire three polished agates that he can use to complete some of the pieces he has left unfinished.\n* Bring polished agates to Guleneth\n* Turn in Polished Agate"},
{area="Combe",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Geoffrey Fuller has a real problem with the splinters he gets daily from working at the Combe lumber-camp.",mobs={{locations={"28.52S, 49.07W"},name="Geoffrey Fuller"}},selectoneof={{q="(x4)",val="Bronze Ingot",id="70001B4C"},{q="(x4)",val="Scoop of Lard",id="700005CA"}},category="Crafting",id=594,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Geoffrey Fuller Hates Splinters",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Piece of Light Leather",id="70001CE3"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Geoffrey Fuller",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGeoffrey Fuller is in the village of Combe.\nGeoffrey is sick to death of the splinters he encounters every day during his work at the lumber-camp and has asked if you can bring him some padded gloves. A tailor should be able to make the gloves.\n* Bring padded gloves to Geoffrey Fuller\n* Turn in Padded Gloves (Level 9)"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Clayton Cole is hoping to improve the discipline of the Bree-town guards under his command by studying the lessons of the past.",mobs={{locations={"30.26S, 50.09W"},name="Clayton Cole"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Ingot",id="70001B4C"},{q="(x6)",val="Carrot Seed",id="70006E8B"}},category="Crafting",id=595,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Knowledge is the Best Defence",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Early Third Age Relic",id="70001A98"}},level=15,c={"* Collect Scroll of Minor Battle Lore\n* Collect Scroll of Minor Weaponsmithing Lore"},minlevel=11,b="Clayton Cole",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nClayton Cole is by the Combe-gate on the east side of the town of Bree.\nClayton has asked you to find a scholar who can provide you with minor weaponsmithing-lore and minor battle-lore.\n* Bring minor battle-lore and minor weaponsmithing-lore to Clayton Cole\n* Turn in Scroll of Minor Battle Lore\n* Turn in Scroll of Minor Weaponsmithing Lore"},
{area="Celondim",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="The Elf Laegon has taken to practising his bow-making, and he often wants for materials.",mobs={{locations={"27.88S, 92.31W"},name="Laegon"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Ingot",id="70001B4C"},{q="(x2)",val="Log of Rowan Wood",id=70003975}},category="Crafting",id=596,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Laegon Practises His Craft",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Rowan Haft",id="70001E96"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Laegon",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLaegon is at Celondim, in Ered Luin.\nLaegon has asked if you could bring him three rowan bowstaves he can use to refine his bow-bending techniques.\n* Bring rowan bowstaves to Laegon\n* Turn in Rowan Bowstaff"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Gagi Cloudbrow tried to make himself some bronze leggings, but the event has been described as something of a disaster.",mobs={{locations={"14.98S, 103.51W"},name="Gagi Cloudbrow"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Piece of Light Leather",id="70001CE3"},{q="(x2)",val="Chunk of Copper Ore",id=70003949}},category="Crafting",id=597,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Leggings for Gagi",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Bronze Plate",id="70001B3A"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Gagi Cloudbrow",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGagi Cloudbrow is west of Frerin's Court.\nGagi Cloudbrow has asked you to procure for him some bronze leggings, because the pair he tried to make for himself turned out poorly, and in no way resembled the leggings for which he was trying.\n* Bring bronze leggings to Gagi Cloudbrow\n* Turn in Bronze Leggings (Level 16)"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Solvi Scrollbearer is certain that better use could be made of the resources found outside Gondamon and wants your help in acquiring information to support this idea.",mobs={{locations={"20.45S, 97.13W"},name="Solvi Scrollbearer"}},selectoneof={{q="(x6)",val="Apprentice Crop Seed",id="700242B1"},{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Ingot",id="70001B4C"}},category="Crafting",id=598,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Making Use of the Low-lands",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Worn Tablet Fragment",id="70001AA8"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Solvi Scrollbearer",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSolvi Scrollbearer is at Gondamon, on the low-lands of Ered Luin.\nSolvi Scrollbearer asked you to have a scholar prepare some minor metalworking-lore and some minor woodworking-lore for him to examine.\n* Bring minor woodworking and metalworking-lore to Solvi Scrollbearer\n* Turn in Scroll of Minor Metalworking Lore\n* Turn in Scroll of Minor Woodworking Lore"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Alf Goodcliff thinks you could be a craftsman of some skill and suggested you visit his friend Emerald Borings at the Craft-fair on the south side of Michel Delving.",mobs={{locations={"34.49S, 75.57W"},name="Emerald Borings"},{locations={"31.84S, 76.73W"},name="Alf Goodcliff"}},category="Crafting",id=599,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Michel Delving Craft-fair",level=5,minlevel=1,b="Alf Goodcliff",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nEmerald Borings is at the Michel Delving Craft-fair, south-west of the statue in the town centre, past the stables, and along the first leftward turning.\nAlf Goodcliff suggested you speak with his friend Emerald Borings if you are interested in pursuing a crafting vocation.\n* Talk to Emerald Borings",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Marigold Twospade has asked you to bring her some minor tailoring-lore so she can learn the trade.",mobs={{locations={"33.57S, 75.56W"},name="Marigold Twospade"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Hilt",id="70001DEA"},{q="(x2)",val="Leather Pad",id="70001CE2"}},category="Crafting",id=600,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Michel Delving's Youngest Seamstress",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Worn Tablet Fragment",id="70001AA8"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Marigold Twospade",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMarigold Twospade is in Michel Delving.\nMarigold asked you to bring her some minor tailoring-lore so she can get a start on learning the trade, even though no one will teach her.\n* Bring minor tailoring-lore to Marigold Twospade\n* Turn in Scroll of Minor Tailoring Lore"},
{area="Hobbiton-Bywater",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Odo Mudbottom is distraught that his favourite eating-place, The Floating Log, is currently undergoing repairs to its roof.",mobs={{locations={"31.86S, 68.08W"},name="Odo Mudbottom"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Southlinch Seed",id="700039B0"},{q="(x3)",val="Copper Ingot",id="70001BFF"}},category="Crafting",id=601,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Mudbottom's High Standards",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Cup of Spring Barley Flour",id="70020B81"}},level=10,c={"* Collect mushroom pie (0/2)"},minlevel=6,b="Odo Mudbottom",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOdo Mudbottom is in Frogmorton.\nOdo refuses to eat at The Floating Log while the repairs on the roof are underway, but he still wants his customary mushroom pies.\n* Bring mushroom pies to Odo Mudbottom\n* Turn in Mushroom Pie"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Ned Diggins has gone and eaten the pie crust you brought him as a replacement for the earlier crust he devoured, and now he is in a real pickle.",mobs={{locations={"33.75S, 74.53W"},name="Ned Diggins"}},selectoneof={{val="Amethyst",id="70001C04"},{q="(x2)",val="Piece of Light Leather",id="70001CE3"}},category="Crafting",id=602,scope="Crafting",prev={617},name="Crafting: Ned in a Pickle",arcs="The Great Pie Crust Robbery",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Chicken Egg",id="700005C7"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Ned Diggins",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNed Diggins is in Michel Delving.\nNed Diggins is waiting for you to return with a pie crust he can use to replace the one he ate that was to replace the one he ate, before his wife discovers it missing.\n* Bring pie crust to Ned Diggins\n* Turn in Pie Crust"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Nefi Gemcutter has broken the setting of a necklace he once fashioned and desires a replacement.",mobs={{locations={"15.80S, 103.48W"},name="Nefi Gemcutter"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Chunk of Tin Ore",id="7000394A"},{q="(x2)",val="Pork Shank",id="700005C6"}},category="Crafting",id=603,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Nefi's New Setting",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Amethyst",id="70001C04"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Nefi Gemcutter",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNefi Gemcutter is along the road that approaches Thorin's Hall.\nNefi Gemcutter has asked you to bring him a glittering copper necklace to replace one he made during his own time as a jeweller.\n* Bring glittering copper necklace to Nefi Gemcutter\n* Turn in Glittering Copper Necklace (Level 11)"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Efi Plateshaper is eager to outfit the dwarves guarding the barricade to Rath Teraig and asked for your help collecting the necessary pieces of armour.",mobs={{locations={"20.32S, 96.83W"},name="Efi Plateshaper"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Log of Rowan Wood",id=70003975},{q="(x3)",val="Chunk of Copper Ore",id=70003949}},category="Crafting",id=604,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Outfitting the Defenders",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Bronze Chain Link",id="70001B3F"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Efi Plateshaper",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nEfi Plateshaper is at Gondamon, in the Low-lands of Ered Luin.\nEfi Plateshaper asked you to bring him bronze gloves and a bronze helm with which he can outfit the defenders of the barricade at Rath Teraig.\n* Bring bronze gloves and a bronze helmet to Efi Plateshaper\n* Turn in Bronze Gloves (Level 16)\n* Turn in Bronze Helm (Level 16)"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Seward Proudfoot wants to provide breakfast for the guards of the town of Bree as a token of his appreciation.",mobs={{locations={"29.74S, 51.38W"},name="Seward Proudfoot"}},selectoneof={{q="(x4)",val="Log of Rowan Wood",id=70003975},{q="(x6)",val="Apprentice Pipe-weed Seed",id="700242B2"}},category="Crafting",id=605,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Seward Proudfoot's First Breakfast",receive={{val="Complete Hobbit Breakfast",id=70003368}},level=15,c={"* Collect Eggs and Onions (0/5)\n* Collect Hard Biscuits (0/5)"},minlevel=11,b="Seward Proudfoot",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSeward Proudfoot is outside The Prancing Pony, in the town of Bree.\nSeward Proudfoot promised some guards he would cook them a breakfast of eggs and onions and hard biscuits, but can't find his recipe-book. He has asked you to find a cook willing to prepare the food and will pay you for the trouble if you bring it to him.\n* Bring eggs and onions and hard biscuits to Seward Proudfoot\n* Turn in Eggs and Onions\n* Turn in Hard Biscuits"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Ingi Steambeard has been hard at work fashioning armour for the dwarves that defend Gondamon, and now he is ready to eat.",mobs={{locations={"20.15S, 96.99W"},name="Ingi Steambeard"}},selectoneof={{q="(x4)",val="Dragonsbreath Seed",id="70006F45"},{q="(x3)",val="Copper Ingot",id="70001BFF"}},category="Crafting",id=606,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Steambeard's Hungry Work",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Fresh Carrot",id="700005C9"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Ingi Steambeard",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIngi Steambeard is at Gondamon, in the Low-lands of Ered Luin.\nIngi Steambeard is hungry and wants you to bring him two servings of roast pork and two hard biscuits with which to feed his appetite.\n* Bring roast pork and hard biscuits to Ingi Steambeard\n* Turn in Roast Pork\n* Turn in Hard Biscuits"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Gríss Stonesmasher would like to teach some of his students how to forge weapons out of bronze and wants you to bring him some of the pieces.",selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Chunk of Copper Ore",id=70003949},{q="(x3)",val="Plank of Treated Rowan",id="70001E8D"}},category="Crafting",id=607,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Stonesmasher's Pupils",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Bronze Ingot",id="70001B4C"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Gríss Stonesmasher",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGríss Stonesmasher is in the Forging Hall inside Thorin's Hall.\nGríss Stonesmasher asked you to bring him two bronze blades and two bronze hilts for him to use as examples for some of his weaponsmithy pupils.\n* Bring bronze blades and bronze hilts to Gríss Stonesmasher\n* Turn in Bronze Blade\n* Turn in Bronze Hilt"},
{area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Following the burning of Archet, Edward Carver and his brother Roderick are hoping to encourage all those with potential to take up a crafting vocation for the good of the Free Peoples.",mobs={{locations={"25.64S, 48.73W"},name="Edward Carver"},{locations={"28.86S, 48.69W"},name="Roderick Carver"}},category="Crafting",id=608,scope="Crafting",prev={1683},name="Crafting: Strong of Arm and Sharp of Mind",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Edward Carver",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nRoderick Carver is by the Craft Hall in Combe, south of Archet. The left path from the Combe town centre climbs up the hill past the Craft Hall.\nEdward Carver wants you to speak to his brother Roderick about taking up a crafting vocation.\n* Talk to Roderick Carver",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Celondim",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Raindis of Celondim has asked you to bring her some minor woodworking-lore that she can apply to the preparation of timbers used in the construction of the White Ships.",mobs={{locations={"27.83S, 92.06W"},name="Raindis"}},selectoneof={{q="(x6)",val="Handful of Fertilizer",id="700039B2"},{q="(x2)",val="Light Hide",id="70001DF7"}},category="Crafting",id=609,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Studying the White Ships",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Early Third Age Relic",id="70001A98"}},level=6,minlevel=2,b="Raindis",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRaindis is at Celondim, in Ered Luin.\nRaindis has asked if you would collect some minor woodworking-lore from a scholar so she can see if any improvements might be made to the wood that is used as the timber for the White Ships.\n* Bring minor woodworking-lore to Raindis\n* Turn in Scroll of Minor Woodworking Lore"},
{area="Chetwood",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="The Combe lumber-camp is in need of supplies with which its workers can increase the production of useable timber.",mobs={{locations={"29.06S, 47.08W"},name="Ember Hayes"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Log of Rowan Wood",id=70003975},{q="(x3)",val="Light Hide",id="70001DF7"}},category="Crafting",id=610,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Supplies for the Lumber-camp",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Plank of Treated Rowan",id="70001E8D"}},level=10,c={"* Collect rowan hammer\n* Collect rowan haft (0/3)"},minlevel=6,b="Ember Hayes",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nEmber Hayes is at the Combe lumber-camp.\nEmber has said she would pay you for a rowan hammer and three rowan hafts, if you could bring them to her. A woodworker should be able to make these items.\n* Bring a rowan hammer and three rowan hafts to Ember Hayes\n* Turn in Rowan Hammer\n* Turn in Rowan Haft"},
{["next"]={608},area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Ned Diggins has gone and eaten the pie crust his wife was planning on filling with delicious pie, and now he needs a replacement in a hurry!",mobs={{locations={"33.75S, 74.53W"},name="Ned Diggins"}},selectoneof={{val="Amethyst",id="70001C04"},{q="(x2)",val="Piece of Light Leather",id="70001CE3"}},category="Crafting",id=611,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: The Great Pie Crust Robbery",arcs="The Great Pie Crust Robbery",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Chicken Egg",id="700005C7"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Ned Diggins",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNed Diggins is in Michel Delving.\nNed Diggins is waiting for you to return with a pie crust he can use to replace the one he ate, before his wife discovers it missing.\n* Bring pie crust to Ned Diggins\n* Turn in Pie Crust"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Bogi Deepdelver has asked you to speak with his friend Egil Oldbeard in Thorin's Hall about contributing to the state of crafting in the Blue Mountains.",mobs={{locations={"13.76S, 103.25W"},name="Bogi Deepdelver"}},category="Crafting",id=612,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: The Maker's Hall",c={"* Egil Oldbeard is in the area before Forging Hall of Thorin's Hall"},level=6,minlevel=2,b="Bogi Deepdelver",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nEgil Oldbeard is in the Maker's Hall, inside Thorin's Hall, east of the entrance chamber.\nBogi Deepdelver suggested that you speak with his friend Egil Oldbeard, who has greeted fledgling craftsmen in the Blue Mountains for more than one hundred years.\n* Talk to Egil Oldbeard",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Verity Tyne has lost the glittering copper ring given to her by her husband Barton, and she is beside herself with worry that he will find out.",mobs={{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Verity Tyne"}},selectoneof={{q="(x4)",val="Cup of Spring Barley Flour",id="70020B81"},{q="(x2)",val="Chunk of Copper Ore",id=70003949}},category="Crafting",id=613,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Verity Tyne Has Lost Her Ring",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Agate",id="70001C06"}},level=15,minlevel=11,b="Verity Tyne",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nVerity Tyne is in the Crafting Hall in Bree.\nVerity Tyne has asked for you to find a jeweller willing to make her a glittering copper ring to replace the wedding ring she lost.\n* Bring glittering copper ring to Verity Tyne\n* Turn in Glittering Copper Ring (Level 11)"},
{area="Combe",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="Leighton Howard has asked you to obtain some weapons of bronze with which he can defend his family.",mobs={{locations={"28.61S, 49.65W"},name="Leighton Howard"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Chunk of Tin Ore",id="7000394A"},{q="(x3)",val="Aged Scrap of Text",id="70001A97"}},category="Crafting",id=614,scope="Crafting",name="Crafting: Weapons for Leighton Howard",receive={{q="(x6)",val="Bronze Ingot",id="70001B4C"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Leighton Howard",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLeighton Howard is in the town of Combe, in Bree-land.\nLeighton has asked you to obtain a bronze axe and two bronze blades for him, because the local weaponsmiths are charging too much for him to pay, and he needs them to protect his family.\n* Bring a bronze axe and two bronze blades to Leighton Howard\n* Turn in Bronze Axe\n* Turn in Bronze Blade"},
{["next"]={668,624},area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="8s 96c"}},d="You were sent to Crannog, the chieftain of Aughaire, to pursue a Fém for the Trév Gállorg.",mobs={{locations={"0.09S, 40.18W"},name="Crannog"}},selectoneof={{val="Boots of Fém",id="7000EADF"},{val="Shoes of Fém",id="7000EADE"},{val="Slippers of Fém",id="7000EADD"}},category="Angmar",id=615,scope="n/a",name="Crannog's Challenge",arcs="Crannog's Challenge",level=43,c={"* Torquil is at [0.0S}40.2W, 0W]\n* Raith is at [0.1S, 40.1W]\n* Osbail is at [0.0S, 40.2W]"},minlevel=38,b="Crannog",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTorquil, Raith, and Osbail are near the ruling seat of Crannog, the chieftain of Aughaire.\nCrannog has tasked you with facing the dangers of which Torquil, Raith, and Osbail will speak. Once you have done so, he expects you to return to him.\n* Complete Torquil's tasks\n* Complete Raith's tasks\n* Complete Osbail's tasks\nObj 2:\nCrannog is at his ruling seat in Aughaire, west of the centre island.\nYou have aided some of the Trév Gállorg with the dangers faced by the settlement and should now tell Crannog of your successes.\n* Talk to Crannog"},
{["next"]={2533},area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="At the behest of Crannog, you fought and defeated three of Aughaire's strongest warriors for the right to represent the Trév Gállorg in the Clúcath, but one more test remains.",mobs={{locations={"0.09S, 40.18W"},name="Crannog"}},selectoneof={{val="Jacket of Fém",id="7000EAD1"},{val="Armour of Fém",id="7000EAD2"},{val="Robe of Fém",id="7000EAD0"}},category="Angmar",id=616,scope="n/a",prev={623},name="Crannog's Fifth Challenge",arcs="Crannog's Challenge",level=43,c={"* Nekhtan is found by a tree in Fasach-larran [1.7N, 37.7W]"},minlevel=38,b="Crannog",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNekhtan goes to train at a great tree east of Aughaire. Crannog told you to leave the settlement by the north, and to then turn east and follow the line of the hills until you see the tree in a basin to the north.\nCrannog told you the story of Nekhtan, the greatest warrior of the Trév Gállorg, whose father was slain in the last Clúcath, where the Trév Duvárdain listened to their Angmarim masters and violated the rules of the rite. You are tasked with defeating him for the right to represent the Trév Gállorg at Clúcath.\n* Challenge Nekhtan\nObj 2:\nCrannog is at his ruling-seat, west of the central island in the settlement of Aughaire.\nYou have defeated Nekhtan and should bring word of your success to Crannog.\n* Talk to Crannog"},
{["next"]={622},area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="The Fém Crannog granted you was to begin the Rite of Clúcath, an ancient Hillman ceremony of judgement. For now, though, he has other tasks for you.",mobs={{locations={"0.09S, 40.18W"},name="Crannog"}},selectoneof={{val="Shoulder Pads of Fém",id="7000EAD4"},{val="Shoulder Guards of Fém",id="7000EAD5"},{val="Shoulders of Fém",id="7000EAD3"}},category="Angmar",id=617,scope="n/a",prev={625},name="Crannog's Fourth Challenge",arcs="Crannog's Challenge",level=43,c={"* Feradakh is at [0.2S, 39.8W]\n* Fonghala is at [0.1N, 39.2W]\n* Moridac is at [0.1N, 40.1W]"},minlevel=38,b="Crannog",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRaith is near Crannog's ruling seat, west of the centre island of Aughaire. Feradakh is at the Búth Luikh, south-east of Crannog's ruling-seat. Fonghala is at the Búth Sánkhas, south-east of the market of Aughaire. Moridac is at the aurochs-pens in Aughaire, north-east of Crannog's ruling-seat.\nIn an effort to see if you are strong enough to represent the Trév Gállorg in the upcoming Clúcath, Crannog has tasked you with fighting several of Aughaire's mightiest warriors. Raith can tell you about each of them.\n* Defeat Feradakh\n* Defeat Fonghala\n* Defeat Moridac\nObj 2:\nCrannog is at his ruling-seat, west of Aughaire's centre island.\nYou have defeated the three warriors set before you by Crannog and should tell him now of your victories.\n* Talk to Crannog"},
{["next"]={461,2309,400,625},area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="8s 96c"}},d="You have completed Crannog's first challenge to prove your worth to the Trév Gállorg of Aughaire, but he does not yet trust you.",mobs={{locations={"0.09S, 40.18W"},name="Crannog"}},selectoneof={{val="Gauntlets of Fém",id="7000EADB"},{val="Leather Gloves of Fém",id="7000EADA"},{val="Gloves of Fém",id="7000EAD9"}},category="Angmar",id=618,scope="n/a",prev={621},name="Crannog's Second Challenge",arcs="Crannog's Challenge",level=43,c={"* Lakhina is at [0.0N, 39.6W]\n* Camran is at [0.1N, 39.6W]\n* Rona is at [0.1N, 39.6W]"},minlevel=38,b="Crannog",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLakhina, Camran, and Rona are at the centre island of Aughaire, east of Crannog's ruling seat.\nCrannog wants you to speak with Lakhina, Camran, and Rona of Aughaire and perform the tasks they ask of you.\n* Complete Lakhina's tasks\n* Complete Camran's tasks\n* Complete Rona's tasks\nObj 2:\nCrannog is at his ruling-seat in Aughaire, west of the centre island.\nYou have performed the tasks given you by Lakhina, Camran, and Rona and should now return to Crannog.\n* Talk to Crannog"},
{["next"]={623,745,2493,676},area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Your accomplishments on behalf of the Trév Gállorg have earned you the recognition and trust of Crannog, their chieftain.",mobs={{locations={"0.09S, 40.18W"},name="Crannog"},{locations={"0.09S, 40.13W"},name="Raith"}},selectoneof={{val="Plate Leggings of Fém",id="7000EAD8"},{val="Trousers of Fém",id="7000EAD7"},{val="Leggings of Fém",id="7000EAD6"}},category="Angmar",id=619,scope="n/a",prev={624},name="Crannog's Third Challenge",arcs="Crannog's Challenge",level=43,c={"* pending"},minlevel=38,b="Crannog",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRaith is standing by Crannog's ruling-seat, in Aughaire, west of the settlement's central island.\nCrannog has granted you your Fém -- to begin the rite of the Clúcath -- and told you to speak with Raith to learn what this involves.\n* Talk to Raith\nObj 2:\nThe Cairn of Honour is north-east of Fail-á-Khro, far to the north of Aughaire. The hilltop on which the Cairn of Honour rests is marked by a line of torches.\nRaith has told you that you must collect the Stone of Clúcath and bring it to Crannog.\n* Turn in Stone of Clúcath\nObj 3:\nCrannog is at his ruling-seat, west of the centre island of Aughaire.\nYou have taken the Stone of Clúcath from the Cairn of Honour and should bring it now to Crannog.\n* Talk to Crannog\n* Turn in Stone of Clúcath"},
{["next"]={1817},area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="Hamall noticed several decaying columns in the caves around the Orc and goblin-camps. If they were to be damaged, the cave should come crashing down atop the enemy forces.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=620,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Crashing Down",arcs="Joy in the Time of Sorrow",level=54,pois={{locations={"2.91S, 104.60W","4.20S, 104.90W","2.87S, 104.88W","4.32S, 104.60W","3.05S, 104.15W","3.08S, 105.03W","4.32S, 104.91W","4.10S, 103.94W"},name="Decaying Column"}},minlevel=49,b="Hamall",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe decaying columns can be found in the Orc-camps at Fehem-dûm and Hadâd-dûm, east of Jazârgund.\nHamall noticed several decaying columns within the nearby Orc-camps. He assures you if they are damaged enough, everything will come crashing down and destroy the camps.\n* Use Decaying Column\nObj 2:\nHamall is at Jazârgund, west of Fehem-dûm and Hadâd-dûm.\nHamall should know that none of the columns collapsed, and the cavern did not collapse.\n* Talk to Hamall at Jazârgund"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyrn Fornech",money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="The isle of Rantost is where the tomb-robbers have made their central camp. A great deal of history is being kept there.",category="Evendim",id=621,scope="n/a",name="Crate and Barrel",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=36,pois={{locations={"7.15S, 69.90W","7.15S, 69.93W","7.18S, 69.64W","7.40S, 69.43W","7.17S, 69.79W","7.41S, 69.43W","7.18S, 69.90W","7.19S, 69.78W","7.41S, 69.44W","7.19S, 69.64W","7.38S, 69.43W","7.39S, 69.45W","7.12S, 69.94W","7.18S, 69.63W","7.19S, 69.77W"},name="Relic-crate"},{locations={"7.00S, 69.86W","7.03S, 69.94W","7.20S, 69.70W","7.01S, 69.71W","7.01S, 69.72W"},name="Relic-barrel"}},minlevel=31,b="Leighton Kipps",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCrates and barrels are spread around Rantost.\nLeighton Kipps has asked you to count the packed crates and barrels around Rantost.\n* Use Relic-crate\n* Use Relic-barrel\nObj 2:\nLeighton Kipps is camped at the south-east corner of Rantost.\nLeighton Kipps will want to know how many crates and barrels there are so he can relay the information to the Rangers.\n* Talk to Leighton Kipps at Rantost",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Efficient hunters within the crags of the Steps of Gram, the Cragstone-spiders allied themselves with the Enemy and stalk the hobbits at Hoarhallow and drive out the Free Peoples from the west.",category="Ettenmoors",id=622,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Crawlers of the Crags",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Quartermaster Cynwiss",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Cragstone-spiders can be found in the crags west of Tol Ascarnen, beyond the tower Lugazag in the shadow of Dâr-gazag.\nQuartermaster Cynwiss asked you to defeat the Cragstone-spiders in the moors of the Steps of Gram.\n* Defeat Cragstone-spiders (20)\nObj 2:\nQuartermast Cynwiss awaits your return at Tol Ascarnen.\nYou made your way into the moors in the Steps of Gram and slaughtered a host of the Cragstone-spiders.\n* Return to Quartermaster Cynwiss at Tol Ascarnen",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Bree-land",area="Southern Barrow-downs",d="Ancient dead has arisen within the Great Barrow.",category="Great Barrows",id=623,scope="n/a",name="Crawling Arms",receive={{val="Great Barrow Mark",id="700230A1"}},level=20,minlevel=15,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nCrawling Arms can be found within the Maze Wing of the Great Barrow.\n* Defeat Crawling Arms"},
{["next"]={640},area="The Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="Thettmárr has been doing his own investigation of the mirrors, but his work was recently disrupted when he was attacked by gredbyg.",selectoneof={{val="Grodbog Leggings",id=70016066},{val="Survivalist's Earring",id="70017CE2"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=624,scope="n/a",prev={1489},name="Creatures of the Dark",arcs="A Faint Gleam",level=52,minlevel=47,b="Thettmárr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe gredbyg can be found at the cavern where Thettmárr had been studying, past the Stone Council, then west and south past the Vault of Durin.\nThettmárr has asked you to dispose of the gredbyg that attacked him.\n* Find the area in which Thettmárr was working\nObj 2:\nThe gredbyg can be found at the cavern where Thettmárr had been studying, past the Stone Council, then west and south past the Vault of Durin.\nThettmárr has asked you to remove the threat of the gredbyg that attacked him.\n* Defeat gredbyg (12)\nObj 3:\nThettmárr is at the Deep Descent encampment, back north and east past the Vault of Durin and down past the Stone Council.\nYou have thinned the numbers of the insects and should report back to Thettmárr.\n* Talk to Thettmárr at the Deep Descent"},
