{area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orc-encampment of Garmadh-maudhûl boasts a mine which produces ore for the use of the armies of Dol Guldur.",mobs={{locations={"17.49S, 48.19W"},name="Eirien"}},category="Mirkwood",id=638,scope="n/a",prev={1924},name="Cut the Supplies",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"16.58S, 46.60W","16.59S, 46.64W","16.69S, 46.71W","16.61S, 46.79W","16.66S, 46.61W"},name="Ore Cart"}},minlevel=60,b="Eirien",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGarmadh-maudhûl can be found to the north-east of Mithechad by following a trail that traverses up the mountain.\nEirien has asked you to destroy the ore-carts which the Orcs at Garmadh-maudhûl are using to resupply Dol Guldur.\n* Use Ore Cart\nObj 2:\nEirien is at Mithechad, south-west of Garmadh-maudhûl.\nYou should return to Eirien and let her know that the ore-carts have been destroyed.\n* Talk to Eirien in Mithechad"},
{["next"]={1126},area="Vale of Thrain",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Grímkell, the commander at Noglond, sent one of his guards, Vífill, to cut some firewood and is concerned because Vífill has failed to return.",mobs={{locations={"19.04S, 101.67W"},name="Vífill"},{locations={"19.34S, 100.46W"},name="Grímkell Stonebearer"}},category="Ered Luin",id=639,scope="n/a",name="Cutting Cords",arcs="Villains in the Vale",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Simple Rations",id="700017DD"}},level=7,c={"* Vifill is in the Vale of Thráin at [19.0S, 101.7W]"},minlevel=3,b="Grímkell Stonebearer",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nVífill is somewhere in the firewood grove down the road west of Noglond.\nGrímkell has asked you to go out and search for Vífill.\n* Find Vífill\nObj 2:\nGrímkell is at Noglond, east of the firewood grove.\nVífill tells you to inform Grímkell of the presence of goblins in the firewood grove.\n* Talk to Grímkell Stonebearer"},
{["next"]={1301},area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Ivar left a captain in command of the wights, more powerful than the protectors.",mobs={{locations={"29.62S, 27.40W"},name="Eriac the Strong"}},selectoneof={{val="Shield of the Strong",id="700161D1"},{val="Reykur's Foil",id="70000CC6"},{val="Reykur's Fall",id="70000CC5"},{val="Gauntlets of the Eglain",id="70000CC4"},{val="Cap of the Eglain",id="70000CC3"}},category="Lone-lands",id=640,scope="n/a",name="Cutting off the Hand",arcs="Angmar's Army",level=31,c={"* Reykur is found on the west side of Agamaur in the back."},minlevel=26,b="Eriac the Strong",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nReykur will likely be found at the furthest chambers of the ruins where the wights are encamped.\nEriac has asked you to kill the gaunt-man Reykur, Ivar's captain among the wights. Because of your victory over other wights, Eriac believes Reykur may be waiting for you.\n* Defeat Reykur\nObj 2:\nEriac awaits you at the Eglan-camp in the southern reaches of Agamaur.\nYou have killed Reykur, throwing the remnant of the wight-army into confusion. Eriac will want to hear of your success.\n* Talk to Eriac at the Eglan-camp in Agamaur"},
{["next"]={729},area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The forest in the Ashenslades appears to have been corrupted by a strange malady that has spread across the area.",mobs={{locations={"17.48S, 44.56W"},name="Himeinior"}},category="Mirkwood",id=641,scope="n/a",prev={1927},name="Cutting to the Core",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"18.73S, 44.17W","19.52S, 44.53W","18.89S, 44.34W"},name="Corrupted Water"},{locations={"19.30S, 44.60W","19.07S, 44.56W","19.38S, 44.88W","18.94S, 44.79W","18.82S, 44.62W","19.44S, 44.80W","19.55S, 44.60W","18.94S, 45.06W","19.04S, 44.96W"},name="Fallen Blighted Wood"}},minlevel=60,b="Himeinior",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSâd Doldúr lies to the south of Barad Angol, down the mountainside.\nHimeinior has asked you to collect some water samples and pieces of fallen blighted wood from the area around Sâd Doldúr.\n* Use Fallen Blighted Wood\n* Use Corrupted Water\nObj 2:\nHeiminior is at the camp near Barad Angol, up the mountain pass north of Sâd Doldúr.\nYou should return the branches and samples of water to Himeinior.\n* Talk to Himeinior\n* Turn in Blighted Wood Sample\n* Turn in Sample of Corrupted Water"},
{["next"]={2267},area="Rushock Bog",zone="The Shire",d="Filibert Bolger told you that his cow, Daffodil, has gone missing, and he suspects that a dwarf named Olwir stole her.",mobs={{locations={"28.16S, 75.80W"},name="Filibert Bolger"}},category="Shire",id=642,scope="n/a",name="Daffodil is Missing",arcs="Beast of the Bog",level=9,pois={{locations={"29.77S, 74.71W"},name="Cow-corpse"}},minlevel=5,b="Filibert Bolger",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTroll's Knoll is in Rushock Bog, south-east of Needlehole.\nFilibert suspects that Olwir took Daffodil out into Rushock Bog somewhere. He suggested you start searching at Troll's Knoll.\n* Find Daffodil\nObj 2:\nAs you searched Troll's Knoll on behalf of Filibert Bolger, you came across the corpse of a cow. A closer examination of the cow should reveal if it is Filibert's cow, Daffodil.\n* Examine the cow\nObj 3:\nFilibert Bolger can be found in Needlehole, north of Troll's Knoll.\nIn your examination of the dead cow you found atop Troll's Knoll, you came across a bell. Perhaps Filibert Bolger will be able to tell from the bell whether the cow you found was his Daffodil.\n* Bring the cow bell to Filibert Bolger\n* Turn in Cow-bell",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={3252},area="Taur Orthon",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+300 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="9s 10c"}},d="Lossoth guards keep watch in a sentry tent located to the north-west of Kauppa-kohta, at the edge of the forest. The guards have had frequent sightings of wolves, which have become increasingly common.",mobs={{locations={"4.13N, 59.88W"},name="Urho"},{locations={"2.79N, 57.99W"},name="Santtu"}},category="Forochel",id=643,scope="n/a",name="Daily Defence",arcs="Wolves at the Door",level=44,minlevel=39,b="Santtu",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe sentry post is north-west of Kauppa-kohta.\nSanttu has instructed you to speak with the guards at the sentry post if you wish to gain their trust.\n* Talk to the guard at the sentry post"},
{area="Tinnudir",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Herthdúr had an unfortunate encounter with the sand-lurkers that prowl among the dunes of the Barandalf and wishes to end the threat they pose to travellers.",category="Evendim",id=644,scope="n/a",name="Danger Among the Dunes",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=32,minlevel=27,b="Herthdúr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSand-lurkers can be found throughout the Barandalf, but especially at Lithost, south-east of the Colossus, on the other side of the river from the ruins of Barad Tharsír.\nHerthdúr has asked you to defeat some of the sand-lurkers that make travel through the Barandalf dangerous for him and his inventory of goods.\n* Defeat sand-lurkers (5)\nObj 2:\nHerthdúr is at the Ranger-camp at the Colossus, north-west of the Barandalf.\nYou have put an end to some of the sand-lurkers that prowl among the dunes of the Barandalf and should report of your success to Herthdúr.\n* Talk to Herthdúr",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Gloomglens",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="The Ranger Himeinior was disturbed by the crushed boulder and skeleton you discovered while patrolling the Gloomglens.",mobs={{locations={"63.46S, 21.46W"},name="Himeinior"}},category="Enedwaith",id=645,scope="n/a",prev={80},destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Danger in the Hills",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Himeinior",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe footprint you found lies to the west of Echad Idhrenfair.\nHimeinior has asked you to return to the site of the footprint you found and track the beast to its lair.\n* Return to the site of the first footprint\nObj 2:\nThe second footprint lies to the south of the first, which was to the west of Echad Idhrenfair.\nYou should continue to track the beast to its lair.\n* Find the second footprint\nObj 3:\nThe third footprint lies to the west of the second, south and west of Echad Idhrenfair.\nYou should continue tracking the beast to its lair.\n* Find the third footprint\nObj 4:\nThe fourth footprint lies to the west of the third, south and west of Echad Idhrenfair.\nYou should continue tracking the beast to its lair.\n* Find the fourth footprint\nObj 5:\nThe fifth footprint lies to the south-west of the fourth.\nYou should continue tracking the beast to its lair.\n* Find the fifth footprint\nObj 6:\nThe creature's lair lies to the north-west of the fifth footprint, south-west of Echad Idhrenfair.\nHimeinior bade you defeat the unknown creature.\n* Enter the Grey King's lair and defeat the creature\nObj 7:\nHimeinior is at Echad Idhrenfair, north-east of the Grey King's lair.\nYou have defeated the creature known as the Grey King and should return to Himeinior with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Himeinior at Echad Idhrenfair"},
{area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="Constable Tanglerush is concerned about the increase in the number of wild animals seen near the borders of Staddle.",mobs={{locations={"31.09S, 49.51W"},name="Constable Tanglerush"}},selectoneof={{val="Boar Hunter's Spear",id="700161BA"},{val="Boar Hunter's Mace",id=70003447}},category="Bree-land",id=646,scope="n/a",name="Dangerous Boars",level=12,minlevel=8,b="Constable Tanglerush",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe boars can be found near Constable Bolger's house, south-east of Staddle, south of Widow Froghorn's farm.\nConstable Tanglerush wants you to thin the boar population near Staddle before one of the hobbits is attacked.\n* Kill 10 Rampaging Bristlehide\nObj 2:\nConstable Tanglerush is in the town square of Staddle.\nConstable Tanglerush will be pleased to hear that you have thinned the boar population near Staddle.\n* Talk to Constable Tanglerush",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={253},area="Tâl Bruinen",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+500 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="8s 96c"}},d="Tongannel has had an uneasy feeling for the last few days and hopes it does not bode ill for the southern-bound traveller she befriended.",mobs={{locations={"37.10S, 14.04W"},name="Tongannel"}},category="Trollshaws",id=647,scope="n/a",name="Dangerous Enterprise",arcs="An End to Enterprise",level=43,pois={{locations={"38.65S, 14.09W"},name="Broken Crate"}},minlevel=38,b="Tongannel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTim Strawley drove his waggon south of Echad Candelleth along the road heading for Hollin, which crosses a small ford east of Garbert's cottage and climbs towards the Hollin Ridge.\nTongannel has asked you to follow the road south and search for any sign of Tim Strawley. She hopes you will not find anything, but if you do she wants to know about it.\n* Use Broken Crate\nObj 2:\nTongannel is at Echad Candelleth, the Elf-camp in Tâl Bruinen.\nYou have found Tim Strawley's waggon, apparently attacked by the Gauredain. The wooden figurines of which Tongannel spoke have all been stolen, and Strawley himself is missing.\n* Talk to Tongannel"},
{["next"]={2294},zone="Enedwaith",area="Thrór's Coomb",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Several clutches of gwiber have begun to build nests in the valley of Thrór's Coomb below Zudrugund, endangering the people of Enedwaith.",mobs={{locations={"65.57S, 8.48W"},name="Frithgeir"}},category="Enedwaith",id=648,scope="n/a",prev={2356},name="Dangerous Quarry",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Frithgeir",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGwiber-nests can be found in the eastern reaches of Thrór's Coomb, south of Zudrugund.\nFrithgeir has asked you to defeat any gwiber that you encounter near their nests.\n* Defeat gwiber near gwiber-nests (10)\nObj 2:\nFrithgeir is at Zudrugund, north of the gwiber-nests.\nYou should return to Frithgeir and let him know that you have been able to defeat a number of gwiber in Thrór's Coomb.\n* Talk to Frithgeir at Zudrugund",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2713},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="The leeches infesting the Water-works have grown out of control and are preventing the dwarves from exploring further.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=649,scope="n/a",name="Dark and Shallow Water",arcs="All Glory",level=55,c={"* The first goblin-corpse is at [17.0S, 116.2W]\n* The second goblin-corpse is at [17.0S, 116.6W]\n* The third goblin-corpse is at [16.7S, 116.5W]\n* The fourth goblin-corpse is at [16.9S, 116.9W]"},minlevel=50,b="Gyrgir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLeeches swarm around goblin corpses near The Drowned Deep, west of the Rotting Cellar.\nGyrgir would like you to find the corpses the leeches have been feasting upon and spread newt-toxin around them to kill the leeches.\n* Use Newt-toxin\n* Find the first goblin-corpse\n* Use Newt-toxin\n* Find the second goblin-corpse\n* Use Newt-toxin\n* Find the third goblin-corpse\n* Use Newt-toxin\n* Find the fourth goblin-corpse\nObj 2:\nGyrgir is in the Rotting Cellar, east of The Drowned Deep.\nGyrgir will be pleased to hear the leeches will no longer pose a problem to the dwarves.\n* Talk to Gyrgir at the Rotting Cellar"},
{["next"]={2485},area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",d="You found this dark crystal at the place where you had banished a Cuthraul.",mobs={{locations={"63.82S, 17.45W"},name="Saeradan"}},category="Enedwaith",id=650,scope="n/a",name="Dark Crystals",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Dark Morgul-stone",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSaeradan is at Echad Saeradan, south-west of Gavar Cadlus.\nYou should bring the crystal to Saeradan for identification.\n* Talk to Saeradan\n* Turn in Dark Morgul-stone",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="43s 12c"}},d="Crystals have been discovered in Moria, bearing marks of the Forgotten Treasury, a sealed vault hiding a substantial amount of wealth. This discovery has piqued the interest of some dwarves who now wish to uncover the vault and save its contents from the pilfering Orcs.",mobs={{locations={"9.86S, 112.76W"},name="Falgir"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=651,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1332},name="Dark Defilers",arcs="The Forgotten Treasury",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Falgir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDark Defilers can be found within the Forgotten Treasury to the south and south-east of the Deep Descent.\nFalgir asked that you find and hunt down the Dark Defilers watching over the new inhabitants of the Forgotten Treasury.\n* Defeat Dark Defilers\nObj 2:\nThe Deep Descent of Moria can be found north and north-west of the Forgotten Treasury.\nYou found and slew a fair number of the Dark Defilers who lurked throughout the interior of the Forgotten Treasury.\n* Talk to Falgir at the Deep Descent"},
{money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="In the Dark Delvings, the most forsaken depths of Khazad-dûm, the Nameless hold sway over the bitter shadows. Like other creatures that hide in the Black Pit that is Moria, the Nameless dread light, but they will not turn aside from any opportunity to spread corruption and dismay. These terrible foes must be purged from the Dark Delvings before they are able to wend their way into other parts of the mines.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=652,scope="n/a",name="Dark Delvings -- Illuminate the Dark",destinypoints={{val=500}},level=60,minlevel=60,b="Geirr",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe Dark Delvings are far to the south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nThe dwarf Geirr has challenged you to make your way into the Dark Delvings and defeat many Nameless foes therein.\nObj 2:\nThe dwarf Geirr is in the Twenty-first hall, north-west of the Great Delvings where the Nameless roam.\nGeirr will wish to hear if you have been brave enough to enter the Dark Delvings and face the Nameless ones in battle.\n* Return to Geirr at the Twenty-first Hall"},
{money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="In the Dark Delvings, the most forsaken depths of Khazad-dûm, the Nameless hold sway over the bitter shadows. Like other creatures that hide in the Black Pit that is Moria, the Nameless dread light, but they will not turn aside from any opportunity to spread corruption and dismay. These terrible foes must be purged from the Dark Delvings before they are able to wend their way into other parts of the mines.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=653,scope="n/a",name="Dark Delvings - Speak No Evil",destinypoints={{val=750}},level=60,minlevel=60,b="Eilíefr",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nGurvand is in the Dark Delvings, far to the south-east of Eilíefr's post at the Twenty-first Hall.\nThe dwarf Eilíefr has challenged you to make your way into the Dark Delvings and defeat the ancient Nameless creature known as the Gurvand, bringing its tongue back as a trophy when you are finished.\n* Show the Gurvand's tongue to Eilíefr at the Twenty-first Hall\n* Turn in Gurvand's Tongue"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Ancient mirrors once reflected light throughout the tunnels of Moria. One of them in the Flooded Deeps has been covered with a thick layer of fungus.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=654,scope="n/a",prev={1885},name="Darkened by Mildew",arcs="Fungus",level=56,c={"* The Fungus-covered Mirror is at [17.7S, 111.5W]"},pois={{locations={"17.70S, 111.54W"},name="Fungus-covered Mirror"}},minlevel=51,b="Thrand",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe fungus-covered mirror can be found just outside the Chamber of Memory, south of the Rotting Cellar.\nThrand believes the acid Ansurr crafted should destroy the fungus covering the mirror.\n* Use Fungus-covered Mirror\n* Turn in Small Acid-phial\nObj 2:\nThorgnyr is in Anazârmekhem, to the east of the Water-works in the Flaming Deeps.\nThrand asked you to report to a dwarf named Thorgnyr if the acid successfully removed the fungus.\n* Talk to Thorgnyr at Anazârmekhem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={47},area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="36s 40c"}},d="Finnán believes that you are trustworthy and can help the Trév Gállorg combat the Orcs of Bûrzum Pushdug.",mobs={{locations={"0.05N, 39.54W"},name="Finnán"}},selectoneof={{val="Aewolf",id="7000224E"},{val="Finnán's Vengeance",id="7000224D"},{val="Belegabnir",id="7000224C"}},category="Angmar",id=655,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={621},name="Dark Hunters",level=44,minlevel=39,b="Finnán",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe cave Bûrzum Pushdug is north of Tór Gailvin, in the western side of the hill on which that fortress is built. Tór Gailvin is north-east of Aughaire.\nFinnán asked you to defeat the Orcs of Bûrzum Pushdug in order to send a message of reproach to the Trév Duvárdain.\n* Defeat Tarkrîp warriors at Bûrzum Pushdug\n* Defeat Tarkrîp skirmishers at Bûrzum Pushdug\nObj 2:\nFinnán is at the centre island in the settlement of Aughaire.\nYou have defeated many orcs in Bûrzum Pushdug and should now bring news of your victory to Finnán.\n* Talk to Finnán"},
{["next"]={1953},area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The slopes of Gathbúrz are dotted with horrific idols of the Dark Lord Sauron. These must all be destroyed if the Elves are to reclaim the forest of Mirkwood from the clutches of the Enemy.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 46.59W"},name="Handelen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=656,scope="n/a",name="Dark Idols",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,c={"* There are Dark Idols in Gathbúrz at [13.0S, 45.0W],  [13.5S, 44.8W], [14.4S, 44.7W], [14.8S, 45.6W], [14.3S, 46.3W]"},pois={{locations={"14.41S, 44.67W","13.77S, 46.32W","15.00S, 46.56W","12.96S, 45.01W","13.72S, 45.48W","14.31S, 46.35W","13.53S, 44.80W","14.78S, 45.55W"},name="Dark Idol"}},minlevel=60,b="Handelen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIdols of the Necromancer may be found across the landscape of Gathbúrz.\nHandelen has tasked you with destroying the dark idols of Sauron that stand as a symbol of his power of Southern Mirkwood.\n* Use Dark Idol\nObj 2:\nHandelen is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nHaving destroyed many of the idols of the Necromancer, you should return to Handelen.\n* Talk to Handelen at Thangúlhad"},
{reputation={{val="+1200 with The Grey Company"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Lich Bluffs",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Below Drug Haniad, within an abandoned crypt, resides the source of the darkness creeping into the Lich Bluffs.",mobs={{locations={"70.57S, 15.46W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Enedwaith",id=657,scope="n/a",prev={592,2027,641},name="Darkness Revealed",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMincham is at his camp in the Lich Bluffs.\nYou should speak with Mincham when you are prepared, and he will lead you to the entrance of Lhe Colvern.\n* Talk to Mincham in the Lich Bluffs\nObj 2:\nMincham's camp lies in a small grove of trees, north of Drug Haniad.\nYou should return to Mincham and inform him that the ritual has been stopped and that a greater force is behind the raising of the wights in the Lich Bluffs.\n* Talk to Mincham  in the Lich Bluffs",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1636},area="Zelem-melek",zone="Moria",money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="A spy of Mordor has been spreading rumours throughout Moria of the arrival of a powerful sorceror out of Dol Guldur.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=658,scope="n/a",name="Dark Power Rising",arcs="Orcs of Mordor",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Knakk",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nRaulik is on the outskirts of Skrithûrz-ulíma, a Moria Orc encampment to the north-west of the Orc-watch.\nAn Orc of Mordor has disguised himself as a Moria Orc and is spreading tales of the power of the Sorceror of Dol Guldur. Knakk has asked you to silence his stories.\n* Defeat Raulik\nObj 2:\nKnakk is at the Orc-watch, south-east of Skrithûrz-ulíma.\nKnakk will be pleased to hear that Raulik has been silenced and none from Moria have thus far bowed a knee to Mordor.\n* Talk to Knakk at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Torquil's brothers were slain by orcs, and he seeks allies to take his vengeance upon them.",mobs={{locations={"0.04S, 40.17W"},name="Torquil"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Refined Celebrant Ointment",id="70008D08"},{q="(x2)",val="Refined Athelas Extract",id="70008CF7"}},category="Angmar",id=659,scope="n/a",name="Dark Raiders",receive={{val="Loop of Búth Sánkhas",id="7000EAE0"}},level=43,c={"* Morfil is a cave located east of the Cairn of Honour"},minlevel=38,b="Torquil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe cave Morfil is in Fasach-larran, east of Aughaire.\nTorquil has asked you to journey to Morfil and defeat the Orcs that killed his brothers.\n* Defeat Ongbúrz Warriors at Morfil\n* Defeat Ongbúrz Skirmishers at Morfil\n* Defeat Ongbúrz Captain at Morfil\nObj 2:\nTorquil is at Aughaire, near Crannog's ruling-seat, west of the settlement's centre island.\nYou have slain many Orcs at Morfil and should return now to Torquil at Aughaire.\n* Talk to Torquil"},
{["next"]={2339},reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="Taur Morvith",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Ianudirel has discovered the location of a number of evil relics being wielded by the sorcerers in Taur Morvith to summon fell spirits.",mobs={{locations={"17.96S, 50.30W"},name="Ianudirel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=660,scope="n/a",prev={1733,867},name="Dark Relics",arcs="The Fell Ruins",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=64,c={"* The Accursed Dagger is in Sâd Morangol at [19.1S, 48.8W]\n* The Accursed Cup is in Sâd Morangol at [19.4S, 48.3W]\n* The Accursed Staff is carried by one of the Sorcerers in Sâd Morangol"},minlevel=59,b="Ianudirel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe dagger and cup are held in the ruins of Sâd Morangol. The staff may be carried by one of the sorcerers of Sâd Morangol.\nIanudirel has asked you to collect three relics -- a dagger, a cup, and a staff -- from the sorcerers of Sâd Mornagol.\n* Turn in Accursed Dagger\n* Turn in Accursed Cup\n* Turn in Accursed Staff\nObj 2:\nIanudirel can be found just south of the bridge at Krul Lugu.\nYou should return the accursed relics you have gathered to Ianudirel.\n* Talk to Ianudirel\n* Turn in Accursed Dagger\n* Turn in Accursed Cup\n* Turn in Accursed Staff"},
{["next"]={674},area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+1200 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Uch-lûth received the gift of the Grey Company, but still do not trust you fully.",mobs={{locations={"61.84S, 14.13W"},name="Rhiain"}},category="Enedwaith",id=661,scope="n/a",prev={274},name="Dark Spirits of the Windfells",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Rhiain",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGwyllion's Gate lies to the south of Gavar Cadlus.\nRhiain has asked you to seek evidence of the Cuthraul's presence and to banish the spirit if you may.\n* Obj 2:\nCuthraul have appeared at Gwyllion's Gate, to the south of Gavar Cadlus.\nRhiain sked you to banish the Cuthraul if you can.\n* Defeat Cuthraul in the Windfells (3)\nObj 3:\nRhiain is at Gavar Cadlus, north from Gwyllion's Gate.\nYou should return to Rhiain with tidings of your success.\n* Talk to Rhiain at Gavar Cadlus"},
{area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+1200 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Uch-lûth were impressed by your victory against the Cuthraul at Gwyllion's Gate and seek your aid once more.",mobs={{locations={"61.85S, 14.12W"},name="Iuan"}},category="Enedwaith",id=662,scope="n/a",prev={673},name="Dark Spirits of the Windfells -- Repeatable",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Iuan",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCuthraul haunt the lands around Gavar Cadlus.\nIuan has asked you to banish the Cuthraul from the land.\n* Defeat Cuthraul (3)\nObj 2:\nIuan is at Gavar Cadlus in the Windfells of Enedwaith.\nYou should return to Iuan with tidings of your victory against the Cuthraul.\n* Talk to Iuan at Gavar Cadlus"},
{area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Camran of Aughaire has prepared a task by which he will know whether you are worthy of Crannog's trust.",mobs={{locations={"0.10N, 39.57W"},name="Camran"}},category="Angmar",id=663,scope="n/a",name="Dark Standards",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Refined Celebrant Ointment",id="70008D08"},{val="Jewel of Búth Sánkhas",id="7000EADC"}},level=43,c={"* Tór Gailvin is at [3.4N, 34.6W]"},pois={{locations={"3.31N, 35.14W","3.10N, 35.14W","3.58N, 35.53W","2.99N, 35.62W","3.12N, 35.73W","3.38N, 34.76W","3.06N, 35.13W","3.24N, 35.48W","3.57N, 34.62W","3.50N, 35.18W","3.53N, 34.62W","3.17N, 35.72W","3.55N, 35.19W","3.18N, 35.10W","3.56N, 35.07W"},name="Tór Gailvin Standard"}},minlevel=38,b="Camran",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe fortress of Tór Gailvin is north-east of Aughaire.\nCamran has asked you to return to Tór Gailvin and destroy the standards that fly over the fortress.\n* Use Tór Gailvin Standard\nObj 2:\nCamran is at the centre island of Aughaire, east of Crannog's ruling-seat.\nYou have destroyed the standards that flew above Tór Gailvin and should return now to Camran.\n* Talk to Camran",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={47},area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="36s 40c"}},d="Eilig, a warrior of the Trév Gállorg, seeks to cause disarray in the ranks of the Orcs that have taken the city of Dûn Covád and to visit his vengeance upon them for his sister, as well.",mobs={{locations={"0.23S, 39.78W"},name="Eilig"}},selectoneof={{val="Ranghâsh's Defeat",id=70002236},{val="Brecham",id=70002235},{val="Golubadanir",id=70002234}},category="Angmar",id=664,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={625},name="Dark Vengeance",arcs="Dark Vengeance",level=44,minlevel=39,b="Eilig",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orcs Nûlthauk and Ranghâsh are in the city of Dûn Covád, far to the north of Aughaire, among the western hills.\nEilig has asked you to defeat one of the two Orcs that slew his sister and so avenge her memory.\n* Kill 1 War-master Ranghâsh\n* Kill 1 Chieftain Nûlthauk\nObj 2:\nEilig is in the Búth Luikh in Aughaire.\nYou should return to Eilig and tell him of your journey into Dûn Covád.\n* Talk to Eilig"},
{["next"]={659},reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="In order to keep the pestilence from creeping to the fair lands beyond the walls of Moria, the Elves of Lothlórien believe the fungus-infested Orcs must be stopped ere they emerge from Moria.",mobs={{locations={"16.23S, 96.84W"},name="Donfuin"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=665,scope="n/a",t="Raid",name="Dâr Narbugud: A Plague Restrained",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Donfuin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe new Globsnaga Orcs can be found throughout Dâr Narbugud, in the southern-most reaches of the Foundations of Stone in Moria.\nDonfuin has asked you to slaughter the weaker, newly-altered Orcs to prevent their use as carriers of the fungus they are now infested with.\n* Defeat weak Globsnaga Orcs\nObj 2:\nDonfuin stands outside of Dâr Narbugud in Moria.\nYou should speak with Donfuin and inform him of your success against the weak Glabsnaga Orcs in Dâr Narbugud.\n* Talk to Donfuin"},
{["next"]={657},reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Elves believe that trolls give a great advantage to the enemy in battle, due to their massive strength and hardiness. The troll-leaders in Dâr Narbugud must be eliminated in order to weaken the enemy's forces.",mobs={{locations={"16.23S, 96.84W"},name="Donfuin"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=666,scope="n/a",t="Raid",name="Dâr Narbugud: Bastions of Doom",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Donfuin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe trolls you seek can be found in Dâr Narbugud, near the Dark Delvings at the southernmost tip of the Foundations of Stone.\nDonfuin has asked you to defeat the trolls' leaders, which should disorganize the trolls and deflate their usefulness in battle.\n* Defeat Rung\n* Defeat Blagh\nObj 2:\nDonfuin stands just outside of Dâr Narbugud.\nYou should speak with Donfuin and inform him of your victory over the troll-leaders.\n* Talk to Donfuin"},
{["next"]={661},reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="The great leaders of the Globsnaga in Dâr Narbugud are essential to the strength and strategy of the enemy. They must be destroyed before they can lead their Globsnaga-hosts to war against the dwarves and Elves of the neighbouring lands.",mobs={{locations={"16.23S, 96.84W"},name="Donfuin"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=667,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={656},name="Dâr Narbugud: Champions of Virulence",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Donfuin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe leaders of the Globsnaga can be found in Dâr Narbugud, in the southern-most reaches of the Foundations of Stone.\nYou should defeat each leader of the Globsnaga to sever the head of the force that rallies in in Dâr Narbugud.\n* Defeat Zholuga\n* Defeat Îstum\n* Defeat Flâgît\nObj 2:\nDonfuin is outside of Dâr Narbugud in Moria.\nYou should speak with Donfuin and tell him of your success against the leaders of the plague-bearing Orcs.\n* Talk to Donfuin"},
{reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="The great fumaroles of Dâr Narbugud fill the chambers of corruption with a noxious gas, creating the perfect atmosphere for the breeding of noxious spores.",mobs={{locations={"16.23S, 96.84W"},name="Donfuin"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=668,scope="n/a",t="Raid",name="Dâr Narbugud: Noxious Vapours",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Donfuin",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe greater fumaroles can be found in Dâr Narbugud, at the southern tip of the Foundations of Stone.\nDonfuin has asked you to destroy the fumaroles that belch their noxious fumes into the poisoned chambers of Dâr Narbugud.\n* Destroy fumaroles\n* Destroy greater fumaroles\nObj 2:\nDonfuin can be found outside of Dâr Narbugud in Moria.\nYou should go to Donfuin and inform him of your success in destroying the belching fumaroles of Dâr Narbugud.\n* Talk to Donfuin",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Celeborn has devised a means to ensure the Globsnaga fungus never survives once the legions of the infested are destroyed.",mobs={{locations={"16.23S, 96.84W"},name="Donfuin"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=669,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={655},name="Dâr Narbugud: Purifying the Fungal Contagions",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Donfuin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe chambers of rancour can be found in Dâr Narbugud, in the southern-most reaches of Moria's Foundations of Stone.\nYou should use the contents of the phial to cleanse the rancourous chambers of transformation within Dâr Narbugud.\n* Use Phial of Pure Water\n* Purify the liquid in Îstum's plague-chamber\n* Use Phial of Pure Water\n* Purify the liquid in Zholuga's plague-chamber\n* Use Phial of Pure Water\n* Purify the liquid in Flâgît's plague-chamber\nObj 2:\nDonfuin is outside of Dâr Narbugud in Moria.\nYou should return to Donfuin and inform him of your success in purifying the most corrupted places in Moria.\n* Talk to Donfuin\n* Turn in Phial of Pure Water"},
{reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Lothlórien",area="Caras Galadhon",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="One of the Nameless creatures that prowled the twisted passages of Dâr Narbugud was found carrying a strange sword-hilt, bearing an inscription in unmistakeable Sindarin letters. While this haft is now fell and cold to the touch, its history might be of interest to one who remembers its making.",mobs={{locations={"16.22S, 73.50W","15.03S, 66.39W"},name="Haldir"},{locations={"15.42S, 66.87W"},name="Celeborn"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=670,scope="n/a",t="Raid",name="Dâr Narbugud: The Bewildering Inscription",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Corrupted hilt",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCeleborn can be found in Lothlórien's main city, Caras Galadhon.\nYou should show the corrupted hilt you have found to Celeborn, whose wisdom and long memory may dispel the mystery surrounding this artifact.\n* Bring the hilt to Celeborn at Caras Galadhon\nObj 2:\nCeleborn believes that the sword hilt will be recognizeable to someone who lives in Lothlórien. He surmises, based on the words on the handle, that the warrior of old was a loyal protector of the Golden Wood.\nYou should seek someone who may recognize the befouled relic.\n* Talk to Haldir\n* Turn in Corrupted hilt",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Celeborn of Lothlórien believes that the restoration of the natural world is key in the battle against the powers of evil in Middle-earth.",mobs={{locations={"16.23S, 96.84W"},name="Donfuin"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=671,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={657},name="Dâr Narbugud: The Deep Places of the World",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Donfuin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe source of the pestilence in Moria is near the Dark Delvings at the southernmost tip of the Foundations of Stone, in a foul place called Dâr Narbugud.\nDonfuin wishes you and your allies to defeat the Nameless sources of the sickness spewing from Dâr Narbugud, thus removing the threat of the fungal plague's spread.\n* Defeat the Mistress of Pestilence\n* Defeat the Blind One\nObj 2:\nDonfuin is outside of Dâr Narbugud in Moria.\nYou should tell Celeborn of your very great deed in defeating the Mistress of Pestilence in Moria.\n* Talk to Donfuin"},
{reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Lothlórien",area="Nimrodel",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Celeborn, Lord of Lothlórien, is gravely concerned by the final and most perilous threat in Moria: the plague of fungus threatening to spread with the infected Orcs as they rally to defend their caverns against the dwarves and Elves.",mobs={{locations={"16.22S, 73.50W","15.03S, 66.39W"},name="Haldir"},{locations={"15.42S, 66.87W"},name="Celeborn"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=672,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={1061},name="Dâr Narbugud: The Heart of the Scourge",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,c={"* Stand in the entrance of the Mistress' room (you don't even have to kill her), you'll get the white text message to use the item in inventory for the quest update."},minlevel=55,b="Haldir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCeleborn is in Caras Galadhon, at the heart of Lothlórien.\nYou should speak with Celeborn at the behest of Baranglim to gain his counsel about the final and most important task to be achieved in Moria.\n* Talk to Celeborn at Caras Galadhon\nObj 2:\nDâr Narbugud is in the Foundations of Stone in Moria, to the south-east near the Dark Delvings.\nCeleborn has given you a phial of Elven light to bring to the heart of plague, sickness, and corruption within Moria.\n* Use Phial of Elven-light\n* Use the phial of light\nObj 3:\nCeleborn stands at the heart of Lothlórien, in the hidden city of Caras Galadhon.\nYou should speak with Celeborn and share the tale of your great success in Dâr Narbugud, dealing a heavy blow to the creatures who would cover the world in sickness.\n* Talk to Celeborn at Caras Galadhon"},
{area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="Stíling pointed out an ancient dead-fall in the mines, constructed by the Dwarves of Moria long ago, and suggested that it might be used to the advantage of the dwarves.",selectoneof={{val="Stíling's Reward",id="700163A1"},{val="Pukhlor's Fall",id="7001605F"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=673,scope="n/a",prev={307},name="Dead-fall",arcs="Sky Fall",level=54,pois={{locations={"10.89S, 111.00W"},name="Dwarf-made Dead-fall"}},minlevel=49,b="Stíling",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe dead-fall trap lies near the goblin-camp at Gamil Filik, south-east of the Deep Descent camp.\nStíling has asked you to find the dead-fall trap and arm it, then lure Pukhlor to his death beneath the rocks.\n* Use Dwarf-made Dead-fall\n* Arm the trap and lure Pukhlor into it\nObj 2:\nStíling is at the Deep Descent camp, north-west of Gamil Filik.\nYou should return to Stíling and let him know of Pukhlor's defeat.\n* Talk to Stíling at the Deep Descent camp"},
{area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="With the terrible presence of wights, Hill-men of Rhudaur, and the darkwater menace, the foe has become too great to be held back by the small Eglain camp.",mobs={{locations={"29.62S, 27.40W"},name="Eriac the Strong"}},selectoneof={{val="The Tusker's Flanks",id="70000CC9"},{val="Leggings of the Stilled Waters",id="7001D1B7"},{val="Eriac's Swamp-stompers",id="7001D1B6"}},category="Lone-lands",id=674,scope="n/a",name="Dead Water",arcs="Angmar's Army",level=31,c={"* pending"},minlevel=26,b="Eriac the Strong",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Gloom-water are in the eastern reaches of Agamaur.\nEriac has asked you to help keep the Gloom-water, creatures formed from the waters of Agamaur, at bay. As evidence of your efforts, he wants you to bring him the ancient tokens of Rhudaur and Arthedain that are caught up into the Gloom-water as they swirl up from the swamp.\n* Return the Tokens to Eriac\n* Turn in Ancient Token"},
{area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Vatnar has detected a band of goblin-sappers digging a tunnel below the cellars of Thangúlhad. He and his brother Thyrnir intend to invade the goblin-tunnel and collapse it before they can undermine the tower's foundation.\nWARNING: Death From Below is a high difficulty solo challenge quest. Beware, all who enter therein.",mobs={{locations={"12.60S, 46.51W"},name="Vatnar"}},category="Mirkwood",id=675,scope="n/a",prev={1187},name="Death From Below",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Vatnar",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nVatnar is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nYou should speak with Vatnar when your are ready to travel with him and Thyrnir to prevent the goblin-sappers from destroying Thangúlhad.\n* Talk to Vatnar to enter the cellars\nObj 2:\nVatnar is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nWith the aid of Vatnar and Thyrnir, you have defeated the goblin-sappers and saved Thangúlhad. You should speak again with Vatnar.\n* Talk to Vatnar at Thangúlhad"},
{zone="Lothlórien",area="Nanduhirion",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="With their communications severed, the Orcs in the Dimrill Dale are now vulnerable. The dwarves wish to demonstrate to them how helpless they truly are.",selectoneof={{val="Dimrill Dale's Messenger",id=70016415},{val="Raskwith's Boots",id="700163E4"}},category="Moria",id=676,scope="n/a",prev={1106},name="Death to the Invaders",arcs="Out of the Mines",level=60,pois={{locations={"12.78S, 77.47W","13.99S, 77.82W","15.14S, 75.62W"},name="Soft Dirt"}},minlevel=55,b="Raskwith",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orc-camps Uruk-gashan, Drû-garmadh, and Athmadhul are to the south-east of Mekhem-bizru.\nRaskwith asked you to go to the three Orc-camps in the Dimrill Dale and plant dwarf-flags in each, to show the Orcs that the Dale will never be theirs.\n* Use Soft Dirt\n* Turn in Dwarf-banner\n* Use Soft Dirt\n* Turn in Dwarf-banner\n* Use Soft Dirt\n* Turn in Dwarf-banner\nObj 2:\nRaskwith is in Mekhem-bizru, north-west of the Orc-camps.\nRaskwith will be pleased to hear that the banners have been placed in the Orc-camps.\n* Talk to Raskwith at Mekhem-bizru",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The last part of Dómárr's plan is to trick the Durub Orcs into viewing Mazog's Orcs as a challenge to their dominance and threatening their territory.",selectoneof={{val="Durub's Downfall",id=70016414},{val="Guile",id="700163A8"}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=677,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1001},name="Death to the Puny Mine-dwellers",arcs="The Durub",level=56,c={"* The Durub Shrine in Gazatu-ru where you must plant the banner is at [8.1S, 105.2W]"},pois={{locations={"8.03S, 105.36W","8.08S, 105.17W"},name="Durub Shrine"}},minlevel=51,b="Dómárr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Durub shrine is in the camp of Gazatu-ru, south of the Twenty-first Hall.\nDómárr has asked you to plant a Moria banner upon the shrine in the Durub Orc-camp. He believes this will enrage them and cause them to attack the Orcs of Mazog.\n* Use Durub Shrine\n* Turn in Moria Banners\nObj 2:\nDómárr is at the Twenty-first hall, north of Gazatu-ru.\nDómárr will be pleased to hear Mazog's banner has been planted on the Durub shrine and the Orcs of Mordor are marching for war.\n* Talk to Dómárr at the Twenty-first Hall"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="A great host of Orcs spilled through Ram Dúath, driving the Men of the North Downs from their farms. Esteldín, home of the few remaining Dúnedain of the North, was spared discovery. It is from there that the Rangers begin to plan their counter-offensive against the black tide of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"13.06S, 55.30W"},name="Mincham"},{locations={"9.44S, 41.27W"},name="Daervunn"}},selectoneof={{val="Daervunn's Hooded Cloak",id=70001788},{val="Daervunn's Shoulder Guards",id=70001787}},category="North Downs",id=678,scope="n/a",prev={1607},name="Deciphering the Black Speech",arcs="The Black Tide of Angmar",level=32,minlevel=27,b="Daervunn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMincham has a small camp overlooking the Greenway just south of the Fields of Fornost.\nDaervunn returned the orders to you and sent you to speak with Mincham, who is proficient in the Black Speech of Mordor, at his camp bordering the Fields of Fornost in the west. He hopes that Mincham will be able to translate the orders.\n* Ask Mincham to translate the Uruk-orders\nObj 2:\nDaervunn awaits your return at Esteldín.\nMincham returned the orders to you and sent you back to Daervunn with his report.\n* Talk to Daervunn\n* Turn in Uruk-orders"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Dardúr has sent you to Elrond Halfelven, one of the Wise, to learn the deep secrets of Rune-craft.",mobs={{locations={"20.10S, 96.82W"},name="Dardúr"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Rune-keeper",id=679,scope="n/a",requiredclasses="Rune-keeper",name="Deep Secrets of Rune-craft",arcs="Learned in Letters",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Dardúr",repeatable="No",traits={{val="That Which Does Not Kill Us"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDardúr knows of a legendary rune-keeper who could teach you great lessons, but first you must be suitably outfitted.\n* Complete A Worthy Garment\n* Complete Hewing a New Stone\nObj 2:\nDardúr is at Gondamon in Ered Luin.\n* Talk to Dardúr\nObj 3:\nElrond's house lies in the vale of Rivendell in the Trollshaws.\nDardúr has bidden you seek the guidance of Elrond Halfelven so you might learn from him.\n* Talk to Elrond in Rivendell"},
{["next"]={1824},reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="Ashenslades",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="At the centre of Ânghum-maudhûl, the long-lived Darúk watches over his forces. This evil creature has served for many long years in the armies of Dol Guldur.",mobs={{locations={"17.67S, 48.30W"},name="Harchador"}},category="Mirkwood",id=680,scope="n/a",prev={1918,1072},name="Defeat Darúk",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,c={"* Darúk and his Standard are in Ânghum-maudhûl at [20.1S, 45.9W]"},pois={{locations={"20.12S, 45.91W"},name="Darúk's Standard"}},minlevel=60,b="Harchador",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDarúk is at Ânghum-maudhûl to the east of Mithechad.\nHarchador has asked you to defeat Darúk and destroy his standard.\n* Defeat Darúk\n* Use Darúk's Standard\nObj 2:\nHarchador is at Mithechad, west of Ânghum-maudhûl.\nYou should return to Harchador with news of your victory against Darúk.\n* Talk to Harchador at Mithechad",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Fil Gashan is the barracks and mustering point for the Orcs' invasion of Lothlórien. Hidden deep within the fiery landscape and sharing an adjacent entrance to the Forges of Khazad-dûm, Orcs train here under the watchful eye of General Talug.",mobs={{locations={"13.41S, 108.07W"},name="Vagun"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=681,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Defeat the Lieutenants",arcs="General's Command",level=60,minlevel=57,b="Vagun",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFil Gashan is south-west of Anazârmekhem.\nVagun believes that the Orcs of Fil Gashan must be driven out, and that by defeating the lieutenants and taking their gear, you might be able to deceive the other Orcs.\n* Defeat lieutenants\n* Defeat chief guards\nObj 2:\nVagun is at Anazârmekhem, north-east of Fil Gashan.\nYou fought your way through Fil Gashan and defeated the lieutenants as you were asked. Now you should return to Vagun with your report.\n* Talk to Vagun at Anazârmekhem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hithlad",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Mayor Wat Mudbottom wants some assistance in clearing the beasts of Angmar out of Hoarhallow.",category="Hoarhallow",id=682,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Defence of Hoarhallow",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Mayor Wat Mudbottom",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nStay within the bounds of Hoarhallow village and stop the forces of Angmar threatening the hobbits there.\nMayor Wat Mudbottom enlisted your aid in fighting back the foes within the area of Hoarhallow.\n* Defeat minions of Angmar at Hoarhallow (15 at Hoarhallow )\nObj 2:\nMayor Mudbottom is in Hoarhallow.\nNow that you have assisted in the defence of Hoarhallow you should speak with Mayor Wat Mudbottom about the reward he offered you.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Steps of Gram",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="At the pinnacle of Lugazag, the tower on the easternmost edge of the Ettenmoors, once a stronghold for Angmar's army, now flies the flags of the Free Peoples. Angmar's army is well aware of this and wishes to return the tower to their control. Moreover, their taskmasters and war-tyrants will drive them to recover the location at all costs.",category="Lugazag",id=683,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Defence of Lugazag",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Ambeng",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nFight and slaughter the foes from Angmar within the area of Lugazag.\nSergeant-at-Arms Ambeng wants to ensure that the Free Peoples are prepared for the onslaught that will ensue at the walls of Lugazag and enlisted your help in driving the foe from the field. Stay within the immediate area of the tower and stand against the foe. If Ambeng or Lugazag falls, report to Captain-General Tordúr at Glân Vraig.\n* Defeat minions of Angmar at Lugazag (30 at Lugazag )\nObj 2:\nIf Lugazag and Sergeant-at-Arms Ambeng still stand, report to him for your reward. If the tower was lost or Ambeng fell in battle, report to Captain-General Tordúr at Glân Vraig.\nYou stood against the foe within the walls of Lugazag. Your efforts were not in vain, and you are owed a well-earned reward.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="The Ettenmoors",area="Arador's End",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Mines provide the ore that is needed to build weapons and armour for the war. The Isendeep long ago stopped being a mine capable of great production, but there are still veins of ore within the stone there and this makes the location desirable to both the forces of Angmar and the Free Peoples.",category="Isendeep Mine",id=684,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Defence of the Isendeep",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Osur",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nLieutenant Otur is within the Isendeep Mine.\nLieutenant Otur asked for your assistance to help defend the Isendeep Mine against the forces of Angmar. If you succeed, speak with Otur or if he or the Isendeep falls into enemy hands, report to Captain-General Tordúr at Glân Vraig.\n* Defeat minions of Angmar within the Isendeep Mine (30 at Isendeep )\nObj 2:\nLieutenant Otur is within the Isendeep Mine. If Otur has fallen or the Isendeep Mine is in the hands of the enemy, you can speak with Captain-General Tordúr at Glân Vraig in his stead.\nThrough a hard fought battle, you defeated great number of the enemy within the Isendeep mine.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hithlad",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Once a harvesting location for the Hobbits of Hoarhallow, the Grimwood Lumber-camp now offers equipment for refining and preparing the wood needed to build palisades throughout the Ettenmoors. Lieutenant Swithulf knows that retribution will come in the form of an assault from Gramsfoot.",category="Grimwood",id=685,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Defence of the Lumber-camp",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="First Marshal Núrdram",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nStay within the area of the Grimwood Lumber-camp and defeat the enemy out of Angmar.\nFirst Marshal Núrdam believes that the Free Peoples can achieve victory with your assistance at the Grimwood Lumber-camp and has asked that you stay and fight to defeat the foe when they come. If Ambeng or Lugazag falls, report to Captain-General Tordúr at Glân Vraig.\n* Defeat minions of Angmar at the Grimwood Lumber-camp (30 at Grimwood Lumber Camp )\nObj 2:\nFirst Marshal Núrdram is at the Grimwood Lumber-camp. If Núrdram fell in battle or the Lumber-camp has fallen to the enemy, make your way to Glân Vraig and speak with Captain-General Tordúr.\nThough it was a hard-fought battle, you made your stand and have earned your reward.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Global",zone="Middle-earth",reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},d="Bree was a beacon of freedom for all in the North, until brigands took it for their own.",category="Skirmish",id=686,scope="n/a",name="Defence of The Prancing Pony -- Daily",level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe citizens of Bree have barricaded themselves within The Prancing Pony Inn and are desperately awaiting help.\n* Complete the Defence of The Prancing Pony Skirmish"},
{area="Coldfells",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Tirith Rhaw, the tower on the eastern-most edge of the Ettenmoors, is a stronghold for the Free Peoples. Angmar's army is well aware of this and often organize raids to overrun the location to provide themselves a strong foothold in the east.",category="Tirith Rhaw",id=687,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Defence of Tirith Rhaw",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Mibrethil",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nDefeat the foes from Angmar within the area of Tirith Rhaw.\nSergeant-at-Arms Mibrethil wants to ensure that the Free Peoples are prepared for the onslaught that will ensue at the walls of Tirith Rhaw and enlisted your help in driving the foe from the field. Stay within the immediate area of the tower and stand against the foe. If Mibrethil or Tirith Rhaw falls, report to Captain-General Tordúr at Glân Vraig.\n* Defeat minions of Angmar at Tirith Rhaw (30 at Tirith Rhaw )\nObj 2:\nIf Tirith Rhaw and Sergeant-at-Arms Mibrethil still stand, report to him for your reward. If the tower was lost or Mibrethil fell in battle, report to Captain-General Tordúr at Glân Vraig.\nYou stood against the foe within the walls of Tirith Rhaw. Your efforts were not in vain and you are owed a well-earned reward.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hoardale",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="South of the falls of the Hoarwell River there stands a keep upon an island. This keep, once a seat of Rhudaur's strength within the Ettenmoors, long ago fell to ruin, but the vantage afforded at the top of the towers makes the location a strategic point within the Ettenmoors. It is for this reason that Lieutenant Solvi believes Angmar's army will strike at the location in an attempt to claim it for their own.",category="Tol Ascarnen",id=688,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Defence of Tol Ascarnen",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Solvi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nStand with Lieutenant Solvi at Tol Ascarnen and defeat the enemy there.\nLieutenant Solvi wants to prepare for battle and hold this all-important location out of the hands of the Enemy. If you succeed, speak with Solvi or if he or Tol Ascarnen falls into enemy hands, report to Captain-General Tordúr at Glân Vraig.\n* Defeat minions of Angmar at Tol Ascarnen (30 at Tol Ascarnen )\nObj 2:\nReport to Lieutenant Solvi at Tol Ascarnen if he stands and you control the location. If he has fallen or the enemy claimed the keep, return to Glân Vraig and speak with Captain-General Tordúr.\nThe battle at Tol Ascarnen earned you victory over your foes.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Drugoth has gathered his lieutenants and generals to his Glacier Fortress. You must kill his Generals so that they may not send evil spreading across the south.\nThis quest will be cancelled if you leave the Glacier Fortress before completing it.",category="In Their Absence",id=689,scope="n/a",name="Defenders of the Fortress",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x6)",val="Medallion of the North-men",id=70025341}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nDrugoth the Death-monger has relocated from the Misty Mountains and made his new home in the largest glacier in Forochel Bay.  Now, his mad rambling mind is planning an attack on Annuminas down south.  You must stop this attack before it happens by killing Drugoth and both of his generals.\n* Defeat the first General\n* Defeat the second General\n* Defeat Drugoth"},
{["next"]={635},reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Cudhaer is working on repairing the ballista, a sensitive and timely process.",category="Evendim",id=690,scope="n/a",prev={1822},name="Defending the Ballista",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=32,minlevel=27,b="Cudhaer",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nScouts can be found in the stands of trees south-west and south-east of the bluff overlooking the colossus.\nCudhaer asked you to flush out several scouts while he repairs the ballista.\n* Defeat scouts\nObj 2:\nCudhaer is at the bluff overlooking the colossus from the south.\nCudhaer will be pleased to hear the scouts have been driven off and his position is secure.\n* Talk to Cudhaer near the colossus\nObj 3:\nSardan is at the Colossus, north of the ballista's bluff.\nSardan will want to know the ballista is repaired and ready to fire.\n* Talk to Sardan",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2305,1055},area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="10s"}},d="Aggy Digweed spotted figures carrying a crate out of Nan Wathren. To signal the guard at Trestlebridge, she fired a fire arrow towards them and struck the crate, which exploded in a ball of flame.",mobs={{locations={"16.15S, 53.49W"},name="Aggy Digweed"}},category="North Downs",id=691,scope="n/a",name="Defending the Bridge",arcs="The Black Fire",level=24,pois={{locations={"15.03S, 49.91W"},name="Black Powder"}},minlevel=19,b="Aggy Digweed",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe crate was destroyed at the western edge of Nan Wathren, just beyond the bridges.\nAggy Digweed, afraid that this new weapon may be the doom of Trestlebridge, asked you to look for the shattered remains of the crate.\n* Bring the crate contents to Aggy Digweed\n* Collect the crate contents"},
{["next"]={2057},area="Kingsfell",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="20s 80c"}},d="Your attacks on the Orcs in Gatson's fields has stirred their peers' wrath. Gatson expects a raid at any moment.",mobs={{locations={"10.33S, 45.62W"},name="Gatson"}},category="North Downs",id=692,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2495},name="Defending the Herd",arcs="The Last Farm",receive={{val="Gatson's Shoulder Pads",id="7000187D"}},level=26,c={"* Defeat several waves of 3 Orcs each."},minlevel=21,b="Gatson",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGatson's man Alwin is with the herd, south of the farm.\nGatson has asked you to help his farmhand, Alwin, defend his herd from the marauding Orcs. Make sure neither Alwin nor any of the herd come to harm.\n* Talk to Gatson's farmhand Alwin\nObj 2:\nGatson is at his farm, north of the fields where his herd grazes.\nYou and Alwin managed to stave off the Orcs' raid on Gatson's herd. You should return to the farm and tell Gatson.\n* Talk to Gatson"},
{area="Arador's End",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="The Free Peoples have been coming into Grothum village, killing goblins and stealing their food and ale.",category="Grothum",id=693,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Defend Us",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Gasham",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSlaughter the Free Peoples as they attempt to destroy the goblins of Grothum.\nYou have been asked to honour the pledge made by Angmar to assist the goblins against the Free Peoples, an obligation you must fulfil.\n* Defeat the Free Peoples at Grothum (15 at Grothum )\nObj 2:\nGrothum is defended and your obligation to the goblins is complete. Return to Gasham and tell him so. If Gasham was killed return to the War-tyrant and tell him of your victory.\nFighting off the enemy within the bounds of Grothum proved a simple task for one such as you.\n* Talk to Gasham\n* Talk to War-tyrant Akúlhun",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2122},area="Nan Sirannon",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="A messenger from Barad Morlas has reached the half-orcs at Târ Stazg, warning them of the presence of the Elves in Eregion.",mobs={{locations={"50.50S, 8.07W"},name="Palanaer"}},category="Eregion",id=694,scope="n/a",name="Delaying Aid",arcs="Aid from the East",level=50,c={"* Târ Stazg is north-east of Echad Dúnann along the mountains before the Redhorn Gate."},minlevel=45,b="Palanaer",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTâr Stazg is north-east of Echad Dúnann along the mountains before the Redhorn Gate.\nPalanaer has asked you to journey to Târ Stazg and defeat the Half-orcs before they can reinforce Barad Morlas.\n* Defeat half-orcs in Târ Stazg (14)\nObj 2:\nPalanaer is in Echad Dúnann south-west of Târ Stazg.\nYou should return to Palanaer and tell him of the half-orc defeat.\n* Talk to Palanaer at Echad Dúnann",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="The pies are freshly baked and ready to be delivered.",category="Evendim",id=695,scope="n/a",prev={970},name="Delivering the Pies",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="Rosa Brockhouse",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe tables for the pies are at the Farmer's Market at Northcotton Farm.\nThe pies are warm and smell delicious. They must be delivered to the tables at the market grounds.\n* Use Table\n* Turn in Warm Pie\nObj 2:\nAlbin Northcotton is at the Farmer's Market on Northcotton Farm.\nAlbin Northcotton will want to know the pies are ready for the market.\n* Talk to Albin Northcotton",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={343},area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Gautar examined the tokens you recovered from the fell spirits and discovered that they bear signs of Angmar, sigils that may be binding the spirits to the mortal world. A name also was written upon them: Deluches.",mobs={{locations={"6.90N, 25.82W"},name="Gautar"}},category="Angmar",id=696,scope="n/a",prev={2044},name="Deluches",arcs="Banishing the Darkness",level=47,pois={{locations={"4.97N, 27.65W"},name="Spirit-shrine"}},minlevel=42,b="Gautar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe shrine of the fell spirits is on an islet in a small pond in the southern part of Imlad Balchorth, south and a little west from Myrkworth.\nGautar has asked you to go to the shrine of the fell spirits in Imlad Balchorth. The shrine can be recognized as a large iron spike, a common feature of the works of the Angmarim which might make the shrine difficult to find.\n* Use Spirit-shrine\nObj 2:\nGautar is back at Myrkworth, north and a bit east from the shrine of Deluches.\nYou were unable to defeat the terrible captain of the spirits, Deluches, so the fell spirits could not be banished. You should return to Gautar and report these events.\n* Talk to Gautar"},
{["next"]={2481},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",d="Glorenglir believed that snow lurkers could be used to unearth fragments of history from the snows of the Misty Mountains, and you have proven her correct.",mobs={{locations={"29.39S, 5.65W"},name="Glorenglir"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Deluros"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=697,scope="n/a",prev={2791},name="Deluros of Rivendell",arcs="Hidden by Drifts",level=39,minlevel=34,b="Glorenglir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe scholar Deluros is within the library of the House of Elrond in Rivendell.\nGlorenglir has asked you to bring the relic fragments you recovered from the snow lurkers of the Misty Mountains to Deluros with the hope that he will recognize her readiness to advance as a scholar.\n* Talk to Deluros\n* Turn in Relic-fragment",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{d="Ost Dunhoth is the fortress of Gortheron the Doom-caller.",category="In Their Absence",id=698,scope="n/a",name="Denizens of Ost Dunhoth",receive={{q="(x20)",val="Medallion of the North-men",id=70025341}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Arnfinnur",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nOst Dunhoth is in Southern Enedwaith.\nYou have been asked to venture within Ost Dunhoth and defeat many of the denizens within.\nObj 2:\nThe Rangers in Thror's Coomb will be pleased to hear you have culled some of Gortheron's forces.\n* Talk to Arnfinnur"},
{area="Chetwood",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Woodcutters from Combe moving further into the Chetwood in search of quality lumber are seeking protection from the local wildlife.",mobs={{locations={"28.86S, 47.10W"},name="Taylor Green"}},selectoneof={{val="Wolf-Pelt Trousers",id="70019BE4"},{val="Wolf-Pelt Leggings",id="70019BE2"}},category="Bree-land",id=699,scope="n/a",name="Den of Wolves",level=8,minlevel=4,b="Taylor Green",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe wolf-den is set in the cliff wall north-east of the lumber camp.\nWoodcutter Taylor Green is concerned that the wolves roaming the woods to the north-east may be a threat to the woodcutters and has asked you to cull their numbers.\n* Defeat wolves at the wolf-den (8)\nObj 2:\nWoodcutter Taylor Green waits at the lumber camp to the south-west, north of the guard-house.\nAs Woodcutter Green requested, you put the fear of Men into the wolves of the Chetwood. He will be pleased to hear of your success.\n* Talk to Taylor Green",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="43s 12c"}},d="Crystals have been discovered in Moria, bearing marks of the Forgotten Treasury, a sealed vault hiding a substantial amount of wealth. This discovery has piqued the interest of some dwarves who now wish to uncover the vault and save its contents from the pilfering Orcs.",mobs={{locations={"9.86S, 112.76W"},name="Garthar"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=700,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1332},name="Depleted Crystals",arcs="The Forgotten Treasury",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Garthar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Forgotten Treasury is located south and south-east of the Deep Descent.\nGarthar asked you to search through the Forgotten Treasury for any sign of the depleted crystals within. Should you find them, he asked you to return them to him.\n* Bring the crystals to Garthar at the Deep Descent\n* Turn in Depleted Crystal"},
{["next"]={1189},area="The Flaming Deeps",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The Flaming Deeps are mostly unexplored, but the dwarves do know that there are strange Orcs inhabiting the Deeps.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=701,scope="n/a",name="Descending",arcs="Ghash-Hai",receive={{val="Gollinn",id="70017CEA"}},level=56,minlevel=51,b="Hysing",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGhâsh-hai can be found throughout the Flaming Deeps.\nHysing wants to know more about the Fire-orcs who inhabit the Flaming Deeps.\n* Defeat Ghâsh-hai (18)\nObj 2:\nHysing is at Anazârmekhem at the north end of the Flaming Deeps.\nHysing will be interested in hearing more about what you encountered while battling the Ghâsh-hai.\n* Talk to Hysing at Anazârmekhem"},
{["next"]={167},area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Elves of the Golden Host discovered a second enemy encampment on the western edge of the Dourstocks, but something seems to be wrong.",mobs={{locations={"13.54S, 58.13W"},name="Mothelen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=702,scope="n/a",name="Deserters",arcs="An Unsettling Matter",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,minlevel=57,b="Mothelen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblin-deserters can be found in the Dourstocks, between Echad Mothelen and Burgûl-stazg, to the north-west.\nMothelen has asked you to hunt down some of the goblin-deserters and discover what has terrified them.\n* Defeat goblin-deserters in the Dourstocks\nObj 2:\nMothelen is at Echad Mothelen in the western Dourstocks, south-east of Burgûl-stazg.\nYou should return to Mothelen with the information you have gathered.\n* Talk to Mothelen at Echad Mothelen"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="9s 10c"}},d="You have been encouraged to learn the ways of the desolate crags of West Angmar, so you may better find the way to Aughaire when needed.",mobs={{locations={"9.52S, 41.07W"},name="Gaellant"},{locations={"12.71S, 67.00W"},name="Cúlith"},{locations={"20.05S, 96.98W"},name="Dagfinn"},{locations={"18.84N, 72.37W"},name="Okko"},{locations={"28.14S, 92.17W"},name="Erydhriel"},{locations={"0.05N, 39.20W"},name="Torcall"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Juniper Smith"},{locations={"29.91S, 5.90W"},name="Mallenhadh"},{locations={"31.86S, 51.28W"},name="Flambard Took"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Bolo Boffin"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Bow Chant: Major Breach-finder",id="7000A717"},{q="(x5)",val="Bow Chant: Whisper-draw",id="7000A871"},{q="(x5)",val="Bow Chant: Wind-rider",id="7000A71A"}},category="Hunter",id=703,scope="n/a",requiredclasses="Hunter",name="Desolation by Aughaire",receive={{val="Guide to West Angmar",id="7000A6DE"}},level=44,pois={{locations={"2.68N, 38.74W","1.92N, 39.44W","2.08N, 37.98W","3.15N, 39.29W","1.42N, 39.07W","2.69N, 38.14W","2.55N, 39.47W","1.76N, 37.95W","1.79N, 38.73W"},name="Subtle Tracks"}},minlevel=44,b="Flambard Took",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTorcall is at Aughaire, in West Angmar.\nYou have been told to speak with Torcall, one of the Hillmen at Aughaire, about secret paths through the desolation of Angmar.\n* Talk to Torcall\nObj 2:\nTorcall has hidden an Orc-skull somewhere within West Angmar.\nYou have been challenged to recover an Orc-skull that Torcall says is hidden somewhere in West Angmar. He left by the road north of Aughaire and slew an Orc at some point along his journey; if you follow his trail, you may be able to find it.\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\nObj 3:\nTorcall is in Aughaire, in West Angmar.\nYou have recovered the Orc-skull Torcall asked you to find and should now return it to him as proof of your skill as a hunter.\n* Talk to Torcall\n* Turn in Orc-skull"},
{["next"]={45},area="Eastern Malenhad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Kol, a resident of Gabilshathûr, told you of their desperate need for food.",category="Angmar",id=704,scope="n/a",prev={2884},name="Desperate Straits",arcs="Scaled Menace",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Kol",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNorboglir and slugs can be found in Duvuinen, north of Gabilshathûr.\nKol has asked you to collect norboglir-legs and slug-tongues to help supplement the provisions at Gabilshathûr.\n* Bring the ingredients to Kol\n* Turn in Corrupted Norboglir Leg\n* Turn in Brimstone-leech Tongue"},
{["next"]={1904,1493},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="Not only are there worms within the western valley of Ram Dúath, but drakes as well. The winged drakes, more intelligent than their lesser kin, present a greater threat to Esteldín and the North Downs.",mobs={{locations={"9.68S, 42.04W"},name="Arastil"}},category="North Downs",id=705,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2795},name="Destroying the Hatchery",arcs="Valley of the Worms",level=33,pois={{locations={"4.60S, 39.71W","2.94S, 41.27W","4.93S, 41.48W","2.89S, 41.22W","3.11S, 41.25W","4.91S, 41.94W","4.60S, 39.66W","4.54S, 39.65W","4.08S, 40.16W","3.14S, 41.23W","4.62S, 41.27W","4.08S, 40.18W","4.62S, 41.28W","5.14S, 41.65W","4.90S, 41.95W","4.10S, 40.17W"},name="Drake-egg"}},minlevel=28,b="Arastil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDrake-nests may be found in the western valley of Ram Dúath, north of Esteldín. Destroy eggs found within the nests to stop the drakes' spread.\nArastil has asked you to destroy the nests of the drakes who dwell within the western valley of Ram Dúath before they can multiply.\n* Use Drake-egg\nObj 2:\nArastil awaits your return in Esteldín.\nYou found several drake-nests in the western Ram Dúath and destroyed them, but worms were plentiful in the area, and the nests were well-defended. Arastil will wish to hear of your victory.\n* Talk to Arastil"},
{area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="The Dunlendings are ravaging Glâd Ereg, cutting down trees to supply the craftsmen of Saruman with wood.",mobs={{locations={"40.15S, 16.48W"},name="Inufileg"}},selectoneof={{val="Wood-cutter's Gloves",id=70016078},{val="Inufileg's Companion",id="7001610B"}},category="Eregion",id=706,scope="n/a",prev={91},name="Destroying their Means",arcs="Axes of the South",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Inufileg",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Dunlending lumber-camp is south-east of Gwingris. Inufileg is at Gwingris, west and north of the Dunlending lumber-camp\nInufileg has asked you to stop the Dunlendings' wood-cutting by taking their axes from them.\n* Talk to Inufileg at Gwingris\n* Turn in Dunlending Axe"},
{["next"]={1961},area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You eliminated much of the threat of traps and archers that made attacking Ashúrz Maufulug a particularly hazardous proposition, but there is more yet to do.",mobs={{locations={"16.50S, 60.30W"},name="Glamodúd"}},category="Mirkwood",id=707,scope="n/a",prev={2059},name="Destroying Their Means",destinypoints={{val=250}},arcs="Breaking the Pincer",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,pois={{locations={"18.43S, 60.89W","18.34S, 60.93W","18.28S, 60.94W","18.09S, 60.88W","18.07S, 61.07W","18.15S, 60.96W","18.05S, 60.73W","18.02S, 61.01W","18.21S, 61.03W"},name="Weapon-rack"},{locations={"18.04S, 60.75W","18.43S, 60.91W","18.06S, 60.98W","18.35S, 60.92W","18.05S, 61.06W","18.14S, 61.03W","18.12S, 60.79W","18.27S, 61.06W","18.17S, 61.05W","18.26S, 60.80W","18.36S, 60.74W","18.16S, 60.83W"},name="Crate of Supplies"}},minlevel=56,b="Glamodúd",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWeapon-racks and crates of supplies can be found in Ashúrz Maufulug, to the south and a little west of Echad Glamodúd.\nGlamodúd has asked you to further weaken the Orcs of Ashúrz Maufulug by destroying their weapons and supplies.\n* Use Crate of Supplies\n* Use Weapon-rack\nObj 2:\nGlamodúd is at Echad Glamodúd, south and a little west from Ashúrz Maufulug.\nYou should return to Ashúrz Maufulug with news of your success.\n* Talk to Glamodúd at Echad Glamodúd"},
{area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Sigar has asked you to kill many wights in Imlad Balchorth in the hopes of thinning their number and stopping the nightly invasions.",mobs={{locations={"6.88N, 25.87W"},name="Sigar"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Distilled Celebrant Salve",id="70000F40"},{q="(x2)",val="Distilled Athelas Essence",id="70000F31"}},category="Angmar",id=708,scope="n/a",name="Destroy the Wights",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Sigar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWights can be found in Imlad Balchorth, west of Myrkworth.\nSigar has asked you to destroy the wights in Imlad Balchorth. You can find them wandering the eastern edges of Imlad Balchorth.\n* Defeat wights in Imlad Balchorth (20)\nObj 2:\nSigar is at Myrkworth, east of Imlad Balchorth.\nHaving destroyed many of the wights as asked, return to Sigar in Myrkworth and tell him the deed is done.\n* Talk to Sigar"},
{["next"]={1383,1384,1382,1385,1787,466,1788,465,1786,1785,462,464},area="Eryn Laer",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orcs of Moria have poured out into Fanuidhol, mustering for an assault upon the Golden Wood.",mobs={{locations={"12.10S, 71.09W"},name="Bahanneth"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Potent Celebrant Salve",id="7001A3E1"},{q="(x2)",val="Potent Athelas Essence",id="7001A3DA"}},category="Lothlórien",id=709,scope="n/a",name="Determining Their Strength",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Bahanneth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMaenhador is at Talan Fanuidhol. Raingon is at Talan Gwilith, north-east of Talan Fanuidhol.\nBahanneth has asked you to aid Maenhador and Raingon with their scouting duties.\n* Aid Maenhador\n* Aid Raingon\nObj 2:\nBahanneth is at Talan Fanuidhol, south-west of Talan Gwilith.\nYou should return to Bahanneth and report your findings.\n* Talk to Bahanneth at Talan Fanuidhol"},
{area="Taur Hith",zone="Lothlórien",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orcs of Moria have poured out into Fanuidhol, mustering for an assault upon the Golden Wood.",mobs={{locations={"11.38S, 70.72W"},name="Raingon"}},category="Lothlórien",id=710,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Determining Their Strength -- Northern Camps",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Raingon",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDrûmaudhul, Prakûth-fulug, Bidroi Maudhul, and Nardur-stazg all lie to the north-west of Talan Gwilith.\nRaingon has asked you to scout four Orc-encampments in Fanuidhol to determine their strength: Drûmaudhul. Prakûth-fulug, Bidroi Maudhul, and Nardur-stazg.\nNote: While Fanuidhol Defence is active, Raingon will not be available for quest completion or comments. You will have to wait for Fanuidhol Defence to end to complete this quest.\n* Find Drûmaudhul\n* Find Bidroi Maudhûl\n* Find Prakûth-fulug\n* Find Nardur-stazg\nObj 2:\nRaingon is at Talan Gwilith, south-east of Fanuidhol.\nYou should return to Raingon with your report.\nNote: While Fanuidhol Defence is active, Raingon will not be available for quest completion or comments. You will have to wait for Fanuidhol Defence to end to complete this quest.\n* Talk to Raingon at Talan Gwilith",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Eryn Laer",zone="Lothlórien",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orcs of Moria have poured out into Fanuidhol, mustering for an assault upon the Golden Wood.",mobs={{locations={"12.07S, 71.12W"},name="Maenhador"}},category="Lothlórien",id=711,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Determining Their Strength -- Southern Camps",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Maenhador",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAll of the Orc-encampments lie to the north of Talan Fanuidhol. Bolg Maufulug lies the furthest to the west. Golugrak is north-west of Talan Fanuidhol. Gazpush is north of Golugrak. Mokûrz Gundul is east of Gazpush.\nMaenhador has asked you to scout four Orc-encampments in Fanuidhol to determine their strength: Bolg Maufulug, Golugrak, Gazpush, and Mokûrz Gundul.\n* Find Bolg Maufulug\n* Find Golugrak\n* Find Gazpush\n* Find Mokûrz Gundul\nObj 2:\nMaenhador is at Talan Fanuidhol, south of Fanuidhol.\nYou should return to Maenhador with your report.\n* Talk to Maenhador at Talan Fanuidhol",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2737},reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Northern Barrow-downs",money={{val="3s 20c"}},d="Tobold Leafcutter's studies in the Bree Library gave him an understanding of some of the secrets the Barrow-downs holds. His concern grows with every new discovery within the Barrows.",mobs={{locations={"31.74S, 56.24W"},name="Tobold Leafcutter"}},category="Bree-land",id=712,scope="n/a",name="Digging in the Dirt",arcs="History in the Barrow-downs",level=18,minlevel=13,b="Tobold Leafcutter",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe barrows of Taradan, Orron, and Ringdor lie in the northern Barrow-downs.\nTobold Leafcutter has told you that you should dig at the entrances to the barrows of Taradan, Orron, and Ringdor. To help in your digging, he has given you a blunted pick-axe to use. This tool will help prevent any damage the digging may cause to any lore-fragments you uncover.\n* Use Blunted Pick-axe\n* Find Taradan's barrow\n* Use Blunted Pick-axe\n* Find Orron's barrow\n* Use Blunted Pick-axe\n* Find Ringdor's barrow\nObj 2:\nTobold Leafcutter waits for you between the Barrow-downs and the Old Forest.\nYour digging at the barrows of Taradan, Orron and Ringdor has uncovered three fragments of lore, written on scraps of parchment. You should bring these fragments to Tobold Leafcutter.\n* Talk to Tobold Leafcutter\n* Turn in Lore-fragment\n* Turn in Blunted Pick-axe",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nanduhirion",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+300 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s"}},d="The Orcs of Moria are attempting to dig through the avalanche blocking the Redhorn Gate and gain access to Eregion.",category="Moria",id=713,scope="n/a",name="Digging West",receive={{val="Raskwith's Blade",id=70016402}},level=59,minlevel=54,b="Raskwith",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orcs are digging at the Fallen Ice, north-west of Nanduhirion.\nRaskwith asked you to stop the Orcs who are attempting to dig through the avalanche at the Fallen Ice.\n* Defeat Orcs at the Fallen Ice (8)\nObj 2:\nRaskwith is at Nanduhirion, south-east of the Fallen Ice.\nRaskwith will be pleased to hear the Orcs' efforts have been disrupted.\n* Talk to Raskwith at Nanduhirion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},d="Mincham is greatly disturbed by your report of the Oathbreaker's invocation of the name Amarthiel, though he has not confided the reasons for his concern.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"13.06S, 55.30W"},name="Mincham"}},selectoneof={{val="Halbarad's Shield",id="7000179B"},{val="Medliechor",id="7000179C"}},category="North Downs",id=714,scope="n/a",prev={2490},name="Dire News",arcs="The Oathbreakers",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nEsteldín is reached by travelling along the road east from the Greenway, passing Amon Raith and crossing the river at the ruins of Ost Lagoros. The ruins where Esteldín lies are due east of Gatson's farm.\nMincham has asked you to go to Esteldín to speak to the Ranger Halbarad, the leader of his people in the absence of their chieftain, Aragorn.\n* Talk to Halbarad"},
{["next"]={425},area="Northern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+500 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="3s 75c"}},d="Rangers, watching movements of enemies from the north and south, are concerned over the appearance of a foe they have long fought in the north.",mobs={{locations={"23.74S, 53.55W"},name="Andreg"}},category="Bree-land",id=715,scope="n/a",prev={1599},name="Dirty Work: Orc-slaying",arcs="My Brethren's Call",level=19,minlevel=14,b="Andreg",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou will find Orcs encamped at Cirith Núr on the west side of the Greenway to the north of the Old Greenway Fort.\nAndreg asked you to attempt to disrupt the Orcs at their encampment at Cirith Núr.\n* Defeat Orcs at Cirith Núr (16)\nObj 2:\nAndreg is at the Old Greenway Fort, south of Cirith Núr.\nThe Orc-encampment was filled with powerful Orcs, and a cave carved into the cliff face lay within the heart of the camp. You should return to Andreg with your report.\n* Talk to Andreg at the Old Greenway Fort"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Fil Gashan is the barracks and mustering point for the Orcs' invasion of Lothlórien. Hidden deep within the fiery landscape and sharing an adjacent entrance to the Forges of Khazad-dûm, Orcs train here under the watchful eye of General Talug.",mobs={{locations={"13.41S, 108.07W"},name="Vagun"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=716,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Disabling Alarms",arcs="General's Command",level=60,minlevel=57,b="Vagun",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFil Gashan lies to the south-west of Anazârmekhem.\nVagun directed you to attempt to disable the massive alarm bells that the Orcs have placed throughout Fil Gashan. He mentioned that the sentries are good at spotting any who are not their own kind.\n* Disable the Alarms of Fil Gashan ($VALUE$/8)\nObj 2:\nVagun is at Anazârmekhem, north-east of Fil Gashan.\nYou attempted to disable several of the alarms. While not always successful, as Vagun had warned, the attempt is more important than the success.\n* Talk to Vagun at Anzârmekhem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={585},area="Eryn Laer",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Bahanneth is concerned about the siege-parts you stole from the Orcs. Even without them, they will be able to construct primitive weapons to conduct a siege.",mobs={{locations={"12.10S, 71.09W"},name="Bahanneth"}},category="Lothlórien",id=717,scope="n/a",prev={1665},destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Disarming the Foe",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,pois={{locations={"9.08S, 73.14W","8.17S, 73.01W","8.26S, 73.63W","8.38S, 72.58W","9.10S, 73.03W","8.36S, 73.45W","8.45S, 73.40W","8.25S, 73.37W","8.42S, 72.68W"},name="Weapon-store"}},minlevel=55,b="Bahanneth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFanuidhol lies to the north-west of Talan Fanuidhol.\nBahanneth wants you to enter Fanuidhol and kill several of the smiths there, as well as to destroy some of the stores of weapons they have forged. The weapons can be found stored towards the back of the camp, further to the north-west.\n* Defeat Orc-smiths\n* Use Weapon-store\nObj 2:\nBahanneth is at Talan Fanuidhol, south-east of Fanuidhol.\nYou should return to Bahanneth with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Bahanneth at Talan Fanuidhol"},
{area="Meluinen",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Lagorlam learned of the presence of North-men during his excursion into Taur Gonwaith. Upon hearing Lagorlam's tale, Baranwen has grown alarmed at this bold move by the Men of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"13.58S, 44.87W"},name="Baranwen"}},selectoneof={{val="Baranwen's Shield",id="700161C0"},{val="Arasbadanir",id="70006AA2"}},category="North Downs",id=718,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1905,2567},name="Disarming the Valley",level=32,minlevel=27,b="Baranwen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe mysterious Angmarim are at the troll-cave in the southern part of Taur Gonwaith, south of Lin Giliath.\nBaranwen has asked you to collect weapon-chests from the Angmarim and to return them to her so she can destroy the foul weapons.\n* Collect weapon-chests (5 Weapons Chest)\nObj 2:\nBaranwen is at Lin Giliath, north-west of Taur Gonwaith.\nBaranwen is awaiting your return with the Orc-weapons, which she will destroy.\n* Talk to Baranwen\n* Turn in Weapons Chest"},
{["next"]={959},area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The pools of Imlad Balchorth are noxious pits of foul water. No one knows if the corruption stems from the Enemy's industry or from a more sinister source.",mobs={{locations={"6.84N, 25.83W"},name="Thorod"}},category="Angmar",id=719,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={933},name="Discovering the Source",arcs="Foul Waters",level=49,pois={{locations={"6.97N, 30.65W","7.02N, 30.25W","6.99N, 29.64W","6.43N, 29.29W","7.23N, 30.18W","6.76N, 29.53W","6.30N, 30.34W","6.17N, 29.43W","5.82N, 29.57W","6.43N, 30.36W","7.25N, 30.43W","6.05N, 29.49W","6.62N, 29.73W","6.09N, 30.10W","6.60N, 29.30W","6.20N, 30.29W","5.93N, 29.67W","6.90N, 30.51W","5.85N, 29.88W","6.24N, 29.30W","6.57N, 29.43W"},name="Roiling Deadly Water"}},minlevel=44,b="Thorod",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe pools of Imlad Balchorth are to the west of Myrkworth.\nThe waters in the western parts of Imlad Balchorth are infused with deadly poison, and Thorod wishes to determine the cause.\n* Use Roiling Deadly Water\n* Turn in Phial\nObj 2:\nThorod is in Myrkworth, east of Imlad Balchorth.\nYour phials are filled with the deadly water from the roiling pools of Imlad Balchorth.\n* Talk to Thorod\n* Turn in Phial of Deadly Water"},
{area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Constable Thistlewool is troubled by the disease spreading through the boars in the wake of the destruction wrought on Archet. The boars must be destroyed before they infect the other wildlife and eradicate the diminished food supply in Archet.",mobs={{locations={"25.03S, 48.83W"},name="Constable Thistlewool"}},selectoneof={{val="Thistlewool's Buckler",id="70019BC1"},{val="Thistlewool's Stone",id="70019BC3"},{val="Thistlewool's Javelin",id="70019BBF"},{val="Thistlewool's Staff",id="70019BBE"},{val="Thistlewool's Bow",id="70019BC0"},{val="Thistlewool's Greataxe",id=70023334},{val="Thistlewool's Knife",id="70006B5B"},{val="Thistlewool's Shield",id="70019BC2"}},category="Bree-land",id=720,scope="n/a",name="Disease Among the Boars",level=6,c={"* Defeat Diseased Bristlehides\n* Return to Constable Thistlewool"},minlevel=2,b="Constable Thistlewool",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDiseased boars roam the lands to the south and east of Archet's gate.\nConstable Thistlewool thinks that the best way to end the disease afflicting the local boars is to slay those already infected.\n* Kill 6 Diseased Bristlehide\nObj 2:\nConstable Thistlewool can be found near the ruins of The Mad Badger Inn in Archet.\nConstable Thistlewool will wish to hear of your success.\n* Talk to Constable Thistlewool",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Fordirith",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You found a set of orders in the quarters of a deserter in Enedwaith that partially detailed Isengard's plans for the region. Such information would doubtless be of interest to the Grey Rangers, and you believe you may be able to find the rest of these papers among the officers in Lhe Lhechu.",mobs={{locations={"58.69S, 14.59W"},name="Dagoras"}},category="Enedwaith",id=721,scope="n/a",name="Disorder",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Dunlending Military Orders",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDunlending officers can be found in Lhe Lhechu, south-west of Echad Dagoras.\nYou should collect papers from the Dunlending officers in Fordirith and learn more of the reason for their presence on the borders of the old North Kingdom.\n* Turn in Dunlending Orders\nObj 2:\nDagoras is at Echad Dagoras, north-east of Lhe Lhechu.\nYou should return the orders you have found to Dagoras.\n* Talk to Dagoras\n* Turn in Dunlending Military Orders\n* Turn in Dunlending Orders",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1738,1328,1918,2730,1873,1071,157,1293},area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Ânug-stazg is host to a muster of the Orcs in the Ashenslades. From here, they plan to lay waste to the Malledhrim encampment at Mithechad.",mobs={{locations={"17.71S, 48.28W"},name="Perindúr"}},category="Mirkwood",id=722,scope="n/a",prev={1915,1072},name="Disrupting the Muster",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Perindúr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFotak and his minions may be found at Ânug-stazg, due east of Mithechad.\nPerindúr has asked you to defeat the Orc Fotak and his warriors.\n* Defeat Fotak\n* Defeat Orcs at Ânug-stazg (10)\nObj 2:\nPerindúr is at Mithechad, west of Ânug-stazg.\nYou should tell Perindúr of your victory over the Enemy forces at Ânug-stazg.\n* Talk to Perindúr at Mithechad"},
{area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Among the ruins of Sâd Doldúr, a foul sorceror is performing a ritual to further spread the blight past the reaches of the Ashenslades.",mobs={{locations={"17.47S, 44.51W"},name="Faerchiril"}},category="Mirkwood",id=723,scope="n/a",prev={647},name="Disrupting the Ritual",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Faerchiril",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ruins of Sâd Doldúr lie south and down the mountain pass from Barad Angol.\nFaerchiril has asked you to travel to Sâd Doldúr, climb to the upper reaches of the ruins, and defeat Lidognir and his men.\n* Defeat sorcerers (15)\n* Defeat Lidognir\nObj 2:\nFaerchiril is at Barad Angol, north and up the hill from Sâd Doldúr.\nYou should speak with Faerchiril and let her know that Lidognir has been stopped and that his men have been defeated.\n* Talk to Faerchiril at Barad Angol"},
{area="Greenfields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Ponto Hornblower of Brockenborings is concerned about the appearance of goblins in the Shire and wants to protect his grazing rights on the Greenfields.",mobs={{locations={"27.30S, 68.13W"},name="Ponto Hornblower"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Stuffed Cabbage",id="7000335F"},{val="Hornblower's Feet",id="700032CC"}},category="Shire",id=724,scope="n/a",name="Distant Dangers",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=11,minlevel=7,b="Ponto Hornblower",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpear-wielding goblins can be found in the north Greenfields.\nPonto Hornblower is afraid that he might be attacked from a distance by goblins throwing spears, if the rumours prove true, and has asked you to remove that threat.\n* Defeat Spear-wielding goblins (6 Gramsfoot Scout, Gramsfoot Hurler)\nObj 2:\nPonto Hornblower is in Brockenborings, near the centre of town.\nRumours of goblins in the Greenfields had Ponto Hornblower concerned for his safety and the safety of his sheep. He had asked you to make sure there were no spear-wielding goblins in the fields. You found many, but managed to dispatch them without too much trouble. You should let Ponto know it should be safe for him to return to the Greenfields, though tact may be required to avoid panicking the Shire-folk.\n* Talk to Ponto Hornblower"},
{area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Glóin is seeking news of one of his distant cousins who is trading in the land of Forochel.",mobs={{locations={"2.54N, 57.97W"},name="Leithólf"},{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=725,scope="n/a",name="Distant Relations",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Glóin",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nForochel lies north of Evendim through Cirith Rhiw, north of Tyrn Fornech. You should start your search in the village of Kauppa-kohta.\n* Talk to Leithólf",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{d="Ancient dead have arisen within the Great Barrow.",category="Great Barrows",id=726,scope="n/a",name="Disturbed Remains",receive={{val="Great Barrow Mark",id="700230A1"}},level=22,minlevel=17,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nDisturbed graves can be found deep within the Flooded Wing of the Great Barrow.\n* Use Open Grave"},
{area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Calelloth believes news of the half-orcs dealings with the worms of Eregion should be conveyed throughout the Elf-camps.",mobs={{locations={"39.79S, 16.32W"},name="Calelloth"},{locations={"46.98S, 12.48W"},name="Lengliel"}},category="Eregion",id=727,scope="n/a",prev={2655},name="Disturbing News",arcs="An Army of Worms",level=49,c={"* Lengliel is at Echad Eregion [47.0S, 12.5W]"},minlevel=44,b="Calelloth",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLengliel is at Echad Eregion, south-east of Gwingris.\nCalelloth has asked you to deliver a letter to Lengliel regarding the half-orcs and worms.\n* Talk to Lengliel at Echad Eregion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="Taur Morvith",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orcs of Taur Morvith have unleashed packs of Wargs to harry intruders who would dare approach through the forests to the north.",mobs={{locations={"16.60S, 50.55W"},name="Iavassúl"}},category="Mirkwood",id=728,scope="n/a",prev={137},name="Dogs of War",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=64,minlevel=59,b="Iavassúl",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWargs can be found roaming throughout Taur Morvith.\nIavassúl has asked you to hunt down the Wargs roaming Taur Morvith and collect their war-collars as trophies.\n* Turn in War Collar\nObj 2:\nIavassúl is at Iavassúl's Watch in Taur Morvith.\nYou should return the war-collars to Iavassúl.\n* Talk to Iavassúl\n* Turn in War Collar",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={51,799},area="Nain Enidh",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="11s 50c"}},d="In Annunlos lay a ruin, long abandoned by the Eglain. Picked clean and having only the depths of the ruin unexplored, the Eglain left the places beneath the ruin be, as is their custom. However, the ruin now teems with life again as dwarves, presumably in league with Orcs, scour the ruin for treasures in the depths.",mobs={{locations={"32.82S, 32.96W"},name="Refr Quicksilver"}},category="Lone-lands",id=729,scope="n/a",name="Dour Dwarves",arcs="The Forsaken Lone-lands",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Refr Quicksilver",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ruins of Thandobel lie to the south of Refr Quicksilver in Annunlos.\nRefr Quicksilver expressed a desire to learn what kind of dwarves would deign to work alongside Orcs and has asked you to go to the ruins of Thandobel and capture one of their banners.\n* Bring the banner to Refr Quicksilver\n* Turn in Dourhand-banner"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="The descendants of Skorgrím Dourhand have ever been a thorn in the side of Durin's Folk, the Longbeards. Though now outcast, they remain a threat to the Free Peoples of Ered Luin.",category="Reputation",id=730,scope="n/a",name="Dourhand Crests -- Introduction",level=46,minlevel=41,b="Tórth",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance to Sarnúr is south of Thorin's Hall and west of Noglond in the ruins of Orodost.\nTórth has asked you to enter the Dourhand stronghold of Sarnúr and defeat the creatures who dwell there, claiming Dourhand crests as the proof of your valour.\n* Bring the Dourhand crests to Tórth\n* Turn in Dourhand Crest",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1721},area="Nan Amlug West",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="17s 50c"}},d="Reports have come to Othrikar that the Dourhands are planning to move against the mines and oust the Longbeards.",mobs={{locations={"7.21S, 44.92W"},name="Hannar"}},category="North Downs",id=731,scope="n/a",prev={2086},name="Dourhand Plans",arcs="Pulling Beards",level=29,c={"* The Dourhand plans are in a chest at [7.2S, 47.3W]"},minlevel=24,b="Hannar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Dourhand plans are in a chest somewhere deep in the camp west of Othrikar, hidden in some old Arnorian ruins.\nWhen you returned from your foray against the Dourhand scouts, Hannar warned you of the Dourhands' plans to attack Othrikar. He has asked you to find those plans and bring them to him.\n* Return the plans to Hannar\n* Turn in Dourhand-plans"},
{area="Northern High Pass",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Having defeated the Warg pack-leader Black-fang and discovered the likely whereabouts of the missing Elvish hunter Glorwen, you now face the grim task of proceeding into the depths of Goblin-town itself to effect her rescue!",mobs={{locations={"20.28S, 5.40E","20.75S, 6.17E"},name="Glorwen"},{locations={"23.28S, 4.28E"},name="Nogmeldir"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=732,scope="n/a",prev={391},name="Down, Down to Goblin-town",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Celebrant Salve",id="70000F40"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Athelas Essence",id="70000F31"}},level=48,minlevel=43,b="Nogmeldir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlorwen is imprisoned in Goblin-town.\nNogmeldir has asked you to find and rescue the scout Glorwen.\n* Talk to Glorwen",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2716},reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Lothlórien",area="Nimrodel",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Hadroneth is worried about the mass of Orcs that have poured from the gates of Moria into the Dimrill Dale, and wants you to thin their numbers.",mobs={{locations={"16.18S, 73.47W"},name="Hadroneth"}},category="Lothlórien",id=733,scope="n/a",name="Down from the Mountains",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Hadroneth",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs can be found all along the road that leads through Nanduhirion, the Dimrill Dale, north-west of Talan Haldir.\nHadroneth has asked you to thin the numbers of the Orcs that have come forth from within the mountains.\n* Defeat Orcs in Nanduhirion (10)\nObj 2:\nHadroneth is on Talan Haldir, along the banks of Nimrodel.\nThe Elf Hadroneth is waiting for you to report of your success slaying the Orcs that have poured from the Gates of Moria into Nanduhirion.\n* Talk to Hadroneth",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="The Trollshaws",area="Bruinen Gorges",money={{val="9s 24c"}},d="You discovered a series of giant footprints in Tâl Bruinen, which Elrohir tells you may be cause for concern.",mobs={{locations={"31.64S, 15.19W"},name="Elrohir"}},category="Trollshaws",id=734,scope="n/a",prev={995},name="Down from the Mountains?",arcs="Giant Footprints",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Pure Flask of Conhuith",id="7000C638"}},level=45,minlevel=40,b="Elrohir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nArifael lives on the slope of Amon Nendir, south of the High Moor on the eastern edge of the Trollshaws.\nElrohir is concerned about the giant footprints you saw in Tâl Bruinen and wants you to ask Arifael if he has heard of giant activity that far south.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1627,2687},area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="2s 55c"}},d="Adso Haybank has asked your aid in serious action against the brigands extorting and threatening him and his workers.",mobs={{locations={"29.12S, 56.78W"},name="Adso Haybank"}},category="Bree-land",id=735,scope="n/a",prev={222},name="Down-payments",arcs="Unfair Cost of Business",level=17,minlevel=12,b="Adso Haybank",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMake your way to the Old Sweetgrass Farm north-east of Adso's Camp and help Adso drive the brigands away from his camp.\nAdso can think of no way to drive the brigands off that does not involve violence. He sent you to fight and defeat brigands near Old Sweetgrass Farm.\n* Defeat brigands at the Old Sweetgrass Farm (12)\nObj 2:\nAdso Haybank awaits your return at his camp to the south-west of Old Sweetgrass Farm along the Great East Road.\nYou should return to Adso Haybank with news of your success.\n* Talk to Adso Haybank"},
{area="Nan Sirannon",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Limlaer has enlisted your aid in setting false trails to lure the Enemy south.",mobs={{locations={"52.05S, 10.18W"},name="Limlaer"}},category="Eregion",id=736,scope="n/a",prev={53},name="Drawing the Enemy",arcs="A False Trail",receive={{val="Limlaer's Axe",id="700160F3"}},level=50,c={"* You can set the false firecamp on a Clear Patch in Emyn Naer, at [54.2S, 11.2W]"},pois={{locations={"54.20S, 11.24W"},name="Clear Patch"}},minlevel=45,b="Limlaer",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe site for the false camp is south-west of Limlaer, between Porth Cadlus and Goeolhad, in a boulder-encircled basin.\nLimlaer has tasked you with setting a trap for the scouts of the Enemy.\n* Kill 1 Râkhuga the Tracker\n* Use Clear Patch\nObj 2:\nLimlaer is south-east of Echad Dúnann, along the Nan Sirannon road.\nYou should return to Limlaer with news of your success.\n* Talk to Limlaer\n* Turn in Bundle of Wood"},
{area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="18s 40c"}},d="While you hunted the Wargs of Nain Enidh, Mugwort prepared a special meal for their leader. All that remains to ease passage along the Great East Road is to draw this leader out of hiding and into battle.",mobs={{locations={"34.34S, 36.90W"},name="Old Mugwort"}},selectoneof={{val="Warg Router",id=70003765},{val="Mugwort's Old Staff",id=70003768},{val="Old Mugwort's Gauntlets",id=70003767},{val="Shadepaw's Defeat",id=70003766}},category="Lone-lands",id=737,scope="n/a",prev={1772},name="Drawing the Pack",arcs="Wolves of the Scrub",level=25,pois={{locations={"32.63S, 34.39W"},name="Ancient Stone Table"}},minlevel=20,b="Old Mugwort",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe stone table where you should pour Mugwort's gruel is at the end of a southward path near a signpost on the road through Nain Enidh.\nOld Mugwort asked you to take the special gruel he prepared to an ancient stone near the lair of the Wargs. The stench of it should draw forth their leader.\n* Summon and Defeat Shadepaw\n* Use Ancient Stone Table\n* Turn in Mugwort's Gruel\nObj 2:\nOld Mugwort is at the camp on the east side of Minas Eriol.\nAfter drawing Shadepaw's pack into the open, you defeated the Warg-leader. Old Mugwort will want to hear of your victory.\n* Talk to Old Mugwort\n* Turn in Mugwort's Gruel"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Gyrgir believes the fungus would rather live in the water than on the Orcs. He wants to study the infestation further.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=738,scope="n/a",name="Drawn to the Water",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Gyrgir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlobsnaga Orcs can be found on the banks near The Chamber of Dark Waters, south of the Rotting Cellar.\nGyrgir wants you to gather fungus-spores from several Globsnaga Orcs. He believes with them, he will be able to learn things important for creating an antidote.\n* Turn in Fungal Spore\nObj 2:\nGyrgir is in the Rotting Cellar, north of The Chamber of Dark Waters.\nYou defeated several Globsnaga Orcs and managed to gather enough fungus-spores for the dwarves to research. You should return to Gyrgir in the Rotting Cellar and deliver the spores.\n* Return to Gyrgir with the spores\n* Turn in Fungal Spore",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Sorkha of the Trév Gállorg is worried about the lesser watching-stones that have been erected in the city of Dûn Covád.",mobs={{locations={"0.22S, 39.76W"},name="Sorkha"}},category="Angmar",id=739,scope="n/a",prev={625},name="Dread in the Fallen City",receive={{val="Small Blade of Búth Luikh",id="7000EAEA"},{q="(x3)",val="Refined Athelas Extract",id="70008CF7"}},level=44,c={"* The lesser watching-stones are found in Dûn Covád at:\n[6.1N, 38.7W]\n* [5.6N, 38.7W]\n* [5.3N, 38.2W]"},minlevel=39,b="Sorkha",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThree lesser watching-stones can be found somewhere within the city of Dûn Covád, far to the north of Aughaire, in the western hills of Fasach-falroid.\nSorkha wants you to find the locations of three lesser watching-stones within Dûn Covád.\nObj 2:\nSorkha is in the Búth Luikh in Aughaire.\nYou have located three lesser watching-stones within the city of Dûn Covád and should return now to Sorkha with the knowledge of their locations.\n* Talk to Sorkha",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Across the Ashenslades, there are small packs of Wargs that harass Malledhrim patrols through the area.",mobs={{locations={"17.71S, 48.28W"},name="Perindúr"}},category="Mirkwood",id=740,scope="n/a",prev={2456},name="Drive Them Off",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Perindúr",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWargs can be found throughout the Ashenslades, but many are gathered to the south of Mithechad, near Naur-hoit.\nPerindúr has asked you to hunt down and defeat the Wargs of the Ashenslades.\n* Defeat Wargs in the Ashenslades (15)\n* Turn in Warg Tooth\nObj 2:\nPerindúr is at Mithechad, north of Naur-hoit.\nYou should return to Perindúr and tell him of your success in the hunt.\n* Talk to Perindúr\n* Turn in Warg Tooth"},
{area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="38s 8c"}},d="The Snow Beasts have been forced out of the Lossoth outpost in the Western Tundra, but will return unless their matron is defeated.",mobs={{locations={"8.00N, 78.98W"},name="Sampo"}},category="Forochel",id=741,scope="n/a",name="Drive Them Out!",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Sampo",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Great Snow-matron can be found in the western tundra.\nDefeating the Snow-matron will frighten the yeti herd and turn them against the Gauredain.\n* Defeat the Great Snow-matron\nObj 2:\n* Talk to Sampo",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2802},area="Taur Orthon",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Your success against the Wargs of Forochel has brought you great respect from the Lossoth hunters. Valtteri seeks your aid one more time.",mobs={{locations={"3.48N, 58.23W"},name="Valtteri"}},category="Forochel",id=742,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2439},name="Driving the Beasts Out",arcs="Hunting for sport",receive={{val="Flask of Warg Oil",id="7000E966"}},level=45,c={"* The red-fang behemoth can be found in Metsästä-sija at [1.4N, 61.2W].\n* Remember to use the Warg Fat Totem you have in your inventory."},minlevel=40,b="Valtteri",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe red-fang behemoth can be found among the dark rocky hills far to the south-west of Kauppa-kohta.\nValtteri has asked you to hunt down and defeat the red-fang behemoth, using a burning Lossoth token to frighten the beast.\n* Defeat the red-fang behemoth\nObj 2:\nValtteri is in the northern part of Kauppa-kohta.\nYou should return to Valtteri and tell him of your victory against the red-fang behemoth.\n* Talk to Valtteri\n* Turn in Warg Fat Totem"},
{area="Tyl Annûn",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="42s"}},d="Orchalwë has told you of a cruel practice of the Angmarim that have occupied the ruins of Annúminas: drowning their prisoners off the docks at the Port of Annúminas.",mobs={{locations={"16.86S, 71.55W","16.62S, 71.23W","16.61S, 71.12W","17.01S, 71.46W","16.72S, 71.56W","16.75S, 71.08W","16.94S, 71.37W"},name="Tortured Prisoner"}},category="Annúminas",id=743,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Drowning at the Docks",receive={{val="Distilled Celebrant Salve",id="70000F40"},{q="(x12)",val="Arnorian Armour Fragments",id="7000AE74"}},level=39,minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nPrisoners are being drowned by Angmarim torturers off the docks of the Port of Annúminas, on the lowest level of the city, by the water.\n* Rescue tortured prisoners (3 Tortured Prisoner )\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will be pleased to hear the prisoners have been saved."},
{area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="The notes you discovered spoke of trolls being kept in the deep parts of Goblin-town, drumming to stir up the goblins and prepare them for battle. Glóin has tasked Vighar with organizing parties to enter the drum areas and kill the trolls and the leader of the lashers there to lessen the threat that they represent to the people west and east of the Misty Mountains.",mobs={{locations={"24.66S, 3.78W"},name="Vighar Roadwalker"}},selectoneof={{val="Vighar's Vest",id="7000D2F9"},{val="Roadwalker's Shoes",id="7000D2FA"},{val="Curunam",id="7000D2D3"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=744,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1454},name="Drum-keepers",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Vighar Roadwalker",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblin-town is far to the north-east of Glóin's camp.\nVighar has asked you to find your way through the stronghold to the area where the troll-drummers are watched over by the lashers. Kill several of these goblins and their leader, Kaushar.\n* Defeat Kaushar\n* Defeat Goblin-town lashers\nObj 2:\nVighar Roadwalker is at Glóin's camp far to the south-west of Goblin-town.\nKaushar and the lashers used their trolls against you, but you were successful in defeating them. You should now return to Vighar with your report.\n* Speak with Vighar at Glóin's camp in the Misty Mountains"},
{["next"]={1440},area="Goblin-town",zone="Misty Mountains",reputation={{val="+900 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="Oghûk wants revenge on Kaushar, the goblin who imprisoned him for causing trouble with the troll-drums in the deep places of Goblin-town.",selectoneof={{val="Oghûk's Gauntlets",id="7000D2F3"},{val="Oghûk's Necklace",id="7000D2B6"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=745,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1308},name="Drummers in the Deep",arcs="The Great Escape",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Oghûk the Hooligan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTroll-drummers can be found in the deep places of Goblin-town.\nOghûk wants to exact vengeance on Kaushar, a goblin who mends the drums in the deep places of Goblin-town. He blames Kaushar for his imprisonment and wants to cause him suffering and pain. It is an unpleasant task, but Oghûk will not help you if you do not help him first.\n* Kill 6 Cave-troll Drummer\nObj 2:\nOghûk is in his cell in the Goblin-town prison.\nThe troll-drummers were found in an area deep within Goblin-town. Watched over by goblin-taskmasters, you found the trolls and defeated them as requested.\n* Return to Oghûk at his cell in the Goblin-town prison"},
{area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="The dwarves at the Chamber of the Crossroads have gotten little sleep since arriving. The goblins nearby have been pounding on drums without respite, sending booming echoes throughout Durin's Way.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=746,scope="n/a",name="Drums of War",pois={{locations={"4.75S, 111.94W","4.55S, 111.79W","4.76S, 112.14W","4.70S, 111.79W","4.54S, 112.04W","4.51S, 111.90W"},name="Goblin-drum"}},level=52,minlevel=47,b="Fostólf",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblin-drummers are encamped in the Hall of the High Stair, north of the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nFostólf has asked you to destroy the goblin-drums so that he and his companions can get some sleep.\n* Use Goblin-drum\nObj 2:\nFostólf is at the Chamber of the Crossroads, south of the Hall of the High Stair.\nAll of the goblin drums have been silenced. Fostólf should be able to get some rest at last.\n* Talk to Fostólf in the Chamber of the Crossroads",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1896},money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Pipe-weed is something hobbits take very seriously. A market would never be visited unless it had a suitable supply and variety.",category="Evendim",id=747,scope="n/a",prev={2026},name="Drying the Pipe-weed",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,minlevel=25,b="Blossom Gamgee",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe drying racks are north-east of Blossom Gamgee on Northcotton Farm.\nThe sorted pipe-weed needs to be placed on the drying racks.\n* Use Drying Rack\nObj 2:\nBlossom Gamgee is on Northcotton Farm.\nBlossom Gamgee will want to know the pipe-weed has been placed on the drying racks.\n* Talk to Blossom Gamgee",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="Tham Andalath is the furthest of the estates from Tinnudir. What was once one of the most opulent houses in all of Evendim is now desecrated by goblins.",category="Evendim",id=748,scope="n/a",name="Dull Blades Still Cut Deep",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=34,pois={{locations={"9.83S, 63.00W","9.65S, 63.33W","9.49S, 63.02W","9.72S, 63.00W","9.43S, 63.09W","9.78S, 63.05W","9.83S, 63.21W","9.36S, 63.26W","9.42S, 63.41W"},name="Ornamental Blade"}},minlevel=29,b="Ornamental Blade",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTham Andalath is north east of Tinnudir and east of Tham Ornen.\nNadfaron asked you to venture to Tham Andalath and gather any ceremonial weapons you find amidst the ruins.\n* Obj 2:\nThe Rangers are at Tinnudir, south west of Tham Andalath.\nOne of the Rangers will be eager to examine the ceremonial blades you found.\n* Bring the Ornamental Blades to the Rangers at Tinnudir\n*",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mirobel",zone="Eregion",money={{val="10s 8c"}},d="The Dunlendings scouring Eregion have been ordered to pillage anything they believe to be of merit to whomever is at the root of the White Hand activity. Though the forces are scattered amongst the ruins of Eregion, there are a good many who have been sent to a more specific location.",mobs={{locations={"52.49S, 16.80W"},name="Gelirwen"}},category="Eregion",id=749,scope="n/a",name="Dunland's Champion",c={"* Orders to the White Hand drops from a Dunlending"},level=51,minlevel=46,b="Orders to the White Hand",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nEchad Mirobel is in the south-western stretches of Eregion.\nYou have found strange orders pertaining to the ransack of the School of Tham Mirdain, and a champion of the Dunlendings who will lead this assault on the lore-vault of the Elves. You should bring this message to Echad Mirobel, where someone will hopefully know what to make of it.\n* Speak with Gelirwen at Echad Mirobel\n* Turn in Orders to the White Hand",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2753},area="Bullroarer's Sward",zone="Evendim",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="The tools to blow glass are unique and require much maintenance. A hobbit who lived in Dwaling used to repair them.",category="Evendim",id=750,scope="n/a",name="Dwaling's Plight",arcs="Dwaling's Plight",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=31,pois={{locations={"20.67S, 64.06W"},name="Satchel of Glassblowing Tools"}},minlevel=26,b="Hob Hillbrow",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Satchel of Glassblowing tools can be found on the stoop of a hobbit hole on the north side of Dwaling.\nHob Hillbrow has asked you to collect a Satchel of Glassblowing Tools for him.\n* Collect the Satchel of Glassblowing Tools\nObj 2:\nHob Hillbrow is at his home at the Bullroarer's Sward in Dwaling, south of the Sand-marshes.\nYou should return to Hob Hillbrow with the satchel of glassblowing tools.\n* Talk to Hob Hillbrow\n*"},
{["next"]={1019},area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",reputation={{val="+300 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="9s 66c"}},d="Dwalin is concerned about rumours that he has heard about stirrings in the Misty Mountains.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"}},category="Ered Luin",id=751,scope="n/a",name="Dwalin's Concern",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Dwalin",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSeek out Glóin at his camp in the western foothills of the Misty Mountains, north of Rivendell, far to the east of Ered Luin.\nDwalin wants you to bring word of warning to his friend Glóin in the Misty Mountains. He believes that the increased goblin activity may not be restricted to the goblins in Ered Luin.\n* Talk to Glóin at his camp in the Misty Mountains",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Steps of Gram",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="The Snowreap long struggled against the remnant of the dwarves in the Misty Mountains. Even now, they dislike the thought of dwarves being so close to their home. As allies to Angmar's Army they are permitted to speak on the behalf of any who aid them.",category="Grothum",id=752,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Dwarf-beards",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Fim the Worm",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nDwarves encroaching throughout the Ettenmoors wear full beards on their faces.\nThe goblins believe that the beards are a matter of pride amongst the dwarves and want you to help them humiliate their hated foes. Fim the Worm bade you strip the beards of the dwarves in return for favour from the Snowreap.\n* Return the beards to Fim the Worm at Dâr-gazag ()\n* Turn in Dwarf Beard",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1470,1468,1469},reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Gansi rebuilt an ancient red dwarf-lamp for you. He told you that this lamp will should reveal any hidden dwarf-doors in Durin's Way.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=753,scope="n/a",name="Dwarf-doors: Mezel-saluch",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Gansi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe door to Mezel-saluch is believed to be somewhere in the vicinity of Salab Nurjundul in Durin's Way.\nGansi has asked you to search for the hidden dwarf-door.\n* Find the dwarf-door to Mezel-saluch\nObj 2:\nGansi is at the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nYou should return to Gansi and inform him you located the secret door to the chamber of Mezel-saluch.\n* Talk to Gansi at the Chamber of the Crossroads",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="The Dwarves of the Blue Mountains are known best for their jewel and iron-craft.",category="Reputation",id=754,scope="Crafting",name="Dwarf-jewels -- Introduction",level=46,minlevel=41,b="Ísrath",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Blue Stone Garrison is located just inside Thorin's Hall.\nÍsrath has requested that you bring him crafted dwarf-jewels.\n* Bring the dwarf-jewels to Ísrath\n* Turn in Dwarf-jewel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",reputation={{val="+1200 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="The Dwarves of the Blue Mountains are best known for their jewel and iron-craft.",category="Reputation",id=755,scope="Crafting",name="Dwarf-necklace - Introduction",level=46,minlevel=41,b="Ísrath",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Blue Stone Garrison is located just inside Thorin's Hall.\nÍsrath has requested that you bring him a crafted dwarf-necklace.\n* Bring the dwarf-necklace to Ísrath\n* Turn in Dwarf-necklace",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",reputation={{val="+900 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="The Dwarves of the Blue Mountains are best known for their jewel and iron-craft.",category="Reputation",id=756,scope="Crafting",name="Dwarf-rings - Introduction",level=46,minlevel=41,b="Ísrath",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Blue Stone Garrison is located just inside Thorin's Hall.\nÍsrath has requested that you bring him crafted dwarf-rings.\n* Bring the dwarf-rings to Ísrath\n* Turn in Dwarf-ring",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Arador's End",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Goblins complain that the mine is overrun by dwarves, and they are not pleased by the intrusion. They bid you to enter the Isendeep to slaughter the dwarf-miners.",category="Grothum",id=757,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Dwarfs in the Mine",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Gasham",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Isendeep mine lay to the west of Grothum. If there are no dwarfs within the mine, make your way to the western entrance and search for them there.\nGasham asked you to enter the mine and slaughter the dwarves so the goblins can return to work.\n* Kill 10 Isendeep Miner\nObj 2:\nGasham awaits news of the mines at Grothum, the goblin-village in the north-east Ettenmoors.\nYou entered the mine and slaughtered all the dwarves you found. You should return to Gasham with the news.\n* Talk to Gasham",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1321,1323,1322},reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Styrr has rebuilt an ancient green dwarf-lamp for you. He told you that this lamp will reveal the hidden door to Khibir-zamu in the Silvertine Lodes.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=758,scope="n/a",name="Dwarven Doors: Khibir-zamu",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Styrr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe hidden door to Khibir-zamu is somewhere within the western tunnels of the Silvertine Lodes.\nStyrr has asked you to find the hidden dwarf-door.\n* Find the door to Khibir-zamu\nObj 2:\nStyrr can be found at the Deep Descent within the Silvertine Lodes.\nYou should return to Styrr at and tell him you have located Khibir-zamu.\n* Talk to Styrr at the Deep Descent",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1324,1325,1326},reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Gansi rebuilt an ancient red dwarf-lamp for you. He told you that this lamp will should reveal any hidden dwarf-doors in Durin's Way.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=759,scope="n/a",name="Dwarven Doors: Khibir-zarur",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Gansi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe door to Khibir-zarur is believed to be somewhere not far from the Chamber of the Crossroads in Durin's Way.\nGansi has asked you to find the hidden dwarf-door.\n* Find the door to Khibir-zarur\nObj 2:\nGansi is at the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nYou should return to Gansi and tell him that you have located the door to Khibir-zarur.\n* Talk to Gansi at the Chamber of the Crossroads",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1460,1459,1461},reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Styrr has rebuilt an ancient green dwarf-lamp for you. He told you that this lamp will show you the door to Menem-nar in the Silvertine Lodes.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=760,scope="n/a",name="Dwarven Doors: Menem-nar",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Styrr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe hidden door of Menem-nar is believed to be somewhere in the centre of the Silvertine Lodes.\nStyrr has asked you to search for the hidden dwarf-door.\n* Find the door to Menem-nar\nObj 2:\nStyrr can be found at the Deep Descent within the Silvertine Lodes.\nYou should return to Styrr tell him you have located the hidden door to Menem-nar.\n* Talk to Styrr at the Deep Descent",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="You have earned the respect of the Lossoth-chieftain Ora, who will now further guide your exploration of Forochel.",mobs={{locations={"11.45N, 69.53W"},name="Ora"},{locations={"9.38N, 81.15W"},name="Thórth"}},selectoneof={{val="Ora's Ring",id="7000E5D2"},{val="Ora's Band",id="7000E5D3"},{val="Ora's Braid",id="7000E5D6"}},category="Forochel",id=761,scope="n/a",prev={1798,114,2461,1045},name="Dwarves and Mammoths",arcs="Dwarves and Mammoths",level=46,c={"* Thórth is at Zigilgund, take the road west from Pynti-peldot"},minlevel=41,b="Ora",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nZigilgund is far along the road to the west of Pynti-peldot.\nOra suggested that you speak with a dwarf there by the name of Thórth.\n* Talk to Thórth"},
{area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="With one last effort and dwindling hope, Fernachar urgently wishes to locate the whereabouts of his missing friends and see them safely returned.",category="Mirkwood",id=762,scope="n/a",prev={1093},name="Dwindling Hope",arcs="The Lost Explorers",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,c={"* The Defiled Remains of the first scout are in Dannenglor at [11.5S, 54.7W]\n* The Defiled Remains of the second scout are in Dannenglor at [11.6S, 55.2W]\n* The Defiled Remains of the third scout are in Dannenglor at [12.4S, 54.7W]"},pois={{locations={"12.36S, 54.73W"},name="Defiled Remains"},{locations={"11.53S, 54.72W","11.56S, 55.18W"},name="Defiled Remains (Level 1)"}},minlevel=57,b="Fernachar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe missing Malledhrim scouts can surely be found in Dannenglor, north of the Haunted Inn.\nYou should search Dannenglor for the missing Elves, though whether they are alive or dead is yet to be seen.\n* Use Defiled Remains (Level 1)\n* Use Defiled Remains (Level 1)\n* Use Defiled Remains\nObj 2:\nFernachar is in the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks, south of Dannenglor.\nYou should speak with Fernachar and tell him that the three scouts met their doom in Dannenglor.\n* Talk to Fernachar at the Haunted Inn"},
{area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="5s 20c"}},d="Hunulf and Gadaric Munce agree that your efforts have aided their people, and they believe you should meet with their leader.",mobs={{locations={"34.38S, 36.91W"},name="Hunulf Munce"},{locations={"31.49S, 29.50W"},name="Frideric the Elder"}},category="Lone-lands",id=763,scope="n/a",prev={1960},name="Earned Trust",level=26,c={"* Frideric the Elder is in Ost Guruth [31.5S, 29.5W]"},minlevel=21,b="Hunulf Munce",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ruins of Ost Guruth lie near the Great East Road, where Nain Enidh meets Talath Gaun.\nHunulf Munce, convinced you could be of great assistance to his people, has asked you to go to the home of the Eglain, Ost Guruth, and speak with Frideric the Elder.\n* Talk to Frideric the Elder at Ost Guruth",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="The once great city of Annuminas is now occupied by a large and powerful enemy force.",category="Evendim",id=764,scope="n/a",name="Eastern Gate of Annuminas",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Nimbellas",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe East gate of Annuminas is to the west of the Ranger camp in the Way of Kings.\nNimbellas asked you to scout the East gate of Annuminas.\n* Scout the East gate to Annuminas\nObj 2:\nNimbellas is at the Ranger camp within the Way of Kings.\nNimbellas will be dismayed to hear about the strength of Angmar's encampment at the East gate of Annuminas.\n* Talk to Nimbellas",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hithlad",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Taskmaster Ghamp offered you a reward to find sticks not as big as logs. This likely means smaller-sized wood, like the kindling found throughout the Grimwood.",category="Grimwood",id=765,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Easy Pickings",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Taskmaster Ghamp",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGrimwood-kindling can be found throughout the Grimwood area, from fallen timber. You might also find it on the Leafcull-trees in the wood.\nTaskmaster Ghamp, in his own way, directed you to get Grimwood-kindling for repairs at the lumber-yard.\n* Return to Taskmaster Ghamp at the Grimwood Lumber-yard ()\n* Turn in Grimwood-kindling",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="The Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Skûmfil is nothing more than a dumping ground, a place where the fallen Orcs of Moria are discarded when they begin to reek. It is here that two foes have gathered, each intent on using the corpses found therein for their own purposes. The kergrim and other scavengers as a source of food, and the insects as a place to lay their eggs to spawn future generations.",mobs={{locations={"13.14S, 101.24W"},name="Throstur"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=766,scope="n/a",name="Eaters of the Dead",arcs="Skumfíl",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Throstur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nYmar, Odmar, and Glorelloth are at the Shadowed Refuge.\nThrostur informed you that the kergrim within Skûmfil are eaters of the dead. As such, they are also rife with disease and filth, and he has set his agents to the task of deciphering what ills the kergrim carry through Skûmfil.\n* Help Ymar to control disease in Skûmfil\n* Help Odmar defeat the kergrim-leaders of Skûmfil\n* Help Glorelloth collect samples in Skûmfil\nObj 2:\nThrostur is at the Shadowed Refuge.\nYou completed each task assigned by Ymar, Odmar and Glorelloth within Skûmfil and should now return to Throstur.\n* Talk to Throstur at the Shadowed Refuge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={55},d="Pada has asked you to find a special sheet of music to accompany the instrument you recovered.",category="Minstrel",id=767,scope="n/a",prev={2022},name="Echoes of Battle",arcs="The Path of the Watcher of Resolve",c={"* Snapjaw is in the Redhorn Lodes at [10.9S, 104.3W]"},level=58,minlevel=58,b="Pada",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe deep-claw Snapjaw can be found in the Redhorn Lodes south-west of the bridge that crosses the crevace south of the Broken Stair.\nSnapjaw has been rumoured to hoard a great deal of paper-scraps and texts, undoubtedly some of great historic value, to build nests for its brood. Pada wishes you to recover a sheet of music that can likely be taken from Snapjaw upon its defeat.\n* Defeat Snapjaw in the Redhorn Lodes\n* Turn in Parchment with Some Old Music\nObj 2:\nPada is in the Foundations of Stone, east from the Redhorn Lodes and then south to the Shadowed Refuge.\nYou should return to Pada with the musical text you have found, and hopefully it will be the one that he is seeking.\n* Return to Pada\n* Turn in Parchment with Some Old Music",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2655},area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Saruman's half-orcs have been seen stealing worm-eggs. Thus far, their full purpose remains unclear.",mobs={{locations={"39.79S, 16.32W"},name="Calelloth"}},category="Eregion",id=768,scope="n/a",prev={2498},name="Egg-collectors",arcs="An Army of Worms",level=48,c={"* A nice concentration of half-orcs can be found at Pembar."},minlevel=43,b="Calelloth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalf-orcs can be found south-east of Gwingris.\nCalelloth has instructed you to go forth and defeat the half-orcs who are stealing worm-eggs for their master.\n* Defeat half-orcs (12)\nObj 2:\nCalelloth is at Gwingris, north-west of where you found the half-orcs.\nYou should speak with Calelloth regarding your victory against the half-orcs.\n* Talk to Calelloth at Gwingris"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Due to his bad leg, Farmer Sandson cannot deliver the eggs Gammer Tunnelly in Tuckborough is waiting for.",mobs={{locations={"32.13S, 74.29W"},name="Farmer Sandson"}},selectoneof={{val="Egg Delivering Gloves",id="700032FC"},{val="Sturdy Club",id="700032FD"}},category="Shire",id=769,scope="n/a",prev={776},name="Eggs for Gammer Tunnelly",arcs="Making the Rounds",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Sandson's Famous Hardboiled Eggs",id="70009C12"},{val="Sandson's Famous Hardboiled Eggs Recipe",id="70009C24"},{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=8,minlevel=4,b="Farmer Sandson",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGammer Tunnelly can be found in the centre of Tuckborough.\nWhen you returned from delivering the eggs to Holly Hornblower, he asked you to make another delivery to Gammer Tunnelly in Tuckborough. Be careful that the rooster doesn't see you with the eggs, as he will let out a call that will upset the hens.\n* Pickup the egg basket\nObj 2:\nGammer Tunnelly was grateful for the eggs. You should return to Farmer Sandson and let him know the eggs were delivered without incident.\n* Talk to Farmer Sandson"},
{["next"]={775},area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",d="Due to his bad leg, Farmer Sandson cannot deliver the eggs Holly Hornblower in Hobbiton is waiting for.",mobs={{locations={"32.13S, 74.29W"},name="Farmer Sandson"}},category="Shire",id=770,scope="n/a",prev={1418},name="Eggs for Holly Hornblower",arcs="Making the Rounds",level=6,minlevel=2,b="Farmer Sandson",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHolly Hornblower's house is in Hobbiton, behind The Ivy Bush.\nPick up the egg basket and carry it to Holly Hornblower in Hobbiton. Be careful that the rooster doesn't see you with the eggs, as he will let out a call that will upset the hens.\n* Collect the egg basket\nObj 2:\nFarmer Sandson is at his farm, west of Waymeet.\nHolly Hornblower was grateful for the eggs. You should return to Farmer Sandson and let him know the eggs were delivered without incident.\n* Talk to Farmer Sandson",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyl Ruinen",money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="The island of Tyl Ruinen has been taken over by salamanders.",category="Evendim",id=771,scope="n/a",name="Eggs Over Easy",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=33,pois={{locations={"11.86S, 72.98W","11.20S, 73.02W","12.68S, 72.10W","11.88S, 73.07W","12.03S, 71.31W","11.00S, 72.93W","11.19S, 73.11W","12.73S, 72.12W","12.06S, 70.99W","12.58S, 71.99W","11.06S, 73.03W","12.73S, 71.89W","11.90S, 72.86W","12.13S, 71.32W","12.23S, 71.16W","11.83S, 72.86W"},name="Salamander Egg"}},minlevel=28,b="Lúgethir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSalamander nests can be found along the shoreline of Tyl Ruinen.\nLugethir asked you to find salamander nests and smash the eggs within.\n* Use Salamander Egg\nObj 2:\nLugethir is with Humphrey on Tyl Ruinen.\nLugethir will be pleased to hear you have smashed many a salamander egg.\n* Talk to Lúgethir",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",money={{val="28s"}},d="Klintur has been studying the spiders of the area in search of a cause for their queer behaviour.",selectoneof={{val="Klintur's Bracer",id=70016397},{val="Cloak of Persuasion",id="700163C9"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=772,scope="n/a",name="Eight-legged Insanity",level=59,minlevel=54,b="Klintur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nKlintur's spider is north-west of the Shadowed Refuge.\nKlintur's spider keeps escaping from its cage. He asked you to find it and 'encourage' it to return, lest it bring an entire clutch back to free the others.\n* Encourage the escaped spider to return to its cage\nObj 2:\nKlintur is at the Shadowed Refuge, east of the spider-cages.\nKlintur will be pleased to hear that you 'encouraged' the spider to return to its cage.\n* Talk to Klintur at the Shadowed Refuge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nain Enidh",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+900 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="13s"}},d="Since long before Orcs and undead crept into the Lone-lands, the Eglain have had to deal with the menace of spiders dwelling within the ruins across the lonely stretch of Eriador. Now as the spiders are driven from the depths of their ruined homes, they creep closer and closer to Ost Guruth and threaten the folk who dwell there.",mobs={{locations={"31.21S, 29.67W"},name="Tortwil"}},selectoneof={{val="Tortwil's Rune-stone",id="700161CF"},{val="Leather Boots of the Eglain",id="70006A83"},{val="Helm of the Eglain Defender",id="7001D177"},{val="Elder's Doom",id="70006BD2"},{val="Robe of the Eglain",id="70006B4B"}},category="Lone-lands",id=773,scope="n/a",name="Elders in the Shadows",arcs="Triumph and Tragedy",level=26,c={"* The Ruin-web Spinner and the Ruin-web Weaver can be found all throughout Amon Ros. They are fairly easy to find, and you will most likely stumble upon them by accident.\n* The Ruin-web Trapper is invisible and is usually found in a corner beneath the bridge or in the corner of the small ruined area on the ground level."},minlevel=21,b="Tortwil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe elders of the spider-brood can be found in Amon Ros, west of Ost Guruth.\nTortwil asked a favour of you: that you go to Amon Ros and slay the elders of the spider-brood.\n* Defeat the Ruin-web Spinner\n* Defeat the Ruin-web Trapper\n* Defeat the Ruin-web Weaver\nObj 2:\nTortwil awaits your return in Ost Guruth, east of Amon Ros.\nTortwil will be pleased to hear of your victory against the spider-elders of Amon Ros.\n* Talk to Tortwil at Ost Guruth"},
{["next"]={1160},reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Lothlórien",area="Cirin-en-Galadh",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Tuilinn is surprised that you did not know the full story of how a Man, even one as respected as Aragorn, was able to successfully court a high-born Elf-lady like Arwen.",mobs={{locations={"13.02S, 67.18W"},name="Meluibrennil"},{locations={"11.98S, 64.86W"},name="Naeris"},{locations={"12.81S, 70.10W"},name="Pennasseth"},{locations={"11.93S, 67.85W"},name="Tuilinn"}},category="Lothlórien",id=774,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Elessar and Undómiel",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,c={"* Pennasseth is at Cerin Nauth [12.8S, 70.1W]\n* Meluibrennil is at Bain Gwaloth [13.0S, 67.2W]\n* Naeris is at The Peaceful Glade [12.0S, 64.9W]"},minlevel=55,b="Tuilinn",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTuilinn has sent you to three Elves who each know an aspect of the tale of the romance of Elessar and Undómiel.\nFrom Cerin Amroth, Pennasseth can be found to the south-west at Cerin Nauth. Naeris is in a the Peaceful Glade, due east. Meluibrennil is in Bain Gwaloth a short ways to the south-east.\n* Talk to Pennasseth\n* Talk to Meluibrennil\n* Talk to Naeris\nObj 2:\nTuilinn awaits you atop the flet at Cerin Amroth.\nYou should return to Tuilinn now that you have heard the tale of Elessar and Undómiel.\n* Talk to Tuilinn",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Caras Galadhon",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You have been charged with the friendly challenge of convincing Aragorn to return to Cerin Amroth.",mobs={{locations={"11.92S, 68.98W"},name="Milwen"},{locations={"14.89S, 66.88W"},name="Miluiel"},{locations={"15.00S, 66.81W","17.48S, 64.68W"},name="Aragorn"}},category="Lothlórien",id=775,scope="n/a",name="Elessar's Return",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,c={"* Milwen can be found in Cirin-en-Galadh [11.9S, 69.0W]\n* As stated, Aragorn is in the Company's Pavilion [15.0S, 66.8W]"},minlevel=55,b="Miluiel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMilwen can be found on the western side of the hill of Cerin Amroth, by the arches. Cerin Amroth is north of Caras Galadhon.\nMiluiel has sent you to retrieve a bloom of elanor from Milwen at Cerin Amroth, in order to convince Aragorn to return to the hill despite his mysterious refusal to do so.\n* Talk to Milwen in Cerin Amroth\nObj 2:\nAragorn is at the Company's Pavilion inside Caras Galadhon, south of Cerin Amroth.\nYou have been given a bloom of elanor to give to Aragorn, and Milwen is certain that it will convince him to return to the hill.\n* Talk to Aragorn\n* Turn in Elanor Bloom\nObj 3:\nMiluiel is outside the Company's Pavilion, in Caras Galadhon.\nAragorn has given his reasons for not returning to Cerin Amroth, and you should tell them now to Miluiel.\n* Talk to Miluiel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+1200 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Imyl has heard tell that the Angmarim and goblins are collecting relics of Elven origin and have come too close to the borders of Rivendell.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Imyl"}},category="Reputation",id=776,scope="n/a",name="Elf-relics -- Introduction",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Imyl",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAngmarim and Hillmen may be found in the many ruins of the Trollshaws, while other relics may have been secreted away in Goblin-town for many years.\nImyl has asked you to recover Elf-relics from the Angmarim and Hillmen in the Trollshaws and from the goblins of Goblin-town and bring them to her in Rivendell.\n* Bring an Elf-relic to Imyl at Rivendell\n* Turn in Elvish Relic",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Wights are not the only source of terror in Imlad Balchorth.",mobs={{locations={"6.88N, 25.87W"},name="Sigar"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Distilled Celebrant Ointment",id="70008D03"},{q="(x2)",val="Distilled Athelas Extract",id="70008CFB"}},category="Angmar",id=777,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Eliminate the Darkwater",receive={{val="Distilled Celebrant Salve",id="70000F40"},{val="Distilled Athelas Essence",id="70000F31"}},level=48,minlevel=43,b="Sigar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDarkwater can be found in Imlad Balchorth, west of Myrkworth.\nSigar has asked you to destroy the darkwater in Imlad Balchorth.\n* Defeat darkwater in Imlad Balchorth (15)\nObj 2:\nSigar is at Myrkworth, east of Imlad Balchorth.\nHaving destroyed the darkwater as asked, return to Sigar in Myrkworth and tell him the deed is done.\n* Talk to Sigar"},
{["next"]={1949},area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="A number of enemy scouts have been sighted along the outskirts of Garmadh-maudhûl, watching for signs of approaching danger.",mobs={{locations={"17.49S, 48.19W"},name="Eirien"}},category="Mirkwood",id=778,scope="n/a",name="Eliminate the Scouts",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Eirien",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGarmadh-maudhûl can be found to the north-east of Mithechad by following a trail that traverses up the mountain.\nEirien has asked you to defeat any scouts that you encounter in the area surrounding Garmadh-maudhûl.\n* Dispatch Hîshtgropor Scouts\nObj 2:\nEinior is at Mithechad, south-west of Garmadh-maudhûl.\nYou should return to Eirien and inform her of your deed.\n* Talk to Eirien in Mithechad"},
{["next"]={1943},area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="29s 68c"}},d="Foul, corrupted beasts of all kinds wander the ruined and crumbling streets of Fornost, twisted and unnatural mockeries of the wildlife of the North Downs. These creatures pose a threat to all that lives in the surrounding lands.",mobs={{locations={"7.94S, 56.08W"},name="Lovenol"}},category="North Downs",id=779,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Eliminating the Beasts",arcs="Fell Beasts",level=32,minlevel=27,b="Lovenol",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCorrupted bears, boars, and aurochs roam the ruined streets of Fornost.\nDismayed by the corruption brought about by the Angmarim, Lovenol has asked you to destroy the twisted bears, boars, and aurochs in Fornost before they can be released into the wild.\n* Defeat bears in Fornost (10)\n* Defeat boars in Fornost (10)\n* Defeated aurochs in Fornost (10)\nObj 2:\nLovenol is at the camp of the Free Peoples at the southernmost reaches of the city of Fornost.\nLovenol will be relieved to learn that you have succeeded at the task she set you.\n* Talk to Lovenol"},
{["next"]={550},area="Northern High Pass",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="The dwarf-trapper Thorgest was recently ambushed by Gauradan hunters who badly injured him. He is afraid that they may yet track him back to his cave.",mobs={{locations={"24.55S, 7.04E"},name="Thorgest"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=780,scope="n/a",name="Eliminating the Trail",arcs="Gauradan Curse",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Thorgest",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Gauradan hunters can be found throughout the southern reaches of High-pass.\nThorgest has asked you to throw the Gauradan hunters off his trail by defeating several of them before they find his dwelling.\n* Defeat Gauradan Wind-masters\n* Defeat Gauradan Wolf-born\nObj 2:\nYou should return to Thorgest at Hrimbarg in central High-pass and tell him that the Gauradan hunters have been defeated.\n* Talk to Thorgest",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Lieutenant Solvi asked that you assist him in collecting emergency rations for the fortress.",category="Ettenmoors",id=781,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Emergency Rations",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Solvi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThere are nerbyg all around Tol Ascarnen. Lieutenant Solvi is at Tol Ascarnen.\nLieutenant Solvi awaits your return with the meat and gizzards from the nerbyg.\n* Return to Lieutenant Solvi at Tol Ascarnen\n* Turn in Norbog Gizzard\n* Turn in Norbog Meat",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Dwarf-scouts have spotted a handful of White Hand Uruks who have somehow slipped into Moria through unknown passages. They seem to be attempting to sway the goblin-tribes of Durin's Way into an alliance with Saruman.",selectoneof={{val="Shield of Ninknakh Faltor",id=70016091},{val="Bronwegor",id=70016392}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=782,scope="n/a",prev={2101},name="Emissaries of the White Hand",arcs="Líkmund's Tasks",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Líkmund",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe White Hand Uruks can be found among the goblins and Orcs inhabiting Durin's Way. One was seen at Ninknakh Faltor, north of the Chamber of the Crossroads. Another was seen at Gloku-ru to the north-east. The last was seen on the road to Jazârgund at Durin's Crossing, to the north and east.\nLíkmund has asked you to go forth and defeat the emissaries of the White Hand.\n* Defeat the Emissary in Ninknakh Faltor\n* Defeat the Emissary in Gloku-ru\n* Defeat the Emissary at Durin's Crossing\nObj 2:\nLíkmund is at the Chamber of the Crossroads in Durin's Way.\nYou should inform Líkmund that the White Hand Emissaries in Durin's Way have been defeated.\n* Talk to Líkmund in the Chamber of the Crossroads",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Frostbluff",zone="Frostbluff",money={{val="90c"}},d="Basil Wyndham fell asleep after stealing away to engage in some festival fun, allowing the kegs in the town centre to run perilously low.",category="Frostbluff",id=783,scope="n/a",prev={2658},name="Empty Keg Emergency",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Frostbluff Coin",id="70024EB1"}},level=10,c={"* Get the keg at the servant's area (by the oven).  Avoid watchers and bring it to the thirsty patron lazily lying down on the only keg outside of the servants' area."},minlevel=6,b="Basil Wyndham",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nFresh kegs can be picked up near the servants' oven in Winter-home.\nYou should deliver the keg to the festival square, but mind that nobody important catches you!\n* Pick up one of the kegs at the servants' area\nObj 2:\nFresh kegs can be picked up near the servants' oven in Winter-home and should be brought to the edge of the festival square, where patrons must surely be getting thirsty.\nYou should deliver the keg to the festival square, but mind that nobody important catches you!\n* Deliver the replacement keg to the festival square\nObj 3:\nBasil Wyndham is in Winter-home, sitting and enjoying the merriment in the festival square.\nYou should speak with the servant Basil Wyndham.\n* Talk to Basil Wyndham",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+500 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="The communal larder of Sûri-kylä is running short, due to the troubled times in Forochel.",mobs={{locations={"17.49N, 64.50W"},name="Olavi"},{locations={"19.54N, 71.38W"},name="Nôra"}},category="Forochel",id=784,scope="n/a",name="Empty Larder",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Nôra",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou will find Olavi east and slightly south of Sûri-kylä at his fishing camp along the road to Itä-mâ.\nNôra has asked you to tell Olavi to bring him as many buckets of dried fish as he is able.\n* Talk to Olavi\nObj 2:\nThe fish Nôra requires can be found along the ice bay west of Olavi's camp.\nOlavi has asked you to take a fishing-pole and collect the fish Nôra requires.\n* Turn in Oily Fish\nObj 3:\nNôra is at Sûri-kylä.\nYou caught the fish where Olavi said you would. You should now bring the fish to Nôra in Sûri-kylä.\n* Talk to Nôra\n* Turn in Oily Fish",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nan Sirannon",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="A plague of crawlers has been a cause of concern for the Elves of Echad Dúnann.",mobs={{locations={"50.50S, 7.91W"},name="Tinúriel"}},category="Eregion",id=785,scope="n/a",name="Emyn Naer's Pests",c={"* Crawlers are found around Emyn Naer"},level=50,minlevel=45,b="Tinúriel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCrawlers can be found at Emyn Naer, south-west of Echad Dúnann.\nTinúriel has asked that you slay the corrupt crawlers of Emyn Naer.\n* Defeat crawlers (12)\nObj 2:\nTinúriel is in Echad Dúnann, north-east of Emyn Naer.\nYou should return at once to Tinúriel and inform her of your success.\n* Talk to Tinúriel at Echad Dúnann",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+500 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},zone="Forochel",area="Itä-mâ",money={{val="37s 52c"}},d="The kalpa-kita have slowly been encroaching on Lossoth territory and are now beginning to launch small raids on Lossoth-outposts virtually every night.",mobs={{locations={"8.96N, 70.75W"},name="Âtos"}},category="Forochel",id=786,scope="n/a",name="Encroaching Kalpa-kita",level=46,minlevel=41,b="Âtos",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nKalpa-kita can be found throughout the tundra of Itä-mâ.\nÂtos has asked you to help purge Itä-mâ of the kalpa-kita scourge.\n* Defeat kalpa-kita in Itä-mâ (18)\nObj 2:\nÂtos is at Pynti-leiri.\nNow that you have defeated many kalpa-kita, you should return to Âtos.\n* Talk to Âtos",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="We have learned some troubling news, $CLIENT_NAME$. It seems that Dolvaethor, one of Amarthiel's Black Númenórean lieutenants, has entered Haudh Valandil. I can think of no good reason for Dolvaethor to enter the tomb, but many terrible ones!\nWhatever Dolvaethor plans within the depths of wise Valandil's crypt, he must be stopped. You must do this, $CLIENT_NAME$ -- fighting your way across the bridge of Ariant and onto the island upon which sits Ost Elendil and Haudh Valandil will be terrible, but the Dúnedain lack the force of arms needed for this task. You and your allies, however, might be able to fight through.\nOnce you have defeated Dolvaethor within Haudh Valandil, set right whatever harm he has caused, then return to me. If the course of battle has drawn me elsewhere, speak instead to Captain-General Daerdan at Echad Garthadir.",selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Masterful Mash",id="700033A4"},{val="Distilled Athelas Essence",id="70000F31"}},category="Annúminas",id=787,scope="n/a",name="End Dolvaethor's Menace",receive={{q="(x10)",val="Arnorian Armour Fragments",id="7000AE74"},{q="(x4)",val="Battered Arnorian Armour",id="7000AE75"}},level=40,minlevel=35,repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDolvaethor is inside Haudh Valandil on the island upon which stands Ost Elendil, beyond the bridge of Ariant, in Annúminas.\nGlangilith has asked you to defeat Dolvaethor and put an end to whatever evil he plans for Haudh Valandil.\n* Kill 1 Dolvaethor\n* Restore Valandil's remains to peace"},
{area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+900 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="You defeated many Orcs in Urugarth, but your task is not yet complete. The Uruk-leader remains.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Donaith"}},selectoneof={{val="Tircham",id=70002222},{val="Lagmâs' Defeat",id=70002226},{val="Tinugor",id=70002225},{val="Maetham",id=70002224},{val="Donaith's Bow",id=70002223}},category="Urugarth",id=788,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2674},name="Ending Terror",arcs="Thinning the Horde",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Donaith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe leader of the Orc-army makes his home deep within Urugarth, west of Gath Forthnír.\nDonaith told you of a mighty Uruk-general that must be defeated.\n* Kill 1 Lagmâs\nObj 2:\nDonaith is at Gath Forthnír, east of Urugarth.\nYou should return to Gath Forthnír and tell Donaith the good news of your victory.\n* Talk to Donaith"},
{area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="31s 36c"}},d="The worms infesting the ruins of Fornost are led by an elder named Gajarpan by the Orcs. Gajarpan must be destroyed if the worms are to be driven from Fornost.",mobs={{locations={"8.15S, 55.90W"},name="Bôrk"}},selectoneof={{val="Anglang",id="70006BDE"},{val="Rehearh",id="70006B08"},{val="Gajarpan's Doom",id="70006BF9"},{val="Skot-leggar",id="70006A9F"}},category="North Downs",id=789,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1865},name="Ending the Elder",arcs="Rock-worms",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Bôrk",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGajarpan can be found somewhere within the ruins of Fornost.\nBôrk has asked you to slay Gajarpan, the worm-elder whom the worms of Fornost follow, in hopes that the worms might be driven out once and for all.\n* Kill 1 Gajarpan\nObj 2:\nBôrk is at the camp of the Free Peoples in the southern reaches of Fornost.\nBôrk awaits word of your victory against the worm Gajarpan.\n* Talk to Bôrk"},
{area="Steps of Gram",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Far to the north, where the Isendeep Mine runs beneath the shadow of the Mountains of Angmar, a brood of Drakes threatens the workers within the mine.",category="Ettenmoors",id=790,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="End of the Wintersebb",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Swithulf",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nWintersebb-drakes can be found north in the area of Arador's End.\nLieutenant Swithulf directed you to make your way north with others in search of a way to destroy the Wintersebb-drakes.\n* Kill 12 Wintersebb Drakeling\n* Kill 8 Wintersebb Drake\nObj 2:\nLieutenant Swithulf awaits your return at the Grimwood Lumber-yard.\nClimbing high into the foothills of the Mountains of Angmar in Arador's end, you faced down many foes from the Wintersebb-brood and emerged to collect your reward.\n* Return to Lieutenant Swithulf at the Grimwood Lumber Camp",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Carn Dûm",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+700 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="You have found Dírdrë, daughter of Éa, alive and well.",mobs={{locations={"12.28N, 31.81W"},name="Éa"}},selectoneof={{val="Éa's Leggings",id="7000237E"},{val="Túrchaim",id="7000237F"},{val="Dírdrë's Bracelet",id=70002380}},category="Angmar",id=791,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="End the Nightmare",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Dírdrë",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nÉa is at Tármunn Súrsa, near Carn Dûm.\nDírdrë has asked your aid returning to her mother, Éa.\n* Escort Dírdrë to safety\nObj 2:\nÉa is at Tármunn Súrsa, near Carn Dûm.\nYou returned Dírdrë to the Hillmen. You should speak with Éa, her mother, at once.\n* Talk to Éa"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Orcs gather beneath several banners, but flock towards a single cause. This is disconcerting for the dwarves, and the intent of the war-host of Moria spurs the staunchest of Durin's Folk to action against the Orcs in the halls they have claimed for many years.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=792,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={332},name="Enemies of Lothlórien",arcs="War Against Lothórien",level=60,minlevel=57,b="Narfi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nNarfi's brethren can be found at the Orc-Watch and Anazârmekhem, south-west of the Twenty-first Hall where Narfi holds his post.\nNarfi has asked you to visit his brothers, Avar, Pálmar, and Teitur at the Orc-watch and Anazârmekhem and learn what assistance they need.\n* Complete Avar's tasks in the Grand Stair\n* Complete Pálmar's tasks in the Forges of Khazad-dûm\n* Complete Teitur's tasks within Fil Gashan\nObj 2:\nNarfi is at the Twenty-first Hall, north-east of the Orc-watch and Anazârmekhem.\nAfter many difficult forays into the very heart of the Orc-strongholds of Moria, you have had decisive victories and thwarted the creatures' attempts to make a devastating blow upon the Elves of Lothlórien.\n* Talk to Narfi at the Twenty-first Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nain Enidh",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="11s 50c"}},d="In Annunlos lay a ruin, long abandoned by the Eglain. Picked clean and having only the depths of the ruin unexplored, the Eglain left the tombs beneath the ruin be, as is their custom. However, the ruin now teems with life again as dwarves, in league with Orcs, scour the ruin for treasures in the depths.",mobs={{locations={"32.82S, 32.96W"},name="Refr Quicksilver"}},selectoneof={{val="Froth-klath",id="70006AC9"},{val="Quicksilver's Mace",id="70006B9D"},{val="Striking Staff",id="70006B79"},{val="Quicksilver's Shield",id="70006BF7"}},category="Lone-lands",id=793,scope="n/a",prev={735},name="Enemies of the Eglain",arcs="The Forsaken Lone-lands",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Refr Quicksilver",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe overseer of the Dourhands may be found within the ruins of Mithrenost, south of Refr Quicklsilver.\nRefr Quicksilver has asked to seek out and defeat the overseer of the Dourhands at Mithrenost, in hopes that his followers will turn from their evil ways. He asked you to bring him evidence of the overseer's defeat.\n* Deliver the Dourhand medallion to Refr Quicksilver\n* Turn in Lord's Medallion"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The presence of goblin-spies in the Mirk-eaves also infers the presence of an enemy encampment somewhere in the vicinity.",mobs={{locations={"16.50S, 60.30W"},name="Glamodúd"},{locations={"15.07S, 61.53W"},name="Falasgon"},{locations={"15.12S, 61.44W"},name="Aemeldir"}},category="Mirkwood",id=794,scope="n/a",prev={1626},name="Enemy upon the Threshold",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Falasgon",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlamodúd is at Echad Glamodúd, south-east from Echad Sirion, at the southern foot of Amon Angened. Aemeldir is at Echad Sirion.\nFarasgon has asked you to speak with Glamodúd regarding the Orc-camp to the south and Aemeldir regarding Dúrburz-stazg, the encampment to the north.\n* Talk to Glamodúd at Echad Glamodúd\n* Talk to Aemeldir at Echad Sirion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="7s"}},d="Lieva Dourlily has an intense dislike for the goblins that have recently arrived in the Lone-lands and seeks to drive them away.",mobs={{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Lieva Dourlily"}},selectoneof={{val="Old Mugwort's Shield",id="7000376F"},{val="Old Mugwort's Shoes",id="7000376E"}},category="Lone-lands",id=795,scope="n/a",prev={1481},name="Enfeebling the Foe",arcs="Little Menaces",level=22,pois={{locations={"32.53S, 38.69W","31.74S, 38.67W","31.72S, 38.67W","31.77S, 38.41W","31.66S, 38.61W","32.03S, 38.53W","31.96S, 38.52W"},name="Goblin Food-barrel"}},minlevel=17,b="Lieva Dourlily",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere will be barrels of uneaten food at the goblin-camps of Weatherfoot, north-east of The Forsaken Inn and south-west of Weathertop.\nLieva Dourlily has asked you to take a special draught she brewed to the goblin-camps in the north-east and introduce it into their food supply. The draught is supposed to have properties that Lieva thinks will encourage the goblins to abandon the Lone-lands.\n* Use Goblin Food-barrel\n* Turn in Foul-smelling Draught\nObj 2:\nLieva Dourlily awaits your return at The Forsaken Inn, south-west of Weatherfoot.\nYou added the contents of Lieva's draught to the food-barrels found at the goblin-encampments north-east of The Forsaken Inn. Lieva will want to know of your success.\n* Talk to Lieva Dourlilly at The Forsaken Inn"},
{["next"]={177,2743},area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Elves of the Golden Host seek a way to cripple the Orcs of Durbúrz-stazg.",mobs={{locations={"15.12S, 61.44W"},name="Aemeldir"}},category="Mirkwood",id=796,scope="n/a",prev={1340},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Engaging the Enemy",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Aemeldir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDurbúrz-stazg lies to the north of Echad Sirion.\nAemeldir has asked you to defeat servants of the Enemy at Durbúrz-stazg. You will need to enter the encampment through the eastern gate.\nObj 2:\nEchad Sirion lies to the south of Durbúrz-stazg.\nYou should return to Aemeldir with news of your success.\n* Talk to Aemeldir at Echad Sirion"},
{["next"]={1997,388},area="The Scuttledells",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="A number of Ivorel's scouts have not returned from their mission in the Scuttledells. Miluimil saw some of them entrapped by the spiders to the north.",mobs={{locations={"12.45S, 50.88W","8.72S, 52.22W"},name="Miluimil"}},category="Mirkwood",id=797,scope="n/a",name="Entangled Elves",arcs="Webs of Treachery",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=64,c={"* There is a Cocooned Elf in the Scuttledells at [11.3S, 52.0W]\n* There is a Cocooned Elf in the Scuttledells at [10.1S, 50.3W]\n* There is a Cocooned Elf in the Scuttledells at [11.3S, 50.6W]\n* There is a Cocooned Elf in the Scuttledells at [11.5S, 51.3W]"},pois={{locations={"10.37S, 51.29W","10.49S, 50.77W","11.24S, 51.49W","11.30S, 51.98W","11.34S, 50.65W","11.53S, 51.29W","10.57S, 51.70W","10.11S, 50.27W"},name="Cocooned Elf"}},minlevel=59,b="Miluimil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ensnared Elves may be found in the nests of the spiders to the north of Ivorel's camp.\nMiluimil has asked you to set forth to free his ensnared companions.\n* Use Cocooned Elf\nObj 2:\nMiluimil is at Ivorel's camp, south of the spider-nests.\nYou should speak with Miluimil and tell him that the scouts have been freed.\n* Talk to Miluimil at Ivorel's camp"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="The Rangers have no record of who is within Haudh Eärendur.",category="Evendim",id=798,scope="n/a",name="Entombed of Haudh Eärendur",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Nimbellas",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHaudh Eärendur is within the Way of Kings, west of the Ranger's camp.\nNimbellas has asked you to take rubbings of those tombs buried within Haudh Eärendur.\nObj 2:\nNimbellas is at the Ranger camp in the Way of Kings.\nNimbellas will be eager to examine the rubbings you took.\n* Talk to Nimbellas",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="Barad Tharsír was once an important shipping port that linked Evendim with the south along the Baranduin.",category="Evendim",id=799,scope="n/a",name="Entrances of Barad Tharsír",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=33,minlevel=28,b="Daerol",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarad Tharsír is south-east of the Colossus on the east bank of the Brandywine river.\nDaerol asked you to scout the ruins of Barad Tharsír and report back on what you find.\n* Discover the first entranceway\n* Discover the second entranceway\n* Discover the third entranceway\n* Discover the fourth entranceway\n* Discover the fifth entranceway\nObj 2:\nDaerol is at the Colossus, north-west of Barad Tharsír.\nDaerol will be very interested to hear what you learned about the doors of Barad Tharsír.\n* Talk to Daerol",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tyrn Fornech",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Clark Standish encountered a gang of tomb-robbers at Duskencleft, and believes they might have hidden a satchel of stolen relics there.",mobs={{locations={"8.01S, 64.59W"},name="Clark Standish"}},category="Evendim",id=800,scope="n/a",name="Escape from Duskencleft",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=35,c={"* The Relic of Satchels is by the pass to The Duskencleft [5.1S, 66.7W]"},minlevel=30,b="Clark Standish",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe satchel of stolen pottery is somewhere in the Duskencleft, south-west of goblin-infested Tûm Fuin. Tûm Fuin is north of Ost Forod.\n* Turn in Satchel of Relics\nObj 2:\nClark Standish is in Ost Forod, the old watch-post in the hills of Tyrn Fornech, south of the Duskencleft.\nYou have reclaimed the satchel of stolen relics and should return it to Clark Standish.\n* Talk to Clark Standish\n* Turn in Satchel of Relics",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Elves of the the Golden Host landed on the shores of the Mirk-eaves and drove the Orcs of the riverbanks into the forest. Once they secured the shores, they established a camp there.",mobs={{locations={"15.11S, 61.35W"},name="Tethafnel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=801,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Establishing a Foothold",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,c={"* You must plant the banner in a Rock-pile in Fállug at [16.7S, 62.0W]"},pois={{locations={"16.71S, 61.96W"},name="Rock-pile"}},minlevel=56,b="Tethafnel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFállug lies to the south of Echad Sirion, overlooking the Anduin.\nTethafnel has asked you to plant the banner of the Malledhrim at Fállug so their kindred in Lothlórien will know of their victory.\n* Use Rock-pile\n* Turn in Banner of the Galadhrim\nObj 2:\nTethafnel is at Echad Sirion, north from Fállug.\nYou should return to Tethafnel and let her know that you have planted the banner as she requested.\n* Talk to Tethafnel at Echad Sirion"},
{["next"]={186},reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="The unexpected invasion of the Orcs from the North have caught the Rangers of Esteldín unprepared, with many of their kindred abroad in other lands. This new threat has forced them to recall as many of their kind as they can and to arm themselves for war.",mobs={{locations={"9.45S, 42.03W"},name="Faronwen"}},category="North Downs",id=802,scope="n/a",name="Esteldín's Preparation",arcs="Preparation for War",level=30,minlevel=25,b="Faronwen",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Rangers' supply troves are hidden throughout eastern Nan Amlug and Rhunenlad.\nIn preparation for war, Faronwen is tasked with recovering the stores of weapons and supplies her predecessor hid. She has asked you to search Nan Amlug and Rhunenlad for these hidden stores. She only knows that these troves are hidden by rocks and trees.\n* Bring the Ranger Troves back to Faronwen\n* Turn in Ranger-trove",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2497},area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="According to the records Larus Sharpshard was given by Heikki Goldwatcher, the strongbox you recovered is missing some of its contents.",mobs={{locations={"24.85S, 4.03W"},name="Larus Sharpshard"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=803,scope="n/a",prev={1576},name="Every Last Ingot",arcs="Every Last Ingot",receive={{val="Amarthron",id="7000383E"}},level=43,minlevel=38,b="Larus Sharpshard",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblins carrying dwarf-gold ingots can likely be found on the Pinnath Fenui, the ridges east of the source of the Bruinen, in the Misty Mountains.\nLarus Sharpshard is outraged that goblins have pilfered from the strongbox you recovered and has demanded that you retrieve all of the stolen ingots.\n* Turn in Ingot of Dwarf-gold\nObj 2:\nLarus Sharpshard is at Glóin's camp, north of Rivendell.\nLarus Sharpshard will be delighted that you have recovered the stolen ingots from the goblins of the Misty Mountains.\n* Talk to Larus Sharpshard\n* Turn in Ingot of Dwarf-gold"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="I grieve to see Ost Elendil in the hands of the Enemy, $CLIENT_NAME$. The great palace of the kings should lie untainted by the forces of evil, not brought low by the machinations of Angmar and its regent!\nFell spirits and their Angmarim masters now stalk the halls of Ost Elendil at Amarthiel's command. We must drive them forth.\nDefeat the spirits within the palace and take from their Angmarim masters the blood-stained runes with which they are commanded. That may lessen Angmar's grip on the palace, shining jewel-that-was. If I am not here when you return, I ask that you bring the runes to Captain-General Daerdan at Echad Garthadir, the Ranger-encampment here in the city. He will be able to destroy the foul things.",category="Annúminas",id=804,scope="n/a",name="Evil in Ost Elendil",receive={{val="Annúminas Mark",id="700216BF"}},level=40,minlevel=35,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nFell spirits and their Angmarim masters can be found in Ost Elendil, beyond the bridge of Ariant.\nLegrindavor has asked you to defeat the fell spirits inside Ost Elendil and bring him the blood-stained runes used by the Angmarim there to command them.\n* Defeat Spirits in Ost Elendil",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1033},area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="The Ranger Forchon is not sure of your trustworthiness. He has asked you to defeat some of the bats and barghests that prowl into Parth Aduial from the Fields of Fornost as a way of proving yourself to him.",mobs={{locations={"12.60S, 67.35W"},name="Forchon"}},category="Evendim",id=805,scope="n/a",name="Evils out of Fornost",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=34,minlevel=29,b="Forchon",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBats and barghests can be found in Parth Aduial, especially near the pass leading to the Fields of Fornost.\nForchon has expressed his distrust of you, but might become less hostile if you fulfil his request.\n* Defeat bats in Parth Aduial (8)\n* Defeat barghests in Parth Aduial (6)\nObj 2:\nRanger Forchon is at the Ranger-camp on the island of Tinnudir, in Evendim.\nYou have defeated bats and barghests in Parth Aduial, as Forchon requested. The Ranger waits to hear of your success.\n* Talk to Forchon"},
{["next"]={574},area="Talvi-mûri",zone="Forochel",d="Arre told you of a strange Gauradan mystic he once encountered upon the glacier. He appeared to be an exile among his people, but was wise in their lore. It is possible that he could tell more of the strange frozen amulet that you found in Kibilzahar.",mobs={{locations={"12.30N, 79.41W"},name="Nicca"},{locations={"19.55N, 83.77W"},name="Arre"}},category="Forochel",id=806,scope="n/a",prev={2012},name="Exiles of Winter",level=49,c={"* Nicca is north-east of Zigilgund"},minlevel=44,b="Arre",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nNicca lives somewhere along the southern edge of the great glacier, in the hills east of Barad Gaurhoth.\nArre suggested you speak with Nicca and learn what you may of the amulets.\n* Talk to Nicca\n* Turn in Frozen Amulet",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="A few Elves who were among the first to cross the Anduin to make way for the main landing were captured by Orcs. If they are not rescued before the Malledhrim make their final assault upon Amon Angened, the prisoners will likely be killed.",mobs={{locations={"15.09S, 61.32W"},name="Agorin"}},category="Mirkwood",id=807,scope="n/a",prev={818},name="Expedition: A Daring Rescue",arcs="Aid the Fallen",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Agorin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElvish prisoners are being held in the Orc-fortress upon Amon Angened, south-east of Echad Sirion.\nAgorin has asked you to mount the rescue of Elvish prisoners from their Orc-captors.\n* Rescue a captured soldier\nObj 2:\nAgorin is at Echad Sirion, on the eastern bank of the Anduin.\nYou should return to Agorin with news of your success.\n* Talk to Agorin at Echad Sirion"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Two bridges ford the stream south of Echad Sirion. By means of these bridges, Orc-reinforcements may flank the Malledhrim.",mobs={{locations={"15.12S, 61.36W"},name="Ivorel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=808,scope="n/a",name="Expedition: Bridging the Gap",arcs="Forerunners",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,c={"* The western bridge can be found in the Mirk-eaves at [16.9S, 61.4W]\n* The eastern bridge can be found in the Mirk-eaves at [17.0S, 60.1W]"},minlevel=56,b="Ivorel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe two bridges lie to the south of Echad Sirion, along a small tributary to the Anduin.\nIvorel has asked you to take the two bridges allowing access to the Mirk-eaves from the south.\n* Capture the western bridge\n* Capture the eastern bridge\nObj 2:\nIvorel is at Echad Sirion, on the eastern banks of the Anduin.\nYou should inform Ivorel that both bridges were already destroyed.\n* Talk to Ivorel at Echad Sirion"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Communication between the Orc-fortifications scattered across the Mirk-eaves are handled by goblin-runners who rush messages from one to another. The defeat of these runners not only would cut the encampments off from each other, but may result in the interception of important information about the Enemy's movements.",mobs={{locations={"15.12S, 61.36W"},name="Ivorel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=809,scope="n/a",name="Expedition: Disrupting Communication",arcs="Forerunners",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Ivorel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblin-runners can be found throughout the Mirk-eaves.\nIvorel has asked you to intercept and defeat the goblin-runners that carry messages from camp to camp in the Mirk-eaves.\n* Defeat goblin-runners\nObj 2:\nIvorel is at Echad Sirion, on the eastern banks of the Anduin.\nYou should return to Ivorel with news of your success.\n* Talk to Ivorel at Echad Sirion"},
{["next"]={813},area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="A handful of Elves have become separated from the main host during the battle to take the Mirk-Eaves.",mobs={{locations={"15.09S, 61.32W"},name="Agorin"}},category="Mirkwood",id=810,scope="n/a",prev={820},name="Expedition: Lost in the Fray",arcs="Aid the Fallen",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,c={"* The desperate soldier is in the Mirk-eaves at [14.1S, 60.5W]\n* The exhausted soldier is in the Mirk-eaves at [14.2S, 59.8W]\n* The wounded soldier is in the Mirk-eaves at [16.0S, 60.5W]"},minlevel=56,b="Agorin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Elf-soldiers may be found among the trees of the Mirk-eaves.\nAgorin has asked you to aid the missing Elves should you find them amongst the forests of the Mirk-eaves.\n* Rescue desperate soldier\n* Rescue exhausted soldier\n* Rescue wounded soldier\nObj 2:\nAgorin is at Echad Sirion on the eastern banks of the Anduin.\nYou should return to Agorin and let her know that you have found and aided the missing soldiers.\n* Talk to Agorin at Echad Sirion"},
{["next"]={818},area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="In battles of such a scale as the Mirkwood landing, severe wounds and even death are an inevitable consequence, even among such fine warriors as the Mallhedrim.",mobs={{locations={"15.09S, 61.32W"},name="Agorin"}},category="Mirkwood",id=811,scope="n/a",name="Expedition: Seeing to the Fallen",arcs="Aid the Fallen",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,pois={{locations={"15.02S, 61.55W","15.35S, 61.52W","15.03S, 61.53W","15.01S, 61.53W","15.16S, 61.44W","15.14S, 61.45W","15.15S, 61.45W","15.13S, 61.46W","15.05S, 61.53W","15.37S, 61.54W","15.38S, 61.54W","15.04S, 61.55W","15.14S, 61.43W","15.37S, 61.52W","15.37S, 61.51W"},name="Supply Crate (Level 1)"}},minlevel=56,b="Agorin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe supplies are at Echad Sirion, on the eastern banks of the Anduin.\nAgorin has tasked you with finding clean bandages that have been misplaced among the rest of the military supplies that were hastily brought across the Anduin.\n* Use Supply Crate (Level 1)\n* Use Supply Crate (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nThe wounded Elves are at Echad Sirion, on the eastern banks of the Anduin.\nNow that you have collected enough bandages, you should see to the treatment of the Elf-soldiers who were seriously wounded during the first wave of the assault upon Mirkwood.\n* Turn in Silken Bandages\n* Turn in Silken Bandages\n* Turn in Silken Bandages\n* Turn in Silken Bandages\n* Turn in Silken Bandages\nObj 3:\nAgorin is at Echad Sirion, on the eastern banks of the Anduin\n* Talk to Agorin at Echad Sirion"},
{["next"]={2449},area="Zelem-melek",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="The Mordor Orcs have suffered great casualties from the attacks of the Moria Orcs. The heart of their forces is weakened and vulnerable.",selectoneof={{val="Gauntlets of Brutal Onslaught",id="70017CEE"},{val="Knakk's Cap",id="70017C8E"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=812,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={243},name="Expulsion",arcs="Orcs of Mordor",level=54,minlevel=49,b="Knakk",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orcs of Mordor and their captains are encamped at Baiúrz-mur, north of the Orc-watch.\nKnakk told you to press an assault against the Orcs of Mordor and their captains.\n* Defeat Mordor Orcs at Baiúrz-mur (14)\n* Defeat Mordor captains at Baiúrz-mur\nObj 2:\nKnakk is at the Orc-watch, south of Baiúrz-mur.\nKnakk will be pleased to hear that the captains of Mordor and many of their troops have been routed from Baiúrz-mur and defeated.\n* Talk to Knakk at the Orc-watch"},
{["next"]={1602},reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="Echad Garthadir, the Rangers encampment within Annumins, is under constant assault.",category="Evendim",id=813,scope="n/a",prev={1897},name="Eye of the Storm",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Nimbellas",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nEchad Garthadir is the Ranger's encampment in Annuminas.\n* Talk to TBD Follow",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Elves of the Golden Host have established an encampment on the shores of the Mirk-eaves and seek to protect it against the spies of the Enemy.",mobs={{locations={"15.32S, 61.56W"},name="Faroniel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=814,scope="n/a",name="Eyes of Dol Guldur",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Faroniel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCrebain and Wargs can be found throughout the Mirk-eaves.\nFaroniel has asked you to blind the eyes of Dol Guldur by defeating many of the crebain and Wargs which roam the Mirk-eaves.\n* Defeat Darkwing spies in the Mirk-eaves (8)\n* Defeat Warg-scouts in the Mirk-eaves (8)\nObj 2:\nFaroniel is at Echad Sirion in the Mirk-eaves.\nYou should return to Faroniel with tidings of your success.\n* Talk to Faroniel at Echad Sirion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1363},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="Falco's garden is failing for an unknown reason, causing distress among the people of Staddle.",mobs={{locations={"31.03S, 49.28W"},name="Himloc Grouse"},{locations={"30.98S, 47.80W"},name="Lily Underhill"},{locations={"31.02S, 49.28W"},name="Ferumbras Attereeve"},{locations={"31.09S, 49.56W"},name="Ferdibrand Took"},{locations={"31.13S, 49.42W"},name="Ethelinda Burr"},{locations={"30.97S, 48.18W"},name="Gammy Boggs"},{locations={"31.02S, 49.40W"},name="Longo Daegmund"}},category="Bree-land",id=815,scope="n/a",prev={582},name="Eyes of Staddle",arcs="Falco's Garden",level=12,minlevel=8,b="Gammy Boggs",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe people of Staddle can be found tending and watching over their farms or in the centre of Staddle.\nGammy Boggs has recommended that you speak to some of the Staddle-folk to learn what happened to Falco's garden.\n* Talk to Ethelinda Burr\n* Talk to Ferdibrand Took\n* Talk to Ferumbras Attereeve\n* Talk to Longo Daegmund\n* Talk to Himloc Grouse\n* Talk to Lily Underhill\nObj 2:\nGammy Boggs is on the second farm north of the road near the Staddle farms.\nThe knowledge you gained from the people of Staddle will be of great interest to Gammy Boggs, the town gossip.\n* Talk to Gammy Boggs at her farm"},
{zone="Angmar",area="Aughaire",money={{val="8s 96c"}},d="You have survived the Clúcath, and Fail-á-Khro has been retaken by the Trév Gállorg.",mobs={{locations={"0.09S, 40.18W"},name="Crannog"},{locations={"2.55N, 37.25W"},name="Cána"}},category="Angmar",id=816,scope="n/a",prev={2533},name="Fail-á-Khro Retaken",c={"* Cána is at Fail-á-Khro."},level=43,minlevel=38,b="Crannog",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCána is at Fail-á-Khro, north of Aughaire.\nThe Trév Gállorg have retaken Fail-á-Khro and now seek your assistance to hold it.\n* Talk to Cána",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1489},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 20c"}},d="Darri wants you to find out if his theory is correct by going to an unbroken mirror and trying to swivel it into position.",selectoneof={{val="Mirrored Shield",id="7001608F"},{val="Survivalist's Ring",id="70017CE9"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=817,scope="n/a",prev={77},name="Faint But Fierce",arcs="A Faint Gleam",level=51,pois={{locations={"8.08S, 111.01W","7.20S, 111.15W","6.96S, 112.13W","8.01S, 111.94W","6.76S, 112.77W"},name="Mirror"}},minlevel=46,b="Darri",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe mirrors were discovered at the Dolven-view in the Great Delving of Moria.\nDarri has asked you to swivel one of the unbroken mirrors you found and see what happens.\n* Use Mirror\nObj 2:\nDarri can be found at the Dolven-view in the Great Delving of Moria.\nYou should return to Darri and tell him what happened when you swivelled the mirror.\n* Return to Darri"},
{["next"]={893},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="Falco's garden is failing for an unknown reason, distressing the people of Staddle.",mobs={{locations={"31.45S, 48.60W"},name="Falco Greenhand"},{locations={"30.97S, 48.18W"},name="Gammy Boggs"}},category="Bree-land",id=818,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1363},name="Falco's Garden",arcs="Falco's Garden",level=12,minlevel=8,b="Gammy Boggs",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFalco Greenhand's farm lies to the south-west of Gammy Boggs' farm.\nGammy Boggs has suggested you speak with Falco Greenhand again and tell him of the mysterious trespassers that were seen near his garden.\n* Talk to Falco Greenhand at his farm\nObj 2:\nConstable Bolger's house is located south-east of Falco Greenhand's farm.\nConfronted with the truth, Falco Greenhand confessed that he had made an underhanded bargain with ruffians. He has asked you to speak with Constable Bolger and warn him that the brigands are coming to burn the town.\n* Talk to Constable Bolger at his farm\nObj 3:\nFalco Greenhand's farm lies to the north-west of Constable Bolger's home.\nYou and Constable Bolger have defeated the Blackwold brigands who had planned to burn the town of Staddle. Falco will be glad that you have succeeded.\n* Talk to Falco Greenhand at his farm"},
{["next"]={1847},area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},d="Falgeirr Twisttongue, a dwarf with a penchant for riddles, left messages for his descendants in his personal papers, which you found in the library of the Great Delving. Öndótt has seen many plaques about, but does not know what they are; could they have anything to do with Twisttongue's game?",category="Moria Central Halls",id=819,scope="n/a",prev={1845},name="Falgeirr Twisttongue",arcs="Riddles in the Dark",level=54,pois={{locations={"11.85S, 112.14W","12.15S, 111.30W"},name="Plaque"}},minlevel=49,b="Öndótt",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou should try and solve Falgeirr Twisttongue's riddle:\nI can sizzle like bacon; I am made with an egg,\nI have plenty of backbone, but lack a good leg,\nI peel layers like onions, but still remain whole,\nI can be long, like a flag-pole, yet fit in small holes.\nWhat am I?\nOndott, when discussing the riddle with you, also mentioned some plaques around Moria, used for marking rooms and chambers....\n* Use Plaque"},
{area="Hobbiton-Bywater",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Gaffer Gamgee was dismissed from his duties as the gardener of Bag End by the Sackville-Bagginses. Before his dismissal, he was in the midst of gathering apples from the orchard but never had a chance to finish.",mobs={{locations={"30.22S, 71.53W"},name="Gaffer Gamgee"}},category="Shire",id=820,scope="n/a",name="Fallen Apples",receive={{val="Apple Seeker",id="700033AF"},{val="Mushroom Pie",id="700005F3"}},level=7,pois={{locations={"29.68S, 71.89W","29.47S, 71.99W","29.51S, 72.21W","29.61S, 72.22W","29.49S, 72.10W","29.68S, 72.01W","29.48S, 71.91W","29.38S, 72.11W","29.78S, 71.98W","29.57S, 72.10W","29.31S, 72.21W","29.76S, 71.89W","29.69S, 72.20W","29.38S, 72.01W","29.58S, 71.89W","29.78S, 72.09W","29.28S, 71.89W","29.29S, 72.10W","29.68S, 72.09W","29.81S, 72.20W","29.39S, 72.21W","29.28S, 72.01W","29.58S, 72.00W","29.38S, 71.89W"},name="Pile of Apples"}},minlevel=3,b="Gaffer Gamgee",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Bag End apple orchard is just to the west of Bag End.\nGaffer Gamgee has asked you to do a little gardening on his behalf by gathering the fallen apples from Bag End's orchard, certain that the Sackville-Bagginses will not chase off a Bounder.\n* Use Pile of Apples\nObj 2:\nGaffer Gamgee is outside his home on Bagshot Row at the foot of the Hill in Hobbiton.\nYou should bring Gaffer Gamgee the apples you were able to salvage from the apple piles.\n* Talk to Gaffer Gamgee\n* Turn in Apple",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Somehow the very essence of the Red Swamp has been corrupted. Radagast the Brown, a Wizard who has come to Agamaur, seeks to learn the cause.",mobs={{locations={"29.79S, 27.39W","29.78S, 27.39W"},name="Radagast the Brown"}},selectoneof={{val="Mace of the Brown Wizard",id="700006EE"},{val="Gauntlets of the Brown Wizard",id="700006ED"},{val="Band of the Brown Wizard",id="700006F0"},{val="Hammer of the Brown Wizard",id="700006EF"}},category="Lone-lands",id=821,scope="n/a",prev={2838},name="Fallen Oak",arcs="Tainted Living",level=30,c={"* Gloomleaf is located at [27.6S, 29.7W]"},minlevel=25,b="Radagast the Brown",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGloomleaf can be found in the north-west of Agamaur.\nRadagast the Brown has tasked you with destroying the corrupted creatures of Agamaur in an effort to cleanse the Gaunt-lord Ivar's evil from the swamp. In your absence, he learned of a great Huorn that was corrupted and is the force stirring the other Huorns. He has asked you to destroy Gloomleaf.\n* Kill 1 Gloomleaf\nObj 2:\nRadagast is in the Eglain camp in the southern reaches of Agamaur, near the entrance.\nRadagast sent you to destroy the great Huorn Gloomleaf in an effort to cleanse Ivar's evil from Agamaur. The deed done, it is time to return to Radagast with the tragic news of your success.\n* Talk to Radagast the Brown"},
{area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="8s 50c"}},d="Nathan Hodges is worried that a hobbit who was visiting him might have been attacked by the Wargs during the retreat to Amon Raith.",mobs={{locations={"12.52S, 52.82W"},name="Nathan Hodges"}},category="North Downs",id=822,scope="n/a",prev={841},name="Fallen to the Wargs",receive={{val="Hodges' Jacket",id="70006B2C"}},level=23,pois={{locations={"7.71S, 49.46W","7.63S, 49.60W","7.71S, 49.62W","8.00S, 49.89W","7.82S, 49.26W","8.29S, 49.52W","7.78S, 49.36W","7.87S, 49.76W","8.36S, 49.48W","7.85S, 49.41W","7.67S, 49.36W","7.80S, 49.55W"},name="Bone-pile"}},minlevel=18,b="Nathan Hodges",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nA large pack of Wargs has moved into northern Annúndir, and the bones of their kills litter the burial mounds in the north.\nNathan Hodges is worried that a friend of his, Ailward Took, a visitor from the Shire, did not make it safely to Amon Raith. Hodges has asked you to retrieve the bones scattered around the Warg-occupied burial mounds, but hopes you will not find any of hobbit-size.\n* Use Bone-pile\nObj 2:\nNathan Hodges is at Amon Raith, west of southern Annúndir.\nNathan Hodges is waiting for you to return with the bones you scavenged from the Wargs.\n* Talk to Nathan Hodges\n* Turn in Gnawed Bones",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1090},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="You had been asked to find Reginald Ward's herald, but upon finding him, he revealed that he lost his Captain's treasured family-banner.",mobs={{locations={"14.84N, 65.26W"},name="Reginald's Ward"},{locations={"19.11N, 70.79W"},name="Reginald Ward"}},category="Forochel",id=823,scope="n/a",prev={279},name="Falling Standards",receive={{val="Simple Rally Horn (Store)",id="7000E962"}},level=48,c={"* Reginald's Banner can be found in Jä-rannit at [15.2N, 66.6W]"},pois={{locations={"15.19N, 66.59W"},name="Reginald's Banner"}},minlevel=43,b="Reginald's Ward",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nReginald Ward's banner is lost in one of the encampments of the Angmarim on the ice-shelf, south-east of Sûri-kylä.\nReginald's herald has asked you to retrieve his Captain's banner, which he lost during the attack by the Angmarim.\n* Bring the banner to Reginald Ward's herald\n* Collect the banner\nObj 2:\nReginald Ward is at Sûri-kylä, north-west of the ice-shelf.\nReginald Ward's herald has asked you to tell his Captain that he is safe and where he can be found.\n* Tell Reginald Ward where his wayward herald can be found"},
{["next"]={1799},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="For many ages, the Earth-kin protected the pass through Ram Dúath from Angmar, but since the betrayal of the Suuri-lehmä tribe by First Hunter Jarkko and his followers, the Earth-kin have themselves become trapped in the North Downs.",mobs={{locations={"9.44S, 41.27W"},name="Daervunn"}},category="North Downs",id=824,scope="n/a",name="Fall of the Earth-kin",arcs="Stemming the Tide",level=31,minlevel=26,b="Daervunn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Earth-kin of the Rauta-lehmä faction are encamped east of Esteldín in Nan Amlug.\nDaervunn, Ranger of Esteldín, has charged you with showing the traitorous Rauta-lehmä that they have chosen the wrong side in the coming war by raiding their encampment.\n* Kill 6 Rauta-lehmä Warrior\n* Kill 6 Rauta-lehmä Hunter\nObj 2:\nDaervunn awaits your return at Esteldín.\nYou defeated the Earth-kin of the Rauta-lehmä at their camp in the eastern section of Nan Amlug. Daervunn will want news of your victory.\n* Talk to Daervunn in Esteldín"},
{["next"]={2463},area="Fasach-larran",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Drostan, now stripped of his name and called Soltakh among the Trév Gállorg, is anxious to redeem himself.",mobs={{locations={"2.72N, 37.29W"},name="Soltakh"}},category="Angmar",id=825,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2533},name="False Orders",arcs="False Orders",level=44,c={"* Sub-commander's strongboxes are found in Dûn Covád at:\n[5.3N, 38.4W]\n* [5.9N, 38.3W]\n* [5.7N, 38.5W]\n* [5.6N, 38.7W]"},pois={{locations={"5.33N, 38.40W","5.86N, 38.49W","5.64N, 38.72W","5.75N, 38.49W","5.86N, 38.29W"},name="Sub-commander's Strongbox"}},minlevel=39,b="Soltakh",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nStrongboxes can be found throughout the city of Dûn Covád, in the western hills north of Fail-á-Khro.\nSoltakh has asked you to slip false orders into the strongboxes used by the Angmarim chain of command for communication of tasks.\n* Use Sub-commander's Strongbox\n* Turn in False Order\nObj 2:\nSoltakh is at Fail-á-Khro, south of Dûn Covád and north of Aughaire.\nHaving slipped the false orders into the Angmarim strongboxes, you should return to Soltakh at Fail-á-Khro.\n* Talk to Soltakh"},
{["next"]={367},area="Northern Emyn Uial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="Erchiel is ready to move forward with the final stages of the plan Lithuifin helped her devise.",mobs={{locations={"6.12S, 71.92W"},name="Erchiel"}},category="Evendim",id=826,scope="n/a",prev={2684},name="False Wards",arcs="Threat from the North",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=36,c={"* 1st ward is located at [5.6S, 71.9W]\n* 2nd ward is located at [5.4S, 72.5W]\n* 3rd ward is located at [6.1S, 73.2W]\n* 4th ward is located at [6.6S, 73.7W]\n* 5th ward is located at [6.6S, 74.2W]"},pois={{locations={"5.63S, 71.94W","5.44S, 72.54W","6.57S, 73.67W","6.09S, 73.16W","6.56S, 74.16W"},name="Gauradan-marker"}},minlevel=31,b="Erchiel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nErchiel has asked you to modify a series of Gauradan-markers into Wards of Doom to prevent the Gauredain from crossing into the Eavespires.\nThe Gauradan-markers are along the river to the north of the Eavespires.\n* Use Gauradan-marker\nObj 2:\nYou should return and tell Erchiel that you have finished placing the wards.\nErchiel is at the Eavespires, south of the river.\n* Talk to Erchiel\n* Turn in Ward of Doom"},
{["next"]={2676},area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="8s 50c"}},d="Falster the Fox, a denizen of The Forsaken Inn, needs assistance acquiring certain curiosities for Ollie Redbrush of Bree.",mobs={{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Falster the Fox"}},selectoneof={{val="The Fox's Trousers",id="7001D10D"},{val="Falster's Tunic",id="7001D11B"},{val="Falster's Helmet",id="7001D11A"}},category="Lone-lands",id=827,scope="n/a",name="Falster's Request",arcs="Traders from Bree",level=23,minlevel=18,b="Falster the Fox",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCoins and heirlooms can be found in the Arnorian rubble located in the valley beneath Minas Eriol, south-east of The Forsaken Inn. Wolves also stalk the valley.\nFalster the Fox, a trader working for a man named Ollie Redbrush, has asked you to collect some old coins and heirlooms for him. Falster wants you to hunt the wolves there for teeth that may help to make up for the delay of his delivery to Ollie Redbrush.\n* Bring curiosities to Falster the Fox\n* Turn in Arnorian Heirloom\n* Turn in Arnorian Coin\n* Turn in Wolf-tooth"},
{["next"]={875,3200,836},area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="8s 50c"}},d="William Peake lost a chest containing an heirloom of his family when he and his wife fled from the Wargs invading Annúndir.",category="North Downs",id=828,scope="n/a",prev={2542},name="Family Heirloom",level=23,pois={{locations={"10.33S, 52.54W"},name="Heirloom Chest"}},minlevel=18,b="William Peake",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWilliam Peake's chest was stolen by a farmhand who fled north towards the ruins upon Amon Amrûn.\nWilliam Peake has asked you to find his heirloom chest and the farmhand who stole it.\n* Use Heirloom Chest\nObj 2:\nWilliam Peake awaits the return of the heirloom chest at Amon Raith, south of Amon Amrûn.\nIn the middle of the ruin of Amon Amrûn, you discovered the grisly scene of the farmhand dead near William Peake's chest. You should return at once to Amon Raith with the chest.\n* Talk to William Peake\n* Turn in Heirloom-chest",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1641},area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Bruner Stoutthrush, a disreputable seeming gentleman from Bree, has decided to do a good deed for the refugees from the Blackwold attacks.",mobs={{locations={"30.26S, 50.17W"},name="Bruner Stoutthrush"}},category="Bree-land",id=829,scope="n/a",name="Family Treasures",arcs="Shady Business",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Bruner Stoutthrush",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe brigands can be found in a large camp in the Yellow Tree Ruins, south of Staddle; but it may be that some others in the Chetwood also carry stolen items.\nWhether as an act of beneficence or complete self-interest, Stoutthrush has asked you to collect stolen heirlooms from the brigands and bring them to him at Bree's Combe-gate.\n* Bring the heirlooms to Bruner Stoutthrush\n* Turn in Heirloom",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2438},area="Emyn Lûm",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="One of Fuirgam's trackers has been ambushed and slain by wolves in the forests of Emyn Lûm.",category="Mirkwood",id=830,scope="n/a",prev={3241,288,1507},name="Fangs Bared",arcs="The Wild Ruins",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,c={"* You need to defeat wolves around Hrigg Vidukuni to summon him. Careful, he will come with a couple adds, making this quest a hard solo quest."},minlevel=58,b="Fuirgam",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSharpfang may be found at Hrigg Vidukuni, west of the Wild Ruins, south-west of Ost Galadh.\nFuirgam has asked you to travel to Hrigg Vidukuni and search the area for the Emyn Lûm pack-leader, Sharpfang, and defeat him.\n* Defeat Sharpfang\nObj 2:\nFuirgam at Ost Galadh is at Ost Galadh, north of the Wild Ruins, north-east of Hrigg Vidukuni.\nYou should return to Fuirgam with news of your success.\n* Talk to Fuirgam at Ost Galadh"},
{area="Lugazag",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Removed so far from the fortresses of Ost Ringdyr and Glân Vraig, Lieutenant Sturla asks you to undertake a dangerous mission for a deadly weapon.",category="Ettenmoors",id=831,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Fangs for Arrows",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Sturla",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nDrakes can be found in Arador's End to the north and east of Lugazag.\nLieutenant Sturla asked you to retrieve drake fangs to assist in the crafting of arrows for the war effort and reinforcement of Lugazag.\n* Speak with Lieutenant Sturla at Lugazag\n* Turn in Wintersebb Drake Fang",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Taur Hith",zone="Lothlórien",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orcs in Fanuidhol have been launching frequent small-scale attacks against the borders of Lórien to test and weaken the resolve of the defenders before they launch a major assault.",mobs={{locations={"11.38S, 70.72W"},name="Raingon"}},category="Lothlórien",id=832,scope="n/a",name="Fanuidhol Skirmish",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,minlevel=60,b="Raingon",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nRaingon is at Talan Gwilith.\nYou should speak with Raingon to prepare the defences for battle.\n* Talk to Raingon\nObj 2:\nRaingon has asked you to defeat the attackers out of Fanuidhol at both Talan Gwilith and Talan Fanuidhol, while protecting the Elven soldiers.\n* Fanuidhol attackers defeated ($VALUE$/30)\nObj 3:\nRaingon is at Talan Gwilith.\nWith the assault turned aside, you should speak with Raingon.\n* Talk to Raingon",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={577},area="Bullroarer's Sward",zone="Evendim",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Locusts are a bane to the livelihood of the oat-farmers of Oatbarton.",mobs={{locations={"23.21S, 66.53W"},name="Nibs Chubb"}},category="Evendim",id=833,scope="n/a",name="Farmers' Bane",arcs="Farmer's Bane",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,minlevel=25,b="Nibs Chubb",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNibs Chubb's fields are east and north-east of his farm.\nNibs Chubb has accepted your offer of aid and has pointed you towards his fields.\n* Defeat swarming locusts\n* Defeat locust-queens\n* Find anything amiss in Nibs Chubb's fields\nObj 2:\nNibs Chubb is at his farm, east of Oatbarton.\nYou should return to Nibs Chubb and tell him of the elk-carcass and the wolf that attacked you.\n* Talk to Nibs Chubb"},
{["next"]={3186},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",d="Eldo Swatmidge is a successful farmer, but he is lonely. He has sought your help to woo his neighbour, the Widow Froghorn.",mobs={{locations={"31.17S, 47.11W"},name="Eldo Swatmidge"},{locations={"31.03S, 49.28W"},name="Himloc Grouse"},{locations={"31.46S, 47.98W"},name="Asphodel Froghorn"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Lesser Athelas Essence",id="70000D5D"},{q="(x3)",val="Lesser Celebrant Salve",id="700005B4"}},category="Bree-land",id=834,scope="n/a",prev={1734},name="Farmer's Market",arcs="Eldo and Asphodel",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Eldo Swatmidge",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Widow Froghorn's farm is on the road west and south of Eldo Swatmidge's farm.\nEldo Swatmidge asked you to collect the produce that Asphodel Froghorn means to sell.\n* Collect produce from Asphodel Froghorn\nObj 2:\nHimloc Grouse can usually be found in the town square of Staddle, west of the Widow Froghorn's farm.\nAsphodel seems to think highly of you and has asked you to sell some of her produce to Himloc Grouse, the trader.\n* Talk to Himloc Grouse\n* Turn in Basket of Vegetables\nObj 3:\nWidow Froghorn's farm is east of Staddle.\nAsphodel Froghorn is waiting for the payment you received from Himloc Grouse for the sale of her vegetables.\n* Talk to Asphodel Froghorn\n* Turn in Produce-payment"},
{money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="The hobbits living in Dwaling will be eager to hear the Northcotton Farmer's Market is open for business.",category="Evendim",id=835,scope="n/a",prev={1545},name="Farmer's Market is Open!",level=31,minlevel=26,b="Albin Northcotton",repeatable="No",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nHob Hillbrow is at Dwaling, north-east of Oatbarton.\nAlbin Northcotton asked you to venture to Dwaling and let them know the farmer's market will be opening early this year.\n* Talk to Hob Hillbrow"},
{area="Bridgefields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Odovacar Bolger is certain the mystery of the trespasser in black will soon be resolved.",mobs={{locations={"31.04S, 65.48W"},name="Odovacar Bolger"},{locations={"31.98S, 63.79W"},name="Fogo Fallohide"},{locations={"31.09S, 65.93W"},name="Greta Fallohide"}},selectoneof={{val="Bolger's Robe",id="700033D7"},{val="Bolger's Leggings",id="700033D6"}},category="Shire",id=836,scope="n/a",prev={570},name="Fate of the Black Rider",arcs="Spectre of the Black Rider",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Odovacar Bolger",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOdovacar Bolger has lent you the services of his hound, Veronica, to track down the mysterious \"Black Rider\". He told you to follow Veronica wherever she lead, and she would find the trespasser.\n* Follow Veronica to the \"Black Rider\"\nObj 2:\nGreta Fallohide is in Budgeford.\nVeronica has led you to Greta Fallohide. Could she be the mysterious \"Black Rider?\"\n* Talk to Greta Fallohide\n* Turn in Black Cloak\nObj 3:\nFogo Fallohide can be found at The Golden Perch in Stock, south-east of Budgeford.\nOdovacar's Bolger's hound, Veronica, led you to Greta Fallohide, who told you she made the cloak for her nephew, Fogo. Fogo Fallohide is very likely the \"Black Rider\". You should seek him out.\n* Talk to Fogo Fallohide\nObj 4:\nOdovacar Bolger can be found at his home in the centre of Budgeford north of his pig sties.\nYou should return to Odovacar Bolger and let him know what you learned about the \"Black Rider.\"\n* Talk to Odovacar Bolger"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Baingaleth has disappeared. She was supposed to meet Carethalph secretly under the shadow of the Hanging Tree but she never showed up. All that he found was a crudely-written note from the Orcs of Dol Guldur.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=837,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Fate Unknown -- Baingaleth",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBaingaleth was taken to the Dungeons of Dol Guldurm.\nCarethalph has asked you to save his love, Baingaleth, quickly before any harm is done to her.\n* Find and rescue Baingaleth",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Bregrochon is gone. Naerdolen lost track of him somewhere in the northern caves when they were attacked by Black Númenóreans. He fears that his long-time friend has been taken to the dungeons of Dol Guldur.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=838,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Fate Unknown -- Bregrochon",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBregrochon is in the Dungeons of Dol Guldur.\nNaerdolen has asked you to find his friend Bregrochon and to save his life.\n* Find and rescue Bregrochon",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Dol Guldur",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Atharnúrel has asked you to find her friend Faelwen. They were revelling in Imlad Lalaith and wandered across the river, seeking to bring mirth to the eaves of Mirkwood. Sadly, a group of uruks came and took her friend, and she fears to return to Imlad Lalaith without her.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=839,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Fate Unknown -- Faelwen",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFaelwen is at the Dungeons of Dol Guldur.\nAtharnúrel has asked you to find her friend Faelwen and rescue her from the uruks of Dol Guldur.\n* Find and rescue Faelwen"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Faenthír is gone. His sister, Puigfinnel, is searching for someone to rescue him. Faenthír is being questioned by the Orcs of Dol Guldur because he was caught sneaking behind their lines.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=840,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Fate Unknown -- Faenthír",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFaenthír is in the Dungeons of Dol Guldur.\nPuigfinnel has asked you to rescue her brother from the dungeons of Dol Guldur.\n* Find and rescue Faenthír",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Dol Guldur",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Agorgened has lost his sweetheart to an ambush by the Orcs of Dol Guldur at the top of a large waterfall.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=841,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Fate Unknown -- Glamrennel",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlamrennel is in the Dungeons of Dol Guldur.\nAgorgened has asked you find and rescue his sweetheart, Glamrennel.\n* Find and rescue Glamrennel"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Laegalar has lost his brother, Hethulír, in the woods of Mirkwood.  They were out searching for rare herbs when they were ambushed by sorcerers.  He has come to the Mourning Well in hopes that someone hears his cries for his lost brother.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=842,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Fate Unknown -- Hethulír",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHethulír is in the Dungeons of Dol Guldur.\nLaegalar has asked you to find Hethulír in the dungeons of Dol Guldur and rescue him.\n* Find and rescue Hethulír",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Maediel has gone missing. Her daughter, Dolhendeth, is worried because lately she has decided to go for long walks in dangerous areas. She is worried that Maediel has been captured and has asked you to bring her back to her.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=843,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Fate Unknown -- Maediel",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMaediel is in the Dungeons of Dol Guldur.\nDolhendeth has asked you to find her mother, Maediel, and rescue her from the evil Black Númenóreans.\n* Find and rescue Maediel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Uiloriel sits in the Haunted Inn trying impossibly to drown her sorrows. Her bethrothed has gone missing. Thimuil went to fetch her more lembas from Lothlórien and never returned.",category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=844,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Fate Unknown -- Thimuil",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThimuil is in the Dungeons of Dol Guldur.\nUiloriel has asked you to look through the dungeons of Dol Guldur for her love Thimuil.\n* Find and rescue Thimuil",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+1200 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Lich Bluffs",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Deep within the forgotten barrows of the Lich Bluffs lies Crug Fernvael, the tomb of Cadelhin's father. His defeat might lead to his people's freedom from an ancient curse.",mobs={{locations={"71.75S, 15.89W"},name="Cadelhin"},{locations={"72.06S, 16.12W"},name="Lhudd"}},category="Enedwaith",id=845,scope="n/a",prev={1833},name="Father of Our Lament",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Cadelhin",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCadelhin is at Crug Cadelhin in the Lich Bluffs.\nYou should talk to Cadelhin when you are ready to travel into Crug Fernvael to confront Cadelhin's father.\nObj 2:\nLhudd is at the Hall of Sanctuary in the Lich Bluffs.\nFollowing Fernvael's defeat, many shades have been released from thier ancient curse. You should return to Lhudd with the news.\n* Talk to Lhudd at the Hall of Sanctuary",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={382},area="Nan Amlug West",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+500 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="16s"}},d="Despite your efforts, the threat of the hendrevail remains as a blight in the hills around Othrikar.",mobs={{locations={"7.21S, 44.92W"},name="Hannar"},{locations={"9.43S, 47.27W"},name="Orthonn"}},category="North Downs",id=846,scope="n/a",prev={9},name="Feathered Foes",arcs="Feathered Foes",level=28,c={"* Talk to Orthonn at [9.4S, 47.3W]\n* Return to Hannar"},minlevel=23,b="Hannar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrthonn is collecting herbs in the Kingsfell, likely at his camp in the ruins of Ost Lagoros north-west of Gatson's farm, some distance south and west of Othrikar.\nHannar explained that his people did not know enough about hendrevail to know how to deal with them, since hunting them did not appear to work. He asked you to go speak with a hunter named Orthonn who might have some insights about the birds.\n* Talk to Orthonn at Ost Lagoros\nObj 2:\nHannar is at Othrikar.\nYou managed to find the Ranger who Hannar sent you to seek, and he suggested you look for the hendroval roosting ground. You should return to Hannar with this information.\n* Talk to Hannar at Othrikar"},
{area="Tirith Rhaw",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Not all who rise to military prominence are capable of complete conversations. Trolls, known for their strength, sometimes manage small words. For instance, Taskmaster Núrsufum. Apparently, Taskmaster Núrsufum likes to place feathers in his helmet and wants you to go about getting the feathers he desires.",category="Tirith Rhaw",id=847,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Feather for His Cap",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Taskmaster Núrsufum",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSun-touched eagles are found throughout the Coldfells and sections of Arador's End.\nTaskmaster Núrsufum wants you to get him tailfeathers for his helm.\n* Return to Taskmaster Núrsufum at Tirith Rhaw ()\n* Turn in Sun-touched Tailfeather",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Rangers of the Grey Company seek to acquire the good will of the Uch-lûth, the Dunlending clan inhabiting Enedwaith.",mobs={{locations={"63.82S, 17.45W"},name="Saeradan"},{locations={"63.81S, 17.47W"},name="Amlan"}},category="Enedwaith",id=848,scope="n/a",name="Feathers for Friendship",pois={{locations={"61.60S, 15.26W","61.55S, 14.89W","61.66S, 15.12W","61.65S, 14.91W","61.60S, 15.14W","61.71S, 15.05W","61.59S, 15.07W","61.75S, 14.97W","61.66S, 15.06W","61.56S, 15.27W","61.76S, 14.94W"},name="Craban-nest"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Amlan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nPristine feathers might be found in the nests of the crebain at Pluvun Gwern, north-east of Echad Saeradan.\nAmlan has asked you to collect pristine feathers to trade to the Algraig of Enedwaith.\n* Use Craban-nest\nObj 2:\nSaeradan is at Echad Saeradan in the Windfells of Enedwaith, south-west of Pluvun Gwern.\nAmlan told you to take the craban-feathers to Saeradan to be prepared for delivery to the Algraig.\n* Talk to Saeradan\n* Turn in Perfect Craban-feather",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={863,106},area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Rangers of the Grey Company are running short of provisions and seek ways to supplement their remaining supplies.",mobs={{locations={"63.83S, 17.47W"},name="Andreg"}},category="Enedwaith",id=849,scope="n/a",name="Feeding the Company",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Andreg",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDun oxen can be found throughout the Windfells.\nAndreg has asked you to hunt the dun oxen of the Windfells for meat. He warned you not to harm the domesticated oxen of the Uch-lûth.\n* Turn in Slab of Wild Ox-meat (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nAndreg is at Echad Saeradan in the Windfells of Enedwaith.\nYou should bring the meat you collected to Andreg.\n* Talk to Andreg\n* Turn in Slab of Wild Ox-meat (Level 1)"},
{area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Rangers of the Grey Company are running short of provisions and seek ways to supplement their remaining supplies.",mobs={{locations={"63.83S, 17.47W"},name="Andreg"}},category="Enedwaith",id=850,scope="n/a",prev={862},name="Feeding the Company -- Repeatable",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Andreg",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDun oxen can be found throughout the Windfells.\nAndreg has asked you to once more hunt the dun oxen of the Windfells, but warned you not to harm the herds of the Uch-lûth.\n* Turn in Slab of Wild Ox-meat (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nAndreg is at Echad Saeradan in the Windfells of Enedwaith.\nYou should bring the ox-meat you collected to Andreg.\n* Talk to Andreg\n* Turn in Slab of Wild Ox-meat (Level 1)"},
{["next"]={300},zone="Evendim",area="Bullroarer's Sward",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="One of the main features of the Northcotton Farmer's Market is its animal petting area.",category="Evendim",id=851,scope="n/a",prev={1503},name="Feeding the Cows",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=31,pois={{locations={"22.94S, 68.34W","23.06S, 68.17W","23.08S, 68.33W","22.98S, 68.37W","23.05S, 68.18W","22.87S, 68.36W","23.07S, 68.26W","23.03S, 68.22W","22.92S, 68.38W","22.86S, 68.22W","22.88S, 68.29W"},name="Bag of Feed"}},minlevel=26,b="Gerard Deephole",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe shrews and feed bags can be found near Gerard Deephole on Northcotton Farm.\nGerard Deephole asked you to gather the feed bags and drive off the shrews stealing from them.\n* Defeat shrews on the Northcotton Farm\n* Collect feed (6 Bag of Feed )\nObj 2:\nThe troughs are at the animal pens on Northcotton Farm.\nThe feed needs to be placed in the feeding troughs for the cows.\n* Use Trough\n* Obj 3:\nGerard Deephole is at the animal pens on Northcotton Farm.\nGerard Deephole will be pleased to hear the troughs have been filled.\n* Talk to Gerard Deephole",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2328},area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Ríki is worried about low supplies for his hungry miners.",mobs={{locations={"9.39N, 81.22W"},name="Ríki"}},category="Forochel",id=852,scope="n/a",name="Feeding the Need",level=47,c={"* Kill Steppe-elk Hart and Steppe-elk Hind around Zigilgund and in Länsi-mâ"},minlevel=42,b="Ríki",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nElk can be found throughout Länsi-mâ.\nRíki has asked you to help restock Zigilgund's stores with Elk-meat.\n* Bring the elk-haunches to Ríki at Zigilgund\n* Turn in Elk-haunch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Gafí, the provisioner of Gondamon, has asked for your help building up their winter stores.",mobs={{locations={"20.24S, 97.14W"},name="Gafí"}},category="Ered Luin",id=853,scope="n/a",name="Feeding the Outpost",arcs="The Garrison of Gondamon",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Gafí",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBears can be found in the wilds around Gondamon, especially to the north.\nGafí has asked you to bring in bear-meat to help fill Gondamon's stores for the coming months.\n* Bring the bear-meat to Gafí in Gondamon\n* Turn in Haunch of Bear-meat",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1894},area="Trestlebridge",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+500 with Men of Bree"}},d="Elsie Woodruff told you that her husband, Mattie, and her brother, Noll, left Trestlebridge in search of trees to fell for the barricades.",mobs={{locations={"17.27S, 53.75W"},name="Elsie Woodruff"}},category="North Downs",id=854,scope="n/a",prev={407},name="Felling Trees",arcs="Bolster the Defences",level=22,minlevel=17,b="Elsie Woodruff",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMattie Woodruff and Noll Tobbit should be found somewhere along the Greenway north out of Trestlebridge.\nElsie told you that she hasn't heard from either her husband Mattie or Noll Tobbit, her brother, since they left and asked you to look for them.\n* Talk to Mattie Woodruff"},
{["next"]={672},reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="Taur Morvith",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Fell spirits drawn into the world by powerful sorcery now haunt the hills of Taur Morvith.",mobs={{locations={"17.96S, 50.30W"},name="Ianudirel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=855,scope="n/a",prev={2486},name="Fell Servants",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=64,minlevel=59,b="Ianudirel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFell spirits gather in the hills south of the river in Taur Morvith.\nIanudirel asked you to banish the fell spirits that are gathering in Taur Morvith.\n* Defeat fell spirits in Taur Morvith (20)\nObj 2:\nIanudirel is hiding in the hills just south of the bridge in Taur Morvith.\nYou should let Ianudirel know that you have done what she asked.\n* Talk to Ianudirel in Taur Morvith",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+900 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="29s 68c"}},d="The very waters of Agamaur have risen up to protect Ivar and the Red-maid, animated by fell spirits of Morgoth from beyond the world.",mobs={{locations={"29.67S, 27.39W"},name="Dannasen"}},category="Garth Agarwen",id=856,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={294},name="Fell Spirits",receive={{val="Emelin's Leggings",id="700006E0"}},level=32,c={"* Gloom-waters can be found the in Garth Agarwen area and near the Garth Agarwen instance entrances.\n* They can also be found inside the instances Garth Agarwen: Arboretum and Garth Agarwen: Fortress."},minlevel=27,b="Dannasen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDarkwater can be found within the area of Garth Agarwen.\nHartrím asked that you assist him in appeasing the spirit at Agamaur, Dannasen, by destroying the fell spirits corrupting the lands within the area of Garth Agarwen.\n* Defeat gloom-waters (30)\nObj 2:\nHartrím can be found at the entrance to the area of Agamaur called Garth Agarwen.\nThe darkwater have the power to strike fear even within the cursed shades of Arthedain, preventing them from advancing on Garth Agarwen and fulfilling their curse. At Hartrim's request, you went forth to destroy them and met with some success. You should return to Hartrím with the report of your victory.\n* Talk to Hartrím"},
{["next"]={2072},area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Among the ruins on the eastern border of the Ashenslades, fell-spirits from beyond the Void have risen and wander the area.",mobs={{locations={"17.48S, 44.56W"},name="Himeinior"}},category="Mirkwood",id=857,scope="n/a",prev={1293},name="Fell the Fallen",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Himeinior",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSâd Doldúr lies to the south of Barad Angol.\nHimeinior has asked you to find and dispatch several fell spirits near Sâd Doldúr and collect tokens of their allegiance.\n* Defeat fell spirits (15)\n* Turn in Ancient Coin\nObj 2:\nHimeinior is at Barad Angol, north and up the mountain from Sâd Doldúr.\nYou should return to Himeinior with the tokens you collected from the fell spirits of Sâd Doldúr.\n* Talk to Himeinior\n* Turn in Ancient Coin"},
{area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="40s 60c"}},d="Silith is part of Gildor Inglorion's company and was sent to keep an eye on Fornost and the defenders of the Council of Esteldín. He is a good friend to Thaliollang and has brought North his hatred for trolls.",mobs={{locations={"8.02S, 56.00W"},name="Silith"}},selectoneof={{val="Troll Ward",id="700161AF"},{val="Longamath",id="70006BF0"}},category="Fornost",id=858,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Fell the Trolls",level=37,c={"* Silith, is located in the Fornost Free Peoples' Camp\n* Jarn-olog Warriors are melee; the trolls named simply Jarn-olog are ranged and will throw stones.\n* The trolls often live or patrol in groups of two. They have a knockback skill which sends the player flying through the air."},minlevel=32,b="Silith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTrolls can be found in Fornost, north of the Fornost camp.\nSilith has asked you to help protect the North Downs from the scourge of Angmar by slaying Angmar's trolls.\n* Defeat trolls (20)\nObj 2:\nSilith is at the Fornost camp, south of Fornost itself.\nSilith will be pleased to learn of your victory against the trolls of Angmar.\n* Talk to Silith"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Fordirith",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Among the fell spirits which have taken form as Shadow-wolves, there is one that is more dangerous than all the rest.",mobs={{locations={"58.69S, 14.56W"},name="Amarion"}},category="Enedwaith",id=859,scope="n/a",prev={198},name="Feral Shadow",arcs="Shadows from Afar",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Amarion",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Fang of Shadows stalks the area outside the Black Dens, south-east of Echad Dagoras.\nAmarion has asked you to hunt the Fang of Shadows, leader of the Shadow-wolves in the Black Dens.\n* Defeat the Fang of Shadows\nObj 2:\nAmarion is at Echad Dagoras, north-west of the Black Dens.\nYou should speak with Amarion and let him know that you have defeated the Fang of Shadows, but that the power of the Black Dens seems unbroken.\n* Talk to Amarion at Echad Dagoras",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2725},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",d="Gailthin the Elf was emissary to the giants in happier days, and she is one of the few who might understand the significance of the tusk-rings you recovered.",mobs={{locations={"20.44S, 97.20W"},name="Gailthin"},{locations={"26.85S, 5.37W"},name="Golhador"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=860,scope="n/a",prev={2474},name="Few Who Dare",arcs="Mighty Giants Indeed",level=43,minlevel=38,b="Golhador",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGailthin is in the dwarf-city of Gondamon, in the low-lands of Ered Luin.\nGolhador has asked you to show the tusk-rings to emissary Gailthin.\n* Talk to Gailthin\n* Turn in Silver Tusk-ring",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Coldfells",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Lieutenant Ingi explained that the Snowreap goblins are the same who inhabit Goblin-town and the bulk of the Misty Mountains. He knows that they are an ally to Angmar and wants to see their numbers culled.",category="Ettenmoors",id=861,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Fiendish Foes",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Ingi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThere are Snowreap-guards and sappers at Grothum, north of Ost Ringdyr.\nLieutenant Ingi wishes to cull the Snowreap goblins from the Ettenmoors and weaken the forces which Angmar can bring to bear agains the Free Peoples.\n* Kill 5 Snowreap Sapper\n* Kill 5 Snowreap Guard\nObj 2:\nIngi is at Ost Ringdyr, south of Grothum.\nWith the goblins dispatched, the time has come to return to Ingi.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Amon Raith",zone="North Downs",money={{val="7s"}},d="Camilla Peake and her husband were driven off their land in Annúndir by the invading Wargs.",selectoneof={{val="Golhathol",id="70006BAF"},{val="Warden of Haudh Eglan",id="700161B8"}},category="North Downs",id=862,scope="n/a",prev={841},name="Fighting Back",level=22,minlevel=17,b="Camilla Peake",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWargs have seized Haudh Eglan, north-east of Amon Raith.\nCamilla Peake has asked you to drive out the Wargs in Annúndir so that she and her husband can return to their farm.\n* Defeat Wargs (16)\nObj 2:\nCamilla Peake is at Amon Raith, west of Annúndir.\nCamilla Peake is waiting for you to return with news that you have defeated the Wargs encroaching on her land.\n* Talk to Camilla Peake"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="43s 12c"}},d="A powerful lizard has been killing dwarf-messengers.",selectoneof={{val="Befuddling Cloak",id="700163C4"},{val="Lizard's Leggings",id="700163D3"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=863,scope="n/a",prev={2713},name="Fighting Slime with Slime",arcs="All Glory",level=56,pois={{locations={"16.70S, 116.84W","16.59S, 116.65W","16.59S, 117.15W","16.72S, 117.09W"},name="Lizard-food"}},minlevel=51,b="Gyrgir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe lizard-food can be found at The Drowned Deep, west of the Rotting Cellar.\nGyrgir says that a powerful lizard, Stonecrest, often feeds on grodbog-corpses. He has crafted a powerful poison to sprinkle on the food. Once Stonecrest eats it, Gyrgir believes you may have a chance to defeat it.\n* Use Lizard-food\n* Turn in Toad-poison\n* Kill 1 Stonecrest\nObj 2:\nGyrgir is in the Rotting Cellar, east of The Drowned Deep.\nGyrgir will be pleased to know his poison worked and that Stonecrest will devour no more dwarves.\n* Talk to Gyrgir\n* Turn in Toad-poison"},
{["next"]={2343},area="North Trollshaws",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Thoroniel has been keeping an eye on the activity of the spiders in the North Trollshaws and has become alarmed at the recent surge in their number.",mobs={{locations={"28.57S, 19.45W"},name="Thoroniel"}},selectoneof={{val="Hunter of Wovenvales",id="70002E2E"},{val="Belegranc",id="70002E2D"}},category="Trollshaws",id=864,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Fighting the Brood",arcs="Fighting the Brood",level=40,minlevel=35,b="Thoroniel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpiders have made their home in the Wovenvales of the North Trollshaws.\nThoroniel has asked you to defeat spiders in the Wovenvales and advised you to bring allies.\n* Defeat spiders in the Wovenvales (10)\nObj 2:\nThoroniel is in the North Trollshaws, just outside the Wovenvales in the north-west corner.\nThoroniel is waiting to hear that you have defeated the spiders that stalk the Wovenvales.\n* Talk to Thoroniel"},
{["next"]={1616},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="The dwarves of the Rotting Cellar camp have many thoughts and ideas about how to best combat the fungus.",selectoneof={{val="Ansurr's Armour",id="700163D7"},{val="Urbhrum's Wall",id="700163EC"},{val="Trinket of Protection",id="70017CE5"},{val="Gyrgir's Bracer",id=70016398}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=865,scope="n/a",prev={2018},name="Fighting the Fungus",arcs="Fighting the Fungus",level=55,minlevel=50,b="Sylfa",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSylfa's dwarves are at the Rotting Cellar.\nSylfa has asked you to assist the other dwarves with their ideas about how to defend against the vile growth.\n* Help Ansurr\n* Help Gyrgir\n* Help Thrand\nObj 2:\nSylfa is in the Rotting Cellar.\nYou should return to Sylfa and inform him you have aided his companions with their ideas.\n* Talk to Sylfa at the Rotting Cellar"},
{money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Fil Gashan is the barracks and training grounds of the Orcs in Moria. Within those walls, a fearsome general has been readying his troops for an assault upon the Elves of Lothlórien to the east of Khazad-dûm. Brogur and Bósi's dwarves, wishing to reclaim Moria, aim to prevent this at any cost, for they would see the Elves and dwarves reinstate old alliances for the good of both.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=866,scope="n/a",name="Fil Gashan - The General's Ring",destinypoints={{val=750}},level=60,minlevel=60,b="Eilíefr",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nGeneral Talug can be found in Fil Gashan, far to the south-west of the Twenty-first Hall.\nThe dwarf Eilíefr has asked you to defeat General Talug to demonstrate your excellence, and return with his ring when you are done.\n* Return the ring to Eilíefr at the Twenty-first Hall\n* Turn in Talug's Ring"},
{money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Fil Gashan is the barracks and training grounds of the Orcs in Moria. Within those walls, a fearsome general has been readying his troops for an assault upon the Elves of Lothlórien to the east of Khazad-dûm. Brogur and Bósi's dwarves, wishing to reclaim Moria, aim to prevent this at any cost, for they would see the Elves and dwarves reinstate old alliances for the good of both.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=867,scope="n/a",name="Fil Gashan - Weaken the War Host",destinypoints={{val=500}},level=60,minlevel=60,b="Geirr",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nFil Gashan is south-west of the Twenty-first Hall.\nThe dwarf Geirr has challenged you to make your way into Fil Gashan and defeat many Orcs therein.\nObj 2:\nThe dwarf Geirr is in the Twenty-first hall, north-east of Fil Gashan\nGeirr will wish to hear if you have been brave enough to enter Fil Gashan and face the Orcs in battle.\n* Return to Geirr at the Twenty-first Hall"},
{["next"]={3182},area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Mírdiniel of the Malledhrim is interested in the Elf-ruins to the north, especially because of their close proximity to Lothlórien. She wishes to recover relics of the Elves who lived there to learn more of them.",category="Mirkwood",id=868,scope="n/a",name="Filth and Riches",arcs="The Treasure Hoard of Dannenglor",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,pois={{locations={"12.08S, 55.23W","11.75S, 54.73W","12.36S, 55.16W","11.72S, 55.08W","11.71S, 54.51W","12.08S, 55.01W","11.85S, 55.23W","12.26S, 54.89W","11.90S, 54.92W","12.10S, 54.72W","11.63S, 54.88W","11.90S, 54.74W"},name="Pile of Treasure"}},minlevel=57,b="Mírdirniel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ruins of Dannenglor are north of the Haunted Inn, in the Dourstocks.\nYou should search the Elf-ruins of Dannenglor for any treasures that might recall the Elves of old.\n* Use Pile of Treasure\nObj 2:\nMírdiniel awaits you in the Haunted Inn, south of Dannenglor.\nYou should speak with Mírdiniel and inform her that there was nothing to be found among the morroval-hoards in Dannenglor.\n* Talk to Mírdiniel at the Haunted Inn"},
{["next"]={2034},area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Cal Sprigley's farm has been overrun by spiders for no apparent reason, leaving Cal and Holly homeless in Archet.",mobs={{locations={"24.93S, 48.88W"},name="Cal Sprigley"},{locations={"24.87S, 48.88W"},name="Atli Spider-bane"}},selectoneof={{val="Atli's Shoulderpads",id="70019BDA"},{val="Atli's Shoulderguards",id="70019BD4"}},category="Bree-land",id=869,scope="n/a",prev={196},name="Finding Reason",arcs="Spider-bane",level=7,c={"* Look for the cocoons on the wall"},pois={{locations={"27.94S, 48.26W"},name="Cocoon"},{locations={"24.85S, 47.93W"},name="Bali"}},minlevel=3,b="Cal Sprigley",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAtli Spider-bane can be found just north of Cal Sprigley.\nCal Sprigley suggested that you speak with Atli Spider-bane about the spiders at his farm and how to be rid of them.\n* Talk to Atli Spider-bane in Archet\nObj 2:\nThe entrance to the cave the hunters blocked off lies in the ruins due east of Archet.\nAtli told you that he sent his cousin Bali to check the caves, but he has not yet returned. If you find him, he may have the answer to what has disturbed the spiders.\n* Search for Bali\nObj 3:\nThe missing pages of Bali's journal must be somewhere within the caves. The spiders may have taken the missing pages and webbed them into their cocoons.\nYou have found Bali's corpse and his journal, but the journal is missing several pages. You need to find the pages before returning to Atli.\n* Use Cocoon\n* Use Cocoon\n* Use Cocoon\n* Use Cocoon\n* Use Cocoon\nObj 4:\nAtli Spider-bane can be found at the north end of Archet.\nAtli Spider-bane will want to know what you discovered among the pages of Bali's journal.\n* Talk to Atli Spider-bane\n* Turn in Bali's Journal\n* Turn in Bali's Journal - page 5\n* Turn in Bali's Journal - page 4\n* Turn in Bali's Journal - page 3\n* Turn in Bali's Journal - page 2\n* Turn in Bali's Journal - page 1"},
{["next"]={2786},area="Bindbole Wood",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Otho is concerned that the spiders infesting his waggon seem to have run off. They may now be a danger elsewhere in the Shire.",mobs={{locations={"31.35S, 71.13W"},name="Shirriff Robin Smallburrow"},{locations={"28.15S, 70.16W"},name="Otho Broadbelt"}},category="Shire",id=870,scope="n/a",prev={2033},name="Finding the Nest",arcs="Spider Plague",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Otho Broadbelt",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRobin Smallburrow can be found at The Ivy Bush Inn in the centre of Hobbiton.\nOtho thinks that the Shirriffs should be made aware of the danger the spiders may pose and has asked you to speak with Robin Smallburrow, the Shirriff in Hobbiton.\n* Talk to Shirriff Robin Smallburrow\nObj 2:\nThere may be spiders in the Bindbole Wood, north and north-west of Overhill.\nOtho Broadbelt sent you to speak with Robin Smallburrow about the spiders, but the Hobbiton Shirriff had already received reports about the creatures in Bindbole Wood. Shirriff Smallburrow has asked you to kill as many of the spiders as you can, but also to find their nest.\n* Defeat spiders (6)\n* Find the spiders' nest\nObj 3:\nRobin Smallburrow can be found in the Ivy Bush in the centre of Hobbiton.\nShirriff Smallburrow sent you to deal with the spider threat in Bindbole Wood and to discover the location of their nest. You should report back to Robin Smallburrow with news of your success.\n* Talk to Shirriff Robin Smallburrow"},
{area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="4s"}},d="Your search for Addie's missing sons found the remains of Amlach Wheatley clutching his brother's journal. The last cryptic entries seem to reveal that Amlach heard fell voices coming from the southern reaches of the Barrow-downs.",mobs={{locations={"32.11S, 53.84W"},name="Addie Wheatley"}},category="Bree-land",id=871,scope="n/a",prev={220},name="Find Malin",arcs="Addie's Missing Sons",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Simple Athelas Essence",id=70001346}},level=20,minlevel=15,b="Addie Wheatley",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe journal you found seemed to indicate that Malin was taken to the southern Barrow-downs to a barrow overlooking an evil mire.\nAddie Wheatley has asked you to search for her other son, Malin.\n* Search for Malin\nObj 2:\nAddie Wheatley awaits your return at the relative safety offered by her guides at the Dead Man's Perch.\nIn your search of the Barrow-downs, you found both of Addie's sons, Amlach and Malin, but far too late to be of any help to either. The foul creatures of the Barrow-downs had killed them both and took Malin's remains for their own. You should return to Addie Wheatley and tell her what has happened to her son.\n* Talk to Addie Wheatley at the Dead Man's Perch"},
{["next"]={1532},area="Redhorn Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="A dwarf named Nykr turned back during a rout because he had dropped a pretty puzzle locket, which cost him his life. His friend Gufi, distraught at this nonsensical choice, wants to know why this trinket was worth dying for.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=872,scope="n/a",prev={3266},name="Finna's Locket",arcs="In His Memory",level=55,minlevel=50,b="Róarr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are many dwarves at the Orc-watch.\nRóarr was surprised at Nykr's passing. While he did not know why his friend valued this little hand-made locket so highly, he suggested you question the other dwarves at The Orc-Watch.\n* Talk to Auti\n* Talk to Knakk\n* Talk to Isólf\n* Talk to Ingifast\n* Talk to Kafli\nObj 2:\nRóarr is in the Orc-Watch.\nRóarr will want to hear of the locket's significance, so that he can relay the information back to Gufi.\n* Talk to Róarr at The Orc-watch"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyl Annûn",money={{val="42s"}},d="The Angmarim are using boats to transport their troops around the ruins and Evendim.",category="Evendim",id=873,scope="n/a",name="Fire and Water",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,pois={{locations={"16.70S, 70.80W","16.54S, 70.80W","16.57S, 70.69W","16.63S, 70.80W","16.52S, 70.77W"},name="Angmarim Boat"}},minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrchalwë wants you to burn the boats at the dock.\n* Use Angmarim Boat\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will want to know the boats have been burned.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Annúminas",money={{val="42s"}},d="The Angmarim keep their stores and supplies in large tents.",category="Evendim",id=874,scope="n/a",name="Fire in the Sky",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,pois={{locations={"17.55S, 68.82W","17.86S, 68.71W"},name="Angmarim Tent"}},minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe two large tents supply the eastern gate forces with supplies.\n* Use Angmarim Tent\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will be pleased to hear the tents are ablaze.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="The descendants of Skorgrím Dourhand have ever been a thorn in the side of Durin's Folk, the Longbeards. Though now outcast, they remain a threat to the Free Peoples of Ered Luin.",category="Reputation",id=875,scope="n/a",name="First Age Relics - Introduction",level=46,c={"* First Age Relics drop from Dourhands in the Icereave Mines and everything in Sarnúr"},minlevel=41,b="Ásgeir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSarnúr lies south of Thorin's Hall and west of Noglond in the ruins of Orodost.\nÁsgeir has asked you to enter the Dourhand stronghold of Sarnúr and defeat the creatures who dwell there, claiming First Age relics for the dwarves of Thorin's Hall.\n* Bring the First Age Relic to Ásgeir\n* Turn in First Age Relic",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Dar-gazag",zone="Ettenmoors",d="First Marshals stand only behind the Captain-General in rank amongst the enemy army. Chieftain Durulkum wants their marks of rank to further the favour this war-host gains with Angmar, Mordirith, and Lugbúrz.",category="Ettenmoors",id=876,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=750}},name="First Marshals' Marks",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Chieftain Durulkum",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nFirst Marshals can only be found in towers and keeps claimed by the enemy.\nChieftain Durulkum at Dâr-gazag informed you that the marks borne by the First Marshals of the enemy army gain great favour with Mordirith in Angmar.\n* Return to Chieftain Durulkum at Dâr-gazag ()\n* Turn in First Marshal's Mark",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="The Angmarim have driven polar bears into the fishing-grounds of the Lossoth.",mobs={{locations={"17.49N, 64.50W"},name="Olavi"}},category="Forochel",id=877,scope="n/a",name="Fisherman's Foe",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Flounder Fillet",id="7000E8D4"}},level=48,c={"* The buckets are at the edge of the east side of the lake south of Sûri-kylä"},minlevel=43,b="Olavi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOlavi's fish-buckets can be found south-west of his camp along the Ice Bay.\nFearing the bears, Olavi has asked you to retrieve his fish-buckets from the fishing-grounds.\nObj 2:\nOlavi is at his fishing camp east of Sûri-kylä along the road in Jä-rannit.\nYou should bring the fish-buckets you recovered to Olavi.\n* Bring the fish buckets to Olavi\n* Turn in Bucket (Level 1)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="In his haste to escape the Angmarim, Olavi dropped his fishing-pole.",mobs={{locations={"17.49N, 64.50W"},name="Olavi"}},category="Forochel",id=878,scope="n/a",name="Fisherman's Friend",receive={{val="Fisherman's Shirt and Waders",id="7000DA4A"}},level=48,c={"* Kill any Angmarim along the shore of the Ice Bay"},minlevel=43,b="Olavi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are Angmarim along the shore of the Ice Bay, southwest of Olavi's camp along the bay.\nOlavi has asked you to recover his fishing-pole from the Angmarim.\n* Turn in Fishing-rod\nObj 2:\nOlavi is at his camp along the road in Jä-rannit.\nYou have recovered Olavi's fishing-pole and should return it to him at once.\n* Talk to Olavi\n* Turn in Fishing-rod",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Vale of Thrain",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Refkell is incredibly proud of his last catch and wishes to show it off to his friend.",mobs={{locations={"19.73S, 100.45W"},name="Nokki"}},category="Special",id=879,scope="n/a",name="Fish-tales",level=5,minlevel=1,b="Refkell",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nNoglond is south of Thorin's Hall, south and east of the Vale of Thrain, along the road to the Low Lands.\nRefkell has asked that you visit Nokki and tell him of his latest catch.\n* Talk to Nokki",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Falco confided that he was originally pressured by a man named Jasper Mudbottom. Mudbottom is a powerful brigand located at the Yellow Tree ruins, south beyond the Staddle farms.",mobs={{locations={"31.45S, 48.60W"},name="Falco Greenhand"}},selectoneof={{val="Mudbottom's Bane",id="70006B96"},{val="Falco's Smasher",id="70006BE5"},{val="Falco's Helmet",id="70006AD5"},{val="Falco's Hammer",id="70006BA9"},{val="Falco's Shirt",id="70006B3F"}},category="Bree-land",id=880,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={831},name="Fixing Falco's Folly",arcs="Falco's Garden",receive={{val="Falco's Earring",id="700069F4"}},level=14,c={"* Jasper Mudbottom is found inside Ost Baranor south of Staddle. [33.7S, 48.6W]"},minlevel=10,b="Falco Greenhand",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nJasper Mudbottom is at the brigand encampment at Ost Baranor, south of the Staddle farms.\nFalco Greenhand has asked you to put a stop to the Blackwold brigand, Jasper Mudbottom. He suggested you take friends.\n* Defeat Jasper Mudbottom\nObj 2:\nFalco Greenhand is at his farm in Staddle, north of Ost Baranor.\nYou should return to Falco Greenhand with news of your victory over Jasper Mudbottom.\n* Talk to Falco Greenhand at his farm"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Flying the flags of the Free Peoples at Tol Ascarnen gives hope to those entrenched in the battle. Each time the fortress is taken, the flags are destroyed by the Enemy and they must be remade.",category="Ettenmoors",id=881,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Flags of The Free Peoples",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Quartermaster Cynwiss",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThistledown-aurochs can be found throughout the Ettenmoors.\nQuartermaster Cynwiss asked you to assist her in collecting hides to craft the flags of the Free Peoples in the Ettenmoors.\n* Return to Quartermaster Cynwiss at Tol Ascarnen\n* Turn in Thistledown Hide",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2550},reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="Geirfast has identified the small cave described in the map and will send the wondrous torch you have assembled to it while you find an ally or two.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=882,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={251},name="Flame and Shadow",arcs="Shadow Map",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Geirfast",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGeirfast is in the Twenty-first Hall.\nYou should speak with Geirfast again when you are prepared to travel to the strange cave.\n* Talk to Geirfast at the Twenty-first Hall\nObj 2:\nGeirfast is at the Twenty-first Hall.\nYou should return to Geirfast and tell him of the strange map you saw projected on the wall by the light of the torch.\n* Talk to Geirfast at the Twenty-first Hall"},
{["next"]={2367},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 60c"}},d="Paladin Took is certain that a band of brigands stole Hyacinth's fireworks and is planning to use them for harmful purposes.",mobs={{locations={"33.60S, 71.13W","33.61S, 71.13W"},name="Thain Paladin Took II"}},selectoneof={{val="Hammer of the Tooks",id="70000DAA"},{val="Paladin's Spear",id="70000DA9"},{val="Firework Starter",id="70000DA8"}},category="Shire",id=883,scope="n/a",prev={471},name="Flare For Danger",arcs="Lobelia's Fireworks",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=11,pois={{locations={"35.50S, 66.92W"},name="Fireworks-crate"}},minlevel=7,b="Thain Paladin Took II",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe brigand encampment is at Narrowcleeve, the heights in the south-west part of the Marish, not far from Woodhall. You can enter the camp by crossing a ford near the brink of a waterfall.\nShirriff Robin Smallburrow sent you to speak with Paladin Took, the Thain of the Shire, about Hyacinth's stolen fireworks. The Thain suggested that they may have been stolen by a band of ruffians camped in the Marish and sent you to destroy the fireworks.\n* Use Fireworks-crate\nObj 2:\nThe Thain is at the Great Smials in Tuckborough.\nThe Thain, Paladin Took, sent you to destroy Hyacinth Took's stolen fireworks at a brigand encampment. With victory in hand, you should return to the Thain at once.\n* Talk to Thain Paladin Took II"},
{area="Tirith Rhaw",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Soldier Fandmau fears reprisal for the assault of Tirith Rhaw and wants you to attack the Free Peoples quickly before they retaliate.",category="Tirith Rhaw",id=884,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Flay the Free Peoples",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Fandmau",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nDefenders of the Free Peoples can be found throughout the Ettenmoors.\nSoldier Fandmau directed you to slaughter the defenders loyal to the Free Peoples.\nObj 2:\nSoldier Fandmau is at Tirith Rhaw.\nYou found and slaughtered a good number of the enemy.\n* Return to Soldier Fandmau at Tirith Rhaw ()",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
