lect butterbur (5 Butterbur )"},
{area="Vale of Thrain",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Óláfr needs help dealing with the lynx in Thrain's Vale.",mobs={{locations={"19.36S, 100.48W"},name="Óláfr"}},selectoneof={{val="Lynx-Pelt Trousers",id="70019C37"},{val="Lynx-Pelt Leggings",id="70019C34"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1070,scope="n/a",name="Herding Cats",arcs="The Garrison of Gondamon",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Óláfr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLynx can be found throughout the Vale of Thráin, but Óláfr suggested heading north to the Thrushstones.\nÓláfr has asked you to secure the safety of the road leading through the Vale of Thráin by hunting the lynx that dwell there.\n* Defeat lynx in the Vale of Thrain (10)\nObj 2:\nÓláfr is at Noglond in Thrain's Vale, south along the road from the Thrushstones.\nÓláfr should be pleased to hear of your success.\n* Talk to Óláfr at Noglond"},
{area="Kingsfell",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="11s 50c"}},d="You discovered a stone marker in the midst of a barren, but fertile land. The marker declared the surrounding land to be the property of Bardulf Gilmar and his heirs. If any such heirs yet live, it is unlikely that they know of their legacy.",mobs={{locations={"9.43S, 47.27W"},name="Orthonn"},{locations={"10.31S, 45.62W"},name="Gilmar"},{locations={"9.61S, 41.05W"},name="Istuienn"}},category="North Downs",id=1071,scope="n/a",name="Heritage of Gilmar",receive={{val="Gilmar's Robe",id=70001856}},level=25,minlevel=20,b="Stone Marker",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAn heir to Bardulf Gilmar may yet be found somewhere in the North Downs.\n* Talk to Gilmar at Gatson's Farm\nObj 2:\nOrthonn is at the ruins of Ost Lagoros, west of Gatson's Farm.\nYou found a stone marker bequeathing land to the forebear of Gatson's workhand, Gilmar. Gilmar has asked you to ask the Ranger Orthonn about his forebear.\n* Talk to Orthonn at Ost Lagoros\nObj 3:\nIstuienn is at Esteldín, east of Gatson's farm.\nYou found a stone marker bequeathing land to the forebear of Gatson's workhand, Gilmar. Gilmar sent you to speak to the Ranger Orthonn, but Orthonn was unable to help. He did, however, suggest you seek Istuienn, the archivist at Esteldín.\n* Talk to Istuienn at Esteldín\nObj 4:\nGilmar is at Gatson's farm.\nIstuienn, who keeps the Rangers' archives, provided you an excerpt of some old chronicles explaining how Gilmar's ancestor saved the life of Eärnur, an ancient Prince of Gondor, and was granted land in perpetuity for his valour.\n* Talk to Gilmar\n* Turn in Chronicle Excerpt",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nan Amlug East",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="When First Hunter Jarkko betrayed the Suuri-lehmä, he left with the totem of the tribe's hunter; the skull of the Great Aurochs -- the namesake of the Suuri-lehmä. You brought a totem skull to Ragnarr, but it appears that it is not sufficient.",mobs={{locations={"9.31S, 39.91W"},name="Ragnarr Hornsounder"}},selectoneof={{val="Threk-klath",id="700018A7"},{val="Hornsounder's Hammer",id="700018A9"},{val="Ellos",id="700018AB"},{val="Lothrinn",id="700018A8"},{val="Hornsounder's Head",id="700018AA"}},category="North Downs",id=1072,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={200},name="Heritage Restored",arcs="Common Blood",level=31,minlevel=26,b="Ragnarr Hornsounder",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe skull of The Great Aurochs is being held in the lands of the Rauta-lehmä, eastward across Nan Amlug.\nIn order to prove his benign intent to the Earth-kin, Ragnarr Hornsounder has asked you to retrieve the stolen skull of The Great Aurochs from the Rauta-lehmä. He suggested taking allies.\n* Collect the skull of the Great Aurochs\nObj 2:\nRagnarr Hornsounder is at the camp of the Suuri-lehmä, west of the Rauta-lehmä camp.\nYou should return the skull of the Great Aurochs to Ragnarr Hornsounder.\n* Talk to Ragnarr Hornsounder"},
{d="The gredbyg of Skûmfil are a vile breed of scavengers, and among them are terrible warrior-class insects.",category="Champion",id=1073,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1007},name="Heroics",arcs="The Path of the Martial Champion",receive={{val="Bracelet of Triumph",id=70018387},{val="Khuzdul Tablets",id="70017AC6"}},level=58,minlevel=58,b="Valthor",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLongpincer is in Skûmfil, east of the Shadowed Refuge in the Foundations of Stone.\nValthor has asked you to complete the Path of the Martial Champion by slaying the grodbog Longpincer.\n* Use Ancient Altar\n* Defeat Longpincer\nObj 2:\nValthor is at the Shadowed Refuge in the Foundations of Stone, west from Skûmfil.\nYou should return to Valthor with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Valthor\n* Turn in Meat Infused with a Foul Scent",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="You helped all the members of the Lost Fellowship in all of their various needs.",mobs={{locations={"3.00N, 58.07W"},name="Cenlieg"},{locations={"11.37N, 69.82W"},name="Déornyd"},{locations={"7.44N, 75.46W"},name="Burgthryth"},{locations={"19.44N, 71.31W"},name="Nef"},{locations={"19.35N, 83.76W"},name="Thurmaer"},{locations={"19.11N, 70.79W"},name="Reginald Ward"},{locations={"9.30N, 81.06W"},name="Warstang"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Bag of Weak Blasting Powder",id="7000E964"},{q="(x5)",val="Battered Horn",id="7000E961"},{q="(x5)",val="Battle Ward",id="7000E968"},{q="(x5)",val="Thick Leather Overshoes",id="7000E965"},{q="(x5)",val="Simple Rally Horn (Store)",id="7000E962"},{q="(x5)",val="Small Trap",id="7000E967"},{q="(x5)",val="Basic Theatre: Lesson",id="7000E963"}},category="Forochel",id=1074,scope="n/a",prev={2466},name="Hero of the Lost",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Nef",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nReginald Ward can be found in Sûri-kylä in Forochel.\nYou were instructed to seek out the captain of the Lost Fellowship, Reginald Ward.\n* Talk to Reginald Ward"},
{area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+900 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="Vämmä fears that a new war-leader may have risen amongst the Gauredain who may bring them into battle in great numbers.",mobs={{locations={"19.54N, 71.99W"},name="Vämmä"}},selectoneof={{val="Vämmä's Sword",id="7000E5DC"},{val="Vämmä's Medium Shield",id="700161E3"},{val="Vämmä's Heavy Shield",id="7000E6E9"},{val="Vämmä's Shield",id="7000E6EA"}},category="Forochel",id=1075,scope="n/a",prev={1125},name="He Who Leads",level=49,c={"* Nadelek can be found in Barad Gaurhoth at [11.5N, 82.5W]"},minlevel=44,b="Vämmä",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNadelek dwells somewhere within Barad Gaurhoth.\nVämmä has asked you to seek out the Gauradan war-leader, Nadelek, and defeat him.\n* Defeat Nadelek\nObj 2:\nWith Nadelek defeated, you should return to Vämmä in Sûri-kylä and tell him of your victory.\n* Talk to Vämmä"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Dardúr will aid you in hewing a rune-stone of great cunning.",mobs={{locations={"20.10S, 96.82W"},name="Dardúr"}},selectoneof={{val="Warm Touch-stone",id="70017D9A"},{val="Cold Touch-stone",id="70017D9B"}},category="Rune-keeper",id=1076,scope="n/a",requiredclasses="Rune-keeper",name="Hewing a New Stone",arcs="Learned in Letters",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Dardúr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe stones can be found among the goblins of Goblin-town. The runic inscription is held by Ánraig, east of Gwaelband in the ruins of Annúminas.\nDardúr wishes you to bring the stones from the roots of the Misty Mountains and a runic inscription held by an Angmarim archivist named Ánraig.\n* Bring the collected items to Dardúr at Gondamon in Ered Luin\n* Turn in Misty Mountain Stone\n* Turn in Archivist Ánraig's Runes\nObj 2:\nNerbeglir can be found in Mallenhad in Angmar. Wargs can be found in Angmar, the Misty Mountains, and Forochel.\nDardúr now requires Neekerbreeker-horns and hooked Warg-claws.\n* Bring the collected items to Dardúr at Gondamon in Ered Luin\n* Turn in Corroded Neekerbreeker Horn\n* Turn in Hooked Warg Claw\nObj 3:\nGruglok may be found at Urugarth in Angmar. Azgoth and Mormoz may be found at Carn Dûm in Angmar.\nDardúr now needs Gruglok's Sigil of War and a Rune of Winged Dominance.\n* Bring the collected items to Dardúr at Gondamon in Ered Luin\n* Turn in Sigil of War\n* Turn in Rune of Winged Dominance"},
{["next"]={768},area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Fernachar has asked you to defeat many merrevail in pursuit of the Malledhrim scouts who have been waylaid at Dannenglor.",category="Mirkwood",id=1077,scope="n/a",prev={2465},name="Hewing Fell Wings",arcs="The Lost Explorers",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,minlevel=57,b="Fernachar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMerrevail can be found in the Elf-ruins of Dannenglor, north of the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks.\nYou should fight the merrevail in pursuit of the Malledhrim Elves who were most likely waylaid at the gates of Dannenglor.\n* Defeat merrevail at Dannenglor (10)\nObj 2:\nFernachar awaits you anxiously at the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks, south of Dannenglor.\nYou should return swiftly to Fernachar and inform him of your relative success against the merrevail of Dannenglor.\n* Talk to Fernachar at the Haunted Inn"},
{area="Northern Emyn Uial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="Longbough believes that some evil power may be twisting the wood to dark ends, perhaps the Wood-trolls that have begun to appear in Evendim. Roused to anger, the Ent is ready to take action.",mobs={{locations={"6.12S, 71.92W"},name="Erchiel"}},category="Evendim",id=1078,scope="n/a",name="Hewing the Wood",arcs="Twisted Forest",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=37,c={"* 21"},minlevel=32,b="Erchiel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Twisted Grove lies to the south-west of the Eavespires.\nAngered by the wanton ruin inflicted upon his grove, Longbough has asked you to defeat the Wood-trolls infesting the Twisted Grove.\n* Defeat Barkskin Wood-trolls\n* Defeat Rotting Wood-trolls\nObj 2:\nHeart-rot is at the Twisted Grove, which lies southwest of the Eavespires.\nAs well as driving the Wood-trolls from his grove, Erchiel also asked you to find and defeat their leader, Heart-rot, in hopes that the remnant will flee.\n* Find and defeat Heart-rot\nObj 3:\nErcheil is at the Eavespires, on the northwest shore of Lake Evendim.\nYou should return to the Eavespires and tell Erchiel of your battle with Heart-rot.\n* Talk to Erchiel"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Malthenor is concerned about the bears that prowl the mountains and wants you to fight against them in many areas.",mobs={{locations={"26.81S, 5.43W"},name="Malthenor"}},selectoneof={{val="Halthol",id="70006B3D"},{val="Malthenor's Shoulder Guards",id="70006AFE"},{val="Hunter of the Mountains",id="70006AB8"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1079,scope="n/a",prev={1775},name="Hidden by Fur and Snow",arcs="Dangers in the High Passes",level=44,minlevel=39,b="Malthenor",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBears are found throughout the Misty Mountains: near the Bruinen Source, by the High Crags, and close to the Giant Halls.\nMalthenor has asked you to defeat bears in many areas throughout the mountains to lessen the threat they pose to potential travellers.\n* Defeat bears near Bruinen source (7)\n* Defeat bears near High Crags (7)\n* Defeat bears near Giant Halls (7)\nObj 2:\nMalthenor is north of Rivendell, in the pass that winds into the mountains.\nMalthenor will be pleased to hear that you have defeated many bears throughout the mountains.\n* Talk to Malthenor"},
{["next"]={2541},area="Gorothlad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Bothwar has told you the location of a cache of gems he was unable to retrieve before he was assigned his current duty in Gabilshathûr.",category="Angmar",id=1080,scope="n/a",prev={3269},name="Hidden Gems",arcs="Prospector of Angmar",level=47,pois={{locations={"1.45S, 21.61W","1.99S, 21.31W"},name="Gem-hoard"}},minlevel=42,b="Bothwar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe gem-hoard is near the cave-claw nests within Dolroth in southern Gorothlad, north and east of Gabilshathûr.\nThe dwarf-miner Bothwar has asked you to retrieve a hoard of gems for him.\n* Bring the gemstone-hoard to Bothwar\n* Collect the gemstone-hoard"},
{["next"]={1036},reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="You discovered a woman's axe among the ruin at Balin's camp. The dwarves believe this points to a women's quarters somewhere in Moria.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1081,scope="n/a",prev={56},name="Hidden Quarters",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Kafli",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe women's quarters are near the Chittering Hole, south-east of the Orc-watch.\nAccording to what he saw on the axe, Kafli believes the women's quarters are located in the Redhorn Lodes, near the gredbyg colony called the Chittering Hole.\n* Find the women's quarters\nObj 2:\nKafli is at the Orc-watch, north-west of the Chittering Hole.\nKafli will be pleased to hear you found the women's quarters.\n* Talk to Kafli at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2603},area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Rollo Newbuck has been asked to play Hiders and Seekers with his friends, Daisy and Polo Brockhouse, but their unimaginative hiding places have made him lose interest in the game.",mobs={{locations={"33.81S, 74.99W"},name="Polo Brockhouse"},{locations={"33.40S, 75.03W"},name="Rollo Newbuck"},{locations={"34.22S, 74.72W"},name="Daisy Brockhouse"}},category="Shire",id=1082,scope="n/a",name="Hiders and Seekers",arcs="Hiders and Seekers",level=6,minlevel=2,b="Rollo Newbuck",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nPolo Brockhouse is hiding behind the carved wooden statue of Marcho and Blanco in the centre of Michel Delving. His sister Daisy is hiding south-east of the carving, in the bushes to the right of Peony Grubb's home.\nRollo Newbuck is playing Hiders and Seekers with his friends, but they always hide in the same places, and he is tired of pretending to be surprised every time he finds them.\n* Find Polo Brockhouse\n* Find Daisy Brockhouse\nObj 2:\nRollo Newbuck is north of the carved statue of Marcho and Blanco at the centre of Michel Delving, within the circle of hedges that surround Town Hole.\nRollo is waiting to hear that you found Polo and Daisy Brockhouse.\n* Talk to Rollo Newbuck",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyrn Fornech",money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Bear-hides make for warm winter blankets, keeping the wind from chilling your bones.",mobs={{locations={"7.33S, 64.25W"},name="Rowena Parker"}},category="Evendim",id=1083,scope="n/a",name="Hides for Blankets",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=35,minlevel=30,b="Rowena Parker",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nNan Orngon is south-east of Ost Forod.\nRowena Parker asked you to venture to Nan Orngon and bring back several bear hides to be turned into blankets.\n* Turn in Bear Hide\nObj 2:\nOst Forod is west of Nan Orngon.\nRowena Parker will want to begin turning the hides into blankets.\n* Talk to Rowena Parker\n* Turn in Bear Hide",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tâl Caradhras",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="By examining the charred wood you brought her, Ruidhriel has discovered that a great battle took place upon the Burnt Tor.",mobs={{locations={"49.10S, 9.34W"},name="Ruidhriel"}},selectoneof={{val="Token of the Burnt Tor",id="700163B3"},{val="Ruidhriel's Shoulder Pads",id="7001607F"}},category="Eregion",id=1084,scope="n/a",prev={2015},name="Hiding Their Passage",arcs="Hiding Their Passage",level=50,c={"* The Hobbit Handkerchief is at [49.0S, 10.1W]\n* The Strange Branch is at [49.1S, 10.4W]\n* The Spent Arrow is at [49.1S, 10.6W]"},pois={{locations={"49.06S, 10.37W"},name="Strange Branch"},{locations={"49.10S, 10.56W"},name="Spent Arrow"},{locations={"48.97S, 10.09W"},name="Hobbit handkerchief"}},minlevel=45,b="Ruidhriel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe remains of the battle are scattered across the Burnt Tor, west of Ruidhriel.\nRuidhriel has asked you to find any remains of the battle that occurred upon the Burnt Tor and hide them.\n* Talk to Ruidhriel\n* Collect the handkerchief\n* Collect the strange branch\n* Collect spent arrow"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Barandalf",money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Crawlers like to bury themselves beneath rocks.",category="Evendim",id=1085,scope="n/a",name="Hiding Underfoot",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=32,pois={{locations={"15.87S, 61.74W","15.63S, 61.70W","15.63S, 61.66W","15.73S, 61.78W","15.75S, 61.81W","15.85S, 61.67W","15.92S, 61.76W","15.86S, 61.83W","15.67S, 61.75W","15.92S, 61.82W"},name="Small Rock"}},minlevel=27,b="Herthdúr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLithost is south of the Colossus, on the west bank of the Baranduin.\nHerthdúr asked you to go to Lithost, flip over some rocks, and defeat the crawlers you find.\n* Use Small Rock\n* Flip over rocks and defeat the crawlers beneath\nObj 2:\nHerthdúr is at the Colossus camp, north of Lithost.\nHerthdúr will be pleased to hear the crawlers' population has been reduced.\n* Talk to Herthdúr",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={3187},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Hillmen from Angmar followed the Orc army through Ram Dúath into the North Downs and established an encampment near the head of the pass. These Hillmen serve to keep open the passage from Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.63S, 41.42W"},name="Arohir"}},category="North Downs",id=1086,scope="n/a",prev={1923},name="Hillmen of the North",arcs="Hillmen of the North",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Arohir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Hillmen are encamped near the mouth of the eastern entrance to Ram Dúath, north-east of Esteldín.\nArohir has asked you to infiltrate the Hillman encampment and collect some of the brooches the Hillmen wear as badges of rank, so that he might determine the composition of their forces.\n* Bring the brooches back to Arohir\n* Turn in Angmarim-brooch"},
{["next"]={233},area="Nimrodel",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Maethoron is worried about the growing number of Orc-waylayers on the road that runs through Nanduhirion toward Lothlórien.",mobs={{locations={"16.24S, 73.45W"},name="Maethoron"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1087,scope="n/a",prev={636},name="Hinder the Orc-schemes",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Maethoron",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrc waylayers can be found all along the road that runs through Nanduhirion, north-west of Talan Haldir.\nMaethoron has asked you to waylay the waylayers in Nanduhirion so that the road may be made safe.\n* Defeat Orc waylayers in Nanduhirion\nObj 2:\nMaethoron is on Talan Haldir, near the banks of Nimrodel, south-east of Nanduhirion.\nYou have defeated many of the Orc Waylayers that make travel on the road through Nanduhirion difficult, and should report of your success to Maethoron.\n* Talk to Maethoron"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Skûmfil is nothing more than a dumping ground, a place where the fallen Orcs of Moria are discarded when they begin to reek. It is here that two foes have gathered, each intent on using the corpses found therein for their own purposes. The kergrim and other scavengers as a source of food, and the insects as a place to lay their eggs to spawn future generations.",mobs={{locations={"13.16S, 101.23W"},name="Moggi"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1088,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Hive Mind",arcs="Skumfíl",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Moggi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSkûmfil lies to the south-east of the Shadowed Refuge.\nMoggi sent you to Skûmfil to destroy the warrior-gredbyg there who have some manner of independence from the queen Brúmbereth. The chief of these is Uammaethor.\n* Defeat Uammaethor\n* Defeat Nestaduan\n* Defeat Grog\n* Defeat Grothulun\n* Defeat Ulugon\nObj 2:\nMoggi is at the Shadowed Refuge, north-west of Skûmfil.\nYou found and kill the grodbog-warrior Uammaethor and its defenders within the corpse-ridden place called Skûmfil.\n* Talk to Moggi at the Shadowed Refuge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Coldfells",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Emissary Pip Diggins of Hoarhallow told you a tale of woe concerning the destruction wrought on his village by the Snowreap-goblins far to the north-east of Hoarhallow.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1089,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Hoarhallow's Dwindling Food",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Emissary Pip Diggins",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblin-village of Grothum lies far to the north-east of Hoarhallow.\nEmissary Pip Diggins asked you to recover food stolen from Hoarhallow. He directed you to search among the goblin village at Grothum or on the persons of the enemy.\n* Deliver the food-sacks to Emissary Pip Diggins at Ost Ringdyr\n* Turn in Food Sack",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={682},area="Nanduhirion",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+300 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="With the ranks of the invading Orcs thinned, it is now time to strike against their leadership, hobbling their communication and throwing their forces into chaos.",category="Moria",id=1090,scope="n/a",prev={1068},name="Hobble the Leadership",arcs="Out of the Mines",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Raskwith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMoria Orc-emissaries can be found at Uruk-gashan, Drû-garmadh, and Athmadhul.\nRaskwith asked to go to the three Orc-camps in the Dimrill Dale and defeat the three Moria Orc-emissaries.\n* Defeat the Orc-emissary at Uruk-gashan\n* Defeat the Orc-emissary at Drû-garmadh\n* Defeat the Orc-emissary at Athmadhul\nObj 2:\nRaskwith is at Mekhem-bizru, north-west of the Orc-camps.\nRaskwith will be pleased to hear the Moria Orc-emissaries have been defeated.\n* Talk to Raskwith at Mekhem-bizru"},
{["next"]={1456},area="Bullroarer's Sward",zone="Evendim",money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Bob Greeneaves believes he has discovered the plans of the goblins.",category="Evendim",id=1091,scope="n/a",prev={2411},name="Hobgoblin's Recipe",arcs="Hobgoblin's Recipe",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=32,pois={{locations={"22.46S, 64.00W","22.19S, 63.78W","22.52S, 64.01W","22.43S, 64.10W","22.34S, 64.26W","22.17S, 64.00W","22.24S, 64.23W","22.14S, 64.15W","22.40S, 63.95W","22.39S, 63.85W","22.28S, 63.97W","22.46S, 64.28W"},name="Bubbling Pot"}},minlevel=27,b="Bob Greeneaves",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblin-camp is in the Bleakleaf Crest, south of Dwaling.\nBob Greeneaves wants you to burn the pots the goblins are using to cook down the spiders, as well as recover the recipe for their tar.\n* Turn in Hobgoblins' Recipe\n* Use Bubbling Pot\nObj 2:\nBob Greeneaves is in Dwaling, north of the Bleakleaf Crest.\nYou should return to Bob Greeneaves with the news of your success.\n* Talk to Bob Greeneaves\n* Turn in Hobgoblins' Recipe"},
{area="The Flaming Deeps",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="The bridge is ready to be repaired, but the dwarves making the repairs will need to be protected from attack.",selectoneof={{val="Ulfied's Staff",id=70016421},{val="Regin's Gloves",id="700163E6"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1092,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Hold the Line",arcs="Jury Rigged",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Ulfied",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRegin is below the southern bridge out of The Crossroads of Ash to the south-west of Anzârmekhem.\nUlfied asked you to go and watch over Regin, the dwarf making the repairs to the bridge, fearing he may be attacked by the creatures of the Flaming Deeps.\n* Talk to Regin below the southern bridge out of The Crossroads of Ash\nObj 2:\nUlfied is in Anzârmekhem, north-east of The Crossroads of Ash.\nUlfied will want to hear that the repairs were succesfully made, Regin is safe, and the bridge should stand for many years to come, with care.\n* Talk to Ulfied in Anzârmekhem"},
{area="Arador's End",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Taskmaster Bárzqhosh is preparing the defence of the Isendeep Mine against the Free Peoples.",category="Isendeep Mine",id=1093,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Hold the Mine",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Taskmaster Bárzqhosh",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nFight off invaders who meant to take the Isendeep mine.\nYou must fight the foe within the Isendeep mine and drive them out for the glory of Angmar.\n* Defeat Free Peoples in the Isendeep Mine (30 at Isendeep )\nObj 2:\nIf the mine is fallen or Taskmaster Bárzqhosh is fallen in the battle, make your way to Gramsfoot and speak with War-tyrant Akúlhun.\nYour success is complete. Return to Taskmaster Bárzqhosh and tell him of your victory.\n* Talk to Taskmaster Bárzqhosh\n* Talk to War-tyrant Akúlhun",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1488},area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="While holly-berries are generally considered to be poisonous, holly-leaves are often used in the brewing of tea.",mobs={{locations={"40.04S, 16.00W"},name="Celebrandir"}},category="Eregion",id=1094,scope="n/a",name="Holly-leaf Tea",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Cup of Red Tea",id="7001549C"}},level=48,pois={{locations={"42.44S, 13.11W","42.36S, 12.97W","42.09S, 13.48W","41.44S, 16.29W","42.07S, 15.80W","42.33S, 15.84W","41.70S, 16.75W","41.90S, 16.37W","42.72S, 13.66W","42.58S, 13.39W","42.07S, 16.33W","42.34S, 13.87W","41.66S, 16.03W","42.42S, 13.92W","41.43S, 16.94W","42.18S, 13.36W","42.74S, 13.84W","41.60S, 16.14W","42.10S, 12.90W","42.42S, 13.30W","42.23S, 13.12W","41.67S, 16.99W"},name="Green Holly-leaf"}},minlevel=43,b="Green Holly Tree Branch",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHolly-trees can be found throughout Glâd Ereg. Celebrandir is encamped at Gwingris in the northern reaches of Glâd Ereg.\nYou should gather more holly-leaves and bring them to the Elf Celebrandir.\n* Bring the holly-leaves to Celebrandir in Gwingris\n* Collect holly-leaves (8 Green Holly-leaf ).",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Ered Luin",area="Falathlorn",d="With the rumours of war, the encroaching enemy driving the inhabitants out of the rural areas of Eriador, and further strife drawing settlers up from the southern lands, smaller communities are springing up in the North. An agent you encountered has suggested you might take the opportunity to purchase your own home by speaking to one of the brokers that can be found near the major communities throughout Eriador.",mobs={{locations={"32.77S, 73.05W","36.48S, 72.76W","32.96S, 71.00W"},name="Andy Brockhouse"},{locations={"28.69S, 49.37W","31.10S, 49.34W","34.26S, 45.65W"},name="Nan Henwood"},{locations={"24.99S, 90.56W","28.10S, 92.08W","24.24S, 93.05W"},name="Barchiril"},{locations={"24.16S, 93.09W"},name="Badennas"},{locations={"31.28S, 51.07W"},name="Tad Ashmead"},{locations={"19.31S, 100.56W","15.55S, 104.75W","20.23S, 97.14W"},name="Rúni"},{locations={"34.01S, 74.77W"},name="Graland Whitfoot"}},category="Housing",id=1095,scope="n/a",name="Homesteads of Eriador",level=15,minlevel=15,b="Ísleif",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpeak with one of the housing brokers that can be found in Eriador.\nThese housing brokers can be found:\n- Across the river from Duillond\n- Across the river, west of Thorin's Gate\n- South of Michel Delving\n- South-east of Staddle\n* Talk to Nan Henwood\n* Talk to Rúni\n* Talk to Barchiril\n* Talk to Andy Brockhouse",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={156},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Farmer Polo Proudfoot has had trouble with bears raiding his beehives and killing his bees.",selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Eggs and Onions",id="700005F5"},{val="Fine Dagger",id="70000DE2"}},category="Shire",id=1096,scope="n/a",name="Honey-bears",arcs="Long Live the Queen",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=9,minlevel=5,b="Polo Proudfoot",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFarmer Proudfoot closed his hives to protect his bees from marauding honey-bears, but they cannot be kept closed or harm will still come to his bees. He has asked you to fend off any bears that are drawn to the honey.\n* Protect Polo and fight off all the bears\nObj 2:\nNow that you've driven off the bears, talk to Polo Proudfoot again for your reward."},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Mathom Society"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Baldwin Foxtail told you that a honey-roasted chicken is always the centerpiece of the Mathom Society dinner, but the Master Chef has been too busy to prepare one.",mobs={{locations={"33.39S, 75.53W"},name="Baldwin Foxtail"}},category="Reputation",id=1097,scope="Crafting",name="Honey-roasted Chicken - Introduction",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Baldwin Foxtail",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBaldwin Foxtail is at the Mathom House in Michel Delving in the Shire.\nBaldwin Foxtail has asked you to bring him a honey-roasted chicken for the cooks of the Mathom Society.\n* Bring the honey-roasted chicken to Baldwin Foxtail\n* Turn in Honey-roasted Chicken",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyl Annûn",money={{val="42s"}},d="The Angmarim have been plundering the tombs of Annuminas.",category="Evendim",id=1098,scope="n/a",name="Honoring the Dead",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,pois={{locations={"16.79S, 69.57W","16.54S, 69.87W","16.43S, 69.60W","16.63S, 69.81W","16.40S, 69.73W","16.48S, 69.58W","16.60S, 69.81W","16.73S, 69.66W"},name="Strongbox"}},minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nStrongboxes full of relics are outside the gates of the tombs of Annuminas on Tyl Ruinen.\n* Collect Strongboxes (6 Strongbox )\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will want to hold on to the strongboxes until he can return them to Tinnudir.\n* Turn in Strongbox",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2734},area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="After Sauron swept through Eregion of old, the Elves of Rivendell returned and placed statues at places where their brave kinsmen fell in battle.",mobs={{locations={"46.94S, 12.50W"},name="Ladenthir"}},category="Eregion",id=1099,scope="n/a",prev={281},name="Honouring the Fallen",arcs="The Ruins of Barad Morlas",level=49,c={"* Barad Morlas is at [48.1S, 13.7W]\n* Statues can be found at:\n[47.9S, 13.6W]\n* [48.0S, 13.8W]\n* [47.7S, 13.4W]\n* [47.6S, 13.7W]\n* [48.5S, 13.8W]\n* [48.6S, 14.1W]\n* [48.5S, 14.2W]\n* [48.2S, 14.5W]\n* Shatogtar can be found at [47.9S, 13.9W]"},pois={{locations={"48.52S, 13.85W","48.59S, 13.29W","48.05S, 14.24W","49.03S, 14.71W","47.74S, 13.41W","48.84S, 14.75W","47.61S, 13.67W","48.05S, 14.63W","48.16S, 14.48W","47.73S, 14.65W","47.98S, 13.77W","48.84S, 14.41W","47.88S, 13.62W","48.48S, 14.16W","48.57S, 14.09W","48.59S, 14.28W"},name="Small Elf-statue"}},minlevel=44,b="Ladenthir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are memorial statues spread all throughout Barad Morlas, south-west of Echad Eregion.\nLadenthir has asked you to preserve the memory of the Elves of Eregion by collecting the memorial statues placed in Barad Morlas by the Elves of Rivendell before the half-orcs can despoil them. He also bade you defeat Shatogtar, one of the Uruk-hai.\n* Defeat Shatogtar\n* Collect statues (8 Small Elf-statue )\nObj 2:\nLadenthir is at Echad Eregion, north-east of Barad Morlas.\nYou should return to Ladenthir with tidings of your success.\n* Talk to Ladenthir\n*"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Haldúr has informed you that Garbert has fallen on hard times and could use some business.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Haldúr"},{locations={"38.23S, 14.51W"},name="Garbert"}},category="Special",id=1100,scope="n/a",name="Hook, Line, and Sinker",level=40,minlevel=35,b="Haldúr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGarbert is at his cottage in Tâl Bruinen, south and west of Rivendell.\nHaldúr has asked that you visit Garbert and purchase fishing supplies from him because of his injuries.\n* Talk to Garbert",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={333},area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="Ión has gotten word that more dwarves are being readied to support the encampment at Jazârgund.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1101,scope="n/a",name="Hope From the East",arcs="Little Revolution",level=54,pois={{locations={"3.47S, 105.00W","3.76S, 104.25W","3.69S, 104.62W","3.48S, 104.64W","3.75S, 105.01W","3.45S, 104.28W"},name="Cauldron"}},minlevel=49,b="Ión",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe cauldrons are to the east in Jundul-dûm.\nIón has asked you to light several cauldrons along the road leading east from Jazârgund.\n* Use Cauldron\n* Turn in Flint and Twigs\nObj 2:\nIón is at Jazârgund, west of Jundul-dûm.\nIón will be pleased to hear that the reinforcements he requested will now be able to find their way.\n* Talk to Ión at Jazârgund\n* Turn in Flint and Twigs",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{d="Tol Ascarnen has fallen to the combined might of Angmar's army, but their forces are meagre, and they must fortify quickly, else the Free Peoples will regain a foothold here.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1102,scope="n/a",name="Horn of Rockwithers",destinypoints={{val=750}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Kaasak",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="Mon",o="Obj 1:\nRockwithers can be found among the Thistledown Grazers, south across the Hoarwell River.\nAngmar's forces at Tol Ascarnen are building a horn with which to call reinforcements to the fight when the Free Peoples return to assault the area. Kaasak has tasked you with retrieving the horn of the great aurochs, Rockwithers.\n* Talk to Soldier Kaasak at Tol Ascarnen ( )\n* Turn in Rockwither's Horn"},
{["next"]={2395},area="Hengstacer Farm",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Thorin's Hall"}},d="Cam Applewood works on a horse-farm called Hengstacer in the Bree-fields. He was approached by a dwarf who wanted to hire some horses for an expedition.",mobs={{locations={"22.35S, 52.34W"},name="Cam Applewood"},{locations={"23.03S, 51.03W"},name="Oddvarr"}},category="Bree-land",id=1103,scope="n/a",name="Horses for Hire",arcs="My Brethren's Call",level=20,minlevel=15,b="Cam Applewood",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe old dwarf was last seen walking towards the old ruins to the south-east.\nCam asked you to check up on an old dwarf who wanted to explore the ruins near Hengstacer.\n* Talk to Oddvarr",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2549},area="Bridgefields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="According to Milo Bolger, the wolves in the ruins were heard fighting among themselves one night. When the fighting ended, a large number of wolves ran through Budgeford, but did no harm to anyone.",mobs={{locations={"30.71S, 64.51W"},name="Milo Bolger"},{locations={"31.45S, 65.61W"},name="Linda Bolger"}},category="Shire",id=1104,scope="n/a",prev={188},name="Howling at Midnight",arcs="New Neighbours",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Milo Bolger",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLinda Bolger is in Budgeford, on the road furthest down the hill.\nMilo Bolger told you that his wife, Linda, had been caught outside when the wolves ran through Budgeford. He told you to go speak with her to learn more.\n* Talk to Linda Bolger\nObj 2:\nThe Yale-height is a far distance south-east of Budgeford, beyond Stock Road, not far north-east of Woodhall. The hill is marked by three pillars atop its pinnacle.\nMilo Bolger asked you to speak with his wife, Linda, about the strange encounter she had with the wolves in the middle of Budgeford. Linda did not have much more to reveal, other than to ask you to investigate the Yale-height, where she saw a large and evil-looking wolf digging in the soil on the night the wolves ran through Budgeford.\n* Turn in Rune-Inscribed Collar\nObj 3:\nLinda Bolger is in Budgeford, on the road furthest down the hill.\nLinda Bolger sent you to investigate the Yale-height, where she claimed to have seen a great, evil-looking wolf digging in the ground. During your search you discovered a strange, rune-inscribed collar. You should take the collar to Linda and see if it means anything to her.\n* Talk to Linda Bolger\n* Turn in Rune-Inscribed Collar"},
{area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The persistence of the Darkrage wolves, despite your efforts to thin their pack, leads Prestadír to believe that the wolf-pack is being used for evil, tamed by the forces of Dol Guldur to combat intruders in the wild.",category="Mirkwood",id=1105,scope="n/a",prev={2561},name="Howling on the Hill",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,c={"* The Wolf-whistle is on the Pack-howler's Hill at [15.4S, 56.0W]"},pois={{locations={"15.40S, 56.05W"},name="Wolf-whistle"}},minlevel=57,b="Prestadír",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nPack-howler's Hill is to the south of the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks.\nYou should go to Pack-howler's Hill and attempt to draw out the wolf-tamer who has trained the Darkrage wolves against the Malledhrim.\n* Use the wolf-whistle to summon the Wolf-keeper and defeat him\n* Use Wolf-whistle\nObj 2:\nPrestadír is at the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks.\nYou should return to Prestadír with news of your success.\n* Speak with Prestadír at the Haunted Inn"},
{["next"]={2327},area="Taur Orthon",zone="Forochel",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Cenlieg has managed to locate his fellows, who are travelling north-west towards an unknown location.",mobs={{locations={"3.00N, 58.07W"},name="Cenlieg"}},category="Forochel",id=1106,scope="n/a",prev={2525},name="Hungry Bear-friend",arcs="The Lost Fellowship Lore-Master",level=44,c={"* The moose are around the southwestern area of the lake"},minlevel=39,b="Cenlieg",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMoose can be found throughout the forest surrounding Kauppa-kohta.\nCenlieg has asked you to hunt for some moose-meat to feed his bear-friend, Linden.\n* Turn in Moose-meat (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nCenlieg is at Kauppa-kohta,  on the eastern shore of the lake.\nYou should bring the meat you gathered back to Cenlieg.\n* Talk to Cenlieg\n* Turn in Moose-meat (Level 1)"},
{["next"]={2675},area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Thrasi's lynx and her cub were reunited thanks to your efforts but they are getting hungry, and Thrasi is still nursing his ankle.",mobs={{locations={"21.59S, 94.17W"},name="Thrasi"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1107,scope="n/a",prev={2325},name="Hungry Mouths to Feed",arcs="The Cat's Meow",level=10,c={"* The trap with the rabbit is in Haudh Lin at [21.9S, 93.9W]. You can see if there's a rabbit in a trap if you watch closely."},pois={{locations={"21.90S, 94.68W","21.60S, 93.85W","21.85S, 93.82W","21.60S, 93.68W","21.49S, 93.84W","21.91S, 94.05W","21.93S, 93.91W","21.90S, 94.38W","21.63S, 93.75W","21.80S, 94.35W","22.00S, 94.17W","21.43S, 94.18W","21.98S, 94.54W","21.87S, 93.98W"},name="Trap"}},minlevel=6,b="Thrasi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are traps for small game scattered not far to the east and west of Thrasi's lodge.\nThrasi asked you to either hunt and kill a live rabbit, or to check his traps and bring back a rabbit carcass for the lynx-mother and her cub.\n* Use Trap\n* Use Trap\n* Turn in Rabbit-carcass\nObj 2:\nBring the rabbit carcass to Thrasi at Thrasi's Lodge.\n* Talk to Thrasi\n* Turn in Rabbit-carcass"},
{area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="13s 60c"}},d="The goblins in Annunlos used Wargs, evil beasts of war, to hunt members of the Eglain in the ruins of Minas Eriol. Gadaric wants vengeance on the foul beasts for the murders of his people.",mobs={{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Gadaric Munce"}},selectoneof={{val="Munce's Cape",id="70000C69"},{val="Munce's Gauntlets",id="70000C67"},{val="Munce's Axe",id="70000C68"}},category="Lone-lands",id=1108,scope="n/a",name="Hunters Become Prey",arcs="Vengeance for the Lost",level=23,minlevel=18,b="Gadaric Munce",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWargs can be found among the ruins of Minas Eriol to the south-east of The Forsaken Inn.\nGadaric Munce believes that taking the tails of the Wargs who murdered his people will renew the will of the Eglain and humiliate the Wargs and their goblin-masters.\n* Bring Warg-tails to Gadaric Munce\n* Turn in Warg-tail"},
{["next"]={1077},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="The Gauredain have been warned that their aggression would not go unmarked yet they have not relented, and so the battle shall commence in earnest.",mobs={{locations={"19.54N, 71.99W"},name="Vämmä"}},category="Forochel",id=1109,scope="n/a",prev={2403},name="Hunters in the Blinding White",level=48,c={"* The best place to hunt those Gauredain is Barad Gaurhoth, where you can find all three types of Gauredain."},minlevel=43,b="Vämmä",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Gauredain can be found on the great glacier across the Ice Bay to the west.\nVämmä has asked you to hunt the Gauredain stalking the glaciers.\n* Defeat Gauradan Ravagers\n* Defeat Gauradan Stalkers\n* Defeat Gauradan Seers\nObj 2:\nVämmä is in Sûri-kylä, far to the east of the glacier, across the Ice Bay.\nWith their numbers weakened, you should return to Vämmä and see what else might be done to end the Gauradan threat.\n* Talk to Vämmä"},
{["next"]={2807},area="Vale of Thrain",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Grímkell scoffed at Vífill's story of goblins in the Vale of Thráin, blaming Vífill's injury instead upon his own clumsiness.",mobs={{locations={"19.34S, 100.46W"},name="Grímkell Stonebearer"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1110,scope="n/a",prev={645},name="Hunting Goblins",arcs="Villains in the Vale",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Grímkell Stonebearer",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nVífill said there were goblins south of his camp.\nGrímkell told you he would only be convinced of Vífill's tale if you could bring him an authentic goblin fetish.\n* Bring the fetish to Grímkell\n* Turn in Goblin-fetish"},
{["next"]={3196},area="Northern Emyn Uial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="Erchiel has asked you to defeat several of the Gauredain in order to frighten them and keep them from exploring further south.",mobs={{locations={"6.12S, 71.92W"},name="Erchiel"}},category="Evendim",id=1111,scope="n/a",name="Hunting the Hunters",arcs="Threat from the North",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=36,minlevel=31,b="Erchiel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nErchiel has asked you to defeat a number of Gauredain in order to instill in them a healthy fear of the forests.\nThe Gauredain she speaks of can be found in the forests north of the river that passes by the Eavespires.\n* Defeat Gauradan Tribesman\n* Defeat Gauradan Gorge-stalker\n* Defeat a Gauradan Soothsayer\nObj 2:\nErchiel is at the Eavespires on the northwest shore of Lake Evendim.\nYou should return and tell Erchiel of your forays against the Gauredain\n* Talk to Erchiel"},
{["next"]={1444},area="Nan Amlug West",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Quartermaster Orgrin has asked for your help in making the hills safer for his hunters.",mobs={{locations={"6.89S, 44.85W"},name="Quartermaster Orgrin"}},category="North Downs",id=1112,scope="n/a",prev={3246},name="Hunting Wargs",arcs="Provisions for the Mines",level=30,c={"* Kill any of the Dire Wargs and Warg Hunters will count in the eastern Nan Amlug"},minlevel=25,b="Quartermaster Orgrin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWarg packs prowl the hills of eastern Nan Amlug depleting the Aurochs herds that serve to feed the dwarves of Othrikar.\nAfter receiving a report that one of his hunters has been savaged by Wargs, Orgrin asks you to clear the Wargs from the hills.\n* Defeat Wargs (12)\nObj 2:\nOrgrin is the quartermaster for the dwarves of Othrikar.\nReturn to Orgrin with the tidings that the aurochs herds of Nan Amlug have a few less Wargs to fear.\n* Talk to Quartermaster Orgrin"},
{zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="A Sage of Eriador has invited you to recollect your experience seeking the palantír deep within Barad Tironn.",mobs={{locations={"11.99S, 68.11W"},name="Maleniel"}},category="Tales of the Shadows of Angmar",id=1113,scope="n/a",prev={2930},name="I.10.14 Tale: The Eye of Angmar",receive={{val="Mark of Triumph",id="7000FC10"}},level=50,minlevel=45,b="Maleniel",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Reflecting Pool on Tinnudir will allow you to revisit 'The Eye of Angmar.'\nA Sage of Eriador has challenged you to revisit your assault on Barad Tironn by using the Reflecting Pool on Tinnudir.\n* Peer into the Reflecting Pool and revisit 'The Eye of Angmar'\nObj 2:\nA Sage of Eriador is by the Reflecting Pool on Tinnudir.\nA Sage of Eriador on Tinnudir is waiting to discuss what you have learned from revisiting your experience seeking the palantír within Barad Tironn.\n* Talk to Maleniel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
