{reputation={{val="+700 with Council of the North"}},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="The Trév Duvárdain have sent an emissary to Agar to treat with the minions of the Iron Crown.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Brúnfair"}},selectoneof={{val="Karstíona's Doom",id="7000D9C3"},{val="Victory at Minas Agar",id="700011DA"},{val="Brúnfair's Leggings",id="700011D9"}},category="Angmar",id=1290,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1652},name="Karstíona, Emissary of the Trév Duvárdain",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Brúnfair",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMinas Agar stands on the western side of Barad Gúlaran, south of Gath Forthnír.\nYou must travel to Barad Gúlaran and defeat Karstíona, the emissary of the Trév Duvárdain, inside Minas Agar.\nObj 2:\nBrúnfair is in Gath Forthníir, north of Barad Gúlaran.\nHaving defeated Karstíona, you should return to Brúnfair and tell him of your success.\n* Talk to Brúnfair"},
{["next"]={751},area="Goblin-town",zone="Misty Mountains",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The goblin Oghûk wants you to help him escape from his cell.",category="Misty Mountains",id=1291,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Keepers and the Kept",arcs="The Great Escape",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Oghûk the Hooligan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblin-jailors can be found in the dungeons of Goblin-town.\nOghûk believes that the jailors in the Goblin-town prison have the keys to his cell. He wants you to kill the jailors and find the keys. Only after you free him will he help you.\n* Deliver the keys to Oghûk in his cell within the Goblin-town prison\n* Turn in Plain Key"},
{["next"]={1435},area="Nan Tornaeth",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="Calenthon believes that the Hillmen of Rhudaur in Nan Tornaeth have some foul association with the wights that stalk the ruins by night.",mobs={{locations={"28.16S, 15.29W"},name="Calenthon"}},category="Trollshaws",id=1292,scope="n/a",prev={481},name="Keepers of the Dead",arcs="Abominations",level=38,minlevel=33,b="Calenthon",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Hillmen of Rhudaur can be found throughout Nan Tornaeth, north-east of Calenthon, at Amon Varadh and Minas Ciliant.\nCalenthon has asked you to defeat some of the Hillmen of Rhudaur in Nan Tornaeth and bring him some sign of their connexion with the wights that stalk the area by night.\n* Turn in Gúrdring's Emblem\nObj 2:\nCalenthon is in Nan Tornaeth, north-west of Thorenhad.\nYou found a curious emblem on the body of a fallen Hillman. You should bring it to Calenthon at once.\n* Talk to Calenthon\n* Turn in Gúrdring's Emblem"},
{["next"]={1341},area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Lithuilas has learned that there is a group of Wood-trolls in the Glâd Ereg and believes that they are responsible for provoking the forest.",mobs={{locations={"40.05S, 15.96W"},name="Lithuilas"}},category="Eregion",id=1293,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={67},name="Keepers of the Wood",arcs="A Foul Wood",level=49,c={"* Holly-troll Warriors, Holly-troll Lobbers, and Holly-troll Elders are in Sâd Thareg"},minlevel=44,b="Lithuilas",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWood-trolls can be found near Sâd Thareg, south of Gwingris.\nLithuilas has asked you to defeat the Wood-trolls of Glâd Ereg and learn their purpose there. He suggests that you take an ally or two with you.\n* Defeat Wood-trolls (16)\nObj 2:\nLithuilas is at Gwingris, north of Sâd Thareg.\nYou should return to Lithuilas with word of your success.\n* Talk to Lithuilas at Gwingris"},
{["next"]={1794},area="Zelem-melek",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},d="You found a missing piece from the statue of Helgi Goblinbane -- the top of his head.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1294,scope="n/a",prev={1976},name="Keeping Ahead of the Goblins",level=55,minlevel=50,b="Statue Head",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are dwarves in the Twenty-first Hall.\nYou have found a piece of the shattered statue and should bring it to a dwarf who may deliver it to Uxi.\n* Bring the statue-piece to the Twenty-first Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={299},area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Mika recognizes the markings on the tusk as Angmarim sorcery in a Gauradan hand. He wishes you to find and defeat the Gauradan Seer who dares try and twist one of the Lossoth's mammoths.",mobs={{locations={"7.47N, 80.52W"},name="Mika"}},category="Forochel",id=1295,scope="n/a",prev={1473},name="Keeping the Norsu Pure",arcs="Protecting the Mammoths",level=47,c={"* The Gauradan Seer is in Norsu-hauta at [8.3N, 81.5W]. He is accompanied by a wolf and is near an Elite Mammoth, but the mamoth won't attack you and will leave when the Seer is defeated."},minlevel=42,b="Mika",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSearch around Norsu-hauta for the Gauradan Seer who is trying to ensorcel a Mammoth.\n* Defeat a Gauradan Seer who is trying to ensorcel a Mammoth\nObj 2:\nReturn to Mika in Norsu-hauta and tell him of your success.\n* Talk to Mika"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Knowledge can be the greatest weapon in war, $CLIENT_NAME$. It can turn the tide of battle, for good or for ill. I speak to you now of a matter so urgent that there can be no delay, for it concerns knowledge that could spell doom for my people...not here in the city, but elsewhere in Middle-earth.\nWhen the darkwater first came to Annúminas, some of my kindred attempted to banish them from the pools of Glinghant. I would have joined their fight, for its pools and gardens are dear to me, but Fainneleg commanded that I help with the initial defence of Gwaelband. I and Gwonil fought bravely and turned back an Angmarim assault, but while we survived to receive other assignments, the Dúnedain that fought in Glinghant did not. The darkwater overwhelmed them and the gardens were taken.\nBut worse still, one of my fallen brethren bore on his person a map to the hidden refuge of Esteldín, in the North Downs. Folly, perhaps, to carry such a map, but what has been done has been done. We must retrieve the map before it can be taken by the Enemy. The darkwater may not appreciate its significance, but one of Amarthiel's more corporeal servants might. We must not let it fall into their hands, $CLIENT_NAME$. Seek out the fallen Rangers in Glinghant and retrieve the map to Esteldín from him that bore it. Do this quickly, my friend, for there is little time to waste! If I am not around when you return, please bring the map with all haste to Captain-General Daerdan, at Echad Garthadir, here in the city.",category="Annúminas",id=1296,scope="n/a",name="Keep It from the Enemy",receive={{val="Annúminas Mark",id="700216BF"}},level=40,minlevel=35,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe fallen Ranger carrying the map to Esteldín is somewhere within the pools and gardens of Glinghant, beyond the court of Clorhir, in Annúminas.\nHarthadril asked you to bring the map to Esteldín out of Glinghant.\n* Use Fallen Ranger\n* Use Fallen Ranger",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1314},area="Trestlebridge",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="7s"}},d="Kemp, the old wheelwright, seeks revenge against the Orcs that attacked Trestlebridge.",mobs={{locations={"17.52S, 53.88W"},name="Kemp the Wheelwright"}},category="North Downs",id=1297,scope="n/a",prev={2397},name="Kemp's Revenge",arcs="Kemp the Wheelwright",level=22,minlevel=17,b="Kemp the Wheelwright",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Tarkrîp, the tribe of Orcs that attacked Trestlebridge, can be found throughout the North Downs. Their main encampment is likely to be near the town.\nKemp the Wheelwright asked you to exact his revenge upon the Orcs of the Tarkrîp tribe.\n* Defeat Tarkrîp Orcs in the North Downs (25)\nObj 2:\nKemp the Wheelwright can be found in Trestlebridge.\nYou should bring Kemp the Wheelwright word of your success.\n* Talk to Kemp the Wheelwright"},
{area="Trestlebridge",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="7s"}},d="Kemp told you the tale of how he survived the Orc-attack and how Nellie Boskins resolved to save Trestlebridge.",mobs={{locations={"17.52S, 53.88W"},name="Kemp the Wheelwright"}},selectoneof={{val="The Wheelwright's Earring",id="700069FC"},{val="The Wheelwright's Shoulders",id="70006AD4"}},category="North Downs",id=1298,scope="n/a",prev={1313},name="Kemp's Stash",arcs="Kemp the Wheelwright",level=22,pois={{locations={"11.43S, 51.36W"},name="Mound"}},minlevel=17,b="Kemp the Wheelwright",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKemp the Wheelwright said his stash lay buried in the ruins of Minas Vrûn north and east of Trestlebridge. The hiding spot is in an archway marked with an  \"X\".\nKemp the Wheelwright asked you to collect his hidden stash of money, so that he can help to maintain Trestlebridge for Nellie Boskins.\n* Use Mound\nObj 2:\nKemp the Wheelwright can be found in Trestlebridge.\nYou should return to Kemp the Wheelwright with his stash.\n* Bring the stash to Kemp\n* Turn in Kemp's Stash"},
{area="The Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Skûmfil is nothing more than a dumping ground, a place where the fallen Orcs of Moria are discarded when they begin to reek. It is here that two foes have gathered, each intent on using the corpses found therein for their own purposes. The kergrim and other scavengers as a source of food, and the insects as a place to lay their eggs to spawn future generations.",mobs={{locations={"13.15S, 101.21W"},name="Odmar"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1299,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Kergrim-leaders",arcs="Skumfíl",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Odmar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBonetooth and Old Gnawer are within Skûmfil, south-east of the Shadowed Refuge.\nOdmar wants you to put an end to the kergrim-leaders who brought the corpse-eating creatures through the tunnels of Moria to Skûmfil.\n* Defeat Bonetooth\n* Defeat Old Gnawer\nObj 2:\nOdmar is at the Shadowed Refuge, north-west of Skûmfil.\nYou found the two kergrim, one ancient and the other a summoner, and destroyed them both. Odmar, at the Shadowed Refuge will be pleased to know that this is done.\n* Talk to Odmar at the Shadowed Refuge"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="Haudh Valandur has become home to a group of Kergrim, foul creatures from unknown origin.",category="Evendim",id=1300,scope="n/a",name="Kergrim of Haudh Valandur",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Maladan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHaudh Valandur is within the Way of Kings, west of the Ranger camp.\nMaladan asked you to go to Haudh Valandur and defeat the kergrim found within.\n* Defeat Kergrim in Haudh Valandur (4)\nObj 2:\nMaladan is at the Ranger camp in the Way of Kings.\nMaladan will be pelased to hear you survived the kergrim of Haudh Valandur.\n* Talk to Maladan",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="The denizens of the Way of Kings have ancient keys that may open some of the crypts and tombs within.",category="Evendim",id=1301,scope="n/a",name="Keys to the Crypts",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Maladan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\n* Turn in Rusted Key\nObj 2:\nMaladan is at the Ranger camp in the Way of Kings.\nMaladan will want to examine the keys you collected.\n* Bring the Keys to Maladan\n* Turn in Rusted Key",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="Kheled-menem is a dwarf-mine famous for its glowing crystals.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1302,scope="n/a",prev={1422},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Kheled-menem: A Light in the Hand",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Endrith",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nCrystal-shards can be found in Kheled-menem, north-east of Anazârmekhem.\nEndrith would like you to go to Kheled-menem and bring back any crystal-shards you find inside. He recommended you bring a friend or two.\n* Collect crystal-shards (8 Crystal-shard)\nObj 2:\nEndrith is at Anazârmekhem, south-west of Kheled-menem.\nEndrith will be eager to begin working with the crystal-shards.\n* Talk to Endrith\n* Turn in Crystal-shard",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="The crystal-mines at Kheled-menem have been taken over by a group of Ghâsh-hai led by Ghâshug.",selectoneof={{val="Endrith's Shield",id="700163F3"},{val="Ghâshug's Woe",id="700163FA"},{val="Cloak of Kheled-menem",id="700163C8"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1303,scope="n/a",prev={1422},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Kheled-menem: Ghâshug",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Endrith",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGhâshug is at the crystal-mines in Kheled-menem, north-east of Anazârmekhem.\nEndrith asked you to head to the crystal-mines of Kheled-menem and liberate them from the control of Ghâshug. He recommended you bring friends.\n* Defeat Ghâshug\nObj 2:\nEndrith is at Anazârmekhem, south-west of Kheled-menem.\nEndrith will be pleased to hear Ghâshug has been defeated.\n* Talk to Endrith at Anazârmekhem"},
{money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="The Ghâsh-hai have taken control of the crystal-mine, Kheled-menem.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1304,scope="n/a",prev={1422},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Kheled-menem: Stolen Lights",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Endrith",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Ghâsh-hai can be found in the crystal-mine at Kheled-menem, north-east of Anazârmekhem.\nEndrith asked you to venture to Kheled-menem and clear the Ghâsh-hai out of the crystal-mine. He warned you might want to bring a friend or two.\n* Defeat Orc-warriors in Kheled-menem\n* Defeat Orc-defilers in Kheled-menem\nObj 2:\nEndrith is at Anazârmekhem, south-west of Kheled-menem.\nEndrith will be pleased to hear the Ghâsh-hai have been cleared out of Kheled-menem.\n* Talk to Endrith at Anzârmekhem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Khibir-zamu is an ancient tomb where many of the builders of the great halls of Khazad-dûm were interred.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1305,scope="n/a",prev={764},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Khibir-zamu: Relics of the Past",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Styrr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe records are within Khibir-zamu, south-west of the Deep Descent.\nStyrr has asked you to venture within Khibir-zamu, gather up any records you find within and bring them to him. He cautioned that you may want to bring an ally or two.\n* Collect records from Khibir-zamu (12 Dwarf-treasure)\nObj 2:\nStyrr is at the Deep Descent, north-east of Khibir-zamu.\nStyrr will be eager to start examining the records you recovered from Khibir-zamu.\n* Talk to Styrr\n* Turn in Dwarf-treasure",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Khibir-zamu is an ancient tomb where many of the builders of the great halls of Khazad-dûm were interred.",selectoneof={{val="The Huntsman's Ear",id="70017CE1"},{val="Styrr's Ring",id="700163B6"},{val="Helm of Khibir-zamu",id="7001607A"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1306,scope="n/a",prev={764},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Khibir-zamu: Stonetooth the Savage",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Styrr",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nStonetooth is within Khibir-zamu, south-west of the Deep Descent.\nStyrr asked you to venture within Khibir-zamu to find and defeat Stonetooth the Savage, a deep-claw that has claimed many dwarves.\n* Defeat Stonetooth\nObj 2:\nStyrr is at the Deep Descent, north-east of Khibir-zamu.\nStyrr will be pleased to hear that Stonetooth has been defeated and will no longer attack any more dwarves.\n* Talk to Styrr at the Deep Descent"},
{money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Khibir-zamu is an ancient tomb where many of the builders of the great halls of Khazad-dûm were interred.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1307,scope="n/a",prev={764},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Khibir-zamu: Tunnellers of the Tomb",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Styrr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe deep-claws are in Khibir-zamu, south-west of the Deep Descent.\nStyrr asked you to venture inside Khibir-zamu and defeat the deep-claws who have nested there. He mentioned you may want to bring an ally or two.\n* Defeat Savage Deep-claws in Khibir-zamu\nObj 2:\nStyrr is at the Deep Descent, north-east of Khibir-zamu.\nStyrr will be pleased to hear the deep-claws have been defeated and Khibir-zamus foundations and supports are safe and stable.\n* Talk to Styrr at the Deep Descent",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="The newly-discovered chamber of Khibir-zarur is said to be consumed by living shadows -- fell spirits of darkness that threaten to consume the light and life of any who dare enter.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1308,scope="n/a",prev={765},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Khibir-zarur: Fragments of Shadow",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Gansi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nFell spirits lie within Khibir-zarur in Durin's Way.\nGansi has asked you to help defeat the living shadows that inhabit the chambers of Khibir-zarur.\n* Defeat shadow-grims\nObj 2:\nGansi is at the Chamber of the Crossroads in Durin's Way.\nYou should tell Gansi that you have defeated the shadow-grims that inhabited Khibir-zarur.\n* Talk to Gansi at the Chamber of the Crossroads",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="41s 44c"}},d="Ancient treasures of Moria remain locked within the hidden halls of Khibir-zarur, though few would dare to confront the fell shadows that threaten to consume all light and life to reclaim it in the name of Durin's Folk.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1309,scope="n/a",prev={765},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Khibir-zarur: Gold in the Darkness",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Gansi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe dwarf-treasures can be found in Khibir-zarur within Durin's Way.\nGansi has asked you to collect dwarf-treasures from the hidden chamber of Khibir-zarur.\n* Collect dwarf-treasures (4 Dwarf-treasure)\nObj 2:\nGansi is at the Chamber of the Crossroads in Durin's Way.\nYou should bring the sealed chests of dwarf-treasure that you have recovered to Gansi.\n* Talk to Gansi at the Chamber of the Crossroads\n* Turn in Dwarf-treasure",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Within the hidden chamber of Khibir-zarur, many spirits of shadow have gathered around a greater spirit that bears the name of Faerdûath. Any who dare to enter will find themselves entrapped in eternal darkness if they cannot defeat Faerdûath and bring light to the ancient hall.",selectoneof={{val="Protector's Defence",id="70017CF4"},{val="Faerdûath's Doom",id="700160FD"},{val="Gansi's Bracelet",id=70016395}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1310,scope="n/a",prev={765},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Khibir-zarur: the Shadows of Faerdûath",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Gansi",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFaerdûath lies within Khibir-zarur in Durin's Way.\nGansi has asked you to seek out and defeat the spirit Faerdûath.\n* Defeat Faerdûath\nObj 2:\nGansi can be found at the Chamber of the Crossroads in Durin's Way.\nYou should return to Gansi and tell him that Faerdûath has been defeated.\n* Talk to Gansi at the Chamber of the Crossroads"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The organized Wargs of Maudhul-ulur remain a great threat to the Elves of the Malledhrim.",mobs={{locations={"16.50S, 60.28W"},name="Goldínwen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1311,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Killing the Wolf",arcs="Jaws of the Enemy",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,c={"* Âthruk can be found inside Maudhûl-ulur at [17.4S, 60.1W]"},minlevel=56,b="Goldínwen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nÂthruk can be found at Maudhul-ulur, south from Echad Glamodúd.\nGoldínwen has asked you to defeat Âthruk, the overseer of Maudhul-ulur.\n* Defeat Âthruk at Maudhul-ulur\nObj 2:\nGoldínwen is at Echad Glamodúd, north from Maudhul-ulur.\nYou should return to Goldínwen with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Goldínwen at Echad Glamodúd"},
{["next"]={2404},area="The Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Tyki has been watching the Globsnaga Orcs closely for any signs that his attempted freshwater cure worked. He has determined that it has not, and the Orkish menace must be purged from Khazad-dûm...with fire.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1312,scope="n/a",prev={68},name="Kill it with Fire",arcs="The Fungus Among Us",level=60,pois={{locations={"14.19S, 101.55W","13.59S, 101.64W","14.09S, 101.04W","13.35S, 101.76W","14.31S, 101.78W","13.69S, 101.26W"},name="Fungal Structure"}},minlevel=55,b="Tyki",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe fungal structures can be found in and near Dalgum-ru, south of the Shadowed Refuge.\nTyki wants you to burn some of the strange fungal structures close to the Orcs' camp.\n* Use Fungal Structure\nObj 2:\nTyki is at the Shadowed Refuge, north of Dalgum-ru.\nYou should return to Tyki to tell him how flammable those fungal structures turned out to be.\n* Speak to Tyki at the Shadowed Refuge"},
{area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The small Orc-camp of Gâthlata sits below Ânghum-maudhûl and serves as a crossroad for the Orcs mustering in the Ashenslades.",mobs={{locations={"17.49S, 48.19W"},name="Eirien"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1313,scope="n/a",prev={728,2456,1949},name="Kill the Messenger",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Eirien",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSealed orders may be found on the Orcs at Gâthlata, east of Mithechad, north of Ânghum-maudhûl.\nEirien has asked you to collect sealed orders from the Orcs of Gâthlata.\n* Turn in Sealed Orders\nObj 2:\nEirien is at Mithechad, west of Gâthlata.\nYou should bring the sealed orders you discovered to Eirien at once.\n* Talk to Eirien\n* Turn in Sealed Orders",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2486},reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="Taur Morvith",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orcs of Taur Morvith are in disarray. Iavassúl now has a plan to keep them that way.",mobs={{locations={"16.60S, 50.55W"},name="Iavassúl"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1314,scope="n/a",prev={6},name="King of the Hill",arcs="Forts of Taur Morvith",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=64,pois={{locations={"17.08S, 50.30W","17.32S, 50.66W"},name="Banner Stones"}},minlevel=59,b="Iavassúl",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe guard-towers are in Krul Lugu below Iavassúl's Watch.\n* Use Banner Stones\nObj 2:\nThe guard-towers are in Krul Lugu below Iavassúl's Watch.\nIavassúl has asked you to claim one of the two guard-towers in Taur Morvith with a banner of the Malledhrim, then hold it against the Orcs for a time.\n* Defend the banner of the Malledhrim\nObj 3:\nIavassúl is at Iavassúl's Watch, above Krul Lugu.\nYou should speak with Iavassúl regarding your efforts in the Orc-camps.\n* Talk to Iavassúl at Iavassúl's Watch"},
{area="Northern Emyn Uial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="Erchiel the Elf is concerned with the giants which have been ruining the forest.",mobs={{locations={"6.12S, 71.92W"},name="Erchiel"}},category="Evendim",id=1315,scope="n/a",name="Knocking Heads",arcs="Befuddled Giants",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Refined Athelas Essence",id="70000F89"},{q="(x2)",val="Refined Celebrant Salve",id="7000228A"}},level=37,pois={{locations={"7.63S, 74.43W"},name="Small stone cairn"},{locations={"7.67S, 74.55W"},name="Giant's Lucky Stone"}},minlevel=32,b="Erchiel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAmon Môth is located to the west and south of the Eavespires, and the cairn Erchiel mentioned is somewhere on the northern outskirts of their camp.\nErchiel has asked you to prove your cunning by stealing a lucky stone from one of the giants of Amon Môth.\n* Use Small stone cairn\nObj 2:\nErchiel can be found at the Eavespires, east and north of Amon Môth, near the shoreline of Lake Evendim.\nYou should bring the lucky stone back to Erchiel.\n* Talk to Erchiel\n* Turn in Giant's Lucky Stone"},
{["next"]={1358},d="Mirwen was pleased with the texts you brought her, but was also unable to immediately translate them.",category="Lore-master",id=1316,scope="n/a",prev={1970},name="Knowledge of the Lore-master",arcs="The Path of the Ancient Master",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Mirwen",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGreatroar is somewhere in the Water-works of Moria, far to the south of Rivendell.\nMirwen told you to find the toad Greatroar and defeat her, for the toad long ago swallowed a book of dwarf-lore.\n* Bring the book to Winiel at the Rotting Cellar\n* Turn in Old Tome with Torn Pages",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={665,706,1811,2006},area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Crystals have been discovered in Moria, bearing marks of the Forgotten Treasury, a sealed vault hiding a substantial amount of wealth. This discovery has piqued the interest of some dwarves who now wish to uncover the vault and save its contents from the pilfering Orcs.",mobs={{locations={"9.86S, 112.76W"},name="Falgir"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1317,scope="n/a",prev={143},name="Know Thine Enemy",arcs="The Forgotten Treasury",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Falgir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Forgotten Treasury lies to the south and south-east of the Deep Descent.\nFalgir has asked that you kill Orcs and goblins between the Deep Descent and Forgotten Treasury to ready yourself for the task of liberating the vault. He also asked you to collect scraps of material from the Orcs and goblins.\n* Bring the items to Falgir in the Deep Descent\n* Turn in Swatch of Fabric"},
{area="Northern Barrow-downs",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="3s 20c"}},d="You have come across a very frightened hobbit-lass, Lalia, in the Barrow-downs. She has asked for your help getting back to Bree and her father, Bob, who works for Barliman Butterbur at the Prancing Pony.",mobs={{locations={"31.77S, 56.19W"},name="Bob"}},selectoneof={{val="Guardian of Lalia",id="70003A08"},{val="Warden of Lalia",id="700161B1"},{val="Lalia's Champion",id="700090FF"},{val="Defender of Lalia",id="70003A09"}},category="Bree-land",id=1318,scope="n/a",name="Lalia's Safe Passage",level=18,minlevel=13,b="Lalia",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou must take Lalia to the North-gate of the Barrow-downs.\nLalia has asked you to help her get back to Bree safely. In addition, she has asked for your help finding the cloak she dropped somewhere in the Barrow-downs. You should protect her as she searches for her cloak, then leaves the Barrow-downs.\n* Escort Lalia to safety\nObj 2:\nBob can be found along the Old Forest Road, between the Barrow-downs and the Old Forest.\nYou have helped Lalia make her way home. As thanks, she has given you her cloak. She has asked you to bring it to her father, Bob, Barliman Butterbur's assistant, as proof that she is safe. You did not have the heart to tell her that Bob was looking for her within the Barrow-downs himself.\n* Talk to Bob\n* Turn in Lalia's Cloak",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Annúminas",money={{val="42s"}},d="Many Rangers have fallen defending Annuminas from the forces of Angmar.",category="Evendim",id=1319,scope="n/a",name="Lament of the Fallen",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,pois={{locations={"17.50S, 69.22W","17.49S, 69.20W","17.49S, 69.21W","17.51S, 69.20W","17.50S, 69.25W"},name="Fallen Ranger"}},minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMany rangers have fallen to defend the city from Angmar. They should be honored.\n* Use Fallen Ranger\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will be pleased to hear you honored the fallen rangers.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Egladil",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="Maliriel has asked you to help her companions finish the prepartions for the upcoming banquet.",mobs={{locations={"17.24S, 64.05W"},name="Galhíril"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1320,scope="n/a",name="Lanterns Aglow",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,pois={{locations={"16.73S, 65.67W","16.49S, 64.94W","16.49S, 65.34W","16.84S, 64.73W","16.66S, 64.76W","16.63S, 65.54W","16.88S, 64.22W","16.56S, 65.13W","16.94S, 64.09W","16.84S, 64.51W","16.75S, 64.35W","17.04S, 64.10W","17.11S, 64.01W"},name="Lantern"}},minlevel=55,b="Galhíril",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are lanterns along the path between Imlad Lalaith and Caras Galadhon. Wait for night fall, and then light them to help lead revellers to the feast.\nAs part of the preparations for the evening feast, Galhíril would like you to light the lanterns that will lead the evening revellers to the banquet.\n* Use Lantern\nObj 2:\nGalhíril is at Imlad Lalaith.\nYou should return to Galhíril with your report.\n* Talk to Galhíril at Imlad Lalaith",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hithlad",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Binding the walls at the lumber-yard requires roots to be used as lashings.",category="Grimwood",id=1321,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Lashing the Walls",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Chieftain Torbok",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nRoots can be found upon the downed trees throughout the Grimwood and the saplings that sprout from the ground. You might also find them on the Leafcull-trees.\nChieftain Torbok wants you to get lashings for the walls at the Grimwood Lumber-yard.\n* Return to Chieftain Torbok at the Grimwood Lumber-yard ()\n* Turn in Grimwood Root",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+700 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="Having discovered a pledge from the Dourhands, you must enter Minas Angos and defeat their emissary to stop an alliance between them and the Iron Crown.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Brúnfair"}},selectoneof={{val="Firitham",id="700011E7"},{val="Laugi Goldentongue's Doom",id="7000D9C5"},{val="Victory at Minas Angos",id="700011E8"}},category="Angmar",id=1322,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1650},name="Laugi Goldentongue, Emissary of the Dourhands",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Brúnfair",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMinas Angos is a tower in Barad Gúlaran, south of Gath Forthnír.\nYou must travel to Barad Gúlaran and defeat Laugi Goldentongue, the emissary of the Dourhands, inside Minas Angos. Brúnfair suggested you take allies.\nObj 2:\nBrúnfair is at Gath Forthnír, north of Barad Gúlaran.\nHaving defeated Laugi Goldentongue, you should return to Brúnfair and tell him of your victory.\n* Talk to Brúnfair"},
{["next"]={307},area="The Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Since the dwarf-expedition entered Moria, there has been no sign of Durin's Bane, and the goblins and Orcs have frequently been seen fighting among one another.",selectoneof={{val="Gathrok's Foe",id="700160FB"},{val="Shoulders of Gamil Filik",id="7001607E"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1323,scope="n/a",name="Lawlessness Among Goblins",arcs="Sky Fall",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Stíling",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGathrok and his goblins are in Gamil Filik, south-east of the Deep Descent.\nStíling has asked you to defeat Gathrok, a goblin-chieftain, and weaken his forces.\n* Defeat Gathrok\n* Defeat goblins in Gamil Filik (12)\nObj 2:\nStíling is at the dwarf-camp in the Deep Descent, north-west of Gamil Filik.\nYou should return to Stíling and tell him of your deeds at Gamil Filik.\n* Talk to Stíling"},
{["next"]={802},area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"},{val="25s 20c"}},d="You have been encouraged to learn the hidden tracks and paths of Eregion so that you may travel there more quickly.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 67.00W"},name="Cúlith"},{locations={"20.05S, 96.98W"},name="Dagfinn"},{locations={"18.84N, 72.37W"},name="Okko"},{locations={"50.50S, 7.91W"},name="Tinúriel"},{locations={"29.91S, 5.90W"},name="Mallenhadh"},{locations={"31.86S, 51.28W"},name="Flambard Took"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Bolo Boffin"},{locations={"9.52S, 41.07W"},name="Gaellant"},{locations={"28.14S, 92.17W"},name="Erydhriel"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Juniper Smith"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1324,scope="n/a",prev={1626},requiredclasses="Hunter",name="Lay of the Land",destinypoints={{val=125}},receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"},{val="Guide to Echad Dúnann",id="70017C7B"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Flambard Took",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTinúriel is at Echad Dúnann in Eregion.\nYou have been instructed to seek out the Elf Tinúriel to learn more of the ways of Eregion.\n* Talk to Tinúriel at Echad Dúnann\nObj 2:\nExplore the Elf ruins and dens of the beasts found in Eregion.\nTinúriel told you that for you to learn the quickest route to Echad Dúnann in Eregion, you must explore the land and learn its hidden tracks and paths.\n* Complete the deed \"Dens of the Beasts\"\n* Complete the deed \"The Ruins of Eregion\"\nObj 3:\nTinúriel is at Echad Dúnann in Eregion.\nNow that you have explored Eregion and become familiar with its ruins and the dens of the beasts here, you will be able to understand Tinúriel's instruction on the secret way to Echad Dúnann.\n* Talk to Tinúriel at Echad Dúnann\n//Aemeldir Location: 15.12S, 61.44W\nMirkwood >> Mirk-eaves';markerList['1879165372_0x0426A88000000077_111.3296.518481088'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879137783_0x041AD5C000000022_98.8959.531384736', new GLatLng(-25.050893554688, 64.150400390625), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879137783_0x041AD5C000000022_98.8959.531384736'; markers['1879137783_0x041AD5C000000022_98.8959.531384736'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Tinúriel Location: 50.50S, 7.91W\nEregion >> Nan Sirannon';markerList['1879137783_0x041AD5C000000022_98.8959.531384736'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879137783_0x041AD5C000000022_98.8959.531384736', new GLatLng(-25.050893554688, 64.150400390625), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879137783_0x041AD5C000000022_98.8959.531384736'; markers['1879137783_0x041AD5C000000022_98.8959.531384736'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Tinúriel Location: 50.50S, 7.91W\nEregion >> Nan Sirannon';markerList['1879137783_0x041AD5C000000022_98.8959.531384736'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879165372_0x0426A88000000077_111.3296.518481088', new GLatLng(-32.37556640625, 169.18457519531), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879165372_0x0426A88000000077_111.3296.518481088'; markers['1879165372_0x0426A88000000077_111.3296.518481088'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Aemeldir Location: 15.12S, 61.44W\nMirkwood >> Mirk-eaves';markerList['1879165372_0x0426A88000000077_111.3296.518481088'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker); GME_DEFAULT_ICON = G_DEFAULT_ICON;      } else {        document.getElementById(\"map3143695894\").innerHTML = \"In order to see the map that would go in this space, you will need to use a compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap3143695894);\n//]]>\nQuest: Lay of the Land\nCategory: Mirkwood\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 56\nPrerequisite Quests:Patrolling the Beach\nNext Quests:Engaging the Enemy\nRewards\nMoney:\n28 35Reputation:\n+300 with Malledhrim\nItem Advancement ExperienceDestiny Points:\n125\nReceive:\nMalledhrim Bronze Feather (x3)\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nThe Elves of the Golden Host seek a way to cripple the Orcs of Durbúrz-stazg.\nBestower\nAemeldir (NPC)\n'Hail, (your name)! Falasgon was right to send you to me. The Orcs of Dol Guldur mustering in the Mirk-eaves were well nigh destroyed, but a few survived and have holed up in the ruins of their encampments, attempting to regroup against us.\n'One such encampment is Durbúrz-stazg, which lies just to the north of Echad Sirion. While the encampment was severely damaged in our first assault, it may still only be entered through two gateways.\n'Go north and find the gateways into Durbúrz-stazg and determine which one is the least heavily guarded; it is upon that gate that we shall lean our assault.'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nDurbúrz-stazg lies to the north of Echad Sirion.\nAemeldir has asked you to scout the gates of Durbúrz-stazg to determine which is the least guarded.\n* Scout the southern gate of Durbúrz-stazg\n* Scout the eastern gate of Durbúrz-stazg\nObj 2:\nAemeldir is at Echad Sirion, south of Durbúrz-stazg.\nYou should return to Aemeldir with the results of your patrol.\n* Talk to Aemeldir at Echad Sirion"},
{["next"]={1032},area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="The leader of the Wood-trolls has been discovered in Glâd Ereg. This may be an opportunity to end their threat in the holly-forest once and for all.",mobs={{locations={"40.05S, 15.96W"},name="Lithuilas"}},selectoneof={{val="Lithuilas' Bow",id=70016108},{val="Saviour of Sâd Thareg",id=70016116},{q="(x3)",val="Infused Athelas Essence",id="7000EA7F"}},category="Eregion",id=1325,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1310},name="Leader of the Foul Wood",arcs="A Foul Wood",level=49,c={"* Zagâfum is found inside a cave Tawarond in Sâd Thareg [42.3N, 16.4W]\n* Quest:Instance: Leader of the Foul Wood"},minlevel=44,b="Lithuilas",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nZagâfum, the leader of the Wood-trolls can be found in the cave of Sâd Thareg, south of Gwingris.\nLithuilas has instructed you to defeat Zagâfum.\n* Defeat Zagâfum\nObj 2:\nLithuilas is at Gwingris, north of Sâd Thareg.\nYou should return to Lithuilas with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Lithuilas at Gwingris"},
{area="Lugazag",zone="Ettenmoors",d="When the Rat-folk in the south were discovered, they scored a blow against the scouts who found them, slaughtering all but one. The leader of the rat-folk village was responsible for the attack, and Taskmaster Fikdag thinks that you can assist with exacting vengeance.",category="Lugazag",id=1326,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Leader of the Rat-folk",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Taskmaster Fikdag",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nMake your way south along the Hoardale river to the village of Hoarhallow.\nTaskmaster Fikdag directed you to find and kill Mayor Wat Mudbottom, the leader of the rat-folk village.\n* Kill 1 Mayor Wat Mudbottom\nObj 2:\nTaskmaster Fikdag is at Dâr-gazag.\nYou stalked through the trails to the centre of Hoarhallow and struck down their leader. You should return to Taskmaster Fikdag with the news.\n* Talk to Taskmaster Fikdag",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="Glóin received information from Rivendell that there are several leaders in the depths of Goblin-town. Vighar Roadwalker, under orders of Glóin, offers rewards for hunting down these leaders within Goblin-town.",mobs={{locations={"24.66S, 3.78W"},name="Vighar Roadwalker"}},selectoneof={{val="Doom of Dâgal",id="7000D2FE"},{val="Avorlang",id="7000D2D0"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1327,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1454},name="Leaders of the Deep",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Vighar Roadwalker",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblin-leaders Zagh, Dâgal and Farmak dwell within Goblin-town. Goblin-town lay far to the north-east of Glóin's camp.\nVighar Roadwalker has tasked you with hunting down and defeating several leaders within the depths of Goblin-town.\n* Find and defeat Zagh Master of the Guard\n* Find and defeat Farmak the Best Runner\n* Find and defeat Dâgal the Observer\nObj 2:\nVighar Roadwalker is at Glóin's camp in the Misty Mountains, far to the south-west of Goblin-town.\nYou found the goblin leaders throughout Goblin-town. Dâgal watched over the Orcs from Angmar, Zagh traveled the tunnels yelling at the guards, and Farmak was found running through the tunnels in search of intruders. Now that thay have been defeated, you should return to Vighar.\n* Talk to Vighar Roadwalker at Glóin's camp"},
{area="Coldfells",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Lieutenant Ingi not only desires the destruction of the goblins, but the dismantling of their leadership as well. He knows that Bok and Gasham are both leaders amongst the Snowreap goblins and wants them removed.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1328,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Leaders of the Goblins",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Ingi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGrothum, the goblin-village in Arador's End, lies to the north. One of the leaders there watches the road into the Isendeep, the other hides deep within the crags of the camp.\nLieutenant Ingi's hatred for the goblins knows no bounds. He wishes you to target the leaders of the Snowreap tribe at Grothum and remove them from the area.\n* Kill 1 Bok\n* Kill 1 Gasham\nObj 2:\nLieutenant Ingi is at Ost Ringdyr, south of Grothum.\nFighting through the Snowreap village of Grothum you found and defeated the two goblin leaders, Bok and Gasham. Now you should return to Lieutenant Ingo for your reward.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Sixteenth Hall is an area overrun with Orcs, many of whom suffer from a terrible illness that sweeps through. Shamans tend to the ill whilst the rest of the halls are defended by those that remain able to do battle.\nMallas, an Elf ally to the dwarves, belives that there is something secret beneath the Sixteenth Hall and wishes to learn the true purpose and source of the plague.",mobs={{locations={"13.15S, 101.21W"},name="Odmar"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1329,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Leaders of the Hosts",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Odmar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGuardians, Shamans, and fungal Orc bombs can be found in the Sixteenth Hall, north-east of the Shadowed Refuge.\nOdmar sent you to find and destroy the Orcs that he believes are leading this diseased incursion into the Sixteenth Hall.\n* Kill 8 Moria Guardian\n* Kill 4 Moria Curse-shouter\n* Kill 6 Crazed Globsnaga\nObj 2:\nOdmar is in the Shadowed Refuge, south-west of the Sixteenth Hall.\nYou fought valiantly against the infected Orcs of the Sixteenth Hall and defeated many guardians, Shamans and the Orcs bearing terrible fungus. You should now tell Odmar that you did as he bade.\n* Return to Odmar at the Shadowed Refuge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1380},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",d="Longo Burrows was of no help in discovering what has become of Gerebert Took, but Esilia thought of someone else you could speak with.",mobs={{locations={"33.03S, 71.08W"},name="Esilia Took"},{locations={"33.42S, 65.66W"},name="Rollo Boffin"}},category="Shire",id=1330,scope="n/a",prev={86},name="Leaf in Woodhall",arcs="Took and Tower",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Esilia Took",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nRollo Boffin is in Woodhall, east of Tuckborough on the Stock Road.\nSince Longo Burrows was unhelpful in learning Gerebert's location, Esilia asked you to speak with Rollo Boffin. Since Rollo oversees much of the pipe-weed that passes through Woodhall, and Gerebert hid on a waggon carrying leaf that was travelling to the east, he may know something about Gerebert.\n* Talk to Rollo Boffin",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={141},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="30s 80c"}},d="At the request of the Ranger Gondranc, you went to the camp of the Earth-kin north-east of Esteldín to retrieve a book of leatherworking lore Asikko, the Earth-kin's chieftain, had promised him. With this lore, he will be able to make much better armour for the people of Trestlebridge.",mobs={{locations={"9.69S, 42.06W"},name="Gondranc"}},selectoneof={{val="Gondranc's Mantle",id="70006AC8"},{val="Drake-hunter's Shoulders",id="70006B24"},{val="Drake-hunter's Gauntlets",id="70006B48"},{val="Rodonham",id="70006AAE"},{val="Faelchrist",id="70006B97"}},category="North Downs",id=1331,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2266},name="Leathery Wings of the Drakes",arcs="Drake-hunter",level=34,minlevel=29,b="Gondranc",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDrakes can be found in the western valley of Ram Dúath, north of Esteldín.\nTo finish the armour he is crafting for the people of Trestlebridge, Gondranc is in need of the leathery hide from the wings of drakes. He has asked you to gather allies and hunt drakes in Ram Dúath.\n* Bring the drake-hides back to Gondranc\n* Turn in Drake-leather Hide"},
{["next"]={3231},area="Celondim",zone="Ered Luin",d="Toronn wants to leave Middle-earth and journey into the West to the Undying Lands, but will not leave as long as his brother, Bregar, refuses to leave.",mobs={{locations={"28.07S, 92.36W"},name="Toronn"},{locations={"24.02S, 92.57W"},name="Bregar"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1332,scope="n/a",prev={1703},name="Leaving Middle-earth",arcs="Brotherly Bond",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Toronn",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBregar is at Duillond, north of Celondim.\nToronn has asked you to try to convince Bregar to accompany him into the West.\n* Talk to Bregar",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1372},area="Nud-melek",zone="Moria",money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="Geirfast has observed goblins dragging supply-carts to their encampments and is concerned that they may be gathering provisions for a major offensive.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1333,scope="n/a",name="Leaving the Mines",arcs="Out of the Mines",level=57,pois={{locations={"8.50S, 102.12W","8.63S, 102.71W","8.51S, 103.23W","8.55S, 102.38W","8.53S, 103.08W","7.88S, 102.69W","8.85S, 102.91W","8.77S, 102.18W","8.72S, 102.89W","8.26S, 102.47W","8.61S, 103.40W","8.09S, 102.35W"},name="Mine-cart"}},minlevel=52,b="Geirfast",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe mine carts are in Nud-melek between Khadar-zarâm and the Bridge of Khazad-dûm, to the south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nMazog's forces are dragging mining-carts filled with supplies through Nud-melek. The dwarves would like to upset this train.\n* Use Mine-cart\nObj 2:\nGeirfast is in the Twenty-first Hall, north-west of Khadar-zarâm.\nGeirfast will be pleased to hear that the carts have been destroyed.\n* Talk to Geirfast in the Twenty-first Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Lothlórien",area="Caras Galadhon",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Rilhathel is determined to sing songs of your efforts in defence of Lórien, and has issued you a truly legendary challenge in addition to simply repelling the Orcs.",mobs={{locations={"16.11S, 67.02W"},name="Rilhathel"}},titles={{val="Victory in Lórien"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1334,scope="n/a",name="Legendary Sentinel's Challenge",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Rilhathel",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nRilhathel has asked you to not only successfully win the battle for Lórien, but to also defeat both Narshpug and Grakâmâb before they leave the field of battle, to prevent Belvagor from sustaining any serious wounds, and to do it all within thirty minutes.\n* You must complete Rilhathel's most legendary challenge during the Battle of Lórien\nObj 2:\nRilhathel has asked you to not only successfully win the battle for Lórien, but to also defeat both Narshpug and Grakâmâb before they leave the field of battle, to prevent Belvagor from sustaining any wounds, and to do it all within thirty minutes.\n* Successfully complete the Battle of Lórien\n* Defeat Narshpug\n* Defeat Grakâmâb\nObj 3:\nRilhathel is at Caras Galadhon, waiting to hear if you successfully completed his legendary challenge.\n* Talk to Rilhathel at Caras Galadhon",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Caras Galadhon",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Lembas is the fabled waybread of Lórien, and a staple for those who stand long guard-shifts.",mobs={{locations={"14.77S, 67.93W"},name="Basdan"},{locations={"16.16S, 67.04W"},name="Minathlang"},{locations={"15.47S, 66.06W"},name="Losdirith"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1335,scope="n/a",name="Lembas for the Gates",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,c={"* Losdirith can be found at [15.5S, 66.1W]\n* Minathlang can be found at [16.2S, 67.0W]"},minlevel=55,b="Basdan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLosdirith is at the entrance to the garden of Lady Galadriel. Minathlang is at the entrance to the city.\nBasdan has given you packets of lembas to bring to the guards at various gates within the city.\n* Talk to Losdirith\n* Turn in Packet of Lembas\n* Talk to Minathlang\n* Turn in Packet of Lembas\nObj 2:\nBasdan is on Telain Bangad in Caras Galadhon.\nYou have delivered packets of lembas to the guards and should return now to Basdan.\n* Talk to Basdan upon Telain Bangad",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="Stirred by the tales of the dwarves' lost battle, Borgar wishes now to honour the memory of the fallen dwarves.",selectoneof={{val="Borgar's Gauntlets",id=70016062},{val="Storied Blade",id=70016101}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1336,scope="n/a",prev={1801},name="Lest We Forget",arcs="Lest We Forget",level=55,c={"* Stand before the northern statue at [3.0S, 109.0W]\n* Stand before the southern fountain at [4.2S, 109.1W]\n* Stand before the central statue at [3.6S, 109.3W]"},minlevel=50,b="Borgar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are three locations in Tharâkh Bazân, west from Jazârgund where Borgar wishes you to tell the story of the battles: a northern statue, a southern fountain, and a central statue.\nBorgar wants you to honour the fallen dwarves of Moria by telling the story of the ancient lost battle at the monuments the dwarves built in Tharâkh Bazân.\n* Tell the story of the ancient battle (Perform /story)\n* Stand before the northern statue\n* Tell the story of the ancient battle (Perform /story)\n* Stand before the southern fountain\n* Tell the story of the ancient battle (Perform /story)\n* Stand before the central statue\nObj 2:\nBorgar is at Jazârgund, east of Tharâkh Bazân.\nBorgar will want to know that you honoured the ancients by telling the story of their defeat.\n* Talk to Borgar at Jazârgund"},
{area="Dol Guldur",zone="Mirkwood",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The goblins of Dol Guldur feed their Warg companions foul meats to make them stronger and more vicious.",mobs={{locations={"16.11S, 44.45W"},name="Maerwen"}},category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=1337,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Let Them Hunger",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Maerwen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Wargs and the foul meats they are fed with can be found at Draugdegil, north-east of Helethir.\nMaerwen has asked you to defeat the Wargs of Draugdegil, after tricking them into eating all of the goblins' foul meats.\n* Complete Maerwen's task\nObj 2:\nMaerwen is at Helethir, south-west of Dol Guldur.\nYou should return to Maerwen for your reward.\n* Talk to Maerwen at Helethir"},
{d="Lieutenants watch over the sergeants and lesser guards of the enemy as they drive their war-efforts deeper into the Ettenmoors. Plucking the seals worn by each of these warriors will earn you greater favour with your leaders.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1338,scope="n/a",name="Lieutenants' Seals",destinypoints={{val=500}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Chieftain Durulkum",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="Mon",o="Obj 1:\nPositions held by the enemy are often watched over by the lieutenants in their army. You may even find a lieutenant flanked by sergeants in the wild-lands.\nChieftain Durulkum commanded that you retrieve the seals worn by the lieutenants in the enemy army and return them to him at Dâr-gazag.\n* Return to Chieftain Durulkum at Dâr-gazag ()\n* Turn in Lieutenant's Seal"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Elves at the waypost atop Amon Angened provide supplies and provisions for the main force of the Malledhrim in the east.",mobs={{locations={"16.01S, 59.92W"},name="Gaerfalas"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1339,scope="n/a",prev={1961},name="Life After Death",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,pois={{locations={"16.59S, 61.72W","16.67S, 61.64W","16.70S, 61.75W","16.84S, 61.75W","16.55S, 61.72W","16.73S, 61.80W","16.63S, 61.69W","16.61S, 61.79W","16.55S, 61.77W","16.66S, 61.81W","16.83S, 61.84W","16.76S, 61.61W","16.75S, 61.77W","16.56S, 61.63W","16.70S, 61.68W","16.58S, 61.76W","16.70S, 61.66W","16.55S, 61.84W","16.74S, 61.72W"},name="Ninglor"}},minlevel=56,b="Gaerfalas",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNinglyr may be found around the ruins of Fállug, west of Amon Angened.\nGaerfalas has asked you to gather ninglor flowers for use in preparing medicines.\n* Collect ninglyr (10 Ninglor )\nObj 2:\nGaerfalas is at the waypost atop Amon Angened, east of Fállug.\nYou should bring the flowers you collected to Gaerfalas.\n* Talk to Gaerfalas\n* Turn in Ninglor"},
{area="The Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Skûmfil is nothing more than a dumping ground, a place where the fallen Orcs of Moria are discarded when they begin to reek. It is here that two foes have gathered, each intent on using the corpses found therein for their own purposes. The kergrim and other scavengers as a source of food, and the insects as a place to lay their eggs to spawn future generations.",mobs={{locations={"12.90S, 100.69W"},name="Mallas"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1340,scope="n/a",name="Life From the Dead",arcs="Skumfíl",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Mallas",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLar, Moggi, and Pentlenn are at the Shadowed Refuge.\nMallas has told you that he will speak well for you to Veúlfur at the Twenty-first Hall after you have assisted his agents in the Shadowed Refuge.\n* Assist Lar in ridding Skûmfil of gredbyg\n* Assist Moggi in ridding Skûmfil of gredbyg\n* Collect samples from the gredbyg of Skûmfil for Pentlenn\nObj 2:\nMallas is at the Shadowed Refuge.\nYou have completed all the tasks set before you by Lar, Moggi, and Pentlenn. You should now return to Mallas and inform him that your efforts are complete.\n* Talk to Mallas at the Shadowed Refuge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2574},area="Carn Dûm",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+900 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Carn Dûm is the evil heart of Angmar, a terrible city protected by gates and hordes of Orc-warriors.",mobs={{locations={"12.28N, 31.81W"},name="Éa"}},selectoneof={{val="Ethirthail",id=70002382},{val="Slave's Defence",id=70002383}},category="Carn Dûm",id=1341,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2884},name="Lifting the Yoke",arcs="Lifting the Yoke",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Éa",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCarn Dûm lies to the west of Tármunn Súrsa.\nÉa's husband Erscin and his fellow warriors were captured by Orcs and taken to Carn Dûm. She has asked you to enter Carn Dûm and rescue Erscin.\n* Free slaves in Carn Dûm (2)\nObj 2:\nÉa is at Tármunn Súrsa, east of Carn Dûm.\nThe slaves of Carn Dûm were set free and may now return to their homes, but you were unable to find Éa's husband, Erscin. You should return to Éa with the news.\n* Talk to Éa"},
{["next"]={2698},reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="With the key to the basement of the lighthouse, you can strike against what now calls it home.",category="Evendim",id=1342,scope="n/a",prev={2106},name="Lighthouse on the Baranduin",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=33,minlevel=28,b="Gaelnarthan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ruins of the lighthouse are south-east of the colossus.\nGaelnarthan asked you to venture into the lighthouse and defeat the creature you find within.\n* Defeat the creature beneath the lighthouse\nObj 2:\nGaelnarthan is at the colossus camp.\nGaelnarthan will be pleased to hear the kergrim hunting them has been defeated.\n* Talk to Gaelnarthan at the colossus camp",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{d="Winiel has deciphered the lore-fragments you brought her with the aid of the book you acquired from the toad Greatroar. With your aid she has gleaned knowledge of a fire-grim that haunts the mines of Moria.",category="Lore-master",id=1343,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1333},name="Light of the Rising Dawn",arcs="The Path of the Ancient Master",receive={{val="Scrivener's Band",id=70018382},{val="Khuzdul Tablets",id="70017AC6"}},level=58,minlevel=58,b="Winiel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nEnter the Forges of Khazad-dum, summon the fire grim, Ruingal, and slay it.\n* Use Brazier\n* Defeat Ruingal\nObj 2:\nWiniel is at the Rotting Cellar in the Water Works, north-east from the Forges of Khazad-dûm.\nYou should return to Winiel with tidings of your victory.\n* Talk to Winiel\n* Turn in Restored Tome of Ancient Runes",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="The paths of the Northcotton Farm are lit by lamps which over time will burn out and need to be replaced.",category="Evendim",id=1344,scope="n/a",name="Lights for the Market",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,minlevel=25,b="Milo Longfurrow",repeatable="No",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nBurned-out lamps can be found on the paths around the Northcotton Farm.\nMilo Longfurrow has asked you to help him illuminate the area by lighting the lamps around the Farmer's Market at the Northcotton Farm.\n* Use Light-post\nObj 2:\nMilo Longfurrow is in Northcotton Farm.\nMilo Longfurrow will be pleased to hear the lamps will burn the night through.\n* Talk to Milo Longfurrow"},
{["next"]={1654},reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="The dwarves at the Chamber of the Crossroads need help establishing their presence there.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1345,scope="n/a",name="Líkmund's Companions",arcs="Líkmund's Tasks",level=52,minlevel=47,b="Líkmund",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFostólf and Gansi are in the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nLíkmund suggested that you speak with Fostólf and Gansi and learn what tasks they might have for you.\n* Help Fostólf\n* Help Gansi\nObj 2:\nLíkmund is in the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nYou should return to Líkmund and tell him of your efforts on behalf of Fostólf and Gansi.\n* Talk to Líkmund at the Chamber of the Crossroads",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={74},area="Bruinen Gorges",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="Arrod was pleased with the feather you brought him and has been inspired by it to craft a necklace for Narlinn.",mobs={{locations={"33.76S, 14.61W"},name="Arrod"}},category="Trollshaws",id=1346,scope="n/a",prev={128},name="Lilies in the Valley",arcs="An Elf-swain's Lament",level=36,pois={{locations={"34.90S, 11.45W"},name="Perfect Lily"}},minlevel=31,b="Arrod",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nA perfect lily grows somewhere along the Bruinen east of Arrod's post.\nArrod has asked you to bring him a perfect lily of exquisite beauty. No other kind will do.\n* Find the perfect lily\nObj 2:\nArrod is watching the road through the Bruinen Gorges from his vantage point near a set of hilltop ruins, west of the Bruinen.\nArrod will be delighted to see that you have found a lily of exquisite beauty.\n* Talk to Arrod\n* Turn in Perfect Lily"},
{["next"]={831},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="42c"}},d="Gammy Boggs is certain that Falco Greenhand has gotten into some kind of trouble that he cannot get out of, and the cryptic message you received from Lily is not helping to ease her mind.",mobs={{locations={"30.98S, 47.80W"},name="Lily Underhill"},{locations={"30.97S, 48.18W"},name="Gammy Boggs"}},selectoneof={{val="Aedail",id="70006AA3"},{val="Boggs' Great Sword",id="70006B82"}},category="Bree-land",id=1347,scope="n/a",prev={828},name="Lily's Secret",arcs="Falco's Garden",level=11,pois={{locations={"32.66S, 48.89W","33.17S, 48.67W","33.75S, 48.91W","33.16S, 47.81W","32.90S, 48.92W","33.22S, 48.84W","32.58S, 48.77W","33.06S, 47.66W","33.13S, 48.95W","32.50S, 47.78W","32.56S, 48.34W","32.47S, 48.42W","32.89S, 48.25W","32.85S, 48.42W","33.73S, 49.07W","32.51S, 48.56W","33.31S, 49.18W","32.44S, 47.88W","33.03S, 47.63W","33.17S, 48.01W"},name="Red Lily"}},minlevel=7,b="Gammy Boggs",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLily Underhill can be found outside her home east of Gammy Boggs' home, at the foot of the hill, north of the road.\nGammy Boggs believes that with the proper coaxing, Lily will tell all that she knows about Falco's plight.\n* Talk to Lily Underhill at her house\nObj 2:\nRed lilies can be found in the forested area south of the Yellow Tree, well to the south of Lily Underhill's house.\nLily Underhill said she could not say specifically what Falco Greenhand's trouble was, but she could show you, if you looked at the right things. As a hint, she sent you to gather red lilies.\n* Collect red lilies (6 Red Lily )\nObj 3:\nLily Underhill can be found outside her home, east of Gammy Boggs' farm.\nLily Underhill said she could not say specifically what Falco Greenhand's trouble was, but she could show you, if you looked at the right things. As a hint, she sent you to gather red lilies. Upon finding the lilies, you also noticed the large encampment of brigands at Ost Baranor.\n* Talk to Lily Underhill\n* Turn in Red Lily\nObj 4:\nGammy Boggs is at her farm, west of Lily Underhill's house.\nLily told you -- without telling you -- that the Big Folk camped at the ruins in the south Chetwood are the reason that Falco Greenhand's farm is suffering. You should tell Gammy Boggs what you know.\n* Talk to Gammy Boggs at her farm."},
{["next"]={957},area="Nud-melek",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Káti believes that unseen lines of power criss-cross the whole of Khazad-dûm, and that their intersections have somehow caused the fungus-infested horrors.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1348,scope="n/a",name="Lines of Power",receive={{val="Káti's Detector",id="700163B2"}},level=56,c={"* The first Fungus Cluster to be examined is at [8.7S, 103.5W]\n* The second Fungus Cluster to be examined is at [8.9S, 102.5W]\n* The third Fungus Cluster to be examined is at [8.6S, 100.5W]"},pois={{locations={"8.61S, 100.51W","8.90S, 102.52W","8.74S, 103.52W"},name="Fungus Cluster"}},minlevel=51,b="Káti",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe fungus spores are along the southern wall of the great chamber of Nud-melek, below Khadar-zarâm, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nKáti wants you to find the three intersection points of the invisible lines of power in which he believes and examine the local fungus there for clues.\n* Use Fungus Cluster\n* Find the first line of power\n* Use Fungus Cluster\n* Find the second line of power\n* Use Fungus Cluster\n* Find the third line of power\nObj 2:\nKáti is in the Twenty-first Hall, north-west of Khadar-zarâm.\nKáti will want to know that his theory was wrong.\n* Talk to Káti in the Twenty-first Hall"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Captain-General Mákan does his best to assist the morale of the troops stationed at Tol Ascarnen. The relentless battle takes its toll on a being over time, and ale is the best way to keep the Free Peoples prepared.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1349,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Liquid Courage",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Solvi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nYou may be able to find some in Hoarhallow itself, but it will likely be costly. You may even find the draughts stored at Grothum and Dâr-gazag.\nLieutenant Solvi asked you to find and recover draughts of Hoarhallow-ale.\n* Return to Lieutenant Solvi at Tol Ascarnen\n* Turn in Hoarhallow Ale",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1893},area="Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",d="Before continuing your learning, Dithrik would like to see how you fare in a duel against the dwarf Brestir.",category="Guardian",id=1350,scope="n/a",prev={2689},name="Litany of Defiance",arcs="The Path of the Defender of the Free",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Dithrik",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Bridge of Khazad-dûm, where Brestir can be found, is north of the Foundations of Stone and east of the Second Hall.\nDithrik has invited you to challenge his friend Brestir to a duel to see if you are prepared for the challenges ahead.\n* Challenge Brestir to a duel at the Bridge of Khazad-dûm\nObj 2:\nReturn to Dithrik at the Foundations of Stone\n* Return to Dithrik at the Foundations of Stone",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hithlad",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="As the battle for the Ettenmoors rages on, the host of the Free Peoples is beginning to realize that they must think about reinforcing their positions throughout the land.",category="Grimwood",id=1351,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Little Folk Harvesters",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Aeglas",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nTortmund Cliffside is at the tower on the eastern border of Hoarhallow, just over the bridge.\nSergeant-at-Arms Aeglas has asked you to see the safe arrival of the hobbits from Hoarhallow. The hobbits will be assisting the Free Peoples in acquiring enough materials to create bulwarks throughout the Ettenmoors.\n* Escort Tortmund Cliffside to the Grimwood Lumber camp",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="Durin's Way",money={{val="43s 12c"}},d="The White Hand Uruk you have been chasing through Moria has established his camp in Durin's Way and is aligning the banners of several goblin and Orc-tribes under his rule.",selectoneof={{val="Ión's First Helm",id=70016053},{val="Ión's Helmet",id=70016064}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1352,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={333},name="Little Revolution",arcs="Little Revolution",level=56,c={"* Zâhof's throne is in the south-eastern corner of Fehem-dûm at [4.3S, 104.0W]"},pois={{locations={"4.28S, 104.02W"},name="Throne"}},minlevel=51,b="Ión",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nZâhof can be found at Fehem-dûm, east from Jazârgund.\nZâhof is the leader of the White Hand Uruks in Moria. If he falls, Saruman's plans for the deeps fall with him.\n* Defeat Zâhof\nObj 2:\nZâhofs throne is in Fehem-dûm, east from Jazârgund.\nIón wishes to stir up strife between the Orcs of Moria and Mordor. He gave you a banner to plant upon the throne of the fallen White Hand Uruk.\n* Use Throne\n* Turn in Banner of Mordor\nObj 3:\nIón is at Jazârgund, west from Fehem-dûm.\nIón will be pleased to hear Zâhof is dead and the Mordor-banner has been planted on his throne.\n* Talk to Ión at Jazârgund"},
{["next"]={1057},area="Gloomglens",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You discovered an object which by all appearances belongs to a child, though it does not seem to be Dunlending in nature.",mobs={{locations={"63.47S, 21.46W"},name="Idhrenfair"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1353,scope="n/a",name="Little Wonders",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,c={"* Small Arrow [64.3S, 22.2W]\n* Small Boots [61.3S, 19.2W]\n* Small Bucket [63.3S, 22.2W]\n* Small Skeleton [63.3S, 22.6W]\n* Small Tool [64.6S, 20.4W]\n* Small Bow [63.7S, 23.0W]"},minlevel=60,b="Small Arrow",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are Rangers at Echad Idhrenfair in the Gloomglens.\nYou should bring the object you found to the Rangers of the Grey Company. Perhaps they will be able to unravel the mystery.\n* Talk to a Ranger at Echad Idhrenfair"},
{["next"]={1941},area="The Hill",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Lobelia Sackville-Baggins is planning a birthday party for herself grand enough to outshine that of Bilbo Baggins several years before. She wants fireworks worthy of her efforts.",mobs={{locations={"33.44S, 71.42W"},name="Hyacinth Took"},{locations={"29.36S, 71.33W"},name="Lobelia Sackville-Baggins"}},category="Shire",id=1354,scope="n/a",name="Lobelia's Fireworks",arcs="Lobelia's Fireworks",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Lobelia Sackville-Baggins",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHyacinth Took is in Tuckborough, west of the Great Smials.\nLobelia Sackville-Baggins has heard that Hyacinth Took knows the art of making fireworks and asked that you place an order for her biggest and brightest.\n* Talk to Hyacinth Took\nObj 2:\nLobelia Sackville-Baggins is at her home at Bag End in Hobbiton.\nLobelia Sackville-Baggins sent you to order fireworks from Hyacinth Took, but Hyacinth informed you that she was out of both fireworks and the materials to make them. She told you to return to Hobbiton and make sure Lobelia will be expected to pay for the materials, if she still wants fireworks.\n* Talk to Lobelia Sackville-Baggins\nObj 3:\nHyacinth Took is west of the Great Smials in Tuckborough.\nHyacinth Took sent you back to Lobelia Sackville-Baggins to request payment for the ingredients to make her fireworks. Lobelia reluctantly agreed and gave you a coinpurse to take back to Hyacinth.\n* Talk to Hyacinth Took\n* Turn in Coin-pouch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2051,2050,2045,2053,2054,2052,2047,2046,2055,2048,2056,2049},area="Hobbiton-Bywater",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Opal Goodbody, who is helping organize Lobelia's upcoming party, has been bothering Holly Hornblower to deliver a pie for the party.",mobs={{locations={"31.21S, 71.11W"},name="Holly Hornblower"}},category="Shire",id=1355,scope="n/a",prev={1635},name="Lobelia's Pie",arcs="Hot Pie Delivery",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Holly Hornblower",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOpal Goodbody is at the Party Field, north of Hobbiton and south of Bag End.\nWhen you returned from delivering a pie to The Green Dragon, Holly Hornblower had another delivery task waiting for you: she has asked you to take the pie she baked for Lobelia Sackville-Baggins's birthday party to Opal Goodbody at the Party Field in Hobbiton, south of Bag End and north of the town proper. Make sure that no hungry hobbits catch a whiff of the pie, or they will be pestering Holly for a slice!\n* Pick up the pie\nObj 2:\nHolly Hornblower can be found north of the main square of Hobbiton and south of the Party Field.\nWhen you delivered the pie to Opal Goodbody, she tasted it and found that it tasted awful. She demanded a new one from Holly Hornblower. You should return to Holly at once.\n* Talk to Holly Hornblower"},
{["next"]={3206},area="The Twenty-first Hall",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="27s 65c"}},d="Geirfast wants to know more about why Mazog's Orcs had all those supply-carts. He thinks that the Dhognûrz, the Orc-lieutenants, might have information.",selectoneof={{val="Symbol of War",id="700163AC"},{val="Goblin Knee-capper",id="700163FC"}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1356,scope="n/a",prev={1349},name="Locating the Advance Guard",arcs="Out of the Mines",level=58,minlevel=53,b="Geirfast",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe orders will be found on the Moria Orc-leaders gathering just before the Bridge of Khazad-dûm in Nud-melek, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nGeirfast told you of a meeting of Mazog's lieutenants. He believes one of them will have a note detailing their plans.\n* Turn in Orders (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nGeirfast is in the Twenty-first Hall, far to the west of the Bridge of Khazad-dûm.\nGeirfast will want to study the orders as soon as possible.\n* Talk to Geirfast\n* Turn in Orders (Level 1)"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyrn Fornech",money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Dry logs can be found around Nan Orngon. The bears root them up when they dig for grubs.",mobs={{locations={"7.19S, 64.43W"},name="Poppy Seaton"}},category="Evendim",id=1357,scope="n/a",name="Logs for the Fire",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=35,pois={{locations={"7.01S, 61.51W","7.49S, 61.36W","7.37S, 61.28W","7.34S, 61.53W","7.11S, 61.95W","7.28S, 61.63W","7.08S, 61.83W","7.07S, 61.40W","7.22S, 61.63W","7.06S, 61.45W","6.99S, 61.57W","7.12S, 61.32W","7.01S, 61.63W","7.07S, 61.75W","7.04S, 61.70W","7.11S, 61.25W"},name="Dry Log"}},minlevel=30,b="Poppy Seaton",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nNan Orngon is east of Ost Forod.\nPoppy Seaton has asked you to venture to Nan Orngon and collect dried logs.\n* Collect dry logs (8 Dry Log )\nObj 2:\nPoppy Seaton is at Ost Forod, west of Nan Orngon.\nPoppy Seaton will be pleased to see all of the wood you collected.\n* Talk to Poppy Seaton\n* Turn in Dry Log",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1905},area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",d="Londrandir, an Elf from the refuge of Lin Giliath, has come to Amon Raith, seeking the aid of the Rangers in a small matter.",mobs={{locations={"12.49S, 52.77W"},name="Londrandir"},{locations={"13.67S, 44.63W"},name="Aglardir"}},category="North Downs",id=1358,scope="n/a",prev={2542},name="Londrandir's Message",level=26,minlevel=21,b="Londrandir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLachenn and Aglardir are at Lin Giliath in Meluinen, east of Amon Raith and south of the road through the Kingsfell.\nSince it is clear that the Rangers have their own burdens to bear, Londrandir has asked you to journey east to speak with Lachenn, the Master of Lin Giliath. If Lachenn is unavailable, he told you to speak instead with Aglardir.\n* Talk to Lachenn or Aglardir at Meluinen",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="Tham Laegamon is a ruin that overlooks the Way of Kings and the entrance to the city of Annúminas.",category="Evendim",id=1359,scope="n/a",name="Longbows of Tham Laegamon",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=37,minlevel=32,b="Rodlam",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTham Laegamon is to the south-west of the Ranger-camp in the Way of Kings.\nRodlam asked you to venture to Tham Laegamon and gather longbows from the tomb-robbers there.\n* Turn in Long-bow\nObj 2:\nRodlam is at the Ranger-camp in the Way of Kings.\nRodlam will want to see the longbows you collected from Tham Laegamon.\n* Talk to Rodlam\n* Turn in Long-bow",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Kingsfell",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="11s 50c"}},d="Farmer Gatson's farmhand, Gilmar, says that new blood is needed for the cattle herd. An aurochs-bull would do nicely, but the wild bulls are far too aggressive to drive to his pasture. Gilmar has asked you to obtain a yearling instead.",mobs={{locations={"10.31S, 45.62W"},name="Gilmar"}},selectoneof={{val="Gilmar's Gloves",id="700018DA"},{val="Gilmar's Rune-stone",id="700161BE"}},category="North Downs",id=1360,scope="n/a",name="Long-horns",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Gilmar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAurochs yearlings can be found amidst the small herd to the south-east of Gatson's farm.\nGilmar, Gatson's farmhand, has asked you to pick out an aurochs-yearling from the local herd and drive it over to his pasture.\n* Find an aurochs-yearling\nObj 2:\nGilmar is back on Gatson's farm.\nYou have brought the aurochs-yearling to Gatson's pasture, now you should return to Gilmar to tell him of your success.\n* Talk to Gilmar",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Bindbole Wood",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 60c"}},d="Polo Proudfoot needs new queens for his hives to replace the ones killed by the honey-bears.",mobs={{locations={"28.26S, 70.19W"},name="Gammer Boffin"}},selectoneof={{val="Beekeeper's Robes",id="70000DDC"},{val="Beekeeper's Hood",id="70000DDB"},{val="Hive Tending Boots",id="70000DDD"}},category="Shire",id=1361,scope="n/a",prev={156},name="Long Live the Queen",arcs="Long Live the Queen",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Gammer Boffin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFarmer Proudfoot is guarding his hives in the meadow south-east of Tuckborough. The wild beehives you are looking for are in a bear-infested area further south-east past the meadow.\nFarmer Proudfoot sent you to Gammer Boffin in Overhill to obtain some balm to keep off the bees, so you can collect a hive for him. Gammer Boffin warned you that the salve will not last long, so you will need to collect the hive as soon as possible and take it to Polo Proudfoot.\n* Find a wild hive before the salve dries\nObj 2:\nPolo Proudfoot would like to take a moment to thank you for your efforts."},
{["next"]={86},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",d="Esilia Took discovered from her cousin's journal that Gerebert was dared to hide on the waggon of a local pipeweed farmer, Longo Burrow, as it went east. She is becoming more concerned, as the entry in the journal was written some time ago, and Longo Burrow's farm is not that far away.",mobs={{locations={"33.12S, 70.43W"},name="Longo Burrow"},{locations={"33.03S, 71.08W"},name="Esilia Took"}},category="Shire",id=1362,scope="n/a",prev={984},name="Longo's Leaf-waggon",arcs="Took and Tower",level=8,minlevel=4,b="Esilia Took",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLongo Burrow is at his farm on the Stock Road, east out of Tuckborough.\nUpset greatly by her cousin's disappearance, Esilia Took has asked you to speak with Longo Burrow to learn if he has seen Gerebert.\n* Talk to Longo Burrow",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1574},area="Green Hill Country",zone="The Shire",d="Rollo Boffin, who oversees the leaf-waggons that come through Woodhall, mentioned that one of Longo Burrow's waggons did go missing a while ago and thinks that perhaps it is related to the disappearance of Gerebert Took.",mobs={{locations={"33.42S, 65.66W"},name="Rollo Boffin"}},category="Shire",id=1363,scope="n/a",prev={1346},name="Longo's Missing Waggon",arcs="Took and Tower",level=10,pois={{locations={"33.33S, 67.50W"},name="Abandoned Waggon"}},minlevel=6,b="Rollo Boffin",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLongo's waggon may be at the Stock Road clearing due west of Woodhall, by the Wellbridge.\nRollo Boffin did not have any information specifically about Gerebert Took, but now wonders if Gerebert's disappearance and the disappearance of Longo Burrow's waggon are somehow connected. He has asked you to go search a clearing just off the Stock Road for any sign of the missing waggon.\n* Use Abandoned Waggon\nObj 2:\nRollo Boffin can be found in the centre of Woodhall.\nAt the Stock Road clearing, you found an abandoned waggon. Your examination of the waggon revealed that it once carried pipe-weed, but all the pipe-weed was removed and carried off to the south.\n* Talk to Rollo Boffin",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Dannasen's desire to be avenged upon the Hillmen of Rhudaur is shared by Emelin, the leader of the shades of Arthedain who dwell in the southern bog.",mobs={{locations={"37.71S, 28.02W"},name="Emelin"},{locations={"29.67S, 27.39W"},name="Dannasen"}},selectoneof={{val="Créoth's Bane",id="700006D1"},{val="Créoth's Justice",id="700006D0"},{val="Emelin's Pads",id="700006D2"},{val="Shield of Rhudaur",id="700006CF"}},category="Garth Agarwen",id=1364,scope="n/a",prev={2798},name="Long Overdue Justice",arcs="Long Overdue Justice",level=32,c={"* The Créoth's are inside the instance Garth Agarwen: Fortress"},minlevel=27,b="Dannasen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Hillmen of Rhudaur occupy the ancient ruins called Garth Agarwen in the north-east of Agamaur. Adherents follow the Red-maid but are not truly Hillmen, they are drawn from the the Grim Créoth, Créoth Apprentices and the Créoth Disciples. The devoted are drawn from the Créoth Devout and Créoth Wardens. Lastly, the masters are drawn from the Créoth Chieftains and Leaders.\nThe shade explained that the Rhudaur were responsible for raising the Red-maid, an evil creature of great power, and were in some way also responsible for the curse that holds the shades of Arthedain in Middle-earth. He has asked you to destroy the Hillmen, allowing him and his brethren to fulfil their curse.\n* Defeat Créoth Apprentices and Disciples (16)\n* Defeat Créoth Wardens (10)\n* Defeat Créoth Chieftains (12)\nObj 2:\nEmelin resides with his brethren in the southernmost reaches of the Harloeg.\nYou were sent to destroy the Hillmen of Rhudaur who dwell within Garth Agarwen. Your victory was not complete, but you struck a telling blow against the Hillmen. Emelin should be told of your efforts.\n* Talk to Emelin"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="42s"}},d="On a clear day you can see nearly across the entirety of Lake Evendim.",category="Evendim",id=1365,scope="n/a",name="Look to the Horizon",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrchalwë spoke of spending time by the shore looking to the far horizon.\n* Look to the horizon (Perform /look)\n* Find a place to look over Lake Evendim\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will want to hear what you thought while looking to the horizon.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
