ring the droppings and flowers you collected back to Iago Glennudh.\n* Talk to Iago Glennudh at Maur Tulhau",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",money={{val="42s 56c"}},d="The mirror located deep within the Water-works has been twisted and is no longer illuminating the flooded depths.",selectoneof={{q="(x4)",val="Brewed Healing Draught",id="7000EFC6"},{q="(x4)",val="Infused Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA8E"},{q="(x4)",val="Brewed Milkthistle Draught",id="7000EFC5"},{q="(x4)",val="Brewed Flask of Conhuith",id="7000EFC4"},{q="(x4)",val="Brewed Flask of Lhinestad",id="7000EFC3"},{q="(x4)",val="Infused Athelas Essence",id="7000EA7F"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1461,scope="n/a",prev={1478},name="Mirror in the Mire",level=55,c={"* The Mirror is in The Lost Palace at [15.1S, 114.8W]"},pois={{locations={"15.11S, 114.78W"},name="Mirror (Level 1)"}},minlevel=50,b="Thrand",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe dwarf-mirror can be found near The Lost Palace, on the western edge of the Water-works and directly west of the Rotting Cellar.\nThrand has asked you to find the mirror within the Water-works and adjust it so it works again.\n* Use Mirror (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nThrand is in the Rotting Cellar, on the eastern edge of the Water-works.\nThrand will be pleased to hear the mirror has been adjusted and light shines throughout the Water-works, at least for today.\n* Talk to Thrand in the Rotting Cellar"},
{["next"]={1477,1808,78,100,1805,1806,1807,1809},area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="41s 44c"}},d="Thettmárr believes that, with the adjustments to the positions of other mirrors he made, a mirror he previously examined might light up nearby crystals.",selectoneof={{val="Mirror Fragment",id="700163B1"},{val="Survivalist's Bracelet",id="70017CDF"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1462,scope="n/a",prev={640},name="Mirror, Mirror",arcs="A Faint Gleam",level=53,pois={{locations={"10.95S, 113.01W"},name="Mirror"}},minlevel=48,b="Thettmárr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTo find the mirror, start from the Deep Descent, head down, and take the western passage. Follow the path until you come to a four-way crossing of mining-cart rails, then follow the left one east and down until you reach the stone cavern-floor.\nThettmárr has asked you to swivel a mirror in the caverns below so that the light strikes the crystals he described.\n* Use Mirror\nObj 2:\nThettmárr is in the Deep Descent camp.\nYou should tell Thettmárr what happened when you swivelled the mirror.\n* Talk to Thettmárr at the Deep Descent encampment"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="Tham Sarch is an ancient ruin that overlooks Lake Evendim from the hills above the southern shore.",category="Evendim",id=1463,scope="n/a",name="Mirrors of Tham Sarch",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=37,minlevel=32,b="Nethrandir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMirrors can be found on tomb-robbers at Tham Sarch, south-west of the Ranger-camp in the Way of Kings.\nNethrandir asked you to recover mirrors from the tomb-robbers in Tham Sarch.\n* Turn in Mirror\nObj 2:\nNethrandir is at the Ranger-camp in the Way of Kings.\nNethrandir will want to examine the mirrors you collected.\n* Talk to Nethrandir\n* Turn in Mirror",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="Ansurr has traded arrows with the Orc Urbhrum for several weeks now. Neither have hit their targets, but he has enjoyed the challenge of their nightly duels. He has not seen an arrow for several days and fears his opponent has fallen to the fungus.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1464,scope="n/a",name="Missing Arrows",level=55,c={"* The Chamber of Dark Waters is at [16.1S, 111.9W]"},minlevel=50,b="Ansurr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBy the flight of the arrows, Ansurr believes Urbhrum can be found near The Chamber of Dark Waters, south of the Rotting Cellar.\nAnsurr has asked you to find and defeat Urbhrum.\n* Find and defeat Urbhrum\nObj 2:\nAnsurr is in the Rotting Cellar, north of The Chamber of Dark Waters.\nYou should return to Ansurr and inform him of your victory against the infected Urbhrum.\n* Talk to Ansurr at the Rotting Cellar",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1015,801},area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="7s"}},d="A cart bound for Bree and due to return to the Forsaken Inn is several days overdue. The recent arrival of goblins and other foes has Anlaf the Forlorn worried that something happened to the cart and its driver.",mobs={{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Anlaf the Forlorn"}},category="Lone-lands",id=1465,scope="n/a",name="Missing Supply Cart",arcs="Inn Troubles",level=22,pois={{locations={"34.48S, 42.56W"},name="Destroyed Supply-cart"},{locations={"34.47S, 43.03W"},name="Cart-driver"}},minlevel=17,b="Anlaf the Forlorn",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAnlaf's missing cart travelled west towards Bree along the Great East Road.\nAnlaf has asked that you search north and south of the cart's estimated route to learn its fate and the fate of its driver.\n* Use Destroyed Supply-cart\n* Use Cart-driver\nObj 2:\nAnlaf is at the Forsaken Inn.\nYou discovered that the cart was destroyed, its supplies stolen, and the driver killed by the nearby goblins. Anlaf should be given this unfortunate news.\n* Talk to Anlaf the Forlorn",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Ronald Dwale is indisposed and will be unable to attend the next meeting of his writing society.",mobs={{locations={"33.38S, 75.36W","33.38S, 75.35W"},name="Jack Lewisdown"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Greater Celebrant Ointment",id="70008D0E"},{q="(x3)",val="Greater Athelas Extract",id="70008D0A"}},category="Evendim",id=1466,scope="n/a",prev={1802},name="Missing the Meeting",arcs="Missing the Meeting",receive={{val="Ronald Dwale's Pipe",id="7000A2F6"},{q="(x3)",val="Brandy Wine",id=70003707},{q="(x3)",val="Superior Steak and Kidney Pie",id="7000336E"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="Ronald Dwale",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Bird and Baby Inn is in Michel Delving, west across the road from Town Hole.\nRonald Dwale has asked you to speak with his friends at The Bird and Baby Inn and let them know that he will not be able to make their next meeting.\n* Talk to Jack Lewisdown\nObj 2:\nRonald Dwale is at Hob Hillbrow's home at the Bullroarer's Sward in Dwaling.\nYou should return to Ronald Dwale and inform him that you completed his task.\n* Talk to Ronald Dwale"},
{area="Ram Dúath",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 5c"}},d="You have assisted the Earthkin scout, but the morroval-threat remains, endangering the Earth-kin and all else who dwell in the hills of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"3.81S, 36.31W"},name="Earth-kin Scout"}},selectoneof={{val="Estelphadanir",id="70002CDD"},{val="Earth-kin's Shoulder Guards",id="70002CDF"},{val="Fall of the Mistress",id="70002CDE"}},category="Angmar",id=1467,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={3244},name="Mistress of Shadows",arcs="Mistress of Shadows",level=42,c={"* The cave Rimpúrod that contains Morcheryn is found down the narrow passage through some cliffs a little north and west of the Earth-kin Scout. She is at the far back of the cave, on the right side. It is recommended to bring 3-5 players to defeat her, since she is an Elite and has a few adds."},minlevel=37,b="Earth-kin Scout",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMorcheryn dwells in a cave on the east side of Ram Dúath, where the other merrevail can also be found.\nThe Earth-kin scout has asked you to seek out and destroy the leader of the Merrevail for the safety of his people. He also suggested you take friends.\n* Slay Morcheryn\nObj 2:\nThe Earthkin Scout is hidden in a valley east of Duvairë in the Ram Dúath.\nWith the Mistress of Shadows slain, you should return to him.\n* Talk to Earth-kin Scout"},
{area="Eryn Laer",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="An arrogant Orc named Târgrat holds great sway over many of his followers, and it would be best if he were removed from his post. Unfortunately, he commands a powerful troll bodyguard. Maenhador believes that the Orc's pride may be his weak point, if you can find some way to exploit it.",mobs={{locations={"12.07S, 71.12W"},name="Maenhador"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1468,scope="n/a",prev={1883},name="Mockery",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,c={"* Târgrat can be found at Nardur-stazg camp [8.3S, 73.5W]"},minlevel=55,b="Maenhador",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTârgrat is at Nardur-stazg in Fanuidhol, north-west of Talan Fanuidhol.\nIn order to defeat Târgrat, despite the protection of his troll bodyguard, Maenhador has suggested that you try mocking him before his underlings.\n* Mock Târgrat the Proud (Perform /mock)\n* Find Târgrat's encampment\nObj 2:\nTârgrat is at Nardur-stazg in Fanuidhol, north-west of Talan Fanuidhol.\nIn his rage over your insults, Târgrat the Proud has forsaken the protection of his bodyguard to pursue you personally. You must defeat him in battle.\n* Defeat Târgrat the Proud\nObj 3:\nMaenhador is at Talan Fanuidhol, south-east of Nardur-stazg.\nYou should return to Maenhador with tidings of your victory against Târgrat.\n* Talk to Maenhador at Talan Fanuidhol"},
{reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyl Annûn",money={{val="41s 30c"}},d="The forces of Angmar have erected several monuments around the city of Annuminas.",selectoneof={{val="Lockmaster Helmet",id="70025DE1"},{val="Helm of the Oathesworn",id=70026518},{val="Helm of the Arnorian Holdfast",id="700261A1"},{val="Helm of Forgotten Hope",id="70025FCA"},{val="Helm of the Northern Star",id="700260D7"},{val="Helm of the Heartmender",id=70026277},{val="Hood of Long Memory",id="700261E6"},{val="Hat of the Vicious Proclamation",id="700264A5"},{val="Helm of True Aim",id="700261CA"}},category="Evendim",id=1469,scope="n/a",name="Monuments of Angmar",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=38,pois={{locations={"19.83S, 70.07W","16.81S, 69.67W","18.04S, 70.62W","17.94S, 69.09W","18.78S, 69.02W","17.10S, 71.11W"},name="Monument to Angmar"}},minlevel=33,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMonuments of Angmar are spread throughout the ruins of Annuminas.\nOrchalwë asked you to find several Monuments of Angmar throughout the ruins and hang flags of the Rangers from them.\n* Use Monument to Angmar\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will want to speak about the Monuments of Angmar.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={591},area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="7s"}},d="Agnes Martlet learned from Amarion that there is something wrong with the bears on the Fields of Fornost, and she is worried that some of them may find their way to her farm.",category="North Downs",id=1470,scope="n/a",prev={2673},name="More Business With Bears",arcs="Agnes and the Bears",level=22,minlevel=17,b="Agnes Martlet",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are bears on the Fields of Fornost, north-west of Amon Raith.\nAgnes Martlet has asked you to deal with the corrupted bears on the Fields of Fornost before they make their way to her farm.\n* Slay Bears in the Fields of Fornost (16)\nObj 2:\nAgnes Martlet is at Amon Raith, south-east of the Fields of Fornost.\nAgnes will be pleased to hear that you have defeated many of the corrupted bears on the Fields of Fornost.\n* Talk to Agnes Martlet"},
{area="Tâl Bruinen",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="22s 5c"}},d="The hunter Cerys is concerned about the Stone-trolls that wander into Tâl Bruinen during night-time and wants something done about them.",mobs={{locations={"37.01S, 14.10W"},name="Cerys"}},selectoneof={{val="Cerys' Gem",id="7000D2C6"},{val="Stone-troll Bane",id="7000D2E4"},{val="Cerys' Shield",id="7000D2CA"}},category="Trollshaws",id=1471,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="More Confused Than Usual",level=42,minlevel=37,b="Cerys",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nStone-trolls sometimes wander out of the north into Tâl Bruinen by night.\nThe hunter Cerys has asked you to combat the Stone-trolls that come into Tâl Bruinen at night-time. He also suggested you take friends.\n* Defeat Stone-trolls in Tâl Bruinen (4)\nObj 2:\nCerys is at Echad Candelleth, the Elf-camp in Tâl Bruinen.\nYou have defeated a number of confused and angry Stone-trolls and should report of your victory to Cerys.\n* Talk to Cerys"},
{area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Celebrandir in Gwingris has offered to make you more holly leaf tea if you bring him enough leaves.",mobs={{locations={"40.04S, 16.00W"},name="Celebrandir"}},category="Eregion",id=1472,scope="n/a",prev={1110},name="More Holly Leaf Tea",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Cup of Red Tea",id="7001549C"}},level=48,pois={{locations={"42.44S, 13.11W","42.36S, 12.97W","42.09S, 13.48W","41.44S, 16.29W","42.07S, 15.80W","42.33S, 15.84W","41.70S, 16.75W","41.90S, 16.37W","42.72S, 13.66W","42.58S, 13.39W","42.07S, 16.33W","42.34S, 13.87W","41.66S, 16.03W","42.42S, 13.92W","41.43S, 16.94W","42.18S, 13.36W","42.74S, 13.84W","41.60S, 16.14W","42.10S, 12.90W","42.42S, 13.30W","42.23S, 13.12W","41.67S, 16.99W"},name="Green Holly-leaf"}},minlevel=80,b="Celebrandir",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nHolly leaves can be found at the bases of holly-trees in Pend Eregion.\nYou should gather more holly leaves and bring them to Celebrandir in Gwingris.\n* Bring the leaves to Celebrandir in Gwingris.\n* Collect Holly Leaves (8 Green Holly-leaf ).",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={630},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="Darri thinks that a friend of his, Thettmárr, might know more about the mirrors. Thettmárr is at the Deep Descent, south of the Dolven-view.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1473,scope="n/a",prev={830},name="More Mirrors?",arcs="A Faint Gleam",level=52,minlevel=47,b="Darri",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThettmárr is at the Deep Descent in the Silvertine Lodes in Moria.\nDarri has recommended that you find his friend Thettmárr and seek his advice on the matter of the mirrors.\n* Talk to Thettmárr"},
{["next"]={393},zone="Bree-land",area="Combe",money={{val="90c"}},d="Constable Sageford believes there may be a second lockbox in the Blackwold's main camp in northern Chetwood.",mobs={{locations={"28.56S, 49.21W"},name="Constable Sageford"}},selectoneof={{val="Delicate Golden Bracelet",id="70019BDB"},{val="Fine Golden Bracelet",id="70019BEC"}},category="Bree-land",id=1474,scope="n/a",prev={2784},name="More Treasure",arcs="Blackwold Valuables",level=10,pois={{locations={"26.60S, 44.02W"},name="Blackwold-strongbox"}},minlevel=6,b="Constable Sageford",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe main Blackwold camp is in the ruins of northern Chetwood, just east of Combe.\nConstable Sageford has asked you to search the Blackwold camp for another strongbox.\n* Collect Blackwold strongbox\nObj 2:\nConstable Sageford can be found near Combe town-centre.\nSageford sent you to the Blackwold Headquarters to find another strongbox. You should return to Sageford with the news of your success.\n* Talk to Constable Sageford\n* Turn in Blackwold-strongbox"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="Bennt Sharp-eye has told you about the Iron Garrison. This company of dwarves is comprised of two parties, the Iron Garrison Guards and the Iron Garrison Miners. While both parties are dedicated to reclaiming Moria, they focus on different threats. The Guards are more concerned with the Orcs infesting Moria, while the Miners seek to reclaim lost treasures and watch for hidden, deeper foes.",mobs={{locations={"8.61S, 112.26W"},name="Bennt Sharp-eye"}},category="Moria",id=1475,scope="n/a",name="Moria's Iron Garrison",receive={{val="Uncut Moria-adamant",id=70017555}},level=52,minlevel=47,b="Bennt Sharp-eye",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBroken engravings can be reclaimed from beasts and other threats in Moria. Bennt Sharp-eye is at the Dolven-view camp.\nBennt Sharp-eye asked you to bring him some broken engravings.\n* Bring the broken engravings to Bennt Sharp-eye\n* Turn in Broken Engraving",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2328},area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Keli has figured out why the snow-beasts have been so aggressive recently and wants you to kill their matron.",mobs={{locations={"9.43N, 81.22W"},name="Keli"}},selectoneof={{val="Keli's Charm",id="7000E5D8"},{val="Keli's Bauble",id="7000E5CA"}},category="Forochel",id=1476,scope="n/a",prev={363},name="Mother of Beasts",arcs="Peikko-slayer",level=47,c={"* The Great Snow-matron is inside the Peikko Cave [9.5N, 79.9W]"},minlevel=42,b="Keli",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Great Snow-matron can be found in the cave east and up the hill from Zigilgund.\nKeli has asked you to rid Forochel of the Great Snow-matron who has been stirring up the peikko.\n* Defeat the Great Snow-matron\nObj 2:\nKeli is at Zigilgund, west of the peikko-cave.\nYou should return to Keli with news of your victory of the Great Snow-matron.\n* Return to Keli at Zigilgund"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="30s 24c"}},d="A drake-matron, the mother of the brood you destroyed, resides within the western valley of Ram Dúath. The pass will not be safe until she is slain.",mobs={{locations={"9.68S, 42.04W"},name="Arastil"}},selectoneof={{val="Arastil's Helmet",id="70006A8E"},{val="Arastil's Hat",id="70006AEE"},{val="Matron's Bane",id="70006BD7"},{val="The Matron Hunter",id="70006BAE"},{val="Arastil's Headgear",id="70006AA0"},{val="Matron's End",id="70006BCF"}},category="North Downs",id=1477,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={712},name="Mother of the Valley",arcs="Valley of the Worms",level=33,minlevel=28,b="Arastil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe drake-matron resides within the western pass of Ram Dúath, north-east of Esteldín.\nArastil has set you one more task: slay the drake-matron of Ram Dúath. As long as she lives, she will only spawn a new brood. Arastil warns you to take allies, for the drake-matron is likely to be enraged by the loss of her brood.\n* Kill 1 Drake Matron\nObj 2:\nArastil awaits you at Esteldín.\nArastil will be pleased to know that you have slain the matron. Return to him at Esteldín with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Arastil"},
{["next"]={1922},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="34s 72c"}},d="Hostile giants in the Stonemere south of Rivendell have violated an ancient treaty by coming down from the mountains and into the Trollshaws.",mobs={{locations={"29.80S, 5.47W"},name="Ringhul"}},category="Trollshaws",id=1478,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={8},name="Mountain Raiders",arcs="Thunder in the Mountains",level=41,minlevel=36,b="Ringhul",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe hostile giants are south of Rivendell, beyond the High Moor, in the Stonemere near the hill where you found Arifael.\nRinghul has asked you to make your way into the Stonemere to defeat the hostile giants and slay their leader.\n* Kill 6 Giant Stone-breaker\n* Kill 6 Giant Rock-thrower\n* Kill 1 Giant Head-smasher\nObj 2:\nRinghul is at Rivendell, waiting to hear that you have defeated some of the giants in the Stonemere.\nRinghul asked you to defeat the hostile giants that have come down from the mountains.\n* Talk to Ringhul"},
{area="Caras Galadhon",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Gandalf the Grey fell in Moria, and his loss has been felt by many of the Elves he once knew.",mobs={{locations={"14.68S, 66.27W"},name="Demlindeth"},{locations={"15.47S, 66.06W"},name="Losdirith"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1479,scope="n/a",name="Mourning Mithrandir",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,c={"* The place within the canopy that matches Losdirith's description is at [14.3S, 66.8W]"},minlevel=55,b="Demlindeth",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLosdirith watches the gate to the garden of Lady Galadriel, south along the path from the pavilion where Demlindeth sings songs of mourning.\nDemlindeth has asked you to speak words of comfort to Losdirith, who has been acting strangely in the wake of Mithrandir's passing.\n* Talk to Losdirith at the gate of Galadriel's Garden\nObj 2:\nTelain Neduil consists of a series of flets north-west of Galadriel's Garden in Caras Galadhon, and the leaves grow over the edge of one of its flets.\nLosdirith wants you to stand at the place he saw in his dream, within the canopy of leaves that cover part of a flet in Telain Neduil, and to look for Gandalf.\n* Look for Mithrandir beneath the overhanging canopy (Perform /look)\n* Travel to Telain Neduil and find the flet where the canopy of leaves intrudes on the platform\nObj 3:\nLosdirith is outside the entrance to Galadriel's Garden.\nLosdirith will want to hear what you saw when you looked through the canopy of leaves at Telain Neduil, even if it is not what he hoped.\n* Talk to Losdirith at the gate to Galadriel's Garden",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Combe",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="42c"}},d="Gail Catchpole's father perished in the flames of The Mad Badger Inn, and many of their belongings were stolen by the Blackwold brigands.",mobs={{locations={"29.13S, 48.30W"},name="Constable Wren"},{locations={"28.53S, 49.52W"},name="Gail Catchpole"}},selectoneof={{val="Catchpole's Gloves",id="70019BD6"},{val="Catchpole's Gauntlets",id="70019BD8"}},category="Bree-land",id=1480,scope="n/a",name="Mourning the Dead",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Gail Catchpole",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nConstable Wren can be found at the guard-house on the hill east of Combe.\nGail wants to find the brigands who stole her dead father's favourite fishing pole and retrieve it. She has sent you to ask Constable Wren for information about the brigands and where they might have taken her stolen goods.\n* Talk to Constable Wren\nObj 2:\nThe main encampment of the Blackwolds is in the Chetwood, north of the guard-house.\nConstable Wren suggested that the brigand who looted the fishing pole belonging to Gail Catchpole's dead father may be near the watering hole beneath the Blackwold main encampment.\n* Deliver the fishing pole to Gail Catchpole\n* Turn in Favourite Fishing-rod",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Arador's End",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="In the crags to the west of the Isendeep, the Shadowmaw pack bolsters the forces of Angmar.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1481,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Mouth of Shadow",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Octa",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Shadowmaw stalk the Steps of Gram.\nLieutenant Octa at the Isendeep Mine asked you to reduce the threat posed by the Shadowmaw-wargs.\n* Defeat Shadowmaw-wargs (20)\nObj 2:\nLieutenant Octa is at the Isendeep Mine.\nLieutenant Octa will be pleased to learn that you have succeeded at destroying a good number of the Wargs in the Steps of Gram.\n* Return to Lieutenant Octa at the Isendeep Mine",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1388},area="Carn Dûm",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+900 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="The Gertheryg, the terrible troll-kin of Angmar, pose one of the greatest threats to the Free Peoples.",mobs={{locations={"12.33N, 31.76W"},name="Táni"}},selectoneof={{val="Estellin",id=70002390},{val="Táni's Boots",id="7000238F"}},category="Urugarth",id=1482,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Moving Mountains",arcs="Lord of the Gertheryg",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Táni",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGertheryg may be found in Urugarth, west of Tármunn Súrsa.\nTáni asked you to seek out the trolls and their leader and slay them all.\n* Kill 1 Dushkâl\n* Defeat trolls in Urugarth (10)\nObj 2:\nTáni is at Tármunn Súrsa, east of Urugarth.\nWith the trolls and their leader defeated, it is time to return to Táni.\n* Talk to Táni"},
{area="Frostbluff",zone="Frostbluff",money={{val="90c"}},d="Hungry beggars can often get too close to the Festival area in Winter-home, which is a strict violation of the Mayor's rules to keep the Yule Celebration pleasant for all.",category="Frostbluff",id=1483,scope="n/a",prev={2658},name="Moving Them Off",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Frostbluff Coin",id="70024EB1"}},level=10,c={"* The beggars are scattered around town.  If the beggars are not there, wait for them to respawn."},minlevel=6,b="Guard Kember",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe beggars can be found in the streets throughout town, and since the Mayor finds them unsightly, Guard Kember has asked you to make them leave.\nYou should remove beggars from the streets about town so that the Festival patrons won't be upset by them.\n* Tell Barrett Nowell to move off\n* Tell Ted Ives to move off\n* Tell Regina Judson to move off\n* Tell Jack Judson to move off\n* Tell Bill Hyde to move off\nObj 2:\nGuard Kember is near the gate of Winter-home.\nYou should return to Guard Kember and tell him that the beggars have been successfully moved away from the eyes of the town.\n* Return to Guard Kember",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The Elves in Eregion use lynx-pelts to craft their cloaks.",mobs={{locations={"46.98S, 12.48W"},name="Lengliel"}},category="Eregion",id=1484,scope="n/a",name="Moving Unseen",receive={{val="Lynx's Cloak",id="7001605B"}},level=49,c={"* Lynx can be found prowling in High Hollin, north-east of Echad Eregion. A high concentration of Lynx can be found at Talath Dindal."},minlevel=44,b="Lengliel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLynx can be found prowling in High Hollin, north-east of Echad Eregion.\nLengliel has asked you to collect lynx-pelts for her, so that she can make cloaks for the scouts.\n* Talk to Lengliel at Echad Eregion\n* Turn in Hollin Lynx-pelt",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={222},area="Buckland",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="86c"}},d="Trumric Ragwort has given you directions to go and meet Adso Haybank himself. He deems it only fitting for all the work you have done.",mobs={{locations={"29.12S, 56.78W"},name="Adso Haybank"},{locations={"31.56S, 62.55W"},name="Trumric Ragwort"}},category="Bree-land",id=1485,scope="n/a",prev={1971},name="Mr. Haybank Meet....",arcs="A Right Proper Place",level=16,minlevel=11,b="Trumric Ragwort",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAdso Haybank is at his camp, about half the distance between Bree and the Buckland Gate, eastward along the Great East Road.\nTrumric Ragwort sent you on to meet Adso Haybank.\n* Talk to Adso Haybank at Adso's Camp"},
{reputation={{val="+1200 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Thrór's Coomb",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="South of Harndirion, there is a small series of ponds which are the prime watering holes of the deer which inhabit Thrór's Coomb.",mobs={{locations={"67.43S, 13.92W"},name="Gronu"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1486,scope="n/a",prev={1995,1916},name="Much-needed Supplies",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"67.06S, 13.94W"},name="Dunlending Cart"}},minlevel=65,b="Gronu",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDeer can be found among a series of ponds, south of Harndirion and Gronu's camp.\nGronu has asked you to hunt the deer that water nearby to help provision his village.\n* Turn in Slab of Wild Venison\nObj 2:\nThe cart lies to the north of Gronu, on the southern shore of the river.\nGronu asked you to bring the venison which you collected and place it on the cart his party left behind.\n* Use Dunlending Cart\nObj 3:\nGronu is at his camp to the south of the cart.\nYou should return to Gronu and let him know that the cart has been filled.\n* Talk to Gronu at his camp",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={864},money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="One of the main features of the Northcotton Farmer's Market is its animal petting area.",category="Evendim",id=1487,scope="n/a",prev={975},name="Mudding the Pigs",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,minlevel=25,b="Gerard Deephole",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe bucket can be found at the nearby pond.\nGerard Deephole asked you to mud the pigs.\n* Mud the pigs\n* Use Water bucket\nObj 2:\nGerard Deephole is at the animal pens on the Northcotton Farm.\nGerard Deephole will be pleased to hear that the pigs have been mudded.\n* Talk to the Gerard Deephole",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Angmar",area="Fasach-falroid",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Raghnaid has charged you with ending the reign of Muiráthakh, the Silent Judge, who holds Donnvail in a grip of fear.",mobs={{locations={"7.31N, 35.44W"},name="Raghnaid"}},selectoneof={{val="Acharcham",id="70006B17"},{val="Gollonn",id="700031A6"},{val="Doom of the Silent Judge",id=70003031}},category="Angmar",id=1488,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2458},name="Muiráthakh, the Silent Judge",level=44,minlevel=39,b="Raghnaid",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMuiráthakh, the Silent Judge, holds court deep within the city of Donnvail, through the arch east of Una and her allies.\nRaghnaid has tasked you and your allies with ending the reign of Muiráthakh.\n* Defeat Muiráthakh\nObj 2:\nRaghnaid is within the city of Donnvail, north-east of Fail-á-Khro.\nYou have defeated Muiráthakh and should bring news of your triumph to Raghnaid.\n* Talk to Raghnaid",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1762},reputation={{val="+700 with Council of the North"}},zone="Angmar",area="Imlad Balchorth",money={{val="38s 64c"}},d="Birgir was pleased with the disruption you caused among the ranks of the Angmarim already, but he feels it was not quite enough.",mobs={{locations={"6.95N, 25.86W"},name="Birgir"}},selectoneof={{val="Birgir's Shield",id="700161D6"},{val="Otham",id="7000136F"},{val="The Keepers Fall",id="7000136E"},{val="Birgir's Boots",id="7000136D"}},category="Angmar",id=1489,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2432},name="Múl Kholuim, The Keeper of Books",arcs="Highwayman",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Birgir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMúl Kholuim has his camp inside a ruin in some high hills south of the large lake in Imlad Balchorth, west from Myrkworth. Birgir has asked you to find the camp of the Angmarim keeper of books.\n* Discover the library of Múl Kholuim\nObj 2:\nYou have found Múl Kholuim's camp inside a ruin in the high hills south of the large lake in Imlad Balchorth.\nBirgir has asked you to defeat Múl Kholuim. He also warned you to gather allies.\n* Kill 1 Múl Kholuim\nObj 3:\nBirgir is at Myrkworth, northeast from Múl Kholuim's camp.\nHaving defeated Múl Kholuim, you should return to Birgir.\n* Talk to Birgir"},
{["next"]={2800},area="Men Erain",zone="Evendim",money={{val="21s"}},d="The ancient ruins of Evendim and those who watch over them are endangered by tomb-robbers.",mobs={{locations={"15.31S, 66.16W"},name="Helechír"}},category="Evendim",id=1490,scope="n/a",prev={2732},name="Murder in the Ruins",arcs="Breakfast in the Ruins",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,c={"* Glirion can be found in the ruins of Arthobel [17.8S, 64.9W]"},minlevel=34,b="Helechír",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlirion makes his camp in a ruin high atop the hills of Men Erain, overlooking the lake.\nHelechír has sent you to aid Glirion, a Ranger helping to guard the Dúnadan-ruins near Annúminas. He warned you that the roads through the highlands have been mostly lost to time, and it will not be easy to climb to the heights.\n* Talk to Glirion\nObj 2:\nHelechír is a little north-west of the Ranger camp on the island of Tinnudir, north and east of Men Erain.\nYou helped Glirion fight off a band of tomb-robbers and should bring word of your success back to Helechír.\n* Talk to Helechír"},
{["next"]={843,2288},area="Emyn Lûm",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Fuirgam believes that the Enemy will use the crebain of Mirkwood as spies against the Malledhrim.",category="Mirkwood",id=1491,scope="n/a",name="Murder on the Wing",arcs="The Wild Ruins",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,minlevel=58,b="Fuirgam",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Wild Ruins lie to the south of Ost Galadh.\nFuirgam has asked you to thin the flocks of crebain that inhabit the Wild Ruins.\n* Defeat crebain within the Wild Ruins (16)\nObj 2:\nFuirgam is at Ost Galadh, north of the Wild Ruins.\nYou should tell Fuirgam that the crebain in the Wild Ruins have been dealt with.\n* Talk to Fuirgam in Ost Galadh"},
{area="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eldgang"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Lore found in the library of Rivendell tell that a particularly deadly variety of mushroom grows within the Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu. This mushroom might be used by the Enemy to create a terrible weapon.",mobs={{locations={"10.83N, 15.56W"},name="Galasebdir"}},selectoneof={{val="Obsidian Rock-shard",id="7000C7BE"},{q="(x2)",val="Scrap of Rift-iron Ore",id="7000C7CC"}},category="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",id=1492,scope="n/a",name="Mushroom for Rivendell",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Galasebdir",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCurtamusgan may be found within the Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu.\nGalasebdir has asked you to bring him a Curtamusgan, so that the scholars at Rivendell might study it and prepare a defence against its poison should Angmar use it as a weapon.\n* Use Curtamusgan\nObj 2:\nGalasebdir is at Iorelen's camp.\nYou have found a Curtamusgan and should bring it to Galasebdir at once.\n* Talk to Galasebdir\n* Turn in Curtamusgan"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="Thrand believes the fungus forms into mushrooms growing on the lake. In his opinion, the Orcs must have eaten the mushrooms, and that is what caused them to become infected.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1493,scope="n/a",name="Mushroom Picking",level=55,pois={{locations={"15.76S, 113.48W","15.36S, 113.86W","15.64S, 113.72W","15.48S, 113.48W","15.40S, 113.17W","15.12S, 112.62W","15.00S, 113.41W","14.82S, 112.71W","15.92S, 113.86W","15.43S, 112.79W","15.64S, 112.60W","15.57S, 113.14W","15.31S, 113.18W","15.06S, 113.59W","15.36S, 113.24W","16.19S, 113.26W","15.20S, 113.63W","15.04S, 112.52W","15.63S, 113.46W"},name="Fungus Mushroom"}},minlevel=50,b="Thrand",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMushrooms can be found around the water's edge to the west of the Rotting Cellar.\nThrand thinks destroying the mushrooms will slow the spread of the fungus into the Orc-population.\n* Use Fungus Mushroom\nObj 2:\nThrand is in the Rotting Cellar, east of the water's edge.\nYou have destroyed many mushrooms and should now return to Thrand.\n* Return to Thrand in the Rotting Cellar",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mirobel",zone="Eregion",money={{val="41s 44c"}},d="If you are to enter the School at Tham Mírdain, I beseech you to seek out whatever remnants of the great knowledge held within you may find. There may be nothing remaining therein or there may be some scrap of knowledge that seems to be naught, but if there is even the least of scraps, the Enemy must not be allowed to obtain it.\nWhat knowledge might remain in the School would be held within the main hall, where all would come to listen to the discourse presented by the greatest crafters of Eregion.\nSeek out this knowledge and bring whatever you find there to me.",category="Eregion",id=1494,scope="n/a",name="Musings and Teachings",receive={{val="Eregion Mark",id="700216BE"}},level=53,minlevel=48,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe School at Tham Mírdain lies to the east, up a small incline from the northern slopes of Echad Mirobel.\nEvil threatens to claim the lost knowledge of Eregion, and it falls to you to recover this knowledge before it is truly lost forever. Faellien has asked you to bring any scraps of knowledge you find back to Echad Mirobel.\n* Collect scraps of knowledge (6 Scrap of Knowledge)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Andrath",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="2s 15c"}},d="The goods and coin typically coming from the southern lands are a lifeblood in Bree. Without the materials much of Bree-land will suffer. Watcher Oakdale asked that you retrieve some of the materials the brigands procured from caravans unwilling to pay the price to pass through.",category="Bree-land",id=1495,scope="n/a",prev={2618},name="Must Have...",level=16,minlevel=11,b="Watcher Oakdale",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSeek out stolen caravan goods within the walls of the Southwatch and carried by the enemies making the ruins their home. Return all that you find to Watcher Oakdale to east of the north entrance of the ruins.\nCaravans cannot all afford to pass through the gates and those that cannot lose their goods to the brigands and all of Bree-land suffers.\n* Deliver the goods to Watcher Oakdale\n* Turn in Caravan Goods",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Many dark and evil things dwell in the southern forests of Mirkwood. Among those are the black wolves.",mobs={{locations={"13.56S, 58.11W"},name="Lavanferon"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1496,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Muzzling the Pack",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,minlevel=57,b="Lavanferon",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBlack wolves can be found throughout the Dourstocks. Blackmaw can be found at the Packhowler's Hill, some distance to the south-east from Echad Mothelen.\nLavanferon has asked you to defeat many wolves and their pack-leader, Blackmaw.\n* Defeat Blackmaw at the Packhowler's Hill\n* Defeat wolves in the Dourstocks (10)\nObj 2:\nLavanferon is at Echad Mothelen, some distance north-west from the Packhowler's Hill.\nYou should return to Lavanferon with news of your success.\n* Talk to Lavanferon at Echad Mothelen"},
{["next"]={1993,1599},area="Northern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 28c"}},d="One of Saeradan's brethren recently called for aid against a foe that the Rangers of the North know all too well.",mobs={{locations={"23.74S, 53.55W"},name="Andreg"},{locations={"25.55S, 52.88W"},name="Saeradan"}},category="Bree-land",id=1497,scope="n/a",name="My Brethren's Call",arcs="My Brethren's Call",level=18,minlevel=13,b="Saeradan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAndreg waits at his post at the Greenway Fort, north along the Greenway from Saeradan's Cabin.\nSaeradan sent you to assist Andreg, one of his kindred.\n* Talk to Andreg at the Greenway Fort",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1668},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Bilbo Baggins has completed his book and would like to make certain that his memory of the important locations and events is correct.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Bilbo Baggins"},{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Pure Flask of Conhuith",id="7000C638"},{q="(x5)",val="Pure Flask of Lhinestad",id="7000C634"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1498,scope="n/a",prev={1623},name="My Dwarf Friends",arcs="Dim Memories of the Dark",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Distilled Celebrant Salve",id="70000F40"}},level=48,minlevel=43,b="Bilbo Baggins",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDwalin is at Thorin's Hall far to the west, beyond the Shire. Glóin is at his camp north of Rivendell.\nBilbo Baggins would like to know if his dwarf-friends Dwalin and Glóin have any recollections which would make good additions to his book.\n* Talk to Glóin in the Misty Mountains\n* Talk to Dwalin\nObj 2:\nBilbo Baggins is at Rivendell in the Trollshaws, south of Glóin's camp and far to the east of Thorin's Hall.\nDwalin and Glóin both shared stories of their adventure in Goblin-town. Now you should return to Bilbo.\n* Talk to Bilbo Baggins in Rivendell"},
{["next"]={1695},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",d="When her grandson Wilcome was younger, Gammer Tunnelly always made him his lunch. Now that he's moved to Scary, where he oversees the quarry, she doesn't get the chance. However, she missed making it so much that she's made him a very special lunch today, but cannot walk all the way to Scary to deliver it to him. She's asked you to take it to him.",mobs={{locations={"27.93S, 66.29W"},name="Wilcome Tunnelly"},{locations={"32.97S, 71.02W"},name="Gammer Tunnelly"}},category="Shire",id=1499,scope="n/a",name="My Grandson's Lunch",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=12,minlevel=8,b="Gammer Tunnelly",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWilcome Tunnelly is the supervisor of the quarry in Scary, to the north-east.\nGammer Tunnelly has asked you to bring the lunch she prepared to her grandson Wilcome, in Scary.\n* Talk to Wilcome Tunnelly\n* Turn in Lunch-basket",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Carn Dûm",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+300 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="The bracelet you found belonged to a girl of the Hillmen called Dírdrë. Her mother wonders if she could still be alive.",mobs={{locations={"12.28N, 31.81W"},name="Éa"}},category="Angmar",id=1500,scope="n/a",prev={2585},name="My Heart's Hope",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Éa",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDírdrë might be found in Nan Gurth, south-east of Carn Dûm.\nÉa's daughter was taken from her many years ago. It could be that Dírdrë still lives.\n* Find Dírdrë",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={185},area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Déornyd has lost his prized weapon, a sword belonging to his sister, who was a champion of great renown among the Eglain.",mobs={{locations={"11.37N, 69.82W"},name="Déornyd"}},category="Forochel",id=1501,scope="n/a",name="My Sister's Sword",arcs="A Champion's Weapons",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Déornyd",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDéornyd thinks his sister's sword is still in or around the ice canyons, south of Pynti-peldot.\nDéornyd has asked you to find his sister's sword and return it to him.\n* Turn in Gránung\nObj 2:\nDéornyd is at Pynti-peldot, north of the ice canyons.\nYou have found Gránung and should now return it to Déornyd at Pynti-peldot.\n* Talk to Déornyd\n* Turn in Gránung",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1934},area="Lich Bluffs",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You have taken a sample of a strange fetid liquid from outside one of the barrows in the Lich Bluffs.",mobs={{locations={"70.57S, 15.46W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1502,scope="n/a",name="Mysterious Residue",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Puddle of Vile Liquid",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMincham's camp is located north and west of the main road, in the north-west portion of the Lich Bluffs.\nYou should return to Mincham and provide him with a sample of the foul liquid that you have recovered.\n* Talk to Mincham in the Lich Bluffs\n* Turn in Mysterious Residue"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="Durin's Way",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Dór of the Chamber of the Crossroads explored near the entrance to Nalâ-dûm near where the Water-wheels once turned, and he is concerned by the abundance of noisome croaking that emerged from within that grimy place. He is certain the the lizards' filth is at least partially responsible for the clogging of the Water-wheels.",mobs={{locations={"5.17S, 111.96W"},name="Dór"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=1503,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Nalâ-dûm: An Abundance of Grime",arcs="The Water-wheels",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Dór",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNalâ-dûm, where the Water-wheels lie still, is below the Chamber of the Crossroads in the Water-works.\nDór wishes for you to defeat lizards around the Water-wheels because of the damage they must wreak upon Nalâ-dûm. He warned that you should take a friend or two with you.\n* Defeat lizards in Nalâ-dûm (25)\nObj 2:\nDór is at the Chamber of the Crossroads, awaiting news of your venture into Nalâ-dûm.\nYou should return to Dór and tell him of your success against the lizards around the Water-wheels.\n* Talk to Dór"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="Durin's Way",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Dór of the Chamber of the Crossroads believes that worms will be among the creeping, slimy beasts in Nalâ-dûm where the Water-wheels sleep. The scales of rock-worms can be used to lend extra strength to armour.",mobs={{locations={"5.17S, 111.96W"},name="Dór"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=1504,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Nalâ-dûm: Hard-plated Armour",arcs="The Water-wheels",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Dór",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe scales can be found on the skins of worms in Nalâ-dûm, below the Chamber of the Crossroads in the Water-works.\nYou should collect scales while in Nalâ-dûm for the dwarves to tailor into their armour. This will strengthen their defences significantly.\n* Turn in Rock-worm scale\nObj 2:\nDór is north of Nalâ-dûm, in the Chamber of the Crossroads in Durin's Way.\nYou should bring the scales to Dór so that he may begin to craft better armour for the dwarves of the expedition.\n* Talk to Dór\n* Turn in Rock-worm scale",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="Durin's Way",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Dór of the Chamber of the Crossroads explored near the entrance to Nalâ-dûm where the Water-wheels once turned, and he recalls that a great feeling of menace turned him from his path.",mobs={{locations={"5.17S, 111.96W"},name="Dór"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=1505,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Nalâ-dûm: Menace of Nalâ-dûm",arcs="The Water-wheels",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Dór",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nNalâ-dûm, where the Water-wheels lie still, is far below of the Chamber of the Crossroads in the Water-works of Moria.\nDór has asked you to travel to Nalâ-dûm and defeat the menace that lurks deep inside that forsaken hall. He warned you to take a friend or two with you.\n* Defeat the menace in Nalâ-dûm\nObj 2:\nDór is at the Chamber of the Crossroads in Moria, above Nalâ-dûm in Durin's Way.\nYou should return to Dór and tell him of the Caerog you bested, thus removing the menace of the Water-wheels.\n* Talk to Dór at the Chamber of the Crossroads",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2318,637},zone="Enedwaith",area="Thrór's Coomb",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Among the dwarf-ruins to the south of Zudrugund, there are two large encampments. These encampments are a mockery to the ancient halls found below.",mobs={{locations={"65.57S, 8.48W"},name="Frithgeir"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1506,scope="n/a",prev={2356},name="Nár Sends His Regards",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Frithgeir",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nMafân-mudun is located in the southeastern reaches of Thrór's Coomb, and the High Home may be found in the shadow of Harndirion to the south-east.\nFrithgeir has asked you to defeat giants at Mafân-mudun and the High Home.\n* Defeat giants near the High Home (5)\n* Defeat giants near Mafân-mudun (5)\nObj 2:\nFrithgeir is at Zudrugund, north of Mafân-mudun and the High Home.\nYou should return to Frithgeir and inform him that Nár's regards have been imparted upon the giants invading Thrór's Coomb.\n* Talk to Frithgeir at Zudrugund",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={207},area="Emyn Lûm",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Lomdognir wonders if the glowing glands of the local fireflies can be used as a more reliable source of light in the unnatural mists surrounding Mirkwood.",category="Mirkwood",id=1507,scope="n/a",name="Natural Light",arcs="Forests of Emyn Lûm",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,minlevel=58,b="Lomdognir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFireflies can be found throughout Emyn Lûm.\nLomdognir has asked you to hunt down the fireflies in Emyn Lûm and attempt to collect a handful of the glands that produce a glow, which can cast a light even through the mists enshrouding Mirkwood.\n* Turn in Glowing Gland\nObj 2:\nLomdognir is at Ost Galadh.\nYou should return to Lomdognir with the firefly-glands which you have collected.\n* Talk to Lomdognir\n* Turn in Glowing Gland"},
{area="Hobbiton-Bywater",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Shirriff Smallburrow believes you should become acquainted with the other Shirriffs and Bounders.",mobs={{locations={"31.35S, 71.13W"},name="Shirriff Robin Smallburrow"},{locations={"28.23S, 75.84W"},name="Bounder Chubb"}},selectoneof={{val="Chubb's Helmet",id="70000DCE"},{q="(x3)",val="Cooked Carrots",id="700005F4"}},category="Shire",id=1508,scope="n/a",name="Needlehole Watch",level=8,minlevel=4,b="Shirriff Robin Smallburrow",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBounder Chubb can be found on duty near the road leading into Needlehole, due north of Michel Delving, north-west of Hobbiton.\nShirriff Smallburrow has asked you to travel to Needlehole and offer your services to Bounder Chubb.\n* Talk to Bounder Chubb",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1003},area="Celondim",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Bregedúr, at the Craftsman's Plaza in Celondim, asked that you deliver a cask meant for storing wine to his friend Brethilwen at Limael's Vinyard.",mobs={{locations={"26.67S, 94.94W"},name="Brethilwen"},{locations={"28.22S, 92.66W"},name="Bregedúr"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1509,scope="n/a",prev={1679},name="Need of a Cask",arcs="Vintner's Aid",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Bregedúr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou will find Brethilwen to the north and west at the outskirts of Limael's Vinyard. Make your way along the roadway heading north-west out of Celondim and follow the small path along the river to the west to find her.\nBregedúr, the local cooper at Celondim, asked you to deliver a cask to his friend Brethilwen at Limael's Vinyard.\n* Talk to Brethilwen\n* Turn in Wine-cask"},
{area="Andrath",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="2s 15c"}},d="Watcher Oakdale asked you for a personal favour while in the area of Southwatch.",category="Bree-land",id=1510,scope="n/a",prev={2618},name="Neeker-breaker",level=16,minlevel=11,b="Watcher Oakdale",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe swamp to the north and east of the Watcher's position outside the Southwatch is home to noisy neeker-breekers.\nWatcher Oakdale has asked for your assistance in eliminating the creatures so that he might find a pleasing rest.\n* Defeat Neeker-breekers in Andrath (12)\nObj 2:\nWatcher Oakdale will be pleased to know that the number of neekers near his encampment at the east edge of the north edge of the Southwatch is diminished.\nWatcher Oakdale has asked for your assistance in eliminating the creatures so that he might find a pleasing rest.\n* Return to Watcher Oakdale",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Midgewater Marshes",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Roderick Neeker-friend is worried about Sniken, his pet Neekerbreeker, and has asked for your help cheering him up.",mobs={{locations={"32.52S, 43.47W"},name="Roderick Neeker-friend"}},category="Bree-land",id=1511,scope="n/a",name="Neeker-friend",receive={{val="Roderick's Key",id="70007A35"},{val="Sniken's Fang",id="70006BD3"}},level=14,minlevel=10,b="Roderick Neeker-friend",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGreater sickle-flies are found mainly in the southern Midgewater Marshes. Roderick Neeker-friend is camped atop a cliff near the Goblinhole Ruins in the south-east part of the Midgewater Marshes.\nRoderick Neeker-friend asked you to collect wings from the sickle-flies found in the Midgewater Marshes to help feed his pet Neekerbreeker, Sniken.\n* Bring the sickle-fly wings to Roderik Neeker-friend\n* Turn in Sickle-fly Wing",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2039},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Though always on the watch for the goblins, Watcher Reedy believes the creatures of the Midgewater Marshes, east of Staddle, are no less of a threat to the town.",mobs={{locations={"31.09S, 49.39W"},name="Watcher Reedy"}},category="Bree-land",id=1512,scope="n/a",name="Neekers in the Marshes",arcs="Menace in the Midgewater",level=14,minlevel=10,b="Watcher Reedy",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Midgewater Marshes lie to the east of Staddle, beyond Swatmidge's farm.\nWatcher Reedy is worried that the growing Neekerbreeker population in the north of the Midgewater Marshes poses a threat to Staddle that is being overlooked by the watchers because of the goblin troubles.\n* Defeat Neekerbreekers in the Midgewater Marshes (8)\nObj 2:\nEdda Twiggins can be found out in the Midgewater Marshes, south-east of the ruins.\nWatcher Reedy asked you to check in with the Watchers stationed in the Marshes after you succeeded in thinning the numbers of the Neekerbreekers in the Marshes.\n* Talk to Edda Twiggins",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Falathlorn",zone="Ered Luin",reputation={{val="- 500 with The Ale Association"},{val="+900 with The Inn League"}},money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="You have received an order to fill a delivery to a member of the Inn League who has been stranded away from the festival this season.",mobs={{locations={"29.97S, 71.58W","24.62S, 93.03W","24.56S, 51.47W"},name="Inn League Tavern Keep"},{locations={"26.27S, 53.60W"},name="Wesley Hopwood"}},category="Inn League",id=1513,scope="n/a",prev={1192},name="Never Far From Home",receive={{val="Badge of Taste",id="700216F0"}},level=15,minlevel=11,b="Inn League Tavern Keep",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLimael's Vintage can be purchased in Celondimn in Ered Luin.\nYou should collect Limael's Vintage from a Vintner in Celondim.\n* Turn in Limael's Vintage\nObj 2:\nWesley Hopwood is at Thornley's Work-site in Bree-land, far to the east of Ered Luin.\nWesley Hopwood has told you that he will never be able to travel to Celondim in Ered Luin to find the \"Limael's Vintage\" he needs to complete the Inn League's Challenge. He has asked you to collect some of the wine for him.\n* Bring Limael's Vintage to Wesley Hopwood at Thornley's Worksite\n* Turn in Limael's Vintage"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="The Black Númenórean Dolvaethor has gone to Haudh Valandil at Amarthiel's bidding, $CLIENT_NAME$, and I fear the mischief he may cause in that hallowed place. The halls and tombs are lined with precious relics of the past -- relics of both great historical and personal value to the Dúnedain -- and they must not be despoiled!\nI ask you to recover as many of these priceless relics from the depths of Haudh Valandil as you can; my brethren will keep them in a safe place until the Angmarim have been defeated and the tomb is once more a place of peace.\nThe entrance to Haudh Valandil is located on the island, beyond the bridge of Ariant. Beware of Dolvaethor and the kergrim that have awakened within its depths and recover the relics with all haste! If I am not here when you return, report to Captain-General Daerdan at Echad Garthadir, the Ranger-encampment here in the city.",category="Annúminas",id=1514,scope="n/a",name="New Home for the Relics of Old",receive={{val="Annúminas Mark",id="700216BF"}},level=40,minlevel=35,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance to the tomb is on the island beyond the bridge of Ariant, on the highest level of the city.\nGlangilith has asked you to recover priceless relics from Haudh Valandil before the Angmarim ruin them.\n* Collect priceless relics (15 Priceless Relic)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1075},area="Buckland",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="2s 15c"}},d="Toly Brockhouse is disturbed by the fact that everything you brought him was spoiled. This, as well as the stirring of the forest creatures, has upset him.",mobs={{locations={"33.81S, 59.30W"},name="Gillemin Brandybuck"},{locations={"32.81S, 61.57W"},name="Toly Brockhouse"}},category="Bree-land",id=1515,scope="n/a",prev={2651},name="New Trouble in the Old Forest",arcs="The Wood-cutter's Tale",level=16,minlevel=11,b="Toly Brockhouse",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGillemin Brandybuck's camp is a distance to the south-east in the Old Forest, beyond Old Muddyfoot's Hill.\nToly Brockhouse asked you to seek the counsel of an old forester named Gillemin Brandybuck.\n* Talk to Gillemin Brandybuck in the Old Forest"},
{["next"]={1159},area="Redhorn Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The sad news of Nykr's passing must be delivered to his next of kin, a dwarf by the name of Kúli, who is studying spider behaviour.",category="Moria",id=1516,scope="n/a",prev={885},name="Next of Kin",arcs="In His Memory",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Róarr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKuli is at The Chittering Hole, south-east of The Orc-watch.\nRóarr asked you to find Kúli at The Chittering Hole and deliver to him the news of Nykr's death.\n* Talk to Kúli at The Chittering Hole"},
{zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="A particularly brutal and cunning troll named Dhît has been waylaying travellers in the Trollshaws as they attempt to reach Rivendell.",mobs={{locations={"9.60S, 42.03W"},name="Níels"}},category="Special",id=1517,scope="n/a",name="Níels' Bounty: Dhît the Troll",receive={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Lore",id="7001F257"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Níels",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nNíels has asked you to seek out the troll Dhît in the western Trollshaws in the vicinity of the Stone-trolls' Glade and claim his club as proof of his death.\n* Turn in Dhît's Club\nObj 2:\nNíels is at Esteldín in the North Downs.\nYou should bring Dhît's club to Níels.\n* Talk to Níels\n* Turn in Dhît's Club",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="One of Níels' clients seeks a rare and unusual scale from the far north...a scale from Farathlúg the Ice-worm.",mobs={{locations={"9.60S, 42.03W"},name="Níels"}},category="Special",id=1518,scope="n/a",name="Níels' Bounty: Farathlúg the Ice-worm",receive={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Learning",id="7001F256"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Níels",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nNíels has asked you to seek out Farathlúg's cave along the northern edge of the Great Glacier in Forochel and collect his scales.\n* Turn in Farathlúg's Scales\nObj 2:\nNíels is at Estldín in the North Downs.\nYou should bring Farathlúg's scales to Níels.\n* Talk to Níels\n* Turn in Farathlúg's Scales",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Níels has offered a bounty for whoever can bring him the fur of Mangemaw, a deadly wolf of unusual cunning that has been devouring helpless Hobbits in the Shire.",mobs={{locations={"9.60S, 42.03W"},name="Níels"}},category="Special",id=1519,scope="n/a",name="Níels' Bounty: Mangemaw the Wolf",receive={{val="Weathered Heritage Rune of Knowledge",id="7001F254"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Níels",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nNíels has asked you to seek out Mangemaw in Rushock Bog in the Shire and claim his pelt as proof of his death.\n* Turn in Mangemaw's Pelt\nObj 2:\nNíels is at Esteldín in the North Downs.\nYou should bring Mangemaw's Pelt to Níels as proof of his death.\n* Talk to Níels\n* Turn in Mangemaw's Pelt",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Rangers of Esteldín tell of a limrafn spirit named Morrafn which has lured many of their kindred to their deaths in the Fields of Fornost.",mobs={{locations={"9.60S, 42.03W"},name="Níels"}},category="Special",id=1520,scope="n/a",name="Níels' Bounty: Morrafn, the Flame of Hate",receive={{val="Weathered Heritage Rune of Knowledge",id="7001F254"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Níels",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nNíels has asked you to seek out Morrafn among the ruins in the western Fields of Fornost and banish the spirit beyond the Void.\n* Turn in Morrafn's Crystal\nObj 2:\nNíels is at Esteldín in the North Downs.\nYou should bring Morrafn's crystal to Níels as proof of its defeat.\n* Talk to Níels\n* Turn in Morrafn's Crystal",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="The Elves of Rivendell have discovered a deadly drake living among the peaks of the Misty Mountains that threatens to consume any who attempt the crossing. They have offered a bounty to any who would take up arms against Rothlúg, the drake of Storms.",mobs={{locations={"9.60S, 42.03W"},name="Níels"}},category="Special",id=1521,scope="n/a",name="Níels' Bounty: Rothlúg, the Drake of Storms",receive={{val="Decorated Heritage Rune of Learning",id="7001F25A"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Níels",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nNíels has asked you to seek out Rothlúg atop the ridges of the southern Misty Mountains and claim his scales as proof of his defeat.\n* Turn in Rothlúg's Scales\nObj 2:\nNíels is at Esteldín in the North Downs.\nYou should bring Rothlúg's scales to Níels as proof of his death.\n* Talk to Níels\n* Turn in Rothlúg's Scales",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="In the deepest sections of Moria, there are strange and frightening creatures. Veúlfur dispatched a host of his finest agents to the Shadowed Refuge to meet up with a company of Elves there to investigate rumours of the deep dark.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1522,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Nightmares in the Abyss",arcs="Nightmares of the Deep",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Veúlfur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMallas, Throstur, and Gelirwen are at the Shadowed Refuge, southeast of the Twenty-first Hall.\nVeúlfur wants to better understand the enemy appearing from the edges of the shadowy dark. He sent you to the Shadowed Refuge to assist his agents and allies there with various tasks meant to divine the dangers and meanings of the nefarious creature found therein.\n* Assist Mallas with his efforts at the Sixteenth Hall\n* Assist Mallas with his efforts at Skûmfil\n* Assist Throstur with his efforts at Skûmfil\n* Assist Gelirwen with her efforts at the Dark Delvings\nObj 2:\nVeúlfur is at the Twenty-first hall, north-west of the Shadowed Refuge.\nYou successfully assisted all of Veúlfur's agents at the Shadowed Refuge, earning from them honour and respect.\n* Return to Veúlfur at the Twenty-first Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2043},area="Cirin-en-Galadh",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Concerned by all the recent upheaval disturbing Lothlórien, Tuilinn has had an idea for bolstering the morale of the Elves throughout the forest.",mobs={{locations={"12.10S, 71.09W"},name="Bahanneth"},{locations={"14.26S, 73.07W"},name="Ambendel"},{locations={"17.24S, 64.00W"},name="Maliriel"},{locations={"11.93S, 67.85W"},name="Tuilinn"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1523,scope="n/a",prev={1160},destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Niphredil and Elanor",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,c={"* Maliriel is at [17.2S, 64.0W]\n* Ambendel is at [14.3S, 73.1W]\n* Bahanneth is at [12.1S, 71.1W]"},pois={{locations={"11.79S, 67.47W","12.09S, 68.18W","11.61S, 67.65W","11.86S, 68.12W","12.21S, 67.82W","12.35S, 67.95W","11.92S, 67.43W","12.15S, 67.97W","12.03S, 67.49W","11.97S, 67.39W","11.93S, 67.56W","11.65S, 67.53W","11.67S, 67.82W","12.32S, 67.75W","12.02S, 68.13W","11.85S, 68.18W","12.36S, 67.89W","12.28S, 67.98W","11.71S, 68.08W","11.72S, 67.42W","12.08S, 67.74W","12.01S, 68.25W","12.18S, 67.65W","11.65S, 67.67W"},name="Elanor"},{locations={"11.91S, 68.22W","11.69S, 67.77W","11.93S, 68.15W","12.29S, 67.92W","11.63S, 67.36W","12.04S, 67.54W","11.96S, 67.58W","12.12S, 68.05W","12.21S, 67.73W","11.83S, 68.24W","12.07S, 68.26W","12.31S, 67.84W","12.03S, 67.99W","11.61S, 67.96W","11.76S, 67.51W","11.87S, 67.47W","12.00S, 67.45W","11.96S, 68.03W","11.73S, 67.87W","11.75S, 68.15W","12.21S, 68.03W","12.22S, 68.22W","11.61S, 67.55W","11.65S, 67.61W"},name="Niphredil"}},minlevel=55,b="Tuilinn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElanor and niphredil can be found upon and around the hill of Cerin Amroth.\nTuilinn has asked you to pick elanor and niphredil.\n* Collect elanor-blossoms (6 Elanor )\n* Collect niphredil-blossoms (6 Niphredil )\nObj 2:\nBahanneth is at Talan Fanuidhol, west of Cerin Amroth. Ambendel is in Echad Andestel, south-west of Cerin Amroth. Maliriel is at the Hythe, east and south of Cerin Amroth, by the river.\nTuilinn has asked you to bring elanor and niphredil-blossoms each to Bahanneth, Ambendel, and Maliriel the Feast-mistress.\n* Talk to Maliriel\n* Turn in Elanor\n* Turn in Niphredil\n* Talk to Ambendel\n* Turn in Elanor\n* Turn in Niphredil\n* Talk to Bahanneth\n* Turn in Elanor\n* Turn in Niphredil\nObj 3:\nTuilinn is atop the flet at Cerin Amroth.\nYou should return to Tuilinn and relate to her how her gift lifted the spirits of her friends.\n* Talk to Tuilinn at Cerin Amroth"},
{["next"]={234},area="Nimrodel",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You have brought some arrows to Celegúien, and now she wants them delivered to Meredhrandir at Mekhem-bizru.",mobs={{locations={"11.69S, 78.58W"},name="Meredhrandir"},{locations={"14.22S, 72.98W"},name="Celegúien"}},selectoneof={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Learning",id="7001F256"},{val="Sealed Copper Setting of the Enduring Hand",id="700185CF"},{q="(x2)",val="Pure Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA85"},{q="(x2)",val="Pure Athelas Essence",id="7000EA84"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1524,scope="n/a",prev={1405},name="No Arrow a Waste",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Celegúien",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCelegúien has a bundle of arrows for you to deliver on the crates by her in Echad Andestel. She wants you to carry them to Meredhrandir at the camp of Mekhem-bizru, very near to the entrance to Moria. She advised you to follow the road west and north as it passes through Nanduhirion, and to beware of Orcs on the road.\nYou have been asked to deliver arrows from Echad Andestel to Mekhem-bizru.\n* Pick up a bundle of arrows next to Celegúien\nObj 2:\nMeredhrandir is at Mekhem-bizru, right by the eastern entrance to Moria.\nYou have brought a bundle of arrows to Meredhrandir and should speak to him about the journey.\n* Talk to Meredhrandir"},
{area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="7s"}},d="Trouble of all manner surrounds the Forsaken Inn, and a retired Constable needs help protecting the Inn from the threats.",mobs={{locations={"34.04S, 40.65W"},name="Constable Bram Ashleaf"}},selectoneof={{val="Watcher's Leggings",id="700007C2"},{val="Constable's Feathered Hat",id="70006B4A"},{val="Deputy's Helm",id="7001D109"},{val="Constable's Javelin",id="700161C2"},{val="Bram's Ring",id="7001D20D"}},category="Lone-lands",id=1525,scope="n/a",name="Noble Deeds",arcs="Noble Deeds",receive={{val="Watcher's Spear",id="700007C3"}},level=22,minlevel=17,b="Constable Bram Ashleaf",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWolves can be found in the Midgewater Pass. Orcs prowl north in the Weather Hills and the Midgewater Pass. Boars wander in Annunlos and the Weather Hills surrounding Weathertop.\nBram Ashleaf has asked you to help protect The Forsaken Inn by clearing the threat of wolves, Orcs, and boars from the area surrounding the inn.\n* Talk to Bram Ashleaf at The Forsaken Inn\n* Turn in Sharp Boar-tusk\n* Turn in Bushy Wolf-tail\n* Turn in Orc-shield"},
{area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="The expedition on which Gufi led you was a disaster. Upon his arrival back at the Deep Descent, he noticed that his friend Nykr had not yet returned, and wishes you to search for the missing dwarf.",selectoneof={{val="Tribute to Nykr",id=70016396},{val="Roarr's Shield",id="7001608D"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1526,scope="n/a",prev={2665},name="No Dwarf Left Behind",level=54,pois={{locations={"11.74S, 112.96W"},name="Nykr's Corpse"}},minlevel=49,b="Gufi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNykr was lost around the mining site near the Deep Descent.\nGufi wishes you to search for Nykr, who was lost during the commotion.\n* Use Nykr's Corpse\nObj 2:\nGufi can be found in the Deep Descent in Moria.\nYou should return to Gufi to tell him the sad news of Nykr's death.\n* Return to Gufi"},
{area="Nain Enidh",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="16s"}},d="Since visiting Agamaur, the swamp north-east of Ost Guruth, Hana the Young has had terrible dreams. She spoke mysteriously about a Woman in the swamp and the song of the nerbyg.",mobs={{locations={"30.99S, 29.55W"},name="Hana the Young"}},selectoneof={{val="Hana's Gloves",id="70000CB2"},{val="Hana's Helmet",id="70000CB3"}},category="Lone-lands",id=1527,scope="n/a",prev={1069},name="Noisome Neighbours",arcs="Song of the Red Swamp",receive={{val="Manadlos",id="70000CB1"}},level=28,c={"* The nerbyg are in the Bloodmire, east of Ost Guruth"},minlevel=23,b="Hana the Young",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNerbyg can be found in Haragmar, the southern reaches of the Red Swamp, in a place called the Circle of Blood.\nHana claims that the Woman her people found in the swamp wishes to harm her and uses the nerbyg to call to her and draw her forth from Ost Guruth. Hana has asked you to slay the insects and bring her their legs so that she will know they can no longer call to her.\n* Deliver the norbog-legs to Hana the Young\n* Turn in Norbog-leg"},
{["next"]={1545},zone="Evendim",area="Bullroarer's Sward",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="The Northcotton Farm is nearing harvest season and preparing for their annual farmer's market.",mobs={{locations={"23.10S, 67.28W"},name="Nod Gardener"}},category="Evendim",id=1528,scope="n/a",name="Northcotton Farm",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,minlevel=25,b="Nod Gardener",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAlbin Northcotton is at the Northcotton Farm, west of Oatbarton.\nNorthcotton Farm is getting ready for their annual harvest market and could use an extra set of hands.\n* Talk to Albin Northcotton",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={847},money={{val="28s 56c"}},d="There is much to do around the Northcotton Farm in order to prepare for the upcoming farmer's market.",selectoneof={{val="Hobbit Crafted Hunting Bow",id="700261BC"},{val="Dusty Mountaineer Axe",id="700260D4"},{val="Disused Bounder Greatsword",id="70025FBA"},{val="Proper Walking Stick",id="700261D7"},{val="Odd-looking Stone",id="700264A6"},{val="Boar-hunter's Spear",id="700264ED"},{val="Notched Bounder's Club",id=70026273},{val="Inherited Warhammer",id="700261A0"},{val="Trusty Shire Knife",id="70025D6C"}},category="Evendim",id=1529,scope="n/a",name="Northcotton Farmer's Market",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,minlevel=25,b="Albin Northcotton",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nPies need making, chores need doing, animals need tending, pipe-weed needs harvesting, and neighbours need helping before the farmer's market can happen.\n* Help Rosa Brockhouse get the pies ready\n* Help Milo Longfurrow with the chores\n* Help Gerard Deephole get the animals ready\n* Help Blossom Gamgee prepare the pipe-weed\n* Help Nibs and Hal Gamgee with their troubles\nObj 2:\nAlbin Northcotton is at the Northcotton Farm.\nAlbin Northcotton will be pleased to hear that everything is ready.\n* Talk to Albin Northcotton",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Thadúr has recently taken over a small farm to the northwest of Oakbarton. He has used some foul type of poison to alter the local flora and fauna. You must defeat him and his minions and foil his plot to poison the Shire.\nThis quest will be cancelled if you leave the Northcotton Farms before completing it.",category="In Their Absence",id=1530,scope="n/a",name="Northcotton Farms",destinypoints={{val=2000}},receive={{q="(x5)",val="Medallion of the North-men",id=70025341}},level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThadúr the Ravager has begun to settle into a farm near Oakbarton. He has begun preparations to\nrelease a powerful poison known as Darkthorn into the Shire's water source.  You must foil Thadúr's plans and defeat him and his minions.\n* Defeat Legbarthil\n* Destoy Úmheryn, the vile cauldron\n* Defeat Thadúr"},
{area="Tâl Bruinen",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Tongannel is seeking information about the origin of the Gauredain.",mobs={{locations={"37.10S, 14.04W"},name="Tongannel"},{locations={"2.79N, 57.99W"},name="Santtu"}},category="Trollshaws",id=1531,scope="n/a",name="Northern Threat",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Tongannel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nForochel lies north of Evendim through Cirith Rhiw, north of Tyrn Fornech. You should start your search in the village of Kauppa-kohta.\nTongannel has asked you to go into the frozen North and seek news of the Gauredain.\n* Go to Kauppa-kohta in Forochel and learn of the Gauredain",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Glain Vraig",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Having assisted the Free Peoples in their battle against the war host of Angmar, you have earned much respect. First Marshals throughout the Ettenmoors authorised the rewards from Quartermaster Ash at Glân Vraig.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1532,scope="n/a",name="Notice of the First Marshal",receive={{val="Key of the First Marshal",id="7000B2C5"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Quartermaster Ash",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nEarn Tokens of Valour by assisting members of the Free Peoples and return them to Quartermaster Ash at Glân Vraig.\n* Deliver the Tokens of Valour to Quartermaster Ash\n* Turn in Token of Valour",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Glain Vraig",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Having assisted the Free Peoples in their battle against the war host of Angmar, you have earned much respect. Second Marshals throughout the Ettenmoors authorise rewards from Quartermaster Ash at Glân Vraig.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1533,scope="n/a",name="Notice of the Second Marshal",receive={{val="Key of the Second Marshal",id="7000B2C4"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Quartermaster Ash",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nEarn Tokens of Valour by assisting members of the Free Peoples and return them to Quartermaster Ash at Glân Vraig.\n* Deliver the Tokens of Valour to Quartermaster Ash\n* Turn in Token of Valour",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2538},area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Great Winter-worms have been interrupting the dwarves' efforts to get hot water from nearby springs. Weth is most annoyed.",mobs={{locations={"9.42N, 81.22W"},name="Weth"}},category="Forochel",id=1534,scope="n/a",name="Not in Hot Water",arcs="Furred Worms",level=47,c={"* There are three Greater Winter-worms, one in each \"Dwarf Channel\"."},minlevel=42,b="Weth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\n* Kill 1 Great Winter-worm\n* Kill 1 Great Winter-worm\n* Kill 1 Great Winter-worm\nObj 2:\nYou have made a dent in the population of worms around the dwarf-channels Weth described to you. You should return to him at Zigilgund.\n* Speak to Weth in Zigilgund"},
{area="Dar-gazag",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Rat-folk living on the banks of the Hoardale, south of Dâr-gazag, are not only a succulent meal, but they are a source of replenishible food. The rat-folk are farmers, supplying the enemy forces with foodstuffs. Foodstuffs can be stolen and eaten by your army as well.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1535,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Not Just for Eating",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Taskmaster Gukthor",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nRations are portioned to enemy forces and found in locations where they hold power.\nTaskmaster Gukthor charged you collecting food for Angmar's Army.\n* Return to Taskmaster Gukthor at Dâr-gazag ()\n* Turn in Food Sack",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2341},area="Falathlorn",zone="Ered Luin",d="Toronn desires to leave Middle-earth, while Bregar, his brother, believes they should remain.",mobs={{locations={"21.63S, 94.14W"},name="Langlas"},{locations={"24.02S, 92.57W"},name="Bregar"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Eggs and Onions",id="700005F5"},{q="(x5)",val="Cooked Carrots",id="700005F4"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1536,scope="n/a",prev={3231},name="Now is Found",arcs="Brotherly Bond",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Pork Sausage",id=70003362}},level=11,c={"* Langlas in Thrasi's Lodge at [21.6S, 94.1W]"},minlevel=7,b="Bregar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLanglas is at the Thrasi's Lodge west of Kheledûl.\nSwayed by Toronn's reminder of their lost friend Thoram, Bregar asks you to bring the broken sword to Langlas, a Ranger of the North who will honour the sword and Thoram's memory.\n* Talk to Langlas\n* Turn in Broken Sword\nObj 2:\nBregar is at Duillond, along the road east and south of the Thrasi's Lodge.\nLanglas gratefully accepted Thoram's sword, promising to honour it, then gave you a scroll to deliver to Bregar.\n* Talk to Bregar\n* Turn in The Lay of Nimrodel"},
{area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="39s 90c"}},d="Sara Oakheart was found prisoner in the depths of Fornost. She needs your help getting free and back to the safety of her home.",mobs={{locations={"8.01S, 56.00W"},name="Ranger Maedhrusc"}},selectoneof={{val="Oakheart's Defender",id="70006B78"},{val="Oakheart's Thanks",id="70006B34"}},category="Fornost",id=1537,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Oakheart's Flight",receive={{val="Oakheart's Earring",id="700069E2"}},level=36,c={"* Sara Oakheart is found in a prison pen directly north of the Fornost entrance\n* Escort Sara Oakheart. As with Oakheart's Plight, she will go in the middle of mob groups so watch out."},minlevel=31,b="Sara Oakheart",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSara Oakheart was apparently taken captive by the Blogmal Orcs while she was gathering wild herbs. She needs you to escort her out of Fornost.\n* Talk to Sara Oakheart again\nObj 2:\nNow that you have successfully escorted Sara Oakheart to safety, report of your success to someone at the Fornost camp.\n* Tell someone in Fornost camp about rescuing Sara Oakheart"},
{area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="37s 10c"}},d="You have found a familiar face as a prisoner within Garth Agarwen: the strange old woman, Sara Oakheart.",mobs={{locations={"29.66S, 27.37W"},name="Elsa the Bold"}},selectoneof={{val="Oakheart's Dagger",id="700092DE"},{val="Oakheart's Leggings",id="70006AF9"},{val="Oakheart's Shoulder Guards",id="70006B35"},{val="Oakheart's Feather",id="700069D4"}},category="Garth Agarwen",id=1538,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Oakheart's Plight",level=32,minlevel=27,b="Sara Oakheart",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFollow Sara Oakheart out of Garth Agarwen and protect her along the way! She seems to have been captured by Ivar and the wights.\n* Talk to Sara Oakheart\nObj 2:\nNow that you have successfully escorted Sara Oakheart to safety, you should speak with someone at the Eglan-camp.\n* Tell someone at the Eglain camp about Sara's rescue"},
{area="Nain Enidh",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="7s 14c"}},d="Hana the Young wants a shipment of oatmeal sent to Ost Guruth from the Forsaken Inn; something has happened to the supply of oatmeal in recent days.",mobs={{locations={"23.10S, 67.28W"},name="Nod Gardener"},{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Anlaf the Forlorn"},{locations={"30.99S, 29.55W"},name="Hana the Young"}},category="Lone-lands",id=1539,scope="n/a",name="Oatmeal Problems",c={"* Nod Gardener is at Oatbarton in Evendim"},level=30,minlevel=25,b="Hana the Young",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAnlaf is in The Forsaken Inn, located in the Lone-lands along the Great East Road, between Bree and Ost Guruth.\nHana the Young has asked you to inquire at The Forsaken Inn about acquiring a shipment of oatmeal for Ost Guruth.\n* Talk to Anlaf the Forlorn at The Forsaken Inn\nObj 2:\nThe Bounder Nod Gardener lives in Oatbarton on the border of the Shire, north of Brockenborings and across the Greenfields.\nAnlaf the Forlorn of The Forsaken Inn has asked you to journey to Oatbarton to talk to Old Mugwort's cousin Nod Gardener. He has heard that there are problems on the northern boundary of the Shire that the Bounders have not been able to solve, and that shipments of oatmeal will not be possible until the trouble in Oatbarton has been resolved.\n* Talk to Nod Gardener in Oatbarton",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Bullroarer's Sward",zone="Evendim",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Nibs Chubb needs assistance filling an order of oats for a customer in the Westfarthing.",mobs={{locations={"23.21S, 66.53W"},name="Nibs Chubb"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Greater Celebrant Salve",id=70000856},{q="(x3)",val="Greater Athelas Essence",id=70000855}},category="Evendim",id=1540,scope="n/a",name="Oats for the Westfarthing",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,pois={{locations={"23.09S, 65.88W","23.09S, 65.83W","23.32S, 66.28W","22.92S, 66.28W","23.26S, 66.34W","22.88S, 65.84W","22.92S, 66.22W","23.02S, 65.83W","23.04S, 66.22W","23.66S, 66.43W","22.95S, 65.89W","23.38S, 66.28W","23.86S, 66.60W","23.73S, 66.95W","22.95S, 65.84W","23.68S, 66.95W","23.32S, 66.34W","22.88S, 65.94W","22.98S, 66.28W","22.86S, 66.22W","22.99S, 66.35W","23.86S, 66.53W","22.86S, 66.27W","23.32S, 66.39W","23.04S, 66.28W","23.66S, 66.38W","23.78S, 66.76W","23.32S, 66.22W","23.26S, 66.28W","23.78S, 66.70W","23.80S, 66.60W","23.38S, 66.34W","23.26S, 66.39W","23.02S, 65.89W","22.95S, 65.94W","23.37S, 66.40W","22.98S, 66.22W","23.02S, 65.94W","23.05S, 66.35W","22.88S, 65.89W","23.09S, 65.94W","23.26S, 66.22W","23.38S, 66.22W","23.80S, 66.53W"},name="Oats"}},minlevel=25,b="Nibs Chubb",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNibs Chubb's fields are east and north-east of his farm.\nNibs Chubb has asked you to help him collect his oats from the fields.\n* Collect oats (12 Oats )\nObj 2:\nNibs Chubb is at his farm, in the south of Oatbarton.\nYou should return to Nibs Chubb with the oats.\n* Talk to Nibs Chubb\n* Turn in Oats"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+500 with The Mathom Society"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Hithlim has asked that you speak with Greylond Bottomley outside the Mathom House in Michel Delving.",mobs={{locations={"33.40S, 75.54W"},name="Greylond Bottomley"},{locations={"9.49S, 42.11W"},name="Hithlim"}},category="North Downs",id=1541,scope="n/a",name="Odd Requests",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Hithlim",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGreylond Bottomley can be found outside the Mathom House in Michel Delving.\nHithlim has asked that you speak with Greylond Bottomley to find out what the Mathom Society is up to.\n* Talk to Greylond Bottomley at the Mathom House",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1892},d="Rumour of the dark things that dwell in the depths of Moria have reached even the ears of Mosco Mudbottom in the Lone-lands.",category="Warden",id=1542,scope="n/a",prev={244},name="Offensive Strike",arcs="The Path of the Masterful Fist",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Mosco Mudbottom",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Dark Warden, if it exists, dwells somewhere within the Foundations of Stone in Moria, far to the east and south of the Lone-lands.\nMosco Mudbottom has tasked you with discovering the lair of the Dark Warden and bringing the creature's head to Sadreda.\n* Talk to Sadreda at the Shadowed Refuge\n* Turn in Severed Head",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1791},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The Water-works is a site of importance to the dwarves who wish to remain in Moria. Once such dwarf, Foreman Indrith, has made it a mission to repair the channel there.",mobs={{locations={"17.65S, 116.88W"},name="Kaldi"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1543,scope="n/a",prev={2773},name="Off to the Channel",arcs="Entering the Vile Maw",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Indrith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKaldi should be in the Vile Maw, west and a little north of the Great Wheel.\nForeman Indrith fears that he may have sent his worker and friend Kaldi to his death. He has sent you to a camp where he believes Kaldi should be.\n* Talk to Kaldi at the entrance to the Vile Maw"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Fil Gashan is the barracks and mustering point for the Orcs' invasion of Lothlórien. Hidden deep within the fiery landscape and sharing an adjacent entrance to the Forges of Khazad-dûm, Orcs train here under the watchful eye of General Talug.",mobs={{locations={"13.42S, 108.06W"},name="Yngvi"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1544,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Off with the Right Hand",arcs="General's Command",level=60,minlevel=57,b="Yngvi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFil Gashan lies to the south-west of Anazârmekhem.\nYngvi has asked you to enter Fil Gashan and defeat General Talug. He suggested that heating the General's armour may make him more vulnerable to attack.\n* Defeat General Talug\nObj 2:\nYngvi is at Anazârmekhem, north-east of Fil Gashan.\nYou found a way to defeat General Talug and turned his forces against him. With the general defeated, it is possible that Mazog and his army will be slowed to a crawl. You should return to Yngvi and tell him this news.\n* Talk to Yngvi at Anazârmekhem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+1200 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Juhani, reported missing by his friend Tero back in Zigilgund, is trapped on the isle of Kissa-sari.",mobs={{locations={"9.43N, 81.04W"},name="Tero"}},selectoneof={{val="Hunter's Saviour",id="7000E6EB"},{val="Hunter's Rescuer",id="7000E6E8"},{val="Hunter's Hero",id="7001619C"}},category="Forochel",id=1545,scope="n/a",name="Of Great Aid",arcs="Sabretooth Isle",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Juhani",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nJuhani, reported missing by his friend Tero back in Zigilgund, is trapped on the isle of Kissa-sari. He wishes your help in ensuring him safe passage.\n* Defend Juhani\nObj 2:\nYou have escorted Juhani to safety. You should tell Tero that he is now safe.\n* Talk to Tero in Zigilgund"},
{["next"]={1739},area="Nan Sirannon",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Caradhras, called the Cruel, rages and throws terrible storms down upon the land.",mobs={{locations={"50.52S, 7.81W"},name="Rostoriel"}},category="Eregion",id=1546,scope="n/a",prev={65},name="Of Mountains and Tempers",arcs="Quelling the Storm",level=50,c={"* Defeat Freezing Grim and Cave Snow-beast at the Redhorn Snowfall [46.9S, 2.1W]"},minlevel=45,b="Rostoriel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFrost-grims and snowbeasts have been seen in the Redhorn Gate, north-east of Echad Dúnann.\nRostoriel has asked you to quell the rage of Caradhras and defeat the beasts that dwell within the Redhorn Gate.\n* Defeat frost-grims\n* Defeat snowbeasts\nObj 2:\nRostoriel is at Echad Dúnann, south-west of the Redhorn Gate and east of the Burnt Tor.\nYou should return to Rostoriel and tell her of your success.\n* Talk to Rostoriel at Echad Dúnann"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+1200 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Cachúnir has expressed a desire to take as much history and lore of Middle-earth as possible when the Elves of Rivendell sail into the West.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Cachúnir"}},category="Reputation",id=1547,scope="n/a",name="Of Mysteries Most Profound -- Introduction",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Cachúnir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCachúnir is at Rivendell, in the Trollshaws.\nCachúnir has asked you to pen an essay entitled 'Of Mysteries Most Profound' and bring it to him.\n* Present 'Of Mysteries Most Profound' to Cachúnir in Rivendell\n* Turn in Of Mysteries Most Profound",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Captain-General Makan wishes to strengthen the defences of Tol Ascarnen by building a terrible weapon to wield against those attacking the fortress.",category="Tol Ascarnen",id=1548,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Oil for Boiling",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Gautr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs and Uruks guarding fortifications and found patrolling the wild of the Ettenmoors may carry barrels of oil.\nSergeant-at-Arms Gautr at Tol Ascarnen is working to forge an iron cauldron to fill with oil to be used against the forces of Angmar as they try to retake the keep from the Free Peoples. He has asked you to collect the oil from the Enemy.\n* Deliver the barrels of oil to Sergeant-at-Arms Gautr at Tol Ascarnen\n* Turn in Barrel of Oil",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Lugazag",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Lugazag is in need of stronger defences. In order to build a significant defence, the Captain-General has ordered that a great cauldron of iron be forged and filled with oil.",category="Lugazag",id=1549,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Oil for the Cauldron of Lugazag",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Kolr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nEnemies throughout the Ettenmoors carry stolen barrels of oil.\nSergeant-at-Arms Kolr received orders to forge a great iron cauldron to fill with oil. This cauldron will be used to defend the walls of Lugazag from the Enemy. He has asked you to recover the stolen barrels of oil which are in the possession of the Enemy.\n* Deliver the oil to Sergeant-at-Arms Kolr at Lugazag\n* Turn in Barrel of Oil",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tirith Rhaw",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Tirith Rhaw is in need of stronger defences. In order to build a significant defence, the Captain-General has ordered that a great cauldron of iron be forged and filled with oil.",category="Tirith Rhaw",id=1550,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Oil for the Cauldron of Tirith Rhaw",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Haliggyr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nFoes throughout the Ettenmoors carry barrels of oil, stolen from the stores of the Free Peoples.\nSergeant-at-Arms Haliggyr received orders to forge a great iron cauldron to fill with oil. This cauldron will be used to defend the walls of Tirith Rhaw from the Enemy. He tasked you with recovering as much oil as you can from the servants of the Enemy.\n* Deliver the oil to Sergeant-at-Arms Haliggyr at Tirith Rhaw\n* Turn in Barrel of Oil",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tirith Rhaw",zone="Ettenmoors",d="The Free Peoples will return to take Tirith Rhaw and Angmar's defenders wish to strengthen the walls with deterents that will drive the foe away.",category="Tirith Rhaw",id=1551,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Oil Up",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Gozad",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Free Peoples carry barrels of oil that can be used to fill the iron pots being built at Tirith Rhaw. Seek out the Free People guarding locations throughout the Ettenmoors and slaughter them for the oil they carry.\nThe War-tyrant desires to use boiling oil at Tirith Rhaw to punish the enemy as they make their assault. You were sent into the Ettenmoors to collect oil from the foe.\n* Deliver the oil to Soldier Gozad at Tirith Rhaw ( )\n* Turn in Barrel of Oil",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Lugazag",zone="Ettenmoors",d="The Free Peoples will return to take Lugazag, and Angmar's defenders wish to strengthen the walls with deterents that will drive the foe away.",category="Lugazag",id=1552,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Oil Well",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Kafaaz",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Free Peoples carry barrels of oil that can be used to fill the iron pots being built at Lugazag. Seek out the Free People guarding locations throughout the Ettenmoors and slaughter them for the oil they carry.\nThe War-tyrant desires to use boiling oil at Lugazag to punish the enemy as they make their assault. You were sent into the Ettenmoors to collect barrels of oil from the foe.\n* Deliver the oil to Soldier Kaafaz at Lugazag ( )\n* Turn in Barrel of Oil",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Chetwood",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="The Blackwold brigands seized Old Bauman's farm during the early days of their uprising.",selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Eggs and Onions",id="700005F5"},{q="(x5)",val="Cooked Carrots",id="700005F4"}},category="Bree-land",id=1553,scope="n/a",name="Old Bauman's Farm",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Pork Sausage",id=70003362}},level=9,c={"* Go right up the path, it will divide in to 2 paths. Choose the left one as it is usually easier to see/access the house. His farm is located right on top of a hill. Killing the Blackwold Supervisor will drop Sally's Chain."},minlevel=5,b="Old Bauman",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOld Bauman's farm lies far to the east of Combe, beyond the brigand camps in the Chetwood, at the end of the eastward path. Old Bauman is at the logging camp, south of the Chetwood, east of Combe.\nOld Bauman lost his farm to the Blackwolds when they retreated from Archet, and he would like you to go there and retrieve his Sally's chain for him.\n* Bring Sally's chain to Old Bauman\n* Turn in Sally's Chain"},
{["next"]={48},area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 25c"}},d="The dwarf-merchant Nithi claims he saw a barrow-wight amid the mounds to the north-east of Gondamon, but his friend Galti does not believe him.",mobs={{locations={"18.95S, 95.19W"},name="Nithi"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1554,scope="n/a",name="Old Bones",arcs="Old Bones",level=13,minlevel=9,b="Nithi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe mounds of the old Edain are a distance to the north-east of Gondamon.\nNithi asked you to journey to the old Edain barrows and collect a trophy to prove to Galti that there are wights amid the old mounds.\n* Bring your trophy back to Nithi\n* Turn in Wight-skull",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Buckland",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Wilmac Brandybuck, Maggot's farmhand, sent you to Brandy Hall to speak with Saradoc Brandybuck, and the Master of Brandy Hall warned you of Rollo and Doderic's musings.",mobs={{locations={"31.72S, 62.63W"},name="Celandine Brandybuck"},{locations={"31.64S, 62.58W"},name="Wilmac Brandybuck"},{locations={"33.34S, 62.41W"},name="Saradoc Brandybuck"},{locations={"31.75S, 59.15W"},name="Doderic Brandybuck"},{locations={"33.86S, 58.65W"},name="Rollo Maggot"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Eggs and Onions",id="700005F5"},{q="(x5)",val="Fried Mushrooms",id="700005F6"},{q="(x5)",val="Cooked Carrots",id="700005F4"}},category="Bree-land",id=1555,scope="n/a",prev={1869},name="Old Forest Investigation",arcs="Old Forestry",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Mushroom Pie",id="700005F3"},{val="Torang",id="700005F2"}},level=15,minlevel=11,b="Saradoc Brandybuck",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDoderic Brandybuck may be at Bald Hill in the Old Forest, east of the Bonfire Glade.\nMaggot's Farmhand sent you to Brandy Hall to look for Farmer Maggot's son Rollo. Saradoc Brandybuck has suggested that his nephew Doderic may have taken Rollo out to the Old Forest.\n* Find Doderic Brandybuck\nObj 2:\nRollo Maggot may be found at an abandoned cottage near the Withywindle, south-east of Bald Hill. It is reached by heading west through the Shifting Wood, then turning south and south-east.\nDoderic Brandybuck is worried about his friend Rollo Maggot, who chased after a brigand into the Forest.\n* Find Rollo Maggot\nObj 3:\nDoderic Brandybuck is waiting at Bald Hill to the north of the cottage, east of the Bonfire Glade.\nYou found Rollo Maggot standing over the corpse of a Man. He asked you to return to Doderic Brandybuck and tell him that he is all right, and there is no need to worry. He also asked you not to tell Doderic what happened with the brigand.\n* Talk to Doderic Brandybuck at Bald Hill\nObj 4:\nCelandine can be found on the border of Newbury and Crickhollow in the northern part of Buckland.\nYou found Rollo Maggot standing in shock over the corpse of a brigand, but he seemed unharmed. He asked that you show his notes to Doderic, and Doderic suggested that you bring them to his cousin Celandine.\n* Talk to Celandine Brandybuck\n* Turn in Old Forest Guide\nObj 5:\nWilmac Brandybuck is just inside the Hay Gate in Newbury, the northern section of Buckland.\nWilmac Brandybuck still knows nothing of Rollo's whereabouts. You should speak with him to put his mind at ease.\n* Talk to Wilmac Brandybuck in Newbury"},
{["next"]={2788},area="Buckland",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Celandine Brandybuck requested notes on the Old Forest from Farmer Maggot, but has yet to receive them. She is concerned that something may have happened.",mobs={{locations={"31.72S, 62.63W"},name="Celandine Brandybuck"},{locations={"31.64S, 62.58W"},name="Wilmac Brandybuck"},{locations={"34.34S, 64.44W"},name="Farmer Maggot"}},category="Bree-land",id=1556,scope="n/a",name="Old Forestry",arcs="Old Forestry",receive={{val="Cyrymaib",id="700090F5"}},level=14,minlevel=10,b="Celandine Brandybuck",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBamfurlong is south on the river road, on the western side of the Brandywine Bridge.\nCelandine Brandybuck has asked you to enquire about notes she requested from Farmer Maggot at his farm, Bamfurlong, on her behalf.\n* Talk to Farmer Maggot at Bamfurlong\nObj 2:\nRollo Maggot, Doderic Brandybuck, or Wilmac Brandybuck are in the area of Newbury just inside the Hay Gate in Buckland\nFarmer Maggot sent you to find Rollo Maggot, Doderic Brandybuck, or Wilmac Brandybuck to retrieve his notes.\n* Talk to Rollo Maggot, Doderic Brandybuck, or Wilmac Brandybuck in Newbury"},
{area="Bruinen Source North",zone="The Misty Mountains",d="With some trepidation, Sigrun has decided that he must cast aside his old enmities if the evil within Helegrod is to be cast out.",mobs={{locations={"19.13S, 2.90W"},name="Sigrun"},{locations={"29.90S, 4.69W"},name="Gonediad"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1557,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={1164},name="Old Friendships",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Sigrun",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGonediad is somewhere in Rivendell.\nSigrun has expressed his doubts about the gifting of Mírdanant to Durin by the Elves of Eregion, but has decided such old enmities must be cast aside if the new evils lurking within Helegrod are to be defeated. He has asked you to speak with Gonediad, learned in the lore of Eregion, about the return of the dragon Thorog.\n* Talk to Gonediad",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2717},area="Green Hill Country",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="Rollo Boffin told you of Odo Burrow, Longo's father. He had a farmstead in the south, but Longo abandoned it when his father died. Rollo is curious if Longo is using it again for some other purpose.",mobs={{locations={"33.03S, 71.08W"},name="Esilia Took"},{locations={"33.42S, 65.66W"},name="Rollo Boffin"}},category="Shire",id=1558,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1380},name="Old Odo's Leaf-Farm",arcs="Took and Tower",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=12,minlevel=8,b="Rollo Boffin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOdo Burrow's old leaf-farm is south of the clearing where you found the missing waggon.\nWhen you found Longo's missing waggon, there was no sign of Gerebert Took, but the leaf had been moved southwards. Rollo Boffin suggested you search boxes and crates at Odo Burrow's old farm for some sign of Gerebert. He warned you to bring friends, for it might be dangerous.\n* Search Old Odo's farmstead\nObj 2:\nEsilia Took can be found near the centre of Tuckborough.\nAt old Odo's leaf-barn, you stumbled across Gerebert Took. Once you freed him, you were attacked by some strange Men. After defending Gerebert from the Men who attacked you, he escaped and said he would meet you back at Esilia Took's house.\n* Talk to Esilia Took"},
{["next"]={371},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Belco Brockhouse found a copy of the Founding Writ of the Shire, but will not give it up until he has received some services in return.",mobs={{locations={"32.81S, 70.95W"},name="Belco Brockhouse"}},category="Shire",id=1559,scope="n/a",prev={2398},name="Old Sally",arcs="The Founding Writ",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lesser Athelas Essence",id="70000D5D"}},level=9,minlevel=5,b="Belco Brockhouse",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBelco Brockhouse's pig, Old Sally, may be found near the big willow south-east of Belco's farm.\nBelco has asked you to find his pig, Old Sally, and bring her back to his barn. He warned you that she spooks easily, and if she gets too scared, she may run away.\n* Find Old Sally\nObj 2:\nBelco Brockhouse can be found south of the Tuckborough town centre.\nYou should speak with Belco Brockhouse and let him know that you led his pig, Old Sally, back to his barn.\n* Talk to Belco Brockhouse"},
{["next"]={809},area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="8s 96c"}},d="The Misty Mountains are dotted with dwarf-ruins, and Larus Sharpshard is eager to reclaim some of the treasures that may still remain in such stony places.",mobs={{locations={"24.85S, 4.03W"},name="Larus Sharpshard"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1560,scope="n/a",name="Old Treasures",arcs="Every Last Ingot",level=43,pois={{locations={"21.71S, 4.44W"},name="Damaged Dwarf-chest"}},minlevel=38,b="Larus Sharpshard",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe strongbox is in the old dwarf-keep that overlooks the source of the Bruinen, north of Glóin's camp. Larus Sharpshard is at Glóin's camp, north of Rivendell.\nLarus Sharpshard asked you to retrieve a strongbox from an old dwarf-keep.\n* Bring damaged dwarf-chest to Larus Sharpshard\n*",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Falathlorn",zone="Ered Luin",reputation={{val="- 500 with The Ale Association"},{val="+900 with The Inn League"}},money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="You have received an order to fill a delivery to a member of the Inn League who has been stranded away from the festival this season.",mobs={{locations={"21.64S, 94.12W"},name="Alrek"},{locations={"29.97S, 71.58W","24.62S, 93.03W","24.56S, 51.47W"},name="Inn League Tavern Keep"}},category="Inn League",id=1561,scope="n/a",prev={1192},name="One Drink Too Many",receive={{val="Badge of Taste",id="700216F0"}},level=15,minlevel=11,b="Inn League Tavern Keep",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nForsaken Ale can be purchased at The Forsaken Inn in the Lone-lands.\nYou should travel to The Forsaken Inn to purchase Forsaken Ale for Alrek, who waits at Thrasi's Lodge for some assistance.\n* Turn in Forsaken Ale\nObj 2:\nAlrek is at Thrasi's Lodge in Ered Luin, far to the west of the Lone-lands.\nAlrek has asked you to collect a Forsaken Ale for him from Anlaf the Forlorn at The Forsaken Inn.\n* Bring the Forsaken Ale to Alrek\n* Turn in Forsaken Ale"},
{area="Dol Guldur",zone="Mirkwood",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Sâd-en-Dagor, the training-grounds of Dol Guldur, are overseen by three champions of the Lieutenant of Dol Guldur.",mobs={{locations={"16.02S, 44.47W"},name="Torist"}},category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=1562,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="One Fell Swoop",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Torist",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nUrcheron, Carchrien, and Durkâr, the champions of Dol Guldur, are in Sâd-en-Dagor, north-east of Helethir, in Dol Guldur.\nTorist has asked you to defeat all three champions of Dol Guldur in one strike.\n* Defeat all three champions of Dol Guldur at once\nObj 2:\nTorist is in Helethir, south-west from Dol Guldur.\nYou should return to Torist for your reward.\n* Talk to Torist at Helethir"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Estmar Bolger has accidentally lost the notes pertaining to his family business.",mobs={{locations={"31.21S, 69.98W"},name="Misty Bolger"},{locations={"31.22S, 69.97W"},name="Brago Puddifoot"},{locations={"33.38S, 75.36W","33.38S, 75.35W"},name="Estmar Bolger"}},category="Special",id=1563,scope="n/a",name="One Fish, Two Fish",level=5,minlevel=1,b="Estmar Bolger",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMisty Bolger is north and east of Michel Delving in the town of Bywater.\nEstmar Bolger has asked that you visit his sister, Misty Bolger, and find out how many fish she caught last week.\n* Talk to Misty Bolger",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={376},area="Southern Emyn Uial",zone="Evendim",d="The Ranger Culang has learned of a great treasure buried long ago by a Dúnadan-landholder and wants it recovered before it is found by tomb-robbers.",category="Evendim",id=1564,scope="n/a",prev={2111},name="One More Marker",arcs="The Treasure Hunt",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,c={"* This Stone Marker is guarded by many tomb-robbers. Across the clearing, there is a group of treasure-hunters, that will attack the tomb-robbers guarding the Stone Marker if you speak with their captain [9.5S, 73.0W]. You can either help the treasure hunters defeat the Tomb-robbers, or avoid getting aggro and complete the quest while they fight."},pois={{locations={"9.30S, 73.12W"},name="Stone Marker"}},minlevel=33,b="Stone Marker",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe treasure may lie beneath another stone marker, somewhere in Evendim, if this riddle is to be believed:\n\"On the western shore of mighty Lake Nenuial,\nStone paths run to the water from a flat clearing.\"\nYou should examine the marker when you find it for some clue to the location of the treasure.\n* Find/Use Stone Marker"},
{area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Thrasi has given you some thistle-mead to feed to the mother lynx, hopefully to help heal her injuries.",mobs={{locations={"21.59S, 94.17W"},name="Thrasi"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1565,scope="n/a",prev={2675},name="On the Mend",arcs="The Cat's Meow",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Lesser Athelas Essence",id="70000D5D"},{q="(x5)",val="Lesser Celebrant Salve",id="700005B4"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Thrasi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe mother lynx is at Thrasi's cabin.\nThrasi asked you to feed the thistle-mead to the mother lynx.\n* Turn in Thistle-mead\nObj 2:\nThrasi is at the hunter's lodge to the north.\nThe mother lynx seems to be completely healed, yet she has returned to Thrasi's side.\n* Talk to Thrasi"},
{["next"]={1090},area="Talvi-mûri",zone="Forochel",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Thurmaer managed to lose his own way and that of most of his fellowship after he lost their map of Forochel! The map was lost during a battle with the Gauredain, and he believes it may have been taken by one of their hunters on the glacier of Talvi-mûri.",mobs={{locations={"19.35N, 83.76W"},name="Thurmaer"}},category="Forochel",id=1566,scope="n/a",prev={2692},name="On the Road to Misfortune",receive={{val="Small Trap",id="7000E967"}},level=49,c={"* Kill any Gauradan for the map"},minlevel=44,b="Thurmaer",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Gauredain can be found in Talvi-mûri, south of Kuru-leiri.\nThurmaer has asked you to hunt down the Gauredain until you find the one who stole his map.\n* Hunt the Gauredain until you find Thurmaer's Map\nObj 2:\nThe Gauredain can be found in Talvi-mûri, south of Kuru-leiri.\nThurmaer has asked you to hunt down the Gauredain until you find the one who stole his map.\n* Turn in Thurmaer's Map\nObj 3:\nThurmaer is at Kuru-leiri, north of Talvi-mûri.\nYou finally found Thurmaer's map in the possession of one of the Gauradain. You should now return it to him.\n* Talk to Thurmaer\n* Turn in Thurmaer's Map"},
{["next"]={566},area="Vale of Thrain",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="With the thickets removed from the canal, the waterflow has been restored to Noglond in the Vale of Thráin.",mobs={{locations={"20.33S, 97.14W"},name="Otkell"},{locations={"19.31S, 100.48W"},name="Geitir"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1567,scope="n/a",prev={1740},name="On to Gondamon",arcs="The Dwarf-canal",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Geitir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOtkell is in Gondamon, east down the road from Noglond, and south at the first crossing.\nGeitir has asked you to inform Otkell in Gondamon about the restoration of the canal.\n* Talk to Otkell"},
{area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",d="Lolo Wendingway mentioned that the people of Staddle are dealing with some peculiar goings-on and told you to visit Watcher Redweed for more information.",mobs={{locations={"31.09S, 49.40W"},name="Watcher Redweed"},{locations={"30.18S, 49.67W"},name="Lolo Wendingway"}},category="Bree-land",id=1568,scope="n/a",prev={2372},name="On to Staddle",c={"* Watcher Redweed is in Staddle, east of Bree"},level=8,minlevel=4,b="Lolo Wendingway",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWatcher Redweed can be found in Staddle centre.\nLolo Wendingway advised you to seek out Watcher Redweed to help out with troubles brewing in the surrounding areas.\n* Talk to Watcher Redweed",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Commander Gisur is impressed with your performance and believes he knows of someone who can use your aid.",mobs={{locations={"10.87N, 23.93W"},name="Areneth"}},selectoneof={{val="Areneth's Necklace",id="7000D9A3"},{val="Thol-klath",id="7000223F"}},category="Angmar",id=1569,scope="n/a",prev={45},name="Onward to Gath Forthnír",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Guard-captain Gisur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGath Forthnír is far to the north of Gabilshathûr.\nCommander Gisur told you that Golodir's army was not completely destroyed, and the Ranger has established a camp in the north, Gath Forthnír.\n* Talk to the gate-keeper of Gath Forthnír",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="42s"}},d="Any support the rangers would hope to get to Annuminas by boat would be cut down by the archers throughout the bay.",category="Evendim",id=1570,scope="n/a",name="Open Channels",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\n* Defeat Angmarim Lookouts\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will be pleased to hear the lookouts have been removed.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1937},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="The bridge running beneath the Dwarf-lords' Gate contains a hidden waterway that once brought fresh water to the Dolven-view. The waterway was closed long ago.",selectoneof={{val="Worker's Helmet",id=70016063},{val="Sót's Bracelet",id="7001639A"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1571,scope="n/a",prev={567},name="Opening the Waterways",arcs="Moria Reclamation",level=52,pois={{locations={"6.68S, 111.95W","6.68S, 112.00W"},name="Waterway-lever"}},minlevel=47,b="Sót",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe bridge lies to the north of the Dolven-view.\nSót has asked you to throw the levers on the bridge to open the waterway running from the Dwarf-Lord's Gate to the Dolven-view.\n* Use Waterway-lever\nObj 2:\nThe bridge lies to the north of the Dolven-view.\nSót has asked you to throw the levers on the bridge to open the waterway running from the Dwarf-Lord's Gate to the Dolven-view.\nObj 3:\nSót is at the Dolven-view camp, south of the bridge.\nYou should return to Sót and inform him that, even though you threw all the levers, you did not hear any water flow through the ancient waterways.\n* Talk to Sót at the Dolven-view camp"},
{["next"]={2458},area="Fasach-larran",zone="Angmar",d="Some of the Trév Gállorg live in Donnvail, a northern city now controlled by the Angmarim.",mobs={{locations={"2.54N, 37.30W"},name="Búdan"},{locations={"6.27N, 34.54W"},name="Branan"}},category="Angmar",id=1572,scope="n/a",prev={2533},name="Oppression's Yoke",arcs="Oppression's Yoke",level=43,c={"* Branan is at Donnvail [6.3N, 34.5W]"},minlevel=38,b="Búdan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBranan is by the gate of the city of Donnvail, north-east of Fail-á-Khro, among the hills of Fasach-falroid.\nBúdan has sent you to find a Man named Branan in the city of Donnvail in an attempt to cast off the oppressive yoke of Angmar.\n* Talk to Branan",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Once the loyal caretakers to the elder Huorns of the great wood, the bog-lurkers of Agamaur are a fallen and corrupt group of beings beyond saving. They have learned to relish the blood of the living, and in so doing, have become the very evil they once stopped from spreading through the lands.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=1573,scope="n/a",name="Optional Objective: Bog-lurkers",c={"* Kill all bog-lurkers. There should be enough bog-lurkers."},level=32,minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nOnce noble guardians of the forest, the bog-lurkers in the Arboretum of Garth Agarwen are now twisted and terrible creatures thriving on blood. They must be slain for they cannot be saved.\n* Defeat bog-lurkers in the Arboretum (8)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Within the fortress at Garth Agarwen, you will find the main force of the Créoth Hillmen loyal to the Red-maid. It is these Men, descendents of the Rhudaur, who poisoned the land and drove the once peaceful Red-maid mad.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=1574,scope="n/a",name="Optional Objective: Créoth",level=32,minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nYou should hunt through the fortress and the ruins for the Créoth Hillmen. Purge the true-blooded minions of Angmar and punish them for defiling the natural order in the Lone-lands.\n* Defeat Créoth Hillmen within the Garth Agarwen fortress (40)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="The pool within the fortress of Garth Agarwen is full of darkwater and their leader. Cleansing this pool will do well to assist the land in recovering from the corruption that has for so long seeped into every facet of the land.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=1575,scope="n/a",name="Optional Objective: Darkwater",level=32,minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nYou should force the darkwater from their hiding places within the pool of the Garth Agarwen fortress and confront their master, Raugzdrok.\n* Defeat darkwater within the Garth Agarwen fortress (7)\n* Defeat Raugzdrok",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Not all Dead are reanimated bodies returned from the grave to lay waste to the innocent and pure. Some take whatever form they can, even if it is only part of a whole. When no body can be found, the fell spirits will seek another refuge and finding only an arm, or other body part, they will inhabit the creation and destroy life through this means.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=1576,scope="n/a",name="Optional Objective: Decayed",c={"* The Decayed are located at the metal gates that drop down. There are three: one near the beginning and two in the back."},level=32,minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nDecayed can be found within unlikely locations, lurking in the crevasses and darkness of stone corridors throughout the barrows. Exposing these creations will require you to spring their trap, but do not be surprised; keep your wits about you, and you will destroy these vile creations.\n* Defeat the decayed",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="In the short-lived time before Rhudaur fell beneath the sway of Angmar, there were three champions and a king who led the Men of Rhudaur with honour and justice. In the Arboretum, the three were interred in a place where the peaceful woods would watch over them and the people could visit them in quiet reflection.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=1577,scope="n/a",name="Optional Objective: Key Locations",level=32,minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Garth Agarwen Arboretum was home to many important locations. These included the tombs of three of their champions: Fuirvaw, Hargram, and Halvegil, a statue to their first king, Nailion, and the founding stone that served as the marker for the bounds of their land: the Stone of Mingond.\n* Discover the Memorial of Nailion\n* Discover the Stone of Mingond\n* Discover Fuirvaw's resting place\n* Discover Hargam's resting place\n* Discover Halvegil's resting place",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Not all Men of Rhudaur were Men of evil. Some were heroes or Men of noble deeds in their time. They are lost now, within the mire of this land and lost to the corruption of their people. Still, they exist in unmarked graves in these barrows.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=1578,scope="n/a",name="Optional Objective: Unnamed Tombs",level=32,minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThough the Rhudaur fell quickly, they had heroes, and not all the Rhudaur were part of the malignancy that crept into the land. There are five such heroes entombed within the Garth Agarwen barrows. You should visit their graves. If for no other reason than to know that these Men were not the culprits behind the great tragedy of this land.\n* Discover the first unmarked tomb\n* Discover the second unmarked tomb\n* Discover the third unmarked tomb\n* Discover the fourth unmarked tomb\n* Discover the fifth unmarked tomb",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="The time of Men is not so long, and the time of Rhudaur before its fall to corruption and alliance with Angmar was shorter still. Heroes, warriors, sacrifices, thieves, villains, and many others were buried in the barrows near the Red-maid's spring. Here, the Gaunt-lord Ivar has chosen to begin raising his army.",category="Garth Agarwen",id=1579,scope="n/a",name="Optional Objective: Wights",level=32,minlevel=27,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nWights patrol the befouled land in an endless journey through the mire. They wait until they will be called on by their dread lord, Ivar, to make war upon the living and began their campaign of corruption through the land. It need not be this way. Armed as you are, you can aid the Free Peoples of the world by ridding the land of these foul creatures.\n* Defeat wights (30)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="Nethúr told you that veteran Orcs carry special medallions which signify their achievements.",mobs={{locations={"9.71S, 40.77W"},name="Nethúr"}},category="Reputation",id=1580,scope="n/a",name="Orc Battle-medallions -- Introduction",level=38,minlevel=33,b="Nethúr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs can be found in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín, in the North Downs. Nethúr is at Esteldín.\nNethúr asked you to collect Orc battle-medallions and bring them to her.\n* Bring Orc Battle-medallions to Nethúr at Esteldín.\n* Turn in Orc Battle-medallion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={3197},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="11s 50c"}},d="Celephadh has asked for your help in securing the safety of the lands around Esteldín.",mobs={{locations={"9.79S, 41.50W"},name="Celephadh"}},category="North Downs",id=1581,scope="n/a",prev={2035},name="Orc-bounty",arcs="Servants of the Enemy",receive={{val="Daerthann",id="70006BEE"}},level=25,minlevel=20,b="Celephadh",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orcs threatening the central North Downs can be found around the farm fields and rolling hills of Kingsfell.\nCelephadh asks that you foray against the Orcs, hoping to drive them away.\n* Defeat Orcs (20)\nObj 2:\nCelephadh can be found in the hidden Ranger stronghold of Esteldín.\nFulfilling your duty to Celephadh, you should return to him and give him news of your victory.\n* Talk to Celephadh"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Nethúr told you of the cunning Orcs who dwell in Malenhad, the swamp in the southern reaches of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.71S, 40.77W"},name="Nethúr"}},category="Reputation",id=1582,scope="n/a",name="Orc Campaign-medallions -- Introduction",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Nethúr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs can be found in Malenhad, far to the north of Esteldín, in Angmar. Nethúr is in Esteldín.\nNethúr has asked you to collect the campaign medallions of Angmar's cunning orcs and bring them to her.\n* Bring Orc Campaign-medallions to Nethúr at Esteldín.\n* Turn in Orc Campaign-medallion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Meluinen",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="13s"}},d="Meluinen is threatened by the presence of a large encampment of Ongbûrz Orcs in the valley to the south-west.",mobs={{locations={"13.77S, 44.87W"},name="Brethilwen"}},category="North Downs",id=1583,scope="n/a",prev={1905},name="Orc Excursions",receive={{val="Cubrog",id="70006B9C"}},level=26,minlevel=21,b="Brethilwen",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrc-scouts have crept into Meluinen from the valley to the south-west of Lin Giliath.\nBrethilwen has asked you to slay any Orcs you find in Meluinen, thus reducing the Ongbûrz threat.\n* Defeat Orcs in Meluinen (8)\nObj 2:\nBrethilwen is in Lin Giliath.\nBrethilwen will be heartened to hear of your victory over the Orcs that had entered Meluinen.\n* Talk to Brethilwen",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1799},reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="41s 30c"}},d="The ruins of Annuminas have fallen to the forces of Angmar.",category="Evendim",id=1584,scope="n/a",name="Orchalwë's Mission",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="TBD Follow",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrchalwë has decided to join the fight and help to reclaim Annuminas.\nIf you become separated from Orchalwë, you can use the smoke signal he gave you to call him to you.\n* Aid Orchalwë with Untoward Aggression\n* Aid Orchalwë with Monuments of Angmar\n* Use Smoke Signal\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will want to discuss all that has happened.\n* Turn in Smoke Signal\n* Use Smoke Signal\nObj 3:\nis at Echad Garthadir in Annuminas.\nwill want a report of how things went with Orchalwë.\n* Talk to TBD Follow",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={721},area="Northern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="3s 20c"}},d="Rangers, watching movements of enemies from the north and south, are concerned over the appearance of a foe they have long fought in the north.",mobs={{locations={"23.74S, 53.55W"},name="Andreg"}},category="Bree-land",id=1585,scope="n/a",prev={1513},name="Orc Out-riders",arcs="My Brethren's Call",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Superior Complete Hobbit Breakfast",id=70003369}},level=18,minlevel=13,b="Andreg",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrc-encampments can be found north and east of the Old Greenway Fort.\nAndreg asked you to make your way north to strike against the Orcs trickling in from the North Downs.\n* Defeat Tarkrîp grunts\n* Defeat Tarkrîp prowlers\n* Defeat Tarkrîp killers\nObj 2:\nAndreg is at his post outside of the Old Greenway Fort.\nOrcs crawling throughout the hills north of the Old Greenway Fort seem to be larger in number than the Rangers previously thought. Andreg must be informed.\n* Talk to Andreg at the Old Greenway Fort"},
{["next"]={2096},zone="Angmar",area="Ram Dúath",money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Orcs marching through Ram Dúath have unsettled the Earth-kin dwelling there and have cut off any hope of safe return for the Earth-kin hunters sojourning in the North Downs.",mobs={{locations={"3.07S, 39.02W"},name="Chief Tuokki"}},category="Angmar",id=1586,scope="n/a",name="Orcs in the Ram Dúath",arcs="Strength of Stone",c={"* There are a number of Orcs to the south-east of the camp that can be pulled and taken down solo. You may need to wait for them to respawn once or twice, since the ones at the Catapults tend to pull in groups of 3-5 and can be very difficult to take down alone."},level=40,minlevel=35,b="Chief Tuokki",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are Blogmal Orcs in the south-east part of the Ram Dúath.\nThe Tuokki, the Earth-kin elder leading the Suuri-lehmä tribe while their chieftain is away south in the North Downs, has asked you to help drive the Blogmal Orcs from Ram Dúath.\n* Defeat Blogmal fighters\n* Defeat Blogmal skirmishers\nObj 2:\nChief Tuokki is at the Suuri-lehmä camp in Ram Dúath.\nYou should return to Chief Tuokki and tell him of your victory against the Orcs of the Blogmal tribe.\n* Talk to Chief Tuokki",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1432},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="30s 24c"}},d="A great host of Orcs spilled through Ram Dúath, driving the Men of the North Downs from their farms. Esteldín, home of the few remaining Dúnedain of the North, was spared discovery. It is from there that the Rangers begin to plan their counter-offensive against the black tide of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.63S, 41.42W"},name="Arohir"}},selectoneof={{val="Arohir's Crossbow",id="7000930B"},{val="Bridge-defenders",id=70001761},{val="Arohir's Necklace",id="7000930C"},{val="Arohir's Axe",id=70001762}},category="North Downs",id=1587,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={488},name="Orcs of the Blood Mountain",arcs="Shattering the Alliance",level=33,minlevel=28,b="Arohir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe strongest warriors of the Ongbúrz tribe can be found patrolling the deep trenches of Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\nIn order to keep the Orc-host in confusion, Arohir has asked you to enter the trenches of Dol Dínen and slay the Ongbúrz tribe's strongest warriors. He suggests you take allies with you.\n* Kill 16 Ongbúrz Combatant\n* Kill 12 Ongbúrz Man-slayer\n* Kill 6 Ongbúrz Battle-master\nObj 2:\nArohir awaits word from you at Esteldín.\nArohir will want to hear news of your victory against the warriors of the Ongbúrz tribe.\n* Talk to Arohir"},
{area="The Weather Hills",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="7s"}},d="Candaith's pursuit of an Orc-company turned deadly when he was discovered, and in his haste to escape, he lost his bow to the Orcs.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 37.88W"},name="Candaith"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Simple Celebrant Salve",id=70001049},{val="Candaith's Spare Bow",id=70000722}},category="Lone-lands",id=1588,scope="n/a",prev={2827},name="Orc-thieves",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=22,c={"*"},minlevel=17,b="Candaith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWhite Hand archers scout the Midgewater Pass, and can be found also within Bleakrift, north-west of Candaith's camp at the foot of Weathertop.\nCandaith has asked you to recover his bow from the archer that has taken it.\n* Bring Candaith's bow to Candaith\n* Turn in Candaith's Bow"},
{["next"]={1454},area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="After hearing how you fared against the goblins at Goblin-town, Glóin grew more concerned.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Pure Healing Draught",id="7000C640"},{q="(x5)",val="Pure Milkthistle Draught",id="7000C63C"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1589,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1019},name="Order from the Darkness",arcs="Investigating Goblin-town",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Distilled Athelas Essence",id="70000F31"}},level=48,minlevel=43,b="Glóin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe main entrance to Goblin-town is some distance to the east and north of Glóin's camp.\nGlóin believes that there may be something afoot within Goblin-town and bade you return to its halls in search of evidence exposing the reason behind the muster of the goblin-forces.\n* Talk to Glóin at his camp in the Misty Mountains\n* Turn in Sheaf of Papers"},
{["next"]={684},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="A great host of Orcs spilled through Ram Dúath, driving the Men of the North Downs from their farms. Esteldín, home of the few remaining Dúnedain of the North, was spared discovery. It is from there that the Rangers begin to plan their counter-offensive against the black tide of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.44S, 41.27W"},name="Daervunn"}},category="North Downs",id=1590,scope="n/a",prev={2302},name="Orders from the Front",arcs="The Black Tide of Angmar",level=32,pois={{locations={"13.04S, 37.87W","13.10S, 37.98W","13.07S, 37.92W","12.82S, 36.53W"},name="Uruk-orders"}},minlevel=27,b="Daervunn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe orders may be found at one of the outer camps in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\nConcerned by the coordinated efforts of three Orc-tribes in the invasion of the North Downs, Daervunn has asked you to seek out their orders.\n* Collect Uruk-orders\nObj 2:\nDaervunn may be found in Esteldín, northwest of the camps at Dol Dínen.\nReturn the Uruk-orders to Daervunn in Esteldín.\n* Bring the Uruk-orders to Daervunn\n* Turn in Uruk-orders"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="An important Angmarim leader has been seen within Haudh Eldacar.",category="Evendim",id=1591,scope="n/a",name="Order's of the  Black Crown",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Rodlam",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHaudh Eldacar is to the West of the Ranger camp in the Way of Kings.\nRodlam asked you to obtain orders from the commander at Haudh Eldacar.\n* Turn in Orders from Angmar\nObj 2:\nRodlam is at the Ranger camp in the Way of Kings.\nRodlam will be eager to begin deciphering the orders you found.\n* Talk to Rodlam\n* Turn in Orders from Angmar",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="37s 52c"}},d="The Lossoth in the eastern tundra have a difficult time staying warm enough in the winters, because of a cold wind that whips through the canyon below.\nThey have discovered a rare kind of ore, which burns longer than wood.",mobs={{locations={"8.98N, 70.79W"},name="Turkka"}},category="Forochel",id=1592,scope="n/a",name="Ore for the Forge",level=46,pois={{locations={"9.22N, 70.11W","9.82N, 70.02W","9.80N, 70.47W","9.27N, 71.06W","9.25N, 70.26W","9.56N, 70.65W","9.47N, 70.38W","9.65N, 71.49W","9.27N, 70.85W","9.97N, 71.04W","9.98N, 71.31W","9.91N, 70.17W"},name="Ore Bearing Rock"}},minlevel=41,b="Turkka",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSearch for ore-bearing rocks in the area surrounding Pynti-leiri.\n* Use Ore Bearing Rock\nObj 2:\nBring the ore you have collected to Turkka in Pynti-leiri.\n* Talk to Turkka\n* Turn in Ore",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",money={{val="7s 98c"}},d="Kelsey West has told you something of Ost Forod, an old watch-post in Tyrn Fornech that has become settled by the hardened Men of Evendim.",mobs={{locations={"12.64S, 67.36W"},name="Kelsey West"},{locations={"7.51S, 64.39W"},name="Basil Gummidge"}},category="Evendim",id=1593,scope="n/a",name="Ost Forod in Tyrn Fornech",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=36,minlevel=31,b="Kelsey West",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBasil Gummidge is in Ost Forod, located in Tyrn Fornech along the road that runs north of the crossroads in Parth Aduial, northeast of Tinnudir.\nKelsey West has asked you to travel to Ost Forod to speak with Basil Gummidge and offer your help to the people there.\n* Talk to Basil Gummidge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nain Enidh",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="4s"}},d="There's an inn by the road from Ost Guruth where you can find food and shelter and perhaps employment.",mobs={{locations={"31.49S, 29.50W"},name="Frideric the Elder"},{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Candac Brightwood"}},category="Lone-lands",id=1594,scope="n/a",name="Ost Guruth to The Forsaken Inn",level=20,minlevel=15,b="Frideric the Elder",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Forsaken Inn can be found along the road to the west.\nGo to the Forsaken Inn and talk to Candac Brightwood.\n* Talk to Candac Brightwood",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1065},reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="Ost Heryn is an ancient fortress built to support Fornost. In the time of need however, its leader betrayed his oath.",mobs={{locations={"10.30S, 60.01W"},name="Torogethir"}},category="Evendim",id=1595,scope="n/a",prev={2722},name="Ost Heryn",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=34,minlevel=29,b="Torogethir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTorogethir is at his camp.\nTorogethir has several tasks he wishes you to complete for him.\nObj 2:\nTorogethir is at his camp.\nTorogethir will want to speak to you about what happened at Ost Heryn.\n* Talk to Torogethir",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2075},area="Northern High Pass",zone="The Misty Mountains",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Aeglas is concerned for the well-being of the other prisoners in the dungeons of Goblin-town and wishes to learn how they came to be there.",mobs={{locations={"20.28S, 5.40E","20.75S, 6.17E"},name="Glorwen"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1596,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Other Prisoners",arcs="In the Foe's Grasp",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Aeglas",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Elf-maiden and the goblin-prisoner are both in the dungeons of Goblin-town.\nAeglas seems unconcerned that he is captured by the goblins of Goblin-town. His concerns are more for the other prisoners within the depths, and he has asked you to discover what the others know of the unrest moving through the goblins of Goblin-town.\n* Talk to Glorwen in the Goblin-town prison\n* Talk to the goblin Oghûk in the Goblin-town prison\nObj 2:\nReturn to Aeglas within his cell in the Goblin-town prison.\nOghûk seemed an untrusting sort and offered no information unless you helped him. Glorwen seemed in good spirits, once she knew that Aeglas lived, and provided some important information. You should return at once to Aeglas.\n* Talk to Aeglas in his cell in the Goblin-town prison"},
{area="Coldfells",zone="The Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Ascwyn mentioned that Hoarhallow is besieged by the forces of Angmar and that the hobbits can use any help you could offer.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1597,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Our Friends in Hoarhallow",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Ascwyn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMayor Wat Mudbottom is at Hoarhallow far to the west of Glán Vraig, through the Grimwood Forest, on the banks of the Hoarwell River.\nBeset by the Enemy, the Hobbits of Hoarhallow are a hardy and proud people. Their Mayor, Wat Mudbottom, leads them and refuses to give up the land they own to the forces of Angmar. Sergeant-at-Arms Ascwyn directed you to speak with Wat Mudbottom."},
{["next"]={149,1054,1960},area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 40c"}},d="As the goblins descended on the Eglain in Minas Eriol, the tribe left something very important behind, hidden in the deepest ruins.",mobs={{locations={"34.38S, 36.91W"},name="Hunulf Munce"}},selectoneof={{val="Munce's Masher",id="70000C8F"},{val="Munce's Carver",id="7001D1E1"},{val="Hunulf's Band",id="7001D218"},{val="Munce's Ring",id="70000C8E"}},category="Lone-lands",id=1598,scope="n/a",name="Our Greatest Find",arcs="The Eglain - People of the Lone-lands",level=25,c={"* The statue drops off random goblins in Minas Eriol. Mobs confirmed to drop this item are White Hand Spear-thrower and White Hand Strong-arm"},minlevel=20,b="Hunulf Munce",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblins of Minas Eriol are in possession of the statue.\nHunulf directed you to seek out the greatest discovery made by the Eglain, a statue dredged from the swamps of the Lone-lands.\n* Deliver the Statue of The Maiden to Hunulf Munce\n* Turn in Statue of a Maiden"},
{["next"]={341},area="Mekhem-bizru",zone="Lothlórien",money={{val="28s"}},d="Orcs have left the depths of Moria to establish a camp in the Dimrill Dale. The dwarves worry as to what the purpose of the camp is.",category="Moria",id=1599,scope="n/a",name="Out from the Depths",arcs="Herald of War",receive={{val="Alrekur's Spear",id="7001641D"}},level=59,minlevel=54,b="Alrekur",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs can be found at Drû-garmadh, south-east of Mekhem-bizru.\nAlrekur is concerned about the number of Orcs setting up camps in the Dimrill Dale and wants you to thin their number.\n* Defeat Orcs in Drû-garmadh (12)\nObj 2:\nAlrekur is at Mekhem-bizru, north-west of Drû-garmadh.\nAlrekur will want to know the Orcs at Drû-garmadh have been thinned.\n* Talk to Alrekur at Mekhem-bizru"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="43s 12c"}},d="The dwarves believe that they have created a mixture that will destroy the fungus-growth infesting the Orcs and allow them to be easily defeated.",selectoneof={{val="Kraibag's Ruin",id=70016416},{val="Bracelet of Protection",id="70017CDD"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1600,scope="n/a",prev={878},name="Out of the Darkness",arcs="Fighting the Fungus",level=56,c={"* Kraibag is in The Chamber of Dark Waters [16.1S, 111.9W]"},minlevel=51,b="Sylfa",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKraibag is somewhere in the Water-works, near The Chamber of Dark Waters, south of the Rotting Cellar.\nSylfa told you to find Kraibag, the most powerful of the infested Orcs, and use the mixture the dwarves gave you on him to determine its effect.\n* Use Flask of Oil\nObj 2:\nKraibag is somewhere in the Water-works near The Chamber of Dark Waters, south of the Rotting Cellar.\nThe mixture appeared to have no effect on Kraibag. He must still be defeated to ensure the safety of the Rotting Cellar.\n* Defeat Kraibag\nObj 3:\nSylfa is at the Rotting Cellar, north of The Chamber of Dark Waters.\nReturn to Sylfa at the Rotting Cellar and inform him that even though the concoction they gave you did not work, in fact quite the opposite, you still defeated Kraibag.\n* Talk to Sylfa at the Rotting Cellar"},
{["next"]={2113},area="Mirobel",zone="Eregion",money={{val="25s 20c"}},d="Angmarim scour Eregion in search of any remnants of the past that may further strengthen their forces. The small band of Elves found at Echad Mirobel wish to preserve the ruins as they are, and have asked you to assist them in this mission.",mobs={{locations={"52.24S, 16.93W"},name="Ornras"}},category="Eregion",id=1601,scope="n/a",name="Out of the North",arcs="Agents of the North",level=51,minlevel=46,b="Ornras",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Angmarim can be found throughout Mirobel in southern Eregion, near the Elf-haven of Echad Mirobel.\nYou should seek out Angmarim in Mirobel and collect proof that they travel with Angmarim Iron. If the fears of Ornras are true, the tide could easily turn against the Elves with the forging of great weapons on the enemy's side.\n* Bring Angmarim iron to Ornras at Echad Mirobel\n* Turn in Angmar Iron",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mirobel",zone="Eregion",money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Forces loyal to Saruman have moved up from the south and begun to sift through the ruins of Eregion. News of their arrival reached Echad Mirobel; there, the small force of Elves employ the assistance of any willing to aid them in driving this foe from the Elf-lands.",mobs={{locations={"52.49S, 16.80W"},name="Gelirwen"}},category="Eregion",id=1602,scope="n/a",name="Out of the South",arcs="Agents of the South",level=53,c={"* Angmarim Scouts drop the symbol"},minlevel=48,b="Gelirwen",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nA symbol of the White Hand may be found among the enemies throughout the lands around Echad Mirobel.\nGelriwen wants to preserve the memory of the School at Tham Mírdain and save it from the befouling evil currently residing there. She will not risk lives without first knowing the enemies that are to be faced. She has asked you to obtain a symbol of the White Hand from among the enemies to help her learn about these foes.\n* Deliver the White Hand symbol to Gelirwen at Echad Mirobel\n* Turn in Symbol of the White Hand",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tâl Caradhras",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Rinneldor has asked you to seek out Ruidhriel who stands watch at the Redhorn Gate.",mobs={{locations={"49.10S, 9.34W"},name="Ruidhriel"}},category="Eregion",id=1603,scope="n/a",name="Over the Pass of Caradhras",arcs="Footsteps of the Company",level=50,c={"* Type /look at [46.4S, 4.7]"},minlevel=45,b="Ruidhriel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Redhorn Gate lies to the north-east of Ruidhriel's camp.\nRuidhriel has asked you to go up into the Redhorn Gate and look for signs of the Company where the snow and trees begin.\n* Look for signs of the Company (Perform /look)\n* Find the Redhorn Gate\nObj 2:\nRuidhriel is south and west of the Redhorn Gate, near the Burnt Tor.\nYou should return to Ruidhriel and tell her what you found.\n* Talk to Ruidhriel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2665},area="The Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Gufi is confident that the dwarves will be able to reclaim Moria quickly and is eager to scout out potential mine-sites.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1604,scope="n/a",name="Overweening Confidence",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Gufi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe bottom of the shaft beneath Menem-berej is in the centre of the Silvertine Lodes. The unmarked chamber is south of the Vault of Durin. The dead-end tunnel lies along the western edge of the Silvertine Lodes.\nGufi has asked you to scout out three potential mine-locations.\n* Scout beneath Menem-berej\n* Scout the unmarked chamber\n* Scout the tunnel\nObj 2:\nGufi is at the Deep Descent at the northern edge of the Silvertine Lodes.\nYou should return to Gufi with the results of your survey.\n* Talk to Gufi at the Deep Descent encampment",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Zelem-melek",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="The dwarves have devised a plan to convince Mazog the Ghâsh-hai are marching against him.",selectoneof={{val="Slayer of Rûgh",id=70016405},{val="Gapi's Armour",id="700163D6"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1605,scope="n/a",prev={195},name="Panic in the Ranks",arcs="Fooling Mazog's Orcs",level=57,pois={{locations={"10.79S, 108.17W"},name="Moria Orc-banner"}},minlevel=52,b="Gapi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRûgh can be found at Uzbad-bakân, north of Anazârmekhem and beyond the bonfires.\nGapi wants you to defeat one of Mazog's leaders at Uzbad-bakân and then set his banner on fire. He believes this will convince Mazog that the Ghâsh-hai are on the march against him.\n* Defeat Rûgh\n* Use Moria Orc-banner\n* Turn in Flint and Twigs\nObj 2:\nGapi is in Anzârmekhem south of Uzbad-bakân.\nGapi will be pleased to hear Rûgh was defeated, and his banner was set ablaze.\n* Talk to Gapi in Anazârmekhem"},
{["next"]={2097},area="Redhorn Lodes",zone="Moria",d="Armbeald has tasked you with finding the four missing teeth from the skull you brought him. He suggested you go to the White Hand Orcs in the Redhorn Lodes and search among the higher-ranking soldiers there.",category="Hunter",id=1606,scope="n/a",prev={397},name="Passage of Foes",arcs="The Path of the Trapper",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Armbeald",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orcs suspected of taking the teeth are in the White Hand Orc-fortress in the Redhorn Lodes.\nLook for high-ranking Orcs in your search for the missing teeth. They should be defeated and their remains searched, and if any teeth are found, Armbeald in the Redhorn Lodes will wish to see them.\n* Retun to Armbeald in the Redhorn Lodes\n* Turn in Yellowed Dwarf-tooth\n* Turn in Chipped Dwarf-tooth\n* Turn in Stained Dwarf-tooth\n* Turn in Flat dwarf-tooth",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1514},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Bilbo Baggins has completed his book and would like to make certain that his memory of the important locations is correct.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Bilbo Baggins"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1607,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="Passage to Darkness",arcs="Dim Memories of the Dark",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Bilbo Baggins",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBilbo Baggins described the location and advised you to use his description to find the hidden entrance to Goblin-town that he and the dwarves of Thorin's Company once came across on their journeys long ago.\nBilbo Baggins would like you to help him correct the directions to Goblin-town that he has written in his book.\n* Find The Black Crack\nObj 2:\nBilbo Baggins is at the Last Homely House in Rivendell, south of Goblin-town.\nHaving completed the task Bilbo set you to, you should return to him at Rivendell.\n* Talk to Bilbo Baggins at Rivendell"},
{area="Glain Vraig",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="As the battle in the Ettenmoors rages, the Free Peoples struggle to keep up their armour and weaponry for the seige.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1608,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Patching the Holes",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Ambeng",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nWild beasts with strong hides roam the Ettenmoors. The leather made from their hides will be useful to the war effort.\nSergeant-at-Arms Ambeng asked you to seek out untreated leather from the wild beasts throughout the Ettenmoors.\n* Speak with Sergeant-at-Arms Ambeng at Lugazag\n* Turn in Untreated Leather Hide",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={357},zone="Bree-land",area="Archet",d="Winiel has summoned you into her presence.",mobs={{locations={"13.76S, 44.82W"},name="Glambaen"},{locations={"19.04N, 72.23W"},name="Sana"},{locations={"15.26S, 101.58W"},name="Pennastan"},{locations={"20.13S, 97.03W"},name="Ráthorm"},{locations={"15.75S, 67.69W"},name="Glorennidh"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Barton Tanner"},{locations={"12.70S, 67.29W"},name="Celairen"},{locations={"9.58S, 41.06W"},name="Gwalothir"},{locations={"29.63S, 3.44W"},name="Elwen"},{locations={"30.40S, 51.71W","64.80N, 133.31W","30.47S, 51.65W","64.73N, 133.25W"},name="Dalton Willow"},{locations={"6.02S, 105.23W"},name="Ettela"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Shepherd Snowden"},{locations={"28.27S, 92.28W"},name="Athradir"},{locations={"25.31S, 48.66W"},name="Cuthbert Rook"}},category="Lore-master",id=1609,scope="n/a",requiredclasses="Lore-master",name="Path of the Ancient Master",arcs="The Path of the Ancient Master",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Cuthbert Rook",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWiniel is in the Water-works in Moria.\nYou have been instructed to look for the lore-master Winiel.\n* Talk to Winiel at the Water-works",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={587},zone="Bree-land",area="Archet",money={{val="27s 65c"}},d="Valthor has summoned you into his presence.",mobs={{locations={"15.13S, 103.31W"},name="Dourhand"},{locations={"29.84S, 4.69W"},name="Celeblas"},{locations={"19.18N, 71.88W"},name="Väinämõ"},{locations={"15.32S, 101.52W"},name="Malthendring"},{locations={"20.22S, 96.89W"},name="Haflith"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Geirr"},{locations={"9.71S, 41.41W"},name="Brethilthor"},{locations={"31.72S, 50.83W","31.71S, 50.83W"},name="Oggur"},{locations={"15.67S, 67.72W"},name="Golfeth"},{locations={"12.72S, 67.20W"},name="Uirod"},{locations={"6.26S, 105.27W"},name="Ormi"},{locations={"28.26S, 92.17W"},name="Drambor"},{locations={"25.30S, 48.70W"},name="Aldred Cartwright"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Sheldon Roper"}},category="Champion",id=1610,scope="n/a",requiredclasses="Champion",name="Path of the Martial Champion",arcs="The Path of the Martial Champion",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Aldred Cartwright",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nValthor is encamped at the Foundations of Stone in Moria.\nYou have been instructed to seek out the guidance of the champion Valthor.\n* Talk to Valthor at the Foundations of Stone",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={800,1340},area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Elves of the Golden Host landed on the eastern shore of the Anduin and drove a wedge through the heart of the Orcs, but there is still danger within the Mirk-eaves.",mobs={{locations={"15.07S, 61.53W"},name="Falasgon"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1611,scope="n/a",name="Patrolling the Beach",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Falasgon",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblin-scouts can be found sneaking throughout the Mirk-eaves.\nFalasgon has asked you to find and defeat some of the goblin-scouts that have been spotted near Echad Sirion. Perhaps they might carry something that will suggest the location of their camp.\n* Turn in Token of Dol Guldur\n* Kill 3 Goblin-scout\nObj 2:\nFalasgon is at Echad Sirion in the Mirk-eaves.\nYou should bring the tokens you found to Falasgon for his examination.\n* Talk to Falasgon\n* Turn in Token of Dol Guldur"},
{["next"]={110,1629},area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="2s 55c"}},d="Adso's problems become more difficult as the brigands continue to harass he and his workers.",mobs={{locations={"29.12S, 56.78W"},name="Adso Haybank"}},category="Bree-land",id=1612,scope="n/a",prev={741},name="Paying Bills",arcs="Unfair Cost of Business",level=17,minlevel=12,b="Adso Haybank",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBrigands in the southern Bree-fields may carry Adso's produce. Adso Haybank is at his camp along the Great East Road.\nAdso worries that his workers will grow ill without proper meals and has asked you to recover his much-needed produce.\n* Return the produce to Adso\n* Turn in Adso's Goods"},
{["next"]={444},area="Greenfields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Bullroarer's Brew is placed at the foot of the statue of the Bullroarer in Brockenborings as part of a ceremony of respect.",mobs={{locations={"27.24S, 67.25W"},name="Tobias Brockhouse"},{locations={"27.23S, 67.71W"},name="Sigismond North-took"},{locations={"31.98S, 63.79W"},name="Gunderic Grubb"}},category="Spring Festival",id=1613,scope="n/a",prev={443},name="Paying Your Respects",level=10,pois={{locations={"27.23S, 67.68W","27.21S, 67.67W","27.22S, 67.69W","27.22S, 67.66W","27.21S, 67.68W","27.22S, 67.70W","27.23S, 67.69W"},name="Stone"}},minlevel=6,b="Sigismond North-took",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGunderic Grubb is at The Golden Perch in Stock, south and east of Brockenborings.\nSigismond North-took told you to take the clover you collected to Gunderic Grubb.\n* Talk to Gunderic Grubb\n* Turn in Clover\nObj 2:\nThe statue of the Bullroarer is at the north edge of Brockenborings, north and west of Stock, overlooking the Greenfields.\nYou have been instructed to pay your respects to Bandobras Took by placing a tankard of Bullroarer's Brew near his statue.\n* Use Stone\n* Turn in Bullroarer's Brew\nObj 3:\nSigismond North-took is in Brockenborings.\nYou have paid your respects to Bandobras Took. Now you should return to Sigismond North-took.\n* Talk to Sigismond North-took\nObj 4:\nSpeak with Tobias Brockhouse just east of Brockenborings.\n* Talk to Tobias Brockhouse",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="4s 8c"}},d="Adso Haybank has had enough of the brigands who have been extorting money and food from him.",mobs={{locations={"29.12S, 56.78W"},name="Adso Haybank"}},selectoneof={{val="Adso's Vest",id=70000643},{val="Torchar",id="700090F9"},{val="Adso's Blade",id=70000644}},category="Bree-land",id=1614,scope="n/a",prev={2687,1627},name="Payment in Full",arcs="Unfair Cost of Business",level=17,minlevel=12,b="Adso Haybank",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe brigand, Brunmor, is encamped at the Outlaw's Haven, west and north of Adso's Camp.\nDesperate to rid himself of his debts and his troubles, Adso Haybank has asked you to deal with Bill Ferny's associate, Brunmor.\n* Defeat Brunmor\nObj 2:\nAdso Haybank is at his camp, south-east along the Great East Road.\nDesperate to rid himself of his troubles, Adso asked you to drive off the brigands who were extorting money from him. The hobbit will be glad to know that you have succeeded.\n* Talk to Adso Haybank at Adso's Camp"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="Ost Heryn is an ancient fortress built to support Fornost. In the time of need however, its leader betrayed his oath.",mobs={{locations={"10.30S, 60.01W"},name="Torogethir"}},category="Evendim",id=1615,scope="n/a",name="Payment of an Ancient Debt",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=34,minlevel=29,b="Torogethir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOst Heryn is south of Torogethir's Camp.\nTorogethir asked you to venture to Ost Heryn and defeat the Oath-breaker Commander there.\n* Kill 1 Oath-breaker Commander\nObj 2:\nTorogethir is at his camp north of Ost Heryn.\nTorogethir will be pleased to hear the Oath-breaker Commander has tasted defeat and disappeared.\n* Talk to Torogethir",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={281},area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Your examination of the rubble at Pembar yielded some relic-fragments, which concern Faenhilith greatly.",mobs={{locations={"47.00S, 12.47W"},name="Faenhilith"}},category="Eregion",id=1616,scope="n/a",prev={2539},name="Pembar's Relics",arcs="The Ruins of Pembar",level=49,c={"* Pembar is at [44.1S, 10.8W]"},minlevel=44,b="Faenhilith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElf-relics and Elf-trinkets are being held by the half-orcs who are encamped at Pembar, north-east of Echad Eregion.\nFaenhilith has asked you to go to Pembar and defeat the half-orcs there, bringing her any relics or trinkets you find in their possession.\n* Bring relics to Faenhilith\n* Turn in Elf-relic (Level 1)\n* Turn in Elf-trinket"},
{["next"]={2058},area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The ancient Elf-ruins of Pembar have been overrun by half-orcs in the service of Saruman. What they may be seeking there is as of yet unknown, though the worm-eggs seen there by Lengliel's scouts are quite disturbing.",mobs={{locations={"46.98S, 12.48W"},name="Lengliel"}},category="Eregion",id=1617,scope="n/a",name="Pembar's Unwelcome Visitors",arcs="Pembar's Unwelcome Visitors",level=49,c={"* Pembar is at [44.1S, 10.8W]"},minlevel=44,b="Lengliel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalf-orcs can be found in Pembar, north-east of Echad Eregion.\nLengliel has asked you to defeat a number of Saruman's half-orcs and investigate their purpose at Pembar.\n* Defeat half-orcs at Pembar (15)\nObj 2:\nLengliel is at Echad Eregion, south-west of Pembar.\nYou should return to Lengliel with news of your success.\n* Talk to Lengliel at Echad Eregion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nan Amlug West",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Ormulf Worm-hunter, impressed with your selflessness, has offered you a reward for slaying ice-drakes after all.",mobs={{locations={"7.21S, 45.00W"},name="Ormulf Worm-hunter"}},titles={{val="the Selfless"}},category="Helegrod",id=1618,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={1754,1164},name="Picks for Delivery",arcs="Fangs for Nothing",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Scroll of the Ages",id=70009839},{val="Ancient Explorer's Pack",id="70009B83"}},level=50,minlevel=45,b="Ormulf Worm-hunter",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWegeir is somewhere within Thorin's Hall.\nOrmulf Worm-hunter has been impressed by your selflessness and asked you to deliver a crate of pick-axes to Wegeir, who can give to you your reward.\n* Talk to Wegeir\n* Turn in Crate of Pick-axes"},
{area="Chetwood",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Mason Thorne's ledger revealed the location of the old Hanging Tree. Now you can search for Ted Pickthorn's treasure.",mobs={{locations={"28.55S, 49.00W"},name="Ted Pickthorn"},{locations={"28.91S, 47.28W"},name="Mason Thorne"}},category="Bree-land",id=1619,scope="n/a",prev={2460},name="Pickthorn's Treasure",arcs="Beneath the Hanging Tree",level=8,c={"* Dig the stumps at Stump Field, then return to Ted"},pois={{locations={"29.93S, 47.79W"},name="Stump"}},minlevel=4,b="Mason Thorne",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe southeasternmost stump in the stump-field -- the one closest to Staddle Falls -- was once the Hanging Tree.\nAfter reading through the ledger you recovered for him, Mason Thorne was able to point you to the location of the Hanging Tree.\n* Use Stump\n* Turn in Rusty Pick-axe\nObj 2:\nTed Pickthorn is on the east side of Combe.\nFollowing Thorne's instructions, you found the stump of the Hanging Tree. You dug up something buried beneath the stump, but it is not what Ted Pickthorn had led you to believe. His father's treasure appears to be a pair of old boots.\n* Talk to Ted Pickthorn\n* Turn in Pickthorn's Boots\n* Turn in Rusty Pick-axe",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1371},area="Hobbiton-Bywater",zone="The Shire",d="Holly Hornblower's pies are in exceeding demand, and she does not have time to deliver them all.",mobs={{locations={"31.21S, 71.11W"},name="Holly Hornblower"}},category="Shire",id=1620,scope="n/a",name="Pie for The Green Dragon",arcs="Hot Pie Delivery",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Holly Hornblower",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGerd Whitfoot is at The Green Dragon Inn in Bywater.\nHolly Hornblower has asked you to deliver a pie to Gerd Whitfoot at The Green Dragon in Bywater. She warned you to not allow any hungry hobbits catch a whiff of the pie, or they will come by pestering her for a slice, and she has no time for that.\n* Pick up the pie from the table\nObj 2:\nHolly Hornblower can be found north of Hobbiton's main square, behind The Ivy Bush.\nYou should return to Holly Hornblower and let her know that the pie has been delivered.\n* Talk to Holly Hornblower",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={243},area="Zelem-melek",zone="Moria",money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="The Orcs of Mordor surround their camps with strong, well-built, difficult to attack walls.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1621,scope="n/a",prev={670},name="Piercing the Walls",arcs="Orcs of Mordor",level=53,pois={{locations={"7.66S, 106.93W","7.64S, 106.90W"},name="Orc Wall-section"}},minlevel=48,b="Knakk",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe barricades block the northern approach to the Mordor Orc-camp at Baiúrz-mur, north of the Orc-watch.\nKnakk believes if one of the barricades at the Mordor Orc-camp of Baiúrz-mur is destroyed, the Moria Orcs will attack the camp.\n* Use Orc Wall-section\nObj 2:\nKnakk is at the Orc-watch, south of Baiúrz-mur.\nKnakk will want to know that the barricade at Baiúrz-mur has been destroyed, and Moria is free to attack.\n* Talk to Knakk at the Orc-watch"},
{money={{val="40s 32c"}},d="Pale-folk pillagers and blades, working under the lash of the Ongbûrz, are ransacking the Libary of Tham Mírdain for anything of value.",category="Eregion",id=1622,scope="n/a",name="Pillagers of Knowledge",receive={{val="Eregion Mark",id="700216BE"}},level=51,minlevel=46,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe Pale-folk pillagers and blades can be found throughout the Library of Tham Mirdaín.\n* Defeat pale-folk pillagers\n* Defeat pale-folk blades"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Battle in the Ettenmoors is uncertain, with forces losing footholds as easily as they gain them. The Free Peoples have taken Tol Ascarnen but now must hold the location. To do this, they will need to strengthen their position as best they can.",category="Tol Ascarnen",id=1623,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Pillar of Strength",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Caddafrith",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nLeafcull Huorns can be found in the Grimwood Forest, south-west of Tol Ascarnen.\nSergeant-at-Arms Caddafrith has asked you to assist her in crafting a horn to call forces to fight against Angmar's army when they assail Tol Ascarnen. To complete the stand, she needs a heartwood from the Leafcull Huorns. She suggests you take allies, for the Huorns are a dangerous foe.\n* Return the heartwood to Sergeant-at-Arms Caddfrith at Tol Ascarnen\n* Turn in Leafcull Heartwood",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2072},area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Among the ruins outside Sâd Doldúr, there are a number of ancient pillars that have resided in this area for a number of years. These stones are ancient and may lead to valuable clues about exactly what is happening to the Ashenslades.",mobs={{locations={"17.48S, 44.56W"},name="Himeinior"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1624,scope="n/a",prev={1293},name="Pillars of Another Age",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,c={"* The northern Ancient Pillar is in the Ashenslades at [18.2S, 44.5W]\n* The central Ancient Pillar is in the Ashenslades at [18.5S, 44.8W]\n* The southern Ancient Pillar is near the Bleakmere at [18.8S, 44.3W]"},minlevel=60,b="Himeinior",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ancient pillars can be located among the ruins of Sâd Doldúr, which can be found by following the path below, down the mountain until you reach the ruins proper. There are three pillars, located in the northern, central, and southern portions of the ruins.\nThe cairn stones located among the ruins appear to be resistant to the blight that is sweeping the area. Himeinior asked you to travel to each of these locations and examine the pillars.\nObj 2:\nHimeinior is at the camp near Barad Angol upon the hill, north of the pillars.\nAfter examining the ancient pillars, you did not see any sign of corruption or taint. Return to Barad Angol and report this to Himeinior.\n* Talk to Himeinior near Barad Angol"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Annúminas",money={{val="42s"}},d="When they returned from a succesful battle the men of Arnor would etch their initials into the pillars of an ancient building.",category="Evendim",id=1625,scope="n/a",name="Pillars of Strength",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,pois={{locations={"18.42S, 71.36W","18.38S, 71.41W","18.28S, 71.36W","18.33S, 71.41W","18.28S, 71.26W","18.33S, 71.36W","18.47S, 71.41W"},name="Pillar"}},minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrchalwë has asked you to read the names etched into the pillars.\n* Use Pillar\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë wants to speak about the etched pillars.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1079},area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Bruner Stoutthrush, a merchant in Bree, has asked you to deliver an order to two of his customers.",mobs={{locations={"30.26S, 50.17W"},name="Bruner Stoutthrush"},{locations={"29.02S, 56.80W"},name="Roger Hawkling"}},category="Bree-land",id=1626,scope="n/a",prev={842},name="Pipe-weed Delivery",arcs="Shady Business",level=9,c={"* Roger is at Adso's camp, west of Bree (just take the road west)"},minlevel=5,b="Bruner Stoutthrush",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRoger Hawkling can be found at Adso Haybank's camp along the Great East Road, west of Bree, north of the Old Forest.\nStoutthrush wants you to bring the cask of pipe-weed to Roger Hawkling.\n* Talk to Roger Hawkling\n* Turn in Barrel of Staddle Pipe-weed"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="31s 36c"}},d="Hillmen from Angmar followed the Orc army through Ram Dúath into the North Downs and established an encampment near the head of the pass. These Hillmen serve to keep open the passage from Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.63S, 41.42W"},name="Arohir"}},selectoneof={{val="Anwarchris",id=70001769},{val="Red Feather",id="7000176A"},{val="Arohir's Cap",id=70001767},{val="Arohir's Gold Bracelet",id=70001766},{val="Hanham",id=70001768},{val="Avorlos",id=70001765}},category="North Downs",id=1627,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={3187},name="Plague-bearer of the North",arcs="Hillmen of the North",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Arohir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWithin the shadow of the Ram Dúath an Angmarim Oath-keeper commands her forces south into the North Downs. You must find her and defeat her.\nArohir enlisted your aid in finding and defeating the leader of the Angmarim forces, making certain that you understood that you should seek aid before assailing the leader.\n* Kill the Hillman Plague-bearer\nObj 2:\nArohir awaits word of the Angmarim's defeat within the confines of Esteldín. Meet him there to share news of your victory.\nAfter entering the Ram Dúath you sought out and defeated the leader of the Angmarim forces.\n* Speak with Arohir"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Sixteenth Hall is an area overrun with Orcs, many of whom suffer from a terrible illness that sweeps through the corridors. Defilers tend to the ill, while the rest of the halls are defended by those that remain able to do battle.",mobs={{locations={"12.90S, 100.69W"},name="Mallas"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1628,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Plague Wind",arcs="Peasant Halls",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Mallas",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Watchers of the Sixteenth Hall are in the Shadowed Refuge in Moria. The Elves and dwarves you seek are named Lar, Ymar, Odmar, Pentlenn, and Glorelloth.\nMallas has asked you to help his fellows at the Shadowed Refuge do various tasks in the Sixteenth Hall.\n* Aid Glorelloth: collect fungus from the Sixteenth Hall\n* Aid Pentlenn: collect samples from the Sixteenth Hall\n* Complete Odmar's task in the Sixteenth Hall\n* Complete Ymar's task within the Sixteenth Hall\n* Complete Lar's task in the Sixteenth Hall\nObj 2:\nThe Elf Mallas is at the Shadowed Refuge.\nYou have completed the tasks set before you by the dwarves Ymar, Lar, and Odmar and the Elves Glorelloth and Pentlenn, and should now bring tidings to Mallas of all that has transpired.\n* Return to Mallas at the Shadowed Refuge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1440},area="Goblin-town",zone="Misty Mountains",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Aeglas used the stake you provided him to prepare a special surprise for the Orcs.",selectoneof={{val="Maethoranc",id="7000D2F8"},{val="Scout's Rune-stone",id="700161E0"},{val="Scout's Ring",id="7000D2BB"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1629,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2075},name="Plan in Motion",arcs="In the Foe's Grasp",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Aeglas",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe stake should be placed on a sturdy patch of earth in the place where the Orcs are gathered within Goblin-town.\nAeglas' plan is nearly complete. He believes that the items within the bag will drive the Orcs into a frenzy and set them upon the goblins of Goblin-town.\n* Use Mound of Earth\n* Turn in Sack of items\nObj 2:\nAeglas is in his cell within the Goblin-town prison.\nAfter placing the Orc-head and pike in the gathering place, the Orcs grew enraged, but the goblins seemed prepared for their aggression and quickly put the matter to end. You should return to Aeglas with your report.\n* Talk to Aeglas in the Goblin-town prison"},
{area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Celebrandir was pleased with the seeds that were brought to him, for they gave him hope that the wood may yet be renewed.",mobs={{locations={"40.04S, 16.00W"},name="Celebrandir"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Infused Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA8E"},{val="Celebrandir's Hope",id=70016069}},category="Eregion",id=1630,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1938},name="Planting Anew",arcs="Planting Anew",level=49,c={"* The plots are around Sâd Thareg [42.7S, 16.8W]"},pois={{locations={"42.96S, 15.54W","42.16S, 16.10W","41.76S, 16.98W","42.20S, 16.65W","42.57S, 16.89W","41.50S, 16.98W","42.61S, 16.17W","42.30S, 16.46W","41.34S, 16.54W","42.30S, 17.03W","41.83S, 16.73W","42.31S, 15.91W","42.16S, 16.84W","42.68S, 15.91W","41.67S, 16.12W","42.70S, 16.81W"},name="Fertile Soil"}},minlevel=44,b="Celebrandir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are clearings throughout Glâd Ereg, the forest south of Gwingris.\nCelebrandir instructed you to plant the seeds in clear spaces where the trees will have room to grow.\n* Use Fertile Soil\nObj 2:\nCelebrandir is at Gwingris, north of Glâd Ereg.\nYou should return to Celebrandir and let him know that you have planted the seeds as he requested.\n* Talk to Celebrandir\n* Turn in Seed Bag"},
{["next"]={551},money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="If the Northcotton Farm is to have a market, a lot will need to be cleaned up.",category="Evendim",id=1631,scope="n/a",prev={1647},name="Planting Flowers",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="Milo Longfurrow",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFlowers can be found around the Northcotton Farm.\nMilo Longfurrow asked you to gather up flowers from around the farm.\n* Collect flowers (5 Flower)\nObj 2:\nThe planters are at the market-grounds.\nThe flowers need to be placed in the planters.\n* Use Planter\n* Obj 3:\nMilo Longfurrow is at the Northcotton Farm.\nMilo Longfurrow will be pleased to hear the flowers have been planted.\n* Talk to Milo Longfurrow",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1646},zone="Evendim",area="Bullroarer's Sward",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="If the Northcotton Farm is to have a market, a lot will need to be cleaned up.",category="Evendim",id=1632,scope="n/a",prev={1722},name="Planting Scarecrows",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,pois={{locations={"22.14S, 68.00W","22.14S, 68.01W","22.15S, 68.03W","22.14S, 68.02W","22.14S, 67.99W"},name="Scarecrow"},{locations={"22.38S, 68.19W","22.22S, 68.37W","22.37S, 67.96W"},name="Mound of Dirt"}},minlevel=25,b="Milo Longfurrow",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe scarecrows are behind a farm-house to the east.\nThe scarecrows must be collected before they can be placed in the fields.\n* Collect scarecrows (6 Scarecrow )\nObj 2:\nThe scarecrows should be placed in the fields around the Northcotton Farm.\nThe hobbit-children will delight in seeing the scarecrows in the fields.\n* Use Mound of Dirt\n* Obj 3:\nMilo Longfurrow is at the Northcotton Farm.\nMilo Longfurrow will be pleased to hear that the scarecrows are placed.\n* Talk to Milo Longfurrow",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1882},area="Nan Amlug West",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+300 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="6s 40c"}},d="The dwarf-mine at Othrikar is almost played out. Regin has heard of a rich \\qfather-lode\\q somewhere in Nan Amlug, and he hopes to determine the location of this lode.",mobs={{locations={"7.12S, 45.14W"},name="Regin"}},category="North Downs",id=1633,scope="n/a",name="Played-out",arcs="The Father-lode",level=28,minlevel=23,b="Regin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe lost mining records are somewhere around Othrikar probably in a chest or locker.\nRegin has asked you to recover old mining records that may give a clue to the location of the legendary \"father lode\".\n* Return the Mining Records to Regin\n* Turn in Mining-records"},
{zone="Enedwaith",area="Gloomglens",money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="After you rescued Gwin Curhonon from the bugan-village, he told you to visit his home.",mobs={{locations={"64.28S, 22.34W"},name="Gwin Curhonon"},{locations={"63.13S, 23.00W"},name="Rhus Cornchúthur"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1634,scope="n/a",prev={1050},name="Pleased to Make an Acquaintance",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Gwin Curhonon",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe hobbit-village of Maur Tulhau lies to the north-west of Gwin Curhonon's hiding place.\nGwin Curhonon asked you to bring word of his rescue to his kinsfolk in Maur Tulhau.\n* Talk to a hobbit at Maur Tulhau",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1338},area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+300 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="You have found a scrap of paper indicating that the Dourhand dwarves and Angmar seek to strengthen their alliance.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Brúnfair"}},category="Angmar",id=1635,scope="n/a",name="Pledge of the Dourhands",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Scrap of a Dwarf Pledge",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSomeone in Gath Forthnír will surely be interested the information you uncovered.\nYou have acquired information about Angmar's allies and plans. You should immediately inform someone of this development.\n* Talk to Brúnfair\n* Turn in Scrap of a Dwarf Pledge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1664},area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+300 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="You have found a scrap of paper indicating that the goblins of the Misty Mountains and Angmar seek to strengthen their alliance.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Brúnfair"}},category="Angmar",id=1636,scope="n/a",name="Pledge of the Goblins",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Scrap of a Goblin Pledge",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGath Forthnír is in the eastern reaches of Angmar, beyond Rammas Deluon.\nYou have acquired information about Angmar's allies and plans. You should immediately inform someone at Gath Forthnír of this development.\n* Talk to Brúnfair\n* Turn in Scrap of a Goblin Pledge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1306},reputation={{val="+300 with Council of the North"}},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="You have found a scrap of paper indicating that the Hillman-tribe called the Trév Duvárdain and Angmar seek to strengthen their alliance.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Brúnfair"}},category="Angmar",id=1637,scope="n/a",name="Pledge of the Trév Duvárdain",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Scrap of a Nomad Pledge",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGath Forthnír lies in the eastern reaches of Angmar, beyond Rammas Deluon.\nYou have acquired information about Angmar's allies and plans. You should immediately inform someone at Gath Forthnír of this development.\n* Talk to Brúnfair\n* Turn in Scrap of a Nomad Pledge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={335},area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+300 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="You have found a scrap of paper indicating that Saruman and Angmar seek to form an alliance.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Brúnfair"}},category="Angmar",id=1638,scope="n/a",name="Pledge of the White-hand",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Scrap of a Half-Orc Pledge",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGath Forthnír is in the eastern reaches of Angmar.\nYou have acquired information about Angmar's allies and plans. You should immediately inform someone at Gath Forthnír of this development.\n* Talk to Brúnfair\n* Turn in Scrap of a Half-Orc Pledge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2101},area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="The dwarves at the Chamber of the Crossroads are constantly on guard against the goblins, who vastly outnumber them. Everyone is expected to pull their own weight and then some in the frequent forays and battles -- particularly in the effort to clear the road between the Chamber of the Crossroads and Jazârgund, which remains nearly impassable.",selectoneof={{val="Líkmund's Bow",id=70016109},{val="Líkmund's Sword",id="700160FF"}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1639,scope="n/a",prev={1361},name="Plenty to Go Around",level=52,minlevel=47,b="Líkmund",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblins can be found throughout the passages of Durin's Way.\nHoping to clear the way to Jazârgund, Líkmund has asked you to defeat a large number of goblins.\n* Defeat goblins in Durin's Way (30)\nObj 2:\nLíkmund is in the Chamber of Crossroads.\nYou should return to the Chamber of the Crossroads and inform Líkmund that while you killed many goblins in Durin's Way, their numbers remain strong.\n* Talk to Líkmund at the Chamber of the Crossroads"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="The last of the tomb-robbers are within the Way of Kings, stripping bare the final resting place of many of the ancient city's rulers.",category="Evendim",id=1640,scope="n/a",name="Plunderers of History",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Nethrandir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTomb-robbers can be found within the Way of Kings.\nNethrandir asked you to defeat tomb-robbers within the Way of Kings.\n* Defeat tomb-robbers in the Way of Kings (12)\nObj 2:\nNethrandir is at the Ranger camp in the Way of Kings.\nNethrandir will be pleased to hear many tomb-robbers have been defeated.\n* Talk to Nethrandir",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="- 700 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Lothlórien",area="Nimrodel",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Asmund has one final request of you: to hunt the Hornéd Wood-lord, mightiest of the animals protected by the Elves of Lothlórien.",mobs={{locations={"14.12S, 73.04W"},name="Asmund"}},titles={{val="Poacher of the Protected Woods"}},selectoneof={{val="Woodlord's Crown",id="700192DC"},{val="Woodlord's Hat",id="700192D8"},{val="Woodlord's Helm",id="700192D7"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1641,scope="n/a",prev={1657},name="Poaching: Hornéd Wood-lord",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Asmund",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Hornéd Wood-lord roams the Golden Wood in an area called Egladil, in south-east Lothlórien.\nAsmund has asked you to undertake one last hunt: to claim the antlers of the Hornéd Wood-lord.\n* Turn in Wood-lord's Antlers\nObj 2:\nAsmund is in Echad Andestel, west of the border of Lothlórien.\nYou have hunted the Hornéd Wood-lord for his antlers and should bring them now to Asmund.\n* Talk to Asmund\n* Turn in Wood-lord's Antlers"},
{["next"]={1656},reputation={{val="- 700 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Lothlórien",area="Nimrodel",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Pleased with your previous hunt, Asmund has another request of you.",mobs={{locations={"14.12S, 73.04W"},name="Asmund"}},selectoneof={{val="Boar's Hide Pauldrons",id="700192DB"},{val="Boar's Hide Shoulder Pads",id="700192D6"},{val="Boar's Hide Spaulders",id="700192DD"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1642,scope="n/a",prev={1658},name="Poaching: Protected Boars in Lórien",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Asmund",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nProtected boars can be found within Lothlórien, in places called Eryn Laer and on the banks of the Anduin in Gelirdor.\nAsmund has asked you to hunt protected boars within Lothlórien.\n* Turn in Protected Boar Meat\nObj 2:\nAsmund is in Echad Andestel, west of the border of Lothlórien.\nYou have hunted the protected boars of Lothlórien and should return now with the meat to Asmund.\n* Talk to Asmund\n* Turn in Protected Boar Meat"},
{["next"]={1657},reputation={{val="- 700 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Lothlórien",area="Nimrodel",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Asmund has asked you to poach protected deer within Lórien, and has promised to reward you for doing so.",mobs={{locations={"14.12S, 73.04W"},name="Asmund"}},selectoneof={{val="Poacher's Cleaver",id="700192DE"},{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Lore",id="7001F257"},{val="Skinning Knife",id="700192D5"},{val="Bone Ring",id="700192D9"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1643,scope="n/a",name="Poaching: Protected Deer in Lórien",level=60,c={"* After accepting this quest, but before turning it in, you will be offered the An End to the Poaching quest. If you complete Asmund's quest, you will fail Limhendeth's one. If you turn in Limhendeth's quest, you will fail the poaching quest and won't be able to take any more poaching quests, should there be more."},minlevel=55,b="Asmund",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nProtected deer can be found in Lórien, wandering in Nan Celebrant and Gelirdor.\nAsmund has asked you to hunt the protected deer of Lórien, promising to reward you well for it.\n* Turn in Protected Deer Meat\nObj 2:\nAsmund is in Echad Andestel, west of the border of Lórien.\nYou have hunted some of the protected deer of Lórien for Asmund and should return now to him.\n* Talk to Asmund\n* Turn in Protected Deer Meat",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="Ivy has grown over the ruins of Tham Nambarth, threatening to rip the building brick by brick.",category="Evendim",id=1644,scope="n/a",name="Poisoned Ivy",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=34,pois={{locations={"11.80S, 65.95W","12.15S, 65.90W","11.76S, 65.36W","12.15S, 65.31W","11.74S, 65.50W","12.07S, 65.30W","12.03S, 65.62W","12.34S, 65.20W"},name="Ivy"}},minlevel=29,b="Gúrhebnir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTham Nambarth is east of Tinnudir.\nGúrhebnir asked you to go to Tham Nambarth and apply his concoction to the ivy you find there.\n* Use Ivy\nObj 2:\nGúrhebnir is at Tinnudir, west of Tham Nambarth.\nGúrhebnir will be discouraged to hear his concoction did nothing immediately.\n* Speak to Gúrhebnir\n* Turn in Concoction",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Gramsfoot",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Uglash provided you with a barrel of poison and a directive. Make your way to the waterfall overlooking the fortress Tol Ascarnen and empty the barrel into the water. With enough poison, you may force the enemy to leave the wood.",mobs={{locations={"12.30S, 20.89W"},name="Uglash"}},category="Ettenmoors",id=1645,scope="n/a",prev={2766},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Poisoning the Hoardale",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Uglash",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe source of the Hoardale is at the waterfall overlooking Tol Ascarnen.\nUglash sent you to poison the enemy's water source.\n* Use Barrel of Poison (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nUglash awaits your return at Gramsfoot.\nYou climbed to the top of the falls and poisoned the waters of the Hoardale. You should return to Uglash with the news.",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Chetwood",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Posco Burrows is concerned that his uncle, Filbert Burrows, has gone deep into the Chetwood to 'have a word' with the Blackwold brigands and wants to make sure he has not gotten himself into trouble.",mobs={{locations={"28.61S, 46.03W"},name="Filbert Burrows"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Lesser Athelas Essence",id="70000D5D"},{q="(x5)",val="Lesser Celebrant Salve",id="700005B4"}},category="Bree-land",id=1646,scope="n/a",name="Posco's Uncle",level=9,c={"* Filbert is at [27.0S, 42.9W]\n* Cole Sickleleaf is at [28.6S, 46.0W]\n* Then return to Filbert, then talk to Posco"},minlevel=5,b="Posco Burrows",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFilbert Burrows should be somewhere along the road east of Combe heading towards the Chetwood.\nPosco Burrows has asked you to look for his uncle, Filbert, and make sure he is unharmed.\n* Talk to Filbert Burrows\nObj 2:\nCole Sickleleaf is at the ruins between the main Blackwold encampment and Skunkwood's Farm.\nYou found Posco Burrow's uncle, Filbert, sitting on a stump at the crossroads in the Chetwood. He wants you to collect a handkerchief taken by Cole Sickleleaf.\n* Turn in Filbert's Handkerchief\nObj 3:\nFilbert Burrows is waiting at the crossroads in the Chetwood.\nYou should return Filbert Burrow's handkerchief to him and convince him to leave the area.\n* Bring the handkerchief to Filbert Burrows\n* Turn in Filbert's Handkerchief\nObj 4:\nPosco Burrows is waiting for you at the Lumber Camp by Combe.\nFilbert Burrows, determined to remain where he is until the Blackwolds relent, has asked you to return to Combe to tell his nephew, Posco Burrows, that he is fine.\n* Talk to Posco Burrows",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Northern Emyn Uial",money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="The even-rills are a series of pools and waterfalls meltwater from Forochel run through before entering the lake of Evendim.",mobs={{locations={"6.00S, 71.82W"},name="Remmenylf"}},category="Evendim",id=1647,scope="n/a",name="Pouches of Poison",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=36,pois={{locations={"2.97S, 68.79W","3.16S, 68.75W","3.28S, 68.80W","3.05S, 68.71W","3.25S, 68.90W","3.13S, 68.80W","3.12S, 68.87W"},name="Gauradan Shaman Pouch"}},minlevel=31,b="Remmenylf",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGauradan pouches can be found at their camp in the Even-rills, north-east of the Eavespires.\nRemmenylf asked you to bring him several of the pouches the Gauradan have amongst their camp.\n* Obj 2:\nRemmenylf can be found at the Eavespires, south-west of the Even-rills.\nRemmenylf will want to examine the Gauradan Shaman Pouches you recovered.\n* Talk to Remmenylf\n*",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tyrn Fornech",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Rowena Parker is concerned at the increasing boldness of the tomb-robbers that creep among the hills of Tyrn Fornech.",mobs={{locations={"7.33S, 64.25W"},name="Rowena Parker"}},category="Evendim",id=1648,scope="n/a",name="Practised Villainy",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=35,c={"* Do alongside Quest:The Thief-takers"},minlevel=30,b="Rowena Parker",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nVeteran tomb-robbers and scouting tomb-robbers can be found among the hills north and west of Ost Forod, in Tyrn Fornech.\nRowena Parker has asked you to defeat the experienced tomb-robbers that prowl the hills of Tyrn Fornech.\n* Kill 8 Veteran Tomb-robber\n* Kill 8 Scouting Tomb-robber\nObj 2:\nRowena Parker is at Ost Forod, the old watch-post in Tyrn Fornech.\nYou have defeated many experienced tomb-robbers in Tyrn Fornech and should return to Rowena with the tale of your success.\n* Talk to Rowena Parker",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+700 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="Goblin-town has sent an emissary to Minas Maur to treat with Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Brúnfair"}},selectoneof={{val="Torphadanir",id="700011E0"},{val="Prakhum's Doom",id="7000D9C2"},{val="Victory at Minas Maur",id="700011E1"}},category="Angmar",id=1649,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1651},name="Prakhum, Emissary of Goblin-town",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Brúnfair",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMinas Maur is one of the large towers of Barad Gúlaran, south of Gath Forthnír.\nYou must travel to Barad Gúlaran and defeat the emissary from Goblin-town inside Minas Maur. Brúfair suggested you take allies with you.\nObj 2:\nGath Forthnir is north of Barad Gúluran.\nHaving defeated Prakhum, return to Gath Forthnír and let Brúnfair know what you have done.\n* Talk to Brúnfair"},
{area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Osbail had a dangerous escape from Wargs in Fasach-larran, and the encounter impressed upon her the threat the creatures pose to Aughaire.",mobs={{locations={"0.03S, 40.15W"},name="Osbail"}},category="Angmar",id=1650,scope="n/a",name="Predators in the Foothills",receive={{val="Necklace of Búth Sánkhas",id="7000EAE2"}},level=43,c={"* Scara Hunters, Scara Corpse-ravagers, and Scara Skulkers are in Fasach-larran"},minlevel=38,b="Osbail",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWargs can be found in Fasach-larran, the foothills north of Aughaire. They can also be found in the fortress of Tór Gailvin, north-east of Aughaire.\nOsbail has asked you to defeat the Wargs that threaten Aughaire from the north, and in return, she will tell Crannog of your efforts.\n* Defeat Wargs in Fasach-larran (18)\nObj 2:\nOsbail is by Crannog's ruling-seat in Aughaire, west of the settlement's centre island.\nYou have defeated many of the Wargs that prowl Fasach-larran and should report of your success to Osbail.\n* Talk to Osbail",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
