{area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Ladenthir does not know how far the reach of Saruman has gone, but his touch has been felt in Eregion.",mobs={{locations={"46.94S, 12.50W"},name="Ladenthir"},{locations={"50.50S, 8.07W"},name="Palanaer"}},category="Eregion",id=1733,scope="n/a",prev={2734},name="Reach of the White Hand",arcs="The Ruins of Barad Morlas",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Ladenthir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nPalanaer is at Echad Dúnann, south-east of Echad Eregion.\nLadenthir has asked you to bear news of Saruman's encroachment upon Eregion to Palanaer, another of the scouts of Rivendell.\n* Talk to Palanaer at Echad Dúnann",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1828},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The Water-works is a site of importance to the dwarves who wish to remain in Moria. Once such dwarf, Foreman Indrith, has made it a mission to repair the channel there.",mobs={{locations={"17.65S, 116.88W"},name="Kaldi"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1734,scope="n/a",prev={1561},name="Readings from the Basin",arcs="Entering the Vile Maw",level=56,c={"* You can collect a water sample at [17.1S, 116.3]"},minlevel=51,b="Kaldi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWater samples can be drawn from the water's edge north-east or north-west from the entrance to the Vile Maw.\nKaldi said that since he heard the noises near the Vile Maw, he has not been down to the water. He asked you to make your way there to take a sample for him and provided you with an empty phial.\n* Use Empty Phial\n* Find a likely place from which to draw water\nObj 2:\nKaldi is at his little camp outside the Vile Maw.\nYou should bring the water sample you collected to Kaldi.\n* Bring the sample to Kaldi outside the Vile Maw\n* Turn in Water-sample"},
{["next"]={1038},reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="The dwarves believe they can trick the Ghâsh-hai into allying with the forces of Mordor by convincing them that Sauron is aware of their betrayal.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1735,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={3267},name="Re-alignment",arcs="Rejecting Mazog",level=57,pois={{locations={"16.67S, 107.15W","16.22S, 107.32W","16.41S, 107.25W","17.01S, 107.24W"},name="Ghâsh-hai Altar"}},minlevel=52,b="Gúthi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Ghâsh-hai altars can be found within Durin's Court to the south of Anazârmekhem.\nGúthi believes the Ghâsh-hai can be convinced to join the forces of Mordor. He wants you to place several stones marked with the Great Eye on the altars in Durin's Court.\n* Use Ghâsh-hai Altar\n* Turn in Mark of the Great Eye\nObj 2:\nGúthi is in Anazârmekhem to the north of Durin's Court.\nGúthi will be pleased to hear all the stones were placed upon the altars.\n* Talk to Gúthi in Anazârmekhem"},
{area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="You have recovered both strongboxes for Larus Sharpshard. Now but one task remains.",mobs={{locations={"24.85S, 4.03W"},name="Larus Sharpshard"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=1736,scope="n/a",prev={2451},name="Real Treasure",arcs="Every Last Ingot",receive={{val="Gaelellon",id=70003842}},level=45,minlevel=40,b="Larus Sharpshard",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHeikki Goldwatcher is inside Thorin's Hall, located within the Blue Mountains.\nLarus Sharpshard has sent you to deliver the two strongboxes you helped reclaim to Heikki Goldwatcher.\n* Talk to Heikki Goldwatcher\n* Turn in Ancient Dwarf-chest\n* Turn in Damaged Dwarf-chest"},
{area="Isendeep",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Ettenmoors is home to many terrifying beasts, but the most frightening are the trolls. It is from here that the trolls pushed to infest the Trollshaws, and still many stalk through the wilds of the Ettenmoors.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1737,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Reaping the Snow and Cold",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Osur",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSnowreap-trolls are likely to be found in the northern stretches of Arador's End, near the Isendeep Mine. You may also find Coldeve stone-trolls, but they have been known to wander the entirety of the Ettenmoors.\nAfter speaking to Lieutenant Osur, you were enlisted to assist in destroying the Snowreap and Coldeve-trolls.\n* Defeat Snowreap-trolls (12)\n* Defeat Coldeve-trolls (12)\nObj 2:\nLieutenant Osur awaits news of your success at the Isendeep Mine.\nYou found and slaughtered the Coldeve and Snowreap-trolls as directed to by Lieutenant Osur. Now you should return to him with the news.\n* Return to Lieutenant Osur at the Isendeep Mine",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="43s 68c"}},d="You have retrieved all the pieces of the statue which the goblins had stolen and scattered.",selectoneof={{val="Shield of the Statue",id="7001608B"},{val="Uxi's Armour",id="7001606A"},{val="Warg-rider's Bane",id="7001610A"},{val="Armour of the Statue",id=70016075}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1738,scope="n/a",prev={2723,932,249,594,1311},name="Reassembling the Statue",receive={{val="Uxi's Bracelet",id=70016391}},level=57,pois={{locations={"5.66S, 111.97W"},name="Statue"}},minlevel=52,b="Uxi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe shattered statue is in the centre of the court, within view of Uxi.\nUxi instructed you to take the mortar to the shattered statue and put it back together with the pieces you recovered from all over Moria.\n* Use Statue\nObj 2:\nUxi is in the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nYou should return to Uxi to celebrate the statue's reassembly.\n* Talk to Uxi at the Chamber of the Crossroads"},
{area="Mekhem-bizru",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The legacy of Durin's Stone is now threatened by one final force: Istash, a powerful Orc from the depths of Moria.",selectoneof={{val="Legacy's Reminder",id=70016394},{val="Istash's Folly",id="700163F0"}},category="Moria",id=1739,scope="n/a",prev={206},name="Reclaiming a Legacy",arcs="Durin's Stone",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Haflith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIstash is at Uruk-gashan, south of Mekhem-bizru.\nHaflith believes Durin's Stone will never be safe until Istash, an Orc-leader, is defeated.\n* Defeat Istash\nObj 2:\nHaflith is at Mekhem-bizru, north of Uruk-gashan.\nHaflith will be pleased to hear Istash has been defeated, and Durin's Stone remains safe.\n* Talk to Haflith at Mekhem-bizru"},
{area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+500 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="38s 64c"}},d="The Gauredain repeatedly raid Lossoth hunting outposts, both to antagonize the Lossoth and to take their provisions.",mobs={{locations={"12.91N, 66.19W"},name="Oiva"}},category="Forochel",id=1740,scope="n/a",name="Reclaiming From the Raiders",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Oiva",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSearch south of Karhu-leiri for the scattered provisions of the Lossoth.\n* Bring the provisions to Oiva\n* Turn in Stolen Provisions",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={767},area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="Ida told you that a nearby homestead is being terrorized by Fëoc, a Gauradan.",mobs={{locations={"10.02N, 69.62W"},name="Ida"},{locations={"11.29N, 69.48W"},name="Lauri"}},selectoneof={{val="Ida's Spear",id="7000E5DE"},{val="Ida's Sword",id="7000E5D9"},{val="Ida's Axe",id="7000E5E5"}},category="Forochel",id=1741,scope="n/a",prev={2013},name="Reclaiming the Homestead",arcs="Threatened Camps",level=46,c={"* Fëoc can be found at Voi-teltta at [10.2N, 71.8W]"},minlevel=41,b="Ida",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFëoc is at Voi-teltta, west of Ida's camp along the road.\nIda has charged you with defeating the Gauradan Fëoc, who has claimed Voi-teltta for himself and driven out the Lossoth scouts.\nObj 2:\nIda is at her encampment, east of Voi-teltta near the entrance to the ice canyons that lead south.\nYou have reclaimed Voi-teltta for the Lossoth. You should return to Ida and tell her of your success.\n* Talk to Ida\nObj 3:\nLauri is at Pynti-peldot, atop a hill north and west along the road from Ida's camp.\nIda has asked that you inform Lauri of your reclamation of the Voi-teltta homestead.\n* Talk to Scout-master Lauri"},
{area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="Radagast instructed you to pour the pure water into the sanctum of the Red-maid's fortress, Garth Agarwen.",mobs={{locations={"29.67S, 27.39W"},name="Dannasen"}},selectoneof={{val="Dannasen's Shirt",id="7000062E"},{val="Dannasen's Breastplate",id="7000062C"},{val="Dannasen's Jacket",id="7000062D"},{val="Dannasen's Oath",id=70000630},{val="Dannasen's Duty",id="7000062F"}},category="Garth Agarwen",id=1742,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={915},name="Reclaim the Lost Maiden",arcs="History of the Red-maid",receive={{val="Strange Rock",id="7000062B"}},level=35,minlevel=30,b="Dannasen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Red-maid is in her sanctum within her fortress of Garth Agarwen.\nDannasen instructed you to obey Radagast and take the pure water to the Red-maid's sanctum. Once there, he told you that you would have to defeat the Red-maid, and when the waters of her pool go still, to pour the water in.\n* Use Pure Water\n* Enter the Red-maid's sanctum when the water is calm\nObj 2:\nDannasen is at the Eglan-camp in Agamaur.\nYou should return to Dannasen and tell him that you poured the pure water into the Red-maid's Sanctum.\n* Talk to Dannasen\n* Turn in Pure Water"},
{["next"]={494},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"},{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="42s 70c"},{val="18s 20c"}},d="Orchalwë has returned to Tinnudir and wishes to speak with you.",mobs={{locations={"9.78S, 42.20W"},name="Elúr"}},selectoneof={{val="Arnorian Cloak Chain",id="70025DEA"},{val="Necklace of the Lost Codex",id="700261EE"},{val="Silver Archer's Chain",id="700261C7"},{val="Strong Beaded Necklace",id="7002652A"},{val="Chain of Arnor Rekindled",id="7002619A"},{val="Silver Elendilmir Pendant",id="7002607C"},{val="Angmarrim Iron Chain",id="700260EA"},{val="Necklace of the Sunken City",id="700264AD"},{val="Shining Necklace of the Tale Teller",id=70026280}},category="North Downs",id=1743,scope="n/a",prev={1602,833},name="Reclamation",arcs="Stemming the Tide",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="TBD Follow",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrchalwë is in Tinnudir, north of Annuminas.\n* Talk to Orchalwë\n//Elúr Location: 9.78S, 42.20W\nThe North Downs >> Esteldín';markerList['1879063187_0x041828F000000008_120.7244.2910401144'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879063187_0x041828F000000008_120.7244.2910401144', new GLatLng(10.741508789063, 3.873515625), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879063187_0x041828F000000008_120.7244.2910401144'; markers['1879063187_0x041828F000000008_120.7244.2910401144'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Elúr Location: 9.78S, 42.20W\nThe North Downs >> Esteldín';markerList['1879063187_0x041828F000000008_120.7244.2910401144'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker); GME_DEFAULT_ICON = G_DEFAULT_ICON;      } else {        document.getElementById(\"map1561719738\").innerHTML = \"In order to see the map that would go in this space, you will need to use a compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap1561719738);\n//]]>\nQuest: Reclamation\nCategory: North Downs\nScope: n/a\nArc(s): Stemming the Tide\nMin Level: 26\nPrerequisite Quests:Fall of the Earth-kin\nNext Quests:Caught in the Wake\nRewards\nMoney:\n18 20Reputation:\n+700 with Rangers of Esteldín\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nEsteldín relied on the Earth-kin to aid in safeguarding the pass to Angmar in the north. Their recent corruption has forced the Rangers' hand and they must now strike down their former allies to ensure that the few remaining Earth-kin allies are safeguarded.\nBestower\nElúr (NPC)\n'I know that you have assisted Daervunn already, and I assume that you are here to learn if you might assist me. My task is not an easy one, and with all the preparations for the coming war, I find myself stretched too far across my duties.\n'The Earth-kin, with whom we have long shared a distant friendship, have lost much with their brethren's betrayal. They may become more open and amenable allies should we recover some of those things which were taken from them.\n'The Earth-kin of the Rauta-lehmä faction in eastern Nan Amlug use weapons taken from the fallen in their insurrection. Go there and steal these weapons back. Be careful not to destroy the weapons in your battle.'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nThe stolen weapons may be found in the camp of the Rauta-lehmä in Nan Amlug, east of Esteldín.\nElúr of Esteldín told you that the Earth-kin betrayers, the Rauta-lehmä, stole weapons from their kindred to use in their insurrection. He has asked you to go to their camp and recover the stolen weapons.\n* Return the Earth-kin Weapons to Elúr\n* Turn in Earth-kin Weapon"},
{area="Combe",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Maida Woodwright had an argument with her son Covell, and she has not seen him since. The Blackwold activity in the area has made her nervous, and she is seeking news of him.",mobs={{locations={"29.13S, 48.30W"},name="Constable Wren"},{locations={"28.57S, 49.43W"},name="Maida Woodwright"}},selectoneof={{q="(x5)",val="Lesser Athelas Essence",id="70000D5D"},{q="(x5)",val="Lesser Celebrant Salve",id="700005B4"}},category="Bree-land",id=1744,scope="n/a",name="Reconnecting Ties",level=9,c={"* Covell Woodwright is at [27.2S, 44.5W]"},minlevel=5,b="Maida Woodwright",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nConstable Wren is at the guard-house, east of Combe.\nMaida Woodwright has asked that you speak with Constable Wren regarding the whereabouts of her son, Covell.\n* Talk to Constable Wren\nObj 2:\nCovell may be found at one of the Blackwold camps north and east of the Combe lumber camp.\nMaida Woodwright sent you to speak with Constable Wren, who suggested that Covell joined the Blackwolds and would likely be found near one of their camps in the Chetwood.\n* Talk to Covell Woodwright\nObj 3:\nConstable Wren patrols near the guard-house on the hill south of the lumber camp and east of Combe.\nYou discovered Covell Woodwright on the path leading through the Chetwood, and he attacked you. Though you defeated him, he escaped deeper into the woods. Constable Wren will want to hear of your encounter with the brigand.\n* Talk to Constable Wren\nObj 4:\nMaida Woodwright is back in Combe.\nMaida Woodwright must be told that her son Covell has joined the Blackwold brigands.\n* Talk to Maida Woodwright",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1352},area="The Twenty-first Hall",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="Moria still holds the secrets of the past, including tales of the dwarves' great defeats by the Orcs of Azog.",mobs={{locations={"5.89S, 105.11W"},name="Bói"}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1745,scope="n/a",prev={2588},name="Records of the Dark Times",arcs="Lest We Forget",level=54,c={"* Bói is the Bard of the Twenty-first Hall, and can be found in The Twenty-first Hall at [5.9S, 105.1W]"},pois={{locations={"4.24S, 108.19W","3.02S, 107.45W","3.79S, 107.29W","3.29S, 107.77W"},name="Ancient Records"}},minlevel=49,b="Borgar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBói is in the Twenty-first Hall, south from Jazârgund.\nBorgar is interested in tales of the battles that the dwarves lost to the Orcs. He believes Moria still holds these secrets and that Bói may know where to find them.\n* Talk to Bói in the Twenty-first Hall\nObj 2:\nThe pages are located in the chambers to the north and south of Salab Nurjundul, west of Jazârgund.\nBói told you the old tales were still in Moria.\n* Use Ancient Records\nObj 3:\nBorgar is at Jazârgund, east of Salab Nurjundul.\nBorgar will want to take the opportunity to read the tales you found.\n* Talk to Borgar at Jazârgund\n* Turn in Old Records"},
{["next"]={1482},area="Bullroarer's Sward",zone="Evendim",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Ronald Dwale has misplaced an important leaf of paper.",category="Evendim",id=1746,scope="n/a",prev={1391},name="Recovering the Lost Leaf",arcs="Missing the Meeting",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="Ronald Dwale",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRonald Dwale remembers dropping his paper somewhere in Dwaling, north of the Bullroarer's Sward.\nRonald Dwale has asked you to find his lost leaf of paper.\n* Turn in Lost Leaf of Paper\nObj 2:\nRonald Dwale is at Hob Hillbrow's home at the Bullroarer's Sward in Dwaling.\nYou should return the leaf of paper to Ronald Dwale.\n* Talk to Ronald Dwale\n* Turn in Lost Leaf of Paper"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Annúminas",money={{val="42s"}},d="The corpses of the Rangers here tried to bargain and make deals with Angmar.",category="Evendim",id=1747,scope="n/a",name="Redeeming the Defiled",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,pois={{locations={"19.58S, 69.90W","19.58S, 70.13W","19.81S, 70.19W","19.78S, 70.11W","19.58S, 70.00W","19.78S, 70.03W","19.45S, 69.86W"},name="Cage"}},minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe corpses should be removed from the crows cages to allow the fallen to rest peacefully.\n* Use Cage\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will be pleased to see his dishonored brethren will now rest peacefully.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Enedwaith",area="Gloomglens",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="After learning that the 'hobbits' of the neighbouring village were actually a breed of wild goblin called the bugan, Mayor Brochtû declared a blood feud against them.",mobs={{locations={"61.96S, 22.94W"},name="Iolo Brochtû"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1748,scope="n/a",prev={83},name="Reducing the Threat -- Repeatable",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Iolo Brochtû",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nKhoblún Utot lies to the south of Maur Tulhau.\nIolo Brochtû has asked you to return to Khoblún Utot and drive out the bugan.\n* Defeat bugan (12)\nObj 2:\nIolo Brochtû is at Maur Tulhau, north of Khoblún Utot.\nYou should return to Iolo Brochtû with news of your success.\n* Talk to Iolo Brochtû at Maur Tulhau",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="43s 68c"}},d="You are, by now, familiar with the Moria-mirrors. Most get knocked out of place by the denizens of the dark on a regular basis; it is up to you to make them right.",selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Brewed Healing Draught",id="7000EFC6"},{q="(x3)",val="Brewed Milkthistle Draught",id="7000EFC5"},{q="(x3)",val="Pure Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA85"},{q="(x3)",val="Brewed Flask of Conhuith",id="7000EFC4"},{q="(x3)",val="Brewed Flask of Lhinestad",id="7000EFC3"},{q="(x3)",val="Pure Athelas Essence",id="7000EA84"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1749,scope="n/a",prev={1478},name="Reflecting on the Greatness That Was Khazad-dûm",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Moria-mirror",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTell Simbi of your continuing efforts towards making Khazad-dûm safe once more.\n* Speak to Simbi",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Flaming Deeps",zone="Moria",money={{val="44s 24c"}},d="The mirror in the Flaming Deeps is constantly being disturbed by Deep-worms, fiery dragonets, and the Ghâsh-hai. Keeping it correctly aligned is a nigh-impossible task.",selectoneof={{q="(x4)",val="Infused Healing Draught",id="7000EFCA"},{q="(x4)",val="Infused Milkthistle Draught",id="7000EFC9"},{q="(x4)",val="Infused Lhinestad Draught",id="7000EFC7"},{q="(x4)",val="Pure Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA85"},{q="(x4)",val="Infused Conhuith Draught",id="7000EFC8"},{q="(x4)",val="Pure Athelas Essence",id="7000EA84"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1750,scope="n/a",prev={1478},name="Reflection of Flame",level=58,pois={{locations={"16.63S, 108.88W"},name="Mirror (Level 1)"}},minlevel=53,b="Thórgnyr",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe mirror lies to the south-east of The Crossroads of Ash, which can be found south-west of Anazârmekhem.\nThe creatures of the Flaming Deeps have tampered with the dwarf-mirror. It needs to be re-aligned in order to be useful to the dwarves.\n* Use Mirror (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nThórgnyr is in Anazârmekhem, north-east of The Crossroads of Ash.\nThórgnyr will want to know you re-aligned the mirror.\n* Talk to Thórgnyr in Anazârmekhem"},
{area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",money={{val="41s 44c"}},d="The dwarf-mirrors of Khazad-dûm once illuminated the underground halls, but many of them have since fallen into disrepair or have been knocked out of alignment.",selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Infused Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA8E"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Milkthistle Draught",id="7000EFC1"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Conhuith Draught",id="7000EFC0"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Lhinestad Draught",id="7000EFBF"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Healing Draught",id="7000EFC2"},{q="(x3)",val="Infused Athelas Essence",id="7000EA7F"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1751,scope="n/a",prev={1478},name="Reflections of Rails",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Moria-mirror",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThettmárr is in the Deep Descent.\nYou should tell Thettmárr of your continuing efforts towards making Khazad-dûm safe once more.\n* Talk to Thettmárr at the Deep Descent"},
{area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="42s"}},d="The dwarf-mirrors of Khazad-dûm once illuminated the underground halls, but many of them have since fallen into disrepair or have been knocked out of alignment.",selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Infused Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA8E"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Milkthistle Draught",id="7000EFC1"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Conhuith Draught",id="7000EFC0"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Lhinestad Draught",id="7000EFBF"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Healing Draught",id="7000EFC2"},{q="(x3)",val="Infused Athelas Essence",id="7000EA7F"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1752,scope="n/a",prev={1478},name="Reflections of Riders",level=54,minlevel=49,b="Moria-mirror",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRambi is at the Chamber of the Crossroads in the south-west corner of Durin's Way, north of the Great Delving.\nYou should tell Rambi of your continuing efforts towards lighting Khazad-dûm once more.\n* Speak to Rambi"},
{area="Redhorn Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="43s 68c"}},d="The mirror in the Redhorn Lodes is constantly being knocked out of alignment by the White Hand Orcs dominating the mine.",selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Infused Healing Draught",id="7000EFCA"},{q="(x3)",val="Infused Milkthistle Draught",id="7000EFC9"},{q="(x3)",val="Infused Lhinestad Draught",id="7000EFC7"},{q="(x3)",val="Pure Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA85"},{q="(x3)",val="Infused Conhuith Draught",id="7000EFC8"},{q="(x3)",val="Pure Athelas Essence",id="7000EA84"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1753,scope="n/a",prev={1478},name="Reflector of the Redhorn",level=57,pois={{locations={"12.54S, 103.10W"},name="Mirror (Level 1)"}},minlevel=52,b="Auti",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe mirror is in Claw Hollow, south-east of the Orc-watch.\nAuti has asked you to re-align the mirror of the Redhorn Lodes.\n* Use Mirror (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nAuti is at the Orc-watch, north-west of the Claw Hollow.\nAuti will be pleased to hear that the mirror in the Redhorn Lodes has been re-aligned.\n* Talk to Auti at the Orc-watch"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Money that had been set aside to refurbish Town Hole in Michel Delving has gone missing, presumably stolen.",mobs={{locations={"28.05S, 76.03W"},name="Griffo Boffin"},{locations={"33.38S, 74.98W"},name="Assistant Fallohide"}},selectoneof={{val="Fallohide's Cape",id="700033B5"},{val="Fallohide's Greatclub",id="700033B4"},{val="Fallohide's Shield",id="7001619D"}},category="Shire",id=1754,scope="n/a",name="Refurbishing the Town Hole",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=8,pois={{locations={"27.77S, 73.78W"},name="Money-bag"}},minlevel=4,b="Assistant Fallohide",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGriffo Boffin may be found at his home near the centre of Needlehole, to the north of Michel Delving. The easiest road to Needlehole runs north from Waymeet, the crossroads east of Michel Delving.\nMayor Whitfoot's assistant has asked you to investigate the disappearance of the money that was set aside for refurbishing Town Hole in Michel Delving.\n* Talk to Griffo Boffin\nObj 2:\nThe dwarves came out of the Rushock Bog to the east, between Needlehole and Overhill. Their camp is somewhere nearby, behind tall wooden bulwarks.\nYou spoke with Griffo Boffin about the missing money, as Assistant Fallohide requested, and discovered that ruffian dwarves may have stolen it. Griffo asked that you seek out the dwarves' camp, retrieve the money bag, and bring it to Assistant Fallohide in Michel Delving.\n* Collect the money bag\nObj 3:\nYou found the missing money, so now it should be delivered to Assistant Fallohide in Michel Delving.\n* Talk to Assistant Fallohide\n* Turn in Money-bag"},
{area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="43s 12c"}},d="The Forgotten Treasury houses a good deal of wealth discovered or mined in Moria in the elder days. Seeing that these remnants of the past are maintained for the dwarves is a duty worth undertaking.",mobs={{locations={"9.85S, 112.76W"},name="Hafberg"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1755,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1332},name="Relics and Coins",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Hafberg",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Forgotten Treasury is in Menem-berej, directly south of the Deep Descent.\nYou should search the Orcs and any spoiled ruins for relics or coins of the Forgotten Treasury. Hafberg would prefer that you not unearth any that may still be lying about untouched.\n* Deliver the coins and relics to Hafberg at the Deep Descent\n* Turn in Relic of the Treasury\n* Turn in Dwarf-coin"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Harmony Grayson has volunteered to help the Rangers collect relics from the ruins of Barad Tharsír.",mobs={{locations={"12.58S, 67.22W"},name="Astiul"},{locations={"12.64S, 67.16W"},name="Harmony Grayson"}},category="Evendim",id=1756,scope="n/a",name="Relics in Barad Tharsír",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=32,c={"* The Broken Sword is at [15.8S, 60.4W]\n* The Broken Shield is at [15.2S, 60.6W]\n* The Time-worn Bottle is at [15.4S, 60.5W], out on the roof of the ruins."},minlevel=27,b="Harmony Grayson",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarad Tharsír is south-east of Tinnudir, in the Barandalf, on the far side of the Brandywine.\nHarmony Grayson wants you to bring her any relics that you can find from Barad Tharsír.\n* Turn in Broken Shield (Level 1)\n* Turn in Broken Sword (Level 1)\n* Turn in Time-worn Bottle\nObj 2:\nHarmony Grayson is at the Ranger camp on the island of Tinnudir, north-west of the Barandalf and west of Parth Aduial.\nYou have gathered several relics from the ruins of Barad Tharsír and should return to Harmony Grayson.\n* Talk to Harmony Grayson\n* Turn in Broken Shield (Level 1)\n* Turn in Broken Sword (Level 1)\n* Turn in Time-worn Bottle\nObj 3:\nRanger Astiul is at the Ranger-camp on the island of Tinnudir, north-west of the Barandalf and west of Parth Aduial.\nHarmony Grayson has asked you to bring the relics you collected to Astiul, as he will appreciate their significance.\n* Talk to Astiul\n* Turn in Broken Shield (Level 1)\n* Turn in Broken Sword (Level 1)\n* Turn in Time-worn Bottle\nObj 4:\nHarmony Grayson is in the Ranger-camp on the island of Tinnudir, north-west of Barandalf and west of Parth Aduial.\nAstiul has expressed his gratitude for your efforts and wants you to thank Harmony for him.\n* Talk to Harmony Grayson",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={590,2067},area="Emyn Lûm",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Agorin believes that relics of the Silvan Elves might remain within Minas Gîl, from the time when it served as an observatory studying the heavens above Ost Galadh.",category="Mirkwood",id=1757,scope="n/a",prev={3193},name="Relics of Old",arcs="The Grim Tower",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,minlevel=58,b="Agorin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRelics might be found within Minas Gîl, east of Ost Galadh.\nAgorin has asked you to recapture Silvan relics from the sorcerers in Minas Gîl.\n* Turn in Silvan Relic\nObj 2:\nAgorin is at Ost Galadh, west of Minas Gîl.\nYou should bring the relics you found to Agorin.\n* Talk to Agorin at Ost Galadh"},
{area="Garth Agarwen",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+900 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="29s 68c"}},d="The Eglain depend upon the trade of ancient relics for food and other necessities of life. Arienh believes that Garth Agarwen holds such a wealth of relics that her people will be sustained for many years.",selectoneof={{val="Necklace of Rhudaur",id="70000CAC"},{val="Guard of the Eglain",id="70000CAD"}},category="Garth Agarwen",id=1758,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1842},name="Relics of Rhudaur",level=32,pois={{locations={"28.02S, 24.54W","27.73S, 24.94W","28.24S, 24.98W","27.71S, 24.48W","28.09S, 24.48W","28.13S, 24.41W","28.17S, 24.83W","27.91S, 24.90W","28.11S, 24.96W","29.00S, 24.43W","28.86S, 24.67W","27.68S, 24.71W","28.26S, 24.52W","28.73S, 24.43W","27.88S, 24.76W","28.72S, 24.62W","28.57S, 24.43W","28.67S, 24.82W","28.13S, 24.77W","28.92S, 24.68W","28.51S, 24.88W","29.10S, 24.61W","28.48S, 24.54W","28.32S, 24.89W","28.10S, 24.53W","28.25S, 24.60W","27.99S, 24.71W","28.20S, 24.80W","28.03S, 24.41W","28.84S, 24.56W","27.92S, 24.80W","27.98S, 25.20W"},name="Artifact"}},minlevel=27,b="Arienh",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nArienh is encamped at the entrance to the area called Garth Agarwen. She asked that you search the areas outside of the barrows, arboretum, and fortress of Garth Agarwen for trinkets that will help provide for the Eglain.\nArienh asked that you watch for relics of the ancient days as you venture within Garth Agarwen.\n* Return the relics to Arienh\n* Collect relics from Agamaur (15 Artifact )"},
{["next"]={2318,637},area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The ruins among which the giants have made their encampments also house lost relics of the exiles from Erebor, who dwelt here once long ago.",mobs={{locations={"65.57S, 8.48W"},name="Frithgeir"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1759,scope="n/a",prev={2356},name="Relics of the Fallen",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Frithgeir",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe giant encampments may be found far to the south of Zudrugund.\nFrithgeir has asked you to recover a relic from the giants in Thrór's Coomb.\n* Defeat giants to recover a relic\nObj 2:\nThe giant encampments may be found far to the south of Zudrugund.\nFrithgeir has asked you to recover a relic from the giants in Thrór's Coomb.\n* Turn in Dwarf-relic\nObj 3:\nFrithgeir is at Zudrugund, north of the giant encampments.\nYou should bring the relic that you recovered to Frithgeir.\n* Talk to Frithgeir\n* Turn in Dwarf-relic"},
{area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The bundle of supplies you brought to Gwingris has concerned Daegennan greatly.",mobs={{locations={"39.99S, 16.26W"},name="Daegennan"}},selectoneof={{val="Daegennan's Gift",id=70016110},{val="Defender of Gwingris",id=70016100}},category="Eregion",id=1760,scope="n/a",prev={1393},name="Remaining Goods",arcs="Shipment from Rivendell",level=49,c={"* Satchels can be found at:\n[40.6S, 10.3W]\n* [40.7S, 10.4W]\n* [40.8S, 10.3W]\n* [40.8S, 10.5W]\n* [40.7S, 10.6W]\n* [40.6S, 10.7W]\n* Crates can be found at:\n[40.6S, 10.2W]\n* [40.5S, 10.1W]\n* [40.6S, 10.3W]\n* [40.8S, 10.4W]\n* [40.8S, 10.4W]"},pois={{locations={"40.56S, 10.36W","40.69S, 10.57W","40.84S, 10.44W","40.59S, 10.65W","40.59S, 10.17W","40.84S, 10.35W","40.48S, 10.13W","40.48S, 10.54W","40.58S, 10.25W","40.64S, 10.33W"},name="Battered Crate"},{locations={"40.80S, 10.66W","40.63S, 10.72W","40.79S, 10.55W","40.69S, 10.40W","40.45S, 10.28W","40.65S, 10.56W","40.58S, 10.28W","40.77S, 10.25W","40.48S, 10.76W","40.47S, 10.41W"},name="Battered Satchel"}},minlevel=44,b="Daegennan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDaegennan believes that the more of the lost supplies may be found along the path from Rivendell, well to the east of Gwingris.\nDaegennan has asked you to recover more of the missing supplies.\n* Bring the recovered supplies to Daegennan\n* Collect satchels (6 Battered Satchel )\n* Collect crates (6 Battered Crate )"},
{area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="With the failure of Hamall's plan, the spirits of the dwarves at Jazârgund have fallen very low.",selectoneof={{val="Lost Minstrel's Sword",id="7001ABF2"},{val="Hamall's Walking Stick",id=70016117}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1761,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={626},name="Remembering the Old Songs",arcs="Joy in the Time of Sorrow",level=55,pois={{locations={"2.95S, 104.19W","4.28S, 104.63W","2.90S, 104.45W","3.00S, 104.73W","4.17S, 104.43W","4.23S, 105.04W"},name="Sheet-music"}},minlevel=50,b="Hamall",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe dwarf-minstrel's sheet music has been spread throughout the Orc-camps in Fehem-dûm and Hadâd-dûm.\nWith the failure of his plan, Hamall wishes to raise the spirits of his fellow dwarves in Jazârgund. He believes collecting the songs of old lost by the maddened minstrel will help achieve this goal.\n* Collect dwarf sheet-music (6 Sheet-music )\nObj 2:\nHamall is at Jazârgund, west of Fehem-dûm and Hadâd-dûm.\nHamall's spirits will be greatly raised by the ancient dwarf-songs you recovered.\n* Bring the sheet-music to Hamall\n* Turn in Sheet-music"},
{["next"]={592,2027,952,641},area="Lich Bluffs",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="The Lich Bluffs are the final resting place of many of the fallen from the Algraig clans. However, a dark force has emerged from the shadows, bringing forth wights to attack the living.",mobs={{locations={"70.57S, 15.46W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1762,scope="n/a",name="Remnants of the Past",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThese creatures move among many of the barrows in the southern reaches of the Lich Bluffs.\nMincham has asked you to seek out and defeat any wights that you might encounter.\n* Defeat wights (10)\nObj 2:\nMincham is located south and slightly east of the large Gondorian ruins in the Lich Bluffs.\nYou should return to Mincham and let him know that you have defeated many wights.\n* Talk to Mincham in the Lich Bluffs"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="44s 80c"}},d="The Forges of Khazad-dûm were once the heart of smithing within Moria. Here, the mighty dwarf-smiths would work the mithril and forge their greastest wonders. In the time since its fall, the Forges of Khazad-dûm have been flooded with massive lava-floes and populated by the Orcs of Moria and their troll and goblin-labourers. Here the Orc war-host hammers away incessantly, as they built their weapons and siege-engines in preparation for their war against Lothlórien.",mobs={{locations={"13.42S, 108.08W"},name="Sigir"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1763,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Remnants of the Ruins",arcs="Forges of Khazad-dûm",level=59,minlevel=57,b="Sigir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Forges of Khazad-dûm lie to the south-west of Anazârmekhem.\nSigir asked you to collect bits of mithril from the forces of the Enemy now inhabiting the Forges of Khazad-dûm.\n* Bring the Mithril Bits to Sigir at Anazârmekhem\n* Turn in Mithril-bit",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={714},area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orcs of Ashúrz Maufulug have placed many traps around their encampment, but those were only one of many defences.",mobs={{locations={"16.50S, 60.30W"},name="Glamodúd"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1764,scope="n/a",prev={2059},name="Removing the Stinger",destinypoints={{val=250}},arcs="Breaking the Pincer",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Glamodúd",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrc-archers can be found patrolling the outskirts of Ashúrz Maufulug, south and a little west from Echad Glamodúd.\nGlamodúd has asked you to defeat the Orc-archers who defend Ashúrz Maufulug.\n* Defeat Taughâsh archers at Ashúrz Maufulug\nObj 2:\nGlamodúd is at Echad Glamodúd, north and a little east from Ashúrz Maufulug.\nYou should return to Glamodúd with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Glamodúd at Echad Glamodúd"},
{reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="The Drownholt",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You now carry a gift of light and hope for the corrupted Mirk-huorns of Sâd Meryrn. However evil they now seem, these old creatures of Mirkwood stir pity, for their long memory has not let them forget the taste of clean air and sunlight, when life was greener.",mobs={{locations={"18.31S, 57.36W"},name="Nífdir"},{locations={"16.93S, 54.69W"},name="Nenedhel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1765,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={76},name="Rending the Shadows of Sâd Meryrn",arcs="The Wroth Glade",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,c={"* There is a Promising Bit of Earth in Sâd Meryrn at [19.0S, 57.4W]"},pois={{locations={"18.96S, 57.42W"},name="Promising Bit of Earth"}},minlevel=58,b="Nífdir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSâd Meryrn can be found due south of Nífdir's camp, but you should strike north and west to reach the glade.\nNífdir has asked you to plant the mallorn seedling in Sâd Meryrn.\n* Use Promising Bit of Earth\n* Turn in Mallorn Sapling\nObj 2:\nNenedhel awaits news of Nífdir's endeavour at Estolad Mernael, east of Nífdir's encampment.\nYou should speak with Nenedhel and inform him that Nífdir's task is complete.\n* Talk to Nenedhel at Estolad Mernael"},
{["next"]={697},reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="The forces of Angmar left behind a ballista on the bluff overlooking the colossus bridge. The Rangers intend to use it.",category="Evendim",id=1766,scope="n/a",name="Repairing the Ballista",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=32,pois={{locations={"14.26S, 61.83W","15.75S, 61.47W","13.57S, 62.27W","15.06S, 61.57W","14.93S, 61.03W","13.61S, 61.84W","16.48S, 61.06W","15.81S, 61.01W"},name="Piece of Driftwood"},{locations={"16.69S, 61.07W","14.44S, 61.76W","16.09S, 61.41W","13.54S, 62.47W","13.77S, 61.61W","15.40S, 61.57W","15.25S, 61.13W"},name="Bundle of Rope"},{locations={"15.11S, 61.10W","14.84S, 61.57W","15.92S, 60.86W","14.24S, 61.97W","15.80S, 61.83W"},name="Pouch of Oil"},{locations={"15.23S, 61.59W","15.95S, 61.62W","16.12S, 60.73W","13.70S, 61.73W"},name="Small Flywheel"}},minlevel=27,b="Sardan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBundles of rope, pieces of driftwood, small flywheels, and oil pouches can be found along the banks of the Baranduin.\nSardan asked you to gather some supplies to help fix a ballista.\n* Collect bundles of rope (6 Bundle of Rope )\n* Collect pieces of driftwood (4 Piece of Driftwood )\n* Collect small flywheels (2 Small Flywheel )\n* Collect oil-pouches (3 Pouch of Oil )\nObj 2:\nCudhaer is on a bluff overlooking the colossus from the south.\nCudhaer will be eager to use these supplies to repair the ballista.\n* Talk to Cudhaer\n* Turn in Bundle of Rope\n* Turn in Piece of Driftwood\n* Turn in Small Flywheel\n* Turn in Pouch of Oil",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="Redhorn Lodes",money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="The sluice boxes used to filter the mined ore have been damaged and broken.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1767,scope="n/a",name="Repairs to the Rails",pois={{locations={"12.31S, 104.70W","12.54S, 105.02W","12.44S, 104.47W","12.20S, 104.63W","12.53S, 104.74W","11.52S, 105.23W","11.52S, 105.37W","12.47S, 105.07W","11.40S, 105.34W","12.03S, 104.97W","11.39S, 104.56W","11.57S, 104.74W","11.58S, 104.94W","11.96S, 104.86W"},name="Sluice-box"}},level=55,minlevel=50,b="Auti",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBroken sluice-boxes can be found at the bases of the elevated tracks throughout the Redhorn Lodes, south-east of the Orc-watch.\nAuti asked you to venture into the Redhorn Lodes and repair the sluice-boxes the White Hand Orcs had broken. They do not serve an immediate value, but once the mining operations are restored, they will be used to filter the ore.\n* Use Sluice-box\n* Turn in Pry Bar\nObj 2:\nAuti is at the Orc-watch, north-west of the Redhorn Lodes.\nAuti will be pleased to hear the sluice boxes have been repaired.\n* Talk to Auti\n* Turn in Pry Bar",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="With the defeat of Darúk, the forces of\nÂnghum-maudhûl have fallen into disarray, providing the perfect opportunity for the Malledhrim to strike.",mobs={{locations={"17.67S, 48.30W"},name="Harchador"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1768,scope="n/a",prev={686,1875,321},name="Repel the Reinforcements",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Harchador",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nÂnghum-maudhûl lies to the south-east of Mithechad.\nHarchador has asked you to journey to Ânhum-maudhûl to defeat the Orcs and collect the grim tokens they bear.\n* Defeat Orcs at Ânghum-maudhûl (15)\n* Turn in Grim Token\nObj 2:\nHarchador is at Mithechad, north-west of Ânghum-maudhûl.\nYou should return to Harchador with news of your success.\n* Talk to Harchador\n* Turn in Grim Token"},
{area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Watcher Redweed would like word of your victory against the goblins carried to Second-watcher Heathstraw of Bree.",mobs={{locations={"30.33S, 51.08W"},name="Second-watcher Heathstraw"},{locations={"31.09S, 49.40W"},name="Watcher Redweed"}},category="Bree-land",id=1769,scope="n/a",prev={2772},name="Report From Staddle",arcs="Goblins in the Marshes",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lesser Celebrant Salve",id="700005B4"}},level=14,minlevel=10,b="Watcher Redweed",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSecond-watcher Heathstraw is at the Boar Fountain in Bree, north and west of Staddle.\nWatcher Redweed has asked you to deliver his message to Second-watcher Heathstraw.\n* Talk to Second-watcher Heathstraw in Bree\n* Turn in Redweed's Report"},
{["next"]={60},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The Water-works is a site of importance to the dwarves who wish to remain in Moria. One such dwarf, Foreman Indrith, has made it a mission to repair the channel there.",mobs={{locations={"17.65S, 116.88W"},name="Kaldi"},{locations={"14.64S, 111.88W"},name="Játgir"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1770,scope="n/a",prev={1791},name="Reporting the Findings",arcs="Entering the Vile Maw",level=56,c={"* Jatgír is in The Rotting Cellar at [14.6S, 111.9W]"},minlevel=51,b="Kaldi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nJátgir is at the Rotting Cellar to the north of the Vile Maw.\nKaldi handed the sample back to you and sent you to speak with Játgir about what is wrong with the water and to find out what should be done at the Vile Maw.\n* Deliver the sample to Játgir at the Rotting Cellar\n* Turn in Water-sample\nObj 2:\nKaldi is at his camp outside the Vile Maw, south of the Rotting Cellar.\nJátgir did not like what he saw within the water and sent you back to Kaldi with a special message.\n* Talk to Kaldi at the Vile Maw"},
{d="Driven by a harsh Krahjarn Taskmaster you find yourself within the Gramsfoot stronghold in the shadow of Mount Gram on the border of the Ettenmoors. Here to support your Ongbúrz brothers under the watchful eye of the Krahjarn, you are ushered south into the Steps of Gram in search of Chieftain Durulkum.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1771,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={2766},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Report to Dâr-gazag, Maggot",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Faltúrz",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSeek out Chieftain Durulkum at Dâr-gazag, along the ridge south of Gramsfoot.\nSoldier Faltúrz ordered you to find your way to Chieftain Durulkum at Dâr-gazag.\n* Talk to Chieftain Durulkum",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Gramsfoot",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="You have been ordered to make your presence known to Soldier Gazlup at Lugazag.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1772,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={2766},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Report to Lugazag",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Nartul",repeatable="No",faction="Mon",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIf the tower has not been taken by the enemy, you should find Soldier Gazlup at Lugazag, south and east of Gramsfoot, in the greener sections of the Steps of Gram.\nSoldier Nartul directed you to speak with Soldier Gazlup at Lugazag.\n* Speak with Soldier Gazlup at Lugazag ()"},
{["next"]={3253},area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Wolves have invaded the Shire, and some of them chased Dora Brownlock from her farm and have begun to feed on her chickens.",mobs={{locations={"32.81S, 72.94W"},name="Dora Brownlock"}},category="Shire",id=1773,scope="n/a",name="Rescue Dora's Chickens",arcs="Worries from Waymeet",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Dora Brownlock",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDora's chickens are at her farm north of Waymeet, at the end of the first stone path on the right off the main road.\nYou went to Waymeet to help Dora Brownlock at the behest of Peony Grubb. Dora has in turn asked you to rescue her chickens from her farm, which has been overrun by the wolves.\n* Collect Dora's chickens (3)\nObj 2:\nDora Brownlock is at the centre of Waymeet.\nDora Brownlock will be pleased to have her chickens returned to her, safe from the threat of the wolves prowling about her farm. You should return to her at once.\n* Talk to Dora Brownlock\n* Turn in Dora's Chicken",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with The Eldgang"}},d="Golodir has ventured into the depths of the Rift, and Corunir has mounted a desperate rescue of his mentor.",category="Skirmish",id=1774,scope="n/a",name="Rescue in Nûrz Ghâshu -- Daily",level=65,minlevel=65,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nGolodir has ventured deep within the Rift.\n* Complete the Rescue in Nûrz Ghâshu Skirmish"},
{["next"]={2567},area="Meluinen",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="17s 50c"}},d="Lagorlam, a member of the company of Elves who came north with Gildor Inglorion, entered Taur Gonwaith, seeking revenge against the trolls who attacked Lin Giliath.",mobs={{locations={"13.72S, 44.55W"},name="Thaliollang"}},category="North Downs",id=1775,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Rescuing Vengeance",arcs="Avenging Lachenn",level=29,minlevel=24,b="Lagorlam",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLagorlam was injured while visiting his vengeance on the trolls. With his anger saited he has offered to leave Taur Gonwaith with you.\n* Escort Lagorlam to safety\nObj 2:\nThaliollang is at Lin Giliath, north-west of Taur Gonwaith.\nThaliollang will be pleased to hear that you rescued Lagorlam from the forest of Taur Gonwaith.\n* Talk to Thaliollang"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyl Annûn",money={{val="42s"}},d="The torches burning along the bridge are used to honor the fallen leaders of Annuminas.",category="Evendim",id=1776,scope="n/a",name="Respecting the Rulers",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,pois={{locations={"16.47S, 69.41W","16.29S, 69.33W","16.37S, 69.40W","16.47S, 69.33W","16.12S, 69.41W","16.29S, 69.41W","16.38S, 69.33W","16.12S, 69.32W"},name="Torch"}},minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBurn incense in the torches on the bridge leading to Tyl Ruinen.\n* Use Torch\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will be pleased to hear his ancient kings have been honored.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={858},area="Lich Bluffs",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The location of the final resting place of Cadelhin's father Fernvael has been lost over the years. There are a series of inscriptions which denote his tomb that, once deciphered, will reveal his location.",mobs={{locations={"72.06S, 16.12W"},name="Lhudd"},{locations={"71.75S, 15.89W"},name="Cadelhin"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1777,scope="n/a",prev={1853},name="Resting Place",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"72.99S, 16.20W","71.40S, 16.43W","72.56S, 15.78W","72.98S, 16.05W","72.67S, 16.00W","72.92S, 16.13W","72.58S, 15.91W","72.58S, 15.66W","71.47S, 16.34W","73.06S, 16.12W","71.50S, 16.42W"},name="Bedh-stones (Level 1)"}},minlevel=60,b="Lhudd",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe first cairn-marker may be found outside a barrow to the north of the Hall of Sanctuary.\nLhudd instructed you to find the cairn-markers which denote the house of Fernvael, bearing the mark of a crowned boar. This symbol may also be found among the barrows of Fernvael's followers.\n* Use Bedh-stones (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nThe first cairn-marker may be found outside a barrow to the north of the Hall of Sanctuary.\nLhudd instructed you to find the cairn-markers which denote the house of Fernvael, bearing the mark of a crowned boar. This symbol may also be found among the barrows of Fernvael's followers.\n* Turn in Transcribed Inscription\nObj 3:\nThe second cairn-marker may be found outside a barrow to the south of the Hall of Sanctuary.\nLhudd instructed you to find the cairn-markers which denote the house of Fernvael, bearing the mark of a crowned boar. This symbol may also be found among the barrows of Fernvael's followers.\n* Use Bedh-stones (Level 1)\nObj 4:\nThe second cairn-marker may be found outside a barrow to the south of the Hall of Sanctuary.\nLhudd instructed you to find the cairn-markers which denote the house of Fernvael, bearing the mark of a crowned boar. This symbol may also be found among the barrows of Fernvael's followers.\n* Turn in Transcribed Inscription\nObj 5:\nThe third cairn-marker may be found outside a barrow further to the south of the Hall of Sanctuary.\nLhudd instructed you to find the cairn-markers which denote the house of Fernvael, bearing the mark of a crowned boar. This symbol may also be found among the barrows of Fernvael's followers.\n* Use Bedh-stones (Level 1)\nObj 6:\nThe third cairn-marker may be found outside a barrow further to the south of the Hall of Sanctuary.\nLhudd instructed you to find the cairn-markers which denote the house of Fernvael, bearing the mark of a crowned boar. This symbol may also be found among the barrows of Fernvael's followers.\n* Turn in Transcribed Inscription\nObj 7:\nCadelhin is at Crug Cadelhin in the Lich Bluffs.\nLhudd told you to bring news of Crug Fernvael's location to the shade Cadelhin.\n* Talk to Cadelhin at Crug Cadelhin"},
{area="Greenfields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 25c"}},d="Something has driven the bats near Scary to swoop from their caves and attack hobbits on the outskirts of the town.",mobs={{locations={"27.90S, 66.74W"},name="Prisca Underhill"}},category="Shire",id=1778,scope="n/a",name="Restless Roost",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"},{val="Trousers of the Underhills",id="700032CF"}},level=13,minlevel=9,b="Prisca Underhill",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nPrisca Underhill is at the entrance of Scary.\nPrisca Underhill wants you to deal with the bats south of Scary which have become hostile, attacking even during the day.\n* Defeat bats (8)\nObj 2:\nPrisca Underhill is in Scary, near the entrance to town.\nPrisca will be pleased to hear that you have done your part to alleviate the threat of the bats outside Scary.\n* Talk to Prisca Underhill",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Trestlebridge",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="8s 50c"}},d="You recovered the Founder's Book for Marla Shelton, but it seems some of the map pages are missing. She is concerned that the Orcs will make use of them to plan another raid against Trestlebridge.",category="North Downs",id=1779,scope="n/a",prev={2397},name="Restoring the Founders' Book",arcs="The Founder's Book",receive={{val="Founders' Staff",id="70006B98"}},level=23,minlevel=18,b="Marla Shelton",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are many Orc camps around the Greenway.\nMarla Shelton has asked you to recover the map pages stolen from the Founder's Book, thereby restoring the book and thwarting the Orcs' attacks.\n* Bring the map pages back to Marla Shelton\n* Turn in Map-page"},
{["next"]={2464},area="Fasach-larran",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Cána is worried that the Trév Duvárdain and their Angmarim masters are getting fat off the land that is rightfully that of the Trév Gállorg.",mobs={{locations={"2.55N, 37.25W"},name="Cána"}},selectoneof={{val="Pease-Picking Gauntlets",id="70002D0D"},{val="Pease-Picking Gloves",id="70002D0C"}},category="Angmar",id=1780,scope="n/a",prev={139,2533},name="Restoring the Peas",arcs="Restoration",level=44,c={"* Pea plants can be found at [5.7N, 36.1W] and [5.5N, 35.1W]"},pois={{locations={"5.68N, 35.96W","5.47N, 34.39W","5.35N, 35.14W","5.33N, 34.31W","5.81N, 35.97W","5.49N, 34.58W","5.35N, 35.07W","5.31N, 35.15W","5.35N, 34.47W","5.42N, 35.14W","5.77N, 36.03W","5.73N, 35.95W","5.70N, 36.04W","5.68N, 36.08W","5.37N, 34.35W","5.47N, 34.50W","5.42N, 34.49W","5.43N, 34.34W","5.79N, 36.09W","5.42N, 34.42W","5.37N, 34.55W","5.44N, 35.10W","5.73N, 36.08W","5.38N, 35.10W","5.31N, 35.06W","5.47N, 34.31W","5.32N, 34.41W","5.41N, 35.05W"},name="Pea Plant"}},minlevel=39,b="Cána",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nPea-plants can be found in the farmland outside the city of Donnvail, north-east of Fail-á-Khro.\nCána has tasked you with recovering the pea-plants from the farms outside Donnvail.\n* Use Pea Plant\nObj 2:\nCána is at Fail-á-Khro, on the road north of Aughaire.\nYou have harvested pea-plants from the farms near Donnvail to keep them from the enemies of the Trév Gállorg.\n* Talk to Cána\n* Turn in Pea-plant"},
{["next"]={2778},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="According to Matti, the Kantâ-vilkku must be maintained with fuel and provisions for the Lossoth who keep watch over it.",mobs={{locations={"19.45N, 71.31W"},name="Matti"}},category="Forochel",id=1781,scope="n/a",prev={356},name="Resupplying the Beacon",arcs="Beacons in the Snow",level=47,c={"* The Kantâ-vilkku (or Snow Beacon) is in Jä-rannit at [18.2N, 66.7W]. The crate you must resupply are at the beacon. To find sign of what destroyed the beacon, inspect some Snow Beacon Supplies near the beacon at [18.5N, 66.3W]"},pois={{locations={"18.54N, 66.32W"},name="Snow Beacon Supplies"},{locations={"18.22N, 66.69W","18.23N, 66.69W"},name="Snow Beacon Supply Crate"}},minlevel=42,b="Matti",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Kantâ-vilkku is east and a little south of Sûri-kylä in Jä-rannit along the snow drifts over the bay of Forochel.\nMatti has asked you to visit the Kantâ-vilkku and replace the missing supplies.\n* Use Snow Beacon Supply Crate\n* Turn in Snow Beacon Supplies (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nThe Kantâ-vilkku is east and a little south of Sûri-kylä in Jä-rannit along the snow drifts over the bay of Forochel.\nBesides restocking the Kantâ-vilkku, Matti asked you to search near it for signs of what damaged the crates.\n* Use Snow Beacon Supplies\nObj 3:\nMatti is at Sûri-kylä, west and a little north of the Kantâ-vilkku.\nYou should return to Matti with your report.\n* Talk to Matti"},
{["next"]={936},area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 70c"}},d="George seems much calmer than before.  You should speak with Wald Sandson.",mobs={{locations={"31.95S, 74.45W"},name="George"},{locations={"32.01S, 74.35W"},name="Wald Sandson"}},category="Shire",id=1782,scope="n/a",prev={908,905,910,909,904,907,906},name="Returning to Wald",receive={{val="Cloak of the Cluck",id="7000A6AF"}},level=6,minlevel=2,b="George",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWald Sandson is in the yard at Sandson's Farm.\nYou should return to Wald Sandson and report your success.\n* Talk to Wald Sandson"},
{["next"]={997},area="Falathlorn",zone="Ered Luin",d="Brethilwen wishes to thank Bregedúr for his kindness.",mobs={{locations={"26.67S, 94.94W"},name="Brethilwen"},{locations={"28.22S, 92.66W"},name="Bregedúr"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1783,scope="n/a",prev={1003},name="Return the Cask",arcs="Vintner's Aid",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Brethilwen",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBregedúr spends his time at the crafters' market in Celondim.\nBrethilwen crushed the grapes you collected into a fine wine and sent them on to her friend Bregedúr in Celondim.\n* Talk to Bregedúr\n* Turn in Wine-cask",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={235},area="Nimrodel",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Dindirith wants you to return the filth you cleaned from the banks of the Nimrodel to the Orcs.",mobs={{locations={"14.23S, 72.98W"},name="Dindirith"}},selectoneof={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Learning",id="7001F256"},{val="Sealed Copper Setting of the Enduring Hand",id="700185CF"},{q="(x2)",val="Pure Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA85"},{q="(x2)",val="Pure Athelas Essence",id="7000EA84"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1784,scope="n/a",prev={643},name="Return Their Filth",receive={{val="Lamb and Onion Soup",id="70018E86"}},level=60,pois={{locations={"15.15S, 75.58W","12.79S, 77.55W","12.90S, 77.55W","14.32S, 77.85W","15.12S, 75.48W","14.22S, 77.96W","15.11S, 75.88W","13.83S, 78.03W","14.30S, 77.72W","14.10S, 77.93W","15.00S, 75.71W"},name="Orc Campfire"}},minlevel=55,b="Dindirith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orc camps of Uruk-gashan, Drû-garmadh, and Athmadhul can be found all along the road that runs through Nanduhirion, west and north of Echad Andestel.\nDindirith has asked you to burn the Orc filth you collected in one of the fires the Orcs have set in their camps in Nanduhirion.\n* Use Orc Campfire\n* Turn in Orc Filth\nObj 2:\nDindirith is in Echad Andestel, the camp north of the road outside Lórien, and east of Nanduhirion.\nYou have disposed of the Orc filth and should return now to Dindirith.\n* Talk to Dindirith"},
{area="Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Nökkvi demands vengeance in the name of the fallen dwarves upon which the Nameless have been feeding.",selectoneof={{val="Necklace of Subtlety",id="70017CE4"},{val="Hammer from the Grave",id="7001640E"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1785,scope="n/a",prev={276},name="Revenge from the Grave",arcs="Lurking in the Shadows",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Nökkvi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMazam-dûm lies upon the eastern shore of the lake in the Foundations of Stone.\nNökkvi has asked you to return to the lair of the nameless creatures and defeat the greatest of their kind. Its death should serve as a decisive statement to the others.\n* Defeat Blind-strider\nObj 2:\nNökkvi is at the Shadowed Refuge in the Foundations of Stone.\nYou should return to Nökkvi and tell him of your victory against Blind-strider.\n* Talk to Nökkvi at the Shadowed Refuge"},
{["next"]={1814,313,1852},area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Dannasen, released from Neven's control, seeks not only to fulfil his curse, but also to exact revenge upon the Hillmen of Rhudaur who serve the enigmatic Red-maid of Garth Agarwen.",mobs={{locations={"29.67S, 27.39W"},name="Dannasen"}},category="Lone-lands",id=1786,scope="n/a",prev={2838},name="Rhudaur's Traitors",arcs="Long Overdue Justice",level=31,c={"* The satchels can drop from the Rhudaur north-east of the Eglan-camp."},minlevel=26,b="Dannasen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Hillmen of Rhudaur are encamped in the north-east corner of Agamaur. Dannasen is at the Eglan-camp south-west of the Hillmen.\nDannasen has asked you to bring him the satchels borne by the Hillmen of Rhudaur so that he might find evidence to remind his brethren in the south of the curse that binds them to Middle-earth.\n* Deliver the satchels to Dannasen\n* Turn in Rhudaurian Satchel"},
{area="The Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Skûmfil is nothing more than a dumping ground, a place where the fallen Orcs of Moria are discarded when they begin to reek. It is here that two foes have gathered, each intent on using the corpses found therein for their own purposes. The kergrim and other scavengers as a source of food, and the insects as a place to lay their eggs to spawn future generations.",mobs={{locations={"13.16S, 101.22W"},name="Ymar"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1787,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Ridding Potential Disease",arcs="Skumfíl",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Ymar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSkûmfil lies to the south-east of the Shadowed Refuge.\nYmar told you that he was set to the task of ridding Skûmfil of the disease-carrying cave-claws within.\n* Defeat cave-claws in Skûmfil (16)\n* Defeat the kergrim-summoner\nObj 2:\nYmar is at the Shadowed Refuge, north-west of Skûmfil.\nYou found your way to Skûmfil and destroyed the cave-claws there, halting the spread of the disease that they carry.\n* Talk to Ymar at the Shadowed Refuge"},
{["next"]={1850},area="The Flaming Deeps",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Öndótt sent you to speak with his friend Gapi regarding the key you found.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1788,scope="n/a",prev={1846},name="Riddles in the Doors",level=56,pois={{locations={"15.42S, 106.88W","15.42S, 106.81W","15.42S, 106.84W","15.33S, 106.83W","15.33S, 106.86W","15.33S, 106.89W","15.33S, 106.79W"},name="Locker"}},minlevel=51,b="Gapi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe lockers can be found at Bhraf-ru, south-east of Anazârmekhem.\nGapi told you of several plaques marked with a riddle:\nWeight in my belly,\nTrees are my back,\nNails in my ribs,\nFeet do I lack.\nHe believes one of them is the answer.\n* Use Locker\n* Use Locker",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={832},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",money={{val="10s 36c"}},d="You found the personal papers of a dwarf in the library of the Great Delving.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1789,scope="n/a",name="Riddles in the Library",arcs="Riddles in the Dark",receive={{val="Infused Garnet",id="700135D7"}},level=53,minlevel=48,b="Falgeirr's Papers",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSót, the librarian of the Dolven-view camp, might know more about the paper you found. You should speak with him.\n* Talk to Sót at the Dolven-view\nObj 2:\nÖndótt is stationed at the Deep Descent, south of the Great Delving.\nSót suggested you speak with his friend Öndótt regarding the paper you found.\n* Talk to Öndótt at the Deep Descent"},
{["next"]={1844},area="The Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="Öndótt has deciphered the runes marked on the key you found as meaning Flame or Fire, and Deep or Chasm.",category="Moria",id=1790,scope="n/a",prev={1847},name="Riddles in the Locks",arcs="Riddles in the Dark",level=55,minlevel=50,b="Öndótt",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGapi is at Anazârmekhem. You can take the path through the Water-works, far to the south of the Deep Descent, and then eastwards, or through Zelem-melek and then southwards.\nÖndótt suggested that you take the key to his friend Gapi, but warned that both paths to the Orc-watch are very dangerous.\n* Talk to Gapi\n* Turn in Chest Key"},
{["next"]={1846},area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="You solved the first riddle, which led to a plaque marked with a snake. Further within the room thus marked is a plaque inscribed with a riddle in Falgeirr's hand.",category="Moria",id=1791,scope="n/a",prev={832},name="Riddles in the Stone",arcs="Riddles in the Dark",receive={{val="Twisttongue's Cloak",id="7001605A"}},level=54,pois={{locations={"12.24S, 111.24W"},name="Stone Chest"}},minlevel=49,b="Riddle",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSolve Twisttongue's riddle by choosing the correct chest:\nAt night, I come without being fetched.\nBy day, though lost, I am not gone.\nAll know me, but only the ocean heeds my call.\n* Use Stone Chest\nObj 2:\nÖndótt can be found at the Deep Descent, north and somewhat west of the Chamber of the Serpent.\nYou should ask him about the key you found in the chest.\n* Talk to Öndótt\n* Turn in Chest Key"},
{area="Nanduhirion",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="55s 30c"}},d="You have solved a long series of riddles set by Falgeirr Twisttongue, and your journey has taken you through Khazad-dûm and out the East-gate, into the Dimrill Dale.",mobs={{locations={"13.47S, 77.87W"},name="Treasure Chest"}},selectoneof={{val="Falgeirr's Final Twist",id="700163B4"},{val="The Riddler's Ring",id="700163B8"},{val="Twisttongue's Legacy",id="700163F2"},{val="The Sword of a Thousand Riddles",id="7001640A"},{val="Falgeirr's Shelter",id="700163CA"}},category="Moria",id=1792,scope="n/a",prev={1849},name="Riddles in the Sunshine",level=58,c={"* Your reward is in a chest inside Ghâr-bayur, a cave locked with a door in Nanduhirion at [13.5S, 77.9W]"},minlevel=53,b="Riddle",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSolve the last of Twisttongue's riddles to find the treasure:\nA room in shadows with no door\nNo wood or tile make up my floor\nNature's art my columns carved\nIn my belly bears have starved\nStep far down and water face\nRight foot follow and road trace\nSunsetward and great rocks paired:\nTwisttongue for his family cared.\n* Find the answer to Twisttongue's last riddle\nObj 2:\nYour reward lies within the chest in Falgeirr's cave.\n* Collect your reward from the chest"},
{["next"]={1848},area="The Twenty-first Hall",zone="Moria",d="Falgeirr's riddle has brought you on a long journey through the great halls of Moria, and at last you are come to the final pieces of the puzzle.",mobs={{locations={"4.74S, 105.28W"},name="Ulfkell"}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1793,scope="n/a",prev={1850},name="Riddles in the Tomb",level=57,c={"* The answer to the first riddle is Bridge. There is Plaque with a bridge in it in the same Chamber of Mazarbul at [4.9S, 105.4W]\n* To complete the quest, you must go outside Moria through the eastern gate to Lothlórien."},pois={{locations={"4.92S, 105.32W","4.79S, 105.41W","4.58S, 105.32W","4.59S, 105.27W","4.92S, 105.38W","4.92S, 105.27W","4.61S, 105.43W","4.58S, 105.39W","4.89S, 105.43W","4.71S, 105.41W"},name="Plaque"}},minlevel=52,b="Ulfkell",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSolve Falgeirr's riddle:\nDwarf walketh over,\nDwarf walketh under.\nIn time of war,\nDwarf burneth asunder.\nUlfkell believes that the answer to Falgeirr's riddle lies somewhere within the great Chamber of Records, known also as the Chamber of Mazarbul.\n* Use Plaque\n* Use Plaque\nObj 2:\nSolve Falgeirr's penultimate riddle:\nMy first is a snake,\nMy second, a bowl;\nMy third is in nail and urn and knoll,\nAnd if you've a quick and ready mind,\nThe last clue of Falgeirr beneath me you'll find.\nTo determine where to seek the plaque that solves Twisttongue's next riddle, you should decipher the meaning of his words.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1849},area="The Flaming Deeps",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Another riddle was waiting for you within the locker, along with three plaque-marked levers.",mobs={{locations={"4.74S, 105.28W"},name="Ulfkell"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1794,scope="n/a",prev={1844},name="Riddles in the Walls",level=56,pois={{locations={"15.42S, 106.84W"},name="Lever"}},minlevel=51,b="Riddle",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFalgeirr Twisttongue's latest riddle reads:\nI turn around once,\nWhat is out will not get in.\nI turn around again,\nWhat is in will not get out.\nSelect the lever that best answers this riddle. The levers are in Bhraf-ru in the Flaming Deeps.\n* Use Lever\nObj 2:\nWhen you chose the Lever of the Key, another riddle was revealed:\nDwarf walketh over\nDwarf walketh under\nIn time of war,\nDwarf burneth asunder.\nYou may want to speak to Gapi about this most recently-revealed riddle. He is at Anazârmekhem, north-east of The Crossroads of Ash.\n* Talk to Gapi in Anazârmekhem\nObj 3:\nSimbi is at the Twenty-first Hall, north-east of Anazârmekhem.\nGapi suggested you speak with his friend Simbi about the new riddle.\n* Talk to Simbi at the Twenty-first Hall\nObj 4:\nSimbi has advised you to seek out his friend Ulfkell in the Chamber of Mazarbul, to the north of the Twenty-first Hall, to solve Falgeirr Twisttongue's riddle:\nDwarf walketh over\nDwarf walketh under\nIn time of war,\nDwarf burneth asunder.\n* Talk to Ulfkell in the Chamber of Mazarbul",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1912,2383},area="Nanduhirion",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+300 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Warg-riders in the Dimrill Dale have been terrorizing the dwarf-encampment at Mekhem-bizru. With the Wargs thinned, it is now time to strike at the riders.",category="Moria",id=1795,scope="n/a",prev={1994},name="Riders in the Dale",arcs="Riders in the Dale",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Ótam",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMoria riders can be found at Athmadhul, south-east of Mekhem-bizru.\nÓtam wants you to defeat the goblins training to become new Warg-riders.\n* Defeat Moria riders\nObj 2:\nÓtam is at Mekhem-bizru, north-west of Athmadhul.\nÓtam will be pleased to hear the goblin Warg-riders have been defeated.\n* Talk to Ótam at Mekhem-bizru"},
{area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="Radagast the Brown was reminded of a legend about rings that were given to the leaders of the Hill-men to signify their service to Angmar. These rings gave them power over their lessers, but exacted their very lives from them, making their bodies vessels for wight-spirits.",mobs={{locations={"29.79S, 27.39W","29.78S, 27.39W"},name="Radagast the Brown"}},selectoneof={{val="Relentless Staff",id="700006F6"},{val="Warmonger",id="700092DC"}},category="Garth Agarwen",id=1796,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1842,2838},name="Rings of Rhudaur",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Radagast the Brown",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWights can be found in Garth Agarwen in the north of Agamaur. Radagast can be found at Barad Dhorn in the Eglan-camp.\nRadagast the Brown has asked you to enter Garth Agarwen and discover if the legendary rings exist. If they do, he wishes them brought to him so that they may be destroyed.\n* Return the Rings to Radagast the Brown\n* Turn in Warrior-ring"},
