{["next"]={2435},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="Wafri claims that the gredbyg hunt and speak among each other mostly using unusual scents. He believes this may be used to their undoing.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1853,scope="n/a",prev={365},name="Scent of the Hive",arcs="Bedbugs!",level=52,minlevel=47,b="Wafri",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGredbyg can be found throughout the Great Delving, below the Dolven-view.\nWafri has asked you to hunt down some Gredbyg and collect their scent-glands.\n* Turn in Grodbog Scent-gland\nObj 2:\nWafri is at the Dolven-view camp, above the Great Delving.\nYou should bring the scent-glands you have collected back to Wafri.\n* Talk to Wafri\n* Turn in Grodbog Scent-gland"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Cachúnir has expressed a desire to take as much history and lore of Middle-earth into the West as is possible.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Cachúnir"}},category="Reputation",id=1854,scope="n/a",name="Scholar's Writs -- Introduction",level=40,minlevel=35,b="Cachúnir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCachúnir is at Rivendell in the Trollshaws.\nCachúnir has asked you to pen some scholar's writs to be preserved in the libraries of Valinor when the Elves of Rivendell sail into the West.\n* Present your Scholar's Writs to Cachúnir in Rivendell\n* Turn in Scholar's Writ",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nanduhirion",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+300 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Dulgurz has terrorized the dwarves of the Dimrill Dale since they first set camp.",category="Moria",id=1855,scope="n/a",prev={1851},name="Scourge of the Dale",receive={{val="Dulgurz's Doom",id="7001640F"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Ótam",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDulgurz is at Athmadhul, south-east of Mekhem-bizru.\nÓtam told you of a particulary dangerous warg-rider, Dulgurz, who must no longer be allowed to roam the Dimrill Dale.\n* Defeat Dulgurz\nObj 2:\nÓtam is at Mekhem-bizru, north-west of Athmadhul.\nÓtam will want to hear of the defeat of Dulgurz.\n* Talk to Ótam at Mekhem-bizru"},
{["next"]={2672},area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="After some time passed, Elrond Halfelven sent scouts into the fields of Eregion to follow the path of the Company which left Rivendell and make sure that no signs of their passing remained for the Enemy to find.",mobs={{locations={"40.17S, 16.04W"},name="Maedlathron"}},category="Eregion",id=1856,scope="n/a",name="Scouring the Path",arcs="Footsteps of the Company",level=48,c={"* You will find a Pipeweed Pouch at an abandoned camp in the High Hollin area [43.8S, 12.9W]"},pois={{locations={"43.81S, 12.93W"},name="Pipeweed Pouch"}},minlevel=43,b="Maedlathron",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe campsite is nestled at the base of some large boulders, some distance to the south-east of Gwingris, beyond Sâd Rechu, south of the road to Pembar.\nMaedlathron has asked you to search a place which may have been a campsite used by the Company. Any signs of the Company's passing must be removed.\n* Scour the company's path\nObj 2:\nMaedlathron is at Gwingris, some distance to the north-west of the abandoned campsite.\nYou should bring the pouch of pipe-weed which you found to Maedlathron.\n* Talk to Maedlathron\n* Turn in Pipeweed Pouch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1025},reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Gloomglens",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Rangers of the Grey Company seek to ensure the secrecy of their purpose and their passage through Enedwaith.",mobs={{locations={"63.47S, 21.46W"},name="Idhrenfair"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1857,scope="n/a",name="Scouring the Wood",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Idhrenfair",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe first patrol point is north-east of Echad Idhrenfair.\nIdhrenfair has asked you to patrol the paths of the Gloomglens with instructions to keep an eye out for any signs of the Enemy's minions.\n* Scout the first patrol point\nObj 2:\nThe second patrol point is north-west of the first.\nIdhrenfair has asked you to patrol the paths of the Gloomglens with instructions to keep an eye out for any signs of the Enemy's minions.\n* Scout the second patrol point\nObj 3:\nThe third patrol point is south-west of the second.\nIdhrenfair has asked you to patrol the paths of the Gloomglens with instructions to keep an eye out for any signs of the Enemy's minions.\n* Scout the third patrol point\nObj 4:\nThe fourth patrol point is south of the third.\nIdhrenfair has asked you to patrol the paths of the Gloomglens with instructions to keep an eye out for any signs of the Enemy's minions.\n* Scout the fourth patrol point\nObj 5:\nThe fifth patrol point is east of the fourth.\nIdhrenfair has asked you to patrol the paths of the Gloomglens with instructions to keep an eye out for any signs of the Enemy's minions.\n* Scout the fifth patrol point\nObj 6:\nIdhrenfair is at Echad Idhrenfair in the Gloomglens of Enedwaith, north-west of the fifth patrol point.\nYou should return to Idhrenfair with news of your discoveries.\n* Talk to Idhrenfair at Echad Idhrenfair",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hoardale",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Quartermaster Apsduf prepares the defence of Tol Ascarnen against the Free Peoples.",category="Tol Ascarnen",id=1858,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Scour the Walls Clean",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Quartermaster Apsduf",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSlaughter the Free Peoples in and around Tol Ascarnen to earn the favour of your masters.\nQuartermaster Apsduf told you to prepare for battle against the Free Peoples and to do your part to repel them from Tol Ascarnen.\n* Defeat the Free Peoples at Tol Ascarnen (30 at Tol Ascarnen )\nObj 2:\nIf Apsduf is slain or Tol Ascarnen was taken by the enemy, go to War-Tyrant Akúlhun at Gramsfoot.\nYou have successfully slaughtered the Free Peoples and should return to Apsduf to claim your reward.\n* Talk to Quartermaster Apsduf\n* Talk to War-tyrant Akúlhun",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={728},reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="Ashenslades",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Orc-camp at Ânug-stazg is the primary sentry-post for the Enemy's forces in the Ashenslades.",mobs={{locations={"17.71S, 48.28W"},name="Perindúr"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1859,scope="n/a",name="Scout Ânug-stazg",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,c={"* The western campfire is in the Ashenslades around [17.8S, 47.5W]\n* The path to Ânug-stazg in the Ashenslades can be explored around [17.9S, 47.2W]\n* The eastern campfire is in the Ashenslades around [17.9S, 47.0W]"},minlevel=60,b="Perindúr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nÂnug-stazg can be found east and slightly north  of Mithechad.\nPerindúr has asked you to scout out the path leading into Ânug-stazg and the campfires at the edges of the camp.\n* Scout the western campfire\n* Scout the path to Ânug-stazg\n* Scout the eastern campfire\nObj 2:\nPerindúr is at Mithechad, west and slightly south of Ânug-stazg.\nYou should return to Perindúr with your report of the Enemy's forces at Ânug-stazg.\n* Talk to Perindúr at Mithechad",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1502,430},reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Thrór's Coomb",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Draig-lûth have created a village on the northern shore of the river, presenting a danger to travellers in the area.",mobs={{locations={"67.43S, 13.92W"},name="Gronu"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1860,scope="n/a",name="Scout Gwâl Draig",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Gronu",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGwâl Draig lies on the southern shore of the river, north-east of Gronu's camp.\nGronu has asked you to scout out the entrances to the camp and dispatch any guards you might encounter.\n* Scout the western entrance of Gwâl Draig\n* Scout the southern entrance of Gwâl Draig\n* Scout the eastern entrance of Gwâl Draig\n* Defeat Draig-lûth guards\nObj 2:\nGronu is at his camp south-east of Gwâl Draig.\nYou should seek out Gronu and let him know what lies within the village of Gwâl Draig.\n* Talk to Gronu at his camp",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1966},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="The goblins have established a large encampment in Gazatmur, which worries the dwarves at the Dolven-view.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1861,scope="n/a",name="Scouting Ahead",arcs="Goblins of the Great Delving",level=52,minlevel=47,b="Slagvi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblin encampment lies below the Dolven-view at Gazatmur. Good vantage points for scouting can be found to the north and south of the encampment.\nSlagvi has asked you to scout a large goblin encampment. He warned you to avoid being seen.\n* Find an overlook south of Gazatmur\n* Find an overlook north of Gazatmur\nObj 2:\nSlagvi is at the dwarf-camp at the Dolven-view, above the Great Delving.\nYou should return to Slagvi at Dolven-view with the information you have obtained.\n* Talk to Slagvi at the Dolven-view encampment",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={686,1875,321},reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="Ashenslades",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="In the southern reaches of the Ashenslades, Ânghum-maudhûl stands as the central rallying point for Orcs in the area.",mobs={{locations={"17.67S, 48.30W"},name="Harchador"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1862,scope="n/a",prev={728,2456,1949},name="Scouting Ânghum-maudhûl",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Harchador",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nÂnghum-maudhûl lies to the south-east of Mithechad.\nHarchador has asked you to explore the western and eastern approaches to the camp and a small camp directly across from the main rallying point at Ânghum-maudhûl.\n* Scout the eastern approach\n* Scout the northern camp\n* Scout the western approach\nObj 2:\nHarchador is at Mithechad, north-west of Ânghum-maudhûl.\nYou should return to Harchador and give your report on Ânghum-maudhûl.\n* Talk to Harchador at Mithechad",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="Arthobel sits high upon the hills above the Way of Kings. Were the robbers to find their way in, it would provide a very strategic viewpoint.",category="Evendim",id=1863,scope="n/a",name="Scouting Arthobel",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=37,minlevel=32,b="Maladan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nArthobel is south-west of the Ranger-encampment in the Way of Kings.\nMaladan asked you to scout the ruins of Arthobel to see if the tomb-robbers are actively using it.\n* Look around for signs of activity (Perform /lookaround)\n* Find the ruins of Arthobel\nObj 2:\nMaladan is at the Ranger-camp in the Way of Kings.\nMaladan will be pleased to hear the tomb-robbers have not gained access to Arthobel.\n* Talk to Maladan",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Handelen fears that the Orcs are mustering their forces in the northern reaches of Gathbúrz.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 46.59W"},name="Handelen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1864,scope="n/a",prev={1953},name="Scouting in Force",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Handelen",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe first point is north-east of Thangúlhad. The second point is to the north-west of the first, direcdly north of Kúfuzg. The third point is directly north of Thangúlhad, a little south of Búrzkala. The fourth point is just north-west of Thangúlhad.\nYou should scout the waypoints of the patrol that Handelen has asked you to undertake and defeat any enemies you might find there.\n* Patrol the first point in northern Gathbúrz\n* Patrol the second point in northern Gathbúrz\n* Patrol the third point in northern Gathbúrz\n* Patrol the fourth point in northern Gathbúrz\nObj 2:\nHandelen is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nYou should return to Handelen with the report of your patrol.\n* Talk to Handelen at Thangúlhad"},
{["next"]={2599},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Watcher Redweed has asked for your help dealing with goblins that have taken up residence in the Midgewater Marshes.",mobs={{locations={"31.09S, 49.40W"},name="Watcher Redweed"}},category="Bree-land",id=1865,scope="n/a",name="Scouting the Marshes",arcs="Goblins in the Marshes",level=14,minlevel=10,b="Watcher Redweed",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Sunken Stones are located south-east of Eldo Swatmidge's farm, east of Staddle. The Goblinhole Ruins are far to the east and south of the Sunken Stones.\nWatcher Redweed wants you to visit two ruins in the southern Midgewater Marshes and defeat goblins at each location to assess the threat the goblins pose to Staddle's well-being.\n* Defeat goblins at the Sunken Stones (3)\n* Defeat goblins at the Goblinhole Ruins (3)\nObj 2:\nBill Mossfoot is stationed south-east of the ruins of Midgewater Marsh.\nRedweed told you to report your findings at the ruins to Bill Mossfoot.\n* Talk to Bill Mossfoot",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={994},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Concerned about hostile giant activity in the Misty Mountains, Ringhul has sent you to meet with a scout in the highlands north of Rivendell.",mobs={{locations={"24.78S, 4.05W"},name="Gwaemithrin"},{locations={"29.80S, 5.47W"},name="Ringhul"}},category="Trollshaws",id=1866,scope="n/a",prev={1494},name="Scouting the Mountains",arcs="Thunder in the Mountains",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Ringhul",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe scout Gwaemithrin is in the highlands north and east of Rivendell at a camp established by the dwarves.\nRinghul has asked you to assist Gwaemithrin with her investigation into the doings of the giants of the Misty Mountains.\n* Talk to Gwaemithrin"},
{["next"]={1102,2795},reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Orcs stormed out of the Ram Dúath and swept across the North Downs. After their passage, Hillmen out of Angmar came through the pass and encamped beyond the cliff faces and treacherous paths.",mobs={{locations={"9.60S, 42.10W"},name="Dagoras"}},category="North Downs",id=1867,scope="n/a",name="Scouting the Ram Dúath",level=31,minlevel=26,b="Dagoras",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Hillman-encampment is north-east of Esteldín. The pass is west of the Hillman-encampment, north-west of an outcropping of spiny rocks.\nDagoras has asked you to scout the Hillman-encampment and the pass through which the Hillmen approached to determine the severity of the threat they pose, so that the Rangers can plan a defence against them.\n* Scout the Hillman camp at the Eastern Ram Dúath\n* Scout the pass through the Western Ram Dúath\nObj 2:\nDagoras awaits your report at Esteldín.\nAngmarim forces have sent a small company of Hillmen to the south-east entrance of Ram Dúath. At the southwest entrance of Ram Dúath, you discovered evidence of many worms and drakes. You should return to Dagoras with your report.\n* Talk to Dagoras at Esteldín",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={644},area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Scouts of the Malledhrim witnessed the Orcs of Garmadh-maudhûl discarding piles of ore.",mobs={{locations={"17.49S, 48.19W"},name="Eirien"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1868,scope="n/a",name="Scouting the Stores",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"16.60S, 46.49W","16.78S, 46.56W","16.72S, 46.46W","16.93S, 46.42W","16.91S, 46.56W","16.50S, 46.46W","16.61S, 46.16W"},name="Sack of Discarded Ore"}},minlevel=60,b="Eirien",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGarmadh-maudhûl lies to the north-east of Mithechad.\nEirien has asked you to collect some of the ore discarded by the Orcs of Garmadh-maudhûl.\n* Use Sack of Discarded Ore\nObj 2:\nEirien is at Mithechad, south-west of Garmadh-maudhûl.\nYou should bring the discarded ore to Eirien. Perhaps she will be able to see if this ore has been affected by the blight.\n* Talk to Eirien at Mithechad"},
{["next"]={2729},area="South Trollshaws",zone="The Trollshaws",d="Alphlanc is watching the road as it runs over the Last Bridge for any sign that servants of the Enemy might slip into -- or out of -- the Trollshaws.",mobs={{locations={"34.04S, 20.16W"},name="Barachen"}},category="Trollshaws",id=1869,scope="n/a",name="Scouting the Wild",level=33,minlevel=28,b="Alphlanc",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarachen is at his camp east of the Last Bridge, on a hill south of the road. Alphlanc told you to follow the road east until you see her friend Rochwen, who can further guide you.\nAlphlanc asked you to bring word to Barachen that no evil has entered the Trollshaws while she has been watching the Last Bridge, though neither has any left.\n* Talk to Barachen",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2704},area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",money={{val="41s 44c"}},d="Something is stirring the bats up, causing concern for the dwarves in Moria.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=1870,scope="n/a",prev={1085},name="Scraps of Shadow",receive={{val="Rambi's Armour",id="7001605D"}},level=53,minlevel=48,b="Rambi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance to the bats' cave lies north and east of the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nRambi has asked you to hunt down the bats that have infested Durin's Way.\n* Find the bat-cave\nObj 2:\nThe entrance to the bats' cave lies north and east of the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nRambi has asked you to hunt down the bats that have infested Durin's Way.\n* Defeat bats\n* Defeat morvul bat-handlers\nObj 3:\nRambi is at the Chamber of the Crossroads in Durin's Way, west and south of the bats' cave.\nYou should return to Rambi with tidings of your success.\n* Talk to Rambi at the Chamber of the Crossroads"},
{["next"]={647},area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="You discovered a blighted branch in the Ashenslades, corrupted by an unknown disease.",mobs={{locations={"17.48S, 44.56W"},name="Himeinior"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1871,scope="n/a",name="Scratching the Surface",receive={{val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Blighted Branch",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHimeinior is at Barad Angol, a small camp at a tower overlooking Sâd Doldúr.\nYou should seek out Himeinior and give him the branch you found. Perhaps he can discern more about what is happening to the trees in the Ashenslades.\n* Talk to Himeinior\n* Turn in Blighted Branch"},
{area="The Scuttledells",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Ivorel is concerned that the damage caused by the Gaunt-masters may not be reversible, but the barrows must be sealed to prevent more of the dead from emerging to threaten the Malledhrim.",mobs={{locations={"12.42S, 50.90W"},name="Ivorel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1872,scope="n/a",prev={3232},name="Sealing the Barrows",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=64,c={"* The Barrow of Brungúr is in the Shrine of the Ancient One at [11.7S, 47.9W]\n* The Barrow of Thorún is in the Shrine of the Ancient One at [11.4S, 48.0W]\n* The Barrow of Mordeloth is in the Shrine of the Ancient One at [11.3S, 48.3W]"},pois={{locations={"11.42S, 47.96W"},name="Barrow of Thorún"},{locations={"11.25S, 48.25W"},name="Barrow of Mordeloth"},{locations={"11.74S, 47.86W"},name="Barrow of Brungúr"}},minlevel=59,b="Ivorel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe barrows lie to the north-east of Ivorel's camp.\nIvorel asked you to shut the barrows of the Scuttledells and place seals of Elven-make upon them so that the fell spirits of Morgoth cannot rise up as wights.\n* Use Barrow of Brungúr\n* Use Barrow of Thorún\n* Use Barrow of Mordeloth\nObj 2:\nIvorel is at her camp, south-west of the barrows.\nYou should return to Ivorel with news of your success.\n* Talk to Ivorel\n* Turn in Barrow Seal"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 20c"}},d="Túbi Thickfist wants the newly discovered goblin-camp taken out. He cautions you to keep an eye out for messengers as aid from the deeps would be disastrous.",selectoneof={{val="Messenger's Pursuit",id=70016077},{val="Thickfist's Thick-axe",id="700160F4"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1873,scope="n/a",prev={210},name="Sealing the Gate",arcs="Goblin Threat",level=51,c={"* The goblins are in Snaga-maudhûl [7.8S, 114.4W]."},minlevel=46,b="Túbi Thickfist",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblin-camp lies in the tunnels beyond the crack above the eastern stair.\nThe dwarves want to end the goblins' reign over the tunnels below to ensure the safety and security of their foothold.\n* Defeat a goblin-messenger\n* Defeat goblins\nObj 2:\nTúbi Thickfist is at Durin's Threshold.\nYou should inform Túbi Thickfist that you have defeated many of the goblins in the small camp and stopped the messenger from seeking aid.\n* Talk to Túbi Thickfist at Durin's Threshold"},
{area="Nan Amlug East",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="There exists a pact between the Suuri-lehmä and the Dwarves of Othrikar, that each would provide aid to the other.",mobs={{locations={"9.22S, 39.92W"},name="Iivari"},{locations={"6.89S, 44.85W"},name="Quartermaster Orgrin"}},selectoneof={{val="Orgrin's Mace",id="70006B8E"},{val="Othronn",id="70006BDC"}},category="North Downs",id=1874,scope="n/a",prev={2068},name="Sealing the Pact",arcs="Coming Battles",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Iivari",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nQuartermaster Orgrin is at Othrikar, north-west of Rusfold.\nIivari has asked you to perform one final task for him: he wishes you to deliver a satchel of herbs to Orgrin, the provisioner at Othrikar, as fulfillment of a pact between Earth-kin and dwarves.\n* Talk to Quartermaster Orgrin\n* Turn in Earth-kin Herb Satchel"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="Angmar has taken an interest in Haudh Eldacar.",category="Evendim",id=1875,scope="n/a",name="Searchers of Haudh Eldacar",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Rodlam",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHaudh Eldacar is west of the Ranger camp in the Way of Kings.\nRodlam asked you to venture within Haudh Eldacar and defeat the Angmarim within.\n* Defeat Angmarim in Haudh Eldacar (8)\nObj 2:\nRodlam is at the Ranger camp in the Way of Kings.\nRodlam will want to know you defeated many Angmarim in Haudh Eldacar.\n* Talk to Rodlam",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2119},area="Talan Revail",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Cúvroval has received orders that every flet must be on the lookout for a sighting of one of the magnificent Great Eagles who hail from the northern Misty Mountains.",category="Lothlórien",id=1876,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Searching for Eagles",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,c={"* Talan Brethil is at [12.2S, 62.4W]\n* Talan Gwilith is at [11.4S, 70.7W]\n* Talan Fanuidhol is at [12.1S, 71.1W]"},minlevel=55,b="Cúvroval",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTalan Brethil is to the south-east of Talan Revail, along the banks of the Anduin. Talan Gwilith and Talan Fanuidhol are well west and a bit south of Talan Revail, along the border of Fanuidhol where the Orcs have recently emerged from Moria.\nCúvroval wants you to go to three of the telain and look into the distance from atop all three of them to search for a Great Eagle in the sky. She was not told why this lookout had to be kept, only that it was essential.\n* Perform /look\n* Perform /look\n* Perform /look\nObj 2:\nCúvroval is at Talan Revail, north-east of Cerin Amroth.\nYou should return to Cúvroval to report that empty skies were all you saw from the telain.\n* Talk to Cúvroval at Talan Revail"},
{area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="2s 55c"}},d="Graham Larkspur is one of Adso's workers. He and his companions are running out of water and need help replenishing their supply.",mobs={{locations={"29.04S, 56.83W"},name="Graham Larkspur"},{locations={"31.11S, 59.39W"},name="Goldberry"}},selectoneof={{val="Adso's Two-Handed Axe",id="7000061B"},{val="Adso's Club",id="7000061A"},{val="Bregdail",id="700090FD"}},category="Bree-land",id=1877,scope="n/a",prev={110},name="Searching for Fresh Springs",arcs="Worth of a Worker",level=17,minlevel=12,b="Graham Larkspur",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance to the Old Forest is to the south of Adso's camp. The spring lies westward within the Forest.\nGraham Larkspur has asked you to fetch water from the spring his hunters found. He warned you to take friends to protect you from the dangers of the Old Forest.\n* Find Goldberry's Spring\nObj 2:\nUpon finding the spring that Graham Larkspur sent you to, you noticed a beautiful but strange-looking woman standing underneath the oak tree on the western bank of the river. Perhaps she possesses the means for you to take water back to Adso's camp.\n* Speak with the beautiful woman at the spring\nObj 3:\nThe entrance of the Old Forest lies to the east, and Adso's camp is north from there.\nAdso sent you into the Old Forest to fetch water, but empty-handed. Goldberry has given you a bucket in which to carry water back to Adso's camp and has granted you leave to draw from her pool, but warns that the Forest is dangerous.\n* Pick up the bucket\nObj 4:\nGraham Larkspur wishes to speak with you again.\n* Talk to Graham Larkspur"},
{["next"]={3217},reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Lich Bluffs",money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="The fetid liquid you discovered in the barrows of the Lich Bluffs may yet provide a clue to the mystery of the Dead in that place.",mobs={{locations={"70.57S, 15.46W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1878,scope="n/a",prev={1518},name="Searching for Signs",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWights can be found in great numbers among the southernmost barrows of the Lich Bluffs.\nMincham has asked you to try and recover an intact phial of the fetid liquid from the wights of the Lich Bluffs.\n* Collect an intact corrupted phial from the wights of the Lich Bluffs\nObj 2:\nWights can be found in great numbers among the southernmost barrows of the Lich Bluffs.\nMincham has asked you to try and recover an intact phial of the fetid liquid from the wights of the Lich Bluffs.\n* Turn in Corrupted Phial\nObj 3:\nMincham is at his camp north of the barrows.\nYou should return to Mincham and deliver the intact corrupted phial you collected.\n* Talk to Mincham\n* Turn in Corrupted Phial",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",reputation={{val="+700 with The Mathom Society"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="The Master Chef is also the Mathom Society's clerk. He has been so busy that he will be unable to prepare the Society's next dinner.",mobs={{locations={"33.39S, 75.53W"},name="Baldwin Foxtail"}},category="Reputation",id=1879,scope="Crafting",name="Seasoned Beef with Cauliflower -- Introduction",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Baldwin Foxtail",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBaldwin Foxtail is at the Mathom House in Michel Delving in the Shire.\nBaldwin Foxtail has asked you to bring him some seasoned beef with cauliflower for the cooks of the Mathom Society.\n* Bring the seasoned beef with cauliflower to Baldwin Foxtail\n* Turn in Seasoned Beef with Cauliflower",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
