{["next"]={258,1920},area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="There are many Watching Stones placed in and around Dol Guldur, guarded by Cargûl sentries. Anyone who foolishly approaches too close to one of these stones is struck with a black curse that sunders the will.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 46.59W"},name="Handelen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1897,scope="n/a",prev={669},name="Sentries of Dol Guldur",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Handelen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWatching Stones and their Cargûl sentries can be found throughout Gathbúrz.\nHandelen has asked you to defeat a number of the Cargûl sentries found near the Watching Stones in Gathbúrz to learn if a way might be found to protect the Malledhrim from the effects of the Stones.\n* Search Cargûl sentries for clues\nObj 2:\nWatching Stones and their Cargûl sentries can be found throughout Gathbúrz.\nHandelen has asked you to defeat a number of the Cargûl sentries found near the Watching Stones in Gathbúrz to learn if a way might be found to protect the Malledhrim from the effects of the Stones.\n* Turn in Engraved Dagger\nObj 3:\nHandelen is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nYou should bring the engraved dagger you found to Handelen.\n* Talk to Handelen in Thangúlhad\nObj 4:\nAgorin is at Ost Galadh in Emyn Lûm, west of Thangúlhad.\nHandelen instructed you to bring the engraved dagger you found to Agorin, the Malledrhim Lore-master in Emyn Lûm.\n* Talk to Agorin\n* Turn in Engraved Dagger\nObj 5:\nHandelen is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nYou should return to Handelen and tell him what you have learned from Agorin about the Watchers of Dol Guldur.\n* Talk to Handelen at Thangúlhad"},
{area="Dar-gazag",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Sergeants command smaller units of the enemy army. These feeble creatures believe that they can stand up to the might of Angmar's army, but they shall soon learn that they face a relentless foe.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1898,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Sergeant-at-Arms' Patches",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Chieftain Durulkum",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSergeant-at-Arms lead small numbers of Men, Elves and Dwarfs throughout the Ettenmoors.\nChieftain Durulkum directed you to obtain sergeants' patches before returning to him at Dâr-gazag.\n* Return the patches to Chieftain Durulkum at Dâr-gazag ()\n* Turn in Sergeant's Patch",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2331},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="An Uruk in the service of the White Hand has appeared in the goblin-camp at Gazatmur. Clearly, he plans to subdue the goblins to his will and drive them against the Dwarves of Dolven-view in great numbers.",selectoneof={{val="Tracker's Leggings",id="70017CF3"},{val="Slagvi's Hat",id="7001606F"},{val="Belegron",id="700160F6"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1899,scope="n/a",prev={1014},name="Servant of the White Hand",arcs="Goblins of the Great Delving",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Slagvi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe White-Hand Lieutenant can be found in Gazatmur, north-east of the Dolven-view.\n* Defeat the White Hand Lieutenant\nObj 2:\nSlagvi is at the Dolven-view camp overlooking the Great Delving, south-west of the goblin-camp.\nYou should return to Slagvi and inform him that the White Hand Lieutenant has fallen.\n* Talk to Slagvi at the Dolven-view encampment."},
{["next"]={592,2027,952,641},area="Lich Bluffs",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="A large pack of Cun Annun haunt the barrows of the Lich Bluffs, presenting a danger to those that would call Enedwaith home.",mobs={{locations={"70.57S, 15.46W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1900,scope="n/a",name="Servants of the Master",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCun Annun can be found in the southern reaches of the Lichbluffs.\nMincham has asked you to find and defeat as many Cun Annun as you are able.\n* Defeat Cun Annun (10)\nObj 2:\nMincham's camp is south and slightly east of the large Gondorian ruins in the Lich Bluffs.\nYou should return to Mincham and let him know that you have located and dispatched a pack of Cun Annun.\n* Talk to Mincham in the Lich Bluffs"},
{area="Lugazag",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Enemies assail the walls of Lugazag often. Trolls are clumsy and strong and often throw enemy soldiers through walls, shattering the stone therein and making holes in the stonework that must be repaired. Fortunately, trolls are also dumb and turn to stone in the sunlight.",category="Lugazag",id=1901,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Set in Stone",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Gazlup",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSoldier Gazlup is at Lugazag.\nSoldier Gazlup directed you to collect troll-stone to repair the damage the trolls delivered to the walls of Lugazag.\n* Return to Gazlup at Lugazag ()\n* Turn in Fragment of Troll Stone\n* Turn in Slab of Troll Stone",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="The Grand Stair",zone="Moria",d="The White Hand Orc-leader, Drâgh, can be found in the Grand Stair of Moria, bringing terror wherever he roams. A dwarf of the expedition was killed, and you have been asked by Armbeald to avenge the innocent by felling this evil foe.",category="Hunter",id=1902,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2097},name="Set the Trap",arcs="The Path of the Trapper",receive={{val="Ring of the Grove",id=70018384},{val="Khuzdul Tablets",id="70017AC6"}},level=58,pois={{locations={"72.06N, 138.11W"},name="Rotted Corpse"}},minlevel=58,b="Armbeald",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDrâgh can be found at the Grand Stair, east from the Redhorn Lodes and south from the Shadowed Refuge in the Foundations of Stone.\nYou should defeat Drâgh at the Grand Stair to prevent his further interference with the dwarf expedition in Moria.\n* Use Rotted Corpse\n* Defeat Drâgh\nObj 2:\nArmbeald can be found at the Orc-Watch in north-west of the Redhorn Lodes.\nYou should return to Armbeald and tell him that Drâgh has been defeated through the efforts of you and your friends.\n* Retun to Armbeald at the Redhorn Lodes\n* Turn in Effigy"},
{["next"]={2534},area="Bullroarer's Sward",zone="Evendim",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="You have collected the bait Hal Gamgee suggested you use to draw out the wolf-leader.",mobs={{locations={"23.03S, 67.24W"},name="Hal Gamgee"}},selectoneof={{val="Sam's Kitchen Knife",id="7000A2FD"},{val="Strange Flowers",id="7000A303"},{val="Hal's Old Hunting Bow",id="7000A2FE"}},category="Evendim",id=1903,scope="n/a",prev={577},name="Setting the Trap",arcs="Farmer's Bane",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,pois={{locations={"21.78S, 67.03W"},name="Rock"}},minlevel=25,b="Hal Gamgee",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe wolf camp can be found north-east of Oatbarton.\nNow that you have brought him the elk-meat, Hal Gamgee suggests that it is time to lay the trap for the big wolf by placing the meat outside of the wolf's cave.\n* Use Rock\n* Kill 1 Bonefang\nObj 2:\nHal Gamgee is in Oatbarton centre.\nYou should return to Hal Gamgee with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Hal Gamgee\n* Turn in Elk-meat"},
{["next"]={1166,311,2369,1355},area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="You have weakened the Orcs of Ashúrz Maufulug by disarming their traps, leaving them vulnerable to attack.",mobs={{locations={"16.50S, 60.30W"},name="Glamodúd"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1904,scope="n/a",prev={2059},name="Severing the Sword-arm",destinypoints={{val=500}},arcs="Breaking the Pincer",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Glamodúd",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMorsharpat is at Ashúrz Maufulug, south and a little west from Echad Glamodúd.\nGlamodúd has asked you to defeat Morsharpat, the captain of the Orcs at Ashúrz Maufulug.\n* Defeat Morsharpat at Ashúrz Maufulug\nObj 2:\nGlamodúd is at Echad Glamodúd, north and a little east from Ashúrz Maufulug.\nYou should return to Glamodúd with news of your victory against Morsharpat.\n* Talk to Glamodúd at Echad Glamodúd"},
{["next"]={769},area="Annunlos",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 40c"}},d="In the shadow of Amon Sûl, at the edge of Nain Enidh, lay an Arnorian ruin. Those ruins afforded the Eglain of Ost Guruth a wealth of material to trade with collectors in Bree-land...until the arrival of half-breeds from the South.",mobs={{locations={"34.38S, 36.91W"},name="Hunulf Munce"}},selectoneof={{val="Quicksilver's Gloves",id=70003226},{val="Quicksilver's Shoulder Pads",id=70003179}},category="Lone-lands",id=1905,scope="n/a",prev={1614},name="Sever the White Hand",arcs="The Eglain - People of the Lone-lands",receive={{val="Sword of the Forsaken Lands",id="70006BB9"}},level=25,minlevel=20,b="Hunulf Munce",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNaerost lies just east of Weathertop, north of Hunulf Munce.\nHunulf Munce is concerned that the half-orcs are servants of a greater power, perhaps even Mordor. He has asked you to enter Naerost and defeat their leader and his guards in hopes that the rest will flee.\n* Defeat Hontimûrz\n* Defeat Hontimûrz guards\nObj 2:\nHunulf Munce awaits your return at his camp on the east side of Minas Eriol, south of Naerost.\nThough the half-orcs did not flee, their leader and his guards have been defeated. You should return to Hunulf Munce with the news.\n* Talk to Hunulf Munce"},
{["next"]={1867},area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Your discovery supports what Grimbriar's spy has been telling him. Grimbriar has arranged an exchange of important papers.",mobs={{locations={"28.16S, 53.33W"},name="Chief Watcher Grimbriar"}},selectoneof={{val="Saeradan's Bow (Level 14)",id=70000774},{val="Saeradan's Iron Bracelet",id=70000776},{val="Saeradan's Leggings",id=70000775}},category="Bree-land",id=1906,scope="n/a",prev={1973},name="Shadow of the White Hand",arcs="The Baying of Wolves",level=14,minlevel=10,b="Chief Watcher Grimbriar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGrimbriar's spy will meet you by a grey rock in a stand of trees, north of Bree-town.\nGrimbriar has sent you to meet a spy he insinuated into the ranks of the brigands in hopes that he will reveal information about Sharkey and his plans.\n* Meet Grimbriar's spy\nObj 2:\nWatcher Grimbriar can be found at the stone house near the crossroads outside of Bree.\nThe spy's notes further supported the brigand's letter, verifying that Sharkey is no brigand himself, but an influential man of the south. Grimbriar must know.\n* Talk to Chief Watcher Grimbriar\n* Turn in Informer's Notes"},
{["next"]={1964},area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+1200 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Uch-lûth goatherd Grufudh accepted the gift of the Rangers, but he still does not trust you.",mobs={{locations={"61.83S, 14.12W"},name="Grufudh"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1907,scope="n/a",prev={274},name="Shadows of Fear",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Grufudh",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goat-herds graze the land to the west of Gavar Cadlus.\nGrufudh asked you to investigate the evil shadows he and his fellow goatherds saw among their herds.\n* Kill 1 Druggavar\nObj 2:\nDruggavar have appeared among the herds of the Uch-lûth, west of Gavar Cadlus.\nGrufudh asked you to find a way to banish the Druggavar from their lands.\n* Defeat Druggavar in the Windfells (3)\nObj 3:\nGrufudh is at Gavar Cadlus in the Windfells of Enedwaith, east of the goat-herd.\n* Talk to Grufudh at Gavar Cadlus"},
{area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+1200 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Impressed by your apparent power over the evil Druggavar of Enedwaith, the Uch-lûth seek your aid once more.",mobs={{locations={"61.85S, 14.12W"},name="Iuan"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1908,scope="n/a",prev={1963},name="Shadows of Fear -- Repeatable",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Iuan",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDruggavar haunt the lands to the west of Gavar Cadlus.\nIuan has asked you to hunt down and banish the Druggavar of Enedwaith.\n* Defeat Druggavar or wolves in the Windfells (3)\nObj 2:\nIuan is at Gavar Cadlus in the Windfells of Enedwaith, east of the goat-herd.\nYou should return to Iuan with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Iuan at Gavar Cadlus"},
{area="Grimwood Lumber Camp",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Arrows are a commodity that will eventually run out and while bone and metal can be used to fashion the arrow-heads, only the straightest of branches can be used for the shaft.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1909,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Shafts for Arrows",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="First Marshal Núrdram",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSmall branches can be found scattered on the ground and on the Leafcull-trees throughout the Grimwood.\nFirst Marshal Núrdram asked you to search along the Grimwood and Hithlad for small branches that might be turned into arrowshafts.\n* Return to First Marshal Núrdram at the Grimwood Lumber-yard\n* Turn in Grimwood-kindling",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1014},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="The goblins have built a series of platforms from which their archers can rain arrows upon any attackers bold enough to confront them.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1910,scope="n/a",prev={1917},name="Shaky Foundations",arcs="Goblins of the Great Delving",level=52,pois={{locations={"7.91S, 111.64W","7.67S, 111.51W","7.51S, 111.69W","7.82S, 111.83W"},name="Support-post"}},minlevel=47,b="Slagvi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblin-platforms are just north-east of the Dolven-view.\nSlagvi has asked you to bring down a few of the goblin's archer-platforms with a simple hammer.\n* Use Support-post\nObj 2:\nSlagvi is at the Dolven-view in the Great Delving.\nYou should return to Slagvi and let him know that you have destroyed the goblin archer-platforms as he requested.\n* Talk to Slagvi\n* Turn in Sturdy Hammer"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Northern Emyn Uial",money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="The even-rills are a series of pools and waterfalls meltwater from Forochel run through before entering the lake of Evendim.",mobs={{locations={"6.05S, 72.01W"},name="Lithuifin"}},category="Evendim",id=1911,scope="n/a",name="Shaman from the North",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=36,minlevel=31,b="Lithuifin",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Even-rills are north-east of the Eavespires.\nLithuifin asked you to head to the Even-rills and defeat the Gauradan there.\n* Defeat Gauradan at the Even-rills (8)\nObj 2:\nLithuifin is at the Eavespires, south-west of the Even-rills.\nLithuifin will want to hear the Guaradan have been driven out of the Even-rills.\n* Talk to Lithuifin",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={930},area="Cirin-en-Galadh",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Thavronwë, a statue-carver currently at Cerin Amroth in search of inspiration, would like you to help him create a stockpile of stone and wood for him and his fellow carvers.",mobs={{locations={"11.89S, 67.78W"},name="Thavronwë"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1912,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Shapes from Shapelessness",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,pois={{locations={"12.63S, 63.03W","12.84S, 63.17W","12.79S, 62.84W","12.98S, 62.69W","12.72S, 62.62W","12.79S, 63.35W","12.76S, 62.41W","12.53S, 62.68W"},name="Stone (Level 1)"},{locations={"10.40S, 63.63W","10.23S, 63.75W","10.03S, 64.11W","10.38S, 64.34W","10.21S, 64.21W","10.66S, 63.78W","10.66S, 64.15W","10.03S, 63.82W","10.58S, 64.34W","10.71S, 63.98W"},name="Birch-wood (Level 1)"}},minlevel=55,b="Thavronwë",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThavronwë has asked that you gather stone and wood for him.\nThere is a high concentration of birch east and north of Cerin Amroth, in the grove of Cerin Brethil. Stone can be found to the east, in Gworast on the banks of the Anduin.\n* Use Birch-wood (Level 1)\n* Use Stone (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nThavronwë is atop the flet in Cerin Amroth.\nYou should return to Thavronwë and give him the raw materials you fetched for him.\n* Return to Thavronwë\n* Turn in Birch-wood\n* Turn in Stone"},
{area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Tûm, the Derudh elder, believes that the essence of the wild spirits which roam the southern reaches of the Mournshaws may be they key to a ritual that will open the way to the Huntsman's Hall.",mobs={{locations={"69.17S, 22.35W"},name="Tûm"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1913,scope="n/a",prev={1854},name="Shards of Light",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Tûm",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe wild spirits known as Elhudan can be found throughout the Mournshaws.\nTûm has asked you to gather the essence of the Elhudan that haunt the Mournshaws.\n* Turn in Wild Essence\nObj 2:\nTûm is at Gwaed Brun at the heart of the Mournshaws.\nYou should return to Tûm with the essence you have procured.\n* Talk to Tûm\n* Turn in Wild Essence"},
{["next"]={1333},d="Winiel was unable to translate the texts you brought to her.",category="Lore-master",id=1914,scope="n/a",prev={357},name="Share the Power",arcs="The Path of the Ancient Master",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Winiel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMirwen is in Elrond's Library at the Last Homely House in Rivendell, far to the north of Moria.\nWiniel has asked you to take the fragments to an Elf named Mirwen.\n* Talk to Mirwen\n* Turn in Scrap of Parchment",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1971,1501},area="Buckland",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="The hobbit Trumric Ragwort is pleased with all the help he has received in Buckland thus far, but the materials that he and his companions have collected for Adso's inn exceeded expectations. He has asked you to secure waggon travel to Adso's camp.",mobs={{locations={"32.81S, 61.57W"},name="Toly Brockhouse"},{locations={"31.56S, 62.55W"},name="Trumric Ragwort"}},category="Bree-land",id=1915,scope="n/a",prev={2371,2745,111},name="Sharing the Load",arcs="A Right Proper Place",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Trumric Ragwort",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nToly Brockhouse can be found outside the stable near Brandy Hall.\nTrumric Ragwort asked you to seek a waggon from Toly Brockhouse to help transport all the goods that he and his fellows have collected since arriving in Buckland.\n* Talk to Toly Brockhouse in Buckland\nObj 2:\nTrumric Ragwort is awaiting your return in Newbury, just inside the gates of Buckland.\nToly Brockhouse seemed concerned with events in the Old Forest, but was amenable to lending Trumric Ragwort the waggon for his journey to Adso's camp.\n* Talk to Trumric Ragwort in Newbury"},
{["next"]={1191},area="Andrath",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="2s 15c"}},d="Sharkey's Men and their half-orc allies from the South have blockaded the Vale of Andrath, inhibiting trade with the southern nations.",category="Bree-land",id=1916,scope="n/a",prev={2618},name="Sharkey's Lieutenant",arcs="The Baying of Wolves",level=16,minlevel=11,b="Watcher Brittleleaf",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSharkey's Lieutenant can be found at his perch, high and far to the south-west, within the Southwatch.\nWatcher Brittleleaf wants to see the leader of the forces at the Southwatch slain.\n* Defeat Sharkey's Lieutenant at the Southwatch\nObj 2:\nWatcher Brittleleaf awaits your return to the east of the northern entrance of the ruins.\nYou hunted down and defeated Sharkey's Lieutenant, but the brigands and half-orcs seemed unaffected by his defeat.\n* Talk to Watcher Brittleleaf"},
{["next"]={1962},area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Chief Grimbriar wants you to investigate the brigands of the Bree-fields, who have become better organized and more dangerous of late.",mobs={{locations={"28.16S, 53.33W"},name="Chief Watcher Grimbriar"}},category="Bree-land",id=1917,scope="n/a",name="Sharkey's Men",arcs="The Baying of Wolves",level=14,minlevel=10,b="Chief Watcher Grimbriar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBrigands have overrun Dogwood's Farm, across the road and north alongside a small stream. Chief Grimbriar awaits your return at the stone house near the crossroads outside of Bree.\nChief Watcher Grimbriar has asked you to investigate the increased brigand activity. He mentioned a small farm across the road and a few paces north he thought was overrun.\n* Bring the brigand medallion to Chief Watcher Grimbriar\n* Turn in Brigand Medallion"},
{["next"]={2391,2618},area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Sharkey's Men have holed up in a camp they call the Brigands' Watch. Grimbriar wants you to go there and gather information about Sharkey and his plans.",mobs={{locations={"28.16S, 53.33W"},name="Chief Watcher Grimbriar"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Lesser Athelas Essence",id="70000D5D"},{val="Saeradan's Shoulder Guards",id=70000779}},category="Bree-land",id=1918,scope="n/a",prev={1867},name="Sharkey's Plan",arcs="The Baying of Wolves",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Chief Watcher Grimbriar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Brigands' Watch sits on a hill north of Adso's camp, and directly west of Grimbriar's Post. Watcher Grimbriar is at his post near the crossroads of Bree.\nGrimbriar has instructed you to search the tent of the brigand-captain at the Brigands' Watch to find any correspondence from Sharkey that may divulge information about his plans.\n* Bring the letter to Chief Watcher Grimbriar\n* Turn in Stained Letter"},
{["next"]={2723,932,594,249,1311},area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Uxi fears for a wonderful statue of Helgi Goblinbane, a dwarf of great renown once, whose name resonates among the goblins the way Azog's does among the dwarves.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1919,scope="n/a",name="Shattered",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Uxi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe statue base is in the courtyard hall just to the south-east of Uxi.\nUxi told you to examine the statue base so that you will be able to recognize its other pieces.\n* Examine the statue\nObj 2:\nUxi is at the Chamber of the Crossroads, north-west of the statue.\nYou should return to Uxi for more instruction.\n* Talk to Uxi at the Chamber of the Crossroads",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1187},area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Vatnar the dwarf has seen the Orcs of northern Gathbúrz moving catapults into position to attack Thangúlhad.",mobs={{locations={"12.60S, 46.51W"},name="Vatnar"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1920,scope="n/a",name="Shattered Engines",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"10.90S, 46.50W","11.83S, 46.63W","12.00S, 46.66W","10.99S, 46.39W","12.14S, 46.65W","11.19S, 46.50W"},name="Orc-catapult"}},minlevel=60,b="Vatnar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrkish catapults can be found throughout northern Gathbúrz.\nVatnar has asked you to destroy several Orkish catapults.\n* Use Orc-catapult\nObj 2:\nVatnar is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nYou should return to Vatnar with tidings of your success.\n* Talk to Vatnar in Thangúlhad"},
{["next"]={488},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="A great host of Orcs spilled through Ram Dúath, driving the Men of the North Downs from their farms. Esteldín, home of the few remaining Dúnedain of the North, was spared discovery. It is from there that the Rangers begin to plan their counter-offensive against the black tide of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.63S, 41.42W"},name="Arohir"}},category="North Downs",id=1921,scope="n/a",prev={2302},name="Shattering the Alliance",arcs="Shattering the Alliance",level=32,minlevel=27,b="Arohir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOngbúrz Skirmishers can be found among the goblins who patrol the outskirts of the Orc-host in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\nArohir told you about the Orc-host in Dol Dínen, and the goblins they use to guard the outskirts of their encampment. He also mentioned that skirmishers of the Ongbúrz tribe were seen among the goblins and has asked you to slay them in hopes that the deaths of the powerful Ongbúrz Skirmishers might break the will of the goblins.\n* Return the Ongbúrz badges to Arohir\n* Turn in Ongbúrz-insignia"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Angmar seeks to reinforce Tol Ascarnen, employing the assistance of goblin-archers, who hide behind the walls and launch deadly attacks at the Free Peoples foolish enough to enter the tunnel leading to the inner courtyard.",category="Tol Ascarnen",id=1922,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Shatter Their Blades",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Glat",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Free Peoples carry weapons from which the blades can be taken and used to craft crossbow bolts. The Free Peoples can be found at any of the locations they control, including the encampment south of Tol Ascarnen.\nIn an effort to better fortify Tol Ascarnen, the War-tyrant has called to the goblins at Grothum and told his soldiers to craft bolts for the goblins to shoot into the tunnel at the mouth of the keep. Glat has left the task of obtaining the blades of the Free Peoples to you.\n* Deliver the shattered blades to Soldier Glat ( )\n* Turn in Shattered Blade",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+900 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Danger lurks within Barad Gúlaran and Uidon, an Elf dispatched to the north to support those sent there by the Council of Esteldín, wishes to examine the armour worn by the fell spirits within the citadel. You must smite the defenders and warriors within Barad Gúlaran to obtain the armour.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Uidon"}},category="Barad Gúlaran",id=1923,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2906},name="Sheathed in Ancient Iron",receive={{val="Ancient Iron Token",id="7000A304"}},level=50,minlevel=45,b="Uidon",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAncient armour wreathes terrifying creatures within Barad Gúlaran. Collect these items and return them to Uidon at the encampment in the northeastern area of Angmar.\nUidon asked you to obtain samples of the armour worn by the defenders within Barad Gúlaran so he might learn a weakness to better defeat them. Make your way into Barad Gúlaran, with the assistance of others and collect the samples.\n* Return to Uidon\n* Turn in Fragment of Ancient Armour"},
{area="Greenfields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="2s"}},d="Mungo Burrows has lost his prized ewe and believes she has been stolen by goblins.",mobs={{locations={"24.80S, 67.38W"},name="Mungo Burrows"}},category="Shire",id=1924,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Sheep Theft",receive={{val="Fried Mushrooms",id="700005F6"},{val="Mushroom Pie",id="700005F3"},{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"},{val="Mungo's Old Bracelet",id="700033CF"}},level=13,minlevel=9,b="Mungo Burrows",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMungo's prized ewe is being held captive in the goblin-camp in the north-east corner of the Greenfields.\nMungo Burrows has asked you to fight your way into a goblin-camp and bring his stolen sheep safely outside. He suggested that you bring friends, or you may end up the goblins' next meal.\n* Find Mungo's stolen sheep\nObj 2:\nMungo Burrows is outside the goblin camp in the north-east corner of the Greenfields.\nMungo is delighted that you brought his sheep safely from the camp of goblins who stole her and wants to speak with you at once.\n* Talk to Mungo Burrows"},
{["next"]={409},area="Northern Barrow-downs",zone="Bree-land",d="A shade found wandering in the Barrow-downs -- meaning no ill, it seems -- felt the pull of its brother and struggles to appease whatever force has returned to awaken them.",mobs={{locations={"31.65S, 55.22W"},name="Wandering Shade"}},category="Bree-land",id=1925,scope="n/a",prev={150},name="Shield-brother",arcs="Shield-brother",level=19,minlevel=14,b="Wandering Shade",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDead rise near a south facing wall among burial mounds of Men.\nThe shade, in its cryptic way, asked you for assistance in ridding the place where he died of the fell barrow-wights.\n* Defeat wights near the place where the brothers placed the Cardolan treasure (6)\nObj 2:\nThe Wandering Shade is in the northern Barrow-downs.\nYou found wights, risen from their graves, and defeated them at the pass leading to the southern Barrow-downs.\n* Talk to the Wandering Shade in the northern Barrow-downs",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={371},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Belco Brockhouse found a copy of the Founding Writ of the Shire, but will not give it up until he has received some services in return.",mobs={{locations={"32.81S, 70.95W"},name="Belco Brockhouse"}},category="Shire",id=1926,scope="n/a",prev={2398},name="Shore Up the Fence",arcs="The Founding Writ",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=9,pois={{locations={"33.23S, 69.65W","33.72S, 70.35W","33.69S, 69.77W","33.66S, 69.96W","33.95S, 70.49W","33.96S, 70.42W","33.94S, 69.49W","33.37S, 70.03W","33.67S, 70.51W","33.31S, 69.36W","33.86S, 69.79W","33.93S, 69.84W","33.84S, 70.03W","33.50S, 70.39W","33.72S, 69.66W","33.63S, 69.74W","33.66S, 70.14W","33.50S, 70.29W","33.46S, 70.03W","33.88S, 69.46W"},name="Small Field-stone"},{locations={"33.78S, 70.50W","33.72S, 69.93W","33.95S, 70.20W","33.64S, 69.80W","33.72S, 70.42W","33.56S, 70.16W","33.28S, 69.73W","33.32S, 70.18W","33.58S, 70.30W","33.96S, 69.97W","33.47S, 70.54W","33.35S, 70.28W","33.83S, 70.61W","33.95S, 69.45W","33.85S, 69.85W","33.38S, 69.91W","33.64S, 69.29W","33.71S, 69.38W","33.68S, 70.63W","33.48S, 69.99W"},name="Flat Field-stone"},{locations={"33.70S, 69.84W","33.55S, 70.11W","33.79S, 70.63W","33.90S, 69.74W","33.52S, 69.32W","33.36S, 70.09W","33.86S, 69.50W","33.39S, 70.47W","33.47S, 70.23W","33.23S, 69.78W","33.62S, 70.62W","33.60S, 69.91W","33.41S, 69.40W","33.65S, 69.45W","33.59S, 70.02W","33.80S, 70.34W","33.68S, 69.65W","33.96S, 69.51W","33.58S, 70.51W","33.95S, 70.05W"},name="Large Field-stone"}},minlevel=5,b="Belco Brockhouse",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nField stones can be found south of Longo Burrow's farm near the big willow. Belco lives north-west of the willow, on the upper slopes of Tuckborough.\nBelco Brockhouse's fences need mending, and he has asked you to gather stones from the field for him to use in patching them.\n* Bring field stones to Belco Brockhouse\n* Collect flat field-stones (3 Flat Field-stone )\n* Collect small field-stones (4 Small Field-stone )\n* Collect large field-stones (2 Large Field-stone )"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Annúminas",money={{val="42s"}},d="The Angmarim use the rubble to hide behind when they attack, making it difficult for the Rangers to drive them off.",category="Evendim",id=1927,scope="n/a",name="Shoring up the Defenses",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,pois={{locations={"19.24S, 70.17W","19.11S, 70.52W","19.31S, 70.29W","19.26S, 70.38W","19.18S, 70.40W","19.32S, 70.40W","19.23S, 70.33W","19.31S, 70.10W"},name="Rubble"}},minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe rubble is just to the east of Echad Garthadir.\n* Gather up the rubble (6 Rubble )\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë may have a use for the rubble.\n* Turn in Rubble",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="The tranquility and protection of Duillond, the Elf-refuge, does not reach so far north as Haudh Lin and foul creatures have begun to creep into that place of peace.",mobs={{locations={"18.95S, 95.24W"},name="Laergil"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1928,scope="n/a",name="Sickening of the Land",arcs="Sickening of the Land",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Blueberry Muffins",id="7000335C"},{val="Bronweolf",id="7000929C"}},level=12,minlevel=8,b="Laergil",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpiders infest north-eastern Haudh Lin, far beyond Duillond.\nLaergil has asked you to kill off as many spiders as you are able.\n* Defeat spiders in Eastern Haudh Lin (12)\nObj 2:\nLaergil waits in north-western Haudh Lin.\nYou should return to Laergil and report your success.\n* Talk to Laergil",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="30s 80c"}},d="A great host of Orcs spilled through Ram Dúath, driving the Men of the North Downs from their farms. Esteldín, home of the few remaining Dúnedain of the North, was spared discovery. It is from there that the Rangers begin to plan their counter-offensive against the black tide of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.49S, 42.11W"},name="Hithlim"}},selectoneof={{val="Hithlim's Mace",id="70006BA4"},{val="Hithlim's Bow",id="70006B6B"}},category="North Downs",id=1929,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1436},name="Siegecraft",level=34,pois={{locations={"15.21S, 38.34W","15.95S, 38.24W","15.31S, 38.49W","16.12S, 38.76W","15.92S, 38.95W","16.08S, 38.05W"},name="Ballista"},{locations={"15.56S, 38.88W","16.14S, 39.11W","15.19S, 37.40W","16.36S, 38.74W","15.09S, 38.59W"},name="Trebuchet"},{locations={"15.81S, 38.60W","14.93S, 36.87W","15.95S, 38.08W","16.18S, 38.48W","16.18S, 38.60W"},name="Catapult"}},minlevel=29,b="Hithlim",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCatapults, trebuchets, and ballistae can be found on the hills and high ground deep within the Orc-encampment in Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\nThough you have slain several of the trolls who transport and maintain the Orcs' siege-engines, the weapons themselves still remain. Hithlim has asked you to gather allies and disable or destroy the catapults, trebuchets, and ballistae.\n* Use Ballista\n* Use Catapult\n* Use Trebuchet\nObj 2:\nHithlim awaits your return at Esteldín.\nYou entered Dol Dínen and disabled several of the Orcs' ballistae, catapults, and trebuchets. You should bring news of your success back to Hithlim.\n* Talk to Hithlim\n* Turn in Ballista-lock\n* Turn in Catapult-pinion\n* Turn in Swing-arm Pin"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+1200 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="A large, armoured troll has been seen walking amongst the siege weapons overlooking the approach to the hills in the southernmost reaches of Dol Dínen. The Ranger Hithlim believes that this great brute leads the trolls who maintain the siege-weapons at Dol Dínen.",mobs={{locations={"9.49S, 42.11W"},name="Hithlim"}},selectoneof={{val="Pakonka's Conqueror",id="70006B9B"},{val="Siege-breaker's Boots",id="70006AAF"},{val="Celegechor",id="700069E3"},{val="Club of the Shire-muster",id="70006BBF"},{val="Ríambadanir",id="70006B47"}},category="North Downs",id=1930,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={3218},name="Siege-master",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Hithlim",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe armoured troll can be found within the shadow of the mountain overlooking the valley of Dol Dínen, far to the south-east of Esteldín.\nHithlim has asked you to gather allies and seek out the armoured captain of the trolls in Dol Dínen. With the death of their captain, the Ranger hopes the trolls will be thrown into disarray.\n* Kill 1 Pakonka, Siege-master\nObj 2:\nHithlim awaits your return at Esteldín.\nYou ventured deep into the heart of the Orc-encampment at Dol Dínen and defeated the troll-siegemaster. You should return to Hithlim with the news of your victory.\n* Talk to Hithlim"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},d="Gondamon is one of the strongest of the fortresses of the Longbeards in the Blue Mountains. The Dourhands and their goblin allies seek to overthrow the stronghold and claim it for themselves.",category="Skirmish",id=1931,scope="n/a",name="Siege of Gondamon -- Daily",level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe defenders of Gondamon have held out for as long as possible. The final assault is looming and they are in dire need of your aid.\n* Complete the Siege of Gondamon skirmish"},
{["next"]={2440},reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Gloomglens",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You found a medallion inscribed in a language with which you are not familiar.",mobs={{locations={"63.48S, 21.45W"},name="Prestadír"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1932,scope="n/a",name="Sigil of the Rhi Helvarch",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sigil of the Rhi Helvarch",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are Rangers at Echad Idhrenfair to the south of where you found the medallion.\nYou should bring the medallion you found to one of the Rangers of the Grey Company.\n* Talk to Prestadír\n* Turn in Sigil of the Rhi Helvarch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="The Corcur falsely claim allegiance to the ancient fallen kingdom of Rhudaur, which allied itself with Angmar before it was destroyed, several centuries ago. These Men wear rings with the insignia of ancient Rhudaur as proof of their allegience to this false kingdom.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Imyl"}},category="Reputation",id=1933,scope="n/a",name="Signets of Rhudaur -- Introduction",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Imyl",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Corcur dwell in the Misty Mountains above the Trollshaws, north-east of Rivendell. Imyl is in Rivendell.\nImyl has asked you to recover the signets of Rhudaur, which the Corcur wear as a symbol of their allegiance to the fallen kingdom of Rhudaur, and bring them to her.\n* Bring signets of Rhudaur to Imyl at Rivendell\n* Turn in Signet of Rhudaur",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="There are many positions throughout Gathbúrz that remain contested by both sides of the conflict in Southern Mirkwood.\nNOTE: This quest will fail on logout, make sure to turn in before you leave the game.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 46.59W"},name="Handelen"},{locations={"12.71S, 46.57W"},name="Rodelleth"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1934,scope="n/a",prev={2301},name="Sign of the Malledhrim",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"11.24S, 45.57W","11.75S, 45.84W","11.53S, 45.36W","11.93S, 44.89W","11.99S, 47.31W"},name="Banner Stones (Level 1)"}},minlevel=60,b="Handelen",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nContested camps can be found in Gathbúrz.\nRodelleth has asked you to place a Malledhrim war-banner at a contested camp.\n* Use Banner Stones (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nDefend the Malledhrim war-banner at the contested camp in Gathburz.\n* Defend the Malledhrim war-banner\nObj 3:\nRodelleth is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nYou should return to Rodelleth with news of your success.\n* Talk to Rodelleth at Thangúlhad"},
{["next"]={2485},area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Near the place called Gwyllion's Gate, you found a banner bearing the symbol of the White Hand.",mobs={{locations={"63.82S, 17.45W"},name="Saeradan"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1935,scope="n/a",name="Sign of the White Hand",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Banner of the White Hand",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSaeradan is at Echad Saeradan, west from Gwyllion's Gate.\nYou should tell Saeradan of the banner you discovered.\n* Talk to Saeradan at Echad Saeradan"},
{area="Nan Laeglin",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Half-orc raiders from the mountains have attacked a number of small farmholds around Nan Laeglin. Guladus Brehures suspects that forces from Isengard may be behind the attacks, but she needs evidence before she dares speak openly of it in council.",mobs={{locations={"66.46S, 17.32W"},name="Guladus Brehures"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1936,scope="n/a",name="Signs Among the Ashes",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Guladus Brehures",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalf-orcs can be found throughout Nan Laeglin, especially where they have raided Uch-lûth farmsteads.\nThere must be some bosses driving the half-orc raiders into Nan Laeglin. It is possible that among them one may be carrying equipment with the sigils of Isengard upon it.\n* Find equipment on Half-orc Bosses (0/2)\nObj 2:\nHalf-orcs can be found throughout Nan Laeglin, especially where they have raided Uch-lûth farmsteads.\nThere must be some bosses driving the half-orc raiders into Nan Laeglin. It is possible that among them one may be carrying equipment with the sigils of Isengard upon it.\n* Turn in Helm of the White Hand\nObj 3:\nHalf-orcs can be found throughout Nan Laeglin, especially where they have raided Uch-lûth farmsteads.\nThere must be some bosses driving the half-orc raiders into Nan Laeglin. It is possible that among them one may be carrying equipment with the sigils of Isengard upon it.\n* Find equipment on Half-orc Bosses (1/2)\nObj 4:\nHalf-orcs can be found throughout Nan Laeglin, especially where they have raided Uch-lûth farmsteads.\nThere must be some leaders driving the half-orc raiders into Nan Laeglin. It is possible that among them one may be carrying equipment with the sigils of Isengard upon it.\n* Turn in Sword of the White Hand\nObj 5:\nGuladus Brehures is at the Brenin's Hall in Lhanuch.\nHaving found gear bearing the sign of the White Hand upon the half-orcs raiding Nan Laeglin, you may return to Guladus Brehures with the evidence she needs to speak out against Isengard in the Council of Brehur.\n* Talk to Guladus Brehures\n* Turn in Helm of the White Hand\n* Turn in Sword of the White Hand",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1147},area="Northern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="3s 20c"}},d="Rangers, watching movements of enemies from the north and south, are concerned over the appearance of a foe they have long fought in the north.",mobs={{locations={"23.74S, 53.55W"},name="Andreg"}},category="Bree-land",id=1937,scope="n/a",prev={1513},name="Signs of Struggle",arcs="My Brethren's Call",level=18,minlevel=13,b="Andreg",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs can be found along the eastern border of the Greenway, north of the Old Greenway Fort. Andreg awaits your return at his post near the Old Greenway Fort.\nAndreg has asked you to search the Orcs along the Greenway's eastern borders for signs of a struggle against the Men of the North Downs. Though the Rangers hope that the Orcs have not attacked the Men of the North Downs, they wish to investigate and ensure that this is not the case.\n* Deliver the cloth strips to Andreg at the Old Greenway Fort\n* Turn in Blood-stained Cloth"},
{["next"]={1851},area="Nanduhirion",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+300 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s"}},d="The Warg-riders of the Dimrill Dale have been harassing the dwarf-encampment at Mekhem-bizru since it was first established.",selectoneof={{val="Cloak of Subtlety",id="70017CEC"},{val="Warg's Fall",id=70016413}},category="Moria",id=1938,scope="n/a",name="Silence of the Wargs",arcs="Riders in the Dale",level=59,minlevel=54,b="Ótam",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWargs can be found at Athmadhul, south-east of Mekhem-bizru.\nÓtam wants you to thin the numbers of the Wargs so there will be fewer Warg-riders to trouble the dwarves.\n* Defeat Wargs at Athmadhul (10)\nObj 2:\nÓtam is at Mekhem-bizru, north-west of Athmadhul.\nÓtam will be pleased to hear that the Wargs around Athmadhul have been thinned.\n* Talk to Ótam at Mekhem-bizru"},
{["next"]={1502},area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="There are two small encampments that the Draig-lûth established. These men are dangerous and prey upon the Uch-lûth.",mobs={{locations={"67.43S, 13.92W"},name="Gronu"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1939,scope="n/a",name="Silence the Sentries",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Gronu",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Draig-lûth camps are east and north-east of Harndirion.\nGronu has asked you to seek out Pruv Cadlus and Sarf Cadlus on the eastern slope below Harndirion and defeat sentries at each of the camps.\n* Discover Pruv Cadlus\n* Defeat sentries near Pruv Cadlus\n* Discover Sarf Cadlus\n* Defeat sentries near Sarf Cadlus\nObj 2:\nGronu's camp lies almost due north of Harndirion.\nYou should return to Gronu and let him know that you have defeated many of the sentries near Pruv Cadlus and Sarf Cadlus.\n* Talk to Gronu at his camp"},
{["next"]={301,2461},area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Niko, the Master of the Hunt, doubts you have the ability to move silently and not scare off game, let alone hunt well.",mobs={{locations={"7.49N, 75.45W"},name="Niko"}},category="Forochel",id=1940,scope="n/a",name="Silent Feet",arcs="Hunting: Serious Business",level=44,pois={{locations={"5.27N, 75.65W","10.05N, 74.85W","5.89N, 75.91W","5.25N, 76.23W","5.60N, 76.00W","10.78N, 74.87W","10.39N, 75.38W","10.58N, 75.16W","10.35N, 74.85W","5.71N, 76.33W","10.10N, 75.31W"},name="Gauradan Trap"}},minlevel=39,b="Niko",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe aurochs-herds are to the north and to the south and south-west of Jänis-leiri.\nNiko instructed you to find and disable some of the Gauredain's traps to protect the aurochs-herds.\n* Use Gauradan Trap\nObj 2:\nNiko is at Jänis-leiri, northward of the aurochs-herds, near the road.\nYou should return to Niko and tell him of your success.\n* Talk to Niko"},
{["next"]={29,1212},area="The Scuttledells",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="One of the Malledhrim scouts reported a goblin-like creature out in the ravines, not unlike the creature Gollum.",mobs={{locations={"12.45S, 50.88W","8.72S, 52.22W"},name="Miluimil"}},category="Mirkwood",id=1941,scope="n/a",prev={3241,803},name="Silent Footsteps",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=64,minlevel=59,b="Miluimil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGollum might be found at one of several locations suggested by Miluimil.\nMiluimil has asked you to search for any signs of Gollum in the Scuttledells. You should start with the Pool of Tranquility.\n* Search for signs of Gollum at the Pool of Tranquility\nObj 2:\nGollum might be found at one of several locations suggested by Miluimil.\nMiluimil has asked you to search for any signs of Gollum in the Scuttledells. Perhaps you should try the Low Pond.\n* Search for signs of Gollum at the Low Pond\nObj 3:\nGollum might be found at one of several locations suggested by Miluimil.\nMiluimil has asked you to search for any signs of Gollum in the Scuttledells. Perhaps you should try the Crawling Waters.\n* Search for signs of Gollum at the Crawling Waters\nObj 4:\nMiluimil is at Ivorel's camp in the Scuttledells.\nYou should return to Miluimil and tell him what you have learned of Gollum's whereabouts.\n* Talk to Miluimil at Ivorel's camp"},
{["next"]={180},zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The Orcs of Moria are preparing to launch another attack against the forces of Mordor, which could prove detrimental to Isólf's plans.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1942,scope="n/a",prev={1272},name="Silent Surprise",arcs="Orcs of Moria",level=56,pois={{locations={"7.52S, 107.52W","7.65S, 107.56W","7.54S, 107.58W","7.72S, 107.59W","7.42S, 107.58W","7.53S, 107.69W","7.59S, 107.69W","7.62S, 107.52W"},name="Spear-mount"}},minlevel=51,b="Isólf",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe spear pits can be found in the Broad Ways, north of the Orc-watch.\nIsólf has asked you to plant several spears between the camps of the Moria Orcs and the Orcs of Mordor as a trap.\n* Use Spear-mount\n* Turn in Bundle of Spears\nObj 2:\nIsólf is at the Orc-watch, south of the Broad Ways.\nIsólf will be pleased to hear that the spears have been set and the trap is prepared.\n* Talk to Isólf at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Ram Dúath",zone="Angmar",money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="The Earth-kin, rugged, practical, and earthy as they are, make extensive use of silk, which they obtain almost exclusively from spiders.",mobs={{locations={"2.90S, 39.17W"},name="Aarnikka"}},selectoneof={{val="Shiny Metal",id="70006B8B"},{val="Shiny Spike",id="700161C5"}},category="Angmar",id=1943,scope="n/a",name="Silken Strands",level=40,c={"* The Spiders are found along the road just to the east of the Earth-kin camp. They seem to share spawn locations with the Hill-claws, so you may need to defeat some of those to get them to spawn."},minlevel=35,b="Aarnikka",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are spiders throughout Ram Dúath.\nAarnikka has asked you to collect silk from the spiders of the Ram Dúath.\n* Bring the spider-silk to Aarnikka\n* Turn in Skein of Spider-silk",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Cirin-en-Galadh",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Mallendathor wishes you to sing to several Malbrethil-saplings again, to aid in their healthy development, and bring her back some Malbrethril-seeds.",mobs={{locations={"11.85S, 68.08W"},name="Mallendathor"},{locations={"11.98S, 64.86W"},name="Sendiel"},{locations={"11.82S, 68.81W"},name="Orthir"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1944,scope="n/a",prev={381},name="Singing to Saplings",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,c={"* Orthir can be found in Cirin-en-galadh at [11.8S, 68.8W]\n* Saplings can be found at:"},pois={{locations={"10.38S, 63.79W","10.66S, 63.66W","10.34S, 64.10W","10.12S, 64.26W"},name="Malbrethil-sapling"}},minlevel=55,b="Mallendathor",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrthir can be found a short distance west of Cerin Amroth, near the path.\nMallendathor wishes you to speak to Orthir, the Scholar of the Trees, to see if he knows what might heal the saplings' mallady.\n* Talk to Orthir\nObj 2:\nThe Malbrethil-saplings can be found around Cerin Brethil in Taur Hith, to the north-east of Cerin Amroth.\nOrthir believes that the saplings, deprived of the everyday music of the now-wary forest, might be revived if you were to sing to them.\n* Perform /sing\n* Perform /sing\n* Perform /sing\n* Perform /sing\n* Use Malbrethil-sapling\nObj 3:\nMallendathor has asked you to gather Malbrethil-seeds from in the area of Taur Hith, to the north-east of Cerin Amroth. The seeds are difficult to find, but are frequently collected by the hungry shrews that scamper about the forest there.\n* Turn in Malbrethil-seed\nObj 4:\nSendiel is in Gelirdor, south-west of the Malbrethil-trees, east of Cerin Amroth.\nOrthir instructed you to tell Sendiel of your success.\n* Talk to Sendiel\n* Turn in Malbrethil-seed"},
{area="Celondim",zone="Ered Luin",d="The hobbits celebrating the Lithe Festival need many fish for their pond. The Elves have granted you permission to catch some off the port of Celondim.",mobs={{locations={"28.17S, 92.12W"},name="Gaellien"}},category="Festival",id=1945,scope="n/a",prev={2077},name="Sitting on the Dock",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Gaellien",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe docks are at Celondim in Ered Luin, far to the west of Bree and the Shire.\nThe docks of Celondim have long been a popular site for Elven Fishermen. They have allowed you some time to catch fish for the hobbits' Lithe Festival.\n* Catch as many fish as you can in twenty minutes",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Zelem-melek",zone="Moria",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="In the Sixteenth Hall, defilers and other Orcs, sworn to some dark power, poison their brethren with a fungal disease. The source of this evil lies far beneath the surface of this stronghold, once inhabited by the dwarves. The dwarves in Moria wish only to drive the Orcs and the evil of the Sixteenth Hall away from their former realm.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1946,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Sixteenth Hall -- Purge the Halls",level=60,minlevel=60,b="Geirr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGlobsnaga spread their poison in the Sixteenth Hall, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall whence you came.\nYou have been asked to slay as many Globsnaga as you can to ensure the safety of the dwarves in Moria.\nObj 2:\nGeirr is in the Twenty-first Hall, north-west of the Sixteenth Hall.\nYou should return to Geirr and tell him of your success against the Globsnaga, for he wishes to see if you are as sturdy a warrior as rumour has assured.\n* Return to Geirr at the Twenty-first Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Zelem-melek",zone="Moria",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="In the Sixteenth Hall, defilers and other Orcs, sworn to some dark power, poison their brethren with a fungal disease. The source of this evil lies far beneath the surface of this stronghold, once inhabited by the dwarves. The dwarves in Moria wish only to drive the Orcs and the evil of the Sixteenth Hall away from their former realm.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1947,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=750}},name="Sixteenth Hall -- The Lost One's Flesh",level=60,minlevel=60,b="Eilíefr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Lost One is below the Sixteenth Hall, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall where Eilíefr stands.\nYou have been challenged to prove your great worth by defeating the Lost One and returning with its hide as a trophy of your victory.\n* Return the hide to Eilíefr at the Twenty-first Hall\n* Turn in The Lost One's Hide",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Carn Dûm",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+900 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="49s"}},d="You obtained some weapons from the Enemy at Urugarth, which Throst the dwarf plans to re-forge for the Rangers' use.",mobs={{locations={"12.38N, 31.80W"},name="Odbjórn"}},selectoneof={{val="Lâmkarn's Hide",id=70002585},{val="Lainthol",id=70002586},{val="Ancient Arrowhead",id=70002587}},category="Urugarth",id=1948,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2370},name="Skinning the Beasts",arcs="Skinning Beasts",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Odbjórn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWargs can be found at Urugarth, west of Tármunn Súrsa. Odbjorn is at Tármunn Súrsa.\nOdbjórn requires Warg hides to craft new armour for the resistance. You should take several hides, as well as the hide of the Warg-leader, and return them to Odbjórn.\n* Bring the Warg-hides to Odbjórn\n* Turn in White Warg-hide\n* Turn in Rugged Warg-hide"},
{area="The Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="With the revelation that Mazog is supporting the goblins in the Silvertine Lodes, Thalfar is worried about the dwarves' ability to defend the miners and support their position. He can't afford to launch a true offensive against the goblins, but wants to keep them off balance.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1949,scope="n/a",prev={2478},name="Skirmishers to the Fore",arcs="Banding Together",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Thalfar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblins can be found in the Silvertine Lodes.\nThalfar has asked you to thin the numbers of the goblins in the Silvertine Lodes to keep them off balance and prevent them from mustering a direct attack against the expedition at Deep Descent.\n* Defeat goblins in the Silvertine Lodes (20)\nObj 2:\nThalfar can be found at the Deep Descent expedition at the northern edge of the Silvertine Lodes.\nYou should return to Thalfar and tell him of your battles against the goblins of the Silvertine Lodes.\n* Talk to Thalfar at the Deep Descent"},
{zone="Moria",area="Silvertine Lodes",money={{val="53s 90c"}},d="Crystals have been discovered in Moria, bearing marks of the Forgotten Treasury, a sealed vault hiding a substantial amount of wealth. This discovery has piqued the interest of some dwarves who now wish to uncover the vault and save its contents from the pilfering Orcs.",mobs={{locations={"9.85S, 112.76W"},name="Hafberg"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=1950,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1332},name="Skûm and Urauth",arcs="The Forgotten Treasury",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Hafberg",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSkûm and Urauth were last seen near the Forgotten Treasury, south and south-east of the Deep Descent in Moria.\nHafberg told you of the twin trolls, Skûm and Urauth, alike in every way, and how they terrorize the dwarves in the area. You were asked to defeat them should you find yourself facing them.\n* Defeat Skûm\n* Defeat Urauth\nObj 2:\nHafberg is at the Deep Descent, north and north-west of the Forgotten Treasury.\nAfter a long and difficult battle, you defeated the twin trolls to avenge the dwarves who fell to their cruelty.\n* Return to Hafberg at the Deep Descent",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="No living Man, Elf, halfling, or dwarf will want to set foot in Skûmfil, grave of the Orcs, feeding and breeding ground of vile kergrim and slavering gredbyg. There the Orcs pile their dead, and there disgusting creatures feast on rotten waste.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1951,scope="n/a",name="Skûmfil -- Clearing Corpses",destinypoints={{val=500}},level=60,minlevel=60,b="Geirr",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nKergrim and gredbyg grow strong and wicked among the Orc-corpses of Skûmfil, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nGeirr has challenged you to defeat many of the vile creatures that lurk in Skûmfil as proof of your worth as a warrior. Few are wilful enough to withstand the reek of that horrific place.\nObj 2:\nGeirr awaits tidings at the Twenty-first Hall, north-west of Skûmfil.\nYou have defeated many kergrim and gredbyg in vile Skûmfil, and should now return to show Geirr that you are indeed as valiant as rumours have described. He will be glad to learn that you have proved yourself against the vile threat in the halls of the corpses.\n* Return to Geirr at the Twenty-first Hall"},
{money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="No living Man, Elf, halfling, or dwarf will want to set foot in Skûmfil, grave of the Orcs, feeding and breeding ground of vile kergrim and slavering gredbyg. There the Orcs pile their dead, and there disgusting creatures feast on rotten waste.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1952,scope="n/a",name="Skûmfil - The Grodbog-queen's Chitin",destinypoints={{val=750}},level=60,minlevel=60,b="Eilíefr",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nBrúmbereth grows strong and raises many spawn among the corpses of Orcs in Skûmfil, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall where Elíefr stands.\nElíefr has challenged you to defeat Brúmbereth in Skûmfil as proof of your worth as a warrior. Few are wilful enough to withstand the reek of that horrific place.\n* Return the carapace to Eilíefr at the Twenty-first Hall\n* Turn in Brúmbereth's Carapace"},
{money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="No living Man, Elf, halfling, or dwarf will want to set foot in Skûmfil, grave of the Orcs, feeding and breeding ground of vile kergrim and slavering gredbyg. There the Orcs pile their dead, and there disgusting creatures feast on rotten waste.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1953,scope="n/a",name="Skûmfil - The Kergrim-king's Tooth",destinypoints={{val=750}},level=60,minlevel=60,b="Eilíefr",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nGrimreaver grows strong and leads many minions among the corpses of Orcs in Skûmfil, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall where Elíefr stands.\nElíefr has challenged you to defeat Grimreaver in Skûmfil as proof of your worth as a warrior. Few are wilful enough to withstand the reek of that horrific place.\n* Return the fang to Eilíefr at the Twenty-first Hall\n* Turn in Grimreaver's Fang"},
{area="Arador's End",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Taskmaster Izubuzri communicated that he wants proof that you killed many eagles. Apparently the eagles are too free with where they perch.",category="Isendeep Mine",id=1954,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Slaughtering Eagles",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Taskmaster Izubuzri",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nEagles can be found throughout the Coldfells and in a small section of Arador's End to the south of the Isendeep Mine.\nTaskmaster Izubuzri wants you to return eagle feathers to him to prove that you have slaughtered a good number of the birds.\n* Return to Taskmaster Izubuzri at the Isendeep Mine ()\n* Turn in Sun-touched Tailfeather",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{d="The trolls of Angmar have a singular vision, one that involves destroying the enemies of Angmar.",category="Ettenmoors",id=1955,scope="n/a",name="Slaughter the Free People",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Taskmaster Sharkúlob",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="Mon",o="Obj 1:\nTaskmaster Sharkúlob is at Gramsfoot in the Ettenmoors.\nThe trolls from Angmar, in an effort to speed the victory of Angmar's army, are willing to come to the Ettenmoors to fight the Free Peoples in exchange for your services in the North. You should speak with Taskmaster Sharkûlob.\n* Talk to Taskmaster Sharkúlob\nObj 2:\nTaskmaster Sharkûlob is at Gramsfoot in the Ettenmoors.\nYou took the place of a troll in Angmar while it wrought destruction against the forces of the Free Peoples in the Ettenmoors.\n* Talk to Taskmaster Sharkúlob at Gramsfoot ( )"},
{["next"]={812},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Launo told you that rumour has come to him that the ancient dwarf-ruins of Kibilzahar have become haunted by fell spirits.",mobs={{locations={"19.55N, 83.77W"},name="Arre"},{locations={"19.54N, 71.99W"},name="Launo"}},category="Forochel",id=1956,scope="n/a",name="Slaves of the Ice",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Launo",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nArre is at the camp of Kuru-leiri, in the northern reaches of the great western glacier.\nLauno has asked you to speak with Arre concerning the fell spirits he reported.\n* Talk to Arre\nObj 2:\nKibilzahar lies upon the northern slope of the glacier, north-west from Kuru-leiri.\nArre asked you to explore the ruins of Kibilzahar. Perhaps you may solve the mystery behind the appearance of the fell spirits.\n* Defeat wights in Kibilzahar ($NUMBER$/15)\nObj 3:\nKibilzahar lies upon the northern slope of the glacier, north-west from Kuru-leiri.\nArre asked you to explore the ruins of Kibilzahar. Perhaps you may solve the mystery behind the appearance of the fell spirits.\n* Defeat wights in Kibilzahar (11/15)\nObj 4:\nKibilzahar lies upon the northern slope of the glacier, North-west from Kuru-leiri.\nWhile exploring Kibilzahar you discovered that some of the wights wandering through its ruins were wearing strange amulets. You should retrieve one of these amulets for Arre.\n* Turn in Frozen Amulet\nObj 5:\nArre is in Kuru-leiri, south-east from Kibilzahar.\nYou should bring the frozen amulet you found in Kibilzahar. Perhaps he will be able to tell you more about it.\n* Talk to Arre\n* Turn in Frozen Amulet",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1798},area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+300 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Lauri reported that one of his scouts, Ida, has been missing for some time and that there has been smoke recently seen in the sky near one of the Lossoth homesteads, west of Pynti-peldot.",mobs={{locations={"10.02N, 69.62W"},name="Ida"},{locations={"11.29N, 69.48W"},name="Lauri"}},category="Forochel",id=1957,scope="n/a",name="Smoke on the Horizon",arcs="Threatened Camps",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Lauri",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIda's supply-encampment is to the south of Pynti-peldot, next to the road and near the entrance to the ice canyons.\nLauri has asked you to investigate Ida's supply-encampment and make sure she is not hurt.\n* Check on Ida at the supply-encampment"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyrn Fornech",money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="The isle of Rantost is where the tomb-robbers have made their central camp. A great deal of history is being kept there.",category="Evendim",id=1958,scope="n/a",name="Smoke on the Water",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=36,pois={{locations={"7.41S, 69.65W","6.87S, 69.47W","6.87S, 69.58W","7.43S, 69.59W"},name="Rowboat"}},minlevel=31,b="Wal Simpkins",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nRow-boats can be found along the coast of Rantost.\nWal Simpkins asked you to burn the row-boats around the island.\n* Use Rowboat\nObj 2:\nWal Simpkins is at a small camp at the south-east corner of Rantost.\nWal Simpkins will be pleased to hear the row-boats have been burned.\n* Talk to Wal Simpkins on Rantost",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1100},area="Tâl Caradhras",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Ruidhriel has asked for your aid in confusing the events of the Burnt Tor.",mobs={{locations={"49.10S, 9.34W"},name="Ruidhriel"}},category="Eregion",id=1959,scope="n/a",name="Smouldering Remains",arcs="Hiding Their Passage",level=50,c={"* Burnt Tor is near Ruidhriel, at [49.1S, 10.5W]"},pois={{locations={"49.44S, 10.35W","49.28S, 10.21W","49.24S, 10.05W","49.11S, 10.05W","48.89S, 10.29W","49.24S, 10.62W","49.35S, 10.44W","49.09S, 10.58W","48.98S, 10.07W","49.26S, 10.47W","49.43S, 10.11W","49.18S, 10.51W","49.09S, 10.69W","48.95S, 10.65W","48.84S, 10.03W","49.40S, 10.24W","49.36S, 10.59W","49.32S, 10.72W","49.08S, 10.20W","49.08S, 10.47W","49.33S, 10.04W","49.18S, 10.73W","48.98S, 10.13W","48.99S, 10.28W"},name="Charred Wood"}},minlevel=45,b="Ruidhriel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCharred wood can be found on the Burnt Tor, west of Ruidhriel.\nRuidhriel has asked that you gather charred wood for her to study in hopes of finding out what happened there.\n* Return to Ruidhriel\n* Collect charred wood (10 Charred Wood )",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hengstacer Farm",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="5s 50c"}},d="Emma Rosethorn has asked for your assistance hunting snapper-turtles for their shells and meat for her famous snapper soup.",mobs={{locations={"22.22S, 52.30W"},name="Emma Rosethorn"}},selectoneof={{val="Rosethorn's Robe",id="700090F6"},{q="(x10)",val="Snapper Soup",id="700092CB"}},category="Bree-land",id=1960,scope="n/a",name="Snapper Soup",level=21,c={"* Collect 5 Snapper-shells and 15 Chunks of Snapper-meat from the Snapper Turtles around Nen Harn in northeast Bree-land.\n* Return them to Emma."},minlevel=16,b="Emma Rosethorn",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSnapper-turtles can be found on the islands and along the shore of Nen Harn, to the east of the Hengstacer Farm. Emma Rosethorn is at the Hengstacer Farm, west of Nen Harn.\nEmma Rosethorn asked you to bring her some snapper shells and meat for her soup.\n* Bring the snapper-shells and meat to Emma Rosethorn\n* Turn in Snapper-meat\n* Turn in Snapper-shell",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="South Trollshaws",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="Rochwen believes that the whiskerback cave-claws in the ruins of Ost Dúrgonn, north-east of the Last Bridge, have become corrupted by some disease.",mobs={{locations={"33.15S, 20.24W"},name="Rochwen"}},selectoneof={{val="Rochwen's Boots",id="70002E42"},{val="Rochwen's Rune-stone",id="700161D9"}},category="Trollshaws",id=1961,scope="n/a",name="Some Disease Affects Them",level=34,minlevel=29,b="Rochwen",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDiseased whiskerbacks come down into the low-lands from the ruins of Ost Dúrgonn, north-east of the Last Bridge.\nRochwen has asked you to defeat some of the ferocious cave-claws in the South Trollshaws.\n* Defeat Whiskerback Cave-claws (14)\nObj 2:\nRochwen is north of Barachen's camp, by the road that runs through the South Trollshaws.\nRochwen will be pleased to know that you have defeated some of the diseased cave-claws that come forth from the ruins of Ost Dúrgonn near the Last Bridge.\n* Talk to Rochwen",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={878},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="Sylfa wants to know the extent and scope of the fungus-growth. He fears the water may be the cause of what is growing on the Orcs.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1962,scope="n/a",prev={1413},name="Some Kind of Safety",arcs="Fighting the Fungus",level=55,c={"* You don't need to go far to test the water. The water at the base of the stairs [15.3S, 112.4W] going down from The Rotting Cellar will do. There, you must use the White Cloth Strip from your inventory."},minlevel=50,b="Sylfa",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe water of the Water-works is west of the Rotting Cellar.\nSylfa told you to take the white cloth he gave you and dip it in the water of the Water-works.\n* Use White Cloth Strip\n* Find a good spot to test the water\nObj 2:\nSylfa is in the Rotting Cellar, east of the Water-works.\nYou dipped the white cloth strip in the water, and it turned green. You should return it to Sylfa at once.\n* Talk to Sylfa\n* Turn in Soaked Green Cloth Strip"},
{["next"]={2363},area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 25c"}},d="After allowing Starkath to take the bow from him, Celairant is now certain that he is not worthy of the Elvish weapon.",mobs={{locations={"21.63S, 94.14W"},name="Celairant"},{locations={"23.88S, 92.60W"},name="Penglir"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1963,scope="n/a",prev={144},name="Someone Worthy",arcs="An Incorrupt Heart",level=13,c={"* Penglir is at Duillond in Ered Luin [23.9S, 92.6W]"},minlevel=9,b="Celairant",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nPenglir is at Duillond, south-east of Gondamon.\nCelairant asked you to return to Penglir at Duillond and explain why he feels unworthy to bear the bow, having lost it once already to the dwarf-brigand Starkath.\n* Talk to Penglir"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Northern Emyn Uial",money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="The Twisted Grove has a pool of water beneath it that feeds the roots of the trees and wood trolls there.",mobs={{locations={"6.00S, 71.82W"},name="Remmenylf"}},category="Evendim",id=1964,scope="n/a",name="Something in the Water",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=37,minlevel=32,b="Remmenylf",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Twisted Grove is south-west of the Eavespires.\nRemmenylf asked you to go to The Twisted Grove and pour the Ent's tear into the pool beneath it.\n* Use Vial of Ent Tears\n* Reach the pool below The Twisted Grove\nObj 2:\nRemmenylf is at the Eavespires, north-east of The Twisted Grove.\nRemmenylf will be dismayed to hear the Ent's tear did not purify the waters.\n* Talk to Remmenylf",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1538},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="In the deepest regions of Moria, there are strange and frightening creatures. Veúlfur dispatched a host of his finest agents to the Shadowed Refuge to meet up with Elves there to investigate rumours of the deep dark.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1965,scope="n/a",name="Something Wicked",arcs="Nightmares of the Deep",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Veúlfur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrc fungus-collectors can be found at the Foundations of Stone, south-east of the twenty-first Hall. Veúlfur is at the Twenty-first Hall.\nVeúlfur wants you to be prepared for the undertaking he intends for you and asked you to retrieve a barrel from the Orc fungus-collectors as the first step in your preparations.\n* Return the barrel to Veúlfur at the Twenty-first Hall\n* Turn in Barrel of Fungus",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={773},d="Now that you've recovered the instrument, Pada has asked you to head to Bree and use it to brighten the spirits of some of the townsfolk there.",category="Minstrel",id=1966,scope="n/a",prev={2741},name="Song of the Hopeful Heart",arcs="The Path of the Watcher of Resolve",c={"* Erling Goodbody is in Bree at [29.8S, 51.4W]\n* To play a song for Erling Goodbody, just use A special sheet of music that Pada put in your inventory."},level=58,minlevel=58,b="Pada",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nErling Goodbody can be found in the throughfare in front of the Prancing Pony.\nPada, a widely-respected Minstrel, has asked you to cheer a friend of his from Bree using the great instrument you recently recovered.\n* Find Erling Goodbody in Bree\n* Use A special sheet of music\nObj 2:\nSpeak with Erling and let him know that Pada sends his best.\n* Speak with Erling Goodbody\nObj 3:\nPada is in the Foundations of Stone in Moria.\nYou should return to Pada and tell him that his friend Erling Goodbody was very pleased with the song you played.\n* Return to Pada",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={381},area="Cirin-en-Galadh",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Mallendathor had no knowledge to share regarding the saplings' malady.",mobs={{locations={"11.85S, 68.08W"},name="Mallendathor"},{locations={"11.98S, 64.86W"},name="Sendiel"},{locations={"11.82S, 68.81W"},name="Orthir"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1967,scope="n/a",prev={1419},name="Songs for the Saplings",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,c={"* Orthir can be found in Cirin-en-galadh at [11.8S, 68.8W]"},pois={{locations={"10.38S, 63.79W","10.66S, 63.66W","10.34S, 64.10W","10.12S, 64.26W"},name="Malbrethil-sapling"}},minlevel=55,b="Mallendathor",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrthir can be found a short distance west of Cerin Amroth, near the path.\nMallendathor wishes you to speak to Orthir, the Scholar of the Trees, to see if he knows what might heal the saplings' malady.\n* Talk to Orthir\nObj 2:\nThe Malbrethil-saplings can be found around Cerin Brethil in Taur Hith, to the north-east of Cerin Amroth.\nOrthir believes that the saplings, deprived of the everyday music of the now-wary forest, might be revived if you were to sing to them.\n* Perform /sing\n* Perform /sing\n* Perform /sing\n* Perform /sing\n* Use Malbrethil-sapling\nObj 3:\nSendiel is in Gelirdor, south-west of the Malbrethil-trees, east of Cerin Amroth.\nOrthir instructed you to tell Sendiel of your success.\n* Talk to Sendiel in Gelirdor"},
{area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+900 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Brúnfair, recently dispatched to the north, brings ill tidings and carries a heavy concern on his careworn shoulders. Recent events within the black citadel of Barad Gúlaran have forced him into action.\nHe has requested that you gather assistance from your fellows in seeking the destruction of a cabal of sorceresses who are attempting to see Amarthiel's will carried forth.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Brúnfair"}},selectoneof={{val="Coblaith's Folly",id="7000A301"},{val="Afraig's Foe",id="7000A30B"},{val="Múlvuirë's Fall",id="7000A313"}},category="Barad Gúlaran",id=1968,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2906},name="Sorceresses of the Black Tower",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Brúnfair",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFind the three Sorceresses within Barad Gúlaran and defeat them. If they are stopped, then there will be no others to carry out the will of Amarthiel.\nBrúnfair asked you to search through the halls of Barad Gúlaran in search of the sorceresses left in charge of carrying out Amarthiel's will. Find them and destroy them.\n* Kill 1 Múlvuirë, High Sorceress\n* Kill 1 Afraig, Gúlaran Sorceress\n* Kill 1 Coblaith, Gúlaran Sorceress\nObj 2:\nYou have defeated the sorceresses within Barad Gúlaran. Return to Brúnfair at the Ranger encampment in the northeastern section of Angmar and tell him of your success.\nSearching through the halls of Barad Gúlaran you discovered and defeated the Sorceresses responsible for carrying out the machinations of Amarthiel in Angmar.\n* Talk to Brúnfair"},
{["next"]={753},money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Pipe-weed is something hobbits take very seriously. A market would never be visited unless it had a suitable supply and variety.",category="Evendim",id=1969,scope="n/a",prev={1074},name="Sorting the Pipe-weed",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=30,minlevel=25,b="Blossom Gamgee",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe pipe-weed barrels are next to Blossom Gamgee.\nThe pipe-weed needs to be sorted before it can be dried.\n* Use Pipeweed Barrel\nObj 2:\nBlossom Gamgee is at the Northcotton Farm.\nBlossom Gamgee will want to know that the pipe-weed has been sorted.\n* Talk to Blossom Gamgee",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+500 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="7s 42c"}},d="You have recovered a number of pottery shards and other relics from the jetsam that washes up on the shores of Lake Nenuial, and now Ranger Astiul wants you to sort the valuable pieces from the rest.",mobs={{locations={"12.58S, 67.22W"},name="Astiul"}},category="Evendim",id=1970,scope="n/a",prev={3211},name="Sort Out the Pieces",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=32,pois={{locations={"15.29S, 60.54W","12.59S, 67.21W","15.32S, 60.53W"},name="Small Salvaged Pieces"},{locations={"15.34S, 60.56W","15.27S, 60.54W","15.29S, 60.50W","12.57S, 67.22W"},name="Large Salvaged Pieces"},{locations={"15.30S, 60.56W","12.58S, 67.23W"},name="Medium Salvaged Pieces"}},minlevel=27,b="Astiul",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDifferent-sized relics and bits of pottery are lying on the mats by Astiul at Tinnudir, on Parth Aduial in Evendim.\nAstiul has asked you to sort the pottery fragments and relics you collected from the shores of Lake Neniul by size on the mats he uses for that purpose.\n* Use Small Salvaged Pieces\n* Use Medium Salvaged Pieces\n* Use Large Salvaged Pieces\nObj 2:\nAstiul is at Tinnudir, on Parth Aduial in Evendim.\nRanger Astiul will be pleased that you sorted out the relics and pottery shards you collected from the shores of Lake Nenuial.\n* Talk to Astiul\n* Turn in Satchel of Pottery"},
{["next"]={678},area="Lich Bluffs",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="Recently, several barrows in the Lich Bluffs have been disturbed. The bodies of the dead have been removed from their crypts and desecrated.",mobs={{locations={"70.57S, 15.46W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Enedwaith",id=1971,scope="n/a",prev={1956,1818},name="Source of the Unrest",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe barrows Mincham wants you to investigate are located to the east of the road, along the southern border of the Lich Bluffs.\nMincham has asked you seek out the entrances to some of the barrows and investigate the corpses of the recently disturbed dead.\n* Find the first skeleton pile\n* Find the second skeleton pile\n* Find the third skeleton pile\nObj 2:\nMincham is at his camp, north of the barrows.\nYou should return to Mincham and report what you found at the ancient barrows.\n* Talk to Mincham in the Lich Bluffs"},
{area="Andrath",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="2s 15c"}},d="Watcher Oakdale spoke in hushed tones of a particularly foul creature leading the half-breeds out of the south.",category="Bree-land",id=1972,scope="n/a",prev={2618},name="Southern Fiend",receive={{val="Fiend-killer Silver Hoop",id="7001AADA"},{q="(x2)",val="Lesser Athelas Essence",id="70000D5D"}},level=16,minlevel=11,b="Watcher Oakdale",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe half-orc leader can be found just inside the gate from the south in the Vale of Andrath.\nWatcher Oakdale has asked you to defeat the leader of the half-orcs from the south.\n* Defeat the half-orc leader in Andrath\nObj 2:\nWatcher Oakdale is at the east edge of the northern part of the Southwatch.\nYou defeated the half-orc leader deep within the enemy camp at Andrath and should now return to Watcher Oakdale.\n* Talk to Watcher Oakdale",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2543},area="Redhorn Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Ingifast believes that the White Hand Orcs can be frightened off if they are confronted with the remains of the previous expedition.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=1973,scope="n/a",prev={140},name="Sowing the Seeds of Fear",arcs="White-Hand Orders",level=56,pois={{locations={"12.86S, 103.67W"},name="White Hand Skull"},{locations={"13.09S, 104.02W"},name="White Hand Leg-bone"},{locations={"12.91S, 103.23W"},name="White Hand Banner"},{locations={"12.65S, 103.03W"},name="White Hand Armour"}},minlevel=51,b="Ingifast",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe White Hand expedition was exploring the Claw Hollow, to the south-east of the Orc-watch.\nIngifast has instructed you to locate the remains of the previous expedition and bring them back in the bag he supplied.\n* Use White Hand Armour\n* Use White Hand Banner\n* Use White Hand Leg-bone\n* Use White Hand Skull\nObj 2:\nIngifast is at the Orc-watch, north-west of the Claw Hollow.\nIngifast will be eager to see the remains you collected of the previous White Hand expedition.\n* Talk to Ingifast\n* Turn in Bag"},
{["next"]={570},area="Bridgefields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Odovacar Bolger's workhands reported that they saw a dark figure lurking around Mr. Bolger's pig sties at night.",mobs={{locations={"31.41S, 65.90W"},name="Black Rider"},{locations={"31.04S, 65.48W"},name="Odovacar Bolger"}},category="Shire",id=1974,scope="n/a",name="Spectre of the Black Rider",arcs="Spectre of the Black Rider",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Odovacar Bolger",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOdovacar Bolger's sties are in the southern part of Budgeford by the stream.\nOdovacar Bolger has asked you to investigate his workhands' reports by going to his pig sties. He was very particular that you should go there at night.\n* Search for the Black Rider at night\nObj 2:\nThe \"Black Rider\" is attempting to menace the Bolger sties.\nThis \"Black Rider\" looks rather less threatening than expected. You should confront him and find out what's really going on.\n* Confront the \"Black Rider\"\nObj 3:\nOdovacar Bolger is at his home up the hill in the centre of Budgeford.\nOdovacar Bolger sent you to investigate his workhands' claims of a Black Rider lurking in his pig sties. What you found was a hobbit dressed in a black cloak. You should report your discovery to Odovacar.\n* Talk to Odovacar Bolger",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="An ancient spider-queen has pursued Atli Spider-bane to Archet and invaded Cal Sprigley's farm.",mobs={{locations={"24.87S, 48.88W"},name="Atli Spider-bane"}},selectoneof={{val="Iornaith's Guard",id="70019BE9"},{val="Iornaith's Ward",id=70003735}},category="Bree-land",id=1975,scope="n/a",prev={883},name="Spider-bane",arcs="Spider-bane",level=9,c={"* Iornaith is on the west side of the cave. Make sure to kill the two mobs not connected to Iornaith, just in case."},minlevel=5,b="Atli Spider-bane",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSprigley's farm is south of Bronwe's Folly. One entrance to the spider tunnels lies through the cellar of Sprigley's shed, while the other is through the cave mouth due west of the Hunter's Lodge.\nTo prevent Iornaith's brood from overrunning Archet, Atli Spider-bane has asked you to find and slay the spider-queen. Atli suggests searching the spider caves beneath Sprigley's farm for a secret entrance into the Iornaith's lair.\n* Defeat Iornaith\nObj 2:\nAtli Spider-bane can be found at the north end of Archet, west of the spider-cave, north-west of Sprigley's farm.\nYou should take news of Iornaith's defeat to Atli Spider-bane.\n* Talk to Atli Spider-bane in Archet\n//Iornaith\n9 Signature (Special)\nSprigley\\'s CellarLocation: 27.94S, 48.26W\nBree-land >> Archet';markerList['1879062323'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879062323', new GLatLng(-2.5604296875, -6.2539453125), { 'icon':MONSTER_ICON }); marker.id = '1879062323'; markers['1879062323'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Iornaith\n9 Signature (Special)\nSprigley\\'s CellarLocation: 24.91S, 47.96W\nBree-land >> Archet';markerList['1879062323'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879062301_0x0417A7C0000000DF_64.0166.48976992', new GLatLng(-2.5203515625, -7.874912109375), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879062301_0x0417A7C0000000DF_64.0166.48976992'; markers['1879062301_0x0417A7C0000000DF_64.0166.48976992'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Atli Spider-bane Location: 24.87S, 48.88W\nBree-land >> Archet';markerList['1879062301_0x0417A7C0000000DF_64.0166.48976992'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879062301_0x0417A7C0000000DF_64.0166.48976992', new GLatLng(-2.5203515625, -7.874912109375), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879062301_0x0417A7C0000000DF_64.0166.48976992'; markers['1879062301_0x0417A7C0000000DF_64.0166.48976992'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Atli Spider-bane Location: 24.87S, 48.88W\nBree-land >> Archet';markerList['1879062301_0x0417A7C0000000DF_64.0166.48976992'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker); GME_DEFAULT_ICON = G_DEFAULT_ICON;      } else {        document.getElementById(\"map2878414044\").innerHTML = \"In order to see the map that would go in this space, you will need to use a compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap2878414044);\n//]]>\nQuest: Spider-bane\nCategory: Bree-land\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 5\nRewards\nMoney:\n90\nSelect one of:\nIornaith's Ward\nIornaith's Guard\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nYou slew a spider-queen that invaded the caves beneath Archet.\nBestower\nThe Head of Iornaith (Item)\nThis brood-queen is far more fearsome than any spider you have come across before and seems to be manipulating many of the events around Archet.\nThe dwarf Atli is known as the Spider-bane. He would likely want to see proof of this creature's demise.\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nAtli Spider-bane is in Archet.\nYou fought and defeated Iornaith, a spider of great power, while searching the tunnels west of Archet. Knowing that the dwarf, Atli, is often referred to as the Spider-bane, you should bring proof of your deeds back to Archet to show to the dwarf.\n* Talk to Atli Spider-bane in Archet"},
{["next"]={1600},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="11s 50c"}},d="Celephadh has asked for your help in securing the lands around Esteldín and warding off any threats.",mobs={{locations={"9.79S, 41.50W"},name="Celephadh"}},category="North Downs",id=1976,scope="n/a",name="Spider-bounty",arcs="Servants of the Enemy",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Celephadh",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe foul spiders reside in the south-eastern area of the Kingsfell in the shadow of the mountain.\nCelephadh has asked you to hunt down and slay the spiders that plague the area.\n* Defeat spiders (20)\nObj 2:\nCelephadh makes his lodging in the valley camp of Esteldín.\nYou should return to Celephadh and let him know that you have done as he asked.\n* Talk to Celephadh"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="13s"}},d="Holger Tanner is the survivor of a party of merchants ambushed by spiders in the Kingsfell. The merchants were carrying a valuable pouch of gems, which the spiders dragged off with one of the bodies.",mobs={{locations={"9.72S, 42.21W"},name="Holger Tanner"}},category="North Downs",id=1977,scope="n/a",name="Spider Gems",receive={{val="Tanner's Jacket",id="70006A82"}},level=26,minlevel=21,b="Holger Tanner",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe lost pouch of gems is somewhere in the area called the Snares, south of Esteldín.\nHolger Tanner, a merchant who escaped an attack by spiders, has asked you to recover his companions' missing pouch of gems from the spiders' lair.\n* Turn in Pouch of Gems\nObj 2:\nHolger Tanner is at Esteldín.\nHolger Tanner, a merchant who escaped an attack by spiders, has asked you to recover his companions' missing pouch of gems.\n* Talk to Holger Tanner\n* Turn in Pouch of Gems",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{d="The Grimwood is secured for Angmar's purposes. To ensure that it remains this way, we must grow our forces and support.\nYou must draw the web-weavers from the nearby tower to come to Angmar's aid at the Grimwood Lumber Camp.",category="Grimwood",id=1978,scope="n/a",name="Spider Harvesters",destinypoints={{val=500}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Golb",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="Mon",o="Obj 1:\nCaragdal can be found in the spider-infested ruins to the west of the Grimwood Lumber Camp.\nLead Caragdal from the tower to the Grimwood camp to enlist the aid of the spiders of Gorogris' brood.\n* Escort Caragdal to the Grimwood Lumber Camp\nObj 2:\nSoldier Golb is in the Grimwood Lumber Camp.\nYou should return to Soldier Golb with the news that Caragdal is on the move.\n* Return to Soldier Golb with news of your success ( )"},
{["next"]={1735},area="Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="28s"}},d="It is a constant struggle to keep the overwhelming numbers of the spiders to a minimum.",selectoneof={{val="Klintur's Charge",id="700163A0"},{val="Bracelet of the Arachnid-slayer",id="7001639C"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1979,scope="n/a",name="Spider-infestation",level=59,minlevel=54,b="Klintur",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpiders may be found around Tunzelgund, east of the Shadowed Refuge.\nKlintur has asked you to defeat many spiders in the Foundations of Stone.\n* Defeat spiders (14)\nObj 2:\nKlintur can be found at the Shadowed Refuge, west from Tunzelgund.\nYou should return to Klintur with news of your success.\n* Talk to Klintur at the Shadowed Refuge"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Thrand has polished the glass-spider legs and prepared them to be placed inside the empty lamp-posts.",selectoneof={{val="Thrand's Tough Shoulders",id="700163EB"},{val="Prism Ring",id="700163BB"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=1980,scope="n/a",prev={569},name="Spider-leg Prisms",arcs="Glass Spiders",level=56,c={"* Gabil-munz is at [16.5S, 114.0]"},pois={{locations={"16.17S, 113.66W","16.60S, 113.30W","15.81S, 114.10W","16.12S, 114.29W","16.73S, 114.44W","16.01S, 113.82W","16.28S, 114.45W","16.95S, 114.22W"},name="Shattered Crystal"}},minlevel=51,b="Thrand",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe empty lamp-posts can be found all over Gabil-munz, south-west of the Rotting Cellar.\nThrand would like you to place the polished glass-spider legs inside the posts to repair them.\n* Use Shattered Crystal\n* Turn in Bag of Polished Glass-spider Legs\nObj 2:\nThrand is in the Rotting Cellar, north-east of Gabil-munz.\nYou should return to Thrand and inform him the glass-spider legs worked and the lamp-posts have been repaired.\n* Talk to Thrand in the Rotting Cellar"},
{["next"]={884},area="Bindbole Wood",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Otho Broadbelt, a trader carrying goods from Bree, had his waggon overrun by spiders.",mobs={{locations={"28.15S, 70.16W"},name="Otho Broadbelt"}},category="Shire",id=1981,scope="n/a",name="Spider Plague",arcs="Spider Plague",level=10,pois={{locations={"27.26S, 69.48W"},name="Trade-goods"}},minlevel=6,b="Otho Broadbelt",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOtho Broadbelt's waggon is just off the road to the north-east of Overhill, next to the falls.\nOtho Broadbelt needs you to recover the trade goods he was bringing back from Bree from the waggon he abandoned outside Overhill.\n* Bring the trade goods back to Otho Broadbelt\n* Collect the trade goods",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="23s 20c"}},d="A monstrous breed of spider has built a nest south of Esteldín, threatening the security of the outpost's inhabitants.",mobs={{locations={"9.60S, 42.10W"},name="Dagoras"}},category="North Downs",id=1982,scope="n/a",name="Spider-queen",receive={{val="Dagoras' Shoes",id=70001865}},level=27,minlevel=22,b="Dagoras",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Kingsfell Spider-queen is somewhere in the spider-lair south of Esteldín.\nDagoras has asked you to slay the queen of the spiders who threaten his people, thereby lessening the danger posed by the foul creatures.\n* Kill 1 Kingsfell Spider-queen\nObj 2:\nDagoras is at Esteldín.\nYou should return to Dagoras and inform him that you have slain the spider-queen.\n* Talk to Dagoras",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Edda Twiggins is still concerned that the creatures of the Midgewater Marshes pose an overlooked danger to the people of Staddle.",mobs={{locations={"31.09S, 49.39W"},name="Watcher Reedy"}},selectoneof={{val="Reedy's Hat",id="70006B1B"},{val="Watcher's Axe",id="70006B73"}},category="Bree-land",id=1983,scope="n/a",prev={1528},name="Spiders in the Midgewater",arcs="Menace in the Midgewater",level=14,minlevel=10,b="Edda Twiggins",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe brood-watcher presence lies between the old Marshwater Fort and the Woodsedge Ruins in the  Midgewater Marshes.\nAccording to Edda Twiggins, a deadly new breed of spider has appeared in the northern Midgewater, and she has asked you to thin their numbers.\n* Defeat marsh brood-watchers\n* Defeat marsh-queen\n* Defeat marsh-spiders\nObj 2:\nEdda Twiggins can be found to the south-east of the ruins in the northern Midgewater Marsh.\nEdda Twiggins will be pleased to hear of your success against the deadly marsh brood-watchers and their queen in the Midgewater Marshes.\n* Talk to Edda Twiggins"},
{area="Greenfields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="The workers at the quarry in Scary have broken into a hidden chamber containing a nest of spiders, and the creatures have now overrun the whole quarry.",mobs={{locations={"27.95S, 66.20W"},name="Lily Proudfoot"}},category="Shire",id=1984,scope="n/a",name="Spiders in the Quarry",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=12,c={"* The spiders to kill are in the Scary Quarry east of Scary"},minlevel=8,b="Lily Proudfoot",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe spiders can be found all throughout the quarry and the cave they swarmed from, cut into the cliff-face by Scary.\nLily Proudfoot, worried that the spiders in the quarry might climb out of the rocky hole and take over her town, has asked you to kill off the creatures.\n* Defeat Greenfields Biters\n* Defeat Greenfields Tree-weavers\n* Defeat Greenfields Queen\nObj 2:\nLily Proudfoot is in Scary, looking out at the quarry.\nLily Proudfoot was afraid that the spiders that the quarrymen unearthed would overrun Scary and asked you to help clear the threat. She will be pleased to learn of your success.\n* Talk to Lily Proudfoot",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rath Teraig",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="Tralli Hammerfist has asked for your help in destroying the spiders that lurk beyond the barricade into Rath Teraig.",mobs={{locations={"22.12S, 96.83W"},name="Tralli Hammerfist"}},category="Ered Luin",id=1985,scope="n/a",name="Spiders of the Vale",arcs="The Southern Road",level=12,minlevel=8,b="Tralli Hammerfist",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are spiders beyond the barricade south of the dwarf-camp.\nTralli Hammerfist, deathly afraid of spiders, has asked you to defeat a few of the creatures for him.\n* Defeat spiders in Rath Teraig (8)\nObj 2:\nTralli Hammerfist is at the dwarf-camp beyond the barricade at the northern entrance to Rath Teraig.\nYou should return to Tralli Hammerfist with news of your success.\n* Talk to Tralli Hammerfist",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2536},reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyrn Fornech",money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="The isle of Rantost is where the tomb-robbers have made their central camp. A great deal of history is being kept there.",mobs={{locations={"7.51S, 64.39W"},name="Basil Gummidge"}},category="Evendim",id=1986,scope="n/a",prev={1148},name="Spies and Robbers",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=36,minlevel=31,b="Basil Gummidge",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nRantost is north-west of Ost Forod.\nBasil sent you to meet with several spies he has among the tomb-robber camp on the isle of Rantost.\n* Talk to Eliot Bencroft at Rantost",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Cirin-en-Galadh",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Tuilinn, delighted by the success of her plan to bolster the morale of her friends, wants you to visit them regularly bearing blossoms from Cerin Amroth.",mobs={{locations={"12.10S, 71.09W"},name="Bahanneth"},{locations={"14.26S, 73.07W"},name="Ambendel"},{locations={"17.24S, 64.00W"},name="Maliriel"},{locations={"11.93S, 67.85W"},name="Tuilinn"}},category="Lothlórien",id=1987,scope="n/a",prev={1539},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Spirits in Bloom",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,c={"* Maliriel is at [17.2S, 64.0W]\n* Ambendel is at [14.3S, 73.1W]\n* Bahanneth is at [12.1S, 71.1W]"},pois={{locations={"11.79S, 67.47W","12.09S, 68.18W","11.61S, 67.65W","11.86S, 68.12W","12.21S, 67.82W","12.35S, 67.95W","11.92S, 67.43W","12.15S, 67.97W","12.03S, 67.49W","11.97S, 67.39W","11.93S, 67.56W","11.65S, 67.53W","11.67S, 67.82W","12.32S, 67.75W","12.02S, 68.13W","11.85S, 68.18W","12.36S, 67.89W","12.28S, 67.98W","11.71S, 68.08W","11.72S, 67.42W","12.08S, 67.74W","12.01S, 68.25W","12.18S, 67.65W","11.65S, 67.67W"},name="Elanor"},{locations={"11.91S, 68.22W","11.69S, 67.77W","11.93S, 68.15W","12.29S, 67.92W","11.63S, 67.36W","12.04S, 67.54W","11.96S, 67.58W","12.12S, 68.05W","12.21S, 67.73W","11.83S, 68.24W","12.07S, 68.26W","12.31S, 67.84W","12.03S, 67.99W","11.61S, 67.96W","11.76S, 67.51W","11.87S, 67.47W","12.00S, 67.45W","11.96S, 68.03W","11.73S, 67.87W","11.75S, 68.15W","12.21S, 68.03W","12.22S, 68.22W","11.61S, 67.55W","11.65S, 67.61W"},name="Niphredil"}},minlevel=55,b="Tuilinn",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElanor and niphredil can be found upon and around Cerin Amroth.\nTuilinn has asked you to pick more elanor and niphredil.\n* Collect elanor-blossoms (6 Elanor )\n* Collect niphredil-blossoms (6 Niphredil )\nObj 2:\nBahanneth is at Talan Fanuidhol, west of Cerin Amroth. Ambendel is at Echad Andestel, south-west of Cerin Amroth. Maliriel is at the Hythe, east and south of Cerin Amroth, near the river.\nTuilinn has asked you to bring elanor and niphredil-blossoms to Bahanneth, Ambendel, and Maliriel the Feast-mistress.\n* Talk to Maliriel\n* Turn in Elanor\n* Turn in Niphredil\n* Talk to Ambendel\n* Turn in Elanor\n* Turn in Niphredil\n* Talk to Bahanneth\n* Turn in Elanor\n* Turn in Niphredil\nObj 3:\nTuilinn is atop the flet at Cerin Amroth.\nYou should return to Tuilinn and relate to her how her gift lifted the spirits of her friends.\n* Talk to Tuilinn at Cerin Amroth"},
{["next"]={702},area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Imlad Balchorth is the dwelling place of a host of fell spirits, servants of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"6.90N, 25.82W"},name="Gautar"}},category="Angmar",id=1988,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2884},name="Spirits of Old",arcs="Banishing the Darkness",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Gautar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are fell spirits in Imlad Balchorth, in the southern upper passes, south and west from Myrkworth. Gautar is in Myrkworth.\nGautar has asked you to confront the fell spirits to learn if there might be a way to banish them from Middle-earth.\n* Bring the tokens back to Gautar\n* Turn in Token of Angmar"},
{area="Greenfields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Holly Hornblower of Hobbiton baked pies using spoiled berries and has asked you to retrieve them before they are eaten. Ivo Brockhouse of Brockenborings had one such pie.",mobs={{locations={"27.63S, 68.11W"},name="Ivo Brockhouse"}},category="Shire",id=1989,scope="n/a",prev={1371},name="Spoiled Pie from Brockenborings",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Ivo Brockhouse",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHolly Hornblower's home is north of the Hobbiton main square.\nIvo Brockhouse has one of Holly's bad pies, which you should take back toher as quickly as possible. Make sure no hungry hobbits catch a whiff of the pie, as Holly doesn't want to be bothered with them asking for a slice, especially since she has to bake fresh pies for all her customers.\n* Collect Ivo Brockhouse's pie",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
