{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Carlo Blagrove, innkeeper of The Bird and Baby, is entering the Four Farthings Brewing-moot.",mobs={{locations={"33.38S, 75.36W","33.38S, 75.35W"},name="Carlo Blagrove"}},category="Shire",id=2244,scope="n/a",name="The Bird and Baby",receive={{val="Blagrove's Brown",id="70000D75"}},level=7,pois={{locations={"33.61S, 71.13W"},name="Yellowed Recipe"}},minlevel=3,b="Carlo Blagrove",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Great Smials are in Tuckborough, to the east of Michel Delving. The Bird and Baby Inn is in Michel Delving, to the west of Tuckborough.\nCarlo Blagrove has asked you to search the Great Smials for a recipe he thinks his great-grandfather might have hidden there.\n* Bring the recipe back to Carlo Blagrove\n* Collect the yellowed recipe",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1989},area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Black Uruks are the masters of Gathbúrz, driving the Orcs and goblins into battle beneath their lashes. As long as they remain in command, it will be difficult to fully break the forces defending Dol Guldur. More importantly, if the uruk-leaders can be defeated, then the masters of the tower will find it considerably more difficult to prepare the upcoming army for their inevitable assault upon Lothlórien.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 46.57W"},name="Rodelleth"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2245,scope="n/a",prev={578},name="The Black Drivers",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Rodelleth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBlack Uruks can be found in Gathbúrz.\nRodelleth has asked you to defeat the uruk-leaders in Gathbúrz to deplete the reserve of officers available to the Orc-forces in the battle for Mirkwood.\n* Defeat Black Uruks in Gathbúrz (8)\nObj 2:\nRodelleth is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nYou should return to Rodelleth with tidings of your victory over the Black Uruks of Mirkwood.\n* Talk to Rodelleth in Thangúlhad"},
{area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="18s 40c"}},d="Aggy Digweed has dubbed the foul substance you found \\qBlack-fire\\q and called it a dark magic of the Orcs. She believes the Orcs have more and that it must be destroyed if Trestlebridge is to be saved.",mobs={{locations={"16.15S, 53.49W"},name="Aggy Digweed"}},category="North Downs",id=2246,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={698},name="The Black-fire",arcs="The Black Fire",level=25,c={"* You will find on of the crates in the northern hill [16.5S, 46.9W]\n* You will find on of the crates in the south-eastern hill [17.0S, 46.7W]\n* You will find on of the crates in the south-western hill [16.7S, 48.2W]"},minlevel=20,b="Aggy Digweed",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Black-fire crates are on three hills in Nan Wathren.\nAggy Digweed said that there are three large hills connected by rope bridges in Nan Wathren and asked you to search those hills for more Black-fire crates. She told you to keep an eye open for half-orcs, as full-blooded Orcs are too brutish to create magic like the Black-fire. As the Black-fire powder explodes when touched by fire, Aggy asked you to put the Black-fire to the torch, destroying it all. She also suggested you take friends.\n* Find the Black-fire on the northern hill\n* Find the Black-fire on the south-eastern hill\n* Find the Black-fire on the south-western hill\nObj 2:\nAggy Digweed can be found in Trestlebridge.\nIn your search of the three hills in the Nan Wathren, you found Black-fire crates atop each hill. You also found half-orcs, who spoke of a someone named Lugbas, who may be their leader. Aggy should know what you found.\n* Talk to Aggy Digweed"},
{["next"]={1978,1607,916},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="A great host of Orcs spilled through Ram Dúath, driving the Men of the North Downs from their farms. Esteldín, home of the few remaining Dúnedain of the North, was spared discovery. It is from there that the Rangers begin to plan their counter-offensive against the black tide of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.44S, 41.27W"},name="Daervunn"}},category="North Downs",id=2247,scope="n/a",name="The Black Tide of Angmar",arcs="The Black Tide of Angmar",level=32,minlevel=27,b="Daervunn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe banners of the Orc-tribes fly at the outskirts of their camps near Fornost at the Norbury Gates, near Trestlebridge at Nan Wathren, and Dol Dínen, south-east of Esteldín.\nDaervunn of Esteldín fears that the Orcs of Angmar are united together for a common cause. He has asked you to bring him the banners from their primary camps to prove whether there is truth to this belief.\n* Return the Orc-banners to Daervunn\n* Turn in Ongbúrz Banner\n* Turn in Blogmal Banner\n* Turn in Tarkrîp Banner"},
{["next"]={2304},zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="27s 65c"}},d="The Forges of Khazad-dûm were once the heart of smithing within Moria. Here, the mighty dwarf-smiths would work the mithril and forge their greastest wonders. In the time since its fall, the Forges of Khazad-dûm have been flooded with massive lava-floes and populated by the Orcs of Moria and their troll and goblin-labourers. Here the Orc war-host hammers away incessantly, as they built their weapons and siege-engines in preparation for their war against Lothlórien.",mobs={{locations={"13.44S, 108.07W"},name="Pálmar"},{locations={"13.43S, 108.06W"},name="Raf"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2248,scope="n/a",name="The Black Uruk of Moria",arcs="Forges of Khazad-dûm",level=58,minlevel=57,b="Pálmar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nRaf is at Anazârmekhem.\nPálmar seemed a bit worried about the leader of the Orcs within the Forges and advised that you speak with Raf before you enter the Forges.\n* Talk to Raf at Anazârmekhem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="56s"}},d="The Forges of Khazad-dûm were once the heart of smithing within Moria. Here, the mighty dwarf-smiths would work the mithril and forge their greastest wonders. In the time since its fall, the Forges of Khazad-dûm have been flooded with massive lava-floes and populated by the Orcs of Moria and their troll and goblin-labourers. Here the Orc war-host hammers away incessantly, as they built their weapons and siege-engines in preparation for their war against Lothlórien.",mobs={{locations={"13.43S, 108.06W"},name="Raf"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2249,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Black Uruk of the Forge",arcs="Forges of Khazad-dûm",level=59,minlevel=57,b="Raf",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nKranklûk is in the Forges of Khazad-dûm, south-west of Anazârmekhem.\nRaf has asked you to find and defeat the Black Uruk Kranklûk. He told you to shield yourself from fire and shadow when facing this terrible foe as he fears that it may be something more than a common Uruk.\n* Defeat Kranklûk\nObj 2:\nRaf is at Anazârmekhem, north-east of the Forges of Khazad-dûm.\nKranklûk proved to be a powerful Uruk and perhaps something more. Still, after scaling down the terrible pit that the Forges of Khazad-dûm has become, you found and defeated the foe.\n* Talk to Raf at Anazârmekhem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="8s 54c"}},d="You have returned the last of the Silithair to Aragorn, and now the time has come for Narsil to be reforged.",mobs={{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},selectoneof={{val="Ithilnaith",id="7000A275"},{val="Gorthol",id="7000A227"},{val="Rongrist",id="7000A269"},{val="Gellanc",id="7000A231"},{val="Golubadanir (Level 40)",id="7000A233"},{val="Flawless Rune-stone",id="700161E2"}},category="Evendim",id=2250,scope="n/a",prev={2453},name="The Blade that was Broken",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=40,minlevel=35,b="Aragorn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAragorn is in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nThe Elf-smiths of Imladris will reforge the blade that was broken, and Aragorn is waiting to walk with you to the forges where it will be done.\n* Talk to Aragorn in Rivendell and travel to the forges\nObj 2:\nAragorn is in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nAndúril, Flame of the West, has been forged from the shards of Narsil, and Aragorn is waiting to speak with you.\n* Talk to Aragorn in Rivendell"},
{["next"]={398},area="Western Malenhad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Lornë only knows the Silk-lady as a name of fear, but hopes you may be able to find more clues in the Angmarim fortress of Bail Boglakh.",mobs={{locations={"1.90S, 32.95W"},name="Lornë"}},category="Angmar",id=2251,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2308},name="The Blood-bond",arcs="Blood-price",level=44,minlevel=39,b="Lornë",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLornë has asked you to gather some allies and seek out any clues as to the whereabouts of the so-called 'Silk-lady' of Bail Boglakh, an Angmarim fortress to the north of Malenhad.\n* Turn in Token of the Silk-lady\nObj 2:\n* Bring the tokens to Lornë at Tyrn Lhuig\n* Turn in Token of the Silk-lady"},
{["next"]={2307},area="Western Malenhad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Lornë told you that she joined the hunting party to find her missing sister, Muirnë, only she fears that the worst has befallen her.",mobs={{locations={"1.90S, 32.95W"},name="Lornë"}},category="Angmar",id=2252,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="The Blood-price",arcs="Blood-price",level=44,minlevel=39,b="Lornë",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Angmarim camp of Bail Róva is North-west of Tyrn Lhuig, guarding the entrance to the Ram Dúath.\nLornë has asked you to look for some sign of her sister and if necessary to confront the outpost's commander for news of Muirnë.\n* Look for Muirnë\n* Confront the Bail Róva camp commander\nObj 2:\nLornë is at the hunters' camp in Malenhad.\nMuirnë was not in Bail Rova, but the Angmarim commander mentioned a Silk-lady who may know more. You should return to Lornë and tell her what you have learned.\n* Talk to Lornë"},
{area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Latharna has welcomed you as a friend of the Trév Gállorg and asks you to set right some of the injuries the people have suffered of late.",mobs={{locations={"0.14N, 39.17W"},name="Latharna"}},selectoneof={{val="Faercham",id="70006B06"},{val="Ruthringor",id="70002FA5"},{val="Bloodstone Staff",id="7000313D"}},category="Angmar",id=2253,scope="n/a",prev={624},name="The Bloodstone Trove",level=44,c={"* The Trove is located at deep within the camp. [3.4N, 35.3 W]  It is not in a corner as the quest suggests, but out in the open in front of a tent."},pois={{locations={"3.52N, 34.60W","3.33N, 35.18W","3.36N, 34.82W"},name="Bloodstone Trove"}},minlevel=39,b="Latharna",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe bloodstone trove is in the fortress of Tór Gailvin northeast of Aughaire, probably hidden in an out-of-the-way corner.\nLatharna has asked you to recover the trove of bloodstones that was stolen by the Trév Duvárdain.\n* Use Bloodstone Trove\nObj 2:\nLatharna is in the Búth Sánkhas in Aughaire, south-east of the market.\nYou have recovered the bloodstone trove from Tór Gailvin and should bring it now to Latharna.\n* Talk to Latharna\n* Turn in Bloodstone Trove"},
{["next"]={95},area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Tales of your daring have spread throughout the lands of Middle-earth, and you are known as a mighty champion in roadside inns everywhere.",mobs={{locations={"15.13S, 103.31W"},name="Dourhand"},{locations={"29.84S, 4.69W"},name="Celeblas"},{locations={"13.72S, 44.95W"},name="Gwesgylliel"},{locations={"31.72S, 50.83W","31.71S, 50.83W"},name="Oggur"},{locations={"12.72S, 67.20W"},name="Uirod"},{locations={"28.26S, 92.17W"},name="Drambor"},{locations={"19.18N, 71.88W"},name="Väinämõ"},{locations={"50.46S, 8.05W"},name="Dómari"},{locations={"9.71S, 41.41W"},name="Brethilthor"},{locations={"15.32S, 101.52W"},name="Malthendring"},{locations={"20.22S, 96.89W"},name="Haflith"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Geirr"},{locations={"25.30S, 48.70W"},name="Aldred Cartwright"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Sheldon Roper"}},category="Champion",id=2254,scope="n/a",prev={13,23},requiredclasses="Champion",name="The Boldest Road is Discipline",arcs="The Boldest Road",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Aldred Cartwright",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGwesgylliel is at Lin Giliath in Meluinen in the North Downs.\nYou have been told that the Elf-maiden Gwesgylliel, herself a mighty champion, desires to speak with you.\n* Talk to Gwesgylliel"},
{area="Tyrn Fornech",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Basil Gummidge is worried that you may have done too good a job at claiming the bounties posted in Ost Forod, and that you have made a number of enemies.",mobs={{locations={"7.51S, 64.39W"},name="Basil Gummidge"}},selectoneof={{val="Iron Tankard",id=70026146},{val="Scratched Silver Coin",id="700264C5"},{val="Tightly Folded Dunedain Speech",id="70025FBB"},{val="Flawed Ruby",id=70026271},{val="Worn Arnorian Dagger Pommel",id="70025D6A"},{val="Ancient Seed",id=70026588},{val="Ceremonial Bronze Horn",id="700260D1"},{val="Ancient Bann Scroll",id="700264AC"},{val="Extra Bowstring",id="700261BB"}},category="Evendim",id=2255,scope="n/a",prev={414,418,411,419},name="The Bounty-hunter",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=35,c={"* The poster Basil Gummidge asks you to read is very close to him [7.4S, 64.4W]"},pois={{locations={"7.42S, 64.42W"},name="Wanted Poster"}},minlevel=30,b="Basil Gummidge",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere is a poster on the wall by the stairs near Basil Gummidge in Ost Forod.\nBasil Gummidge has directed your attention to a poster on the wall near him, asking you to read it, then bring it to him.\n* Read the poster near Basil Gummidge\nObj 2:\nBasil Gummidge is in Ost Forod.\nYou have found a wanted poster placing a bounty on your head at the behest of one Cuthbert Sprunt.\n* Talk to Basil Gummidge\n* Turn in Wanted Poster (Level 1)\nObj 3:\nBasil Gummidge is in Ost Forod.\nBasil Gummidge, the arbiter of Ost Forod, has agreed to ensure that Cuthbert Sprunt does not cheat when you challenge him to single combat. Basil is waiting to speak with you so you can travel together to the Sparring Circle.\n* Talk to Basil Gummidge and travel to the Sparring Circle\nObj 4:\nBasil Gummidge is in Ost Forod.\nYou have defeated Cuthbert Sprunt, despite his underhanded attempts to cheat at the competition, and should now speak with Basil Gummidge about the victory.\n* Talk to Basil Gummidge"},
{["next"]={1474},area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="14s 50c"}},d="Colbert was dismayed when he saw the bracelet you found, but he would not tell you why.",mobs={{locations={"13.06S, 55.30W"},name="Mincham"},{locations={"13.04S, 55.28W"},name="Colbert the Mad"}},category="North Downs",id=2256,scope="n/a",prev={2735},name="The Bracelet's Past",arcs="Mincham's Dream",level=27,c={"* The graves are located in the Fields of Fornost [11.1S, 57.1W]"},pois={{locations={"11.07S, 57.17W","11.06S, 57.16W"},name="Grave"}},minlevel=22,b="Colbert the Mad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMincham is at his camp.\nAccording to Colbert, the bracelet you found belongs to Mincham. Without explaining why, he asked you to give it to Mincham yourself.\n* Talk to Mincham\n* Turn in Golden Bracelet\nObj 2:\nThe graves of Mincham's wife and child are to the north-west near some burial mounds.\nUnsettled by your discovery of the bracelet his wife was buried with, Mincham asked you to investigate the graves of his wife and child.\n* Use Grave\n* Use Grave\nObj 3:\nMincham awaits you at his camp.\nYou found Mincham's child's grave undisturbed, but his wife's grave was open and empty. You should return to him with this news at once.\n* Talk to Mincham"},
{["next"]={99},area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="You are a guardian almost without equal, and the Free Peoples of Middle-earth are shielded by your arm and your will.",mobs={{locations={"15.13S, 103.27W"},name="Dourhand"},{locations={"15.34S, 101.59W"},name="Anglor"},{locations={"25.36S, 48.69W"},name="Teal Saddler"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Rollo Hemming"},{locations={"28.25S, 92.17W"},name="Gwathel"},{locations={"20.19S, 96.83W"},name="Mergeth"},{locations={"19.13N, 72.19W"},name="Mainio"},{locations={"19.37S, 100.44W"},name="Wáli"},{locations={"12.71S, 67.31W"},name="Tirnedhruith"},{locations={"50.46S, 8.07W"},name="Thandelen"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Garrett Beardsley"},{locations={"31.72S, 50.83W","31.71S, 50.83W"},name="Tralli"},{locations={"9.71S, 41.35W"},name="Dagorom"},{locations={"28.11S, 5.33W"},name="Mirdoron"}},category="Guardian",id=2257,scope="n/a",prev={82,168},requiredclasses="Guardian",name="The Bravest Deed is Selfless",arcs="The Bravest Deed",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Teal Saddler",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe dwarf Wáli is at the outpost of Noglond, south of Thorin's Hall and west of the dwarf-city of Gondamon in Ered Luin.\nYou have been told to speak to Wáli, a courageous guardian who may have some words for you.\n* Talk to Wáli"},
{["next"]={1427,2423},area="Nan Laeglin",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The chieftains of Nan Laeglin will soon hold a council under Glynn Brenin to decide how to treat with the emissaries of Isengard and the passage of the Grey Company through Enedwaith.",mobs={{locations={"66.46S, 17.32W"},name="Dufrig"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2258,scope="n/a",prev={2425},name="The Brenin's Council",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Dufrig",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe brehur of Lhanuch are in the brenin's hall in Lhanuch.\nDufrig has told you to earn the favour of the brehur of Lhanuch before Glynn Brenin's council comes to a decision on whether to bow to the demands of Isengard.\n* Complete 'A Weapon of Old'\n* Complete 'The Half-orcs'\n* Complete 'Signs Among the Ashes'\n* Complete 'Where There is Smoke....'\nObj 2:\nDufrig is in the brenin's hall in Lhanuch.\nYou should speak with Dufrig to enter the brenin's hall and observe the deliberations of the Council of Brehur.\n* Convince Glynn Brenin to reject the emissary's demands"},
{area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Taraghlan told you of a hunting-camp, Tyrn Lhuig, on the south-western edge of the great swamp of Malenhad.",mobs={{locations={"0.06S, 40.18W"},name="Taraghlan"},{locations={"1.78S, 33.29W"},name="Othran"}},category="Angmar",id=2259,scope="n/a",prev={2533},name="The Brimstone Swamp",receive={{val="Halchol",id="700031EF"}},level=43,c={"* The hunting-camp of Tyrn Lhuig is located at [1.9S, 33.2W]."},minlevel=38,b="Taraghlan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOthran is at Tyrn Lhuig, the hunting-camp in the south-western corner of Malenhad, east of Fasach-larran.\nTaraghlan has asked you to bring the supplies to his kinsman Othran at the hunting camp in Malenhad.\n* Talk to Othran\n* Turn in Hunting Supplies",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1880},area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="Many strange creatures have begun to appear in Evendim, not least of which are the fearsome salamanders.",mobs={{locations={"11.75S, 72.00W"},name="Humfrey Rumming"},{locations={"12.21S, 68.01W"},name="Calatherdir"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Refined Athelas Essence",id="70000F89"},{q="(x3)",val="Refined Celebrant Salve",id="7000228A"}},category="Evendim",id=2260,scope="n/a",name="The Burning Island",arcs="The Burning Island",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=33,c={"* To complete this quest you must speak with Humfrey Rumming at Tyl Ruinen [11.7S, 72.0W]"},minlevel=28,b="Calatherdir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe island of Tyl Ruinen on the west side of the lake, opposite Tinnudir, has become infested with salamanders.\nCalatherdir has asked you to make the journey to Tyl Ruinen and the ruin of Tollobel to investigate the salamanders that have appeared there.\n* Investigate Tyl Ruinen"},
{["next"]={1715},area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Uch-lûth were greatly displeased by the gift of meat presented to them, for they suspect the Grey Company of slaughtering their herds.",mobs={{locations={"65.10S, 16.43W"},name="Alun"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2261,scope="n/a",prev={106},name="The Butchered Herd",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,c={"* [64.9S, 15.8W]\n* [64.9S, 16.0W]\n* [64.9S, 16.2W]"},minlevel=60,b="Alun",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere may be dead oxen among the herds of the Uch-lûth at Uch Cadlus in the Windfells.\nAlun has asked you to examine the dead oxen among the herds of the Uch-lûth to determine what may have slain them.\nObj 2:\nThe Black Sow wanders the wilds of the Windfells.\nHaving determined that a great boar did indeed slay the oxen of the Uch-lûth, you should hunt down the Black Sow of the Windfells.\n* Defeat the Black Sow of the Windfells\nObj 3:\nAlun is at Uch Cadlus in the Windfells of Enedwaith.\nYou should return to Alun with news of your success.\n* Talk to Alun at Uch Cadlus"},
{["next"]={1053},area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Among the ruins in the southern reaches of Thrór's Coomb, several pillars with rune-carvings still stand. The messages on the pillars may speak of lost knowledge and should be recovered.",mobs={{locations={"65.57S, 8.48W"},name="Frithgeir"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2262,scope="n/a",prev={1522,1815},name="The Call of Our Fathers",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"69.36S, 9.33W","69.32S, 8.91W","69.34S, 8.49W","69.77S, 9.51W","69.01S, 8.61W"},name="Rune-pillar"}},minlevel=65,b="Frithgeir",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ruins on the southern hills lie to the south of Nár's Peak, through the mountain pass.\nFrithgeir has asked you to seek out the ruined pillars among the ancient dwarf-ruins and take rubbings of the runes found upon them.\n* Use Rune-pillar\nObj 2:\nFrithgeir is at Zudrugund within Nár's Peak, north of the ruins, through the mountain pass.\nYou should return to Frithgeir and present him with the rubbings of these pillars.\n* Talk to Frithgeir at Zudrugund"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="The craft of making jewellery is one that requires a steady hand and a precise eye, traits that can only be developed through training and experience.",mobs={{locations={"28.52S, 6.20W"},name="Glavroliel"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Ted Ragwort"},{locations={"17.92S, 53.69W"},name="Maud Mottershead"},{locations={"33.73S, 62.10W"},name="Peony Burrows"},{locations={"11.98S, 67.90W"},name="Priscilla Quince"},{locations={"31.36S, 66.04W"},name="Betony Hornblower"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Madge Woodsey"},{locations={"31.88S, 69.42W"},name="Briffo Burrows"},{locations={"22.84S, 66.54W","7.46S, 64.09W"},name="Ida Mabbitt"},{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Kobbi Stonestar"},{locations={"27.42S, 68.28W"},name="Hamo Brockhouse"},{locations={"28.21S, 92.66W"},name="Haldan"},{locations={"20.14S, 97.08W"},name="Gyrgir"},{locations={"34.60S, 75.42W"},name="Berylla Goodchild"},{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Nisti"}},category="Crafting",id=2263,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Call of Precious Things, Part I",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Dathi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nKobbi Stonestar is within the Forsaken Inn located on the edge of the Lone-lands, east of Bree.\nYou have been told to journey to the Forsaken Inn in the Lone-lands to speak with the great jeweller Kobbi Stonestar, if you wish to advance in your craft.\n* Talk to Kobbi Stonestar",traits={{val="Apprentice Jeweller Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="Every piece of jewellery you fashion brings your fingers greater skill and your eyes more clarity, but you still have need of instruction.",mobs={{locations={"28.52S, 6.20W"},name="Glavroliel"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Ted Ragwort"},{locations={"17.92S, 53.69W"},name="Maud Mottershead"},{locations={"33.73S, 62.10W"},name="Peony Burrows"},{locations={"11.98S, 67.90W"},name="Priscilla Quince"},{locations={"31.36S, 66.04W"},name="Betony Hornblower"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Madge Woodsey"},{locations={"31.88S, 69.42W"},name="Briffo Burrows"},{locations={"22.84S, 66.54W","7.46S, 64.09W"},name="Ida Mabbitt"},{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Kobbi Stonestar"},{locations={"27.42S, 68.28W"},name="Hamo Brockhouse"},{locations={"28.21S, 92.66W"},name="Haldan"},{locations={"20.14S, 97.08W"},name="Gyrgir"},{locations={"34.60S, 75.42W"},name="Berylla Goodchild"},{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Nisti"}},category="Crafting",id=2264,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Call of Precious Things, Part II",receive={{val="White Tree Trinket",id="700037AB"}},level=25,minlevel=20,b="Dathi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nKobbi Stonestar has apparently become a permanent resident of The Forsaken Inn of the Lone-lands.\nKobbi Stonestar is interested in your progress as a jeweller and has been asking about you.\n* Talk to Kobbi Stonestar\nObj 2:\nKobbi Stonestar is an apparently permanent resident of the Forsaken Inn of the Lone-lands.\nKobbi Stonestar has asked you to craft a White Tree Trinket to demonstrate your technique and has given you the recipe as well as his notes on the subject.\n* Turn in Delicate White Tree Mould\n* Turn in Polished Opal\n* Turn in Silver Ingot\nObj 3:\nKobbi Stonestar is apparently a permanent resident of the Forsaken Inn located in the Lone-lands.\nKobbi Stonestar is waiting to judge the craftsmanship of the White Tree Trinket he asked you to make.\n* Bring the White Tree Trinket to Kobbi Stonestar\n* Turn in White Tree Trinket (Level 15)",traits={{val="Journeyman Jeweller Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={255,2322},area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="You can see the shape of precious stones taking form before you have begun to carve them, but there are still fine techniques that escape you.",mobs={{locations={"26.51S, 53.73W"},name="Millicent Greenlake"},{locations={"28.52S, 6.20W"},name="Glavroliel"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Ted Ragwort"},{locations={"17.92S, 53.69W"},name="Maud Mottershead"},{locations={"33.73S, 62.10W"},name="Peony Burrows"},{locations={"11.98S, 67.90W"},name="Priscilla Quince"},{locations={"31.36S, 66.04W"},name="Betony Hornblower"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Madge Woodsey"},{locations={"31.88S, 69.42W"},name="Briffo Burrows"},{locations={"22.84S, 66.54W","7.46S, 64.09W"},name="Ida Mabbitt"},{locations={"27.42S, 68.28W"},name="Hamo Brockhouse"},{locations={"28.21S, 92.66W"},name="Haldan"},{locations={"20.14S, 97.08W"},name="Gyrgir"},{locations={"34.60S, 75.42W"},name="Berylla Goodchild"},{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Nisti"}},category="Crafting",id=2265,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Call of Precious Things, Part III",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Dathi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nMillicent Greenlake supervises construction at Thornley's work-site in the Bree-fields, north of the town of Bree.\nYou have been told to speak with Millicent Greenlake, supervising construction in the Bree-fields, to improve your jewelsmithing techniques. You have also been warned of her impatient nature.\n* Talk to Millicent Greenlake",traits={{val="Expert Jeweller Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Twenty-first Hall",zone="Moria",d="Your fingers are nimble and your eyes precise, allowing you to create stunning pieces that astound those who have not reached the same level of mastery.",mobs={{locations={"5.42S, 104.94W"},name="Helf"},{locations={"29.84S, 4.79W"},name="Merilos"},{locations={"15.49S, 67.70W"},name="Mírien"},{locations={"30.98S, 29.92W"},name="Berwyth"},{locations={"18.48S, 63.77W"},name="Mírdi"},{locations={"9.70S, 40.50W"},name="Daemirdan"},{locations={"14.54S, 51.07W"},name="Nimpiel"}},category="Crafting",id=2266,scope="Crafting Advancement",prev={255,2321},name="The Call of Precious Things, Part IV",receive={{val="Memorium Ring",id="700037CD"}},level=40,minlevel=35,b="Gaddi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe master jeweller Merilos is in Rivendell, by the Spire of Meeting west of the House of Elrond.\nYou have been told that Merilos asks to speak with all jewellers who attain your level of skill.\n* Talk to Merilos\nObj 2:\nMerilos gave you the recipe for a memorium ring and her notes on its fashioning.\nMerilos, a rather intimidating jeweller in Rivendell, has asked you to craft a memorium ring that she can examine to determine your worth as a jeweller.\n* Turn in Gondorian Sapphire\n* Turn in Platinum Ingot\nObj 3:\nMerilos is in Rivendell, by the Spire of Meeting west of the House of Elrond.\nMaster-jeweller Merilos asked you to fashion a memorium ring to prove your understanding of the craft, and most likely, to teach you a lesson of some sort.\n* Bring the memorium ring to Merilos\n* Turn in Memorium Ring (Level 35)",traits={{val="Artisan Jeweller Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Eregion",area="Glâd Ereg",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Dunlendings have established a lumber-camp in the wooded land of Sâd Rechu, where they collect wood for the use of Saruman's craftsmen.",mobs={{locations={"40.15S, 16.48W"},name="Inufileg"}},selectoneof={{val="Tudur's Challenge",id=70016065},{val="Tudur's Curse",id="700163A6"}},category="Eregion",id=2267,scope="n/a",prev={2421},name="The Captain of Sâd Rechu",arcs="The Wood of Sâd Rechu",level=49,c={"* The Sâd Rechu Mustering-horn is in Pend Eregion [42.2S, 13.0W]"},pois={{locations={"42.19S, 12.99W"},name="Sâd Rechu Mustering-horn"}},minlevel=44,b="Inufileg",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe battle-horn is in the camp east of the pond at Sâd Rechu, east of Gwingris.\nInufileg has instructed you to use the Dunlendings' battle-horn to issue a challenge to their leader, Tudur.\n* Kill 1 Tudur\n* Use Sâd Rechu Mustering-horn\nObj 2:\nInufileg is at Gwingris, west of Sâd Rechu.\nYou should return to Gwingris and tell Inufileg of your success.\n* Talk to Inufileg at Gwingris",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},zone="Moria",area="Nud-melek",money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="Now that the Puzzle of the Carvings has been solved, Mögr thinks the carver's stash is within reach.",selectoneof={{val="Melkólf's Gift",id="700163B0"},{val="Melkólf's Art",id="700163FB"},{val="Mögr's Armour",id="700163E1"}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=2268,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1732},name="The Carver's Stash",arcs="Stonecarver's Stash",level=55,c={"* You will find several hide-bound books in some Rubble in Nud-melek at [8.5S, 103.9W], but before you can search the rubble you will have to defeat the signature orc and the troll that are nearby."},pois={{locations={"8.50S, 103.95W"},name="Rubble"}},minlevel=50,b="Mögr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe riddle in the carvings seemed to suggest that treasure is south of the top of Khadar-zarâm, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nMögr believes the treasure can be found nearby in Nud-melek, but cautioned you that he knew naught regarding what might be living there or guarding it. He suggested you take a friend or two with you.\n* Use Rubble\nObj 2:\nMögr is in the Twenty-first Hall, north-west of Khadar-zarâm.\nMögr will want to see what the Stone-carver's stash actually is: several bound books containing treatises on stone-carving and decoration.\n* Talk to Mögr\n* Turn in Stonecarver's Legacy"},
{["next"]={1123},area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Thrasi, a dwarf hunter, rescued a mother lynx while out hunting bears. He was attacked by a flock of hendrevail and had to leave the mother's cubs behind.",mobs={{locations={"21.59S, 94.17W"},name="Thrasi"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2269,scope="n/a",name="The Cat's Meow",arcs="The Cat's Meow",level=10,c={"* The Abandoned Den can be found in Haudh Lin at [20.8S, 94.3W]"},minlevel=6,b="Thrasi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe abandoned den should be north of the hunter's lodge near the standing stones.\nThrasi hurt his leg while rescuing an injured lynx from hendrevail and asked you to retrieve the surviving cubs.\n* Search the abandoned bear den\nObj 2:\nThere are hendrevail throughout the woods.\nA frightened lynx-cub cowers in an old den, too scared to venture out into the light. You must defeat the hendrevail lurking nearby to prove that you mean it no harm.\n* Defeat hendrevail\nObj 3:\nCoax the lynx-cub from its den.\nWith the hendrevail defeated, the lynx-cub seems to feel safe enough to leave its den.\n* Coax the lynx-cub from its den\nObj 4:\nThrasi is back at the hunter's lodge, south of here.\nYou recovered the lynx-cub as Thrasi requested. Return it to him at the hunter's lodge.\n* Talk to Thrasi\n* Turn in Lynx-cub",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1762},area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+700 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="Oflár believes the Cauldron of Death is located near the central lake of Imlad Balchorth.",mobs={{locations={"6.94N, 25.86W"},name="Oflár"}},selectoneof={{val="Helthail",id=70001364},{val="Oflár's Shoulder Guards",id=70001363},{val="Cauldron Purger",id=70001365}},category="Angmar",id=2270,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1728},name="The Cauldron of Death",arcs="Cauldron of Death",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Oflár",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Cauldron of Death and its guardian are before the central lake of Imlad Balchorth, west from Myrkworth.\nOflár has asked you to fight your way to the Cauldron of Death and destroy its guardian. He suggested you gather allies.\n* Find the Cauldron of Death\n* Defeat the Cauldron's guardian\nObj 2:\nOflár is at Myrkworth, east from the Cauldron of Death.\nWith the Iron-bound Giant destroyed, the Cauldron of Death ceased spewing forth wights, at least for now. You should return and report your success to Oflár.\n* Talk to Oflár"},
{["next"]={1090},area="Taur Orthon",zone="Forochel",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="You hunted the moose as Cenlieg requested, but the lore-master's bear-friend did not like the meat you had given it.",mobs={{locations={"3.00N, 58.07W"},name="Cenlieg"}},category="Forochel",id=2271,scope="n/a",prev={1122},name="The Choicest Cut",arcs="The Lost Fellowship Lore-Master",receive={{val="Bag of Weak Blasting Powder",id="7000E964"}},level=45,c={"* Silvan Thirty-Point is southwest of the lake"},minlevel=40,b="Cenlieg",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe great elk can be found to the south-west of Kauppa-kohta.\nCenlieg has asked you to kill the great elk and bring its flank to him.\n* Turn in Buck-flank\nObj 2:\nCenlieg is at Kauppa-kohta, east from where you found the elk-buck.\nYou should return to Cenlieg with the elk-flank you collected.\n* Bring Silvan Thirty-Point's flank to Cenlieg\n* Turn in Buck-flank"},
{area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+500 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Fotri has agreed to give you directions to the famed Lossoth capital, Sûri-kylä.",mobs={{locations={"19.02N, 70.79W"},name="Lothrandir"},{locations={"9.32N, 81.09W"},name="Fotri"}},category="Forochel",id=2272,scope="n/a",prev={865,1492},name="The City in the Ice",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Fotri",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMake your way far to the east and north to Sûri-kylä, the City in the Ice.\n* Talk to Lothrandir",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={480},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="7s 42c"}},d="Elrond told you of Aragorn's youthful journey to Annúminas and has given his approval that Narsil be reforged.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},category="Evendim",id=2273,scope="n/a",prev={105},name="The City of His Fathers",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",level=32,minlevel=27,b="Elrond",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAragorn is in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nMaster Elrond told you of Aragorn's youth and agreed that Narsil must be reforged. He has decided on a name for the new sword: Andúril, Flame of the West.\n* Talk to Aragorn in Rivendell"},
{["next"]={2294},area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="In the valley below, in the eastern reaches of Thrór's Coomb, gwiber have begun building nests to swell their numbers.",mobs={{locations={"65.57S, 8.48W"},name="Frithgeir"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2274,scope="n/a",prev={2356},name="The Clutch Collapses",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"67.25S, 9.32W","67.73S, 9.31W","67.97S, 8.49W","67.92S, 8.91W","67.91S, 8.55W","67.44S, 9.24W","67.52S, 8.71W"},name="Gwiber-eggs"}},minlevel=65,b="Frithgeir",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGwiber-nests may be found to the south of Zudrugund.\nFrithgeir has asked you to hunt down nests of gwiber-eggs and destroy them.\n* Use Gwiber-eggs\nObj 2:\nFrithgeir is at Zudrugund, north of the gwiber-nests.\nYou should return to Frithgeir and inform him that you have destroyed many gwiber-eggs.\n* Talk to Frithgeir at Zudrugund"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="The Cooling Chamber is an ancient structure used to collect and cool the hot steam from the forges below.",selectoneof={{val="Tracker's Boots",id="70017CF1"},{val="Slagvi's Sword",id=70016106},{val="Celeglos",id="700163A2"},{val="Gloves of the Cooling Chamber",id=70016079}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2275,scope="n/a",prev={1955},name="The Cooling Chamber",arcs="Goblins of the Great Delving",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Slagvi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSlagvi is at the Dolven-view camp.\nThe guards at the Dolven-view saw several goblins drag another of their kind into the Cooling Chamber. Slagvi wishes to learn what is going on within.\n* Explore the Cooling Chamber with Slagvi\nObj 2:\nSlagvi is at the Dolven-view camp.\nInside the Cooling Chamber, you discovered the goblins of Moria were torturing a Mordor goblin for information. You attacked and slew many before being chased off by the Warg-riders of Durin's Way. You should speak with Slagvi regarding your experiences in the Cooling Chamber.\n* Talk to Slagvi at the Dolven-view camp"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+500 with Elves of Rivendell"}},d="The Corcur of the Misty Mountains fell under the sway of the Angmarim that now control Helegrod.",mobs={{locations={"31.65S, 15.18W"},name="Elladan"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2276,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={1164},name="The Corcur Arise",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Elrond",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElladan is at Thorenhad, his camp among the Bruinen Gorges, west of Rivendell.\nLord Elrond has asked you to bring news of the Corcur now living within Helegrod under the power of Angmar to his son Elladan, who has fought long against them.\n* Talk to Elladan"},
{area="Northern Emyn Uial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},d="Lithuifin gave you a cleansing draught with which to purify the corrupted statue of Elendil on Tyl Ruinen.",mobs={{locations={"6.05S, 72.01W"},name="Lithuifin"}},category="Evendim",id=2277,scope="n/a",name="The Corrupted Statue",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,pois={{locations={"12.62S, 72.90W"},name="Corrupted Statue"}},minlevel=33,b="Lithuifin",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe corrupted statue of Elendil is on one of the islands of Tyl Ruinen, to the south.\nLithuifin gave you a draught to cleanse one of the statues of Elendil on Tyl Ruinen.\n* Use Corrupted Statue\n* Turn in Cleansing Draught",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Arohir of Esteldín has bade you seek the hidden camp of Gath Forthnír in the far north, somewhere east of the gates of Carn Dûm, and once there to speak with Annábla.",mobs={{locations={"9.63S, 41.42W"},name="Arohir"}},category="Reputation",id=2278,scope="n/a",prev={2884},name="The Council of the North",level=45,c={"* Talk to Annábla in Gath Forthnír"},minlevel=40,b="Arohir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpeak with Annábla of Gath Forthnír.\n* Talk to Annábla",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eldgang"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Two of the Orc-tribes of Angmar, the Blogmal and the Tarkrîp are in conflict over mining rights in Bornabar.",mobs={{locations={"10.82N, 15.54W"},name="Jónsi"}},category="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",id=2279,scope="n/a",t="Raid",name="The Craft of the Enemy",receive={{val="Obsidian Rock-shard",id="7000C7BE"},{q="(x2)",val="Scrap of Rift-iron Ore",id="7000C7CC"}},level=50,minlevel=45,b="Jónsi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarz and Zurm are in Bornabar, within the crumbling seal below Iorelen's camp.\nJónsi has asked you to enter the mines of the Orcs and defeat the Gorthorog-overseers, Barz and Zurm.\n* Defeat Barz\n* Defeat Zurm\nObj 2:\nJónsi is at Iorelen's Camp.\nYou should return to Jónsi and tell him of your victory against Barz and Zurm.\n* Talk to Jónsi"},
{["next"]={2564},area="Nan Sirannon",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Crebain out of Dunland in the service of Saruman spy out the crevices of the Redhorn Gate, threatening the efforts of the Elves in Eregion.",mobs={{locations={"50.52S, 7.80W"},name="Authlanc"}},category="Eregion",id=2280,scope="n/a",name="The Crebain of Caradhras",arcs="Crebain of Caradhras",level=50,c={"* The crebain are scattered at Tâl Caradhras"},minlevel=45,b="Authlanc",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCrebain can be found north-east of Echad Dúnann in the Redhorn Gate.\nAuthlanc has asked that you defeat crebain in the Redhorn Gate.\n* Defeat crebain (14)\nObj 2:\nAuthlanc can be found at Echad Dúnann south-east of the Redhorn Gate.\nYou should return to Authlanc and tell him of your success.\n* Talk to Authlanc at Echad Dúnann",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2494},area="Tâl Bruinen",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="21s 70c"}},d="Wistan has told you that he saw a creeping shadow along the banks of the Bruinen that he thinks may have been the same creature Adwold encountered.",mobs={{locations={"36.91S, 14.21W"},name="Wistan"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2281,scope="n/a",prev={2441},name="The Creeping Shadow",arcs="The Creeping Shadow",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Lhinestad Draught",id="7000EFBF"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Healing Draught",id="7000EFC2"}},level=41,pois={{locations={"39.01S, 14.23W","37.82S, 14.34W","37.47S, 14.59W"},name="Chewed Fishbones"}},minlevel=36,b="Wistan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nClues to some means of trapping the creature seen by Adwold and Wistan will surely be found along the banks of the Bruinen, east of Echad Candelleth.\nWistan has decided that he wants to catch the mysterious creature he and Adwold have seen and has asked you to check the banks of the Bruinen for clues to the creature's habits.\n* Use Chewed Fishbones\nObj 2:\nWistan is at his campfire at Echad Candelleth, in Tâl Bruinen.\nYou have learned that the creature seems to enjoy fish and should report your discovery to the hunter Wistan.\n* Talk to Wistan"},
{area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Tûm, a mystic of the Algraig clans known as a Derudh, told you of an old woman who plies the waters of the river. He believes this crone may know more about the spirits they call the Forest Lords than any other.",mobs={{locations={"67.09S, 22.78W","72.32S, 22.72W"},name="The River-woman"},{locations={"69.17S, 22.35W"},name="Tûm"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2282,scope="n/a",prev={2360},name="The Crone's Ferry",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Tûm",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe old woman Tûm spoke of can occasionally be found along the banks of the river that passes through the Mournshaws.\nTûm suggested you find the old woman who plies the river of the Mournshaws. It is possible that she knows something of the Forest Lords.\n* Talk to the old woman of the river in the Mournshaws\nObj 2:\nCun Annun can be found throughout the Mournshaws.\nThe River-woman has offered you passage along the river's length if you can bring her the teeth of the Cun Annun that haunt the forest in the Mournshaws.\n* Turn in Cun Annun Tooth\nObj 3:\nThe River-woman may be found along the banks of the river in the Mournshaws.\nYou should return to the River-woman with the Cun Annun teeth that you have collected.\n* Talk to The River-woman\n* Turn in Cun Annun Tooth"},
{reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="Taur Morvith",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Cargûl, Mâb Rhûnadan, dwells among the ruins of Sâd Morangol, using a corrupt altar to summon fell spirits to Taur Morvith.",mobs={{locations={"17.96S, 50.30W"},name="Ianudirel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2283,scope="n/a",prev={672},name="The Dark Apprentice",arcs="The Fell Ruins",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=64,c={"* The Corrupted Altar is in Sâd Morangol at [18.6S, 48.7W]\n* Destroying the Altar will summon Mâb Rhûnadan"},pois={{locations={"18.64S, 48.74W"},name="Corrupted Altar"}},minlevel=59,b="Ianudirel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMâb Rhûnadan and his altar may be found at Sâd Morangol.\nIanudirel has asked you to destroy the altar of Mâb Rhûnadan or defeat the Cargûl himself.\n* Defeat Mâb Rhûnadan\n* Use Corrupted Altar\nObj 2:\nIanudirel is just south of the bridge at Krul Lugu.\nYou should return to Ianudirel with news of your success.\n* Talk to Ianudirel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2553},area="Esteldín",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+1200 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},money={{val="44s 10c"}},d="Ranger-scouts reported that there were wraiths within the ruins of Fornost.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"9.61S, 41.05W"},name="Istuienn"}},category="Fornost",id=2284,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Darkness Within",arcs="Wraiths of Fornost",receive={{val="Ríangol",id=70009310}},level=42,c={"* The hilts do not stack, and therefore the player will need four available inventory slots to carry the hilts until the quest is completed.\n* The Elite Master and Nemesis level bosses that drop these hilts are Megoriath, Rhavameldir, Brogadan, and Remmenaeg.\n* The hilts are named after the creature that drops them."},minlevel=37,b="Halbarad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIstuienn can be found outside the library in Esteldín.\nHalbarad suggested that you speak with Istuienn, a lore-master of the Rangers. She might know how to defeat the wraiths of Fornost.\n* Talk to Istuienn\nObj 2:\nThe morgul-hilts are in the possession of the four wraiths within Fornost.\nIstuienn believes that you may be able to find and recover the hilts of the four morgul-blades discussed in Laerdan's text inside the ruins of Fornost.\n* Turn in Remmenaeg's Morgul-hilt\n* Turn in Brogadan's Morgul-hilt\n* Turn in Rhavameldir's Morgul-hilt\n* Turn in Megoriath's Morgul-hilt\nObj 3:\nIstuienn is outside the library in Esteldín.\nYou should bring the four morgul-hilts to Istuienn at once.\n* Talk to Istuienn\n* Turn in Remmenaeg's Morgul-hilt\n* Turn in Brogadan's Morgul-hilt\n* Turn in Rhavameldir's Morgul-hilt\n* Turn in Megoriath's Morgul-hilt"},
{area="Falathlorn",zone="Ered Luin",d="Langlas had given you a scroll to bring to Bregar at Duillond. Bregar recognized the poem as the \\qLay of Nimrodel\\q and realized that a passage from the Lay might be enough to convince Toronn to remain in Middle-earth.",mobs={{locations={"28.07S, 92.36W"},name="Toronn"},{locations={"24.02S, 92.57W"},name="Bregar"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2285,scope="n/a",prev={1552},name="The Days Ahead",arcs="Brotherly Bond",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Bregar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nToronn is at Celondim, south of Duillond.\nBregar has asked you to take the scroll to Toronn in the hope that it will convince his brother to remain.\n* Talk to Toronn\n* Turn in The Lay of Nimrodel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2659},area="North Trollshaws",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Thoroniel believes that the Wovenvales are infested with two different broods of spider, and she has formed a plan to deal with both of them.",mobs={{locations={"28.57S, 19.45W"},name="Thoroniel"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2286,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={877},name="The Deadly Broods",arcs="Fighting the Brood",level=40,minlevel=35,b="Thoroniel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTwo broods of spiders make their home in the Wovenvales of the North Trollshaws.\nThoroniel has asked you to collect fangs from the two different spider-broods in the North Trollshaws: the trapdoor-spiders and the flesh-gnawer spiders.\n* Turn in Trapdoor Fang\n* Turn in Flesh-gnawer Fang\nObj 2:\nThoroniel is just outside the Wovenvales of the North Trollshaws.\nThoroniel is waiting for you to return with the fangs you collected from each of the broods of spider in the North Trollshaws.\n* Talk to Thoroniel\n* Turn in Trapdoor Fang\n* Turn in Flesh-gnawer Fang"},
{area="Northern Barrow-downs",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="3s 20c"}},d="Tobold Leafcutter, an aged and well-to-do resident of Bree, was interested in learning the history of the Barrow-downs and joined the expedition that headed into the Barrow-downs.",mobs={{locations={"31.74S, 56.24W"},name="Tobold Leafcutter"}},category="Bree-land",id=2287,scope="n/a",name="The Dead Spire",arcs="History in the Barrow-downs",level=18,minlevel=13,b="Tobold Leafcutter",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Dead Spire lies due south of the northern entrance to the Barrow-downs. Tobold Leafcutter waits for you between the Barrow-downs and the Old Forest.\nTobold Leafcutter wants you to gather rune-marked stone-fragments from near the Dead Spire, then return to him.\n* Bring the stone-fragments to Tobold Leafcutter\n* Turn in Carved Stone",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1164},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+500 with Thorin's Hall"}},d="Lord Elrond believes the dwarf Glóin should be warned of the evil that might hide within Helegrod, not far to the north of his camp in the Misty Mountains.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2288,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={2076},name="The Deeds of Durin",arcs="Stirrings Within Helegrod",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Elrond",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlóin is at his camp in the Misty Mountains, north of Rivendell.\nLord Elrond asked you to warn Glóin of the threat rumoured to be growing within the walls of Helegrod.\n* Talk to Glóin"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="44s 24c"}},d="The Grand Stair once stood at the foot of a great crossroads within Moria. At the height of the great city, it led to all areas of the halls and was a majestic wonder to behold. Now it has fallen to the care of Igash, a lieutenant of the Moria Orc-leader Mazog. Igash assembled the forces of Orcs and trolls within Moria in one place and has collected tribute from each to one day bring to the leader of the Orcs. For now, each tribe vies for favour from the lieutenant, a fanatical follower of Mazog.",mobs={{locations={"11.20S, 106.74W"},name="Ossur"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2289,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Deep Drums",arcs="The Grand Stair",receive={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Legend",id="7001F259"}},level=58,minlevel=57,b="Ossur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOssur is at the Orc-watch.\nOssur has asked you to help him against the Orcs and trolls of the Grand Stair. Once satisified, you will earn a portion of the respect needed to earn favour from Ossur to satisfy Avar and his task at watching the Grand Stair.\n* Defeat the Orcs and trolls in the Grand Stair\n* Complete the task involving the troll-handlers within the Grand Stair\nObj 2:\nOssur is at the Orc-watch.\nYou should return to Ossur and tell him that you completed the tasks focusing on the trolls of Moria.\n* Talk to Ossur at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nimrodel",zone="Lothlórien",money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="You have been acknowledged as a friend of Lothlórien through your efforts on behalf of the Elves.",mobs={{locations={"12.10S, 71.09W"},name="Bahanneth"},{locations={"16.22S, 73.50W","15.03S, 66.39W"},name="Haldir"},{locations={"13.48S, 72.46W","15.77S, 72.51W","16.20S, 72.48W"},name="Galadhrim Lookout"}},category="Lothlórien",id=2290,scope="n/a",name="The Defence of Fanuidhol",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Lothlórien Sentinel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBahanneth is at Talan Fanuidhol to the north.\nYou have been instructed to speak with Bahanneth, who will tell you how best you might aid the defenders there in thwarting the Orcs that foray out of Moria.\n* Talk to Bahanneth at Talan Fanuidhol",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Naethmunn has asked you to lend your aid to the Ranger Pantescal, defending the ruins of House Brumbar in Parth Aduial.",mobs={{locations={"12.73S, 66.98W"},name="Naethmunn"}},category="Evendim",id=2291,scope="n/a",prev={2666},name="The Defence of House Brumbar",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=35,c={"* Pantescal is at [10.4S, 66.3W]"},minlevel=30,b="Naethmunn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe remains of House Brumbar are in Parth Aduial, north-east of Tinnudir. Naethmunn told you to cross the bridge to the mainland and then follow the shoreline north until you see the few walls that remain of House Brumbar.\nNaethmunn has asked you to lend your aid to Pantescal, currently planning the defence of an important Dúnedain site against a crowd of boggarts.\n* Talk to Pantescal\nObj 2:\nNaethmunn is at the Ranger camp on Tinnudir, in Evendim, south-west of House Brumbar.\nYou defended House Brumbar from the band of boggarts that threatened it and should now return to Naethmunn with the tale of your success.\n* Talk to Naethmunn"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",d="Many Guardians wish to be Defenders of the Free, but not all can accomplish their goals alone.",mobs={{locations={"15.46S, 97.38W"},name="Ingthor"}},category="Guardian",id=2292,scope="n/a",name="The Defender of the Free:  Lending a Hand",receive={{val="Mark of Victory (Level 1)",id=70018341}},level=58,minlevel=58,b="Ingthor",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Dark Delvings lie in the south-eastern reaches of the Foundations of Stone.\nIngthor has instructed you to help a fellow Guardian complete his or her final task at the Dark Delvings.\n* Defeat Nightshine\nObj 2:\nIngthor is just outside the Dark Delvings.\nWith Nightshine slain, you should return to Ingthor with news of your success.\n* Return to Ingthor",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2802},area="Taur Orthon",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="After fighting the wolves back to the edges of the forest, the Lossoth are confident that the beasts can be prevented from doing more damage if the den-mother is slain.",mobs={{locations={"2.79N, 57.99W"},name="Santtu"},{locations={"4.13N, 59.88W"},name="Urho"}},selectoneof={{val="Rugged Silvan-hide Shoes",id="7000E5B5"},{val="Thin Silvan-hide Boots",id="7000E5AE"},{val="Sturdy Silvan-hide Boots",id="7000E5B2"}},category="Forochel",id=2293,scope="n/a",prev={3252},name="The Den-mother",arcs="Wolves at the Door",level=45,c={"* The den-mother can be found in a small island in the nearby lake at [2.9N, 60.5W]"},minlevel=40,b="Urho",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe den-mother may be found on an island near the lake's western shore.\nUrho has asked you to seek out the den-mother of the wolf-pack and defeat her.\n* Defeat the den-mother\nObj 2:\nSanttu is at Kauppa-kohta, on the eastern shore of the lake.\nNow that you have defeated the wolves' den-mother, you should return to Santtu with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Santtu"},
{["next"]={1854},area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Umfrë told you of a small community of Dunlendings who are chosen by their clans to enter the Mournshaws and commune with the spirits who live there. He believes that they might know of a way through the deep woods into the south.",mobs={{locations={"67.65S, 21.86W"},name="Enit"},{locations={"66.60S, 21.49W"},name="Umfrë"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2294,scope="n/a",prev={2467},name="The Derudhs' Circle",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,pois={{locations={"67.42S, 21.87W","67.22S, 21.56W","67.44S, 20.59W","67.14S, 20.88W","67.45S, 22.29W","67.51S, 21.42W","66.88S, 21.67W","67.07S, 21.28W","67.01S, 22.14W","67.37S, 21.02W","67.49S, 22.61W","67.35S, 20.79W","67.09S, 20.52W","67.17S, 22.41W","66.86S, 20.62W","67.07S, 21.89W","67.23S, 22.68W"},name="Wild Berries"}},minlevel=60,b="Umfrë",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBerries may be found along the forest paths in the Mournshaws.\nUmfrë suggests that you gather berries as a tithe to the Derudh of the Mournshaws before you approach them.\n* Collect wild berries in the Mournshaws (12 Wild Berries )\nObj 2:\nThe Derudh of the Mournshaws may be found at a stone circle called Galar Culch to the south of Echad Daervunn.\nUmfrë told you to approach the Derudh with an offering of berries.\n* Talk to Enit\n* Turn in Wild Berries\nObj 3:\nEnit is at Galar Culch, south of Echad Daervunn.\nEnit the Derudh may know a way through the Mournshaws into Dunland.\n* Talk to Enit at Galar Culch"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="The Black Númenórean that sits in Ost Elendil is named Balhest. He is a powerful foe, but he is not the only evil that resides now in that place. We have learned that the passage into the throne room where Balhest commands his forces is guarded by the Cargûl known as Guloth. If you are to defeat Balhest, you will first need to do something about Guloth.\nHe possesses some terrible power over creatures of shadow, drawing strength out of the darkness with which he commands them to his will. You must somehow sever Guloth's ability to strengthen the fell spirits under his command.\nOst Elendil lies across the bridge of Ariant. Go there only if you are able and willing to face not only Balhest, lieutenant of Amarthiel, but also Guloth the Cargûl. If the battle has drawn me elsewhere by the time you return, report of your victory to Captain-General Daerdan at Echad Garthadir, the Ranger-encampment here in the city.",category="Annúminas",id=2295,scope="n/a",name="The Door-warden of the Inner Chamber",receive={{val="Annúminas Mark",id="700216BF"}},level=40,minlevel=35,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Cargûl Guloth is inside Ost Elendil, beyond the bridge of Ariant on the highest level of Annúminas.\nLegrindavor has warned you that Balhest is defended by a fearsome Cargûl, Guloth by name, who wields power over creatures of shadow.\n* Kill 1 Guloth",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Carn Dûm",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+900 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="The drake-queen rules the wilds of Urugarth, spawning broods of drakelings that ravage the countryside.",mobs={{locations={"12.32N, 31.84W"},name="Esmë"}},selectoneof={{val="Esmë's Jacket",id="700021F9"},{val="Egg Smasher",id="700021FA"}},category="Urugarth",id=2296,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2884,1742},name="The Drake-queen's Brood",level=50,pois={{locations={"9.00N, 30.27W","9.01N, 30.28W","8.54N, 30.24W","8.71N, 30.18W","8.92N, 30.25W","9.00N, 30.15W","8.92N, 30.24W","8.72N, 30.16W","8.83N, 30.19W","8.72N, 30.17W","8.56N, 30.15W","8.54N, 30.23W","8.56N, 30.13W","8.81N, 30.18W"},name="Drake-egg"}},minlevel=45,b="Esmë",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe drake-queen and her brood of eggs lies in Urugarth to the west of Tármunn Sûrsa.\nEsmë advised you to destroy the eggs of the drake-queen.\n* Use Drake-egg\nObj 2:\nEsmë is at Tármunn Súrsa, east of Urugarth.\nYou should return to Esmë with news of your success.\n* Talk to Esmë"},
{["next"]={2735},area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="13s"}},d="Colbert has sent you off into the fields of Fornost in search of the lost girl Idalene.",mobs={{locations={"17.88S, 53.93W"},name="Dallin Endholder"},{locations={"13.04S, 55.28W"},name="Colbert the Mad"}},selectoneof={{val="Túronn (Level 25)",id="700017F4"},{val="Endholder's Boots",id="700017F3"}},category="North Downs",id=2297,scope="n/a",prev={2545},name="The Dream Voice",arcs="The Search for Idalene",level=26,minlevel=21,b="Colbert the Mad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIdalene is to the north-west of Mincham's camp, north of Trestlebridge.\nColbert has sent you out looking for Idalene with a plethora of dire warnings about the hazards of Deadmen's Dike.\n* Find Idalene\nObj 2:\nDallin Endholder is back in Trestlebridge.\nHaving driven off a fell spirit that had somehow been possessing Idalene, you should return to Dallin Endholder and tell him what happened.\n* Talk to Dallin Endholder"},
{area="The Drownholt",zone="Mirkwood",money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="Athradnir, a Galadhrim stationed at the Haunted Inn, wishes to convey a message to Laidhriel at Estolad Mernael.",mobs={{locations={"16.73S, 54.61W"},name="Laidhriel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2298,scope="n/a",name="The Drowned Wood",receive={{val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,minlevel=58,b="Athradnir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe second part of the Golden Host set off south, to the drowned part of the wood known as the Drownholt.\nYou should seek Estolad Mernael, the camping place of the Elves in the Drownholt, so that the Elves stationed in the Dourstocks can maintain communication with their brethren nearby.\n* Talk to Laidhriel in the Drownholt",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1522,2330,1815,654},area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="This letter reveals that a group of the Draig-lûth are in the process of making plans to send men to kill anyone hiding in an old dwarf home.",mobs={{locations={"65.57S, 8.48W"},name="Frithgeir"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2299,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="The Dwarves' Demise",receive={{val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Ruddy Parchment",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe dwarf-hall can be found high within a mountain pass, north of the river on the north-west face of Thrór's Coomb.\nAs the note reveals a threat upon those that make their home in the heights of the mountains, you may wish to warn them.\n* Travel to the dwarf-hall in Thrór's Coomb"},
{["next"]={75},area="Rushock Bog",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="According to Filibert Bolger, his cow, Daffodil, was stolen by a dwarf named Olwir; however, Bounder Chubb hesitates to accuse a dwarf of cow-theft without evidence.",mobs={{locations={"27.92S, 75.94W"},name="Ulfar"},{locations={"28.23S, 75.84W"},name="Bounder Chubb"}},selectoneof={{val="Ulfar's Hammer",id="70000DED"},{q="(x3)",val="Pork Sausage",id=70003362}},category="Shire",id=2300,scope="n/a",prev={2267},name="The Dwarves of Needlehole",arcs="Beast of the Bog",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Bounder Chubb",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nUlfar is at the dwarf buildings north of Needlehole.\nIn order to avoid angering the dwarves with accusations of theft, Bounder Chubb told you to obtain the aid of the dwarves through their overseer, Ulfar. Chubb believes that Ulfar might be able to point out any potential thieves among his folk.\n* Talk to Ulfar\nObj 2:\nThe dwarf-hunters prowl the northern and eastern sections of Rushock Bog. The bog lies to the south-east of Needlehole.\nWhen you told Ulfar the tale of Filibert's cow, and Olwir's involvement, he wasn't surprised. A number of dwarves of low character have been passing through Needlehole lately, and Olwir seemed to be the worst of them. Ulfar has asked you to acquire letters from the dwarf-hunters that he suspects of working for Olwir.\n* Bring the orders to Ulfar\n* Turn in Dourhand Orders"},
{["next"]={2559},area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Wald Sandson told you that Billina, Farmer Sandson's best hen, has stopped laying eggs, and that Farmer Sandson is considering butchering her if she does not start laying again.",mobs={{locations={"32.01S, 74.35W"},name="Wald Sandson"}},category="Shire",id=2301,scope="n/a",prev={3235},name="The Early Bird",arcs="The Sky is Falling",level=6,minlevel=2,b="Wald Sandson",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBillina is in the yard at Sandson's Farm.\nWald Sandson has asked you to see if you can discover what is wrong with Billina.\n* Examine Billina\nObj 2:\nWald Sandson can be found on Sandson's Farm, north and east of Michel Delving.\nNow that you have learned what ailed Billina, you should talk to Wald Sandson again.\n* Talk to Wald Sandson"},
{zone="Angmar",area="Ram Dúath",money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Lehma-koti is a small earthkin camp just over the border of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"3.07S, 39.02W"},name="Chief Tuokki"}},category="Evendim",id=2302,scope="n/a",name="The Earthkin of Lehma-koti",level=40,minlevel=35,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLehma-koti is a small earthkin camp just over the border of Angmar.\n* Talk to Chief Tuokki",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Fordirith",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},d="Braigiar told you that the Dúnedain are not welcome in the halls of Lhanuch, for the Uch-lûth are wary of strangers.",mobs={{locations={"58.69S, 14.58W"},name="Braigiar"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2303,scope="n/a",name="The Edge of the Wild",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Braigiar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLhanuch lies far to the south of Echad Dagoras, in Nan Laeglin.\nBraigiar has asked you to seek entry into the Uch-lûth village of Lhanuch.\n* Approach the gates of Lhanuch\nObj 2:\nThe guard is at the entrance to the Brenin's Hall of Lhanuch.\nThe guard at the village gate instructed you to speak with the guard before the Brenin's Hall of Lhanuch.\n* Speak with the guard before the Brenin's Hall in Lhanuch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2377,2338},area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Enit was greatly angered and shamed by the spirit's rejection of her demands.\nIn her anger she has told you to speak with her elders upon a great hill in the center of the forest.",mobs={{locations={"67.65S, 21.86W"},name="Enit"},{locations={"69.17S, 22.35W"},name="Tûm"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2304,scope="n/a",prev={1854},name="The Elders",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Enit",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTûm, the elder of the Derudh, is at Gwaed Brun, south of Galar Culch.\nEnit has instructed you to speak with Tûm, the Derudh elder.\n* Talk to Tûm at Gwaed Brun"},
{area="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with The Eldgang"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Iorelen was sent to the Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu to investigate the activities of Angmar in the area and the existence of a deadly mushroom found there which could be used by the Enemy to create a terrible weapon. He is also seeking a race of giants of which he learned from Glorfindel at Rivendell.",mobs={{locations={"10.92N, 15.51W"},name="Iorelen"}},category="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",id=2305,scope="n/a",t="Raid",name="The Eldgang",receive={{val="Obsidian Rock-shard",id="7000C7BE"},{val="Scrap of Rift-iron Ore",id="7000C7CC"}},level=50,minlevel=45,b="Iorelen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Eldgang can be found deep within the Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu.\nIorelen has asked you to seek out signs of the Eldgang, the legendary Fire-giants of Nûrz Ghâshu.\nObj 2:\nIorelen is at Iorelen's Camp.\nYou should return to Iorelen with news of what you found within the Rift.\n* Talk to Iorelen"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="The Elves of Ered Luin remain to prepare for the last voyage of the Elves from Middle-earth, but also to ward Middle-earth from the evils that remain.",mobs={{locations={"20.44S, 97.20W"},name="Gailthin"},{locations={"18.92S, 95.23W"},name="Glamír"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2306,scope="n/a",name="The Elf-stone",arcs="Old Bones",level=13,minlevel=9,b="Gailthin",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlamir dwells at the ruins north-east of Gondamon, at the southern end of the Grimwater.\nGailthin gave you an Elf-stone and sent you to an Elf named Glamir, who may be able to help you against the wights of Haudh Lin.\n* Talk to Glamír\n* Turn in Elf-stone",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Falathlorn",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="After allowing Starkath to take the bow from him, Celairant is now certain that he is not worthy of the Elvish weapon.",mobs={{locations={"21.63S, 94.14W"},name="Celairant"},{locations={"23.88S, 92.60W"},name="Penglir"}},selectoneof={{val="Celairant's Boots",id="70019C27"},{val="Celariant's Shoes",id="70019C36"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2307,scope="n/a",prev={2019},name="The Elf-sword",arcs="An Incorrupt Heart",level=15,c={"* The Elf-friend Sword is in Emyn Hoedh at [18.7S, 93.8W]"},minlevel=11,b="Penglir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe sword Elvellon can be found at a grave marker amongst the mounds of the Edain, north-east of Gondamon. Celairant is at the hunter's lodge, west of Kheledûl.\nPenglir has asked you to retrieve a sword which he placed by his companion's grave long ago and take it to Celairant.\n* Bring the Elf-sword to Celairant\n* Turn in Elf-friend Sword"},
{area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="The Elves of Eregion need the help of experienced adventurers.\nAn Explorer of Eregion has asked you to travel to the Elven outpost of Gwingris in Eregion, to the south of Rivendell.  Once you arrive you should look for the Elf Daegennan.",mobs={{locations={"39.99S, 16.26W"},name="Daegennan"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2308,scope="n/a",name="The Elves of Eregion",c={"* Daegennan is at Gwingris in Eregion"},level=48,minlevel=48,b="Maerhiniath",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDaegennan is at Gwingris in Eregion.\nYou were instructed to seek out the Elf Daegennan.\n* Talk to Daegennan in Gwingris",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+500 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Broderic Willowmeade, a man of Bree-town has bade you seek out Imyl in the Last Homely House of Rivendell, and offer aid to her if you may.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Imyl"},{locations={"31.83S, 51.37W"},name="Broderic Willowmeade"}},category="Reputation",id=2309,scope="n/a",name="The Elves of Rivendell",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Broderic Willowmeade",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpeak with Imyl of Rivendell.\n* Talk to Imyl",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",reputation={{val="+900 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="Information received from the letters you recovered in Black Speech led Glóin to offer rewards for the defeat of the Uruk-emissary from Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"24.89S, 4.12W"},name="Tralli Gemfinder"}},selectoneof={{val="Amarthan",id="7000D2F2"},{val="Jewel of Skill",id="7000D2B3"},{val="Armlet of Virtue",id="7000D2B0"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2310,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1183},name="The Emissary",level=50,c={"* Go north to Gondamon\n* Speak with Gailthin"},minlevel=45,b="Tralli Gemfinder",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBhoghad is in the Great Goblin's throne room in Goblin-town. Goblin-town lies far to the north-east of Glóin's camp.\nTralli seemed pleased with all you have done for Glóin in the past and offered you a reward for hunting down and defeating the Uruk-emissary Bhoghad in Goblin-town.\n* Kill 1 Bhoghad, Emissary to Goblin-town\nObj 2:\nTralli Gemfinder is at Glóin's camp in the Misty Mountains, far to the south-west of Goblin-town.\nYou entered the Great Goblin's throne room and found Bhoghad entreating with the goblins there. You defeated the Uruk and should now return with the news to Tralli Gemfinder.\n* Talk to Tralli Gemfinder"},
{area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",d="With Hyacinth's stolen fireworks destroyed, there are none left for Lobelia Sackville-Baggins' birthday party.",mobs={{locations={"33.44S, 71.42W"},name="Hyacinth Took"},{locations={"33.60S, 71.13W","33.61S, 71.13W"},name="Thain Paladin Took II"}},category="Shire",id=2311,scope="n/a",prev={896},name="The End of the Matter",arcs="Lobelia's Fireworks",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Fireworks",id="70000D9F"},{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Thain Paladin Took II",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHyacinth Took is at her home in Tuckborough near the Great Smials.\nPaladin Took was grateful for your help destroying the stolen fireworks. He has tasked you with delivering the news to Hyacinth Took.\n* Talk to Hyacinth Took",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Malledhrim of Echad Sirion have discovered the location of yet another enemy encampment.",mobs={{locations={"13.54S, 58.13W"},name="Mothelen"},{locations={"15.92S, 59.97W"},name="Dannaswen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2312,scope="n/a",prev={49,1387,2408},name="The Enemy in the East",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Dannaswen",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMothelen is at Echad Mothelen, far to the north-east from Amon Angened.\nDannaswen has suggested you speak with Mothelen regarding the recently discovered enemy encampment in the western Dourstocks.\n* Talk to Mothelen at Echad Mothelen",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The presence of goblin-spies in the Mirk-eaves also infers the presence of multiple enemy encampments somewhere in the vicinity of the Mirk-eaves.",mobs={{locations={"15.92S, 59.97W"},name="Dannaswen"},{locations={"16.50S, 60.30W"},name="Glamodúd"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2313,scope="n/a",prev={1961},name="The Enemy is upon Us!",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Glamodúd",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDannaswen is at Amon Angened, atop Amon Angened to the north, above Echad Mothelen.\nGlamodúd has asked you to speak with Dannaswen regarding the Orc-camp near the Gostannon in the north.\n* Talk to Dannaswen atop Amon Angened",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2004},area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",money={{val="49s"}},d="The resistance at Gath Forthnír needs equipment if they are to make a stand against Carn Dûm.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Throst"}},selectoneof={{val="Uruk Iron Club",id="7000257F"},{val="Uruk Iron Two-Handed Club",id=70002580}},category="Urugarth",id=2314,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2884},name="The Enemy's Arms",arcs="Skinning Beasts",level=49,pois={{locations={"8.74N, 31.78W","10.68N, 31.49W","10.24N, 31.98W","10.22N, 30.08W","8.55N, 31.06W","9.12N, 31.43W","9.03N, 32.15W","10.29N, 32.01W","8.59N, 31.13W","9.74N, 31.04W","9.14N, 31.38W","10.24N, 31.24W","9.51N, 31.32W","8.99N, 31.64W","10.22N, 31.95W","8.68N, 31.99W","9.74N, 31.03W","9.31N, 31.52W","9.39N, 32.29W","8.59N, 31.20W","9.51N, 30.27W","9.73N, 31.88W","10.23N, 31.24W","9.98N, 31.49W","9.04N, 31.17W","8.84N, 31.81W","9.52N, 32.09W","10.25N, 31.12W","9.49N, 31.45W","8.55N, 31.05W","9.73N, 31.67W","9.53N, 31.21W","9.04N, 32.09W","10.42N, 31.41W","10.23N, 31.94W","9.50N, 32.22W","9.94N, 30.47W","8.80N, 31.26W","9.16N, 31.51W","8.55N, 32.07W","8.54N, 31.25W","9.76N, 31.69W","8.51N, 32.00W","8.73N, 31.62W","10.30N, 31.52W","9.39N, 32.00W","10.45N, 32.17W","10.23N, 32.15W","9.01N, 31.17W","9.45N, 31.47W","9.29N, 32.09W","10.40N, 30.47W","10.48N, 31.17W","9.64N, 31.53W","9.74N, 31.19W","8.85N, 31.72W","10.63N, 31.80W","8.56N, 31.06W"},name="Weapon-crate"}},minlevel=44,b="Throst",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nUrugarth is in Carn Dûm to the west of Gath Forthnír.\nThrost devised a clever plan to steal supplies from the Enemy and use them to equip the resistance at Gath Forthnír.\n* Use Weapon-crate\nObj 2:\nThrost is at Gath Forthnír, east of Carn Dûm.\nYou should return to Throst with tidings of your victory.\n* Talk to Throst\n* Turn in Assorted Weapons"},
{["next"]={1971},area="Buckland",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Adso Haybank is a hobbit with a vision in need of assistance in setting up an inn along the road leading from The Shire into Bree. His assistants are looking for help in Buckland.",mobs={{locations={"31.56S, 62.55W"},name="Trumric Ragwort"}},category="Bree-land",id=2315,scope="n/a",name="The Envy of the Four Farthings",arcs="A Right Proper Place",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Trumric Ragwort",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWild mushrooms can be found along the eastern banks of the Brandywine River, north of Bucklebury.\nTrumric Ragwort has asked you to gather wild mushrooms from the banks of the Brandywine River. He informed you that the mushrooms are to be used to help build a menu worthy of the Shire at Adso Haybank's inn.\n* Deliver the mushrooms to Trumric Ragwort in Buckland\n* Turn in Wild-mushroom",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1580,1273},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="Lolo wants to resume Burl Beeman's profitable trade between Combe and Staddle, but a bear ran off with his pack and the coinpurse therein.",mobs={{locations={"30.18S, 49.67W"},name="Lolo Wendingway"}},selectoneof={{val="Wendingway's Shoulder Pads",id="70006A84"},{val="Wendingway's Club",id="70006B81"}},category="Bree-land",id=2316,scope="n/a",prev={945},name="The Errant Coinpurse",arcs="Friendships Renewed",level=12,c={"* Collect Lolo Wendingway's pack from the bears east of Lolo\n* Bring the pack to Lolo Wendingway"},minlevel=8,b="Lolo Wendingway",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLolo Wendingway is on the road between Combe and Staddle.\nThe bear that made off with Lolo Wendingway's pack dragged it away to the valley east of him. You need to bring Lolo's pack back to him within fifteen minutes; otherwise, he will miss the good prices on Staddle pipe-weed.\n* Bring the pack to Lolo Wendingway\n* Turn in Lolo's Backpack"},
{area="Bruinen Source North",zone="The Misty Mountains",reputation={{val="+500 with Elves of Rivendell"}},d="Sigrun and Greip learned that the evil that has taken Helegrod is much worse than Glóin had suspected.",mobs={{locations={"19.13S, 2.90W"},name="Sigrun"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2317,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={1164},name="The Extent of the Threat",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Sigrun",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElrond is in his library in Rivendell.\nSigrun has asked you to return to Elrond with news of the extent of the threat lurking now within Helegrod.\n* Talk to Elrond at Rivendell"},
{area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Derudh Tûm claims that the spirits of the forest have been angered and have driven away the rest of the Derudh. He hopes to reclaim their grove and perhaps help you find the way into the Huntsman's hall.",mobs={{locations={"69.17S, 22.35W"},name="Tûm"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2318,scope="n/a",prev={2360},name="The Fallen Grove",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Tûm",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nA maddened Elhudan spirit has claimed Oirnad Culch, south of Gwaed Brun.\nTûm has asked you to defeat the wild spirits that have overrun the grove the Derudh once called their own.\n* Defeat the Maddened Elhudan at Oirnad Culch\nObj 2:\nTûm is at the grove atop Gwaed Brun in the Mournshaws, north of Oirnad Culch.\nYou should return to Tûm with news of your success.\n* Talk to Tûm at Gwaed Brun"},
{area="The Walls of Moria",zone="The Walls of Moria",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="Skygni wishes to tell you the tale of the fall of Moria so that you can better appreciate what the expedition has accomplished.",category="Moria",id=2319,scope="n/a",prev={3042},name="The Fall of Moria",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Skygni",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSkygni is in the Twenty-first Hall in Moria.\nSkygni has agreed to tell you the tale of the fall of Moria.\n* Talk to Skygni and listen to the tale of the fall of Moria\nObj 2:\nSkygni is in the Twenty-first Hall in Moria.\nSkygni has told you the tale of the fall of Moria and is waiting to speak with you.\n* Talk to Skygni",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eldgang"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="You have defeated Thaurlach and hold in your possession a broken link of the great chain which once held the Balrog in his prison.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 3.06W"},name="Glorfindel"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},titles={{val="{ Lord[m] | Lady[f] } of the Shattered Chain"}},selectoneof={{val="Mest-baug",id="7000D2FF"},{val="Glorfindel's Locket",id="7000D300"}},category="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",id=2320,scope="n/a",t="Raid",name="The Fall of Thaurlach",receive={{val="Glorfindel?s Band",id="7000C70B"}},level=50,minlevel=45,b="Broken Chain Link",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElrond is at the Last Homely House in Rivendell, in the Trollshaws far to the south of Angmar.\nYou have defeated the Balrog Thaurlach and should inform Elrond Halfelven of your deeds.\n* Talk to Elrond\nObj 2:\nGlorfindel may be found outside the Last Homely House standing next to the Bruinen.\nElrond suggested you speak with Glorfindel about the defeat of Thaurlach, for the tale concerns him greatly.\n* Talk to Glorfindel\n* Turn in Broken Chain Link"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="55s 30c"}},d="The Moria Orcs hold control over the Grand Stair, and leading them are Igash the Fanatic and his Devoted minion. Alongside them are a host of fearsome Orcs from the very heart of Moria.",mobs={{locations={"10.98S, 106.77W"},name="Avar"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2321,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Fanatic and his Devoted",arcs="The Masters of Moria",level=58,minlevel=57,b="Avar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nIgash and his Devoted are high up in the Grand Stair, north-east of the Orc-watch.\nAvar has asked you to go forth and defeat Igash and his Devoted.\n* Defeat the Devoted\n* Defeat Igash\nObj 2:\nAvar is at the Orc-watch, south-west of the Grand Stair.\nYou should return to Avar and inform him that you have slain Igash and his Devoted.\n* Talk to Avar at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1455},area="Ram Dúath",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 5c"}},d="Chief Tuokki is worried that the Angmarim who command the Orcs will send them to fight the Earth-kin.",mobs={{locations={"3.07S, 39.02W"},name="Chief Tuokki"}},selectoneof={{val="Foe of the Iron-crown",id="7000EAEE"},{val="Tuokki's Halberd",id="7000EAED"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Athelas Extract",id="70008CFB"}},category="Angmar",id=2322,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2096},name="The Far Reaching Hand",arcs="Strength of Stone",level=42,minlevel=37,b="Chief Tuokki",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFrith-vailë is in the north-east part of Ram Dúath.\nChief Tuokki, hoping to discourage the Orcs and the Angmarim, has asked you to defeat the Captain of the Angmarim in Ram Dúath.\n* Kill 1 Iron Crown Captain\nObj 2:\nChief Tuokki is at the Suuri-lehmä camp in Ram Dúath.\nNow that you've defeated the Iron-crown Captain, return to the Earth-kin Chief and tell him of your deed.\n* Talk to Chief Tuokki"},
{area="Greenfields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="1s 25c"}},d="Fosco Boffin in Scary is worried about his aunt, a reputable hobbit named Prunella.",mobs={{locations={"27.72S, 66.37W"},name="Fosco Boffin"}},selectoneof={{val="Boffin's Legs",id="70006ADE"},{q="(x5)",val="Roast Pork",id="700005B5"}},category="Shire",id=2323,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Fate of Prunella Boffin",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=13,pois={{locations={"24.55S, 68.00W"},name="Prunella's Umbrella"}},minlevel=9,b="Fosco Boffin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblins may be found in the north-west Greenfields. If one of them took Aunt Prunella's umbrella, it might be lying somewhere inside one of their camps.\nYou promised Fosco Boffin that you would look for his Aunt Prunella's umbrella. He fears that she ran afoul of goblins.\n* Use Prunella's Umbrella\nObj 2:\nFosco Boffin is in Scary, near the centre of town.\nYou promised Fosco Boffin that you would look for his Aunt Prunella's umbrella. He fears that she ran afoul of goblins.\n* Talk to Fosco Boffin\n* Turn in Prunella's Umbrella\nObj 3:\nFosco Boffin is in Scary, near the centre of town.\nFosco was distressed by your recovery of his Aunt Prunella's umbrella; however, a neighbour informed him that she had actually been visiting her all day, and that Prunella had lost her umbrella earlier in the day. Fosco motions you over.\n* Talk to Fosco Boffin"},
{area="Nan Amlug West",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="28s"}},d="With the map you recovered from Foreman Nyrad and the runes from the old records, Regin may have determined the general location of the father-lode.",mobs={{locations={"7.12S, 45.14W"},name="Regin"}},selectoneof={{val="Amarthlos (Level 28)",id="70021DF5"},{val="Regin's Hammer",id="70002F06"}},category="North Downs",id=2324,scope="n/a",prev={2468},name="The Father-lode",arcs="The Father-lode",level=29,pois={{locations={"5.60S, 47.13W","5.67S, 47.20W","5.69S, 47.23W"},name="Ore-deposit"}},minlevel=24,b="Regin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe father-lode is somewhere to the north-west of Othrikar.\nFind the father in the raw rock\nThe lode lies amongst high hills\nFell falcons soar through skies and\nSavage lynx guard the gorges\nShining the silver, glittering the gold\nA cliff's crags keep the secret\nThe old records combined with the mining map suggested to Regin the location of the father-lode, but the directions were far from precise. Regin has asked you to find a suitable rock formation and take an ore sample.\n* Use Ore-deposit\nObj 2:\nRegin is at Othrikar.\nYou found a rock formation matching the description Regin compiled from the map and old records. You should bring the ore sample you took from the site back to Regin.\n* Talk to Regin\n* Turn in Ore-sample\n* Turn in Mining Pick"},
{["next"]={2520},area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Bávor is an artificer tasked with repairing the great lock which opens access to the fabled Vault of the Mountain.",category="Ered Luin",id=2325,scope="n/a",prev={2400},name="The Fifth Gear",arcs="The Puzzle-vault",level=14,c={"* The Chest is in Talath Ondren at [18.9S, 91.0W]. It is near the brood mother, in some shallow water next to some large rocks."},pois={{locations={"18.94S, 91.02W"},name="Chest"}},minlevel=10,b="Bávor",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe fifth gear is in a chest in a spider lair north and east of Kheledûl in eastern Haudh Lin.\nBávor has asked you to recover the fifth and final gear from a terrible spider-lair.\n* Use Chest\nObj 2:\nBávor is in Thorin's Hall.\nBávor will be pleased to see you have recovered the fifth and final gear.\n* Bring the fifth gear to Bávor\n* Turn in Gear"},
{area="Nanduhirion",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+300 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Wargs and the riders of Athmadhul have been defeated. Now, it is time to destroy the training camp itself.",selectoneof={{val="Gloves of Dismantling",id="700163DA"},{val="Course Crasher",id="700163F7"}},category="Moria",id=2326,scope="n/a",prev={1851},name="The Final Offence",arcs="Riders in the Dale",level=60,pois={{locations={"15.05S, 76.05W","15.16S, 75.72W","14.99S, 75.93W","15.19S, 75.86W","15.12S, 75.95W","15.03S, 75.80W"},name="Gate"}},minlevel=55,b="Ótam",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe track is at Athmadhul, south-east of Mekhem-bizru.\nÓtam wants you to return to Athmadhul, but this time wishes you to dismantle the track fences the Warg-riders use to train.\n* Use Gate\nObj 2:\nÓtam is at Mekhem-bizru, north-west of Athmadhul.\nÓtam will be pleased to hear that the training track has been destroyed.\n* Talk to Ótam at Mekhem-bizru"},
{["next"]={97},area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="You inspire the Free Peoples with your songs of hope and your tales of heroism, a renowned minstrel of talent and bravery.",mobs={{locations={"15.07S, 103.22W"},name="Dourhand"},{locations={"28.04S, 92.06W"},name="Baillindiel"},{locations={"9.59S, 41.42W"},name="Gelirwen"},{locations={"29.83S, 3.41W"},name="Bailinn"},{locations={"19.48N, 72.03W"},name="Ulla"},{locations={"25.34S, 48.72W"},name="Tolman Gardner"},{locations={"12.58S, 67.37W"},name="Nírthathar"},{locations={"52.38S, 16.65W"},name="Ganneldúr"},{locations={"28.15S, 92.17W"},name="Melthindir"},{locations={"20.24S, 97.00W"},name="Galfi"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Ardo Aleford"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Marjorie Wainwright"},{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Burt Ninetails"},{locations={"15.28S, 101.59W"},name="Thalchyl"}},category="Minstrel",id=2327,scope="n/a",prev={175,115},requiredclasses="Minstrel",name="The Finest Melody is Understanding",arcs="The Finest Melody",level=50,c={"* Baillindiel is at Celondim by the docks"},minlevel=45,b="Tolman Gardner",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBaillindiel is at Celondim, the Elf-harbour in Ered Luin.\nYou have been told to speak with Baillindiel, a talented minstrel who may desire to speak with you.\n* Talk to Baillindiel"},
{["next"]={2696},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+500 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Nef lost his shield while escaping from a dangerous creature in the tundras of Forochel.",mobs={{locations={"19.44N, 71.31W"},name="Nef"}},category="Forochel",id=2328,scope="n/a",name="The Finest Shield in the Land",arcs="The Finest Shield in the Land",level=47,c={"* Nef's is a Broken Shield that can be found in Jä-rannit at [16.0N, 63.7W]"},pois={{locations={"16.01N, 63.72W"},name="Broken Shield"}},minlevel=42,b="Nef",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNef thinks he dropped his shield in Jä-rannit along the road to Itä-mâ at a junction in the roads.\nNef has asked you to search for the shield he lost and return it to him.\n* Find Nef's shield\nObj 2:\nNef is in Sûri-kylä, north from Itä-mâ along the Ice Bay.\nYou should return Nef's shield to him at once.\n* Talk to Nef\n* Turn in Broken Shield"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="44s 24c"}},d="The Grand Stair once stood at the foot of a great crossroads within Moria. At the height of the great city, it led to all areas of the halls and was a majestic wonder to behold. Now it has fallen to the care of Igash, a lieutenant of the Moria Orc-leader Mazog. Igash assembled the forces of Orcs and trolls within Moria in one place and has collected tribute from each to one day bring to the leader of the Orcs. For now, each tribe vies for favour from the lieutenant, a fanatical follower of Mazog.",mobs={{locations={"11.20S, 106.74W"},name="Ossur"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2329,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Fire-dwellers",arcs="The Grand Stair",receive={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Legend",id="7001F259"}},level=58,minlevel=57,b="Ossur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOssur is at the Orc-watch.\nOssur has tasked you with aiding him against the trolls and Ghâsh-hai of the Grand Stair.\n* Deal with the leader of the Ghâsh-hai in the Grand Stair\n* Deal with the war-host of the Ghâsh-hai within the Grand Stair\nObj 2:\nOssur is at the Orc-watch, south-west of the Grand Stair\nYou should return to Ossur at the Orc-watch and inform him that the tasks set before you regarding the Ghâsh-hai are complete.\n* Talk to Ossur at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2547},area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Bávor is an artificer tasked with repairing the great lock which opens access to the fabled Vault of the Mountain.",category="Ered Luin",id=2330,scope="n/a",name="The First Gear",arcs="The Puzzle-vault",level=6,c={"* The Winterheight is in Thorin's Gate at [15.8S, 101.7W]\n* The gear is inside a chest at the bottom of the cave."},pois={{locations={"15.75S, 102.30W","15.85S, 102.53W"},name="Chest"}},minlevel=2,b="Bávor",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe first missing gear is in a cave in the Winterheight, south-east of Thorin's Hall.\nBávor has asked you to help reassemble the dwarf-built device which opens the Vault.\n* Use Chest\nObj 2:\nBávor is in Thorin's Hall.\nBávor will be pleased to see you have acquired the first gear.\n* Bring the gear to Bávor\n* Turn in Gear",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hobbiton-Bywater",zone="The Shire",d="The hobbits are celebrating the Lithe Festival! They have given you permission to catch fish from the freshly-stocked fishing-hole.",mobs={{locations={"31.23S, 69.96W"},name="Neddie Grub"}},category="Festival",id=2331,scope="n/a",prev={2077},name="The Fishing-hole",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Neddie Grub",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe pond is north of Bywater.\nNeddie Grub has invited you to fish from the Lithe Festival pond. All fish caught go back into the pond, but the more you catch, the more you win.\n* Catch as many fish as you can in ten minutes",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="44s 24c"}},d="Deep within the halls of Moria, flames lick out of oily pools. It is here that the Ghâsh-hai make their home. A faction of these is aligned with the master of Moria, Mazog, and has come to the Grand Stair to pay tribute to their leader.",mobs={{locations={"11.20S, 106.74W"},name="Ossur"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2332,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Flaming Depths",arcs="The Host of Flame",level=58,minlevel=57,b="Ossur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGhâsh-hai Orcs can be found within the Grand Stair, north-east of the Orc-watch.\nOssur sent you to face the Orc-forces of the fiery depths of Moria, who came to the Grand Stair to pay their tribute to Igash, an Orc devoted to Mazog.\n* Defeat Ghâsh-hai Firebrands\n* Defeat Ghâsh-hai Wrathcallers\nObj 2:\nOssur is at the Orc-watch, south-west of the Grand Stair.\nYou should return to Ossur and inform him that you have defeated many of the Ghâsh-hai.\n* Talk to Ossur at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Hobbiton-Bywater",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Ponto Hopsbloom, innkeeper of The Floating Log in Frogmorton, is entering the Four Farthings Brewing-moot.",mobs={{locations={"31.66S, 68.04W"},name="Ponto Hopsbloom"}},category="Shire",id=2333,scope="n/a",name="The Floating Log",receive={{val="Toad's Tongue Ale",id=70003703},{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=9,minlevel=5,b="Ponto Hopsbloom",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFrog Hops grow in the marsh north of Frogmorton. The Floating Log Inn is in Frogmorton, south of the Frogmoors.\nPonto Hopsbloom has asked you to pick some Frog Hops for his famous beer.\n* Bring the hops to Ponto Hopsbloom\n* Turn in Frog Hops",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Brigands attacking the farms and roadways of Bree-land have made off with many of the goods necessary to keep the town stocked.",mobs={{locations={"28.19S, 53.34W"},name="Watcher Rosecane"}},category="Bree-land",id=2334,scope="n/a",prev={1974},name="The Flow of Goods",level=15,pois={{locations={"27.26S, 56.19W","26.53S, 55.71W","27.14S, 55.88W","27.17S, 55.98W","27.13S, 56.17W","27.06S, 55.92W","26.92S, 55.91W","26.85S, 56.06W","26.87S, 56.09W","26.49S, 55.65W","27.15S, 56.13W","26.91S, 55.86W","26.96S, 56.23W","26.91S, 55.83W"},name="Stolen Goods"}},minlevel=11,b="Watcher Rosecane",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nStolen goods are being kept by the brigands at Brigands' Watch.\nWatcher Rosecane requested that you search Brigands' Watch for goods stolen from the roadways and farms of Bree-land.\n* Bring the goods to  Watcher Rosecane\n* Collect stolen-goods (12 Stolen Goods )",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1740},area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Tindr hopes the repairs to the canal in Thorin's Hall has restored the flow of water to Noglond, the way-station in the Vale of Thráin.",mobs={{locations={"19.31S, 100.48W"},name="Geitir"},{locations={"14.92S, 103.13W"},name="Tindr"}},selectoneof={{val="Bright Copper Earring",id="70019BDF"},{val="Shiny Copper Earring",id="70019BD7"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2335,scope="n/a",prev={126},name="The Flow to Noglond",arcs="The Dwarf-canal",level=7,minlevel=3,b="Tindr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGeitir is in Noglond, south on the road from Thorin's Halls.\nTindr has asked you to speak with Geitir in Noglond to learn if the flow of water in the canal has returned to normal.\n* Talk to Geitir"},
{area="Nan Celebrant",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Hadhelen has written a letter to Andiriniel, whom he was supposed to meet at the Lady's Rest.",mobs={{locations={"16.37S, 69.98W"},name="Andiriniel"},{locations={"18.61S, 63.83W","16.39S, 69.84W"},name="Hadhelen"}},category="Lothlórien",id=2336,scope="n/a",prev={1445},name="The Fool's Letter",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Hadhelen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAndiriniel is at the Lady's Rest, south-west of the gates of Caras Galadhon.\nHadhelen asked you to deliver his letter to Andiriniel.\n* Talk to Andiriniel\n* Turn in Sealed Letter"},
{area="High Moor",zone="Trollshaws",d="The Ford of Bruinen is the last bulwark leading into the hidden vale of Rivendell. Orcs in the service of Angmar lay siege at the Ford, seeking to break through the defences of Imladris.",category="Skirmish",id=2337,scope="n/a",name="The Ford of Bruinen",level=40,minlevel=35,repeatable="Yes",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nElrohir and Elladan, sons of Elrond, are prepared to stand against the army of the Enemy attempting to cross the Bruinen. Elrohir is awaiting your arrival.\n* Talk to Elrohir at the Ford of Bruinen\nObj 2:\nThe first assault has been launched. The Ford and the sons of Elrond must be defended.\n* Push back the first assault\nObj 3:\nThe second assault has been launched. The Enemy shows no signs of slowing.\n* Push back the second assault\nObj 4:\nThe third assault has been launched. The Enemy appears to be wavering in morale and decreasing in number.\n* Push back the third assault\nObj 5:\nThe fourth assault has been launched. The Enemy's forces are dwindling quickly and are nearly at their end.\n* Push back the fourth assault\nObj 6:\nThe final assault begins as the leader of the Enemy's forces enters the battle. Defeat him, and the invasion will be thwarted\n* Fend off the final assault"},
{["next"]={2078},area="The Horsefields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="4s"}},d="You met an old dwarf named Oddvarr who seems a bit absent-minded. He is an explorer of some renown...or at least he says he is.",mobs={{locations={"23.03S, 51.03W"},name="Oddvarr"}},category="Bree-land",id=2338,scope="n/a",name="The Forgetful Dwarf",arcs="My Brethren's Call",level=20,minlevel=15,b="Oddvarr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOddvarr asked you to search the ruins to the north.\nOddvarr set his pack down somewhere in the area and cannot seem to remember where.\n* Search the ruins for Oddvarr's pack\nObj 2:\nOddvarr awaits you to the south of the ruins.\nYou found Oddvarr's pack in the old ruins to the north.\n* Turn in Oddvarr's Provisions\nObj 3:\nOddvarr is by the haystacks south of the ruins where you found the pack.\nYou found Oddvarr's pack containing his much-needed provisions.\n* Talk to Oddvarr\n* Turn in Oddvarr's Provisions"},
{area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="39s 90c"}},d="The Tooks in the camp at Fornost are desperately looking for proof that hobbits fought in the Battle of Fornost. They have been ridiculed for their beliefs, so they have come to find the proof they so desperately need.",mobs={{locations={"8.04S, 56.01W"},name="Bartelot Took"}},selectoneof={{val="Hanhar",id="70006B0D"},{val="Took's Rune-stone",id="700161AD"}},category="Fornost",id=2339,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Forgotten Company",level=36,c={"* Bartelot Took is found in the Fornost Free Peoples' Camp\n* The skeletons for these arrowheads are found in the entry areas of the instance:\nin the entry area as you come through the gate into Fornost\n* up the stairs in and around Sara Oakheart's \"pens\"\n* in the swamp\n* to the right of the swamp near the Jarg-Olog trolls.\n* Skeletons drop one arrowhead each, and they are usable only by one person. Be advised, it may take your group two trips into Fornost to get all the arrowheads you need.\n* Tip: Kill every mob in an area before looting the skeletons. This will prevent you from accidentally drawing aggro while trying to loot a skeleton."},pois={{locations={"5.11S, 54.91W","4.48S, 55.35W","5.02S, 55.14W","3.93S, 55.42W","5.28S, 55.27W","5.75S, 54.45W","4.96S, 54.81W","4.65S, 55.18W","5.42S, 54.02W","4.17S, 55.20W","4.89S, 55.15W","4.42S, 55.21W","5.40S, 55.32W","4.71S, 55.28W","5.31S, 54.59W","5.07S, 55.30W","4.96S, 54.97W","5.45S, 54.44W","5.68S, 53.99W","5.53S, 54.95W","5.45S, 55.32W","5.83S, 54.93W","5.77S, 54.58W","5.03S, 54.83W","5.50S, 54.40W","5.65S, 54.92W","5.76S, 54.93W","5.21S, 55.32W","5.75S, 54.15W","5.26S, 55.20W","5.63S, 55.22W","5.79S, 54.16W","5.71S, 54.65W","5.07S, 54.84W","5.72S, 53.98W","4.53S, 55.26W","5.38S, 53.60W","5.79S, 54.22W","4.10S, 55.32W","5.65S, 55.33W","4.60S, 55.37W","5.61S, 54.92W","5.39S, 55.08W","5.21S, 54.72W","3.94S, 55.28W","5.75S, 53.60W","4.92S, 55.30W","4.54S, 55.12W","5.36S, 54.16W","4.85S, 55.25W","5.79S, 53.94W","4.83S, 55.33W","5.46S, 54.09W","5.78S, 53.77W","4.91S, 54.90W","4.91S, 54.86W","5.48S, 54.93W","5.49S, 53.37W","4.19S, 55.42W","5.37S, 54.34W","5.59S, 53.63W","5.50S, 53.81W","4.97S, 55.31W","5.77S, 53.98W","5.32S, 54.76W","5.17S, 55.06W","5.58S, 55.21W","5.50S, 53.89W","5.72S, 53.40W","5.43S, 54.98W","5.48S, 54.46W","5.53S, 53.91W","5.50S, 53.50W","5.42S, 53.49W","5.07S, 55.09W"},name="Small Skeleton"}},minlevel=31,b="Bartelot Took",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou might find hobbit arrowheads among the skeletons within Fornost, north of the Fornost camp.\nBartelot Took has asked you to collect hobbit arrowheads from the ruins of Fornost, believing that they will prove to everyone that there really were hobbits at the Battle of Fornost.\n* Use Small Skeleton\nObj 2:\nBartelot Took is at the Fornost Camp, south of Fornost itself.\nYour search produced a large number of arrowheads. You should take them to Bartelot Took.\n* Talk to Bartelot Took\n* Turn in Hobbit-arrowhead"},
{["next"]={1313,1835},area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="8s 50c"}},d="Marla Shelton is concerned that the history of Trestlebridge may be lost because the Founder's Book has been stolen by Orcs.",category="North Downs",id=2340,scope="n/a",name="The Founder's Book",arcs="The Founder's Book",level=23,pois={{locations={"14.98S, 52.09W","14.93S, 51.49W","15.18S, 51.85W","15.96S, 52.78W","15.24S, 51.91W","15.97S, 52.78W","14.97S, 52.09W","15.31S, 52.17W"},name="Stolen goods"}},minlevel=18,b="Marla Shelton",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are Orc encampments to the east, once you cross the Trestlebridge to the north.\nMarla Shelton has asked you to search Orc encampments near Trestlebridge for signs of the Founding Book.\n* Use Stolen goods\n* Use Stolen goods\nObj 2:\nMarla Shelton is back in Trestlebridge.\nYou have found the Founder's Book and should bring it back to Marla Shelton.\n* Talk to Marla Shelton\n* Turn in The Founders' Book",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={155,1982,1575},area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",d="Adelard Took has sent word that a copy of the Founding Writ, the document that established the Bounds of the Shire, has been discovered. The original document was given to the Fallohide brothers, Marcho and Blanco, by the old King.",mobs={{locations={"32.81S, 70.95W"},name="Belco Brockhouse"},{locations={"33.41S, 75.57W"},name="Keeper Brombard Foxtail"},{locations={"33.60S, 71.13W","33.61S, 71.13W"},name="Adelard Took"}},category="Shire",id=2341,scope="n/a",name="The Founding Writ",arcs="The Founding Writ",level=8,minlevel=4,b="Keeper Brombard Foxtail",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAdelard Took can be found in the Great Smials in Tuckborough.\nBrombard Foxtail, the Keeper of the Mathom-house heard rumour of Adelard Took's find and asked you to try and obtain the copy of the Founding Writ from Adelard.\n* Talk to Adelard Took\nObj 2:\nBelco Brockhouse can be found north of Tuckborough town centre, up the hill and on the right of the path.\nTo his embarassment, Adelard Took revealed that he doesn't have the Founding Writ. A local farmer, Belco Brockhouse, is the one who found the Writ, but he refuses to hand it over to Adelard until someone helps him around his farm.\n* Talk to Belco Brockhouse",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Caras Galadhon",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Nembes watches over the fountain of the Lady Galadriel.",mobs={{locations={"14.82S, 67.09W"},name="Nembes"}},category="Lothlórien",id=2342,scope="n/a",name="The Fountain of the Lady",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,c={"* The first pitcher must be carried to the Parched Elf at [14.5S, 66.3W]\n* The second pitcher must be carried to the Parched Elf at [14.5S, 67.0W]\n* The second pitcher must be carried to the Parched Elf at [15.3S, 67.1W], at the end of the carpeted path just before the stairs that lead to the House of Celeborn"},minlevel=55,b="Nembes",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nPitchers can be found on the terrace near Nembes, and there are three locations to which she would have you bring pitchers of water: parched Elves beneath Telain Neduil, at the base of the ladder that climbs up to the House of Celeborn, and at a gathering of musicians north of Celúrlin.\nNembes has asked you to deliver pitchers of cool water to parched Elves.\n* Pick up a pitcher for Telain Neduil\nObj 2:\nPitchers can be found on the terrace near Nembes, and there are three locations to which she would have you bring pitchers of water: parched Elves beneath Telain Neduil, at the base of the ladder that climbs up to the House of Celeborn, and at a gathering of musicians north of Celúrlin.\nNembes has asked you to deliver pitchers of cool water to parched Elves.\n* Pick up a pitcher for the gathering of musicians\nObj 3:\nPitchers can be found on the terrace near Nembes, and there are three locations to which she would have you bring pitchers of water: parched Elves beneath Telain Neduil, at the base of the ladder that climbs up to the House of Celeborn, and at a gathering of musicians north of Celúrlin.\nNembes has asked you to deliver pitchers of cool water to parched Elves.\n* Pick up a pitcher for the House of Celeborn\nObj 4:\nNembes is at Celúrlin, Galadriel's fountain in the centre of Caras Galadhon.\nYou have delivered pitchers of cool water to parched Elves throughout the city and should return now to Nembes.\n* Talk to Nembes at Celúrlin",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2382},area="Kheledûl",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="Bávor is an artificer tasked with repairing the great lock which opens access to the fabled Vault of the Mountain.",category="Ered Luin",id=2343,scope="n/a",prev={2598},name="The Fourth Gear",arcs="The Puzzle-vault",level=12,c={"* The Chest is in Kheledûl at [21.0S, 92.2W]. To find it, turn left immediately on entering Kheledûl and follow along the wall until you reach it."},pois={{locations={"21.00S, 92.18W"},name="Chest"}},minlevel=8,b="Bávor",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe fourth gear is in a chest at the Dourhand port of Kheledûl, east of Gondamon.\nBávor has asked you to recover the fourth missing gear from the Dourhands of Kheledûl.\n* Use Chest\nObj 2:\nBávor is in Thorin's Hall, far to the north-west of Kheledûl.\nBávor will be pleased to see you have recovered the fourth gear.\n* Bring the fourth gear to Bávor\n* Turn in Gear"},
{area="Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="Many crystals can be found within Moria, but this one seems different than the others. Darkened by time and appearing burned out, perhaps there is something to be learned from this crystal fallen from a Moria Orc.",mobs={{locations={"9.86S, 112.76W"},name="Falgir"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2344,scope="n/a",name="The Fractured Crystal",level=55,minlevel=50,b="Crystal Fragment",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFalgir is at the Deep Descent.\nYou should bring the crystal you found to a dwarf who might know of such things.\n* Talk to Falgir at the Deep Descent\n* Turn in Crystal Fragment",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2402},area="Frostbluff",zone="Frostbluff",money={{val="90c"}},d="A hobbit working for the G.L.O.B.E. has asked you to attend a showing of 'An Ode to Old Bloodtusk' and return with your thoughts.",category="Frostbluff",id=2345,scope="n/a",prev={2658,2402},name="The Frostbluff Theatre",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Frostbluff Coin",id="70024EB1"}},level=10,c={"* You should find the fireworks (at the top of the stairs overlooking the Festival square) and set them off first. That will distract the wealthy people, wich you can pickpocket now."},minlevel=6,b="Hobbit",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAttend a performance in the Frostbluff Theatre.\n* Attend a performance in the Frostbluff Theatre\nObj 2:\nSpeak with the hobbit outside the Frostbluff Theatre in Winter-home.\nYou should tell the hobbit about the performance you saw.\n* Talk to the Announcer\nQuest: The Frostbluff Theatre\nCategory: Frostbluff\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 6\nPrerequisite Quests:The Yule Celebration of Winter-home\nNext Quests:The Frostbluff Theatre\nRewards\nMoney:\n90\nReceive:\nFrostbluff Coin (x4)\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nA hobbit working for the G.L.O.B.E. has asked you to attend a showing of 'An Ode to Old Bloodtusk' and return with your thoughts.\nBestower\nHobbit (NPC)\n'Hullo there, you're in Frostbluff for the Yule Festival, aren't you? That's splendid! This is my first visit to Winter-home, quaint little village, isn't it? I work for Mr. Shakesburrow...he's the owner of the Green Lilly Inn you know! He's also the director of the G.L.O.B.E.\n'What is the G.L.O.B.E.? Of course! I can't be forgetting my manners, expecting everyone to know everything...the G.L.O.B.E. is the Green Lilly Orators, Bards, and Entertainers. Mr. Shakesburrow put together an acting company to amuse his customers, and people liked it so much he's taken it on the road!\n'Mr. Shakesburrow has asked me to find folks willing to review the show. There are two Shire-critics who've come along with us...but they've been...well, you'll see for yourself.\n'We've got a special showing of 'An Ode to Old Bloodtusk' scheduled for this evening...you won't want to miss it!'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nAttend a performance in the Frostbluff Theatre.\n* Attend a performance in the Frostbluff Theatre\nObj 2:\nSpeak with the hobbit outside the Frostbluff Theatre in Winter-home.\nYou should tell the hobbit about the performance you saw.\n* Talk to the Announcer"},
{["next"]={1125},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="The Lossoth of Forochel have found themselves swept up in the rising tide of war in their northern realm, for the Angmarim have incited the ancient hatred between the Lossoth and the Gauredain. Hoping to make an alliance with the Lossoth, representatives of Men and dwarves from the south have come to Forochel to lend their aid.",mobs={{locations={"19.54N, 71.99W"},name="Vämmä"}},category="Forochel",id=2346,scope="n/a",name="The Frozen War",level=48,c={"* The Territory Markers can be found forming a line in Länsi-mâ at [13.6N, 84.8W], [13.9N, 84.5W], [14.2N, 84.3W], [14.2N, 83.8W], [14.2N, 83.3W], [14.6N, 82.9W]"},pois={{locations={"14.63N, 82.91W","13.87N, 84.49W","13.62N, 84.85W","14.15N, 83.34W","14.16N, 83.82W","14.20N, 84.28W","14.98N, 81.68W","15.08N, 82.56W"},name="Territory Marker"}},minlevel=43,b="Vämmä",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Gauradan wards run in a line north of the Guaredain encampment Barad Gaurhoth, near Zigilgund. These wards are far across the bay to the south-west of Sûri-kylä.\nVämmä has asked you to make a symbolic attack upon the wards that define the borders of the Gauredain's homeland.\n* Use Territory Marker\nObj 2:\nTell Vämmä that the Guaradan Territory Markers have been destroyed. He can be found at Sûri-kylä.\n* Speak with Vämmä at Sûri-kylä",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="28s 35c"},{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Sixteenth Hall is an area overrun with Orcs, many of whom suffer from a terrible illness that sweeps through. Shamans tend to the ill whilst the rest of the halls are defended by those that remain able to do battle.\nMallas, an Elf ally to the dwarves, belives that there is something secret beneath the Sixteenth Hall and wishes to learn the true purpose and source of the plague.",mobs={{locations={"12.90S, 100.69W"},name="Glorelloth"}},selectoneof={{val="Tyki's Pauldrons",id="700163D5"},{val="Zarza's Ruin",id="7001641C"},{val="Purity of Dalgum-ru",id="700163A7"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2347,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1327},name="The Fungus Among Us",arcs="The Fungus Among Us",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Glorelloth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe fungus of which Glorelloth spoke are to the north-east of the Sixteenth Hall.\nGlorelloth wishes you to collect fungus so that she may get a closer look at it and determine its nature.\n* Return to Glorelloth in the Shadowed Refuge\n* Collect Chunks of Noxious Fungus (8 Chunk of Noxious Fungus)\n//Glorelloth (Gwathrendath)Location: 12.90S, 100.69W\nMoria >> The Foundations of Stone';markerList['1879143122_0x042FEDC00000000F_102.3960.864561112'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);marker = new GPolygon( [ new GLatLng(-32.008666992188, 97.893676757813), new GLatLng(-31.305541992188, 97.893676757813), new GLatLng(-31.305541992188, 99.299926757812), new GLatLng(-32.008666992188, 99.299926757812), new GLatLng(-32.008666992188, 97.893676757813) ], '#000000', 3, 0.00390625, '#0000fd', 0.3359375); marker.id = '1879140163'; polygons['1879140163'] = marker;markerList['1879140163'] = marker;map.addOverlay(marker); GME_DEFAULT_ICON = G_DEFAULT_ICON;      } else {        document.getElementById(\"map3225611561\").innerHTML = \"In order to see the map that would go in this space, you will need to use a compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap3225611561);\n//]]>\nQuest: The Fungus Among Us\nCategory: Moria Lower Deeps\nScope: n/a\nArc(s): The Fungus Among Us\nMin Level: 55\nPrerequisite Quests:Kill it with Fire\nRewards\nMoney:\n28 35Reputation:\n+700 with Iron Garrison Guards\nSelect one of:\nPurity of Dalgum-ru\nTyki's Pauldrons\nZarza's Ruin\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nThough fire seemed to destroy the fungal structures, Tyki thinks that an end should be put to the leader of the Globsnaga Orcs.\nBestower\nTyki (NPC)\n'Burning fungus-infested structures may be a slow help, but it is not enough, I fear. To end the infestation, I believe we will have to cut the head from the serpent, so to speak.\n'The leader of the Globsnaga Orcs can be found to the south at Dalgum-ru. I think his existence has been tolerated quite long enough.\n'When the deed is done, return to me.'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nThe Globsnaga leader can be found at Dalgum-ru, south of the Shadowed Refuge.\nTyki wants you to find the Orc-leader at Dalgum-ru and put an end to his offending existence.\n* Defeat Zarza\nObj 2:\nTyki is at the Shadowed Refuge, north of Dalgum-ru.\nYou should return to Tyki to tell him of the death of Zarza, the Orc-leader.\n* Speak to Tyki at the Shadowed Refuge"},
{["next"]={3257},area="Tyrn Fornech",zone="Evendim",money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="Robin Dunkley has asked you to defeat the Gauredain of Emyn Uial and return with their weapons.",mobs={{locations={"8.07S, 64.29W"},name="Robin Dunkley"}},category="Evendim",id=2348,scope="n/a",prev={88},name="The Gauredain of Emyn Uial",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=37,minlevel=32,b="Robin Dunkley",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Gauredain prowl the hills and forests of Emyn Uial, north-west of Ost Forod.\nRobin Dunkley desires revenge for the death of Nat Rapkins and wants you to defeat the evil men that slew him. He has also asked you to bring him some of the Gauredain's unusual weapons.\n* Kill 6 Gauradan Tribesman\n* Kill 4 Gauradan Gorge-stalker\n* Turn in Makeshift Claws\nObj 2:\nRobin Dunkley is in Ost Forod, in Tyrn Fornech of Evendim, south-east of Emyn Uial.\nYou have defeated a number of the Gauredain that slew Nat Rapkins and collected some of their unusual weapons. Robin Dunkley will be pleased to hear the tale.\n* Talk to Robin Dunkley\n* Turn in Makeshift Claws"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+900 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="Fastarr knows of a forge where you may craft the heart of the qualities you seek, but the dwarves believe that it may be haunted by evil spectres of some sort.",mobs={{locations={"8.48S, 112.35W"},name="Fastarr"}},selectoneof={{val="Wight-rager",id=70011327},{val="Fused Bronze Relics",id=70018606},{val="Flashing Bane",id=70013698},{val="Iron Will",id="7001369E"},{val="Dark-cleaver",id="7001131F"},{val="Pest-hewer",id=70011316}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2349,scope="Legendary Items",name="The Ghost-forge",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Fastarr",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFastarr has asked you to bring him an infused sapphire with which the qualities you desire may be bestowed upon your weapon.\n* Talk to Fastarr\n* Turn in Infused Sapphire\nObj 2:\nFastarr can be found at the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nFastarr has bidden you to speak with him when you are ready to seek out the forge, but warns you that some unnatural force appears to have taken control of it.\n* Talk to Fastarr to travel to the Ghost-forge\nObj 3:\nFastarr can be found at the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nYou should return to Fastarr to complete the enhancement of your weapon.\n* Talk to Fastarr\n* Turn in Empowered Sapphire"},
{area="Nimrodel",zone="Lothlórien",money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="You have been acknowledged a friend of Lothlórien through your efforts on behalf of the Elves.\nYou should visit the glades of Hythe, well to the south and east, along the banks of the river Anduin.",mobs={{locations={"17.24S, 64.00W"},name="Maliriel"},{locations={"16.22S, 73.50W","15.03S, 66.39W"},name="Haldir"},{locations={"13.48S, 72.46W","15.77S, 72.51W","16.20S, 72.48W"},name="Galadhrim Lookout"}},category="Lothlórien",id=2350,scope="n/a",name="The Glades of Egladil",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Lothlórien Sentinel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMaliriel can be found in the field of Imlad Lalaith in the eastern reaches of Egladil, along the banks of the river Anduin.\nYou have been asked to introduce yourself to Maliriel, the Mistress of the Feast for Lothlórien.\n* Talk to Maliriel at Imlad Lalaith",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2368},area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Elves of the Golden Host are concerned with the continuing presence of Orcs in the Mirk-eaves and in procuring supplies for the Malledhrim in the east.",mobs={{locations={"15.92S, 59.97W"},name="Dannaswen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2351,scope="n/a",prev={1166},destinypoints={{val=250}},name="The Glory of the Malledhrim",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,pois={{locations={"14.52S, 59.26W"},name="Rock-pile (Level 1)"}},minlevel=56,b="Dannaswen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe pile of stones is atop a small rise in the Orc-camp at the Gostannon, north-east of Amon Angeled.\nDannaswen has asked you to plant the banner of the Malledhrim at the Orc-camp near the Gostannon and defend it against the Orcs.\n* Use Rock-pile (Level 1)\n* Turn in Banner of the Malledhrim\nObj 2:\nThe Gostannon lies to the north of Amon Angened.\nDannaswen asked you to defend the banner you planted in the enemy encampment at the Gostannon.\n* Defend the banner of the Malledhrim\nObj 3:\nDannaswen is at the Elf-waypost atop Amon Angened, south of the Gostannon.\nYou should return to Dasswen with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Dannaswen atop Amon Angened"},
{["next"]={2657},area="The Drownholt",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Elves of the Drownholt are missing one of their own -- a curious Elf who fancied he heard the sorrow of the trees as they made their way through the swamplands. He has not returned, and his companions yearn for news of him.",mobs={{locations={"18.31S, 57.36W"},name="Nífdir"},{locations={"16.93S, 54.69W"},name="Nenedhel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2352,scope="n/a",name="The Glowering Trees of the Drownholt",arcs="The Wroth Glade",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,c={"* Nífdir is in the Drownholt at [18.3S, 57.4W]"},minlevel=58,b="Nenedhel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNenedhel parted ways with Nífdir to the west of Estolad Mernael.\nNenedhel, leader of the Malledhrim in the Drownholt, has asked you to seek Nífdir in the swamp-lands.\n* Seek Nífdir in the Drownholt\nObj 2:\nNenedhel is at Estolad Mernael, east of Nífdir's small camp.\nYou should speak with Nenedhel and assure him that Nífdir is safe, but not yet ready to rejoin his companions.\n* Talk to Nenedhel at Estolad Mernael"},
{area="Minas Eriol",zone="Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+500 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="18s 40c"}},d="The goblins of Minas Eriol are led by a terrible creature named Nishrûk.",selectoneof={{val="Osmann's Pride",id="7001D131"},{val="Nishrûk's Foe",id="70006BDF"},{val="Constable's Halberd",id="70006BA5"},{val="Deputy's Trinket",id="7001D22D"},{val="Ashleaf's Jeweled Bracelet",id="700069DC"}},category="Lone-lands",id=2353,scope="n/a",name="The Goblin-leader",arcs="Noble Deeds",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Deputy Osmann",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblin's leader, Nishrûk, dwells in a goblin-fort built among the ruins south-east of The Forsaken Inn.\nDeputy Osmann has asked you to slay Nishrûk, the leader of the goblins troubling The Forsaken Inn.\n* Defeat Nishrûk\nObj 2:\nDeputy Osmann awaits you across the bridge at the eastern edge of the ruins at Minas Eriol.\nYou entered the ruins and defeated Nishrûk, as Deputy Osmann requested. You should return to him with news of your success.\n* Talk to Deputy Osmann"},
{["next"]={1107},area="Bullroarer's Sward",zone="Evendim",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Bob Greeneaves is confused by your discoveries among the goblin-camps.",category="Evendim",id=2354,scope="n/a",prev={1018},name="The Goblins' Source",arcs="Hobgoblin's Recipe",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="Bob Greeneaves",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are spiders in the North Moors, south of Dwaling.\nBob Greeneaves asked you to go out and slay spiders, in the hopes that the goblins will leave.\n* Defeat Wood-web Spinners\n* Defeat Wood-web Hunters\nObj 2:\nBob Greeneaves is in Dwaling, north of the North Moors.\nYou should return to Bob Greeneaves with news of your success.\n* Talk to Bob Greeneaves"},
{area="Ram Dúath",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Aslak of the Suuri-lehmä, told you that the goblins have collected hoards of gems in the fort they share with the Angmarim on the north-eastern pass of Ram Dúath.",mobs={{locations={"3.07S, 39.06W"},name="Aslak"}},category="Angmar",id=2355,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="The Goblins' Treasure",receive={{val="Rescued Gem",id="70002CD8"}},level=43,c={"* The gems can be looted from goblins and found in chests around Bail Róva [0.0N, 34.5W] in north-east Ram Dúath. A Small Fellowship is recommended."},pois={{locations={"0.11S, 34.41W","0.50S, 35.34W","0.54S, 35.25W","0.32S, 35.33W","0.23S, 34.30W","0.34S, 35.05W","0.20S, 34.41W","0.29S, 34.28W","0.15S, 34.46W","0.44S, 35.32W","0.46S, 35.23W","0.09S, 35.20W"},name="Goblin-gems"}},minlevel=38,b="Aslak",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblins of the Ram Dúath have stolen several treasures from the Suuri-lehmä.\nAslak has told you that the gems might be found in chests within the Angmarim fort to the North-east.\n* Collect goblin-gems (6 Goblin-gems )\nObj 2:\nYou have recovered several semi-precious gems stolen from the Surri-lehmä by the goblins of the Ram Duath.\nYou must return them to Aslak at Lehmä-koti.\n* Talk to Aslak\n* Turn in Goblin-gems"},
{area="The Marish",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Gunderic Grubb, innkeeper of The Golden Perch is entering the Four Farthings Brewing-moot.",mobs={{locations={"31.98S, 63.79W"},name="Gunderic Grubb"}},category="Shire",id=2356,scope="n/a",name="The Golden Perch",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"},{val="Old Withywindle",id="7000368F"}},level=10,pois={{locations={"35.07S, 66.90W"},name="Old Yeast"}},minlevel=6,b="Gunderic Grubb",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe brigand camp is in the hills south of Woodhall, about midway between Tuckborough and Maggot's farm. The Golden Perch Inn is in Stock, east of Woodhall.\nGunderic Grubb has sent you to search a brigand camp for his missing package of yeast.\n* Bring the yeast to Gunderic Grubb\n* Collect the yeast",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1061},area="Nimrodel",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Galadhrim of Lothlórien feel the pressing of danger upon their borders from many sides, but never so violently as the recent attacks from Moria since the arrival of a secret company in the Golden Wood. Haldir, a marchwarden of the Nimrodel, wishes to secure a friendship with the dwarves of Khazad-dûm so that the evils of Moria may be kept at bay, for the safety of both lands.",mobs={{locations={"5.16S, 111.96W"},name="Hrólfur"},{locations={"16.22S, 73.50W","15.03S, 66.39W"},name="Haldir"}},category="Lothlórien",id=2357,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="The Good Will of the Galadhrim",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Haldir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHrólfur, an important overseer, can likely be found in the Chamber of the Crossroads in Moria, in Durin's Way.\nHaldir has pressed you to bring an important message from Celeborn to Hrólfur after a previous attempt to make contact was spurned by the proud dwarf.\n* Talk to Hrólfur\n* Turn in Celeborn's Letter\nObj 2:\nHrólfur is in the Chamber of the Crossroads, in Durin's Way.\nYou should speak with Hrólfur and accept his two charges: the conquering of Nalâ-dûm, where the water-wheels are, and Lumul-nar, the Hall of Mirrors.\n* Help the dwarves regain control of Lumul-nar\n* Help the dwarves regain control of Nalâ-dûm\nObj 3:\nHaldir awaits news of your good deeds towards the dwarves upon his flet near the River Nimrodel, on the western border of Lothlórien.\nYou should seek Haldir and inform him of all that passed while you assisted the dwarves.\n* Talk to Haldir at Talan Haldir"},
{money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Once a great and beautiful crossroads of Moria, the Grand Stair is a vile haven of many of the gathered tribes of Orcs. Igash, regarded as a leader by all of the varied groups, gathers tribute from every tribe to give to Mazog, the mightiest and greatest of Orcs in Khazad-dûm. The dwarves wish to unseat Igash's Orcs from this Grand Stair and stop Mazog from receiving valuable and unsavoury gifts.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2358,scope="n/a",name="The Grand Stair - Igash's Lash",destinypoints={{val=750}},level=60,minlevel=60,b="Eilíefr",repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nIgash can be found atop the Grand Stair, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall where Eilífr holds his post.\nEilífr has asked you to defeat Igash and collect his lash to assist in efforts to reclaim that crossroads for the dwarves. He wishes to see the lash as proof of your deed.\n* Return the lash to Eilíefr at the Twenty-first Hall\n* Turn in Igash's Lash"},
{area="The Twenty-first Hall",zone="Moria",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Once a great and beautiful crossroads of Moria, the Grand Stair is a vile haven of many of the gathered tribes of Orcs. Igash, regarded as a leader by all of the varied groups, gathers tribute from every tribe to give to Mazog, the mightiest and greatest of Orcs in Khazad-dûm. The dwarves wish to unseat Igash's Orcs from this Grand Stair and stop Mazog from receiving valuable and unsavoury gifts.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2359,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=750}},name="The Grand Stair - Master's Mark",level=60,minlevel=60,b="Eilíefr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nMany tribes of Orcs prowl the Grand Stair, their leaders among them, found south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nEilífr has asked you to defeat Orc leaders in the Grand Stair to assist in efforts to reclaim that crossroads for the dwarves. He wishes to see their Marks as proof of your deed.\n* Return the marks to Eilífr at the Twenty-first Hall\n* Turn in The Devoted's Mark\n* Turn in The Beast's Mark\n* Turn in Gothgaash's Mark\n* Turn in Forzunk's Mark",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Twenty-first Hall",zone="Moria",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Once a great and beautiful crossroads of Moria, the Grand Stair is a vile haven of many of the gathered tribes of Orcs. Igash, regarded as a leader by all of the varied groups, gathers tribute from every tribe to give to Mazog, the mightiest and greatest of Orcs in Khazad-dûm. The dwarves wish to unseat Igash's Orcs from this Grand Stair and stop Mazog from receiving valuable and unsavoury gifts.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2360,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="The Grand Stair -- Sweeping the Stairs",level=60,minlevel=60,b="Geirr",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nMany tribes of Orcs prowl the Grand Stair, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall.\nGeirr has asked you to defeat many Orcs in the Grand Stair to assist in efforts to reclaim that crossroads for the dwarves.\nObj 2:\nGeirr is in the Twenty-first Hall, north-west of the Grand Stair.\nGeirr will wish to hear of your success among the Orcs in the once-beautiful crossroads of the dwarves.\n* Return to Geirr at the Twenty-first Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="After you recovered the master key from the goblin-torturer, Aeglas decided it is time to depart from Goblin-town.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},selectoneof={{val="Friend of Aeglas",id="7000D2F6"},{val="Ally of Glorwen",id="7000D2F4"},{val="Fall of a Great Goblin",id="7000D2F7"},{val="Tarnaith",id="7000D2D8"},{val="Avorhigil",id="7000D2D6"},{val="Oghûk's Foil",id="7000D2F5"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2361,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1440},name="The Great Escape",arcs="The Great Escape",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Aeglas",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAeglas must be protected as he attempts to lead Glorwen and Oghûk to safety. It falls to you to defend him along his way.\n* Speak with Aeglas\nObj 2:\nElrond is at the Last Homely House in Rivendell, far to the south of Goblin-town.\nWith your aid, Aeglas and Glorwen escaped to safety. Oghûk proved as treacherous as any goblin. You should report your victories to Elrond Halfelven.\n* Talk to Elrond at Rivendell"},
{area="Hobbiton-Bywater",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Gerd Whitfoot, innkeeper of The Green Dragon in Bywater, is entering the Four Farthings Brewing-moot.",mobs={{locations={"31.80S, 69.64W"},name="Barmy Rootknot"}},category="Shire",id=2362,scope="n/a",name="The Green Dragon",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"},{val="Green Dragon's Breath Ale",id="700036FE"}},level=9,pois={{locations={"26.77S, 71.84W"},name="Dwarf-barrel"}},minlevel=5,b="Barmy Rootknot",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe lost barrel is somewhere north-west of Overhill. The Green Dragon Inn is in Bywater, south-east of Overhill.\nBarmy Rootknot, the assistant innkeeper at The Green Dragon Inn, has sent you off in search of a lost brandy-barrel.\n* Bring the barrel back to Barmy Rootknot\n* Collect the dwarf-barrel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Enedwaith",area="Gloomglens",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="Iolo Brochtû has told you of a legendary creature they call the Grey King who haunts the bluffs of the Gloomglens, crushing passers-by with great stones.",mobs={{locations={"61.96S, 22.94W"},name="Iolo Brochtû"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2363,scope="n/a",prev={83},destinypoints={{val=500}},name="The Grey King",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Iolo Brochtû",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance to the Grey King's lair lies in a gully to the south-west of Maur Tulhau.\nIolo Brochtû has asked you to rid his village of the threat of the Grey King.\n* Find and defeat the Grey King\nObj 2:\nIolo Brochtû is at Maur Tulhau, north-east of the Grey King's lair.\nYou should return to Iolo Brochtû with news of the Grey King's defeat.\n* Talk to Iolo Brochtû at Maur Tulhau",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2323},zone="Eregion",area="Glâd Ereg",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Dunlendings have established a lumber-camp in the wood of Sâd Rechu, where they collect wood for the use of Saruman's craftsmen.",mobs={{locations={"40.15S, 16.48W"},name="Inufileg"}},category="Eregion",id=2364,scope="n/a",prev={2537},name="The Guards of Sâd Rechu",arcs="The Wood of Sâd Rechu",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Inufileg",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDunlendings can be found to the southeast of Gwingris.\nInufileg has asked you to defeat the Dunlendings who are laying waste to the forest of Sâd Rechu.\n* Defeat Dunlendings southeast of Gwingris (12).\nObj 2:\nInufileg is at Gwingris, northwest of the Dunlending camp.\nYou should report back to Inufileg regarding your success against the Dunlendings.\n* Talk to Inufileg at Gwingris",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nan Laeglin",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Bands of savage half-orcs have set upon the folk living on the outskirts of Lhanuch. Siorus Brehur of the Council of Thanes has asked if you have the strength to aid the people of Lhanuch and defeat these raiders before they destroy more homesteads. If you can do so, he will argue in council against the demands of Isengard.",mobs={{locations={"66.46S, 17.32W"},name="Siorus Brehur"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2365,scope="n/a",name="The Half-orcs",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Siorus Brehur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalf-orcs can be found throughout Nan Laeglin, especially where they have raided Uch-lûth farms.\nSiorus Brehur has asked you to repel the half-orc raiders and their leader Bûzog from Nan Laeglin.\n* Defeat half-orcs (12)\n* Defeat Bûzog\nObj 2:\nSiorus Brehur is at the Brenin's Hall in the village of Nan Laeglin.\nYou should return at once to Siorus Brehur with news of your success.\n* Talk to Siorus Brehur in the Brenin's Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2650},area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The half-orcs at Barad Morlas are using evil wolves to scour the ruins.",mobs={{locations={"46.95S, 12.47W"},name="Dornhador"}},category="Eregion",id=2366,scope="n/a",prev={281},name="The Half-orcs' Beasts",arcs="Wolf-keepers of Barad Morlas",level=49,c={"* Barad Morlas is at [48.1S, 13.7W]"},minlevel=44,b="Dornhador",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalf-orc wolf-keepers can be found patrolling Barad Morlas, south-west of Echad Eregion.\nDornhador has asked you to defeat the half-orc wolf-keepers at Barad Morlas to help throw their efforts into disarray.\n* Defeat half-orc wolf-keepers at Barad Morlas\nObj 2:\nDornhador is at Echad Eregion, north-east of Barad Morlas.\nYou should return to Dornhador with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Dornhador at Echad Eregion"},
{area="Nan Laeglin",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Bands of savage half-orcs have set upon the folk living on the outskirts of Lhanuch. Siorus Brehur has asked if you have the strength to aid the people of Lhanuch and defeat these raiders before they destroy more homesteads.",mobs={{locations={"66.46S, 17.32W"},name="Siorus Brehur"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2367,scope="n/a",prev={2314},name="The Half-orcs -- Repeatable",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Siorus Brehur",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalf-orcs can be found throughout Nan Laeglin, especially where they have raided Uch-lûth farms.\nSiorus Brehur has asked you to repel the half-orc raiders from the farms of his people.\n* Defeat half-orcs (12)\nObj 2:\nSiorus Brehur is at the Brenin's Hall in the village of Nan Laeglin.\nYou should return at once to Siorus Brehur with news of your success.\n* Talk to Siorus Brehur in the Brenin's Hall"},
{["next"]={2314},area="Nan Laeglin",zone="Enedwaith",d="You have encountered an unusual pair of Men, sent it seems from Isengard to offer a treaty of fealty between the Uch-lûth and Saruman.",mobs={{locations={"66.46S, 17.32W"},name="Gwilhum"},{locations={"66.46S, 17.32W"},name="Gergenau"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2368,scope="n/a",name="The Hand of Isengard",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Gwilhum",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe emissary's champion is in the Brenin's Hall in Lhanuch.\nYou should speak with the emissary's champion.\n* Talk to the emissary's champion in the Brenin's Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nan Laeglin",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You have learned that an unknown Ranger of the Grey Company has entered the Mournshaws in search of a hidden path to the south. The Algraig firmly believe this forest is haunted by powerful and fey spirits. Only the Derudh of Nan Laeglin and a few brave hunters dare enter the place. Even fewer return....",mobs={{locations={"66.46S, 17.32W"},name="Penlhun Brehur"},{locations={"66.59S, 21.50W"},name="Daervunn"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2369,scope="n/a",name="The Haunted Forest",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Penlhun Brehur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFind the Ranger who has wandered into the northern reaches of the Mournshaws. It is uncertain whether he still lives, but if so it is possible he has found a path into Dunland that is unwatched by enemy eyes.\n* Find Daervunn in the Mournshaws",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
