ourneyman Woodworker Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={255,2430},area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="You can see the shape of objects hidden within pieces of wood before you have even begun to work on them, but you still lack a certain flourish of technique.",mobs={{locations={"26.51S, 53.73W"},name="Millicent Greenlake"},{locations={"20.12S, 97.10W"},name="Tyrvi"},{locations={"28.54S, 6.18W"},name="Mallasil"},{locations={"7.50S, 64.12W"},name="Turbert Pither"},{locations={"22.85S, 67.60W"},name="Gundabald Gardner"},{locations={"31.86S, 69.41W"},name="Porto Chubb"},{locations={"34.61S, 75.43W"},name="Belba Bracegirdle"},{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Almar"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Toby Sandheaver"},{locations={"17.94S, 53.71W"},name="Henry Suggs"},{locations={"33.71S, 62.10W","31.36S, 66.05W"},name="Madulas Brandybuck"},{locations={"11.99S, 67.78W"},name="Lewis Marshbanks"},{locations={"27.44S, 68.27W"},name="Olo Brockhouse"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Gib Heathstraw"},{locations={"28.20S, 92.66W"},name="Lendaellin"}},category="Crafting",id=2372,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Heart of the Wood, Part III",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Tyrvi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nMillicent Greenlake supervises construction at Thornley's work-site in the Bree-fields, north of the town of Bree.\nYou have been told to speak with Millicent Greenlake, supervising construction in the Bree-fields, to improve your woodworking techniques. You have also been warned of her impatient nature.\n* Talk to Millicent Greenlake",traits={{val="Expert Woodworker Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Twenty-first Hall",zone="Moria",d="With a speed that astounds those who see you working, you deftly carve pieces of art and utility from wood that formerly held but their promise.",mobs={{locations={"12.79S, 14.84W","38.06S, 12.99W","30.71S, 6.19W","14.35S, 51.55W","5.19S, 112.08W","41.27S, 15.24W","13.49S, 58.09W","7.22S, 66.22W","117.69S, 128.90W","28.08S, 23.42W","27.46S, 1.60E","32.00S, 55.14W","117.99S, 41.21W","22.40S, 52.58W","13.93S, 103.22W","61.95S, 16.26W","87.98S, 144.01W","17.29S, 61.64W","68.83S, 31.83W","97.49S, 143.98W","27.47S, 1.60E","119.45S, 35.81W","84.70S, 15.79W","72.10S, 16.13W"},name="Nekros"},{locations={"18.31S, 53.81W"},name="Giles Chadwick"},{locations={"28.16S, 70.09W"},name="Primula Diggins"},{locations={"31.05S, 29.84W"},name="Cuthdag"},{locations={"15.49S, 67.70W"},name="Tawaril"},{locations={"5.42S, 104.94W"},name="Grái"},{locations={"14.54S, 51.07W"},name="Rosnir"},{locations={"9.70S, 40.50W","18.47S, 63.76W"},name="Tawariel"}},category="Crafting",id=2373,scope="Crafting Advancement",prev={255,2429},name="The Heart of the Wood, Part IV",receive={{val="Bow of Shadowy Might",id="70006C56"}},level=40,pois={{locations={"35.72S, 7.16W"},name="Black Huorn Heartwood"}},minlevel=35,b="Óleif",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGiles Chadwick is in the town of Trestlebridge, north of Bree.\nYou have been told that Giles Chadwick, a master woodworker, might help you refine your technique.\n* Talk to Giles Chadwick\nObj 2:\nGiles Chadwick gave you his notes and the recipe for fashioning a Bow of Shadowy Might.\nGiles Chadwick asked you to prove your woodworking ability by making a Bow of Shadowy Might for him to judge.\n* Use Black Huorn Heartwood\n* Turn in Plank of Treated Lebethron\nObj 3:\nGiles Chadwick is in the town of Trestlebridge, north of Bree.\nGiles Chadwick asked you to make a Bow of Shadowy Might for him to inspect and thereby determine your skill at woodworking.\n* Bring the Bow of Shadowy Might to Giles Chadwick\n* Turn in Bow of Shadowy Might",traits={{val="Artisan Woodworker Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={434,324},area="Lich Bluffs",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+900 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Mincham is interested in finding the remaining fragments of the amulet you brought him, in hopes that a local hermit might be able to decipher the mystery it represents.",mobs={{locations={"72.06S, 16.12W"},name="Lhudd"},{locations={"70.57S, 15.46W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2374,scope="n/a",prev={187},name="The Hermit",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe second half of the broken amulet may be found on shades throughout the Lich Bluffs.\nWhen you locate the other half of the broken amulet, seek out and locate the hermit Lhudd in a small grove of trees to the west of the road called the Hall of Sanctuary.\n* Kill 6 Condemned Warrior\nObj 2:\nThe second half of the broken amulet may be found on shades throughout the Lich Bluffs.\nWhen you locate the other half of the broken amulet, seek out and locate the hermit Lhudd in a small grove of trees to the west of the road called the Hall of Sanctuary.\n* Turn in Second Half of the Broken Amulet\nObj 3:\nLhudd the hermit dwells at the Hall of Sanctuary, west of the main road and south-west of Mincham's camp.\nMincham told you to bring both halves of the amulet to Lhudd the hermit.\n* Talk to Lhudd\n* Turn in Second Half of the Broken Amulet\n* Turn in Nod Rhûmiad (Level 1)"},
{["next"]={1505},area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Angmarim patrols regularly carry orders and payroll through Imlad Balchorth.",mobs={{locations={"6.95N, 25.86W"},name="Birgir"}},category="Angmar",id=2375,scope="n/a",prev={2884},name="The Highwayman",arcs="Highwayman",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Birgir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAngmarim patrols can be found on the roads in Imlad Balchorth, west of Myrkworth.\nBirgir has asked you to waylay Angmarim patrols and recover any orders or money-boxes they may be carrying.\n* Bring the orders and the money-box back to Birgir\n* Turn in Angmarim-orders\n* Turn in Money-box"},
{["next"]={2632},reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="The tomb-robbers have fled to the hills above the Way of Kings. From them, they alert the forces of Angmar, their new allies, to the actions of the Rangers.",category="Evendim",id=2376,scope="n/a",name="The Hills Have Eyes",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=37,minlevel=32,b="Nimbellas",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe crypts line the Way of Kings leading into Annúminas.\nBefore the Rangers can move to investigate the state of the crypts within the Way of Kings, they must secure the hills from the remaining tomb-robbers. Nimbellas has asked you to do this.\n* Help Maladan scout Arthobel\n* Aid Nethrandir with the robbers of Tham Sarch\n* Aid Nethrandir with the mirrors of Tham Sarch\n* Aid Rodlam with the robbers of Tham Laegamon\n* Aid Rodlam with the longbows of Tham Laegamon\nObj 2:\nNimbellas is at the Ranger-camp along the Way of Kings.\nThe hills have been cleared of threats. You should return at once to Nimbellas.\n* Talk to Nimbellas in the Way of Kings",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1715},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+300 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="9s 52c"}},d="Ilmo is a herdsman and requires some supplies for which he has already traded to care for his herd.",mobs={{locations={"19.18N, 70.89W"},name="Kaleva"},{locations={"19.42N, 70.22W"},name="Ilmo"},{locations={"19.45N, 71.31W"},name="Matti"}},category="Forochel",id=2377,scope="n/a",name="The Hirvi-herd",arcs="Herding Elk",level=47,c={"* Matti is in Sûri-kylä at [19.5N, 71.3W]\n* Kaleva is in Sûri-kylä at [19.2N, 70.9W]\n* Rauno is inside the Great Lodge of Sûri-kylä at [19.5N, 72.0W]"},pois={{locations={"19.54N, 71.99W"},name="Elk-saddle"}},minlevel=42,b="Ilmo",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIlmo has asked you to collect a saddle from Rauno, reins from Matti, and a salt lick from Kaleva within Sûri-kylä.\n* Collect the reins from Matti\n* Collect the salt lick from Kaleva\n* Collect the saddle from Rauno\nObj 2:\nIlmo is outside of Sûri-kylä with his elk-herd.\nYou should bring the items you collected to Ilmo at once.\n* Talk to Ilmo\n* Turn in Elk-saddle\n* Turn in Elk-reins\n* Turn in Salt-lick"},
{["next"]={228},area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="Wafri's plan involves using the scent-glands you collected to trick the queen of the grodbog-hive into revealing herself, allowing you to dispatch her.",selectoneof={{val="Shield of the Palace of Náin",id=70016089},{val="Gamli's Shield",id="7001608C"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2378,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1909},name="The Hive-Queen",arcs="Bedbugs!",level=52,pois={{locations={"6.47S, 113.41W"},name="Hive Nest"}},minlevel=47,b="Wafri",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe grodbog-lair is in the Palace of Náin, north-west of the Dolven-view camp and directly north of Lamâb-dûm.\nWafri told you to take the scent-glands to the grodbog-hive and crush them. The resulting scent should draw forth the hive-queen.\n* Use Hive Nest\n* Kill 1 Grodbog Hive-queen\nObj 2:\nWafri is at the Dolven-view camp, south-east of the Palace of Náin.\nYou should report back to Wafri with news of your success.\n* Talk to Wafri\n* Turn in Grodbog Scent-gland"},
{["next"]={2116},area="Gathbúrz",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Wargs of the Enemy will present the greatest threat to the Malledhrim when it comes time for the Golden Host to withdraw from Mirkwood, for they would be able to overtake the Elves swiftly.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 46.57W"},name="Rodelleth"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2379,scope="n/a",prev={579},name="The Howling Regiment",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Rodelleth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWargs can be found in Gathbúrz.\nRodelleth has asked you to defeat several of the Wargs prowling through Gathbúrz to help ensure a safe retreat for the Malledhrim.\n* Defeat Wargs in Gathbúrz (15)\nObj 2:\nRodelleth is at Thangúlhad in Gathbúrz.\nYou should return to Rodelleth and let her know that many Wargs fell beneath your assaults.\n* Talk to Rodelleth at Thangúlhad"},
{["next"]={2111},area="Tyrn Fornech",zone="Evendim",d="The Ranger Culang has learned of a great treasure buried long ago by a Dúnadan-landholder and wants it recovered before it is found by tomb-robbers.",category="Evendim",id=2380,scope="n/a",prev={2608},name="The Hunt Continues",arcs="The Treasure Hunt",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=33,pois={{locations={"6.94S, 63.83W"},name="Stone Marker"}},minlevel=28,b="Stone Marker",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe treasure may lie beneath another stone marker, somewhere in Evendim, if this riddle is to be believed:\n\"To settle disputes, men fight in the ring of stone.\nOutside the wall, my marker lies hidden.\"\nYou should examine the marker when you find it for some clue to the location of the treasure.\n* Find the solution to the riddle"},
{reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Gloomglens",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="According to Prestadir, the medallion you found says something about a Hunter King and the Mournshaws.",mobs={{locations={"66.59S, 21.50W"},name="Daervunn"},{locations={"63.48S, 21.45W"},name="Prestadír"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2381,scope="n/a",prev={1988},name="The Hunter King?",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Prestadír",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nDaervunn is at Echad Daervunn in the Mournshaws, far to the south of Echad Idhrenfair.\nPrestadir suggested you take the sigil you found to Daervunn in the Mournshaws.\n* Talk to Daervunn\n* Turn in Sigil of the Rhi Helvarch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2337},area="Tâl Bruinen",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="8s 54c"}},d="Wistan is furious that the white hart he tracked across the Trollshaws may have been killed and its meat taken by a rival of his.",mobs={{locations={"36.91S, 14.21W"},name="Wistan"},{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Adwold"},{locations={"34.04S, 20.16W"},name="Barachen"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2382,scope="n/a",prev={2635},name="The Hunter's Injury",arcs="The Creeping Shadow",level=40,minlevel=35,b="Wistan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarachen is at his camp south of the road that runs through the Trollshaws, east of the Last Bridge.\nWistan has asked you to speak with Barachen to learn the whereabouts of Adwold.\n* Talk to Barachen\nObj 2:\nAccording to Barachen, Adwold has probably reached the Forsaken Inn by now.\nWistan is furious that Adwold has taken the meat and the glory from the death of the white hart he tracked across the Trollshaws and has sent you to confront him with a number of demands. Adwold stopped at Barachen's camp, but has probably arrived at the Forsaken Inn by now.\n* Talk to Adwold\n* Turn in Adwold's Distinctive Arrows\nObj 3:\nThe hunter Wistan is at Echad Candelleth, in Tâl Bruinen.\nYou have learned that Adwold did not take the meat of the white hart tracked by Wistan, but was interrupted by the arrival of some creature, the sight of which filled him with fear and caused him to renounce any further hunting in Tâl Bruinen. You should report this to Wistan.\n* Talk to Wistan"},
{["next"]={2576,90},area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="For a true hunter, speed and precision are everything. A lack of one brings ill fortune. A lack of both brings disaster.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 67.00W"},name="Cúlith"},{locations={"20.05S, 96.98W"},name="Dagfinn"},{locations={"18.84N, 72.37W"},name="Okko"},{locations={"29.34S, 56.79W"},name="Gytha Lainey"},{locations={"29.91S, 5.90W"},name="Mallenhadh"},{locations={"31.86S, 51.28W"},name="Flambard Took"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Bolo Boffin"},{locations={"15.33S, 101.59W"},name="Glanwen"},{locations={"9.52S, 41.07W"},name="Gaellant"},{locations={"28.14S, 92.17W"},name="Erydhriel"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Juniper Smith"},{locations={"25.27S, 48.71W"},name="Darren Mills"}},category="Hunter",id=2383,scope="n/a",requiredclasses="Hunter",name="The Hunter's Path",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Simple Celebrant Salve",id=70001049},{val="Avornhar",id="700010AB"}},level=15,minlevel=15,b="Darren Mills",repeatable="No",traits={{val="Fast Draw"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGytha Lainey, a hunter of great skill, can be found in Bree-land at Adso's Camp on the road between Bree and Buckland.\nYou have been told to speak with Gytha Lainey for instruction in the art of the hunter.\n* Talk to Gytha Lainey\nObj 2:\nGytha Lainey, a hunter of great skill, can be found in Bree-land at Adso's Camp on the Great East Road between Bree and Buckland.\nGytha is waiting to speak with you about journeying into the Old Forest.\n* Journey with Gytha Lainey into the Old Forest\nObj 3:\nGytha Lainey, a hunter of great skill, can be found in Bree-land at Adso's Camp, on the Great East Road between Bree and Buckland.\nGytha is waiting to speak with you about your victory over Yellowfang within the Old Forest.\n* Talk to Gytha Lainey"},
{["next"]={1997},area="The Scuttledells",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Fuirgam believes that Gollum has fled into the twisted paths of the Scuttledells to avoid capture and wishes you to aid his scouts in attempting to track down the skulking creature before he escapes or falls into the hands of the Enemy in Dol Guldur.",mobs={{locations={"12.45S, 50.88W","8.72S, 52.22W"},name="Miluimil"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2384,scope="n/a",prev={843},name="The Hunt for Gollum",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,minlevel=58,b="Fuirgam",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMiluimil is at Ivorel's camp in the Scuttledells, north of Ost Galadh.\nFuirgam has asked you to inform the scout Miluimil that Gollum may have come north into the Scuttledells and to offer what aid you can in finding and capturing him.\n* Talk to Miluimil in the Scuttledells"},
{["next"]={748,178},area="Taur Orthon",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+500 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="The Lossoth hunters were impressed by your display against the Warg, though they will not freely admit it.",mobs={{locations={"3.48N, 58.23W"},name="Valtteri"}},category="Forochel",id=2385,scope="n/a",prev={250},name="The Hunt is Afoot",arcs="Hunting for sport",level=44,minlevel=39,b="Valtteri",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWargs can be found in the south-west foothills.\nValtteri has instructed you to go into the forest and hunt the Wargs, collecting the fat from their underbelles for the Lossoth to use later.\n* Turn in Warg-fat\nObj 2:\nValtteri stands by his warg cage in Kauppa-kohta.\nYou should return the Warg-fat to Valtteri as he requested.\n* Talk to Valtteri"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="A charred and crumpled note found on the corpse of Kranklûk confirmed some suspicions held by the dwarf-agents watching over the Forges of Khazad-dûm. What is worse, it mentioned that Talug, the general of Fil Gashan, was nothing more than a puppet.",mobs={{locations={"13.43S, 108.08W"},name="Teitur"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2386,scope="n/a",name="The Illusion of Leadership",level=60,minlevel=57,b="Charred Note",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTeitur is at Anazârmekhem.\nYou discovered the note on the corpse of the Uruk Kranklûk, and after divining what you could, it became clear that it should be brought to Teitur who watches over Fil Gashan at Anazârmekhem.\n* Talk to Teitur\n* Turn in Charred Note",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={27},area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="21s 70c"}},d="Legend tells of a powerful Warg once offered the ability to rule all Wargs in return for service to the Iron Crown. A collar fashioned of iron was made and powerful sorceries used to enchant the item. The great beast was slain and the collar removed, but tales of the beast have been passed down through the ages amongst the Men of the North Downs.",mobs={{locations={"12.53S, 52.77W"},name="Amarion"}},category="North Downs",id=2387,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Iron Collar",arcs="Krithmog's Collar",level=41,minlevel=36,b="Heavy Iron Collar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAmarion is at his camp at Amon Raith in the North Downs.\nThe Ranger Amarion knows the story of the Warg-king. It is possible that the collar you have found has something to do with the legend. He should be shown the collar you have discovered. While fighting against the Wargs at Dol Dínen you discovered an iron collar. The discovery reminded you of legends long told here in the North Downs.\n* Talk to Amarion\n* Turn in Heavy Iron Collar"},
{["next"]={1737},area="North Trollshaws",zone="The Trollshaws",reputation={{val="+900 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="21s 70c"}},d="Thoroniel has prepared two bottles of poison from the trapdoor and flesh-gnawer fangs you brought to her, hopeful that their venom can be used against them.",mobs={{locations={"28.57S, 19.45W"},name="Thoroniel"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2388,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2343},name="Their Own Weapons",arcs="Fighting the Brood",level=41,pois={{locations={"26.99S, 19.50W","26.97S, 19.08W","26.85S, 18.92W","26.40S, 18.87W","27.54S, 19.42W","27.01S, 19.18W","26.56S, 19.26W","26.52S, 19.02W","27.22S, 19.30W"},name="Flesh-gnawer Eggs"},{locations={"27.69S, 18.91W","26.42S, 18.40W","26.94S, 18.06W","26.26S, 18.75W","26.89S, 18.32W","27.31S, 18.37W","27.81S, 18.87W","26.26S, 18.44W"},name="Trapdoor-eggs"}},minlevel=36,b="Thoroniel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTrapdoor egg sacs and flesh-gnawer egg sacs can be found throughout the Wovenvales.\nThoroniel has given you two bottles of venom, and asked you to pour venom from one bottle onto egg sacs belonging to the other brood, and to do the same for the remaining bottle.\n* Use Trapdoor-eggs\n* Turn in Bottle of Flesh-gnawer-venom\n* Use Flesh-gnawer Eggs\n* Turn in Bottle of Trapdoor-venom\nObj 2:\nThoroniel is outside the Wovenvales in the North Trollshaws.\nThe Elf-scout Thoroniel is waiting to hear whether you successfully made use of the venom-bottles she gave you.\n* Talk to Thoroniel\n* Turn in Bottle of Trapdoor-venom\n* Turn in Bottle of Flesh-gnawer-venom"},
{["next"]={2524},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+500 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Menikko has told you of a lost Lossoth treasure that has now returned to light.",mobs={{locations={"19.54N, 71.99W"},name="Menikko"},{locations={"11.45N, 69.70W"},name="Esko"}},category="Forochel",id=2389,scope="n/a",name="The Jewel of Ice",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Menikko",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nEsko is in Pynti-peldot, just south of the great bay.\nMenikko has asked you to speak with a man named Esko to learn the story of the lost Lossoth treasure.\n* Talk to Esko in Pynti-peldot",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+700 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="Your constant harassment of the Angmarim has not gone unnoticed. The Rangers wish to push the fight to the Gates of Carn Dûm itself and defeat the leader of the Angmarim in Himbar.",mobs={{locations={"10.87N, 23.93W"},name="Areneth"}},selectoneof={{val="Areneth's Staff",id="700011F3"},{val="Slayer of Garthamendir",id="7000EAE6"},{val="Areneth's Shield",id="700161D7"},{val="Great Axe of the Hill-chieftain",id="700011F4"},{val="Areneth's Mantle",id="700011F2"}},category="Angmar",id=2390,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1274},name="The Keeper Garthamendir",arcs="A Tenuous Thread",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Areneth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGarthamendir guards the gates of Carn Dûm to the west.\nAreneth warned you of the Cargûl and its terrible wrath. But killing the fell creature is the only way to break the Angmarim forces. He warned you not to face Garthamendir alone.\n* Kill 1 Garthamendir\nObj 2:\nAreneth is at Gath Forthnír, east of Carn Dûm.\nGarthamendir was defeated and his forces shattered. You should return to Areneth with the news.\n* Talk to Areneth"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Ost Elendil, the great palace of the kings of old, is on the island beyond the bridge of Ariant. At its base is the entrance to Haudh Valandil, the tomb of Valandil son of Isildur. I fear that the tomb, long-undisturbed, has become the home to great evils: both of Angmar's design and otherwise.\nHave you seen the vile creatures known as Kergrim? They are believed to be some relative of the cave-claw, but more prone to disease and the desecration of hallowed places.\nSome of these beasts have come to Haudh Valandil, and they must be cleared from the tomb, especially their brute of a leader: Shingrinder, he is called, and he is vile. You will do this, $CLIENT_NAME$, if you honour the ancient places of the Dúnedain, and you will return to me with news of your success. If I have been drawn elsewhere, report instead to Captain-General Daerdan at Echad Garthadir, the Ranger-encampment here in the city.",category="Annúminas",id=2391,scope="n/a",name="The Kergrim Stalk Haudh Valandil",receive={{val="Annúminas Mark",id="700216BF"}},level=40,minlevel=35,repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nKergrim stalk Haudh Valandil, the tomb on the island beyond the bridge of Ariant, in Annúminas.\nGlangilith has asked you to defeat the kergrim that stalk the depths of Haudh Valandil, including their leader Shingrinder.\n* Defeat Kergrim in Haudh Valandil (20)\n* Defeat Shingrinder",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={309},area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Thórth suspects that whoever is leading the Dourhands at the Icereave Mines is hiding in a locked area within the mines.",mobs={{locations={"9.38N, 81.15W"},name="Thórth"}},category="Forochel",id=2392,scope="n/a",prev={1906},name="The Key to their Greed",arcs="The Icereave Mines",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Thórth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Icereave Mines lie to the southwest of Zigilgund.\nThórth has asked you to drive the Dourhands from the Icereave Mines.\n* Take a key from a Dourhand within the ancient Icereave Mines\nObj 2:\nThórth is at Zigilgund.\nYou should return to Thórth with news of your victory.\n* Bring the key to Thórth\n* Turn in Bent Dwarf-key"},
{money={{val="53s 90c"}},d="Due to the extent of their losses, the leaders of the Moria and Mordor Orcs are meeting to discuss a truce.",selectoneof={{val="Bane of Khîl and Ozût",id="700163CB"},{val="Pauldrons of Brutal Onslaught",id="70017CEF"},{val="Truce Breaker",id=70016417}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2393,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={180,825},name="The Killing Blow",arcs="Orcs of Mordor",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Knakk",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKhîl and Ozût are meeting in the Great Hall of Durin, north-east of the Orc-watch.\nKhîl and Ozût, the leaders of the Moria and Mordor Orcs, are meeting to discuss a truce. The dwarves want to use this opportunity to strike at and defeat both leaders. Knakk suggested you bring allies.\n* Defeat Ozût, leader of Mordor's Orcs\n* Defeat Khîl, leader of Moria's Orcs\nObj 2:\nKnakk is in the Orc-watch, south-west of the Great Hall of Durin.\nKnakk will want to hear how you succesfully interrupted the meeting and defeated Khîl and Ozût.\n* Talk to Knakk at the Orc-watch"},
{["next"]={2495},area="Kingsfell",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="11s 50c"}},d="Orcs have entered the North Downs from the north. The farmers of the region fled south, except old Gatson, who is determined to hold his land against the Orcs.",mobs={{locations={"10.33S, 45.62W"},name="Gatson"},{locations={"9.43S, 47.27W"},name="Orthonn"}},category="North Downs",id=2394,scope="n/a",name="The Last Farm",arcs="The Last Farm",level=25,c={"* Talk to Orthonn [9.4S, 47.3W]\n* Return to Gatson"},minlevel=20,b="Gatson",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrthonn may be found at the ruins of Ost Lagoros, north-west of Gatson's farm by the river.\nFarmer Gatson told you that he has been helping the Rangers with provisions for many years and now expects them to help him protect his farm. He has sent you to speak with the Ranger he delivers the food to, a man named Orthonn.\n* Talk to Orthonn\nObj 2:\nGatson awaits you at his farm to the east of Ost Lagoros.\nOrthonn admitted that Gatson had provisioned them often, but told you that the Rangers did not have the numbers to defend the farms of the North Downs. He asked you to return to Gatson and exhort the farmer and his workhands to flee at once.\n* Talk to Gatson",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1792},area="Giant Halls",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Halmur Stoneshaper, a descendant of the original Halmur Stoneshaper, son of Vithurr, has been charged with guarding the strongbox you seek until all its contents are returned.",mobs={{locations={"24.85S, 4.03W"},name="Larus Sharpshard"}},selectoneof={{val="Boots of the Long March",id=70003836},{val="Sharpshard's Shield",id=70003838},{val="Thol-mundar",id=70003835},{val="Sharpshard Axe",id=70003837}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2395,scope="n/a",prev={2497},name="The Last Ingot",arcs="Every Last Ingot",level=45,pois={{locations={"30.33S, 1.39E"},name="Hjortur's Chest"},{locations={"28.29S, 0.22E"},name="Ancient Dwarf-chest"}},minlevel=40,b="Halmur Stoneshaper",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe stolen ingot might be found atop Orod Laden.\nHalmur Stoneshaper suggested you seek the stolen ingot atop Orod Laden.\n* Find Hjortur Dourhand\nObj 2:\nThe stolen ingot might be inside Hjortur's strongbox, atop Orod Laden.\nYou defeated Hjortur Dourhand and should now search the strongbox he guarded for the stolen ingot.\n* Use Hjortur's Chest\nObj 3:\nHalmur Stoneshaper is in the tomb of his ancestor on the hill to the right as you approach the dwarf-keep in the pass of Gabilazan from the south.\nHalmur Stoneshaper is waiting for you to return with the stolen dwarf-gold ingot you retrieved from the descendant of the thief who stole it long ages ago.\n* Talk to Halmur Stoneshaper\n* Turn in Stolen Dwarf-gold Ingot\nObj 4:\nThe second strongbox is within the tomb of Halmur Stoneshaper in the pass of Gabilazan. Larus Sharpshard at Glóin's camp, north of Rivendell.\nAfter helping Halmur Stoneshaper reclaim the stolen ingot and fulfil his family's oath, he has allowed you to take the strongbox to bring it to Larus Sharpshard.\n* Bring the ancient dwarf-chest to Larus Sharpshard\n*"},
{["next"]={584},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="In tidying up his library, Adelard Took came across a rocket from the Old Took's last Midsummer's Eve party. He sent it off to the Mathom-house in Michel Delving, but he thinks that might have upset the Old Took's ghost.",mobs={{locations={"33.41S, 75.57W"},name="Keeper Brombard Foxtail"},{locations={"33.60S, 71.13W","33.61S, 71.13W"},name="Adelard Took"}},category="Shire",id=2396,scope="n/a",prev={2491},name="The Last of the Fireworks",arcs="Ghost of the Old Took",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Adelard Took",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBrombard Foxtail is at the Mathom-house in Michel Delving, far west of Tuckborough.\nAdelard Took asked you to travel to the Mathom-house in Michel Delving and ask Keeper Foxtail for the fireworks rocket he had sent there.\n* Talk to Keeper Brombard Foxtail\nObj 2:\nThe Methel-stage is on the southern side of the road heading west out of Bywater.\nAdelard Took had asked you to fire the rocket off at the Methel-stage in Bywater in hopes that the sight of this last rocket will appease the Old Took's ghost.\n* Use Fireworks-rocket\n* Find the Methel-stage in Bywater\nObj 3:\nAdelard Took can be found at the Great Smials in Tuckborough.\nYou should return to Adelard Took and let him know that you have done as he asked.\n* Talk to Adelard Took"},
{["next"]={2306},area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+300 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="8s 54c"}},d="You have recovered the last of the Silithair, shining adamants crafted by Elves of the house of Fëanor in days of old. It must be used to reforge the blade that was broken.",mobs={{locations={"12.72S, 67.18W"},name="Calenglad"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},category="Evendim",id=2397,scope="n/a",prev={2602},name="The Last of the Silithair",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=40,minlevel=35,b="Calenglad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAragorn is in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nCalenglad has given you the Silithar to bring to Aragorn. Its light will be used to remake the blade that was broken.\n* Talk to Aragorn\n* Turn in Silithar"},
{area="Redhorn Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Now that the White Hand Orcs have learned of the grisly fate of the previous expedition, Ingifast thinks they must be demoralized enough to be chased off.",selectoneof={{val="Ingifast's Ring",id="700163B7"},{val="Dwarf-shield of Battle",id="700163ED"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2398,scope="n/a",prev={2543},name="The Last of the White Hand",arcs="White-Hand Orders",level=56,pois={{locations={"12.63S, 104.74W","11.84S, 105.99W","11.76S, 104.34W","11.79S, 105.43W","11.21S, 105.48W","12.37S, 105.87W","12.27S, 104.83W","11.75S, 105.74W"},name="White Hand Helm"}},minlevel=51,b="Ingifast",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWhite Hand Orcs and their helms can be found at the Ore-house, Menem-mezel, and Malmezel, all structures in The Redhorn Lodes to the south-east of the Orc-watch.\nIngifast has asked you to take the battle to the Orcs, collecting their helms as you fight.\n* Collect White Hand helms (4 White Hand Helm )\nObj 2:\nIngifast is in the Orc-watch to the north-west of the Ore-house, Menem-mezel, and Malmezel.\nIngifast will be pleased to see all the White Hand helms you claimed as trophies and to hear of your victories against the Orcs.\n* Talk to Ingifast\n* Turn in White Hand Helm"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Elves of the Golden Host are concerned with the continuing presence of Orcs in the Mirk-eaves and in procuring supplies for the Malledhrim in the east.",mobs={{locations={"15.91S, 59.96W"},name="Rongal"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2399,scope="n/a",prev={1166},destinypoints={{val=250}},name="The Last Vestiges",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Rongal",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe road to the Gostannon lies to the north of Amon Angeled, leading eastwards.\nRongal has asked you to utterly destroy the Enemy at the Gostannon.\nObj 2:\nRongal is at the Elf-waypost atop Amon Angened, south of the Gostannon.\nWhile the Enemy encamped at the Gostannon is greatly weakened, they are still stronger than Rongal surmised. You should return to Rongal with the tidings.\n* Talk to Rongal atop Amon Angened"},
{["next"]={1328,1918,746,2730,1873,1071,157,1293},area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Wargs of Naur-hoit are led by a great pack-leader called Morglok. The Elves of the Golden Host believe that his defeat may be the key to driving forth the Wargs from the ruins.",mobs={{locations={"17.71S, 48.28W"},name="Perindúr"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2400,scope="n/a",name="The Leader of the Pack",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Perindúr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMorglok is at Naur-hoit, south of Mithechad.\nPerindúr has asked you to seek out and defeat the Warg-packleader Morglok.\n* Defeat Morglok the Warg-packleader\nObj 2:\nPerindúr is at Mithechad, north of Naur-hoit.\nYou should return at once to Perindúr and let him know that Morglok has been defeated.\n* Talk to Perindúr at Mithechad"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+1200 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Mundgeirr has told you that the quality you wish to bestow upon your weapon can only be performed at the forge within the Library of Steel.",mobs={{locations={"8.48S, 112.34W"},name="Mundgeirr"}},selectoneof={{val="Storm-hammer",id="7001369C"},{val="Ice-fist",id=70013696},{val="Shadow-piercer",id=70011322},{val="Uruk-slayer",id="7001131A"},{val="Beast-master",id=70011325},{val="Fused Copper Relics",id="700185BF"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2401,scope="Legendary Items",name="The Library of Steel",level=60,minlevel=55,b="Mundgeirr",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMundgeirr has asked you to bring him an infused adamant with which he can help you to bestow a quality upon your weapon. Unfortunately, he does not know where to find such a stone.\n* Talk to Mundgeirr\n* Turn in Infused Adamant\nObj 2:\nMundgeirr can be found at the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nMundgeirr has bidden you to seek out the Library of Steel, but warns you that a band of Fire-orcs from the depths of Moria have taken control of the library.\n* Talk to Mundgeirr to travel to the Library of Steel\nObj 3:\nMundgeirr can be found at the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nYou should return to Mundeirr to complete the enhancement of your weapon.\n* Talk to Mundgeirr\n* Turn in Empowered Adamant"},
{["next"]={960,20,2479,1504},area="Fasach-falroid",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Búdan sent you to the city of Donnvail to speak with the Trév Gállorg there who might rise up against the Angmarim.",mobs={{locations={"7.30N, 35.46W"},name="Una"},{locations={"6.72N, 34.31W"},name="Morven"},{locations={"6.20N, 34.29W"},name="Garvan"},{locations={"6.27N, 34.54W"},name="Branan"}},selectoneof={{val="Great Arm of Búth Luikh",id="7000EACB"},{val="Blade of Búth Luikh",id="7000EACC"}},category="Angmar",id=2402,scope="n/a",prev={1588},name="The Light of Hope",arcs="Oppression's Yoke",level=44,c={"* Garvan is at Donnvail [N, W]"},minlevel=39,b="Branan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGarvan is in the city of Donnvail, north-east of Fail-á-Khro.\nBúdan told you of the three leaders sent to Donnvail by Carn Dûm: Fûshath the Beast, Muiráthakh the Silent Judge, and Gillë Andras the Lord of the Western Marches. He also told you to speak to a Man named Garvan further within the city of Donnvail.\n* Talk to Garvan\nObj 2:\nMorven is within the city of Donnvail, north-east of Fail-á-Khro.\nGarvan gave you the name of someone who might be sympathetic to the cause, telling you to seek Morven further into the city.\n* Talk to Morven\nObj 3:\nUthagan is in the city of Donnvail, north-east of Fail-á-Khro.\nMorven has told you to speak with Uthagan, but with caution: his family was recently taken by Muiráthakh, and she does not think they have been seen since.\n* Talk to Uthagan\nObj 4:\nUthagan spoke of Una, located somewhere within the city of Donnvail, north-east of Fail-á-Khro.\nThough he sought to slay you, Uthagan unwittingly gave you the name of someone you might speak to: a woman named Una.\n* Talk to Una"},
{area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="Águti has determined that the Deep-toads are the linchpin to the food-chain in the Water-works.",selectoneof={{val="Águti's Hat",id="700163DC"},{val="Creeping Crusher",id="700163F9"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2403,scope="n/a",prev={2103},name="The Local Wildlife is Deadly",arcs="Western Insects",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Águti",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDeep-toads can be found all over the Water-works.\nÁguti believes that when the toads are killed, the lizards and spiders will fall upon each other for food.\n* Defeat Deep-toads (12)\nObj 2:\nÁguti is in the Rotting Cellar.\nÁguti will be pleased to hear the Deep-toad population has been thinned.\n* Talk to Águti in the Rotting Cellar"},
{["next"]={1634},area="Combe",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="90c"}},d="Ted Pickthorn was greatly distressed when you told him the Hanging Tree and all the trees surrounding it had been chopped down.",mobs={{locations={"28.91S, 47.28W"},name="Mason Thorne"},{locations={"28.55S, 49.00W"},name="Ted Pickthorn"}},category="Bree-land",id=2404,scope="n/a",prev={372},name="The Logger's Ledger",arcs="Beneath the Hanging Tree",level=8,minlevel=4,b="Ted Pickthorn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMason Thorne is at the lumber-camp, north and east of the guard-house.\nTed Pickthorn asked you to speak with Mason Thorne, the foreman at the Combe lumber-camp. He may recall which tree had been the Hanging Tree.\n* Talk to Mason Thorne at the Combe lumber-camp\nObj 2:\nMason Thorne awaits you at the lumber-camp that lies east and north of Combe, south of the Chetwood.\nThorne sent you to retrieve his ledger from the Blackwold brigands encamped along the road. You should return the ledger to him at once.\n* Bring the ledger to Mason Thorne\n* Turn in Mason Thorne's Ledger"},
{["next"]={767},area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="Niko has challenged you with hunting the kalpa-kita that haunt Leijona-kotin, a wooded area east of Jänis-leiri.",mobs={{locations={"7.49N, 75.45W"},name="Niko"}},selectoneof={{val="Niko's Bow",id="7000E5E2"},{val="Niko's Spear",id="7000E5DD"},{val="Niko's Crossbow",id="7000E5E0"}},category="Forochel",id=2405,scope="n/a",prev={1996,301},name="The Longest Fangs",arcs="Hunting: Serious Business",level=46,minlevel=41,b="Niko",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKalpa-kita can be found at Leijona-kotin, east of Jänis-leiri.\nNiko wants you to cull the numbers of kalpa-kita in the area and especially to defeat a vicious cat named Pitkä-hammas.\n* Defeat kalpa-kita (12)\n* Defeat Pitkä-hammas\nObj 2:\nNiko is at Jänis-leiri, west from Leijona-kotin.\nYou should return to Niko and tell him of your success.\n* Talk to Niko"},
{["next"]={3236},area="Nan Sirannon",zone="Eregion",money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="The Dunlendings remain in Eregion, despite their defeat, indicating the presence of a powerful leader.",mobs={{locations={"50.49S, 8.06W"},name="Glavroleth"}},selectoneof={{val="Gâmzhurm's Woe",id="7001610D"},{q="(x5)",val="Infused Athelas Essence",id="7000EA7F"}},category="Eregion",id=2406,scope="n/a",prev={1457},name="The Lord of Porth Cadlus",arcs="The Dunlendings of Nan Sirannon",level=50,pois={{locations={"53.43S, 9.56W"},name="Nan Sirannon Mustering-horn"}},minlevel=45,b="Glavroleth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Uruk Gâmzhurm can be found south and slightly west of Echad Dúnann, across Nan Sirannon.\nYou must use the horn of challenge to summon Gâmzhurm, the leader of the Dunlendings, and defeat him.\n* Kill 1 Gâmzhurm, Lord of Porth Cadlus\n* Use Nan Sirannon Mustering-horn\nObj 2:\nGlavroleth is at Echad Dúnann, north and slightly east of Porth Cadlus.\nYou should return to Glavroleth with the news of Gâmzhurm's death.\n* Talk to Glavroleth at Echad Dúnann"},
{["next"]={2464},area="Fasach-larran",zone="Angmar",money={{val="36s 96c"}},d="Soltakh has arranged for the transfer of Gillë Andras, the Lord of the Western Marches, to Dûn Covád, where he can be faced on more even terms.",mobs={{locations={"2.72N, 37.29W"},name="Soltakh"}},selectoneof={{val="Hill-hunter's Lock",id="700031F1"},{val="Soltakh's Dagger",id="7000F9C3"},{val="Soltakh's Shoes",id="70006A95"}},category="Angmar",id=2407,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={838,2533},name="The Lord of the Western Marches",arcs="False Orders",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Soltakh",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGillë Andras, the Lord of the Western Marches, can be found within the city of Dûn Covád, in the western foothills north of Fail-á-Khro.\nSoltakh has asked you and your allies to defeat Gillë Andras, the Lord of the Western Marches.\n* Kill 1 Gillë Andras\nObj 2:\nSoltakh is at Fail-á-Khro, north of Aughaire and south of Dûn Covád.\nYou have defeated Gillë Andras, the Lord of the Western Marches, and should now bring news of your triumph to Soltakh.\n* Talk to Soltakh"},
{["next"]={2720},area="Western Malenhad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="Torcuil was grateful for the help you have offered his people and told you that his people needs additional allies if they are to survive under Angmar's harsh rule. He told you about a tale he has heard of dwarves living in Angmar's shadow and wonders if they could be allies for his people in the future.",mobs={{locations={"1.70S, 33.32W"},name="Torcuil"}},category="Angmar",id=2408,scope="n/a",prev={398,2884,1836},name="The Lost Dwarves",level=46,c={"* Must have access to Eastern Malenhad via completion of Volume 1, Book 6 epic quest line.  *Note - If you don't have access to this region, you will die trying to get past the statues.\n* Entrance to the Gabilshathûr is at [2.7S, 26.4W]"},minlevel=41,b="Torcuil",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe dwarf-holding is east of Rammas Deluon and south of Duvuinen.\nThe merchant Torcuil asked you to seek the lost dwarves and obtain their allegiance.\n* Find Gabilshathûr\nObj 2:\nThere are many dwarves within Gabilshathûr.\nYou have discovered hidden holding of the dwarves in Angmar, Gabilshathûr. You should speak with someone within the holding and convey Torcuil's message.\n* Talk to the leader of Gabilshathûr\n//Búdan Location: 2.54N, 37.30W\nAngmar >> Fasach-larran';markerList['1879102379_0x041889E000000024_140.46107.4510881264'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879063734_0x041969600000001B', new GLatLng(15.947534179688, 31.438916015625), { 'icon':POI_ICON }); marker.id = '1879063734_0x041969600000001B'; markers['1879063734_0x041969600000001B'] = marker; marker.caption = 'GabilshathûrLocation: 3.86S, 26.51W\nAngmar >> Eastern Malenhad';markerList['1879063734_0x041969600000001B'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879063734_0x0419697000000013', new GLatLng(16.214809570313, 31.640009765625), { 'icon':POI_ICON }); marker.id = '1879063734_0x0419697000000013'; markers['1879063734_0x0419697000000013'] = marker; marker.caption = 'GabilshathûrLocation: 3.55S, 26.40W\nAngmar >> Eastern Malenhad';markerList['1879063734_0x0419697000000013'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879063734_0x0419697000000019', new GLatLng(16.42376953125, 31.039892578125), { 'icon':POI_ICON }); marker.id = '1879063734_0x0419697000000019'; markers['1879063734_0x0419697000000019'] = marker; marker.caption = 'GabilshathûrLocation: 3.31S, 26.74W\nAngmar >> Eastern Malenhad';markerList['1879063734_0x0419697000000019'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879063734_0x0419697000000017', new GLatLng(16.36681640625, 31.12681640625), { 'icon':POI_ICON }); marker.id = '1879063734_0x0419697000000017'; markers['1879063734_0x0419697000000017'] = marker; marker.caption = 'GabilshathûrLocation: 3.38S, 26.69W\nAngmar >> Eastern Malenhad';markerList['1879063734_0x0419697000000017'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879063734_0x041969600000001B', new GLatLng(15.947534179688, 31.438916015625), { 'icon':POI_ICON }); marker.id = '1879063734_0x041969600000001B'; markers['1879063734_0x041969600000001B'] = marker; marker.caption = 'GabilshathûrLocation: 3.86S, 26.51W\nAngmar >> Eastern Malenhad';markerList['1879063734_0x041969600000001B'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879063734_0x0419697000000013', new GLatLng(16.214809570313, 31.640009765625), { 'icon':POI_ICON }); marker.id = '1879063734_0x0419697000000013'; markers['1879063734_0x0419697000000013'] = marker; marker.caption = 'GabilshathûrLocation: 3.55S, 26.40W\nAngmar >> Eastern Malenhad';markerList['1879063734_0x0419697000000013'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879063734_0x0419697000000019', new GLatLng(16.42376953125, 31.039892578125), { 'icon':POI_ICON }); marker.id = '1879063734_0x0419697000000019'; markers['1879063734_0x0419697000000019'] = marker; marker.caption = 'GabilshathûrLocation: 3.31S, 26.74W\nAngmar >> Eastern Malenhad';markerList['1879063734_0x0419697000000019'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879063734_0x0419697000000017', new GLatLng(16.36681640625, 31.12681640625), { 'icon':POI_ICON }); marker.id = '1879063734_0x0419697000000017'; markers['1879063734_0x0419697000000017'] = marker; marker.caption = 'GabilshathûrLocation: 3.38S, 26.69W\nAngmar >> Eastern Malenhad';markerList['1879063734_0x0419697000000017'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker); GME_DEFAULT_ICON = G_DEFAULT_ICON;      } else {        document.getElementById(\"map2105794870\").innerHTML = \"In order to see the map that would go in this space, you will need to use a compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap2105794870);\n//]]>\nQuest: The Lost Dwarves\nCategory: Angmar\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 41\nPrerequisite Quests:Vol. I, Book 6, Chapter 6: Challenging the StoneRestoring the Peas OR Fuel for the Forge OR The Lord of the Western Marches OR A Call for Allies\nNext Quests:Tools of the Orcs\nRewards\nMoney:\n23 45\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nBúdan told you that there are others who may need your help in Angmar. There are tales of a hidden holding of the dwarves, east of Rammas Deluon. If the tale is indeed true, the dwarves have hidden themselves well, but Búdan fears it is only a matter of time before Angmar discovers them.\nBestower\nBúdan (NPC)\n'There is much that we owe to you, (your name). You have given us hope that one day we will throw off Angmar's yoke. There are others, though, in these lands that need such hope as well.\n'There are tales and whispers that there are dwarves to the east of Rammas Deluon. If it is true, they have hidden there long and well, but as Angmar stretches forth its hand, they may soon find they can hide no longer.\n'If you wish to discover if these tales are true, travel past Rammas Deluon and look for these lost dwarves. The dwarves' hall should be somewhere south of Duvuinen.'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nThe dwarf-holding lies to the east of Rammas Deluon and south of Duvuinen.\nBúdan spoke to you of a hidden holding of the dwarves in Angmar and suggests that the dwarves could use your aid.\n* Find Gabilshathûr\nObj 2:\nThe leader of the dwarves is at Gabilshathûr.\nYou have discovered hidden holding of the dwarves in Angmar, Gabilshathûr. You should seek out and speak with the leader of the dwarves.\n* Talk to the leader of Gabilshathûr",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1093},area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="A small party of explorers set off for Dannenglor and have not yet returned, and Fernachar is anxious for word of their fate.",category="Mirkwood",id=2409,scope="n/a",name="The Lost Explorers",arcs="The Lost Explorers",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,c={"* There is an Elf-sword outside the southern entrance to Dannenglor, in the Dourstocks, at [12.4S, 55.1W]"},pois={{locations={"12.41S, 55.12W"},name="Elf-sword"}},minlevel=57,b="Fernachar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDannenglor is to the north of the Haunted Inn.\nFernachar has asked you to search the ruins of Dannenglor for signs of the Elf-scouts who went that way. You should approach Dannenglor cautiously, following the road where the Elf explorers went.\n* Use Elf-sword\nObj 2:\nFernachar awaits you in the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks, south of Dannenglor.\nYou should speak with Fernachar and tell him of the worrying scene you beheld when you approached Dannenglor.\n* Talk to Fernachar at the Haunted Inn"},
{area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Helegdir has asked for your help in ensuring the safety of a group of individuals known as the Lost Fellowship.",mobs={{locations={"3.00N, 58.07W"},name="Cenlieg"},{locations={"0.09S, 39.87W"},name="Helegdir"}},category="Angmar",id=2410,scope="n/a",name="The Lost Fellowship",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Helegdir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nForochel lies north of Evendim, through Cirith Rhiw, north of Tyrn Fornech. You should start your search in the town of Kauppa-kohta.\nHelegdir asked you to seek out a member of a fellowship of adventurers who journeyed to Forochel, passing through Aughaire in Angmar.\n* Talk to Cenlieg",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2350},area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Daervunn has befriended a Dunlending hunter by the name of Umfrë on the fringes of the Mournshaws after the hunter rescued him from a pack of vicious hounds. However, Umfrë has recently disappeared into the Mournshaws after giving chase to one of the hounds, and Daervunn is concerned that he may be in some danger...or even dead.",mobs={{locations={"66.60S, 21.49W","67.39S, 20.26W"},name="Umfrë"},{locations={"66.59S, 21.50W"},name="Daervunn"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2411,scope="n/a",name="The Lost Hunter",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Daervunn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nUmfrë is lost somewhere in the Mournshaws.\nDaervunn asked you to find Umfrë the hunter, who disappeared into the forest, hunting for a Cun Annun that had been terrorizing his village.\n* Find Umfrë in the Mournshaws\n* Talk to Umfrë\nObj 2:\nUmfrë is at Echad Daervunn in the Mournshaws.\nYou should return to Daervunn's camp and speak with Umfrë.\n* Talk to Umfrë at Echad Daervunn"},
{["next"]={2381},area="Nan Amlug West",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+900 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="28s"}},d="Glambaen deciphered the runes on the old prospecting records, but they reference a map that appears to be missing.",mobs={{locations={"7.12S, 45.14W"},name="Regin"}},category="North Downs",id=2412,scope="n/a",prev={1882},name="The Lost Map",arcs="The Father-lode",level=29,c={"* The chest with the map is inside a tent in Thurûm [4.9S, 45.5W]\n* Or kill Foreman Nyrad for it."},minlevel=24,b="Regin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nForeman Nyrad can be found in the Dourhand camp north of Othrikar. Regin is at Othrikar.\nRegin believes that Nyrad, the previous foreman, stole the map, but left the records, since he could not read the runes. Regin has suggested that you may find the map either in Foreman Nyrad's tent or on Nyrad himself.\n* Deliver the Mining Map to Regin\n* Turn in Mining-map"},
{area="Tyrn Fornech",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},d="Robin Dunkley has given you the statue of Elendil he remade from the pieces you brought him during your time in Ost Forod.",mobs={{locations={"8.07S, 64.29W"},name="Robin Dunkley"}},category="Evendim",id=2413,scope="n/a",name="The Lost Statue",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,pois={{locations={"12.66S, 70.92W"},name="Smooth Pedestal"}},minlevel=33,b="Robin Dunkley",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere is a pedestal on the islands of Tyl Ruinen, in the middle of Lake Nenuial, where the statue of Elendil you bear once stood. Tyl Ruinen is across the lake from the island of Tinnudir.\nWhile you journeyed to meet with Gwindeth, Robin Dunkley set about remaking the broken statue you recovered from robbers in Tyrn Fornech. This is the statue that once stood upon Tyl Ruinen.\n* Use Smooth Pedestal\n* Turn in Statue of Elendil",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Flosi, an elderly dwarf-prospector, lost his pick while digging in an old cave infested by cave-claws.",mobs={{locations={"14.06S, 103.17W"},name="Flosi"}},selectoneof={{val="Flosi's Javelin",id="70019C30"},{val="Flosi's Staff",id="70019C1F"},{val="Flosi's Stone",id="70019C21"},{val="Flosi's Knife",id="70019C53"},{val="Flosi's Bow",id="70019C23"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2414,scope="n/a",name="The Lost Tool",level=6,c={"* The Winterheight is in Thorin's Gate at [15.8S, 101.7W]\n* When you are almost at the bottom you can find the pick axe.\n* Kill the required amount of cave-claws."},pois={{locations={"15.75S, 102.30W","15.85S, 102.53W"},name="Pick-axe"}},minlevel=2,b="Flosi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe cave is south-east of Thorin's Hall, in the Winterheights.\nCertain that he was nearing a vein of gold before being driven out of the cave, Flosi asked you to retrieve his pick-axe, as well as clear some of the cave-claws from the cave.\n* Use Pick-axe\n* Defeat cave-claws in cave (8)\nObj 2:\nFlosi is on the stairs in front of the main gate to Thorin's Hall.\nYou should return the pick-axe to Flosi and let the old prospector know it should be safe for him to return to the cave.\n* Talk to Flosi\n* Turn in Pick-axe",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Drownholt",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Nestawen has turned the herbs you brought her into a tincture that will dispel the evil poisons of the forbidding pool. It is time for the source of the sickness to be driven away so that it can do no more harm to unwitting passersby.",mobs={{locations={"16.70S, 54.93W"},name="Nestawen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2415,scope="n/a",prev={2544},name="The Malice of the Lights",arcs="The Mysterious Affliction",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,minlevel=58,b="Nestawen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNestawen gave you a draught for your inventory that will protect you against the fell lights that gently sap life from all around.\nNestawen wants you to sip from the tincture she made so that you will be strengthened against the bog-lights.\n* Use Elven-draught\nObj 2:\nThe sickly pool is just to the south of Estolad Mernael.\nNestawen wants you to drive away the bog-lights that reside in the Drownholt and has provided you with a draught that will protect you against the dire effects of the water.\n* Defeat bog-lights\nObj 3:\nNestawen is at Estolad Mernael, north of the sickly pool.\nYou should return to Nestawen at once and inform her of your success against the fell lights in the pool.\n* Talk to Nestawen at Estolad Mernael"},
{["next"]={2478},area="The Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Thalfar of the Deep Descent needs to discover if the nearby goblins serve some more powerful master, or if they are a tribe separate from the rest of the Moria goblins.\nFind some evidence of their allegiance if you can.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2416,scope="n/a",name="The Mark of Loyalty",arcs="Banding Together",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Thalfar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThalfar hopes you can find some evidence amongst the goblins of the Silvertine Lodes indicating their allegiance within the other tribes of Moria.\n* Find evidence of the goblins' allegiance\nObj 2:\nThalfar hopes you can find some evidence amongst the goblins of the Silvertine Lodes indicating their allegiance within the other tribes of Moria.\n* Turn in Mark of Mazog\nObj 3:\nThalfar is in the Deep Descent within the Silvertine Lodes.\nYou should return to Thalfar and show him the Mark of Mazog.\n* Talk to Thalfar\n* Turn in Mark of Mazog"},
{area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The mervyl-slaves are led by one of their own in subjugation to the merrevail.",category="Mirkwood",id=2417,scope="n/a",prev={2560},name="The Master of the Roost",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,c={"* The Summoning Horn to summon the Morvul Guard is in Dannenglor at [11.4S, 54.8W]"},pois={{locations={"11.41S, 54.79W"},name="Summoning Horn (Level 1)"}},minlevel=57,b="Puiguil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe master of the morvul-slaves can be summoned in Dannenglor, north of the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks.\nYou should use the merrevail's horn to summon the morvul-guard.\n* Summon and defeat the morvul-guard\n* Use Summoning Horn (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nPuiguil can be found in the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks, south of Dannenglor.\nYou should return with news of your success to Puiguil.\n* Talk to Puiguil in the Haunted Inn"},
{["next"]={873},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Golhador has cautioned you about the great mammoths of the Misty Mountains, some of which seem to have become allies of the giants.",mobs={{locations={"26.85S, 5.37W"},name="Golhador"}},selectoneof={{val="Othlang",id="700032B6"},{val="Ladhigil",id=70003267},{val="Golhador's Vest",id="700032B5"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2418,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Masters of the Mammoth",arcs="Mighty Giants Indeed",level=43,minlevel=38,b="Golhador",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMammoths can be found throughout the Misty Mountains, but especially in areas where giants walk.\nGolhador has expressed concern that the mammoths and the giants have formed an alliance and asked you to bring the silver tusk-rings worn by the mammoths for him to examine.\n* Turn in Silver Tusk-ring\nObj 2:\nGolhador is on the northern pass that leaves Rivendell.\nGolhador is waiting for you to return with tusk-rings that might illuminate the nature of the alliance between the mammoths and the giants of the Misty Mountains.\n* Talk to Golhador\n* Turn in Silver Tusk-ring"},
{area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Tasgall has devised a plan by which you and he will draw out Bangrath and Murragrath and end their menace.",mobs={{locations={"0.10N, 39.58W"},name="Rona"}},selectoneof={{val="Emerthdail",id="70006ADD"},{val="Ferollos (Level 41)",id=70003033},{val="Winter Cloak",id="7000313F"},{val="Rona's Great Sword",id=70003032}},category="Angmar",id=2419,scope="n/a",prev={2731},name="The Matron and the Master",arcs="Strange Beasts",receive={{val="Gillinn",id="70002FA4"}},level=43,c={"* pending"},minlevel=38,b="Tasgall",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTasgall's campsite is north of Aughaire and south-east of Nád Nathair.\nTasgall is waiting to travel with you in search of Bangrath and Murragrath.\n* Talk to Tasgall and travel to Nád Nathair\nObj 2:\nTasgall's campsite is north of Aughaire and south-east of Nád Nathair.\nYou and Tasgall were successful in your hunt of Bangrath and Murragrath. He is waiting to speak with you.\nObj 3:\nRona is at the centre island of Aughaire, east of Crannog's ruling-seat.\nTasgall has been satisfied with the aid you lent him and wants you to tell his sister Rona that he will soon return to the settlement.\n* Talk to Rona"},
{["next"]={340},area="Bridgefields",zone="The Shire",d="By reading the reassembled journal, Wilimar has learned it was written by a Man named Callum. Callum's ancestor was killed in a great battle by Wilimar's ancestor, and the family has borne this death as a black mark for centuries. Callum has decided to erase the mark by coming to the Shire and killing a descendant of that hobbit.",mobs={{locations={"31.20S, 68.47W"},name="Callum"},{locations={"30.95S, 65.81W"},name="Wilimar Bolger"}},category="Shire",id=2420,scope="n/a",prev={58},name="The Menace Confronted",arcs="The Veiled Menace",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Wilimar Bolger",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCallum's campsite is on the far west side of the Frogmoors, west of Budgeford.\nIn light of the revelations gleaned from Callum's journal, Wilimar Bolger has asked you to go to Callum's camp and stop him from carrying out his intended revenge.\n* Talk to Callum\nObj 2:\nWilimar Bolger can be found near his hole on the north-west side of Budgeford.\nWhen you arrived at Callum's campsite, you found him wounded. Racked with pain, he told of how he had fled from his hiding place near Wilimar's home, only to startle a wild boar, which gored him. He feels that he will soon succumb to his wounds and told you to let Wilimar know he has nothing more to fear.\n* Talk to Wilimar Bolger"},
{area="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Eldgang"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Tortrygg is concerned with the invasion of Norbar by the Orcs.",titles={{val="Saviour of the Eldgang"}},category="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",id=2421,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Message",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Obsidian Rock-shard",id="7000C7BE"}},level=50,minlevel=45,b="Tortrygg",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNarnûlubat and Zogtark can be found within Noruidor.\nTortrygg has asked to you to find and defeat two of the leaders of the Ghâshfra, Narnûlubat and Zogtark.\n* Defeat Narnûlubat\n* Defeat Zogtark\nObj 2:\nTortrygg is at the Eldgang camp within the Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu.\nYou should return to Tortrygg with news of your victory against Narnûlubat and Zogtark."},
{["next"]={2005},area="The Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Thalfar has asked you to patrol the huge mining platform of Menem-berej to the south.\nHe needs it cleared of creatures so that the miners can safely prospect for Mithril.",selectoneof={{val="Thalfar's Burden",id=70016072},{val="Miner's Hammer",id=70016105}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2422,scope="n/a",prev={2472},name="The Miner's Plight",arcs="Banding Together",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Thalfar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nPatrol the platform of Menem-berej to the south of the Deep Descent, and clear it and the area immediately around it of any dangerous creatures.\nObj 2:\nThalfar is in the Deep Descent within the Silvertine Load.\nReturn to Thalfar and inform him that the platform has been cleared, for now.\n* Talk with Thalfar"},
{zone="Angmar",area="Fasach-falroid",money={{val="36s 40c"}},d="Muiráthakh, the Silent Judge, commands the loyalty of many warriors sent from Carn Dûm. Artagan wants them eliminated.",mobs={{locations={"7.34N, 35.46W"},name="Artagan"}},selectoneof={{val="Nomad's Shield",id="7000EAFA"},{val="Artagan's Spear",id="7000EAF9"},{val="Left Bracelet of Arms",id="7000EAF8"}},category="Angmar",id=2423,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2458},name="The Minions of Muiráthakh",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Distilled Celebrant Ointment",id="70008D03"},{q="(x2)",val="Distilled Athelas Extract",id="70008CFB"}},level=44,minlevel=39,b="Artagan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIron Crown warriors and crossbowmen can be found in the neighbourhood beyond the arch east of Una's allies.\nArtagan wants you to undermine Muiráthakh's rule in Donnvail by defeating his servants.\n* Defeat Iron Crown warriors\n* Defeat Iron Crown crossbowmen\nObj 2:\nArtagan is in the city of Donnvail, among Una's allies.\nYou have defeated many of Muiráthakh's servants and should bring news of your success to Artagan.\n* Talk to Artagan"},
{area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",d="Bersi, a dwarf-cook, went off to collect herbs near a large lair of evil spiders north-east of Kheledûl, but he never returned.",mobs={{locations={"18.95S, 95.19W"},name="Nithi"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2424,scope="n/a",name="The Misplaced Cook",receive={{val="Both-herthar",id="700033E0"}},level=14,minlevel=10,b="Nithi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBersi is probably at or near the spider-lair north and east of Kheledûl.\nNithi has asked you to seek out his friend Bersi who went to gather herbs near a lair of vicious spiders. He recommended that you head north-east before you reach Kheledûl so as not to risk an encounter with the Dourhands.\n* Find Bersi",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={159},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="21s 70c"}},d="The fragments you retrieved from the snow lurkers of the Misty Mountains are of interest to the scholar Deluros, though Glorenglir missed their significance.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Deluros"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2425,scope="n/a",prev={703},name="The Missing Fragments",arcs="Hidden by Drifts",level=41,minlevel=36,b="Deluros",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSnow Lurkers can be found near the source of the Bruinen and drifts of snow in the area may also hold the jagged relic fragments sought by Deluros.\nScholar Deluros has asked you to collect jagged relic fragments from near the source of the Bruinen so he may reassemble the vase so readily dismissed by Glorenglir.\n* Turn in Jagged Relic-fragment\nObj 2:\nScholar Deluros is in the library of the House of Elrond in Rivendell.\nYou have retrieved some jagged relic fragments. Perhaps Deluros can use them to reassemble the ancient vase.\n* Talk to Deluros\n* Turn in Jagged Relic-fragment"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="Mundgeirr knows of an ancient mithril mine containing a smelting forge where you may lay the foundation of the quality you seek to bestow upon your weapon. Unfortunately, a band of particularly savage Orcs has claimed the mine and enslaved their own goblin brethren to work the played-out veins in hope of coming up with a few poor scraps of mithril ore for their masters.",mobs={{locations={"8.48S, 112.34W"},name="Mundgeirr"}},selectoneof={{val="Wild Fighter",id=70011323},{val="Foe-stinger",id="7001369A"},{val="Dark-banisher",id=70011314},{val="Fused Bronze Relics",id=70018606},{val="Cold-heart",id=70013694},{val="Goblin-piercer",id=70011318}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2426,scope="Legendary Items",name="The Mithril Slaves",level=54,minlevel=49,b="Mundgeirr",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMundgeirr has asked you to bring him an infused garnet with which he may aid you in bestowing a quality upon your weapon. He does not know, however, where to find such a stone.\n* Talk to Mundgeirr\n* Turn in Infused Garnet\nObj 2:\nMundgeirr can be found at the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nMungeirr has bidden you to talk to him again when you are ready to seek out the forge, but warns you that a vicious band of Orcs and their goblin slaves have taken over the mithril mine.\n* Talk to Mundgeirr to travel to the mithril mine\nObj 3:\nMundgeirr can be found at the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nYou should return to Mundgeirr to complete the enhancement of your weapon.\n* Talk to Mundgeirr\n* Turn in Empowered Garnet"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+900 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="Mundgeirr has told you of an ancient forge where some of the finest weapons in Moria were once crafted...but shortly after the dwarves rediscovered it, a band of merrevail driven out of their own caverns have begun raiding it and making off with the tools and materials inside.",mobs={{locations={"8.48S, 112.34W"},name="Mundgeirr"}},selectoneof={{val="Savage-tamer",id=70011324},{val="Sky-rager",id="7001369B"},{val="Orc-hewer",id=70011319},{val="Fused Bronze Relics",id=70018606},{val="Scion of the Drowned Kingdom",id="70017D81"},{val="Fell-slayer",id=70011321},{val="Frost-reaver",id=70013695}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2427,scope="Legendary Items",name="The Morroval-outcasts",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Mundgeirr",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMundgeirr has asked you to bring him an infused sapphire through which a quality may be placed upon your weapon. Unfortunately, Mundgeirr does not know exactly where to find such a sapphire.\n* Talk to Mundgeirr\n* Turn in Infused Sapphire\nObj 2:\nMundgeirr can be found in the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nMundgeirr has bidden you to seek out the forge he spoke of, but warns you that a desperate band of morroval-outcasts has taken control of the forge. You should speak with him when you are ready to leave.\n* Speak with Mundgeirr to travel to the ancient forge\nObj 3:\nMundgeirr can be found at the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nYou should return to Mundgeirr to complete the enhancement of your weapon.\n* Talk to Mundgeirr\n* Turn in Empowered Sapphire"},
{["next"]={2544},area="The Drownholt",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="One of the horses travelling with the Malledhrim has fallen ill, and the Elves begin to lose hope that he can be healed. His illness began as they passed through the Drownholt and has grown steadily more grave over time.",mobs={{locations={"16.70S, 54.93W"},name="Nestawen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2428,scope="n/a",name="The Mysterious Affliction",arcs="The Mysterious Affliction",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,c={"* Check the pools in the Drownholt around [17.4S, 56.1W]"},minlevel=58,b="Nestawen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNestawen rode upon Alagos on her route to Estolad Mernael.\nYou should explore possible routes Nestawen may have travelled and look for anything out of the ordinary that could have induced the steed's strange illness.\n* Explore the Drownholt for the source of illness\nObj 2:\nNestawen can be found at Estolad Mernael, the Malledhrim camp in the Drownholt.\nYou should speak with Nestawen immediately and tell her of the particularly fell pool in the Drownholt.\n* Talk to Nestawen at Estolad Mernael"},
{["next"]={2492},area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Using the items and information you brought to him, Saeradan believes that it is a certainty that Saruman the White has a hand in the strange happenings in the Windfells.",mobs={{locations={"61.83S, 14.12W"},name="Grufudh"},{locations={"63.82S, 17.45W"},name="Saeradan"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2429,scope="n/a",prev={575,1990,664},name="The Mystery Deepens",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Saeradan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGrufudh is at Gavar Cadlus, north-east of Echad Saeradan.\nSaeradan instructed you to speak with Grufudh about the banner of the White Hand that you found near Gwyllion's Gate.\n* Talk to Grufudh at Gavar Cadlus\nObj 2:\nGwyllion's Gate, the entrance to the path which leads to Gwyllion's hut, lies to the south of Gavar Cadlus.\nGrufudh told you to speak with Gwyllion, the Old Woman of the Mountain, if you wished to know the source of the White Hand banner.\n* Talk to Gwyllion at her hut\nObj 3:\nSaeradan is at Echad Saeradan, west of Gwyllion's Gate.\nYou should return to Saeradan with news of your discovery of the Uruk-hai Filskûm at Gwyllion's hut.\n* Talk to Saeradan at Echad Saeradan"},
{["next"]={1733,867},reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},zone="Mirkwood",area="Taur Morvith",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Elven scout Ianudirel was sent ahead to explore the far side of the river from Krul Lugu, but she has not yet returned.",mobs={{locations={"16.60S, 50.55W"},name="Iavassúl"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2430,scope="n/a",prev={2285,1330},name="The Narrow Way",arcs="Forts of Taur Morvith",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=64,minlevel=59,b="Iavassúl",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIanudirel may be found on the far side of the river from Krul Lugu.\nIavassúl has asked you to find Ianudirel, his sister, and help her to return safely, if she still lives.\n* Talk to Ianudirel to assist in her escape\nObj 2:\nIavassúl is at Iavassúl's Watch in Taur Morvith.\nYou should report to Iavassúl regarding his sister's rescue.\n* Talk to Iavassúl at Iavassúl's Watch"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Fanged Pit",money={{val="27s 65c"}},d="The merrevail use several perches as nests. Borgar believes that if they were destroyed, the colony would be crippled.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=2431,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="The Nests",level=58,pois={{locations={"3.79S, 99.69W","3.44S, 100.07W","3.39S, 99.29W","3.96S, 99.65W","3.57S, 99.42W","3.93S, 99.31W","3.56S, 99.03W","3.31S, 99.60W","3.65S, 99.14W","3.56S, 100.15W","4.08S, 99.81W","3.59S, 99.93W"},name="Nest"}},minlevel=53,b="Borgar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe morroval-camp is located at Skoiruzg, far to the east of Jazârgund.\nBorgar asked you to destroy the morroval-perches and defeat several morroval-slingers.\n* Use Nest\n* Defeat slingers in Skoiruzg\nObj 2:\nBorgar is at Jazârgund, far to the west of Skoiruzg.\nBorgar  will be pleased to hear that the morroval-perches have been destroyed and the approach to the camp is free from the attacks of the slingers.\n* Talk to Borgar at Jazârgund",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={94},area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Your banner brings the flame of hope to the hearts of good people, and your name is praised by those who follow you into battle against the evils of the shadow.",mobs={{locations={"28.25S, 92.23W"},name="Nelson Grimm"},{locations={"31.72S, 50.83W","31.71S, 50.83W"},name="Dawn Appledore"},{locations={"28.76S, 4.19W"},name="Heath Wheaton"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Nelson Blake"},{locations={"19.12N, 72.16W"},name="Tahvo"},{locations={"12.70S, 67.19W"},name="Inurawen"},{locations={"25.32S, 48.66W"},name="Dawn Stockard"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Hayley Carver"},{locations={"9.51S, 41.51W"},name="Thenimbor"},{locations={"25.35S, 48.69W"},name="Edgar Standish"},{locations={"50.45S, 8.09W"},name="Alun"}},category="Captain",id=2432,scope="n/a",prev={21,261},requiredclasses="Captain",name="The Noblest Path is Service",arcs="The Noblest Path",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Edgar Standish",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDawn Stockard is in the town of Archet, north of Bree, in Bree-land.\nYou have been told to speak with Dawn Stockard, a great captain, to learn what troubles her.\n* Talk to Dawn Stockard"},
{area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Hwati in Gabilshathûr thinks his cousin to the north in Myrkworth may have need for your help.",mobs={{locations={"6.89N, 25.82W"},name="Eiláf"}},category="Angmar",id=2433,scope="n/a",prev={45},name="The Northern Cousin",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Hwati",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMyrkworth lies in Imlad Balchorth atop a high hill, north of Gabilshathûr.\nHwati has asked you to travel to Myrkworth and speak with his cousin, Eiláf.\n* Talk to Eiláf",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={720},area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="18s 40c"}},d="In the days of King Arvedui, last king at Fornost, a company of the king's men betrayed their oaths to Arthedain, allowing Fornost to fall to the armies of Angmar. Arvedui cursed these men to never know rest until they had fulfilled their oaths.",mobs={{locations={"13.06S, 55.30W"},name="Mincham"}},category="North Downs",id=2434,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Oathbreakers",arcs="The Oathbreakers",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe shade of the Oathbreaker-captain can be found north-east of Mincham's camp, in some scattered ruins by the walls of Fornost.\nMincham has asked you to find the shade of the Oathbreaker-captain and recall him and his followers to their ancient duty.\n* Talk to the shade of the Oathbreaker-captain\nObj 2:\nMincham awaits you at his camp.\nThe Oathbreaker-captain told you that he and his followers had sworn a new allegiance to someone named Amarthiel. Mincham may know what this means.\n* Talk to Mincham"},
{["next"]={2452},area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="With the ghost still troubling his library, Adelard has come up with another idea on how to appease the Old Took: food. The Old Took was known for his love of spiced boar ribs, and he thinks that if he presents a plate of the ribs to the ghost in the library, he will return to his rest.",mobs={{locations={"33.47S, 70.91W"},name="Edilina Proudfoot"},{locations={"33.60S, 71.13W","33.61S, 71.13W"},name="Adelard Took"}},category="Shire",id=2435,scope="n/a",prev={993},name="The Old Took's Favourite",arcs="Ghost of the Old Took",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Adelard Took",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nEdilina Proudfoot's hole is east of the Great Smials.\nAdelard sent you to ask his niece, Edilina Proudfoot, to prepare a plate of spiced boar ribs to appease the ghost of the Old Took, but warned you not to tell her the reason. He does not want to start a panic.\n* Talk to Edilina Proudfoot\nObj 2:\nBoars can be found in the hills east of Tuckborough. Edilina Proudfoot's home is just east of Tuckborough.\nEdilina Proudfoot said she could make the spiced boar-ribs that Adelard wants to appease the ghost of the Old Took, but lacks the actual ribs. She asked you to bring her some ribs from the boars in the hills beyond Tuckborough.\n* Bring the boar-ribs to Edilina Proudfoot\n* Turn in Boar-ribs\nObj 3:\nAdelard Took is waiting at the Great Smials in Tuckborough.\nAfter gathering the ribs Edilina Proudfoot needed, she cooked up a plate of spiced boar-ribs for you to give to Adelard Took. You should bring them to Adelard, so he can use them to try and appease the Old Took's ghost.\n* Talk to Adelard Took\n* Turn in Spiced Boar-ribs"},
{area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="You learned that Gwyllion, the Old Woman of the Mountain, is in league with the traitor Saruman. It is likely that she is responsible, as well, for the appearances of evil creatures in the Windfells.",mobs={{locations={"63.82S, 17.45W"},name="Saeradan"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2436,scope="n/a",prev={2485},destinypoints={{val=750}},name="The Old Woman of the Mountain",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Saeradan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\n* Talk to Saeradan to journey to Gwyllion's hut\nObj 2:\nSaeradan is at Echad Saeradan in the Windfells of Enedwaith.\nYou should return to Saeradan with news of your victory against Gwyllion.\n* Talk to Saeradan at Echad Saeradan"},
{zone="Angmar",area="Aughaire",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Guirmán of the Trév Gállorg of Aughaire has returned from Fasach-falroid with troubling news of that land.",mobs={{locations={"0.18S, 39.79W"},name="Guirmán"}},selectoneof={{val="Bracer of Blades",id="7000EAEC"},{val="Right Bracelet of Arms",id="7000EAEB"}},category="Angmar",id=2437,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={625},name="The Ongbúrz and the Iron Crown",level=43,minlevel=38,b="Guirmán",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs of the Ongbúrz tribe and their Iron Crown allies can be found in and around the city of Dûn Covád, far to the north of Aughaire, in the western hills.\nGuirmán has asked you to combat the foes of the Trév Gállorg that can be found in Fasach-falroid.\n* Defeat Ongbúrz Orcs in Fasach-falroid (12)\n* Defeat Angmarim in Fasach-falroid (8)\nObj 2:\nGuirmán is at the Búth Luikh of Aughaire, far to the south of Dûn Covád.\nYou have defeated many Ongbúrz Orcs and their Iron Crown allies and should return now to Guirmán with word of your victories.\n* Talk to Guirmán",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={202},area="Tâl Bruinen",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="22s 5c"}},d="Wistan has a plan to trap the creature he and Adwold have seen sneaking around Tâl Bruinen, but it is going to require fish.",mobs={{locations={"36.91S, 14.21W"},name="Wistan"},{locations={"38.26S, 14.53W"},name="Afanen"},{locations={"38.23S, 14.51W"},name="Garbert"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Distilled Healing Draught",id="7000EFC2"},{q="(x3)",val="Quality Quick Trap",id="7000A6A0"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2438,scope="n/a",prev={2337},name="The Open Window",arcs="The Creeping Shadow",level=42,pois={{locations={"38.69S, 14.64W","39.24S, 14.97W","37.63S, 14.65W","37.65S, 13.85W","37.25S, 13.59W","36.92S, 15.50W","36.86S, 13.32W","36.52S, 13.30W"},name="Fishing Net (Level 1)"},{locations={"37.56S, 14.69W","37.74S, 14.57W","37.57S, 13.80W","38.65S, 14.64W","36.92S, 15.46W"},name="Fishing Net"}},minlevel=37,b="Wistan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe fisherman Garbert and his wife Afanen has a cottage south of Echad Candelleth, at a fork in the river Bruinen.\nWistan has sent you to Garbert's wife Afanen to see about procuring some fish.\n* Talk to Afanen\nObj 2:\nGarbert is at his cottage south of Echad Candelleth, at a fork in the river Bruinen.\nAfanen told you the story of the creature that crawled through the window into their house before she chased it off and insists that Garbert will not be able to collect his catch of fish for you today. You should speak with Garbert to see if any other arrangements might be made.\n* Talk to Garbert\nObj 3:\nGarbert's fishing nets are placed throughout the waters that flow through Tâl Bruinen.\nGarbert has given you permission to check his nets for fish, but has cautioned you that not every net will have fish in it.\n* Use Fishing Net (Level 1)\n* Use Fishing Net\nObj 4:\nGarbert is at his cottage south of Echad Candelleth, at a fork in the river Bruinen.\nYou have collected the day's catch for Garbert and should now return the fish to him.\n* Talk to Garbert\n* Turn in Tasty-looking Fish\nObj 5:\nWistan is at his campfire at Echad Candelleth, in Tâl Bruinen.\nYou have acquired several fish from Garbert the fisherman and should now bring them to Wistan for use in his plan.\n* Talk to Wistan\n* Turn in Tasty-looking Fish"},
{["next"]={2489,1585},area="Eastern Malenhad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Gabilshathûr is in danger. A raiding party of Orcs is making their way toward the dwarf-holding and may overrun it.",selectoneof={{val="Gisur's Jacket",id="70006B07"},{val="Longor",id="7000224B"},{val="Gisur's Thanks",id="7000EAE3"},{val="Orc-fighter's Stone",id="700161D4"}},category="Angmar",id=2439,scope="n/a",prev={427},name="The Orc-raid",arcs="Breathing Space",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Guard-captain Gisur",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs are moving against Gabilshathûr.\nGuard-captain Gisur has asked you to help defend Gabilshathûr against an Orc-attack.\n* Talk to Guard-Captain Gisur when you are ready\nObj 2:\nGuard-captain Gisur is at Gabilshathûr.\nYou helped stave off the Orc-attack and should speak with Gisur, now that the danger is over."},
{["next"]={699},area="Kingsfell",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="11s 50c"}},d="Orc scouts have been sneaking around Gatson's farm, stealing food, and Gatson is sure it is only a matter of time before they raid his farm in force.",mobs={{locations={"10.33S, 45.62W"},name="Gatson"}},category="North Downs",id=2440,scope="n/a",prev={2450},name="The Orc Threat",arcs="The Last Farm",level=25,c={"* Defeat Orcs just south of his farm."},minlevel=20,b="Gatson",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs can be found in Gatson's south fields.\nFarmer Gatson is resigned to the knowledge that the Rangers cannot help him, but he is still concerned for the safety of his workhands. He hopes that by dealing with the Orcs scouts that have been stealing from his fields, you might be able to deter a violent raid on his farm.\n* Defeat Orcs in Gatson's south fields (12)\nObj 2:\nGatson is at his farm, north of the fields.\nYou found and defeated many Orcs in Gatson's south fields. You should return to Gatson and tell him of your success.\n* Talk to Gatson"},
{["next"]={2451},area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",d="Larus Sharpshard discovered that there was a second strongbox, which remains missing.",mobs={{locations={"24.85S, 4.03W"},name="Larus Sharpshard"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2441,scope="n/a",prev={809},name="The Other Chest",arcs="Every Last Ingot",level=43,minlevel=38,b="Larus Sharpshard",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLarus Sharpshard believes the second strongbox is inside a building on the hill to your right as you approach the Dourhand-controlled keep in the pass of Gabilazan from the south. Gabilazan is east and south of Glóin's camp.\nLarus Sharpshard is very worried that Heikki Goldwatcher will record unflattering things about him if you are not able to recover a second dwarf-strongbox from the Misty Mountains.\n* Collect the second strongbox",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2656,774},area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Vile worms threaten the routes from Rivendell to the Elf-waypost at Gwingris.",mobs={{locations={"39.99S, 16.26W"},name="Daegennan"}},category="Eregion",id=2442,scope="n/a",name="The Path From Rivendell",arcs="The Path from Rivendell",level=48,c={"* Worms can be found in the valleys east of Gwingris."},minlevel=43,b="Daegennan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWorms can be found in the valleys east of Gwingris.\nDaegennan has asked you to help clear the routes between Rivendell and Gwingris of worms.\n* Defeat worms\nObj 2:\nDaegennan is at Gwingris, west of the worm-valleys.\nYou should return to Daegennan in Gwingris.\n* Talk to Daegennan at Gwingris",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",d="Many lore-masters seek the Path of the Ancient Master, but not all can accomplish their goals alone.",mobs={{locations={"16.41S, 109.63W"},name="Hugi"}},category="Lore-master",id=2443,scope="n/a",name="The Path of the Ancient Master: Lending a Hand",receive={{val="Mark of Victory (Level 1)",id=70018341}},level=58,minlevel=58,b="Hugi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nRuingal can be found in the Forges of Khazad-dûm, south of the Crossroads of Ash in the Flaming Deeps, east of the Water Works.\nHugi has asked you to aid a fellow lore-master against the fire-grim Ruingal, in order to fulfil the Path of the Ancient Master.\n* Defeat Ruingal\nObj 2:\nHugi is at the campsite outside the Forges of Khazad-dûm.\nYou should return to Hugi and inform him of your success.\n* Talk to Hugi at outside the Forges of Khazad-dûm",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
