hremmin on the Fields of Fornost has asked you to reconstruct the Chant of the Stalwart to prove your mastery of the scholarly art.\n* Bring the Chant of the Stalwart to Idhremmin\n* Turn in Chant of the Stalwart (Level 35)",traits={{val="Artisan Scholar Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Horsefields",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="42c"}},d="It is time for the pie-eating contest at the Bree-fields fair-ground. Come one, come all, and enjoy the fare.",mobs={{locations={"24.47S, 51.42W"},name="Humbert Sandheaver"}},titles={{val="Pie-Eating Champion"}},category="Bree-land",id=2461,scope="n/a",name="The Pie-eating Contest",level=5,pois={{locations={"24.47S, 51.43W"},name="Blackberry Pie"},{locations={"24.47S, 51.43W"},name="Rhubarb Pie"},{locations={"24.47S, 51.44W","24.47S, 51.43W"},name="Apple Pie"},{locations={"24.47S, 51.44W","24.47S, 51.43W"},name="Gooseberry Pie"}},minlevel=1,b="Humbert Sandheaver",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nEat six pies within the allotted amount of time.\n* Use Gooseberry Pie\n* Use Apple Pie\n* Use Blackberry Pie\n* Use Rhubarb Pie\nObj 2:\nEat five more pies within the allotted amount of time.\n* Use Gooseberry Pie\n* Use Apple Pie\n* Use Blackberry Pie\n* Use Rhubarb Pie\nObj 3:\nEat four more pies within the allotted amount of time.\n* Use Gooseberry Pie\n* Use Apple Pie\n* Use Blackberry Pie\n* Use Rhubarb Pie\nObj 4:\nEat three more pies within the allotted amount of time.\n* Use Gooseberry Pie\n* Use Apple Pie\n* Use Blackberry Pie\n* Use Rhubarb Pie\nObj 5:\nEat two more pies within the allotted amount of time.\n* Use Gooseberry Pie\n* Use Apple Pie\n* Use Blackberry Pie\n* Use Rhubarb Pie\nObj 6:\nEat one more within the allotted amount of time.\n* Use Gooseberry Pie\n* Use Apple Pie\n* Use Blackberry Pie\n* Use Rhubarb Pie\nObj 7:\nStuffed and sticky with pie, you should now speak to the Pie-man.\n* Talk to Humbert Sandheaver",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Pipe-weed is something hobbits take very seriously. A market would never be visited unless it had a suitable supply and variety.",category="Evendim",id=2462,scope="n/a",prev={1896},name="The Pipe-weed is Done",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="Blossom Gamgee",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAlbin Northcotton is at the market-grounds at the Northcotton Farm.\nAlbin Northcotton will be pleased to hear the pipe-weed is ready.\n* Talk to Albin Northcotton",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Greenfields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Halson Tubwort, innkeeper of The Plough and Stars, is entering the Four Farthings Brewing-moot.",mobs={{locations={"27.64S, 68.08W","27.63S, 68.08W"},name="Halson Tubwort"},{locations={"27.93S, 66.29W"},name="Wilcome Tunnelly"}},category="Shire",id=2463,scope="n/a",name="The Plough and Stars",receive={{val="Wooly-foot Stout",id="70000D7A"},{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=11,pois={{locations={"24.83S, 66.93W"},name="Gypsum"}},minlevel=7,b="Halson Tubwort",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWilcome Tunnelly is in Scary, east of Brockenborings. The Plough and Stars Inn is in Brockenborings, west of Scary.\nHalson Tubwort of The Plough and Stars has sent you down to Scary to fetch a shipment of gypsum that has gone astray.\n* Talk to Wilcome Tunnelly\nObj 2:\nThe goblins who stole the gypsum cart came from the Scrag-dells north of Brockenborings.\nIt seems that goblins have the gypsum intended for The Plough and Stars, you should travel to their camp and search for the missing cart.\n* Bring the gypsum to Halson Tubwort\n* Collect the powdered gypsum",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 5c"}},d="Unsatisfied by the death of the Dourhand who killed his brother, Áskell seeks to hurt the Dourhands further by reclaiming their stolen wealth.",mobs={{locations={"20.26S, 96.77W"},name="Áskell"}},selectoneof={{val="Herth-herthar",id="700033E4"},{val="Raider of Kheledûl",id="700033E6"},{val="Pillager of Kheledûl",id="700033E8"},{val="Skirmisher of Kheledûl",id="700033E7"},{val="Herth-klath",id="700033E5"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2464,scope="n/a",prev={3183},name="The Plundered Port",arcs="Sundered Shield",receive={{val="Champion over Kheledûl",id="700033E3"}},level=12,pois={{locations={"21.36S, 92.22W","20.95S, 92.03W","20.89S, 91.90W","21.32S, 91.72W","21.23S, 92.22W","21.31S, 91.95W","20.87S, 91.83W","20.95S, 92.04W","20.99S, 91.77W","21.03S, 91.67W","21.46S, 92.07W","21.45S, 92.08W","21.24S, 92.13W","21.10S, 92.21W","21.36S, 91.72W"},name="Treasure-box"}},minlevel=8,b="Áskell",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe treasure boxes are kept in the river port of Kheledûl, east of Gondamon.\nÁskell has devised a new plan to punish the Dourhands for Gellir's death. He has asked you to raid the port-town of Kheledûl and recover boxes of treasure stolen from the Longbeards by the Dourhands.\n* Bring the treasure boxes to Áskell\n* Collect treasure-boxes (6 Treasure-box )"},
{area="Chetwood",zone="Bree-land",d="The Men of Bree wish to help the hobbits in their annual fishing derby by allowing fishermen to catch fish from the pond by the farm.",mobs={{locations={"33.03S, 49.95W"},name="Will Hindmarsh"}},category="Festival",id=2465,scope="n/a",prev={2077},name="The Pond",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Will Hindmarsh",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe fish pond is east of Andrath farm.\nWill Hindmarsh has asked you to catch fish for the hobbits' Lithe Festival.\n* Catch as many fish as you can in twenty minutes.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="Anurandir was captured by half-orcs and it is up to you to save him.",mobs={{locations={"46.95S, 12.47W"},name="Dornhador"}},category="Eregion",id=2466,scope="n/a",name="The Prisoner of Barad Morlas",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Infused Athelas Essence",id="7000EA7F"}},level=49,c={"* You must escort Anurandir till [47.3S, 13.5W]"},minlevel=44,b="Anurandir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBring Anurandir to safety.\n* Save Anurandir\nObj 2:\nReturn to Dornhador in Echad Eregion.\nInform Dornhador that you rescued Anurandir.\n* Talk to Dornhador",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Now that you have assembled all the gears, it is time to open the vault.\nYou found these clues etched in the faces of the gears:\nThe axe bites deep before first light of the sun.\nThe sun rises after the moon has set.\nA jewel may be found in the light of the sun.\nJewels are only found after much hard work.\nBefore all else, the silvery light of the moon can be seen.",selectoneof={{val="Crown Finder",id=70003851},{val="Bávor's Blade",id=70003850},{val="Puzzle-stone",id="7001618D"},{val="Jofur-hálm",id="7000384F"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2467,scope="n/a",prev={2382},name="The Puzzle-vault",arcs="The Puzzle-vault",level=14,c={"* The stairs are on the right just after the Bard in Thorin's Hall. The levers are just left of Heikki Goldwatcher. The sequence of the levers is: Moon, Axe, Sun, Jewel."},minlevel=10,b="Bávor",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe vault is across Thorin's Hall to the north and up the stairs.\nPull the vault levers in the right sequence. If you make a mistake, go back to Bávor Redstone to reset the gears.\n* Use Moon\nObj 2:\nThe vault is across Thorin's Hall to the north and up the stairs.\nPull the vault levers in the right sequence. If you make a mistake, go back to Bávor Redstone to reset the gears.\n* Use Axe\nObj 3:\nThe vault is across Thorin's Hall to the north and up the stairs.\nPull the vault levers in the right sequence. If you make a mistake, go back to Bávor Redstone to reset the gears.\n* Use Sun\nObj 4:\nThe vault is across Thorin's Hall to the north and up the stairs.\nPull the vault levers in the right sequence. If you make a mistake, go back to Bávor Redstone to reset the gears.\n* Use Jewel\nObj 5:\nBávor Redstone is back on the far side of Thorin's Hall to the south.\nNow that you have solved the riddle of the puzzle-vault, you should collect the treasure and bring it back to Bávor Redstone.\n* Bring the contents of the puzzle-vault to Bávor Redstone\n* Turn in Crown of the Mountain"},
{area="Windfells",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You harvested the enormous tusks of the Black Sow, which remain in pristine condition.",mobs={{locations={"63.82S, 17.45W"},name="Saeradan"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2468,scope="n/a",name="The Queen of Boars",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Black Sow's Tusks",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSaeradan is at Echad Saeradan in the Windfells of Enedwaith.\nYou should bring the tusks of the Black Sow to Saeradan for his examination.\n* Talk to Saeradan\n* Turn in Black Sow's Tusks",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Redhorn Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="Nud-heden will never be recovered until the grodbog-queen is struck down.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2469,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1044},name="The Queen's Chamber",arcs="Grodbog Young",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Auti",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe grodbog-queen is at Nud-heden, within the Chittering Hole, south-east of the Orc-watch.\nAuti is convinced the grodbog-infestation will not be resolved until their queen is defeated.\n* Defeat the grodbog-queen\nObj 2:\nAuti is at the Orc-watch, north-west of Nud-heden.\nAuti will be pleased to hear the grodbog-queen has been defeated and the insects have left Nud-heden.\n* Talk to Auti at the Orc-watch"},
{reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="Calenglad of Tinnudir has bidden you speak with Nethúr of Esteldín in the North-downs concerning the Rangers of Esteldín and the Orkish forces pouring down from Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"9.71S, 40.77W"},name="Nethúr"},{locations={"12.72S, 67.18W"},name="Calenglad"}},category="Reputation",id=2470,scope="n/a",name="The Rangers of Esteldín",level=38,minlevel=33,b="Calenglad",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nNethúr is at Esteldín, far to the east of Evendim.\nCalenglad sent you to speak with Nethúr.\n* Talk to Nethúr",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={558},area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Esko told you the tale of the Jewel of Ice and how the Angmarim are using it as leverage against the Lossoth.",mobs={{locations={"11.45N, 69.70W"},name="Esko"}},category="Forochel",id=2471,scope="n/a",prev={2445},name="The Ransom of Angmar",level=48,c={"* Drops off of Angmarim soldiers."},minlevel=43,b="Esko",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Angmarim are encamped near the Ironspan, in the mountains of Forochel well to the east of the bay.\nEsko has asked you to search the encampments of the Angmarim for some evidence of the Jewel of Ice.\n* Search for evidence of the Jewel of Ice\nObj 2:\nThe Angmarim are encamped near the Ironspan, north-east of Pynti-peldot.\nEsko has asked you to search the encampments of the Angmarim for some evidence of the Jewel of Ice.\n* Turn in Angmarim Orders\nObj 3:\nEsko is at Pynti-peldot, south-west of the Ironspan.\nYou found a set of orders that tell when and where the Jewel of Ice will be brought into Forochel. You should bring the orders to Esko at once.\n* Talk to Esko\n* Turn in Angmarim Orders"},
{["next"]={1122},area="Taur Orthon",zone="Forochel",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Cenlieg the Lore-Master has lost his party, and is now stranded at Kauppa-kohta. He sent his raven to find traces of his fellows, but the raven has not returned.",mobs={{locations={"3.00N, 58.07W"},name="Cenlieg"}},category="Forochel",id=2472,scope="n/a",name="The Raven",arcs="The Lost Fellowship Lore-Master",level=44,c={"* The raven is in Metsästä-sija at [1.6N, 60.9W]"},minlevel=39,b="Cenlieg",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCenlieg's raven may be found near a rocky outcropping to the south-west of Kauppa-kohta\nCenlieg has asked you to find his missing raven.\n* Find and rescue Cenlieg's raven\nObj 2:\nCenlieg is at Kauppa-kohta, north-east of the rocky outcropping where you found the raven.\nYou found Cenlieg's raven, but it quickly hid in panic. Perhaps you should speak again with Cenlieg.\n* Talk to Cenlieg",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",money={{val="33s 4c"}},d="The Ranger Culang has learned of a great treasure buried long ago by a Dúnadan-landholder and wants it recovered before it is found by tomb-robbers.",mobs={{locations={"12.18S, 67.78W"},name="Culang"}},category="Evendim",id=2473,scope="n/a",prev={376},name="There and Back Again",arcs="The Treasure Hunt",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=38,c={"* This last Stone Marker is the first one you found, the one in Canadiach [10.7S, 64.8W]"},pois={{locations={"10.74S, 64.78W"},name="Stone Marker"}},minlevel=33,b="Stone Marker",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe treasure may lie beneath another stone marker, somewhere in Evendim, if this riddle is to be believed:\n\"The end of your search lies at the beginning.\nMy treasure was always there, but you did not see.\"\nYou should examine the marker when you find it for some clue to the location of the treasure.\n* Find the solution to the riddle\nObj 2:\nCulang is at the Ranger-camp on the island of Tinnudir, west of the crossroads of Canadiach.\nYou found a hollow compartment in the stone marker that you believed to mark the location of the treasure and recovered a mouldy book from the hidden space. You should bring this book to Culang.\n* Talk to Culang\n* Turn in Mouldy Book"},
{["next"]={2586},zone="Ered Luin",area="Falathlorn",d="You now have a place to call home, but it would be even nicer with some fine decorations.",mobs={{locations={"24.99S, 90.56W","28.10S, 92.08W","24.24S, 93.05W"},name="Barchiril"},{locations={"25.97S, 90.72W"},name="Barthavron"}},selectoneof={{val="Small Table",id="7000D0AC"},{val="Dresser",id="7000D079"},{val="Small Woven Brown Rug",id="7000D20F"},{val="Red Chair",id="7000D0E4"}},category="Housing",id=2474,scope="n/a",name="There is No Place Like Home",receive={{val="Birch Tree",id="7000D1FF"}},level=15,minlevel=11,b="Barchiril",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarthavron is in the market square of the Falathlorn homestead.\nBarchiril has sent you to speak with her friend Barthavron.\n* Talk to Barthavron",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1300},area="The Flaming Deeps",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="The Deep-worms of the Flaming Deeps produce a large amount of heat. The dwarves believe this heat could be enhancing the growth of the fungus in the nearby Water-works.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2475,scope="n/a",name="There is our Problem",receive={{val="Earring of Tanunshush",id="7001639F"}},level=57,minlevel=52,b="Ölfun",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDeep-worms are at Tanunshush, south-west of Anazârmekhem, north of The Burning Stair.\nÖlfun believes the fungus in the Water-works is caused by a Deep-worm nest adjoining the flooded depths. He believes that if you defeat several of them, the Water-works should cool, and the fungus will wither and die.\n* Defeat Deep-worms in Tanunshush (12)\nObj 2:\nÖlfun is at Anazârmekhem, north-east of Tanunshush.\nÖlfun will want to know that while you defeated many Deep-worms, it did not feel any cooler.\n* Talk to Ölfun in Anazârmekhem"},
{money={{val="28s"}},d="Bogrian wants to know what became of the remains of Durin's Bane. She has sent a detachment of her personal guards and defilers to attempt to recover trophies or information from his corpse.",selectoneof={{val="Bogrian's Bane",id="700163C0"},{val="Oxi's Lesson",id="700163C6"},{val="Wingless' Bane",id=70016406}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=2476,scope="n/a",prev={406},name="The Remains of the Bane",level=59,minlevel=54,b="Oxi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe passage to Zirakzigil lies west through the gardens, then north.\nOxi has instructed you to prevent Bogrian's expedition from bringing back any potentially valuable or dangerous trophies from the Balrog's remains.\n* Defeat Bogrian's morroval-guards\n* Defeat Bogrian's morvul-defilers\nObj 2:\nOxi is at Jazârgund, south and east of the entrance to Zirakzigil.\nOxi is awaiting your return and hoping for your success.\n* Talk to Oxi at Jazârgund",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
