o call home, but it would be even nicer with some fine decorations.\nBestower\nNan Henwood (NPC)\nNan Henwood (NPC)\nNan Henwood (NPC)\n'Well, now that you have a place to live, (your name), you should certainly consider buying some furniture and other comforts for it. I recommend you speak with Bill Twiggins. You can find his shop in the market square of the community...I'm sure he'll be able to help you out!'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nBill Twiggins is in the market square of the Bree homestead.\nNan Henwood has sent you to speak with Bill Twiggins in hopes that he can help you furnish your home.\n* Talk to Bill Twiggins\n//Andy Brockhouse Location: 36.48S, 72.76W\nThe Shire >> The Delving Fields';markerList['1879096841_0x0415C6D000000006_88.38143.61736872'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879096841_0x0415C72000000047_30.4686.24736912', new GLatLng(-9.464765625, -50.35728515625), { 'icon':QUEST_ICON }); marker.id = '1879096841_0x0415C72000000047_30.4686.24736912'; markers['1879096841_0x0415C72000000047_30.4686.24736912'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Andy Brockhouse Location: 32.77S, 73.05W\nThe Shire >> The Delving Fields';markerList['1879096841_0x0415C72000000047_30.4686.24736912'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879096841_0x0415E72000000021_120.1148.22752912', new GLatLng(-9.631845703125, -46.756845703125), { 'icon':QUEST_ICON }); marker.id = '1879096841_0x0415E72000000021_120.1148.22752912'; markers['1879096841_0x0415E72000000021_120.1148.22752912'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Andy Brockhouse Location: 32.96S, 71.00W\nThe Shire >> Tookland';markerList['1879096841_0x0415E72000000021_120.1148.22752912'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879101496_0x041308800000000A_110.3897.743841088', new GLatLng(6.054521484375, -111.52986328125), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879101496_0x041308800000000A_110.3897.743841088'; markers['1879101496_0x041308800000000A_110.3897.743841088'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Rambi Location: 15.11S, 107.85W\nEred Luin >> Thorin\\'s Hall Homesteads';markerList['1879101496_0x041308800000000A_110.3897.743841088'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879101498_0x0417C6E00000002C_104.67105.24992880', new GLatLng(-12.19376953125, -4.705048828125), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879101498_0x0417C6E00000002C_104.67105.24992880'; markers['1879101498_0x0417C6E00000002C_104.67105.24992880'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Bill Twiggins (Homestead Provisions)Location: 35.87S, 47.08W\nBree-land >> Bree-land Homesteads';markerList['1879101498_0x0417C6E00000002C_104.67105.24992880'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879101498_0x0417C6E00000002C_104.67105.78992880', new GLatLng(-12.191396484375, -4.705048828125), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879101498_0x0417C6E00000002C_104.67105.78992880'; markers['1879101498_0x0417C6E00000002C_104.67105.78992880'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Bill Twiggins (Homestead Provisions)Location: 35.87S, 47.08W\nBree-land >> Bree-land Homesteads';markerList['1879101498_0x0417C6E00000002C_104.67105.78992880'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879097321_0x0415B6D000000034_61.0769.66728872', new GLatLng(-13.053251953125, -51.494501953125), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879097321_0x0415B6D000000034_61.0769.66728872'; markers['1879097321_0x0415B6D000000034_61.0769.66728872'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Rolf Bracegirdle (Homestead Provisions)Location: 36.85S, 73.69W\nThe Shire >> Shire Homesteads';markerList['1879097321_0x0415B6D000000034_61.0769.66728872'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker); GME_DEFAULT_ICON = G_DEFAULT_ICON;      } else {        document.getElementById(\"map1393237455\").innerHTML = \"In order to see the map that would go in this space, you will need to use a compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap1393237455);\n//]]>\nQuest: There's No Place Like Home\nCategory: Housing\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 11\nNext Quests:The Taxidermist of Bree\nRewards\nReceive:\nBirch TreeSelect one of:\nDresser\nSmall Table\nRed Chair\nSmall Woven Brown Rug\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nYou now have a place to call home, but it would be even nicer with some fine decorations.\nBestower\nAndy Brockhouse (NPC)\nAndy Brockhouse (NPC)\nAndy Brockhouse (NPC)\n'You shan't be disappointed with your new home, my friend, but it comes with precious little in the way of amenities. For those, you should speak with Rolf Bracegirdle, who can be found in the market square within the community.'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nRolf Bracegirdle is in the market square in the Michel Delving homestead.\nAndy Brockhouse has asked you to speak with Rolf Bracegirdle, a decorator who might be able to help you furnish your home.\n* Talk to Rolf Bracegirdle",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2531},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",d="Lindir has found a new riddle for you to solve. Again, he is sure the answer can be found somewhere in Imladris.",mobs={{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Boromir"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Bilbo Baggins"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Lindir"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Refined Athelas Essence",id="70000F89"},{val="Lindir's Gauntlets",id="70000F88"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2478,scope="n/a",prev={2529},name="The Riddle-finder",arcs="The Riddle-game",level=36,minlevel=31,b="Bilbo Baggins",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLindir is with Bilbo in the Hall of Fire at Rivendell.\nLindir has a new riddle to offer.\n* Talk to Lindir\nObj 2:\nThe answer to Lindir's riddle can be found somewhere in Rivendell.\nLindir has asked you to find an item that provides an answer to his riddle.\nBreath is needed\nWarning heeded\nSome will arrive\nWith sword and knife\nMy work is completed\n'Til once more I'm needed.\n* Talk to Boromir\nObj 3:\nLindir is with Bilbo in the Hall of Fire at Rivendell.\nBoromir has given you a token that provides the answer to Lindir's Gondorian riddle.\n* Talk to Lindir\n* Turn in Boromir's Badge"},
{["next"]={2529},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",d="Bilbo has asked you to help out in a riddle-game he is playing with Lindir:\nI often hold your hand,\nBut I have no hands wherewith to hold.\nI often sleep in summer,\nBut I do my best when it grows cold.\nI often lose my mate,\nBut I feel no sorrow, if truth be told.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Bilbo Baggins"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Lindir"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2479,scope="n/a",name="The Riddle-game",arcs="The Riddle-game",level=36,pois={{locations={"29.32S, 6.75W"},name="Work-gloves"}},minlevel=31,b="Bilbo Baggins",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLindir is standing with Bilbo in the Hall of Fire.\nBilbo has asked you to speak with Lindir about the riddle he asked the old hobbit.\n* Talk to Lindir\nObj 2:\nThe answer to Lindir's riddle lies somewhere in Rivendell. Lindir is in the Last Homely House in Rivendell.\nLindir is waiting for you to bring him whatever thing is the answer to his riddle.\n* Bring the gloves to Lindir at the Last Homely House\n* Find an item that solves Lindir's riddle",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2527},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",d="Bilbo has a riddle of his own for you to solve:\nA long beard I have of bristly hair,\nBut no chin or cheek on which to bear.\nMany hands hold me, with ne'er a caress,\nYet I'm e'er the first to clean up a mess.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Bilbo Baggins"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Lindir"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2480,scope="n/a",prev={2528},name="The Riddle-maker",arcs="The Riddle-game",level=36,pois={{locations={"29.31S, 6.79W"},name="Besom-broom"}},minlevel=31,b="Lindir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBilbo is standing with Lindir in the Hall of Fire.\nBilbo has a riddle for you to solve.\n* Talk to Bilbo Baggins\nObj 2:\nThe solution to Bilbo's riddle is somewhere around Rivendell. Bilbo is in the Last Homely House in Rivendell.\nBilbo is waiting for you to bring him the item that solves his riddle.\n* Bring the broom to Bilbo Baggins at the Last Homely House\n* Find an item that solves Bilbo's riddle",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",d="Glorfindel does not know where lies Celebrían's legacy for Arwen, but he has given you some advice which may help you to find it.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 3.06W"},name="Glorfindel"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},selectoneof={{val="Master of Riddles",id="70000FEC"},{val="Riddle Master's Hat",id="70000FEA"},{val="Dannellas",id="70000FEB"},{val="Riddle-stone",id="700161DD"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2481,scope="n/a",prev={2531},name="The Riddle-master",arcs="The Riddle-game",level=36,minlevel=31,b="Glorfindel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe lost Elf-vault is somewhere in the Trollshaws in the vicinity of Rivendell. Once the legacy is found, return to Glorfindel outside the house of Elrond, by the waterfall.\nGlorfindel advised you to place a hand on a rock by the entrance of the Elf-vault and to recite the verses of the riddle. Celebrían's legacy for Arwen, a white jewel, should be somewhere in the vault. If you find the jewel, return to Glorfindel with your prize.\n* Bring Celebrían's legacy to Glorfindel\n* Collect Celebrían's legacy\nObj 2:\nElrond is in the library of Rivendell.\nGlorfindel asked you to bring Arwen's legacy to Elrond.\n* Talk to Elrond\n* Turn in Celebrían's Legacy"},
{["next"]={2530},area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",d="A final riddle that bears on Elrond's House in Rivendell is yet to be solved.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Bilbo Baggins"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Lindir"},{locations={"30.14S, 3.06W"},name="Glorfindel"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2482,scope="n/a",prev={2527},name="The Riddle-seeker",arcs="The Riddle-game",level=36,minlevel=31,b="Lindir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBilbo is standing with Lindir in the Hall of Fire.\nBilbo will tell you the unsolved riddle.\n* Talk to Bilbo Baggins\nObj 2:\nElrond is in the library of Imladris.\nBilbo thinks Elrond may know more about the riddle.\nThe jewel of the moon,\nEnshrined in the water,\nFrom mother to daughter\nIs given a boon.\nShips sail to the west,\nForgetting all sorrow,\nLandfall on the morrow,\nThe isles of the blest.\n* Talk to Elrond\nObj 3:\nGlorfindel is outside the house of Elrond, by the waterfall.\nElrond has directed you to speak to Glorfindel about the riddle.\nThe jewel of the moon,\nEnshrined in the water,\nFrom mother to daughter\nIs given a boon.\nShips sail to the west,\nForgetting all sorrow,\nLandfall on the morrow,\nThe isles of the blest.\n* Talk to Glorfindel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="55s 30c"}},d="Warg-riders make their way through the mountain-crags and slip into and out of the shadows of Moria with ease. At the Grand Stair, a leader and his aged mount have come to bend knee to Igash the Fanatic and Mazog.",mobs={{locations={"10.99S, 106.77W"},name="Thithrand"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2483,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Rider and his Mount",arcs="Riders of the North",level=58,minlevel=57,b="Thithrand",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlothrok the Vile is within the Grand Stair, north-east of the Orc-watch.\nThithrand seemed unnerved at the sight of a powerful goblin riding an even more powerful-looking Warg. The pair entered the Grand Stair at the head of the Warg-riders and have not been seen since.\n* Defeat Glothrok the Vile\n* Defeat Forzunk\nObj 2:\nThithrand is at the Orc-watch, south-west of the Grand Stair.\nYou should return to Thithrand with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Thithrand at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={829,1588,1836,139,2463,838,951,2070,2315},zone="Angmar",area="Aughaire",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Crannog's design has been revealed: your Fém is to stand for the Trév Gállorg in Clúcath against the Trév Duvárdain and their Angmarim masters.",mobs={{locations={"0.03S, 40.15W"},name="Osbail"},{locations={"0.09S, 40.18W"},name="Crannog"},{locations={"0.10N, 39.57W"},name="Camran"}},selectoneof={{val="Tasgall?s Gift of Wisdom",id="7000EACF"},{val="Tasgall?s Gift of Valour",id="7000EACD"},{val="Tasgall?s Gift of Destiny",id="7000EACE"}},category="Angmar",id=2484,scope="n/a",prev={622},name="The Rite of Clúcath",arcs="Crannog's Challenge",level=44,c={"* Osbail is at Aughaire [0.0S, 40.2W]\n* Camran is at Aughaire [0.1N, 39.6W]\n* Tasgall is at Fasach-larran [2.5N, 38.4W]"},minlevel=39,b="Crannog",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOsbail is by Crannog's ruling-seat in Aughaire, Camran is at the centre island of the settlement, and Tasgall is still hunting hill-beasts north of Aughaire and south-east of Nád Nathair.\nCrannog has advised you to speak with the people of Aughaire to learn what you may about your upcoming challenge: the Clúcath with the Trév Duvárdain.\n* Talk to Osbail\n* Talk to Camran\nObj 2:\nCrannog is at his ruling-seat in Aughaire, west of the settlement's central island.\nYou have spoken with some of the Trév Gállorg and should return to Crannog as he advised.\n* Talk to Crannog\nObj 3:\nCrannog is at his ruling-seat in Aughaire, west of the settlement's central island.\nCrannog is waiting for you to speak with him so you may travel together to Fail-á-Khro for the Clúcath with the Trév Duvárdain.\n* Talk to Crannog and travel to Fail-á-Khro\nObj 4:\nCrannog is at his ruling-seat in Aughaire, west of the settlement's central island.\nYou have emerged victorious from the Clúcath with the Trév Duvárdain and should now speak with Crannog.\n* Talk to Crannog\n* Turn in Tasgall's Gift"},
{zone="Evendim",area="Bullroarer's Sward",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="The road has been cleared and the wolf defeated.",mobs={{locations={"23.03S, 67.24W"},name="Hal Gamgee"}},category="Evendim",id=2485,scope="n/a",prev={1959},name="The Road is Clear",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=31,minlevel=26,b="Hal Gamgee",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAlbin Northcotton is at the Northcotton Farm.\nAlbin Northcotton will be pleased to hear that Nibs is ready and the road is clear.\n* Talk to Albin Northcotton",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="Athradnir is anxious to hear what has become of the Malledhrim host who marched east to Emyn Lûm, for the closer the Elves draw to Dol Guldur, the more perilous the journey becomes.",category="Mirkwood",id=2486,scope="n/a",name="The Road to Emyn Lûm",receive={{val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,minlevel=58,b="Athradnir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nFuirgam should be among the Malledhrim at their stronghold in Emyn Lûm.\nYou should seek Fuirgam and establish a line of communication between the Elves of Emyn Lûm and the Dourstocks.\n* Talk to Fuirgam in Emyn Lum",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2667},reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="The isle of Rantost is where the tomb-robbers have made their central camp. A great deal of history is being kept there.",category="Evendim",id=2487,scope="n/a",prev={2042},name="The Robbers of Rantost",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=36,minlevel=31,b="Eliot Bencroft",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are several things to be done around Rantost to disturb the tomb-robbers operations.\n* Aid Eliot Bencroft in Rantost\n* Aid Leighton Kipps in Rantost\n* Aid Wal Simpkins in Rantost\nObj 2:\nEliot Bencroft is at the south-east corner of Rantost.\nEliot Bencroft will want to hear that Rantost has been weakened to the point of being open to a larger assault.\n* Talk to Eliot Bencroft at Rantost",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2421},area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="The crebain in northern Eregion have established themselves in the land, finding good roosting grounds.",mobs={{locations={"40.00S, 16.50W"},name="Thaliondir"}},selectoneof={{val="Holly-tree Shield",id="7001608E"},{val="Thaliondir's Sacrifice",id=70016104}},category="Eregion",id=2488,scope="n/a",prev={248},name="The Roosting Tree",arcs="Crebain on the Ridge",level=48,c={"* The Roosting Tree is at [39.3S, 8.2W]"},pois={{locations={"39.32S, 8.16W"},name="Roosting Tree"}},minlevel=43,b="Thaliondir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe crebain's roosting tree lies in the valley to the east of Gwingris.\nThaliondir has asked you to burn down the roosting tree of the crebain.\n* Use Roosting Tree\nObj 2:\nThaliondir is at Gwingris, west of the roosting tree.\nYou should return to Thaliondir with news of your success.\n* Talk to Thaliondir at Gwingris"},
{area="Länsi-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="The root of the problem with the great winter-worms which have been attacking the dwarf-canals seems to lie with a particularly vicious worm dubbed Ringdagnir.",mobs={{locations={"9.42N, 81.22W"},name="Weth"}},selectoneof={{val="Chillbane's Woe",id="7000E5E4"},{val="Chillbane's Curse",id="7000E5DA"},{val="Chillbane's Doom",id="7001619A"}},category="Forochel",id=2489,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1548},name="The Root of the Problem",arcs="Furred Worms",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Glacier Surprise",id="7000E8D2"}},level=47,c={"* Ringdagnir can be found in the sulfur pools of Länsi-mâ at [10.5N, 82.8W]"},minlevel=42,b="Weth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRingdagnir can be found on the westside of the hot springs near Zigilgund.\nWeth has asked you to defeat the great winter-worm Ringdagnir.\n* Defeat Ringdagnir\nObj 2:\nWeth can be found in Zigilgund, south of the thermal vents.\nYou have defeated the great worm Ringdagnir. Weth will be pleased with you.\n* Talk to Weth"},
{["next"]={1631},area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The ruins of Pembar have become a haven of half-orcs in the service of Saruman the White, who has fallen to evil. What they seek within the ancient Elf-ruins remains a mystery.",mobs={{locations={"47.00S, 12.47W"},name="Faenhilith"}},category="Eregion",id=2490,scope="n/a",name="The Ruins of Pembar",arcs="The Ruins of Pembar",level=49,c={"* Pembar is at [44.1S, 10.8W]\n* Rubble are located at\n[44.2S, 11.1W]\n* [44.2S, 10.8W]\n* [44.3S, 10.7W]\n* [44.1S, 10.6W]\n* [44.0S, 10.7W]\n* [44.0S, 10.8W]\n* [44.1S, 10.9W]\n* [43.9S, 10.9W]"},pois={{locations={"44.11S, 10.63W","43.86S, 10.89W","44.22S, 11.07W","44.04S, 10.85W","44.23S, 10.79W","44.12S, 10.94W","44.03S, 10.69W","44.27S, 10.69W"},name="Rubble (Level 1)"}},minlevel=44,b="Faenhilith",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are many rubble piles in Pembar, north-east of Echad Eregion.\nFaenhilith has asked you to search the rubble piles at Pembar to see if you can learn what interest the minions of Saruman have there.\n* Use Rubble (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nFaenhilith is at Echad Eregion, south-west of Pembar.\nYou should return to Faenhilith and let her know what you found at Pembar.\n* Talk to Faenhilith at Echad Eregion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2277},area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="You have found a book of records buried in the ruins of Audaghaim, but many pages are missing from the period when Sauron returned to Mirkwood.",mobs={{locations={"14.73S, 56.23W"},name="Record-keeper of Audaghaim"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2491,scope="n/a",prev={384,3229},name="The Scattered Tales of Audaghaim",arcs="The History of Audaghaim",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,c={"* Over the blank gravestone you will find the shade of the Record-keeper of Audaghaim, who will tell you the whole story. He is at [14.7S, 56.2W]"},minlevel=57,b="Prestadír",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe blank gravestone is in the graveyard to the south of Audaghaim and the Haunted Inn.\nYou should search the area of the uninformative gravestone again for anything you may have missed.\n* Examine the blank gravestone more closely this time\n* Use\nObj 2:\nPrestadír is at the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks, north of the graveyard.\nYou should tell Prestadír of your encounter with the condemned Record-keeper who appeared when you searched his grave.\n* Talk to Prestadír\n* Turn in Lost Pages"},
{["next"]={2489,1585},area="Eastern Malenhad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="The dwarf Arngrim has vanished after telling some of the other miners that he was sure he knew the location of a mithril vein in the hills of Imlad Balchorth.",selectoneof={{val="Bothwar's Praise",id="7000EAC9"},{val="Herth-fótar",id="70006AAB"},{val="Bothwar's Javelin",id="700161D3"}},category="Angmar",id=2492,scope="n/a",prev={1096},name="The Scent of Mithril",arcs="Prospector of Angmar",level=48,c={"* Arngrim is at Imlad Balchorth [4.5N, 27.3W]"},minlevel=43,b="Bothwar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nArngrim is seeking mithril atop a ridge on the very southern reaches of Imlad Balchorth, north of Gabilshathûr.\nBothwar is concerned that Arngrim, slightly befuddled at the best of times, might have gotten himself into trouble in the southern reaches of Imlad Balchorth.\n* Find Arngrim\nObj 2:\nBothwar is on the bridge in the middle of Gabilshathûr, south of Imlad Balchorth.\nYou have returned Arngrim to his senses and should report back to Bothwar."},
{["next"]={1374,282,2673,591,326,841},area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="7s"}},d="Your assessment of the goblin camp in Annúndir has given hope to the Ranger Amarion, and now he believes you can strike a blow against the goblins.",mobs={{locations={"12.53S, 52.77W"},name="Amarion"}},selectoneof={{val="Medliron",id="70006B66"},{val="Amarion's Rune-stone",id="700161B2"},{val="Amarion's Necklace",id=70009311},{val="Skotskold",id="700017BE"}},category="North Downs",id=2493,scope="n/a",prev={2061},name="The Scout Becomes the Hunter",arcs="Protecting the Refugees",level=22,minlevel=17,b="Amarion",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblin camp is east of Amon Raith, on the southern hills of Annúndir.\nEncouraged by your skills and the light presence of the goblins in the hills of Annúndir, Amarion has asked you to begin driving the goblins from that land.\n* Defeat goblins (12)\nObj 2:\nThe Ranger Amarion is at Amon Raith, west of Annúndir.\nAmarion is waiting to hear about your attack on the goblins of Annúndir.\n* Talk to Amarion"},
{["next"]={2454},area="Redhorn Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The remains you brought to Ingifast yielded some useful items to help him stage the next step in his plan.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2494,scope="n/a",prev={2029},name="The Scout's Report",arcs="White-Hand Orders",level=56,pois={{locations={"13.67S, 104.15W"},name="Crate"}},minlevel=51,b="Ingifast",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe crate is near the Chittering Hole, south-east of the Orc-watch.\nIngifast wants you to place the bag containing the remains of the previous White Hand expedition on a raised surface, such as a crate, near a patrol-route often used by White Hand scouts.\n* Use Crate\n* Turn in Evidence\nObj 2:\nIngifast is at the Orc-watch, north-west of the Chittering Hole.\nIngifast will be pleased to hear the evidence has been placed on the crate for the scout to find.\n* Talk to Ingifast in the Orc-watch"},
{["next"]={2471},area="The Drownholt",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Antidotes often grow from the same soil as poisons; herbs from near the sickly pool should be collected so that the Elves can examine them for medicinal properties.",mobs={{locations={"16.70S, 54.93W"},name="Nestawen"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2495,scope="n/a",prev={2484},name="The Search for a Remedy",arcs="The Mysterious Affliction",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,c={"* The plants and herbs can be found around the pools in the Drownholt around [17.4S, 56.1W]"},pois={{locations={"17.87S, 55.17W","17.88S, 55.80W","17.76S, 55.92W","17.69S, 55.99W","17.61S, 56.10W","17.78S, 55.75W","17.82S, 55.77W","17.81S, 55.88W","17.58S, 56.11W","17.90S, 55.50W","17.85S, 55.66W","17.96S, 55.34W","17.85S, 55.87W"},name="Strange Plant"},{locations={"17.91S, 55.40W","17.87S, 55.22W","17.86S, 55.18W","17.51S, 56.13W","17.91S, 55.27W","17.75S, 55.80W","17.65S, 55.94W","17.85S, 55.24W","17.87S, 55.55W","17.72S, 55.97W","17.66S, 56.06W","17.90S, 55.37W"},name="Strange Herb"}},minlevel=58,b="Nestawen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nPlants can be found growing near the dreadful pool in the Drownholt, south from Estolad Mernael.\nYou should hasten to the pool and collect many herbs there, for these may possess some property that could heal the steed Alagos.\n* Use Strange Plant\n* Use Strange Herb\nObj 2:\nNestawen can be found at Estolad Mernael, tending her sick steed Alagos.\nYou should bring the plants and flowers you collected to Nestawen to see if they can be of any use to her.\n* Talk to Nestawen\n* Turn in Strange Plant (Level 1)\n* Turn in Strange Herb (Level 1)"},
{["next"]={2353},area="Trestlebridge",zone="The North Downs",d="Dallin Endholder is concerned about his friend Idalene. She has gone missing after telling him about dreams she had that called her to the fields of Fornost.",mobs={{locations={"17.88S, 53.93W"},name="Dallin Endholder"},{locations={"13.04S, 55.28W"},name="Colbert the Mad"}},category="North Downs",id=2496,scope="n/a",name="The Search for Idalene",arcs="The Search for Idalene",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Dallin Endholder",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nColbert's camp is north of Trestlebridge, overlooking the Greenway.\nDallin Endholder has sent you to a strange man named Colbert in hopes that he will be able to tell you something of Idalene.\n* Talk to Colbert the Mad",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Northern Barrow-downs",zone="Bree-land",d="Bob's daughter, Lalia, has gone missing. Bob fearing she may have gone off in search of the \\qLast Prince,\\q a character in one of the tales Barliman Butterbur tells to travellers, joined a foray into the Barrow-downs to find his daughter.",mobs={{locations={"31.77S, 56.19W"},name="Bob"}},category="Bree-land",id=2497,scope="n/a",name="The Search for Lalia",level=18,minlevel=13,b="Bob",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAccording to Butterbur's tale, the Barrow of the Last Prince lies between Northern Barrow and the Dead Spire, near a large standing stone.\nBob has asked you to search the Barrow-downs for his missing daughter, who likely has come here in search of the fabled \"Last Prince.\"\n* Find Bob's daughter, Lalia",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2598},area="Vale of Thrain",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Bávor is an artificer tasked with repairing the great lock which opens access to the fabled Vault of the Mountain.",category="Ered Luin",id=2498,scope="n/a",prev={2387},name="The Second Gear",arcs="The Puzzle-vault",level=7,c={"* The second gear is in a Chest in Orodost at [20.6S, 102.4W]"},pois={{locations={"20.62S, 102.40W"},name="Chest"}},minlevel=3,b="Bávor",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe chest containing the second gear can be found on the south side of the goblin-infested ruins in the Vale of Thráin, south of Thorin's Halls and west of Noglond.\nBávor discovered the location of the second gear and has sent you to search for it, while he repairs the first gear.\n* Use Chest\nObj 2:\nBávor is in Thorin's Hall.\nBávor will be pleased to begin working with the second gear.\n* Bring the second gear to Bávor\n* Turn in Gear"},
{area="The Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",money={{val="56s 70c"}},d="The Sixteenth Hall is an area overrun with Orcs, many of whom suffer from a terrible illness that sweeps through. Shamans tend to the ill whilst the rest of the halls are defended by those that remain able to do battle.\nMallas, an Elf ally to the dwarves, belives that there is something secret beneath the Sixteenth Hall and wishes to learn the true purpose and source of the plague.",mobs={{locations={"13.15S, 101.23W"},name="Lar"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2499,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Secret Beneath",arcs="Peasant Halls",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Lar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Sixteenth Hall lies to the north-east of the Shadowed Refuge.\nLar has asked you to delve deep into the Sixteenth Hall and see if you can locate the source of his unease.\n* Find and eliminate the source of Lar's worry\nObj 2:\nLar can be found in the Shadowed Refuge, south-west of the Sixteenth Hall.\nYou should return to Lar and tell him what you discovered and slew: a terrible headless creature in the depths of the hall, lurking in a room full of spores and slime.\n* Retrurn to Lar at the Shadowed Refuge"},
{["next"]={2627},area="Bridgefields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="You found a collar inscribed with runes you cannot read, apparently buried by the unusually large wolf Linda Bolger saw the night the wolves ran through Budgeford.",mobs={{locations={"33.41S, 66.09W"},name="Orthir"},{locations={"31.45S, 65.61W"},name="Linda Bolger"}},category="Shire",id=2500,scope="n/a",prev={1120},name="The Secret of the Collar",arcs="New Neighbours",level=11,minlevel=7,b="Linda Bolger",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAn Elf may be camped near Woodhall, south of Budgeford.\nLinda Bolger was confounded by your discovery of a collar where she had seen the great wolf. She was unable to read the letters on the collar, but thought that perhaps the Elf Milo thought he saw might be able to decipher them.\n* Talk to Orthir\n* Turn in Rune-Inscribed Collar"},
{money={{val="27s 65c"}},d="From your description of the map the torch projected onto the wall, Geirfast thinks the secret chamber must lie somewhere within Nud-melek, perhaps in the southern part of the Second Hall.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2501,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={895},destinypoints={{val=250}},name="The Secret of the Council",level=58,c={"* The secret chamber is in the Second Hall, in Nud-melek, at [8.9S, 103.2W]"},minlevel=53,b="Geirfast",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance lies somewhere in Nud-melek, south-east of the Twenty-first Hall, perhaps the Second Hall.\nGeirfast has asked you to find the entrance to the secret chamber depicted in the shadow-map.\n* Discover the entrance to the secret chamber\nObj 2:\nGeirfast is at the Twenty-first Hall, north-west of the Second Hall.\nYou should return to Geirfast to tell him where the chamber is.\n* Talk to Geirfast\nObj 3:\nGeirfast is at the Twenty-first Hall.\nYou should speak with Geirfast when you are ready to travel.\nObj 4:\nGeirfast is at the Twenty-first Hall.\nYou should return at once to Geirfast.\n* Talk to Geirfast\n* Turn in Geirfast's Transcript\nObj 5:\nLenglammel is encamped at the Shadowed Refuge.\nGeirfast suggested you speak with the Elf Lenglammel.\n* Talk to Lenglammel at the Shadowed Refuge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Gorothlad",zone="Angmar",d="There are many old tales long forgotten in Angmar, but Nethraw is interested in only one.",mobs={{locations={"1.27S, 22.92W"},name="Nethraw"}},category="Angmar",id=2502,scope="n/a",prev={2884},name="The Secret of the Swords",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Banfuir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe lore-master Nethraw can be found at the Krúsle Lannan, a considerable distance to the east of Gabilshathûr.\nBanfuir suggested you speak with the lore-master Nethraw.\n* Talk to Nethraw",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Coldfells",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Fandmau prepares the defence of Tirith Rhaw against the Free Peoples.",category="Tirith Rhaw",id=2503,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="These People Be Pests",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Fandmau",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nSlaughter the Free Peoples within the bounds of Tirith Rhaw.\nFandmau seems unimpressed with your capability, but you can show him that you are more of a soldier of Angmar than he.\n* Slaughter the Free People in Tirith Rhaw (15 at Tirith Rhaw )\nObj 2:\nIf Fandmau was killed or Tirith Rhaw was lost, make your way to War-tyrant Akúlhun at Gramsfoot.\nFandmau's fears were unfounded. You repelled the attack and scored a great victory over the Free People. You should return to him with your report.\n* Talk to Soldier Fandmau\n* Talk to War-tyrant Akúlhun",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{area="Gorothlad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="47s 60c"}},d="You have come with Nethraw into the heart of the Krúsle Lannan.",selectoneof={{val="Herth-mundar",id="70006B0C"},{val="Evervaib",id="70006A80"},{val="Sapphire Charm",id="700069FD"},{val="Ríemaib",id="7000313E"},{val="Shield of the North-star",id=70003092}},category="Angmar",id=2504,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2582,2578,2583,2577,2580,2579,2581},name="The Seven Swords",receive={{val="Delver of Krúslë Lannan",id="7000D9A4"}},level=47,c={"* the Sword of Abb from Owen [1.8N, 24.6W]\n* the Sword of Kolmak from Ruraikh [2.2N, 25.6W]\n* the sword of Ánraig from Tobaid [2.3N, 27.8W]\n* the sword of Guinokh from Brekhin [3.7N, 27.4W]\n* the sword of Innis from Dugald [0.6S, 26.2W]\n* the sword of Kevoka from Frangan [0.9S, 24.9W]\n* the sword of Mánas from Huisdán [0.4S, 24.5W]"},pois={{locations={"1.19S, 22.94W","1.31S, 22.93W","1.32S, 22.79W","1.16S, 22.88W","1.35S, 22.86W","1.25S, 22.76W"},name="Pedestal (Level 1)"},{locations={"1.18S, 22.79W"},name="Pedestal"}},minlevel=42,b="Nethraw",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNethraw is at the Krúsle Lannan, east of Gabilshathur.\nYou must place the Seven Swords in their pedestals to open the Krúsle Lannan.\n* Use Pedestal (Level 1)\n* Use Pedestal (Level 1)\n* Use Pedestal\n* Use Pedestal (Level 1)\n* Use Pedestal (Level 1)\n* Use Pedestal (Level 1)\n* Use Pedestal (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nSearch the Krúslë Lannan with Nethraw.\nObj 3:\nYou must escape from the Krúslë Lannan with Nethraw.\n* Escape from Krúslë Lannan\n//Nethraw Location: 1.27S, 22.92W\nAngmar >> Gorothlad';markerList['1879082465_0x0419A99000000004_135.73145.1712321224'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879103354', new GLatLng(18.290390625, 37.725380859375), { 'icon':INTERACT_ICON }); marker.id = '1879103354'; markers['1879103354'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Pedestal (Level 1) Location: 1.19S, 22.94W\nAngmar >> Gorothlad';markerList['1879103354'] = m