{area="Agamaur",zone="The Lone-lands",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eglain"}},money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Somehow the very essence of the Red Swamp has been corrupted. Radagast the Brown, a Wizard who has come to Agamaur, seeks to learn the cause.",mobs={{locations={"29.79S, 27.39W","29.78S, 27.39W"},name="Radagast the Brown"}},category="Lone-lands",id=2536,scope="n/a",prev={2838},name="The Tainted Living",arcs="Tainted Living",level=30,c={"* The stumps are scattered north-west of the Eglain-encampment."},pois={{locations={"27.93S, 28.35W","27.88S, 27.95W","28.32S, 28.64W","27.63S, 28.25W","27.71S, 28.84W","28.15S, 29.17W","28.38S, 28.32W","27.87S, 27.66W","27.65S, 29.17W","28.09S, 27.99W","28.01S, 28.81W","28.39S, 27.65W","28.24S, 27.73W","28.05S, 29.02W"},name="Corrupted Stump"}},minlevel=25,b="Radagast the Brown",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are many corrupted stumps in the north-west of Agamaur.\nRadagast has asked you to gather bark from the corrupted tree-stumps in Agamaur, so that he may continue his study into Ivar's means of causing the corruption. He warns you that Agamaur should not be traversed alone. You should gather allies.\n* Use Corrupted Stump\nObj 2:\nRadagast is in the Eglan-camp in the southern parts of Agamaur.\nThe task was not simple, for enemies were abundant in the swamp, but you managed to gather nine strips of bark for Radagast. You should return to the Wizard with your bounty.\n* Talk to Radagast the Brown\n* Turn in Root-bark"},
{["next"]={1516},area="Carn Dûm",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+300 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="You found a bracelet of burnished gold, covered in grime and filth. The name \\qDírdrë\\q was marked upon it.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Thoriel"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Húriel"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Lorniel"},{locations={"12.33N, 31.76W"},name="Táni"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Throst"},{locations={"12.07N, 31.89W"},name="Gormal"},{locations={"12.28N, 31.81W"},name="Éa"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Donaith"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Fimreg"},{locations={"10.87N, 23.93W"},name="Areneth"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Laerdan"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Lunathron"}},category="Angmar",id=2537,scope="n/a",name="The Tarnished Bracelet",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Tarnished Bracelet",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTármunn Súrsa lies in the northern part of eastern Angmar.\nYou should go to Tármunn Súrsa and question its inhabitants about the bracelet you found.\n* Talk to Éa\n* Turn in Tarnished Bracelet\n* Talk to Lorniel\n* Talk to Golodir\n* Talk to Laerdan\n* Talk to Fimreg\n* Talk to Areneth\n* Talk to Lunathron\n* Talk to Húriel\n* Talk to Thoriel\n* Talk to Donaith\n* Talk to Gormal\n* Talk to Táni\n* Talk to Throst",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thorin's Hall Homesteads",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="The furnishing supplier in your homestead has asked you to deliver an important order to Clar Whitethorn in Bree-town.",mobs={{locations={"35.87S, 47.08W"},name="Bill Twiggins"},{locations={"30.28S, 52.35W","64.92N, 133.95W"},name="Clar Whitethorn"},{locations={"15.11S, 107.85W"},name="Rambi"},{locations={"36.85S, 73.69W"},name="Rolf Bracegirdle"},{locations={"25.97S, 90.72W"},name="Barthavron"}},category="Housing",id=2538,scope="n/a",name="The Taxidermist of Bree",receive={{val="Large Bear-skin Rug",id="7000D22F"}},level=15,minlevel=15,b="Rambi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBring the Clar's Work Order to Clar Whitethorn in Bree. He can be found across the street from the bank in western Bree-town.\n* Talk to Clar Whitethorn\n* Turn in Clar's Work Order",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tyl Ruinen",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="30s 24c"}},d="Now that you have defeated Humfrey Rumming in his riddle-contest, he may at last be willing to tell you the terrible secret of the salamanders.",mobs={{locations={"11.75S, 72.00W"},name="Humfrey Rumming"},{locations={"12.21S, 68.01W"},name="Calatherdir"}},category="Evendim",id=2539,scope="n/a",prev={1878},name="The Terrible Secret of the Salamanders",arcs="The Burning Island",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=33,c={"* The door in the ruins near Humfrey Rumming can be opened with the key he will give you. Both Salamanders are at the basement."},minlevel=28,b="Humfrey Rumming",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe two original salamanders can be found in the cellar of Tollobel, on Tyl Ruinen.\nHumfrey Rumming confided in you that he was the one responsible for the plague of salamanders on Tyl Ruinen and gave you the key to the cellar where he trapped the two original creatures. He asked you to slay the two originals to help reduce their numbers.\n* Kill 1 Salamander-dam\n* Kill 1 Salamander-sire\nObj 2:\nHumfrey Rumming is by the ruins of Tollobel on Tyl Ruinen.\nHumfrey Rumming is waiting to hear of your victory over the two original salamanders he brought to Tyl Ruinen.\n* Talk to Humfrey Rumming\n* Turn in Cellar Key\nObj 3:\nCalatherdir is at the Ranger-camp on the island of Tinnudir, east of Tyl Ruinen.\nHaving learned the origin of the salamanders and helped to slow their proliferation, you should return to Calatherdir to tell him the tale of your deeds.\n* Talk to Calatherdir"},
{["next"]={1801},area="Durin's Way",zone="Moria",money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="Arnfinn ventured out towards Tharâkh Bazân to gather information about Mazog and has yet to return.",mobs={{locations={"2.86S, 106.87W"},name="Arnfinn"}},category="Moria Upper Levels",id=2540,scope="n/a",name="The Terror that was Azog",arcs="Lest We Forget",level=54,c={"* Arnfinn is in a corner in The Mustering Hall at [2.9S, 106.9W]"},minlevel=49,b="Borgar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nArnfinn was last seen heading west towards Tharâkh Bazân.\nBorgar fears for the safety of one of his friends, Arnfinn who was last seen venturing out to find information about Mazog and the Orcs of Moria.\n* Talk to Arnfinn\nObj 2:\nBorgar is at Jazârgund, east from Tharâkh Bazân.\nBorgar will be pleased to know that Arnfinn is safe.\n* Talk to Borgar at Jazârgund",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="The craft of tailoring is one that rewards methodical care with toughness and resilience.",mobs={{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Jes"},{locations={"28.21S, 92.69W"},name="Cannasgam"},{locations={"12.01S, 67.78W"},name="Trudy Lavender"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Sara Crabgrass"},{locations={"27.44S, 68.28W"},name="Halfred Greenhand"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Mat Hedgerow"},{locations={"22.88S, 67.60W"},name="May Gardner"},{locations={"20.15S, 97.07W"},name="Dragmáll"},{locations={"28.54S, 6.19W"},name="Miluidan"},{locations={"26.36S, 53.67W"},name="Carver Greenlake"},{locations={"34.60S, 75.43W"},name="Halfred Bolger"},{locations={"7.50S, 64.13W"},name="Tilly Hogben"},{locations={"33.71S, 62.12W"},name="Rowan Brandybuck"},{locations={"31.87S, 69.41W"},name="Garnet Grubb"},{locations={"17.92S, 53.70W"},name="Biddy Yeandle"},{locations={"31.38S, 66.05W"},name="Walerand Bolger"}},category="Crafting",id=2541,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Thickest of Skins, Part I",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Dragmáll",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nCarver Greenlake is at Thornley's Work Site, north of the town of Bree.\nYou have been instructed to speak with Carver Greenlake, a skilled tailor who may be able to aid you in your training.\n* Talk to Carver Greenlake",traits={{val="Apprentice Tailor Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="With every piece you prepare, you learn something new about the process and about yourself.",mobs={{locations={"9.47S, 42.06W"},name="Erandir"},{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Jes"},{locations={"28.21S, 92.69W"},name="Cannasgam"},{locations={"12.01S, 67.78W"},name="Trudy Lavender"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Sara Crabgrass"},{locations={"27.44S, 68.28W"},name="Halfred Greenhand"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Mat Hedgerow"},{locations={"22.88S, 67.60W"},name="May Gardner"},{locations={"20.15S, 97.07W"},name="Dragmáll"},{locations={"28.54S, 6.19W"},name="Miluidan"},{locations={"34.60S, 75.43W"},name="Halfred Bolger"},{locations={"7.50S, 64.13W"},name="Tilly Hogben"},{locations={"33.71S, 62.12W"},name="Rowan Brandybuck"},{locations={"31.87S, 69.41W"},name="Garnet Grubb"},{locations={"17.92S, 53.70W"},name="Biddy Yeandle"},{locations={"31.38S, 66.05W"},name="Walerand Bolger"}},category="Crafting",id=2542,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Thickest of Skins, Part II",receive={{val="Deft Gauntlets",id="7000390F"}},level=25,minlevel=20,b="Dragmáll",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Ranger Erandir is at Esteldín in the North Downs.\nA Novice Tailor has seen your improvement at the trade and recommended that you seek the counsel of Ranger Erandir.\n* Talk to Erandir\nObj 2:\nThe Ranger Erandir is at Esteldín in the North Downs.\nErandir has asked you to fashion deft gauntlets, which he will examine to determine whether you are sufficiently skilled at tailoring to proceed with the craft.\n* Turn in River-maiden's Thread\n* Turn in Leather Brace\n* Turn in Leather Guard\n* Turn in Tough Leather Pad\nObj 3:\nThe Ranger Erandir is at Esteldín in the North Downs.\nErandir is waiting to judge the craftsmanship of the deft gauntlets he asked you to make.\n* Bring the deft gauntlets to Erandir\n* Turn in Deft Gauntlets",traits={{val="Journeyman Tailor Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={255,2592},area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="Like a cut of leather that has been cured and prepared, you have gained a deal of toughness that you once did not possess, but you still lack the assured technique of the finest tailors.",mobs={{locations={"26.51S, 53.73W"},name="Millicent Greenlake"},{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Jes"},{locations={"28.21S, 92.69W"},name="Cannasgam"},{locations={"12.01S, 67.78W"},name="Trudy Lavender"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Sara Crabgrass"},{locations={"27.44S, 68.28W"},name="Halfred Greenhand"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Mat Hedgerow"},{locations={"22.88S, 67.60W"},name="May Gardner"},{locations={"20.15S, 97.07W"},name="Dragmáll"},{locations={"28.54S, 6.19W"},name="Miluidan"},{locations={"34.60S, 75.43W"},name="Halfred Bolger"},{locations={"7.50S, 64.13W"},name="Tilly Hogben"},{locations={"33.71S, 62.12W"},name="Rowan Brandybuck"},{locations={"31.87S, 69.41W"},name="Garnet Grubb"},{locations={"17.92S, 53.70W"},name="Biddy Yeandle"},{locations={"31.38S, 66.05W"},name="Walerand Bolger"}},category="Crafting",id=2543,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Thickest of Skins, Part III",level=25,minlevel=20,b="Dragmáll",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nMillicent Greenlake is at Thornley's work-site on the Bree-fields, north of Bree.\nYou have been told to speak with Millicent Greenlake, supervising construction in the fields north of Bree, to improve your tailoring technique. You have also been warned of her impatient nature.\n* Talk to Millicent Greenlake",traits={{val="Expert Tailor Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Twenty-first Hall",zone="Moria",d="The speed with which you can fashion animal skins into quality leather goods astounds those who have not followed a similar course.",mobs={{locations={"9.70S, 40.50W"},name="Fladdan"},{locations={"14.54S, 51.07W"},name="Ardir"},{locations={"18.49S, 63.74W"},name="Condir"},{locations={"15.49S, 67.70W"},name="Fladron"},{locations={"5.42S, 104.94W"},name="Glond"},{locations={"30.98S, 29.93W"},name="Branda Rumble"},{locations={"31.04S, 29.93W"},name="Herhalig"}},category="Crafting",id=2544,scope="Crafting Advancement",prev={255,2591},name="The Thickest of Skins, Part IV",receive={{val="Drakeskin Cuirass",id="70006C31"}},level=40,minlevel=35,b="Fielò",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nBranda Rumble is in Ost Guruth, the Ruin-hold in the Lone-lands.\nYou have been told that Branda Rumble might be able to teach you some more techniques to aid in your craft.\n* Talk to Branda Rumble\nObj 2:\nBranda Rumble gave you her notes on the fashioning of a drake-skin cuirass.\nAfter boasting of her accomplishments, Branda Rumble eventually asked you to craft a drake-skin cuirass for her to judge both its worth and your own.\n* Turn in Drake Hide\n* Turn in Darkened Leather Guard\n* Turn in Darkened Leather Binding\n* Turn in Pristine Leather Brace\nObj 3:\nBranda Rumble is at Ost Guruth, the Ruin-hold in the Lone-lands.\nBranda Rumble asked you to make a drake-skin cuirass to prove your skill at tailoring.\n* Bring the drake-skin cuirass to Branda Rumble\n* Turn in Drake-skin Cuirass",traits={{val="Artisan Tailor Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Mírdiniel of the Malledhrim wishes you to search Dannenglor one last time -- this time for the most priceless remnants of the days when Elves lived there, before the merrevail took hold.",category="Mirkwood",id=2545,scope="n/a",prev={3182},name="The Thief of Dannenglor",arcs="The Treasure Hoard of Dannenglor",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,c={"* The Greedy Morroval-thief is by the Dark Gap in Dannenglor at [12.4S, 54.6W]"},minlevel=57,b="Mírdirniel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe primary thief among the merrevail can be found in Dannenglor, north of the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks.\nYou should confront the morroval who hoards the priceless Elf-treasure and attempt to reclaim it for the Elves.\n* Defeat the greedy morroval-thief\n* Turn in Priceless Elf-treasure\nObj 2:\nMírdiniel awaits you at the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks, south of Dannenglor.\nYou should bring the priceless Elf-treasure to Mírdiniel so that she may send it to be kept by the Galadhrim in Lothlórien, where it will remain safe as long as the Elves exist to watch over it.\n* Talk to Mírdirniel\n* Turn in Priceless Elf-treasure"},
{["next"]={2668},area="Tinnudir",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="Tomb-robbers are threatening the peace of Evendim, despoiling the ancient sites of the Dúnedain.",selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Refined Celebrant Ointment",id="70008D08"},{q="(x2)",val="Refined Athelas Extract",id="70008CF7"}},category="Evendim",id=2546,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Thief-takers",arcs="The Thief-takers",receive={{val="Superior Salted Beef Delights",id="7000338B"},{q="(x2)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"},{val="Superior Hobbiton Omelet",id="7000338E"},{val="Superior Roasted Chicken",id="7000338F"}},level=36,c={"* Crates can be found at [7.4S, 69.4W]\n* This quest is incorrectly marked as fellowship. The crates are guarded by 36 and 37 non-elite mobs. This is a solo-able quest.\n* Do this alongside Quest:Practised Villainy, the objectives are the same."},minlevel=31,b="Eliot Bencroft",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTomb-robbers have established a camp on Rantost, an island north of Tinnudir on Lake Nenuial.\n* Kill 10 Veteran Tomb-robber\n* Kill 10 Scouting Tomb-robber\nObj 2:\nEliot Bencroft is at the south east corner of Rantost.\nEliot Bencroft will be pleased to here the island has been thinned.\n* Talk to Eliot Bencroft"},
{["next"]={546},area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="You discovered that half-orcs had ransacked the vestiges of a campsite, taking something away with them.",mobs={{locations={"47.02S, 12.53W"},name="Golgallon"}},selectoneof={{val="Scout's Trousers",id=70016071},{val="Golgallon's Armour",id=70016074}},category="Eregion",id=2547,scope="n/a",prev={911},name="The Thieves' Trail",arcs="Footsteps of the Company",level=50,c={"* Thlûk is still in the Tâl Caradhras area [48.1S, 8.7W]"},minlevel=45,b="Golgallon",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe half-orcs were seen to the east and a little south of Echad Eregion, almost due south of the Company's campsite.\nGolgallon told you to hunt down the half-orcs and recover whatever they took from the campsite.\n* Find half-orcs bearing the item from the Company's campsite\nObj 2:\nGolgallon is at Echad Eregion, west and north of where you found Thlûk.\nYou should return to Golgallon with tidings of your encounter with Thlûk.\n* Talk to Golgallon at Echad Eregion"},
{area="Caras Galadhon",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+700 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="A thieving shrew has made off with Pippin's pipe-weed pouch.",mobs={{locations={"14.95S, 66.86W"},name="Gladmeldis"}},category="Lothlórien",id=2548,scope="n/a",name="The Thieving of the Shrew",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,c={"* As you follow the track of the shrew, you will come across some Elves that will point you in the correct direction, as shown above.\n* Cordofron is the first NPC that will offer a hint on the shrew's path, and can be found at [14.6S, 66.8W]\n* Luinhen is the next NPC that will offer a hint on the shrew's path, and can be found at [15.5S, 66.4W]\n* Aecthor is the last NPC that will offer a hint on the shrew's path, and can be found at [15.9S, 66.9W]\n* The Pipe-weed Pouch is in a rock in the middle of a nearby pool [15.7S, 67.0W]"},pois={{locations={"15.73S, 66.98W"},name="Pipe-weed Pouch"}},minlevel=55,b="Gladmeldis",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe shrew ran off to the north of the Company's Pavilion.\nA shrew has run off with Pippin's pipe-weed pouch, and you should find it before the hobbit awakes.\n* Find the stolen pipe-weed pouch\nObj 2:\nGladmeldis is at the Company's Pavilion in Caras Galadhon.\nYou have recovered Pippin's pipe-weed pouch and should bring it to Gladmeldis at once.\n* Talk to Gladmeldis\n*",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Foundations of Stone",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="In the deepest dark of Moria there is a place where the only light that shone emanated from dwarf-lamps and luminescant fungus. Now, these delvings are dim and darker than ever and home to creatures that exist in nightmares. Yet here they are, and Veúlfur's agents sent to the Shadowed Refuge draw little comfort in knowing that there is something within the Dark Delvings that commands the Orcs to poison themselves in a manner that gives them over to some greater will.",mobs={{locations={"13.16S, 101.23W"},name="Moggi"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2549,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Things in the Dark",arcs="Dark Delvings",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Moggi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Dark Delvings lie far to the south-east of the Shadowed Refuge.\nMoggi made mention of lamps placed in the Dark Delvings by the dwarves and how they may drive back some of the Nameless, but he thinks that there are others who are unafraid of such Light. Use caution as you fulfil this task.\n* Defeat howling overseers in the Dark Delvings\n* Defeat snarling overseers in the Dark Delvings\n* Defeat Dark-maw masters in the Dark Delving\n* Defeated dark world-eaters in the Dark Delving\nObj 2:\nMoggi is at the Shadowed Refuge, far to the north-west of the Dark Delving.\nYou fought your way into the Dark Delving and there defeated many of the nameless horrors. You should now return to the Shadowed Refuge and inform Moggi of your success.\n* Talk to Moggi at the Shadowed Refuge",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2400},area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Bávor is an artificer tasked with repairing the great lock which opens access to the fabled Vault of the Mountain.",selectoneof={{val="Bávor's Boots",id=70003856},{val="Túrchathol",id=70003857}},category="Ered Luin",id=2550,scope="n/a",prev={2547},name="The Third Gear",arcs="The Puzzle-vault",level=10,c={"* The chest is located inside some ruins in Emyn Hoedh at [17.9S, 94.0W]. You must enter the ruins from the rear; the chest will be against the west wall near the northwest corner of the building."},pois={{locations={"17.90S, 93.98W"},name="Chest"}},minlevel=6,b="Bávor",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe third gear is in a chest in the ruins of an ancient crypt in Emyn Hoedh, the barrow-mounds in Haudh Lin, north-east of Gondamon.\nBávor has asked you to recover the third missing gear for the Vault of the Mountain. He warned you of rumours regarding the presence of barrow-wights amongst the old mounds.\n* Use Chest\nObj 2:\nBávor is in Thorin's Hall.\nBávor will be pleased to begin working with the third gear.\n* Bring the third gear to Bávor\n* Turn in Gear"},
{["next"]={2772},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="The burning oil carried by the goblin-sappers that have crept into the Midgewater Marshes are particularly worrisome to Bill Mossfoot, charged with the defence of Staddle.",mobs={{locations={"31.09S, 49.40W"},name="Watcher Redweed"}},category="Bree-land",id=2551,scope="n/a",prev={1921},name="The Threat of Fire",arcs="Goblins in the Marshes",level=14,minlevel=10,b="Bill Mossfoot",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGoblin-sappers have infiltrated the southern expanse of the Midgewater Marshes.\nBill Mossfoot has tasked you with defeating the Midgewater sappers before they can take their deadly burning oil to Staddle.\n* Defeat Midgewater sappers in the Midgewater Marsh\nObj 2:\nBill Mossfoot is at his camp in the Midgewater Marsh to the south-east of the Midgewater Ruins.\nNews of your success against the goblin-sappers should relieve Bill Mossfoot of some of his worries.\n* Talk to Bill Mossfoot"},
{["next"]={114},area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="Kaj is now prepared to embark upon the Lossoth-ritual he has vowed to complete.",mobs={{locations={"11.41N, 69.45W","8.95N, 73.41W","8.88N, 73.32W"},name="Kaj"},{locations={"8.84N, 73.34W"},name="Pinja"}},category="Forochel",id=2552,scope="n/a",prev={147},name="The Ties That Bind",arcs="Capture the Bride",level=46,c={"* Complete Instance: The Ties That Bind"},minlevel=41,b="Kaj",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKaj is in Pynti-peldot.\nYou should speak with Kaj when you are ready to assist him with his ritual.\n* Talk to Kaj\nObj 2:\nPinja is outside her house at Lumi-talletta, south-west of Pynti-peldot in Itä-ma.\nYou should speak with Pinja at once.\n* Talk to Pinja"},
{["next"]={1728},area="Imlad Balchorth",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Oflár is disturbed by the news of the wights spreading throughout Imlad Balchorth and has developed a plan to get rid of them.",mobs={{locations={"6.94N, 25.86W"},name="Oflár"}},category="Angmar",id=2553,scope="n/a",prev={2884},name="The Tincture",arcs="Cauldron of Death",level=48,c={"* The nightshade-plants are in Gorothlad around [1.4N, 20.9W]"},minlevel=43,b="Oflár",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe nightshade plant grows north and east of Maethad, to the south-east of Myrkworth.\nOflár has asked you to collect Nightshade plants to prepare a tincture that he hopes will prove useful against the wights of Imlad Balchorth.\n* Bring the nightshade-plants back to Oflár\n* Turn in Nightshade"},
{["next"]={2453},area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="34s 16c"}},d="Gwindeth has agreed to lower the flood-waters in the tomb of Elendil so that you can recover the Silithar for Aragorn.",mobs={{locations={"12.72S, 67.18W"},name="Calenglad"}},selectoneof={{val="Jofurskold",id="7000A262"},{val="Calenglad's Shield (Level 38)",id="700161A5"},{val="Elloch",id="7000A25A"},{val="Calenglad's Cloak",id="7000A239"}},category="Evendim",id=2554,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2276},name="The Tomb of Elendil",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=40,minlevel=35,b="Calenglad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCalenglad is at the Ranger-camp on Tinnudir, in Evendim.\nCalenglad is waiting to speak with you about travelling to the tomb of Elendil to reclaim the Silithar for Aragorn.\n* Talk to Calenglad and travel to the tomb of Elendil\nObj 2:\nCalenglad is at the Ranger-camp on Tinnudir, in Evendim.\nCalenglad is waiting for you to speak with him about your adventures in the tomb of Elendil.\n* Talk to Calenglad"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Rollo Newbuck has learned that Odo Pipes is also playing Hiders and Seekers, but Rollo doesn't know where the hobbit is hiding.",mobs={{locations={"33.32S, 75.42W"},name="Odo Pipes"},{locations={"33.40S, 75.03W"},name="Rollo Newbuck"}},selectoneof={{val="Hider's Cloak",id="70006A78"},{val="Seeker's Shoes",id="70006AB1"}},category="Shire",id=2555,scope="n/a",prev={1098},name="The Top Hiding-Place",arcs="Hiders and Seekers",level=6,minlevel=2,b="Rollo Newbuck",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOdo Pipes is hiding somewhere in Michel Delving.\nRollo Newbuck has sent you to find Odo Pipes, rumoured to be the best Hider in the Shire. Odo is hiding somewhere in Michel Delving. Rollo thinks that Daisy or Polo, in their usual hiding-places, might have some clue to Odo's location.\n* Find Odo Pipes\nObj 2:\nRollo Newbuck is east of The Bird and Baby Inn, within the stone wall around Town Hole.\nRollo is waiting to hear that you have found Odo Pipes and his hiding-place.\n* Talk to Rollo Newbuck"},
{d="The Gaunt-lord Ivar, aided by a band of sellswords, swept through the village of Stoneheight in his search for his helm. When his goals were reached, he abandoned the village to the mercy of the sellswords.",category="In Their Absence",id=2556,scope="n/a",name="The Town of Stoneheight",destinypoints={{val=250}},receive={{q="(x5)",val="Medallion of the North-men",id=70025341}},level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nGundúl is one of the minions of the Gaunt-lord Ivar who remain behind in the village of Stoneheight. You should seek him out and put an end to his evil.\n* Find Gundúl\nObj 2:\nGundúl is one of the minions of the Gaunt-lord Ivar who remain behind in the village of Stoneheight. You should seek him out and put an end to his evil.\n* Defeat Gundúl\nObj 3:\nBúbhosh-grat is yet another of the minions of Ivar at Stoneheight. He must be found and defeated as well.\n* Find Búbhosh-grat\nObj 4:\nBúbhosh-grat is yet another of the minions of Ivar at Stoneheight. He must be found and defeated as well.\n* Defeat Búbhosh-grat\nObj 5:\nBúbhosh-grat has fled before you. You must chase him down and defeat him.\n* Follow Búbhosh-grat\nObj 6:\nDale Truitt is the last of the sellswords in the service of Ivar who must be defeated.\n* Defeat Dale Truitt"},
{["next"]={2606},area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+500 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="This note describes a hideous end for any that would fall into the clutches of the Draig-lûth, which have come north out of Dunland.",mobs={{locations={"67.43S, 13.92W"},name="Gronu"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2557,scope="n/a",name="The Trail Begins",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Sealed Scroll",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGronu can be found at his camp north of Harndirion, at the foot of the mountain.\nYou should seek out Gronu and give him the message that you found.\n* Bring the note to Gronu at is camp"},
{area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="According to a note that you discovered, the members of Gronu's hunting-party may still be alive and held in a secret cave beneath a waterfall.",mobs={{locations={"67.43S, 13.92W"},name="Gronu"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2558,scope="n/a",prev={2605},name="The Trail Ends",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Gronu",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe dungeon is behind the second waterfall, east of Gronu's camp.\nGronu has asked you to find the dungeon where the Draig-lûth hold their prisoners and free his companions.\n* Discover the cavern and save the captives\nObj 2:\nGronu is at his camp, west of the waterfall.\nYou should return to Gronu and let him know that all of the captives that could be found have been freed.\n* Talk to Gronu at his camp"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+700 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="Fastarr knows of an ancient anvil where you may craft the heart of the quality you seek for your weapon, but scouts report that the ancient armoury in which it lies has recently been overrun by a well-organized force of Moria Orcs, who are even now training in preparation for their next assault to drive the dwarves from Moria.",mobs={{locations={"8.48S, 112.35W"},name="Fastarr"}},selectoneof={{val="Firm Resolve",id="7001369D"},{val="Fused Bronze Relics",id=70018606},{val="Gleaming Striker",id=70013697},{val="Shadow-master",id="7001131E"},{val="Dead-reaver",id=70011326},{val="Guardian of the Deep Halls",id="70017D83"},{val="Vermin-slayer",id=70011315}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2559,scope="Legendary Items",name="The Training Hall",level=54,minlevel=49,b="Fastarr",repeatable="Yes",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nFastarr has asked you to bring him an infused garnet with which he may be able to aid you in bestowing a quality upon your weapon. He does not, however, know where to find such a stone.\n* Talk to Fastarr\n* Turn in Infused Garnet\nObj 2:\nFastarr can be found at the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nFastarr has bidden you to speak with him again when you are ready to seek out the old armoury, but warns you that a well-organized band of Moria Orcs has taken control of the hall.\n* Talk to Fastarr to travel to the old armoury\nObj 3:\nFastarr can be found at the Dolven-view camp in Moria.\nYou should return to Fastarr to complete the enhancement of your weapon.\n* Talk to Fastarr\n* Turn in Empowered Garnet"},
{["next"]={2437},area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",d="The Ranger Culang has learned of a great treasure buried long ago by a Dúnadan-landholder and wants it recovered before it is found by tomb-robbers.",mobs={{locations={"12.18S, 67.78W"},name="Culang"}},category="Evendim",id=2560,scope="n/a",name="The Treasure Hunt",arcs="The Treasure Hunt",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=32,pois={{locations={"10.74S, 64.78W"},name="Stone Marker"}},minlevel=27,b="Culang",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nA stone marker in Evendim may hide treasure. Culang told you this riddle, which may hold a clue to the marker's location:\n\"Two roads pass through green fields.\nFour kings watch the meeting of the ways.\"\nYou should examine the marker when you find it for some clue to the location of the treasure.\n* Find the solution to the riddle",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Meluinen",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="Thaliollang believes that Lachenn had tried to write \\qAngmar\\q on the back of his ornament and takes it as a sign that it is an emissary of Angmar that had stirred the Stone-trolls.",mobs={{locations={"13.72S, 44.55W"},name="Thaliollang"}},selectoneof={{val="Favour of the North-downs",id="70019E99"},{val="Eldram",id="70006B64"},{val="Favargair's Folly",id="70019E98"},{val="Favargair's Foil",id="70006B6C"},{val="Longbeard's Hammer",id="70006B71"},{val="Túrphadanir",id="70006B25"}},category="North Downs",id=2561,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1720,2567},name="The Troll-keeper",level=33,minlevel=28,b="Thaliollang",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAngmar's emissary must reside deep within the cave in Taur Gonwaith, south-east of Lin Giliath.\nThaliollang has asked you to defeat the emissary of Angmar that has gained the allegiance of the Stone-trolls.\n* Kill 1 Favargair Troll-keeper\nObj 2:\nThaliollang is at Lin Giliath, north-west of Taur Gonwaith.\nThaliollang will be pleased to know that he was correct in his belief: there was an emissary from Angmar among the trolls. To the benefit of all, you have defeated him.\n* Talk to Thaliollang"},
{area="The Great Delving",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="25s 55c"}},d="Gamli desires revenge against the gredbyg who recently infested his bedding.",selectoneof={{val="Gamli's Fly-swatter",id="700160F8"},{val="Gamli's Leggings",id="7001607C"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2562,scope="n/a",prev={365},name="The Trouble With Gredbyg",level=52,minlevel=47,b="Gamli",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGredbyg can be found throughout the Great Delving.\nGamli wants you to kill off as many gredbyg as you can.\n* Defeat gredbyg in the Great Delving (16)\nObj 2:\nGamli is at the Dolven-view camp, in the Great Delving.\nYou should return to Gamli and tell him of your forays against the Gredbyg.\n* Talk to Gamli at the Dolven-view camp"},
{area="Bridgefields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Harvest flies are generally just a nuisance to the crops, but recently they have begun attacking hobbits in the Marish.",mobs={{locations={"31.22S, 65.87W"},name="Bingo Bolger"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Hard Biscuits",id="700032ED"},{val="Bolger's Shoes",id="700032EC"}},category="Shire",id=2563,scope="n/a",name="The Trouble With Harvest-flies",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=10,minlevel=6,b="Bingo Bolger",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere is a nest of harvest-flies on the Yale-height a distance to the south and east of Budgeford, not far north-east of Woodhall. The hill is marked by three pillars at its pinnacle.\nBingo Bolger is disturbed by the increased aggression in the harvest-flies and has asked you to help deal with them.\n* Defeat harvest-flies (10)\nObj 2:\nBingo Bolger is in Budgeford, by a pig pen on the lower slope of the town.\nBingo Bolger reported increased aggression among the harvest-flies in the Marish and asked you to deal with them. You should return to him with word of your success.\n* Talk to Bingo Bolger"},
{["next"]={1973},area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="60c"}},d="Now that you are acquainted with Bree-town, Graeme Tenderlarch has decided to ask you for some real help on the outskirts of town.",mobs={{locations={"31.08S, 51.24W","31.08S, 51.25W"},name="Mayor Graeme Tenderlarch"},{locations={"28.16S, 53.33W"},name="Chief Watcher Grimbriar"}},category="Bree-land",id=2564,scope="n/a",prev={201},name="The Trouble with the Southerners",arcs="Welcome to Bree-town",level=14,minlevel=10,b="Mayor Graeme Tenderlarch",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nChief Watcher Grimbriar is at a stone cottage along the roadway, out the West-gate of Bree and north along the Greenway.\nGraeme Tenderlarch, the mayor of Bree, asked you to speak with Chief Watcher Grimbriar regarding the brigands threatening the safety of Bree-land.\n* Talk to Chief Watcher Grimbriar outside Bree-town"},
{["next"]={93},area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="You are a light shadow flitting against the moon, only seen when you wish to be, a soft breeze on the night air, soon past.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.44W"},name="Celsia 'Lightfinger' Gosling"},{locations={"33.53S, 62.49W"},name="Sterling Proudfoot"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Jennet Brockhouse"},{locations={"31.00S, 52.18W","64.20N, 133.78W"},name="Albra Lowbanks"},{locations={"28.23S, 92.25W"},name="Falco Broadhouse"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Lilabet Roper"},{locations={"25.24S, 48.72W"},name="Fastred Burrows"},{locations={"18.75N, 71.96W"},name="Kalervo"},{locations={"12.73S, 66.99W"},name="Dreda Penney"},{locations={"29.86S, 3.32W"},name="Elmo Brown"},{locations={"50.51S, 7.91W"},name="Herward Took"}},category="Burglar",id=2565,scope="n/a",prev={19,194},requiredclasses="Burglar",name="The Truest Course is Awareness",arcs="The Truest Course",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Fastred Burrows",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSterling Proudfoot is in Buckland, west of the town of Bree, in Bree-land.\nYou have been told to speak with Sterling Proudfoot, a skilled burglar who likely has much to share about your chosen career.\n* Talk to Sterling Proudfoot"},
{["next"]={2562},area="South Trollshaws",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="Heithur Ironfist believes that you are now very near to recovering the stones that were stolen from his couriers.",mobs={{locations={"33.15S, 20.24W"},name="Rochwen"},{locations={"34.03S, 20.19W"},name="Heithur Ironfist"}},selectoneof={{val="Ironfist's Wall",id="7000113B"},{val="Stone Finder's Gloves (Level 33)",id=70024483},{val="Tirithranc (Level 33)",id=70024482},{val="Ladbeng",id="7000113A"},{val="Ironfist's Javelin",id="700161D8"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2566,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2568},name="The True Thieves",arcs="A Gift from the Dwarves",receive={{val="Lord Glóin's Thanks",id="7000113C"}},level=34,minlevel=29,b="Heithur Ironfist",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRochwen is north of Barachen's camp, on the road that runs through the South Trollshaws.\nHeithur Ironfist has asked you to speak with Rochwen about the stone-trolls of the region so you may retrieve the stones stolen from his couriers.\n* Talk to Rochwen\nObj 2:\nStone-trolls in the South Trollshaws can be found north-east of Rochwen's post.\nRochwen believes that one of the stone-trolls of the South Trollshaws must have taken the stones from the dwarf-couriers, though that is most unusual. She advised you to bring friends with you, for even a single stone-troll is a dangerous opponent.\n* Turn in Unremarkable Stones\nObj 3:\nHeithur Ironfist is at Barachen's camp, south of the road, atop the sloping hill that lies in the shadow of the tall cliffs.\nHeithur Ironfist is waiting for you to return with the stones stolen from Glóin's couriers.\n* Talk to Heithur Ironfist\n* Turn in Unremarkable Stones"},
{["next"]={2722},reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="38s 50c"}},d="The estates East of Tinnudir, within the Twilight Fields, used to belong to families of great wealth and standing within the Northern Kingdom.",selectoneof={{val="Boots of the Oathesworn",id="7002651A"},{val="Lockmaster Boots",id="70025DE4"},{val="Shoes of the Vicious Proclamation",id="700264AB"},{val="Boots of Forgotten Hope",id=70026075},{val="Boots of the Arnorian Holdfast",id="700261A5"},{val="Boots of True Aim",id="700261BF"},{val="Shoes of Long Memory",id="700261E4"},{val="Shoes of the Heartmender",id=70026279},{val="Boots of the Northern Star",id="700260E2"}},category="Evendim",id=2567,scope="n/a",name="The Twilight Estates",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=34,minlevel=29,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrchalwë's journal can be found amongst your possessions.\nOrchalwë's journal details what need be done to reclaim the Fields of Twilight.\n* Read Orchalwë's Journal and reclaim Tham Nambarth\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë's journal can be found amongst your possessions.\nOrchalwë's journal details what need be done to reclaim the Fields of Twilight.\n* Read Orchalwë's Journal and reclaim Tham Varan\nObj 3:\nOrchalwë's journal can be found amongst your possessions.\nOrchalwë's journal details what need be done to reclaim the Fields of Twilight.\n* Read Orchalwë's Journal and reclaim Tham Ornen\nObj 4:\nOrchalwë's journal can be found amongst your possessions.\nOrchalwë's journal details what need be done to reclaim the Fields of Twilight.\n* Read Orchalwës Journal and claim Tham Andalath\nObj 5:\nOrchalwë is at Tinnudir.\nOrchalwë will be eager to get his journal back and discuss your exploits within the Fields of Twilight.\n* Talk to Orchalwë"},
{["next"]={239},area="Northern Emyn Uial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="Longbough believes that some evil power may be twisting the wood to dark ends.",mobs={{locations={"6.09S, 72.02W"},name="Longbough"}},selectoneof={{val="Tribal War Earring",id="700260EB"},{val="Twisted Platinum Earring",id="7002627E"},{val="Curious Ruby Earring",id="700264B1"},{val="Iron Loop of the Hills",id="7002619B"},{val="Crude Onyx Earring",id="70025DE9"},{val="Delicate Ruby Stud",id="700261C6"},{val="Etched Golden Loop",id="700261EB"},{val="Elf-wrought Silver Loop",id="7002607D"},{val="Elegantly Runed Earring",id=70026527}},category="Evendim",id=2568,scope="n/a",prev={2771},name="The Twisted Heart",arcs="Twisted Forest",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=37,minlevel=32,b="Longbough",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLongbough is at the Eavespires, on the north-west shore of Lake Evendim.\nLongbough told you to gather allies to accompany him against the Twisted Heart.\n* Accompany Longbough against the Twisted Heart\nObj 2:\nLongbough is at the Eavespires, on the north-west shore of Lake Evendim.\nYou should speak again with Longbough.\n* Talk to Longbough"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="38s 64c"}},d="Bilbo Baggins has completed his book and would like to make certain that his memory of the important locations and events is correct.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Bilbo Baggins"}},selectoneof={{val="Pathfinder's Javelin",id="700161DF"},{val="Aechathol",id="7000D2D2"},{val="Erugrist",id="7000D2D1"},{val="Pathfinder's Bow",id="7000D2D5"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2569,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1668},name="The Undiscovered Path",arcs="Dim Memories of the Dark",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Bilbo Baggins",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGollum's cave is deep within the tunnels of Goblin-town, beyond the central hall.\nBilbo Baggins provided you with some writing materials and sent you off to find Gollum's cave, with instruction to verify the details of his book regarding the cave.\n* Use Writing Materials\nObj 2:\nBilbo Baggins is in the Hall of Fire in the Last Homely House at Rivendell, south of Goblin-town.\nYou found Gollum's cave in the depths of Goblin-town and discovered the creature's makeshift hut on an island in the lake. Once there, you wrote down what you saw. Now you should return to Bilbo Baggins.\n* Talk to Bilbo Baggins\n* Turn in Writing Materials"},
{["next"]={1526,1972,432,2028,1511},area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+1200 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="3s 60c"}},d="Sharkey's Men and their half-orc allies from the South have blockaded the Vale of Andrath, inhibiting trade with the southern nations.",mobs={{locations={"28.16S, 53.33W"},name="Chief Watcher Grimbriar"}},category="Bree-land",id=2570,scope="n/a",prev={1974},name="The Vale of Andrath",arcs="The Baying of Wolves",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Chief Watcher Grimbriar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe brigand-encampment is at the southern end of the Vale of Andrath, south down the Greenway, far beyond the Greenway Crossing. Grimbriar's men, Watchers Brittleaf and Oakdale, will be hidden somewhere nearby.\nWatcher Grimbriar has learned that Sharkey's Men and their half-orc allies have blockaded the Vale of Andrath. He has asked you to travel south to support his men.\n* Find and speak with Grimbriar's scouts"},
{area="Glain Vraig",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Having assisted the Free Peoples in their battle against the war-host of Angmar, you have earned much respect. The respect you earn entitles you to receive rewards from Quartermaster Ash at Glân Vraig.",category="Ettenmoors",id=2571,scope="n/a",name="The Valourous",receive={{val="Key of Glân Vraig",id="70008ABA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Quartermaster Ash",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nQuartermaster Ash is at Glân Vraig in the Ettenmoors.\nAsh sent you to earn tokens of valour by assisting members of the Free Peoples.\n* Deliver the tokens of valour to Quartermaster Ash\n* Turn in Token of Valour",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Western Malenhad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Malenhad, the vile brimstone swamp of Angmar, is rife with vile and disgusting creatures, but even the strangest of these creatures has its uses to the Hillmen of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"1.78S, 33.29W"},name="Othran"}},selectoneof={{val="Swamp-stone",id="700161CC"},{q="(x3)",val="Pure Milkthistle Draught",id="7000C63C"}},category="Angmar",id=2572,scope="n/a",name="The Value of Vermin",level=43,minlevel=38,b="Othran",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSwamp-lurkers and swamp-flies can be found throughout the swamp near the hunters' camp.\nOthran has asked you to collect Swamp-lurker legs and swamp-fly wings, which his people use to their benefit.\n* Bring the trophies to Othran\n* Turn in Swamp-fly wings\n* Turn in Swamp-lurker legs",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={58},area="Bridgefields",zone="The Shire",d="When Wilimar Bolger woke up this morning, he found a threatening arrow stuck in the door of his home. The arrow's head was of hobbit-make, although very old, while the shaft looked like it was made by Men.",mobs={{locations={"30.95S, 65.81W"},name="Wilimar Bolger"}},category="Shire",id=2573,scope="n/a",name="The Veiled Menace",arcs="The Veiled Menace",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Wilimar Bolger",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe arrow came from the area near the hedge-gate that leads to the Bridgefields, north of Wilimar Bolger's home.\nWilimar Bolger has asked you to search the place where he thinks the arrow came from, in hopes of finding some sign of the person who loosed it and what it might mean.\n* Search north of Wilimar Bolger's home\nObj 2:\nWilimar Bolger can be found near his hole on the north-west side of Budgeford.\nIn the area Wilimar Bolger asked you to search, you found an abandoned campsite and a journal. Perhaps this journal will contain some information helpful to Wilimar. You should take it back to him.\n* Bring the journal to Wilimar Bolger\n* Turn in Torn Journal",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 50c"}},d="Himloc Grouse is certain the Blackwold brigands that have been stealing his crop of pipe-weed will not give up simply because you recovered some of it.",mobs={{locations={"31.03S, 49.28W"},name="Himloc Grouse"}},selectoneof={{val="Pipe-weed Defender",id="70006BEC"},{val="Everdail",id="70006B01"}},category="Bree-land",id=2574,scope="n/a",prev={2079},name="The Vigil",arcs="Defending the Harvest",receive={{val="Earring of the Vigil",id="700069D6"}},level=14,c={"* The Vance Waithman and thieves are at [30.5S, 47.6W]"},minlevel=10,b="Himloc Grouse",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHimloc Grouse's pipe-weed field is on the hill above Eldo Swatmidge's home, east of Staddle.\nHimloc is sure the Blackwold brigands will keep stealing from his pipe-weed crop unless you can defeat them as they try. Himloc thinks that you can handle these thieves by yourself and advised that you look for them in his field, but be wary of the leader.\n* Defeat Blackwold thieves\n* Defeat Vance Waithman\nObj 2:\nHimloc Grouse is in the town square of Staddle.\nHimloc will be pleased to hear that you have prevented the Blackwolds from stealing more of his pipe-weed.\n* Talk to Himloc Grouse in Staddle"},
{["next"]={2808,1872},area="The Marish",zone="The Shire",d="Mat Harfoot told you that one of the members of his \\qVigilance Committee\\q, Violet Underhill, has gone missing.",mobs={{locations={"32.01S, 63.80W"},name="Mat Harfoot"},{locations={"34.34S, 64.44W"},name="Farmer Maggot"}},category="Shire",id=2575,scope="n/a",name="The Vigilance Committee",arcs="The Vigilance Committee",level=9,minlevel=5,b="Mat Harfoot",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBamfurlong, Maggot's farm, is south along the river road, in the Marish.\nMat Harfoot has asked you to look for Violet Underhill and suggested you speak first with old Farmer Maggot.\n* Talk to Farmer Maggot",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Sixteenth Hall is an area overrun with Orcs, many of whom suffer from a terrible illness that sweeps through this area. Shamans tend to the ill whilst the rest of the halls are defended by those that remain able to do battle.\nMallas, an Elf ally to the dwarves, believes that there is something secret beneath the Sixteenth Hall and wishes to learn the true purpose and source of the plague.",mobs={{locations={"13.16S, 101.22W"},name="Ymar"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2576,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Vile Infected",arcs="Peasant Halls",level=60,minlevel=58,b="Ymar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCrawlers can be found in the Sixteenth Hall, north-east of the Shadowed Refuge.\nYmar seems to be affected differently than all the others who keep watch at the Shadowed Refuge. He is haunted by visions of crawlers, and wishes you kill them while you are in the Sixteenth Hall.\n* Defeat crawlers (50)\nObj 2:\nYmar is at the Shadowed Refuge, south-west of the Sixteenth Hall.\nYou have slain many, many vile crawlers and should inform Ymar that the nightmarish threat has passed.\n* Return to Ymar at the Shadowed Refuge"},
{area="Caras Galadhon",zone="Lothlórien",reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Bruicheron is hopeful that her beloved friend Belvagor will leave the Orc-fighting to others and instead share a relaxing visit with her.",mobs={{locations={"18.31S, 64.08W"},name="Glasnír"},{locations={"16.11S, 67.03W"},name="Belvagor"},{locations={"15.74S, 67.17W"},name="Bruicheron"}},category="Lothlórien",id=2577,scope="n/a",name="The Vintage of War",receive={{val="Lothlórien Gold Leaf",id="70018E33"}},level=60,c={"* Glasnír can be found just outside the Vinyards of Lórien [18.3S, 64.1W]\n* Belvagor can be found just after you zone in Caras Galadhon [16.1S, 67.0W]"},minlevel=55,b="Bruicheron",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe vintner Glasnír is outside the Vinyards of Lórien, south-east of Caras Galadhon.\nBruicheron has asked you to retrieve a special vintage of wine from the vintner and to bring it to her beloved Belvagor, with the request that he join her for a relaxing day.\n* Talk to Glasnír at the Vinyards of Lórien\nObj 2:\nBelvagor is guarding the gates of Caras Galadhon.\nGlasnír has given you the special vintage of wine requested by Bruicheron, and now you should deliver it to Belvagor.\n* Talk to Belvagor\n* Turn in Special Vintage\nObj 3:\nBruicheron is on Telain Glorelloth, in Caras Galadhon.\nBelvagor has decided his duty requires him to remain on guard against the Orcs for the moment, and he regretfully cannot yet join Bruicheron for a day of relaxation. You should return to Bruicheron with the tidings.\n* Talk to Bruicheron\n* Turn in Special Vintage",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+500 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Arohir of Esteldín has bade you seek the camp of Tinnudir along the eastern shore of Lake Evendim, and once there to speak with Cannuion.",mobs={{locations={"9.63S, 41.42W"},name="Arohir"}},category="Reputation",id=2578,scope="n/a",name="The Wardens of Annúminas",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Arohir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nCannuion is at the Ranger-camp at Tinnudir, in Evendim, to the west of the North Downs.\nArohir has sent you to speak with Cannuion in Evendim.\n* Talk to Cannuion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Green Hill Country",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Orthir, the Elf encamped above Woodhall, revealed that the large wolf was, in fact, one of the great and evil Wargs of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"33.41S, 66.09W"},name="Orthir"},{locations={"31.45S, 65.61W"},name="Linda Bolger"}},selectoneof={{val="Laugfût's Fall",id="700033C9"},{val="Laugfût's Bane",id="700033C7"},{val="Shirriff's Leggings",id="700033C8"}},category="Shire",id=2579,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2549},name="The Warg of Budgeford",arcs="New Neighbours",receive={{val="Gift Mathom",id="7000D6C2"}},level=11,minlevel=7,b="Orthir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLaugfût can be found among the wolf-pack in the ruins east of Budgeford, beyond Milo and Linda Bolger's farm.\nLinda Bolger sent you to show the collar to the Elves at Woodhall. Orthir revealed the identity of the mysterious wolf -- Laugfût, a Warg of Angmar -- and asked you to confront and slay the Warg-chieftain.\n* Kill 1 Laugfût\nObj 2:\nLinda Bolger is in Budgeford, on the road furthest down the hill.\nOrthir told you to speak with Linda Bolger after you had slain Laugfût. Linda will be pleased to know that the threat of the Warg has been removed.\n* Talk to Linda Bolger"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="44s 24c"}},d="The Grand Stair once stood at the foot of a great crossroads within Moria. At the height of the great city, it led to all areas of the halls and was a majestic wonder to behold. Now it has fallen to the care of Igash, a lieutenant of the Moria Orc-leader Mazog. Igash assembled the forces of Orcs and trolls within Moria in one place and has collected tribute from each to one day bring to the leader of the Orcs. For now, each tribe vies for favour from the lieutenant, a fanatical follower of Mazog.",mobs={{locations={"10.99S, 106.77W"},name="Thithrand"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2580,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="The Warg-riders",arcs="The Grand Stair",receive={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Legend",id="7001F259"}},level=58,minlevel=57,b="Thithrand",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThithrand is at the Orc-watch.\nThithrand is responsible for guarding against the threat posed by the Warg-riders within the Grand Stair. You should assist him by completing his tasks.\n* Help Thithrand defeat the Leader of the Warg-riders\n* Help Thithrand thin the number of Warg-riders within the Grand Stair\nObj 2:\nThithrand is at the Orc-watch, south-west of the Grand Stair.\nYou should return to Thithrand and tell him that each of his tasks involving the Warg-riders are complete.\n* Talk to Thithrand at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Dol Guldur",zone="Mirkwood",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Sâd-en-Dagor, the training-grounds of Dol Guldur, are overseen by three champions of the Lieutenant of Dol Guldur.",mobs={{locations={"16.02S, 44.47W"},name="Torist"}},category="Dungeons of Dol Guldur",id=2581,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="The Warriors of Dol Guldur",receive={{val="Malledhrim Gold Star Emblem",id="7001F098"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Torist",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nUrcheron, Carchrien, and Durkâr in Sâd-en-Dagor in Dol Guldur, north-east of Helethir.\nTorist has asked you to slay Urcheron, Carchrien, and Durkâr, three champions of Dol Guldur.\n* Defeat Urcheron\n* Defeat Carchrien\n* Defeat Durkâr\nObj 2:\nTorist is at Helethir, south-west from Dol Guldur.\nYou should return to Torist for your reward.\n* Talk to Torist at Helethir"},
{area="The Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",d="Many Minstrels wish to become Watchers of Resolve, but not all can accomplish their goals alone.",mobs={{locations={"13.45S, 100.36W"},name="Bassela"}},category="Minstrel",id=2582,scope="n/a",name="The Watcher of Resolve:  Lending a Hand",receive={{val="Mark of Victory (Level 1)",id=70018341}},level=58,minlevel=58,b="Bassela",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe Skûmfil is east from the Foundations of Stone.\nBassela has instructed you to help a fellow Minstrel complete his or her final task in Skûmfil.\n* Defeat Cracktooth\nObj 2:\nBassela is just outside Skûmfil, east of the Shadowed Refuge in the Foundations of Stone.\nWith Cracktooth slain, you should return to Bassela with news of your success.\n* Talk to Bassela",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Moria",area="Durin's Way",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Haldir of Lórien has sent you to the aid of Hrólfur in Moria, a deed that may in turn provide some security for the Elves. Hrólfur and Haldir hope to see the legendary water-wheels of Nalâ-dûm functioning as they did long ago, in Durin's Day.",mobs={{locations={"5.16S, 111.96W"},name="Hrólfur"}},category="Dungeons of Lothlórien",id=2583,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",name="The Water-wheels: To Stagnant Nalâ-dûm",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Lothlórien Silver Branch",id="70018E34"}},level=60,minlevel=55,b="Hrólfur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nNalâ-dûm is south of the Chamber of the Crossroads, in the Water-works.\nHrólfur wishes for you to investigate the ancient waterway of Nalâ-dûm and recover any lost information about the water-wheels that once fueled Moria of old.\n* Use Lock-box\nObj 2:\nHrólfur is in the Chamber of the Crossroads, in Durin's Way.\nYou should bring the ancient records you found to Hrólfur, who will be excited to find a ledger of records of the lore that was lost when Moria fell.\n* Talk to Hrólfur\n* Turn in Water-works Records",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1897},reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="The rulers of the great city of Annuminas are buried within the Way of Kings.",category="Evendim",id=2584,scope="n/a",prev={2433},name="The Way of Kings",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Nimbellas",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Rangers at the camp within the Way of Kings need help scouting the surrounding area.\n* Aid Maladan with Gateways to the Past\n* Aid Nethrandir with Plunderers of History\n* Aid Rodlam with Foulness from the Deep\n* Aid Maladan with Keys to the Crypts\n* Aid Nimbellas with Eastern Gate to Annuminas\nObj 2:\nNimbellas will be pleased to hear the Way of Kings has been thoroughly scouted.\n* Talk to Nimbellas",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+900 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="48s 30c"}},d="Ilmo was grateful for your assistance against the peikko, but troubles seem ever ready to assail him.",mobs={{locations={"19.42N, 70.22W"},name="Ilmo"}},selectoneof={{val="Thick Elk-Hide Vest",id="7000E5B1"},{val="Thick Elk-Hide Breastplate",id="7000E5A6"},{val="Thick Elk-Hide Jacket",id="7000E5B3"}},category="Forochel",id=2585,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={1715},name="The Wayward Bull",arcs="Herding Elk",level=48,c={"* The Wayward Bull can be found in Jä-rannit at [20.5, 72.4W]"},minlevel=43,b="Ilmo",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe wayward bull may be nearby, among the mountains north of Sûri-kylä and Ilmo's camp.\nIlmo fears that his prize bull has been taken by the peikko and has asked you to search for him.\n* Find the wayward bull\nObj 2:\nIlmo is outside of Sûri-kylä, north from its gates.\nYou should return to Ilmo and let him know that his bull has been returned safely.\n* Talk to Ilmo"},
{area="Meluinen",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="16s"}},d="Lagorlam, a member of the company of Elves who came north with Gildor Inglorion, entered Taur Gonwaith, seeking vengeance against the trolls who attacked Lin Giliath. He has not returned, which concerns Thaliollang.",mobs={{locations={"13.72S, 44.55W"},name="Thaliollang"}},category="North Downs",id=2586,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1905},name="The Wayward Companion",arcs="Avenging Lachenn",level=28,minlevel=23,b="Thaliollang",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLagorlam has gone to the forest of Taur Gonwaith, south-east of Lin Giliath.\nThaliollang has sent you to find Lagorlam and make certain he is well.\n* Search for Lagorlam in Taur Gonwaith"},
{["next"]={2441},area="Tâl Bruinen",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Wistan told you of the white hart he tracked through many lands and believes that he finally brought it down, though he could not find the body.",mobs={{locations={"36.91S, 14.21W"},name="Wistan"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2587,scope="n/a",name="The White Hart",arcs="The Creeping Shadow",level=40,pois={{locations={"37.53S, 15.99W"},name="White Hart Corpse"}},minlevel=35,b="Wistan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWistan thinks the body must be somewhere to the west of Echad Candelleth, between the dwelling-places of the Gauredain and Wood-trolls.\nWistan has asked you to search for the body of the white hart he tracked across the Trollshaws and return to Echad Candelleth with both it and the arrows with which he brought it down.\n* Use White Hart Corpse\nObj 2:\nWistan is at his campfire at Echad Candelleth, the Elf-camp to the east, in Tâl Bruinen.\nYou found the body of the white hart and recovered Wistan's arrows, but someone seems to have found the body first and removed most of the meat. You should return the arrows to Wistan and tell him what you discovered.\n* Talk to Wistan\n* Turn in Handful of Arrows",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+1200 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Having finally found an entrance to the court of the Wild Huntsman, you have come upon a number of powerful spirits -- some of whom look upon you with disdain. Now you must prove yourself before them if you are to find a way through the haunted forests of the Mournshaws for the Grey Company.",mobs={{locations={"72.77S, 24.29W"},name="The Huntsman"},{locations={"72.80S, 23.88W"},name="Lavaneth"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2588,scope="n/a",name="The Wild Hunt",receive={{val="Golden Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7E"}},level=65,c={"* A hidden entrance, covered by trees across the river at [72.8S, 24.0W]\n* The portal close to Tûm at [69.2S, 22.3W]"},minlevel=60,b="Lavaneth",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Wild Huntsman resides in the Huntsman's Hall.\nYou have been instructed to approach the Huntsman and ask that the Grey Company be allowed to pass through the southern Mournshaws into Dunland.\n* Talk to the Wild Huntsman in the Huntsman's Hall\nObj 2:\nThe servants of the Wild Huntsman are in the Huntsman's Hall.\nThe Huntsman has bidden you complete the tasks that the his hand-maidens set before you.\n* Hunt Munfaeril's spirit\n* Hunt Gwenaewen's spirit\n* Hunt Lavaneth's spirit\nObj 3:\nArassiel is at the Huntsman's Hall.\nOne last spirit remains to be challenged. You should speak with Arassiel and hunt as she bids you.\n* Hunt Arassiel's spirit\nObj 4:\nThe Wild Huntsman is at the Huntsman's Hall.\nHaving completed the Wild Hunt, you should return and speak with the Huntsman on behalf of the Dúnedain.\n* Talk to the Wild Huntsman in the Huntsman's Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Arassiel has sent you forth to challenge the last of the spirits of the Wild Hunt in a test of wisdom.",mobs={{locations={"67.61S, 21.94W","72.79S, 24.26W"},name="Arassiel"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2589,scope="n/a",name="The Wild Hunt: Arassiel's Spirit",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Arassiel",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe stag-spirit of Arassiel dwells in the southern reaches of the Mournshaws.\nArassiel has charged you with challenging her stag-spirit servant.\n* Challenge Arassiel's spirit\nObj 2:\nArassiel is in the Huntsman's Hall.\nYou should return to Arassiel with news of your success.\n* Talk to Arassiel at the Huntsman's Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Gwenaewen has bidden you challenge an ancient spirit as a test of quickness in the Wild Hunt that the Huntsman has set before you.",mobs={{locations={"72.84S, 23.99W"},name="Gwenaewen"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2590,scope="n/a",name="The Wild Hunt: Gwenaewen's Spirit",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Gwenaewen",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGwenaewen's spirit dwells in the heart of the Mournshaws.\nGwenaewen has charged you with hunting her falcon-spirit servant.\n* Challenge Gwenaewen's spirit\nObj 2:\nGwenaewen is at the Huntsman's Hall.\nYou should return to Gwenaewen and tell her that you have overcome her challenge.\n* Talk to Gwenaewen at the Huntsman's Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Wild Huntsman has tasked you with hunting the spirit servants of his hand-maidens.",mobs={{locations={"72.80S, 23.88W"},name="Lavaneth"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2591,scope="n/a",name="The Wild Hunt: Lavaneth's Spirit",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lavaneth",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nLavaneth's spirit roams in the north-west eaves of the Mournshaws.\nLavaneth has bidden you hunt her boar-spirit.\n* Challenge Lavaneth's spirit\nObj 2:\nLavaneth is at the Huntsman's Hall.\nYou should return to Lavaneth and tell her of your successful challenge against the boar-spirit.\n* Talk to Lavaneth at the Huntsman's Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mournshaws",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+700 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Munfaeril has bidden you challenge an ancient spirit as a test of endurance in the Wild Hunt that the Huntsman has set before you.",mobs={{locations={"72.67S, 24.04W"},name="Munfaeril"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2592,scope="n/a",name="The Wild Hunt: Munfaeril's Spirit",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Munfaeril",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ox-spirit dwells beneath the north-east eaves of the Mournshaws.\nMunfaeril has bidden you challenge her ox-spirit servant.\n* Challenge Munfaeril's Spirit\nObj 2:\nMunfaeril is at the Huntsman's Hall.\nYou should return to Munfaeril and tell her of your success in the challenge of endurance.\n* Talk to Munfaeril at the Huntsman's Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="Your skill as a metalsmith has improved, but you still have much to learn.",mobs={{locations={"22.92S, 67.58W"},name="Cotman Gamgee"},{locations={"28.49S, 6.24W"},name="Dringlinn"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Bill Digweed"},{locations={"31.79S, 69.37W"},name="Uffo Bracegirdle"},{locations={"11.94S, 67.84W"},name="Sadie Marshbanks"},{locations={"34.66S, 75.43W"},name="Cotman Brown"},{locations={"17.94S, 53.80W"},name="Adeline Wragg"},{locations={"9.70S, 40.50W"},name="Roddan"},{locations={"33.82S, 62.16W"},name="Mosco Bracegirdle"},{locations={"28.32S, 92.74W"},name="Anorthint"},{locations={"27.48S, 68.31W"},name="Moro Brockhouse"},{locations={"7.50S, 64.09W"},name="Fina Swarbrick"},{locations={"20.14S, 97.00W"},name="Harthgríp"},{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Gestur"},{locations={"31.24S, 66.16W"},name="Isengar Bolger"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Tom Thornwell"}},category="Crafting",id=2593,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Will of the Iron, Part I",level=10,minlevel=6,b="Ekkill",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGlasi Ironhand is by the forges within Thorin's Hall, in Ered Luin.\nYou have been told to speak with Glasi Ironhand in Thorin's Hall, for he is a metalsmith of great skill and can further your training in the art.\n* Talk to Glasi Ironhand",traits={{val="Apprentice Metalsmith Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="You have achieved great progress in the art of metalworking, but you have not yet matched your potential.",mobs={{locations={"22.92S, 67.58W"},name="Cotman Gamgee"},{locations={"28.49S, 6.24W"},name="Dringlinn"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Bill Digweed"},{locations={"31.79S, 69.37W"},name="Uffo Bracegirdle"},{locations={"11.94S, 67.84W"},name="Sadie Marshbanks"},{locations={"34.66S, 75.43W"},name="Cotman Brown"},{locations={"17.94S, 53.80W"},name="Adeline Wragg"},{locations={"9.70S, 40.50W"},name="Roddan"},{locations={"33.82S, 62.16W"},name="Mosco Bracegirdle"},{locations={"28.32S, 92.74W"},name="Anorthint"},{locations={"27.48S, 68.31W"},name="Moro Brockhouse"},{locations={"7.50S, 64.09W"},name="Fina Swarbrick"},{locations={"20.14S, 97.00W"},name="Harthgríp"},{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Gestur"},{locations={"31.24S, 66.16W"},name="Isengar Bolger"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Tom Thornwell"}},category="Crafting",id=2594,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Will of the Iron, Part II",receive={{val="Featherweight Shield",id=70003689}},level=26,c={"* The Ancient Emblem drops from the Shades in the Fields of Fornost in North Downs"},minlevel=21,b="Ekkill",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGlasi Ironhand is at the forges inside Thorin's Hall, in Ered Luin.\nA Novice Metalworker suggested you return to Glasi Ironhand to further your training.\n* Talk to Glasi Ironhand\nObj 2:\nGlasi Ironhand is at the forges inside Thorin's Halls, in Ered Luin.\nGlasi has asked you to fashion a Featherweight Shield for him to examine and has given you the appropriate recipe. The dwarf also included his notes on the process.\n* Turn in Iron Chain Link\n* Turn in Steel Brace\n* Turn in Iron Band\n* Turn in Ancient Emblem\nObj 3:\nGlasi Ironhand is at the forges inside Thorin's Hall, in Ered Luin.\nGlasi has asked you to fashion a Featherweight Shield for him to examine and has given you the appropriate recipe to make one. The dwarf also included his notes on the process.\n* Bring the Featherweight Shield to Glasi Ironhand\n* Turn in Featherweight Shield",traits={{val="Journeyman Metalsmith Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={245,2644},area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",d="You bend metal to your will and command it to defend those who need defending, but still you have not mastered the art.",mobs={{locations={"7.10S, 45.11W"},name="Ottar"},{locations={"22.92S, 67.58W"},name="Cotman Gamgee"},{locations={"28.49S, 6.24W"},name="Dringlinn"},{locations={"28.76S, 48.60W"},name="Bill Digweed"},{locations={"31.79S, 69.37W"},name="Uffo Bracegirdle"},{locations={"11.94S, 67.84W"},name="Sadie Marshbanks"},{locations={"34.66S, 75.43W"},name="Cotman Brown"},{locations={"17.94S, 53.80W"},name="Adeline Wragg"},{locations={"9.70S, 40.50W"},name="Roddan"},{locations={"33.82S, 62.16W"},name="Mosco Bracegirdle"},{locations={"28.32S, 92.74W"},name="Anorthint"},{locations={"27.48S, 68.31W"},name="Moro Brockhouse"},{locations={"7.50S, 64.09W"},name="Fina Swarbrick"},{locations={"20.14S, 97.00W"},name="Harthgríp"},{locations={"15.08S, 103.54W"},name="Gestur"},{locations={"31.24S, 66.16W"},name="Isengar Bolger"},{locations={"30.52S, 50.99W","64.68N, 132.59W"},name="Tom Thornwell"}},category="Crafting",id=2595,scope="Crafting Advancement",name="The Will of the Iron, Part III",level=30,minlevel=25,b="Ekkill",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nOttar is in the mining-town of Othrikar, in the North Downs.\nA Novice Metalsmith asked you to speak with Ottar about learning his metalsmithing techniques and acquiring a superior place at which you can work.\n* Talk to Ottar",traits={{val="Expert Metalsmith Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",d="Your ability to bend and shape metals to your will astounds those who have not also toiled by the heat of the flames.",mobs={{locations={"14.54S, 51.07W"},name="Braigelen"},{locations={"5.42S, 104.94W"},name="Gamli"},{locations={"15.49S, 67.70W"},name="Roddaneth"},{locations={"31.43S, 29.74W"},name="Alfbald"},{locations={"18.56S, 63.74W"},name="Tincbrennil"},{locations={"12.79S, 14.84W","38.06S, 12.99W","30.71S, 6.19W","14.35S, 51.55W","5.19S, 112.08W","41.27S, 15.24W","13.49S, 58.09W","7.22S, 66.22W","117.69S, 128.90W","28.08S, 23.42W","27.46S, 1.60E","32.00S, 55.14W","117.99S, 41.21W","22.40S, 52.58W","13.93S, 103.22W","61.95S, 16.26W","87.98S, 144.01W","17.29S, 61.64W","68.83S, 31.83W","97.49S, 143.98W","27.47S, 1.60E","119.45S, 35.81W","84.70S, 15.79W","72.10S, 16.13W"},name="LinkFrost"},{locations={"31.53S, 15.21W"},name="Birrungur Blacksteel"},{locations={"32.24S, 2.10W"},name="Ruineth"}},category="Crafting",id=2596,scope="Crafting Advancement",prev={245,2643},name="The Will of the Iron, Part IV",receive={{val="Steadfast Helm (Level 49)",id="7000F220"}},level=40,minlevel=35,b="Molda",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nBirrungur Blacksteel, the master metalsmith, is at Thorenhad, the camp of the sons of Elrond in the Trollshaws.\nYou have been told to speak with Birrungur Blacksteel if you wish to develop even greater techniques of metalsmithing.\n* Talk to Birrungur Blacksteel in the Trollshaws\nObj 2:\nBirrungur Blacksteel gave you his notes on the creation of a Steadfast Helm.\nBirrungur has asked you to fashion a Steadfast Helm for him to judge.\n* Turn in Westernesse Steel Ingot\n* Turn in Westernesse Scale\n* Turn in Ancient Crown\nObj 3:\nBirringur Blacksteel is at Thorenhad, the camp of the sons of Elrond, in the Trollshaws.\nBirringur Blacksteel is waiting for you to fashion a Steadfast Helm so he can judge its quality.\n* Bring the Steadfast Helm to Birrungur Blacksteel\n* Turn in Steadfast Helm",traits={{val="Artisan Metalsmith Proficiency"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Twenty-first Hall",zone="Moria",d="Wárr is most likely anxious for news of the rest of the dwarves from the expedition. A natural passage, great and winding, connects the Twenty-first Hall with the Chamber of the Crossroads.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2597,scope="n/a",prev={1948},name="The Winding Way",arcs="Líkmund's Tasks",level=51,minlevel=46,b="Líkmund",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWárr is in the Chamber of Mazarbul, just north of the Twenty-first Hall, far to the east of the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nYou must travel east from the Chamber of the Crossroads through the great winding road leading to the Twenty-first Hall.\n* Find The Twenty-first Hall: West Arch\nObj 2:\nWárr is in the Chamber of Mazarbul, north of the Twenty-first Hall, far to the east of the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nLíkmund has asked you to speak with Wárr and relay what you know of recent events from the Chamber of the Crossroads.\n* Talk to Wárr",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={633,1736},area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+500 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Himbar is haunted by the merrevail and their kindred, the bats. These creatures prey upon the Rangers of Gath Forthnír, showing no mercy.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Thoriel"}},category="Angmar",id=2598,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2884},name="The Winged Host",arcs="Winged Host",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Thoriel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe merrevail and the bats hunt throughout Himbar, the lands west of Gath Forthnír.\nThoriel warned you of the merrevail, winged monsters in service to the Enemy. They prey upon the Rangers and must be destroyed, along with their lesser kindred, the bats.\n* Defeat merrevail in Himbar (15)\n* Defeat bats in Himbar\nObj 2:\nThoriel waits for you in Gath Forthnír, the hidden Ranger camp east of Himbar.\nYou defeated the winged servants of the Enemy and may now return to claim victory.\n* Talk to Thoriel"},
{["next"]={98},area="Archet",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="The mysteries of the past lie open to you, but still you seek to uncover more, never resting in your pursuit of knowledge.",mobs={{locations={"13.76S, 44.82W"},name="Glambaen"},{locations={"19.04N, 72.23W"},name="Sana"},{locations={"15.26S, 101.58W"},name="Pennastan"},{locations={"52.54S, 16.81W"},name="Handelleth"},{locations={"20.13S, 97.03W"},name="Ráthorm"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Barton Tanner"},{locations={"12.70S, 67.29W"},name="Celairen"},{locations={"9.58S, 41.06W"},name="Gwalothir"},{locations={"15.31S, 101.59W"},name="Isdi"},{locations={"29.63S, 3.44W"},name="Elwen"},{locations={"30.40S, 51.71W","64.80N, 133.31W","30.47S, 51.65W","64.73N, 133.25W"},name="Dalton Willow"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Shepherd Snowden"},{locations={"28.27S, 92.28W"},name="Athradir"},{locations={"25.31S, 48.66W"},name="Cuthbert Rook"}},category="Lore-master",id=2599,scope="n/a",prev={213,103},requiredclasses="Lore-master",name="The Wisest Way is Contemplation",arcs="The Wisest Way",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Cuthbert Rook",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nIsdi is at the ruins of Edhelion, on the slopes above Thorin's Hall, in Ered Luin.\nYou have been told to speak with the lore-master Isdi, for she may have some wise words to share with you.\n* Talk to Isdi"},
{["next"]={939},area="Staddle",zone="Bree-land",d="Lily Underhill is concerned about the report you brought her from Longo Daegmund.",mobs={{locations={"30.98S, 47.80W"},name="Lily Underhill"},{locations={"32.30S, 47.44W"},name="Willowsong"}},category="Bree-land",id=2600,scope="n/a",prev={2789},name="The Wise Woman",arcs="Poisoned Well",level=12,minlevel=8,b="Lily Underhill",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Staddle Town Well is in Staddle town centre. To find the Silverwater Spring, take the road east from the town square to the Widow Froghorn's farm, then south to Constable Bolger's house. The Silverwater Spring is south-east of there.\nDraw a bucket of water from the well and bring it to Willowsong.\n* Draw water from the  Staddle town well\nObj 2:\nWillowsong is at Silverwater Spring.\nYou drew a bucket of water from the Staddle town well and brought it to Willowsong.\n* Bring the bucket of poisoned water to Willowsong",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Delving Fields",zone="The Shire",money={{val="90c"}},d="Dora Brownlock thinks an admirer of hers has gone to try and kill the exiled leader of the wolves near Waymeet.",mobs={{locations={"32.81S, 72.94W"},name="Dora Brownlock"}},selectoneof={{val="Brownlock's Spear (Level 7)",id="70021DF2"},{val="Brownlock's Blade",id="700032C4"},{val="Jolly's Defender",id="700032C5"}},category="Shire",id=2601,scope="n/a",prev={3253},name="The Wolf in Exile",arcs="Worries from Waymeet",level=8,minlevel=4,b="Dora Brownlock",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nJolly Smallburrow may be after the wolf that was seen across the road from the wolf-den, north of Dora Brownlock's farm.\nDora Brownlock is worried that her neighbour, Jolly Smallburrow, may be in trouble and has asked you to find him.\n* Find Jolly Smallburrow\nObj 2:\nDora Brownlock is at the centre of Waymeet.\nDora will be pleased to know that you have rescued Jolly Smallburrow and defeated the scarred leader of the wolves that have been harassing her farm and town.\n* Talk to Dora Brownlock"},
{area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="You defeated many wolf-keepers at Barad Morlas, but Dornhador still has one more task for you.",mobs={{locations={"46.95S, 12.47W"},name="Dornhador"}},selectoneof={{val="Dornhador's Helm",id="7001607B"},{val="Nûkhud's Ruin",id="700160FA"}},category="Eregion",id=2602,scope="n/a",prev={2424},name="The Wolves' Master",arcs="Wolf-keepers of Barad Morlas",level=50,c={"* Barad Morlas is at [48.1S, 13.7W]"},minlevel=45,b="Dornhador",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNûkhud, Wolf-master is at Barad Morlas, south-west of Echad Eregion.\nDornhador has asked you to find and defeat Nûkhud, Wolf-master, the leader of the wolf-keepers at Barad Morlas.\n* Defeat Nûkhud, Wolf-master\nObj 2:\nDornhador is at Echad Eregion, north-east of Barad Morlas.\nYou should return to Dornhador with tidings of Nûkhud's downfall.\n* Talk to Dornhador at Echad Eregion"},
{["next"]={1531},area="Buckland",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="The wood-cutter has sprained his ankle and is unable to finish his chores for the day. He swears that the Old Forest intentionally tripped him.",mobs={{locations={"32.81S, 61.57W"},name="Toly Brockhouse"}},category="Bree-land",id=2603,scope="n/a",name="The Wood-cutter's Tale",arcs="The Wood-cutter's Tale",level=15,pois={{locations={"31.71S, 59.07W","31.70S, 59.07W"},name="Tapped Maple"},{locations={"32.91S, 60.01W"},name="Wood-pile"}},minlevel=11,b="Toly Brockhouse",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe mushrooms can be found in the western part of Old Forest, between the Bonfire Glade and Bald Hill. The wood can be collected from the wood-cutter's seasoning pile east of the Bonfire Glade and a little south. The sap can be collected from the old maple growing on Bald Hill, east of the Bonfire Glade.\nBecause Toly Brockhouse, the wood-cutter, has sprained his ankle, he has asked you to gather mushrooms, wood, and maple sap for him.\n* Use Wood-pile\n* Turn in Savoury Mushroom\n* Use Tapped Maple\n* Turn in Empty Bucket\nObj 2:\nDeliver the sap, wood and mushrooms to Toly Brockhouse near the stables outside of Brandy Hall.\nThe Old Forest surrendered its bounty to you, now you must return to Toly Brockhouse.\n* Talk to Toly Brockhouse\n* Turn in Bucket of Sap\n* Turn in Savoury Mushroom\n* Turn in Seasoned Lumber",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1443},zone="Bree-land",area="Bree",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Rune-keepers are masters of the written word, and the words of healing captured in runic form are especially powerful and useful in a dangerous world.",mobs={{locations={"15.07S, 103.23W"},name="Dourhand"},{locations={"15.32S, 101.57W"},name="Lennasthrieln"},{locations={"30.40S, 51.71W","64.80N, 133.31W","30.47S, 51.65W","64.73N, 133.25W"},name="Biarn"},{locations={"18.86N, 71.50W"},name="Ciryalen"},{locations={"29.69S, 3.47W"},name="Cerebthos"},{locations={"7.11S, 44.96W"},name="Huldar"},{locations={"12.70S, 67.28W"},name="Selarfrin"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Gerenr"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Teithadir"},{locations={"28.24S, 92.25W"},name="Althrendir"},{locations={"20.14S, 97.05W"},name="Relorimel"},{locations={"9.56S, 41.51W"},name="Merenas"}},selectoneof={{val="Stone of a Healer",id=70018577},{val="Hat of a Healer",id=70018576}},category="Rune-keeper",id=2604,scope="n/a",prev={257},requiredclasses="Rune-keeper",name="The Word of a Healer",receive={{q="(x5)",val="Greater Celebrant Salve",id=70000856}},level=30,minlevel=30,b="Biarn",repeatable="No",traits={{val="Writ of Well-being"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Rune-keeper Huldar is at Othrikar, in the North Downs.\nYou have been told that the dwarf Huldar may be able to teach you about beneficial runes of healing.\n* Talk to Huldar\nObj 2:\nHuldar is at Othrikar, in the North Downs.\nThe dwarf Huldar has agreed to teach you what he knows about runes of healing if you help repel an attack by the Dourhands.\n* Talk to Huldar and assist in the defence of Othrikar\nObj 3:\nHuldar is at Othrikar, in the North Downs.\nYou were of great assistance to the dwarves of Othrikar during the Dourhand attack and should speak now to Huldar as was agreed.\n* Talk to Huldar at Othrikar"},
{area="Western Malenhad",zone="Angmar",d="Machan the hunter has gone missing after vowing to return with hides from the fearsome worms of Malenhad.",mobs={{locations={"1.78S, 33.30W"},name="Murdaigán"}},category="Angmar",id=2605,scope="n/a",prev={3262},name="The Worm-hunter",level=43,minlevel=38,b="Murdaigán",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMachan the hunter should be somewhere in the region of Sálgaitë to the south-east.\nThe hunter Murdaigán has asked you to locate Machan, who was hunting fire-worms in Malenhad.\n* Find the hunter Machan",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Bruinen Source North",zone="The Misty Mountains",d="Sigrun told you of Ormulf Worm-hunter, a dwarf at Othrikar renowned for his brave deeds against the worms and drakes that stalk the crevices of the North Downs.",mobs={{locations={"19.13S, 2.90W"},name="Sigrun"},{locations={"7.21S, 45.00W"},name="Ormulf Worm-hunter"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2606,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={1164},name="The Worm-hunter's Lament",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Sigrun",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrmulf Worm-hunter is at Othrikar, far to the west in the north-central North Downs.\nSigrun has seen from afar that the keep of Helegrod appears to be crawling with worms and drakes and has asked you to consult with Ormulf Worm-hunter about what must be done.\n* Talk to Ormulf Worm-hunter",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={733},area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The egg-stealing half-orcs are being overseen by a particularly vicious creature named Arzgât.\nCalelloth has asked you to head out to the northern hillside of Carchres and slay Arzgât.",mobs={{locations={"39.79S, 16.32W"},name="Calelloth"}},selectoneof={{val="Calelloth's Gift",id="700163B5"},{val="Arzgât's Folly",id=70016090}},category="Eregion",id=2607,scope="n/a",prev={774},name="The Worm-keeper",arcs="An Army of Worms",level=49,c={"* Arzgât is in Carchres [42.2S, 9.4W]"},minlevel=44,b="Calelloth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nArzgât dwells near a small range of mountains, on the hillside of Carchres south of the road to Rivendell, east of Gwingris.\nCalelloth has instructed you to go forth and defeat the half-orc Arzgât.\n* Bring the note to Calelloth at Gwingris\n* Turn in Note to the Worm-keeper"},
{area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The worm Brunanc and his spawn terrorize the paths leading from Rivendell to Gwingris.",mobs={{locations={"39.99S, 16.26W"},name="Daegennan"}},selectoneof={{val="Daegennan's Armour",id=70016073},{val="Brunanc's Demise",id=70016114}},category="Eregion",id=2608,scope="n/a",prev={2498},name="The Worm-sire",arcs="The Path from Rivendell",level=49,c={"* Brunanc is found at Carchres [42.2S, 9.3W]"},pois={{locations={"42.43S, 9.36W","41.93S, 9.73W","42.23S, 9.26W","42.28S, 9.73W","42.19S, 9.39W","42.32S, 9.70W"},name="Worm Egg"}},minlevel=44,b="Daegennan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe worm-eggs belonging to the spawn of Brunanc lie upon the hillsides south-east of Gwingris.\nDaegennan has asked you to destroy the eggs of the worms to draw forth their leader, Brunanc.\n* Defeat Brunanc\n* Use Worm Egg\nObj 2:\nDaegennan is at Gwingris, north-west of Brunanc's nest.\nYou should return to Daegennan with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Daegennan at Gwingris"},
{["next"]={76},area="The Drownholt",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Nífdir wishes to learn what ails the violent trees of the Drownholt, and help them if it is possible to do so.",mobs={{locations={"19.01S, 57.25W"},name="Wrathful Huorn"},{locations={"18.31S, 57.36W"},name="Nífdir"},{locations={"16.93S, 54.69W"},name="Nenedhel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2609,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={2409},name="The Writhing Glade",arcs="The Wroth Glade",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=63,c={"* You will need to defeat 5 Mirk-huorns. Those are Signature creatures, but you might find yourself fighting more than one at the same time. Hence the Small Fellowship type of the quest.\n* After defeating the 5 Mirk-huorns, speak with the Wrathful Huorn in Sâd Meryrn at [19.0S, 57.3W]"},minlevel=58,b="Nenedhel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nNífdir can be found at a small camp to the west of Estolad Mernael.\nNenedhel has asked you once again to seek out Nífdir in the heart of the Drownholt.\n* Talk to Nífdir at his camp\nObj 2:\nHuorns can be found in Sâd Meryrn, due south of Nífdir's small camp. You should travel north and west to reach their glade.\nYou should approach Huorns and attempt to speak with them, but Nífdir has advised you to be prepared for much open hostility.\n* Approach Mirk-huorns\nObj 3:\nThe Wrathful Huorn stands in Sâd Meryrn.\nOne Mirk-huorn does not seem as malicious as the rest; you should approach it and learn what you can from it.\n* Approach the largest Mirk-huorn and attempt to speak with it\nObj 4:\nNífdir is at the camp overlooking Sâd Meryrn from the north.\nYou should speak with Nífdir and tell him of the strange conversation of sorts that passed between yourself and the Mirk-huorn.\n* Talk to Nífdir at his camp"},
{["next"]={1541},area="The Silvertine Lodes",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="25s 90c"}},d="Gufi believes that you are exaggerating the dangers you encountered during your scouting mission but has asked you to check up on Nykr and his mining expedition - just in case.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2610,scope="n/a",prev={1620},name="They Mined Too Fast",level=53,minlevel=48,b="Gufi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGufi is at the Deep Descent encampment.\nGufi has asked you to look in on his party at one of the mining sites.\n* Talk to Gufi to travel to the mine-site\nObj 2:\nGufi is at the Deep Descent, along the north edge of the Silvertine Lodes.\nYou should speak with Gufi about the survey-expedition.\n* Talk to Gufi at the Deep Descent encampment"},
{["next"]={2347},area="Parth Aduial",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Naethmunn has asked you to defeat Jabe Grimshaw, a leader among the tomb-robbers who often plans their activities from high atop Barad Rath, an overlook in Tyrn Fornech.",mobs={{locations={"12.73S, 66.98W"},name="Naethmunn"}},category="Evendim",id=2611,scope="n/a",name="They Spy from the Heights",arcs="The Blade That Was Broken",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=35,minlevel=30,b="Naethmunn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nJabe Grimshaw plans his band's attacks from atop Barad Rath, a flat stone overlook atop the tall hills of Tyrn Fornech, north-east of Tinnudir and north of Tham Ornen.\nRanger Naethmunn has asked you to find and defeat Jabe Grimshaw, leader of a band of tomb-robbers that has plagued the Rangers of Evendim for a long time.\n* Kill 1 Jabe Grimshaw\nObj 2:\nNaethmunn is at the Ranger-camp on the island of Tinnudir, in Evendim, south-west of Barad Rath.\nYou should report your victory over Jabe Grimshaw to Naethmunn.\n* Talk to Naethmunn"},
{["next"]={2295,1417,1499,2695,2297,2790,789,2296,355,354,2104,24,2298,2402,2299},area="Frostbluff",zone="Frostbluff",money={{val="90c"}},d="You have arrived in Winter-home, and the Town Crier has offered to give you a tour of the many sights to be seen.",category="Frostbluff",id=2612,scope="n/a",name="The Yule Celebration of Winter-home",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Yule Festival Token",id="70018CBD"}},level=10,c={"* The Mayor is north of Albert Yule.\n* The Mayor's Wife is beside him.\n* Cecil Voller is north of town in the Snowball Field.\n* Mabel Mitford is north of the Mayor.\n* Guard Kember patrols the entrance of town.\n* The hobbit-announcer is square in the middle of town by the Festival Theater door.\n* Ona Kay is south of the Mayor.\n* Gareth Rust and Daley Utteridge is in the south-west corner of town.\n* Return to the Mayor."},minlevel=6,b="Albert Yule",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe mayor and his wife, hosts of the Yule Festivities, are in the centre of the celebration.\nYou should speak with the mayor about the various events of the festival, for he wishes to greet all who arrive.\n* Speak with the mayor of town about the festivities\nObj 2:\nThe mayor's wife is standing near the mayor, Winston Goodnough, watching over the festivities.\nThe mayor's wife wishes to speak with you.\n* Speak with the mayor's wife\nObj 3:\nCecil Voller is at the Snowball Field, north of the town.\nYou should travel north to speak with Cecil Voller, and observe the Snowball Fight game.\n* Speak with Cecil Voller at the Snowball Field\nObj 4:\nThe town of Winter-home is south of the Snowball Field.\nYou should find your next destination on your tour of the town.\n* Speak with someone from Winter-home to continue your tour\nObj 5:\nGuard Kember can be found near the front gate of Winter-home.\nYou should speak with Guard Kember about where to continue on the tour of town.\n* Speak with Guard Kember for directions\nObj 6:\nThe hobbit-announcer of the travelling theatre can be found in Winter-home.\nYou should speak with the hobbit-announcer about the Theatre event.\n* Speak with the hobbit-announcer about the Theatre Event\nObj 7:\nThe Eating Contest begins at Ona Kay, the first Announcer.\nYou should speak with Ona Kay in Winter-home.\n* Visit Ona Kay, the Eating Contest Announcer\nObj 8:\nThe road ahead of you looks interesting; you should explore it before returning to the mayor....\n* Explore the other corner of Winter-home, for it looks interesting\nObj 9:\nA man standing near Gareth Rust beckons you.\nYou should speak with the man near Gareth Rust.\n* Speak with the man near Gareth Rust; he seems to have something to say\nObj 10:\nMayor Goodnough is in the centre of town.\nYou should return to Mayor Goodnough now that you have finished your tour of Winter-home's many events.\n* Return to Mayor Goodnough to finish your tour",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={264},reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="31s 92c"}},d="A group of Rangers are prepared to launch an assault on the island of Rantost, currently held by tomb-robbers.",selectoneof={{val="Bracer of the Guard Captain",id=70026078},{val="Simple Iron Bracelet",id="700261C9"},{val="Arnorian Knight's Bracelet",id="700260E9"},{val="Elegant Performer's Bracelet",id="7002627A"},{val="Ruby-flecked Bracelet",id="70025DE8"},{val="Bracelet of the Blue Mountains",id=70026198},{val="Finely Adorned Sentry's Bracelet",id=70026525},{val="Ancient Copper Bracelet",id=70026589},{val="Silver Bracelet of Annuminas",id="700264B3"}},category="Evendim",id=2613,scope="n/a",prev={2536},name="Thief-taker's Bane",arcs="The Thief-takers",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=36,minlevel=31,b="Eliot Bencroft",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLeighton Kipps is at the spies camp in the south east of Rantost.\nLeighton Kipps is waiting to signal the rangers to assault Rantost.\n* Talk to Leighton Kipps and aid the Rangers\nObj 2:\nEliot Bencroft is at the south east of Rantost.\nEliot Bencroft will be pleased to hear the rangers were able to recover their relics and the spies can return to Ost Forod.\n* Speak to Eliot Bencroft"},
{["next"]={2667},reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="33s 4c"}},d="Grave-robbers and brigands abound in Evendim, looting the tombs of the Dúnedain.",mobs={{locations={"12.06S, 68.09W"},name="Balchelos"}},category="Evendim",id=2614,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={2594},name="Thief-taker's Reward",arcs="The Thief-takers",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=38,minlevel=33,b="Balchelos",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe robber-camp is on a tiny island at the mouth of the Brandywine river in Lake Evendim.\nHaving successfully defeated the brigands at Rantost Island, you have been sent to another small brigand camp, where it is hoped you will be able to recover some more stolen treasure.\n* Recover the stolen treasure\nObj 2:\nYou have discovered a tomb-robber ambush.\n* Kill 1 Ned Leggett\nObj 3:\nBalchelos is back at Tinnudir.\nYou overcame the tomb-robber ambush and should report the incident to Balchelos.\n* Talk to Balchelos"},
{area="Global",zone="Middle-earth",reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},d="Bree is a beacon for the Free Peoples of the North...it must be freed at all costs.",category="Skirmish",id=2615,scope="n/a",name="Thievery and Mischief -- Daily",level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe town of Bree must be reclaimed from the brigands and ruffians who have overrun it.\n* Complete the Thievery and Mischief Skirmish"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="West of Tol Ascarnen, across the Hoardale River, the Orcs make their main keep. It is here that Lieutenant Solvi believes the Orcs have stolen precious food stores moved into Tol Ascarnen during the initial push by the Free Peoples, and he wants them back.",category="Ettenmoors",id=2616,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Thieving Orcs",receive={{val="Token of Valour",id="700087FA"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Lieutenant Solvi",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nFood-sacks might be found on the Orcs, trolls, and goblins in the Ettenmoors.\nLieutenant Solvi advised you to search Grothum and Dâr-gazag for more plentiful amounts of the food-sacks, but also said that the Ongbûrz and Snowreap may have some on their persons.\n* Return to Lieutenant Solvi at Tol Ascarnen\n* Turn in Food Sack",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={911},area="Glâd Ereg",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Maedlathron is concerned that the hobbits or Gimli the dwarf may have dropped something else upon their journey which may divulge to the Enemy the way of their passing and the composition of the Company.",mobs={{locations={"47.02S, 12.53W"},name="Golgallon"},{locations={"40.17S, 16.04W"},name="Maedlathron"}},category="Eregion",id=2617,scope="n/a",prev={1913},name="Things Left Behind",arcs="Footsteps of the Company",level=48,c={"* You will find a Pipeweed Pouch at an abandoned camp in the High Hollin area [43.8S, 12.9W]"},minlevel=43,b="Maedlathron",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGolgallon is at Echad Eregion, far to the south-east of Gwingris.\nMaedlathron has asked you to warn Golgallon that the Company may have left further signs of their passing in the wild.\n* Talk to Golgallon at Echad Eregion"},
{["next"]={1486},area="Greenway",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="7s"}},d="Agnes Martlet has kept her own farm for years, and although she left it when the Wargs appeared, she is already thinking ahead to her return.",category="North Downs",id=2618,scope="n/a",prev={2542},name="Thinking Ahead",arcs="Agnes and the Bears",level=22,minlevel=17,b="Agnes Martlet",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBears can be found on the northern hills of Annúndir, east of Amon Raith.\nAgnes Martlet believes the threat of Wargs will soon pass, and she is more concerned with the bears that have troubled her livestock over the years. She has asked you to cull the bears' numbers and collect their thick hides for tents and clothing while also reducing the threat to her livestock.\n* Return the Heavy Bear-hides to Agnes Martlet\n* Turn in Heavy Bear-hide"},
{["next"]={796},area="Himbar",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+900 with Council of the North"}},money={{val="49s"}},d="The Hillman called Donaith is concerned about the Orcs in the vicinity of Urugarth and Carn Dûm.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Donaith"}},selectoneof={{val="Donaith's Longsword",id=70002229},{val="Daenam",id=70002228}},category="Urugarth",id=2619,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Thinning the Horde",arcs="Thinning the Horde",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Donaith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nUrugarth and Carn Dûm lie to the west of Gath Forthnír.\nDonaith asked you to support the cause of his people and defeat the Orcs which gather in Urugarth or Carn Dûm.\n* Defeat Uruks in Urugarth and Carn Dûm (10)\n* Defeat Orcs in Urugarth and Carn Dûm (20)\nObj 2:\nDonaith can be found at Gath Forthnír.\nReturn to Donaith in eastern Angmar and tell him of your deeds.\n* Talk to Donaith"},
{area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+500 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Naur-hoit, the ruins south of Mithechad, is home to a roving pack of Wargs.",mobs={{locations={"17.71S, 48.28W"},name="Perindúr"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2620,scope="n/a",name="Thin the Pack",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Perindúr",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Wargs make their den in Naur-hoit, south of Mithechad.\nPerindúr has asked you to hunt down and defeat the Wargs of the Ashenslades.\n* Defeat Wargs (15)\nObj 2:\nPerindúr is at Mithechad, north of Naur-hoit.\nYou should return to Perindúr with news of your success against the Wargs of the Ashenslades.\n* Talk to Perindúr at Mithechad",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1577},area="Haudh Lin",zone="Ered Luin",d="You found a rabbit carcass with which to feed the mother lynx. But she still does not seem well enough to hunt on her own.",mobs={{locations={"21.59S, 94.17W"},name="Thrasi"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2621,scope="n/a",prev={1123},name="Thistle-mead",arcs="The Cat's Meow",level=10,pois={{locations={"20.50S, 94.88W","20.73S, 94.98W","20.51S, 95.44W","20.83S, 94.12W","20.59S, 93.83W","20.49S, 93.95W","20.49S, 93.66W","20.92S, 93.92W","20.71S, 94.05W","20.60S, 94.04W","20.62S, 95.48W","20.43S, 94.07W"},name="Sharp-thistle"}},minlevel=6,b="Thrasi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are sharp-thistle plants around the wood north of Thrasi's lodge.\nThrasi asked you to collect sharp-thistle plants to make a draught to cure the mother lynx's injuries.\n* Bring the sharp-thistle plants to Thrasi\n* Collect sharp-thistle plants (6 Sharp-thistle )",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="2s 80c"}},d="Thomas Thistlewool received a letter from Anlaf the Forlorn at The Forsaken Inn, mentioning money owed and a man he employed to collect some artifacts from the area.",mobs={{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Anlaf the Forlorn"},{locations={"30.16S, 52.48W"},name="Thomas Thistlewool"}},selectoneof={{val="Thistlewool's Shoes",id="700007D9"},{val="Thistlewool's Rune-stone",id="700161B7"}},category="Bree-land",id=2622,scope="n/a",name="Thistlewool's Sullied Name",arcs="Traders from Bree",level=22,minlevel=17,b="Thomas Thistlewool",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAnlaf the Forlorn can be found at The Forsaken Inn, eastward along the Great East Road.\nThomas Thistlewool has asked you to deliver a letter to Anlaf the Forlorn, the proprietor of The Forsaken Inn, promising payment for a debt incurred by a man he hired to seek ancient relics for him.\n* Talk to Anlaf the Forlorn\n* Turn in Letter from Thistlewool"},
{area="Northern High Pass",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Thorgest has been poisoned by the Gauredain, and Afwald, Thorgest's assistant, believes the chief shaman of the Gauredain may hold the key to curing him.",mobs={{locations={"24.55S, 7.04E"},name="Thorgest"},{locations={"24.55S, 7.04E"},name="Afwald"}},selectoneof={{val="Thol-men",id="7000D2B7"},{val="Thorgest's Staff",id="7000D2DA"},{val="Thorgest's Shield",id="700164A7"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2623,scope="n/a",prev={550},name="Thorgest's Last Hope",arcs="Gauradan Curse",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Afwald",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Gauradan-camps lie to the south of Thorgest's dwelling.\nAfwald has asked you to try and find the chief shaman of the Gauredain in the last desperate hope that he may hold the cure to the poison that is slowly killing Thorgest.\n* Turn in Ice-fang Antidote\nObj 2:\nAfwald is at Thorgest's dwelling, north of the Gauradan-camps.\nYou should bring the Ice-fang antidote to Afwald before Thorgest succumbs to the poison.\n* Bring the Ice-fang antidote to Afwald\nObj 3:\nThorgest is at his dwelling, with Afwald.\nAfwald has told you that Thorgest is fading quickly and that you must administer the antidote to the dying dwarf before it is too late.\n* Talk to Thorgest\n* Turn in Ice-fang Antidote"},
{area="Northern High Pass",zone="The Misty Mountains",money={{val="38s 64c"}},d="Thorgest's brother Thorkell was killed a few days earlier by worms.",mobs={{locations={"24.55S, 7.04E"},name="Thorgest"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2624,scope="n/a",name="Thorkell has Fallen",arcs="Scales of Vengeance",level=48,minlevel=43,b="Thorgest",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe worm caves are to the south-east of Thorgest's dwelling.\nThorgest has asked you to find and return Thorkell's belongings.\n* Return Thorkell's belongings to Thorgest\n* Turn in Thorkell's Axe\n* Turn in Thorkell's Helm",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2680},area="Northern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="3s 20c"}},d="Brigands referring to themselves as Sharkey's Men have taken over the old Dogwood farm, threatening the neighbouring steads.",mobs={{locations={"25.38S, 53.74W"},name="Rose Thornley"},{locations={"25.55S, 52.88W"},name="Saeradan"}},category="Bree-land",id=2625,scope="n/a",name="Thornley's Farm",arcs="Thornley's Farm",receive={{val="Thornley's Bow",id=70009104}},level=18,minlevel=13,b="Saeradan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRose Thornley is at her home, west of Saeradan's cabin.\nThe Ranger Saeradan suggested you speak with Rose Thornley concerning her husband's disappearance.\n* Talk to Rose Thornley at Thornley's Farm\nObj 2:\nRobb was last seen heading north along the road.\nRose Thornley has asked you to find her husband.\n* Find Robb Thornley"},
{["next"]={2681},area="Northern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="3s 20c"}},d="Robb Thornley, a Bree-land farmer, has been captured by marauding Orcs.",mobs={{locations={"25.38S, 53.74W"},name="Rose Thornley"}},category="Bree-land",id=2626,scope="n/a",name="Thornley's Rescue",arcs="Thornley's Farm",receive={{val="Thornley's Robe",id="7001B39B"}},level=18,minlevel=13,b="Robb Thornley",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRobb Thornley has asked you to help him escape from the Orc-camp.\n* Free Robb Thornley and escort him to safety.\nObj 2:\nRose Thornley can be found at their farm in the Bree-fields, south of the Orc-camp.\nRobb Thornley's wife, Rose, should be told of her husband's escape from the Orcs.\n* Talk to Rose Thornley at Thornley's Farm"},
{area="Northern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="6s"}},d="You rescued Robb Thornley from the Orcs, battered and beaten, but he is not satisfied with rescue. He wants retribution.",mobs={{locations={"25.38S, 53.74W"},name="Rose Thornley"}},selectoneof={{val="Red Reaver's Doom",id="70006A79"},{val="Thornley's Revenge",id="700069E9"}},category="Bree-land",id=2627,scope="n/a",prev={2680},name="Thornley's Revenge",arcs="Thornley's Farm",level=19,minlevel=14,b="Rose Thornley",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Red Reaver is in the Orc-stockade on the western side of the Greenway, north of Thornley's farm.\nOn behalf of her husband, Rose Thornley has offered you a reward if you would go to the stockade and slay the Red Reaver.\n* Defeat the Red Reaver\nObj 2:\nThornley's farm is south along the Greenway from the Orc-stockade.\nYou should return to Thornley's farm at once to tell Rose of your victory and claim your reward.\n* Talk to Rose Thornley at Thornley's Farm"},
{["next"]={1732},money={{val="26s 60c"}},d="You found a journal written by a stone-carver who decorated the ancient halls of Khâzad-dum.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=2628,scope="n/a",name="Thoughts Left Behind",arcs="Stonecarver's Stash",level=55,minlevel=50,b="Stonecarver's Journal",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThere are dwarves in the Twenty-first Hall, west of Uzbad-bakân.\nOne of the dwarves in the Twenty-first Hall may be able to tell you more about the stone-carver's journal that you found.\n* Find a dwarf in the Twenty-first Hall who recognizes the journal",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="The faded tapestries of Tham Nambarth tell of a heraldry long since lost to Evendim.",category="Evendim",id=2629,scope="n/a",name="Threads of the Past",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=34,pois={{locations={"12.10S, 65.48W","11.92S, 65.32W","12.03S, 65.32W","11.80S, 65.37W","12.16S, 65.32W","12.38S, 65.27W","11.92S, 65.56W","12.20S, 65.54W","11.83S, 65.55W","12.01S, 65.59W","11.79S, 65.46W","12.37S, 65.46W"},name="Tattered Tapestry Piece"}},minlevel=29,b="Ancient Tapestry",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTham Nambarth is east of Tinnudir.\nNadfaron asked you to venture to Tham Nambarth and find scraps of ancient tapestries.\n* Obj 2:\nThe Rangers are at Tinnudir, west of Tham Nambarth.\nOne of the Rangers at Tinnudir will be eager to examine the pieces of tapestry you collected.\n* Bring the tapestry pieces to Nadfaron\n*",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={839},reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Northern Emyn Uial",money={{val="19s 95c"}},d="The Guaradan have slowly begun encroaching further and further south, and now threaten even the Eavespires.",mobs={{locations={"6.12S, 71.92W"},name="Erchiel"},{locations={"6.09S, 72.02W"},name="Longbough"}},category="Evendim",id=2630,scope="n/a",name="Threat From the North",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=36,minlevel=31,b="Longbough",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Gauradan encampment is north of the Eavespires.\n* Aid Erchiel with the Gauradan Camp\n* Aid Erchiel with the Gaurdan Camp\n* Aid Remmenylf with the Gauradan Camp\nObj 2:\nErchiel is at the Eavespires.\nErchiel will want to know the first tasks are complete.\n* Talk to Erchiel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1037},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="The Lossoth blame the harsh winter on the invading Angmarim and have asked for your help in driving them away.",mobs={{locations={"19.03N, 70.76W"},name="Pasi"}},category="Forochel",id=2631,scope="n/a",name="Threat from the South",arcs="The Hand of the Enemy",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Pasi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe camps of the Angmarim are south and east of Sûri-kylä, near the Pass of Forodwaith.\nPasi has asked you to help defeat the invading Angmarim.\n* Turn in Angmarim Weapons\nObj 2:\nPasi is at Sûri-kylä, north and west of the Angmarim encampment.\nYou should return at once to Pasi and show him the weapons of the Angmarim.\n* Bring the Angmarim Weapons to Pasi\n* Turn in Angmarim Weapons"},
{area="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",zone="Angmar",reputation={{val="+700 with The Eldgang"}},money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="The Ghâshfra, a breed of Fire-orcs from Angmar, have invaded the Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu.",category="The Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu",id=2632,scope="n/a",name="Threat of Fire",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Hyrrokkin",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nOrcs of the Ghâshfra can be found throughout the Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu.\nHyrrokkin has asked you to defeat the Ghâshfra which have invaded the Rift of Nûrz Ghâshu.\n* Defeat Ghâshfra (25)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={110,1629},area="Southern Bree-fields",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="2s 55c"}},d="Adso's problems deepen as the brigands become more aggressive towards the poor hobbit.",mobs={{locations={"29.12S, 56.78W"},name="Adso Haybank"}},category="Bree-land",id=2633,scope="n/a",prev={741},name="Threats and Follow-through",arcs="Unfair Cost of Business",level=17,minlevel=12,b="Adso Haybank",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDirk Hawthorn is on the south side of the ruined wall at the foot of the hills surrounding the Barrow-downs, east of Adso's Camp.\nAdso fears that the brigand leader, Dirk Hawthorn, will return and kill his workers in the night and asked you to deal with this threat before he could follow through.\n* Defeat Dirk Hawthorn\nObj 2:\nAdso awaits your return at his camp along the Great East Road.\nThe brigands at the ruined wall proved to be no true threat and were dispatched with ease.\n* Talk to Adso Haybank"},
{["next"]={240},area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="After becoming separated from the rest of her fellowship by a storm, Burgthryth was pursued through the wilderness by a variety of hostile beasts. During the course of her flight, she lost some of her most prized sheets of music and despairs of ever finding them again.",mobs={{locations={"7.44N, 75.46W"},name="Burgthryth"}},category="Forochel",id=2634,scope="n/a",name="Three Sheets to the Wind",level=47,c={"* Tundra Bears drop the first sheet\n* Any peikko in the Peikko Cave drops the second sheet\n* Gauradan Hunters drop the third sheet"},minlevel=42,b="Burgthryth",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBurgthryth believes the first of her sheets was swiped from her pack by a Tundra Bear. You will have to hunt them down until you find the one that stole it -- assuming it has not already been devoured.\nTundra Bears can be found in Länsi-mâ.\n* Turn in Stained Sheet-music\nObj 2:\nBurgthryth told you that the second of her anthem sheets might have been grabbed by a curious peikko during her performance. You will have to hunt down the peikko that stole it.\nMany Peikko may be found in a small cave due east of Zigilgund.\n* Turn in Torn Sheet-music\nObj 3:\nBurgthryth thinks she probably dropped the third sheet of her anthem when she was being pursued by Gauradan-hunters. You will have to hunt down the Gauredain and retrieve that sheet before they use it as a hankerchief -- or worse.\nGauredain can be found in Länsi-mâ.\n* Turn in Crumpled Sheet-music\nObj 4:\nBurgthryth is at Jänis-leiri.\nYou finally found all the sheets of Burgthryth's scattered anthem. You will need to return them to her at once.\n* Talk to Burgthryth\n* Turn in Stained Sheet-music\n* Turn in Torn Sheet-music\n* Turn in Crumpled Sheet-music",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1366},area="Foundations of Stone",zone="Moria",d="Dithrik has tasked you with acquiring materials that will aid in challenging an old horror from ages long passed.",category="Guardian",id=2635,scope="n/a",prev={4},name="Thrill of Danger",arcs="The Path of the Defender of the Free",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Dithrik",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Nameless beings and the ancient creature prowl the vicinity of the Foundations of Stone, especially to the south-east of this region.\nDithrik has asked you to collect twelve unspoiled heads from the Nameless of the Foundations of Stone.\n* Return to Dithrik in the Foundations of Stone\n* Turn in Severed head of The Dark Warden",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nan Sirannon",zone="Eregion",money={{val="25s 20c"}},d="Rinneldor has asked you to seek out Limlaer who stands watch near the southern border of Eregion.",mobs={{locations={"52.05S, 10.18W"},name="Limlaer"}},category="Eregion",id=2636,scope="n/a",name="Through the Gap of Rohan",arcs="Footsteps of the Company",level=51,c={"* The tower on the hill is at [52.7S, 10.6W]"},minlevel=46,b="Limlaer",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe tower is upon a hill, south-west of Limlaer, who stands near the road leading south-west from Echad Dúnann.\nLimlaer has asked you to go to a nearby tower and look for signs of the Company's passing.\n* Look for signs of the Company (Perform /look)\n* Find the tower on the hill\nObj 2:\nLimlaer is south-west of Echad Dúnann, along the Nan Sirannon road.\nYou should report your findings to Limlaer.\n* Talk to Limlaer",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Bruinen Source West",zone="The Misty Mountains",reputation={{val="+1200 with Elves of Rivendell"}},money={{val="46s 20c"}},d="The Thunder-lord, leader of the giants, has ordered them to battle. If he can be defeated, this threat might fall with him.",mobs={{locations={"24.78S, 4.05W"},name="Gwaemithrin"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},selectoneof={{val="Thunder Lord's Fall",id="70000FF4"},{val="Túannadir",id="70000FF2"},{val="Feremaib",id="70000FF1"},{val="Thunder Stabber",id="70000FF3"},{val="Balangon",id="70000FF5"}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2637,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={994},name="Thunder in the Mountains",arcs="Thunder in the Mountains",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Gwaemithrin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Thunder-lord rules the giants from Iorbar, south and east of the Giants' Table in the Misty Mountains.\nThe Thunder-lord is the source of the giants' recent hostility, and he must be defeated before all the giants in the region heed his commands. You will need the aid of brave allies if you hope to defeat him.\n* Kill 1 Thunder Lord\nObj 2:\nElrond is in the library at Imladris.\nYou must tell Elrond that the Thunder-lord is now defeated and the threat of the giants has been lessened.\n* Talk to Elrond at Rivendell"},
{["next"]={1578},area="Talvi-mûri",zone="Forochel",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Thurmaer lost his favorite 'lucky arrow' during a recent hunt in Talvi-mûri. He was stalking a particularly cunning Snow-worm and had just loosed his arrow when he was ambushed by a band of Gauradan-hunters and was forced to flee. Though he made it to shelter, Thurmaer twisted his ankle during his flight.",mobs={{locations={"19.35N, 83.76W"},name="Thurmaer"}},category="Forochel",id=2638,scope="n/a",name="Thurmaer's Lucky Arrow",level=49,c={"* Beleganc can be found in Talvi-mûri around [16.0N, 84.0W]"},minlevel=44,b="Thurmaer",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBeleganc wanders far and wide over the great glacier, south of Kuru-leiri.\nThurmaer has asked you to hunt down the snow-worm called Beleganc and retrieve his Lucky Arrow from it.\n* Turn in Thurmaer's Lucky Arrow\nObj 2:\nThurmaer is at Kuru-leiri, north of the glacier.\nYou should return the lucky arrow to Thurmaer.\n* Talk to Thurmaer\n* Turn in Thurmaer's Lucky Arrow",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="Fil Gashan is the barracks and mustering point for the Orcs' invasion of Lothlórien. Hidden deep within the fiery landscape and sharing an adjacent entrance to the Forges of Khazad-dûm, Orcs train here under the watchful eye of General Talug.",mobs={{locations={"13.43S, 108.08W"},name="Teitur"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2639,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Thwarting the Moria Orcs",arcs="General's Command",level=60,minlevel=57,b="Teitur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nÚlfur, Vagun, and Yngvi can be found in Anazârmekhem.\nTeitur directed you to speak with his aides and complete their tasks before he tells Narfi that Fil Gashan is no longer a threat.\n* Help Vagun disable alarms in Fil Gashan\n* Help Vagun with lieutenants in Fil Gashan\n* Help Úlfur gather plans from Fil Gashan\n* Help Yngvi defeat General Talug in Fil Gashan\nObj 2:\nTeitur can be found in Anzârmekhem.\nYou successfully completed each of the tasks  Úlfur, Vagun, and Yngvi gave you. Now you should return to Teitur with your report.\n* Talk to Teitur in Anazârmekhem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="44s 24c"}},d="The Grand Stair once stood at the foot of a great crossroads within Moria. At the height of the great city, it led to all areas of the halls and was a majestic wonder to behold. Now it has fallen to the care of Igash, a lieutenant of the Moria Orc-leader Mazog. Igash assembled the forces of Orcs and trolls within Moria in one place and has collected tribute from each to one day bring to the leader of the Orcs. For now, each tribe vies for favour from the lieutenant, a fanatical follower of Mazog.",mobs={{locations={"10.99S, 106.77W"},name="Thithrand"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2640,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Thwarting the White Hand",arcs="The Grand Stair",receive={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Legend",id="7001F259"}},level=58,minlevel=57,b="Thithrand",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThithrand is at the Orc-watch.\nThirthrand believes that the White Hand will openly rebel against the Moria Orcs, but fears they could amass enough strength to wrest control for themselves. To avert this, he would like you to complete a variety of tasks.\n* Help Thithrand defeat the leaders of the White Hand Orcs within the Grand Stair\n* Help Thithrand cripple the White Hand's power in the Grand Stair\nObj 2:\nThithrand is at the Orc-watch, south-west of the Grand Stair.\nYou should return to Thithrand with news of your successes in the Grand Stair.\n* Talk to Thithrand at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Frostbluff",zone="Frostbluff",money={{val="90c"}},d="The festival patrons have left a lot of filth in their wake and tidying up is a rather unpleasant chore that must be performed.",category="Frostbluff",id=2641,scope="n/a",prev={2658},name="Tidying Up",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Frostbluff Coin",id="70024EB1"}},level=10,c={"* There are four areas to clean up in the north, east, south, and west side of Winter-home."},minlevel=6,b="Basil Wyndham",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGarbage can be found at each of the Eating Contest stations in Winter-home, and the servant Basil Wyndham deems himself above the task of cleaning it up.\nYou should clean up garbage, spills, and dirty dishes around the Eating Contest's tables.\n* Use Grimy Dish\n* Use Smelly Garbage\n* Use Unsightly Spill\nObj 2:\nBasil Wyndham can be found in Winter-home.\nYou should return to Basil Wyndham now that you have cleaned up some of the mess from the Eating Contest.\n* Talk to Basil Wyndham",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1090},area="Jä-rannit",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+700 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="You found Nef's shield, but it had been broken by the beast that drove him off.",mobs={{locations={"19.44N, 71.31W"},name="Nef"},{locations={"19.54N, 71.99W"},name="Rauno"}},category="Forochel",id=2642,scope="n/a",prev={2385},name="Time for a New Shield",arcs="The Finest Shield in the Land",receive={{val="Battle Ward",id="7000E968"}},level=48,c={"* Rauno is inside the Great Lodge of Sûri-kylä\n* Kill bears and worms around Sûri-kylä"},minlevel=43,b="Nef",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Lossoth craftsmen are in the Great Lodge in Sûri-kylä, west of Nef.\nNef has asked you to speak with the Lossoth craftsmen to learn if they are able to repair his broken shield.\n* Talk to the Lossoth craftsmen\nObj 2:\nNef is in Sûri-kylä, east from the Great Lodge.\nYou should return to Nef and tell him what you learned from Rauno.\n* Talk to Nef\nObj 3:\nRauno is in Sûri-kylä, west from Nef in the Great Lodge of Sûri-kylä.\nNef has asked you to return to Rauno and try to convince him to craft a new shield for him.\n* Talk to Rauno\n* Turn in Broken Shield\nObj 4:\nHard bone can be found on beasts throughout Jä-rannit. Worm scale can be found on worms throughout Jä-rannit.\nRauno has asked you to collect hard bones and worm scales so that he may make a shield for Nef.\n* Turn in Hard Bone\n* Turn in Worm-scale\nObj 5:\nRauno is in Sûri-kylä, north from where you collected the items he requested.\nYou should bring the hard bones and worm scales to Rauno so he can complete Nef's shield.\n* Talk to Rauno\n* Turn in Hard Bone\n* Turn in Worm-scale\nObj 6:\nRauno is in Sûri-kylä.\nYou should speak with Rauno to see if Nef's shield is ready.\n* Get the shield from Rauno\nObj 7:\nNef is in Sûri-kylä, east from Rauno.\nRauno told you to take the shield he made to Nef and bid him leave Sûri-kylä.\n* Talk to Nef\n* Turn in Shield"},
{area="Annúminas",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+500 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="21s"}},d="Dannassel has told you of a number of supply stores hidden throughout the city in times of peace.",mobs={{locations={"18.97S, 70.88W"},name="Dannassel"}},category="Annúminas",id=2643,scope="n/a",name="Time of Need",receive={{q="(x12)",val="Arnorian Armour Fragments",id="7000AE74"},{val="Distilled Athelas Essence",id="70000F31"}},level=39,pois={{locations={"17.36S, 69.59W","19.19S, 70.77W","17.23S, 71.29W","17.79S, 69.69W","19.59S, 70.17W","17.16S, 71.59W","18.51S, 71.85W","18.36S, 68.57W","17.96S, 69.86W","17.18S, 71.08W","18.97S, 69.58W","18.83S, 70.48W","17.90S, 70.01W","18.84S, 70.17W","18.51S, 69.26W","18.41S, 68.84W","19.19S, 70.06W","19.34S, 70.53W","17.13S, 70.68W","18.27S, 71.49W","19.59S, 69.99W","18.46S, 71.31W","17.71S, 69.56W","19.30S, 68.84W","19.52S, 69.55W","19.11S, 69.90W"},name="Hidden Cache"}},minlevel=34,b="Dannassel",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nStores of supplies are hidden in out-of-the-way locations throughout Annúminas.\nDannassel has asked you to search for supply stores hidden throughout the city and to bring their contents to her. She warned you that Angmarim patrols may have already discovered and looted some of the stores.\n* Use Hidden Cache\n* Use Hidden Cache\nObj 2:\nDannassel is at Echad Garthadir, the Ranger-encampment in the heart of Annúminas.\nYou have recovered some of the supplies from the stores hidden throughout Annúminas and should bring them to Dannassel.\n* Talk to Dannassel\n* Turn in Recovered Supplies",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="Tinnudir is where the Rangers now base all of their operations from within Evendim.",category="Evendim",id=2644,scope="n/a",prev={1771},name="Tinnudir, Vestige of Men",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=33,minlevel=28,b="Sardan",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOrchalwë is at Tinnudir, north and west of the Colossus.\nAfter thanking you for aiding them, the Rangers at the Colossus directed you to the island of Tinnudir.\n* Talk to Orchalwë",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tirith Rhaw",zone="Ettenmoors",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Tirith Rhaw is once again under the control of the Free Peoples. The forces here are still meagre, and a strong show of force from the Enemy could mean that the tower is lost as quickly as it is taken.",category="Tirith Rhaw",id=2645,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=125}},name="Tirith Rhaw Reinforcements",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Sergeant-at-Arms Malhathel",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nGlân Vraig lay to the south and east of Tirith Rhaw.\nAfter taking Tirith Rhaw away from the Enemy, the army of the Free Peoples sent you to Glân Vraig to request reinforcements for the tower.\n* Inform Captain-General Tordúr that Tirith Rhaw needs reinforcements",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="42s"}},d="A terrible gorthorog stands on the terrace of Tyl Ruinen, overlooking the whole of Lake Evendim.",category="Evendim",id=2646,scope="n/a",name="Titan of Tyl Ruinen",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,minlevel=34,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Titan of Tyl Ruinen must fall.\n* Defeat the Tital of Tyl Ruinen\nObj 2:\nOrchalwë will want to speak of the battle with the Titan of Tyl Ruinen.",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={876},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+500 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},money={{val="26s 95c"}},d="The toads of the Water-works are known to exude a slime that has befuddling qualities.",category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2647,scope="n/a",prev={663},name="Toad-slime",arcs="All Glory",level=56,minlevel=51,b="Gyrgir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nToads can be found all over the Water-works in the areas around the Rotting Cellar.\nGyrgir believes with some toad-slime he can create a solution to the lizard problem.\n* Turn in Toad-slime\nObj 2:\nGyrgir is in the Rotting Cellar.\nYou should bring the toad-slime you collected to Gyrgir.\n* Talk to Gyrgir in the Rotting Cellar\n* Turn in Toad-slime"},
{["next"]={374},area="Tâl Bruinen",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="21s 35c"}},d="Indor is very excited to try a recipe that the dwarf Wéthorm gave to him, but he does not have the necessary ingredients.",mobs={{locations={"36.92S, 14.21W"},name="Indor"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2648,scope="n/a",name="Toad Stews",arcs="Toad Stews",level=40,pois={{locations={"36.90S, 14.22W"},name="Grinding Stone"}},minlevel=35,b="Indor",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nToads can be found along the riverbanks in Tâl Bruinen.\nIndor has asked you to help him collect the various ingredients he needs to make toad stew, a recipe given to him by the dwarf Wéthorm. He reminded you that only the green river-toads will provide tongues and legs of sufficient quality.\n* Turn in Rough Toad Tongue\n* Turn in Slimy Toad Legs\nObj 2:\nIndor is at Echad Candelleth, the Elf-camp in Tâl Bruinen.\nYou have collected many bits of toad with which Indor plans to make toad stew. You should bring them to him.\n* Talk to Indor\n* Turn in Slimy Toad Legs\n* Turn in Rough Toad Tongue\nObj 3:\nThere is a grinding stone right next to the campfire by Indor, at Echad Candelleth.\nIndor is waiting for you to grind the ingredients for toad stew into a mush.\n* Use Grinding Stone\n* Turn in Slimy Toad Legs\n* Turn in Rough Toad Tongue\nObj 4:\nIndor is at the campfire at Echad Candelleth, in Tâl Bruinen.\nYou have ground the toad pieces into mush and should now give them to Indor so he can add the finishing touches to the toad stew.\n* Talk to Indor\n* Turn in Ground Toad Mush",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Nain Enidh",zone="The Lone-lands",money={{val="7s 14c"}},d="Agamaur is a place full of foul corruption and grave danger, home to a terrible evil.",mobs={{locations={"29.62S, 27.40W"},name="Eriac the Strong"},{locations={"31.49S, 29.50W"},name="Frideric the Elder"}},category="Lone-lands",id=2649,scope="n/a",prev={2835},name="To Agamaur",level=30,c={"* Go to Eriac the Strong in Agamaur."},minlevel=25,b="Frideric the Elder",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAgamaur is east and north of Ost Guruth. It lies beyond the Red Pass in the Haragmar swamp.\nFrideric has bid you journey to Agamaur to speak with Eriac the Strong.\n* Talk to Eriac the Strong",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="7s 56c"}},d="The Elf Barachen patrols near the Last Bridge, guarding the passage from the Lone-lands into the Trollshaws.",mobs={{locations={"30.86S, 5.26W"},name="Anhebir"},{locations={"34.04S, 20.16W"},name="Barachen"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2650,scope="n/a",name="To Barachen",level=33,minlevel=28,b="Anhebir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarachen makes his camp not far east of the Last Bridge from the Lone-lands, on a hill south of the road.\nAnhebir has sent you to lend what aid you may to the Elf Barachen.\n* Talk to Barachen",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="7s 84c"}},d="After spending some time with you, the Elves of Rivendell are prepared to welcome you into the inner halls of Imlad Gelair.",mobs={{locations={"29.88S, 3.48W"},name="Barbethnir"},{locations={"32.31S, 2.10W"},name="Atharbain"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2651,scope="n/a",name="To Imlad Gelair",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Barbethnir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nImlad Gelair is located to the south-east of The Last Homely House, below the Falls of Imladris.\nYou have been instructed to speak with Atharbain in Imlad Gelair.\n* Talk to Atharbain",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2810},money={{val="26s 25c"}},d="Rambi has little idea what the mervyl are, but they sound to him like something his friend Oxi mentioned in a recent message.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=2652,scope="n/a",prev={1926},name="To Jazârgund",level=54,minlevel=49,b="Rambi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nOxi can be found at Jazârgund in Durin's Way, north and east of the Chamber of the Crossroads.\nRambi recommends that you speak with his friend Oxi about the mervyl.\n* Talk to Oxi at Jazârgund",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={3229},area="The Dourstocks",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="The Ranger Prestadír is very perturbed by the atmosphere around Audaghaim and is curious about the history of the town.",category="Mirkwood",id=2653,scope="n/a",prev={127},name="Tokens of Fealty",arcs="The History of Audaghaim",receive={{val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=62,minlevel=57,b="Prestadír",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nShades can be found in Audaghaim in the Dourstocks, just east of the Haunted Inn.\nYou should confront shades and see if you can find anything out about why this ruined town feels so fell.\n* Turn in Token of Fealty\nObj 2:\nPrestadír can be found in the Haunted Inn in the Dourstocks, west of Audaghaim.\nYou should return to Prestadír with the strange tokens you collected from the shades of Audaghaim.\n* Talk to Prestadír\n* Turn in Token of Fealty"},
{area="Tinnudir",zone="Evendim",reputation={{val="+700 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Cannuion told you of the terrible threat the Angmarim and tomb-raiders pose to the Rangers of Evendim.",category="Reputation",id=2654,scope="n/a",name="Tomb-raiders' Sashes -- Introduction",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Cannuion",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTomb-raiders can be found throughout Evendim. Cannuion is at Tinnudir.\nCannuion has asked you to collect the tomb-raiders' sashes of allegiance and bring them to him.\n* Bring Tomb-raiders' Sashes to Cannuion at Tinnudir.\n* Turn in Tomb-raider's Sash",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={232},reputation={{val="+1200 with Galadhrim"}},zone="Lothlórien",area="Nimrodel",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Hadroneth is concerned about the Orc camps that have been established in Nanduhirion, and wants you to tear down the barricades that have sprung up outside them.",mobs={{locations={"16.18S, 73.47W"},name="Hadroneth"}},selectoneof={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Learning",id="7001F256"},{val="Sealed Copper Setting of the Enduring Hand",id="700185CF"},{q="(x2)",val="Pure Celebrant Salve",id="7000EA85"},{q="(x2)",val="Pure Athelas Essence",id="7000EA84"}},category="Lothlórien",id=2655,scope="n/a",prev={738},name="Too Close to Lórien",receive={{val="Lamb and Barley Soup",id="70018E99"}},level=60,pois={{locations={"13.76S, 77.66W","13.90S, 77.64W","10.24S, 79.14W","10.49S, 79.07W","13.00S, 77.53W","12.68S, 77.55W","12.96S, 77.47W","14.84S, 75.65W","10.87S, 79.09W","14.85S, 75.52W"},name="Barricade"}},minlevel=55,b="Hadroneth",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou will find barricades to the north-west of Talan Haldir, outside the Orc camps of Uruk-gashan, Drû-garmadh, and Athmadhul, along the road that runs through Nanduhirion.\nHadroneth has asked you to damage the permanence of the Orc camps in Nanduhirion by burning down the barricades they erect outside them.\n* Use Barricade\nObj 2:\nHadroneth is on Talan Haldir, located on the banks of the Nimrodel, south-east of Nanduhirion.\nYou have set fire to many of the Orc barricades in Nanduhirion and should report now to Hadroneth.\n* Talk to Hadroneth"},
{area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",d="Esilia Took told you that Gerebert finally made it to her house and told a fantastic tale of his journey aboard Longo's waggon.",mobs={{locations={"33.04S, 71.08W"},name="Gerebert Took"},{locations={"33.03S, 71.08W"},name="Esilia Took"},{locations={"33.60S, 71.13W","33.61S, 71.13W"},name="Thain Paladin Took II"}},selectoneof={{val="Paladin's Shoulders",id="70000DB1"},{val="Paladin's Hat",id="70000DB0"},{val="Sturdy Took Dagger",id="70000DB3"},{val="Paladin's Club",id="70000DB2"},{val="Paladin's Earring",id="70000DAE"},{val="Paladin's Bracelet",id="70000DAF"}},category="Shire",id=2656,scope="n/a",prev={1574},name="Took and a Tower",arcs="Took and Tower",level=12,minlevel=8,b="Esilia Took",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGerebert Took is inside Esilia's house.\nEsilia Took thanked you for rescuing her cousin and told you that Gerebert spun an astounding tale. She recommended that you go inside and speak with him yourself.\n* Talk to Gerebert Took\nObj 2:\nPaladin Took, the Thain, is at the Great Smials in Tuckborough.\nEsilia Took sent you into her house to speak with her cousin, Gerebert. Gerebert told you a fantastic tale about a terrible tower in far away lands, where he saw a strange, robed man named Sharkey. He asked you to tell his story to the Thain.\n* Talk to Thain Paladin Took II"},
{area="Arador's End",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Your war-host claims to have enough metal now that the mine is in-service and under your control, but the picks used by the goblins are dulled with time and the wood rots out from their hands.",category="Isendeep Mine",id=2657,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Tools for the Mine",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Taskmaster Bárzqhosh",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nKindling can be found in the Grimwood.\nTaskmaster Bárzqhosh tasked you with garnering enough wood to repair the picks used to pull ore from the Isendeep.\n* Return to Taskmaster Bárzqhosh at the Isendeep Mine ()\n* Turn in Grimwood-kindling",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="The Flaming Deeps",money={{val="44s 80c"}},d="The Forges of Khazad-dûm were once the heart of smithing within Moria. Here, the mighty dwarf-smiths would work the mithril and forge their greastest wonders. In the time since its fall, the Forges of Khazad-dûm have been flooded with massive lava-floes and populated by the Orcs of Moria and their troll and goblin-labourers. Here the Orc war-host hammers away incessantly, as they built their weapons and siege-engines in preparation for their war against Lothlórien.",mobs={{locations={"13.42S, 108.08W"},name="Sigir"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2658,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Tools from the Past",arcs="Forges of Khazad-dûm",level=59,minlevel=57,b="Sigir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Forges of Khazad-dûm lie to the south-west of Anazârmekhem.\nSigir is disgusted that dwarf-tools are being used to forge the Orcs' weapons of war. He tasked you with rescuing the tools from their ignoble fate within the confines of the Forges of Khazad-dûm.\n* Talk to Sigir at Anazârmekhem\n* Collect dwarf-tools (1 Dwarf-tool)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={3219},area="Eastern Malenhad",zone="Angmar",money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="Avar, the leader of the dwarf-outpost at Gabilshathûr, told you of their desperate situation. The Orcs have discovered their hidden holding and are felling trees to the north. Avar fears they are taking the trees to construct siege-weapons, with which they can assault and destroy the outpost.",category="Angmar",id=2659,scope="n/a",prev={2884},name="Tools of the Orcs",arcs="Schemes of Sabotage",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Avar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orc-camp of Ongbishúk lies to the north-east of Gabilshathûr.\nAvar asked you to take the tools of the Orcs to help slow down their efforts to construct siege-weapons.\n* Bring the Orc-tools to Avar\n* Turn in Orc-axe\n* Turn in Orc-pick\n* Turn in Orc-saw"},
{area="Tinnudir",zone="Evendim",money={{val="18s 55c"}},d="Mundaric Sandheaver is concerned about the salamanders that crawl among the dunes of the Barandalf.",category="Evendim",id=2660,scope="n/a",name="Tooth and Scale",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=32,minlevel=27,b="Mundaric Sandheaver",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSalamanders slither among the dunes and sands of the Barandalf, north and east of Dwaling.\nMundaric Sandheaver wants you to defeat salamanders in the Barandalf and bring him their sand-crusted teeth.\n* Turn in Sand-crusted Tooth\nObj 2:\nMundaric Sandheaver is at Dwaling.\nYou have collected the teeth that Mundaric Sandheaver asked you to gather and have thinned the population of deadly salamanders that make dangerous the sands of the Barandalf. You should return now to him so he may study the teeth.\n* Talk to Mundaric Sandheaver\n* Turn in Sand-crusted Tooth",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={1611},reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="Torogethir monitors the pass from the Northdowns into Evendim, and watches over the fortresses of Fornost and Ost Heryn.",mobs={{locations={"10.30S, 60.01W"},name="Torogethir"}},selectoneof={{val="Arnorian Scholar's Cloak",id="700261D8"},{val="Dunedain Hunter's Cloak",id="700261BE"},{val="Dunedain Fighter's Cloak",id="700260D6"},{val="Annuminas Watcher's Cloak",id="7002619F"},{val="Dunedain Stalker's Cloak",id="70025D6E"},{val="Annuminas Steward's Cloak",id="70025FBC"},{val="Cloak of the Dunedain Runner",id="700264EE"},{val="Wandering Minstrel's Cape",id=70026272},{val="City Councilor's Cape",id="700264A4"}},category="Evendim",id=2661,scope="n/a",prev={2272},name="Torogethir's Charge",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=34,minlevel=29,b="Orchalwë",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTorogethir's camp is along the road to the Northdowns, west of Tinnudir and north of Ost Heryn.\nOrchalwë asked you to find Torogethir and help him in his efforts to solve the problems facing Ost Heryn.\n* Talk to Torogethir"},
{["next"]={1794},area="The Water-works",zone="Moria",reputation={{val="+300 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},money={{val="27s 30c"}},d="You have discovered the torso of the statue of Helgi Goblinbane.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2662,scope="n/a",prev={1976},name="Torso of Legend",level=57,minlevel=52,b="Statue Torso-piece",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nÁguti is at the Rotting Cellar to the north.\nÁguti will want to know you found the final piece of the shattered statue.\n* Talk to Águti in the Rotting Cellar"},
{money={{val="25s 20c"}},d="Haflithi has asked you to check on the progress of the dwarf-expedition at the Chamber of the Crossroads, in Durin's Way. Once there, you should speak with Líkmund.",category="Moria Upper Levels",id=2663,scope="n/a",prev={3225},name="To the Chamber of the Crossroads",level=51,minlevel=46,b="Haflithi",repeatable="No",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nTo reach the Chamber of the Crossroads, head east through twisting caverns into the Great Delving. Once there, you must find your way to the northern end of the cavern, and cross the great bridge that passes through the Dwarf-lords' Gate. After the gate, you'll turn west, then north, then east - each in short order. This should bring you to the Chamber of the Crossroads.\n* Speak with Líkmund"},
{money={{val="25s 20c"}},d="There is much work to be done for the Longbeards to reclaim their ancient home of Moria.",category="Moria Central Halls",id=2664,scope="n/a",prev={3225},name="To the Deep Descent",level=51,minlevel=46,b="Athils",repeatable="No",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nTo reach the Dolven-view from Durin's Threshold, head east through twisting caverns into the Great Delving. Once there, go east into the cavern and then south up a short stair followed by a long upwards slope lit by torches -- this path leads to the Dolven-view. Immediately upon reaching the Dolven-view proper, turn south and exit the cavern through a hewn tunnel, this will lead through the Stone Council chamber into the Silvertine Lodes -- just a short ways south of there you should come upon the Deep Descent expedition.\nAthils has instructed you to find the Deep Descent expedition and speak with Thalfar.\n* Talk to Thalfar at the Deep Descent"},
{area="Trestlebridge",zone="The North Downs",d="Captain Trotter of Trestlebridge has received a message from an old companion of his -- Constable Bram Ashleaf out in the Lone-lands -- asking for help dealing with a wave of lawlessness and worse.\nSpeak with Constable Ashleaf on his behalf and see what aid you can offer him.",mobs={{locations={"17.67S, 53.89W"},name="Captain Trotter"}},category="North Downs",id=2665,scope="n/a",name="To the Lonely Frontier",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Captain Trotter",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpeak with Captain Trotter in Trestlebridge to requisition a fast horse to the Forsaken Inn in the western Lonelands.\n* Talk to Captain Trotter",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+300 with The Grey Company"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Fordirith",money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="Braigiar has asked you to forge ahead to find Saeradan's encampment in the Windfells to the south. The southern Dunlendings are reported to have a large watchtower and encampment in this region, watching the Great North Road for unwanted intrusion from the direction of Bree or the Shire.",mobs={{locations={"63.82S, 17.45W"},name="Saeradan"},{locations={"58.69S, 14.58W"},name="Braigiar"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2666,scope="n/a",prev={198,368},name="To The Windfells: Saeradan's Encampment",receive={{val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Braigiar",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSaeradan is at Echad Saeradan in the Windfells, south of Echad Dagoras.\nBraigiar instructed you to find Saeradan and lend him your aid.\n* Talk to Saeradan at Echad Saeradan",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Rivendell Valley",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="7s 84c"}},d="Elf-scouts are encamped at Thorenhad, charged with patrolling the Trollshaws for signs of evil.",mobs={{locations={"30.86S, 5.26W"},name="Anhebir"},{locations={"31.64S, 15.19W"},name="Elrohir"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2667,scope="n/a",name="To Thorenhad",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Anhebir",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThorenhad is a ruin atop a hill north of the bear-dens of the Bruinen Gorges. It is to the east of Barachen's camp, and some distance west of Rivendell.\nAnhebir has sent you to Thorenhad, to report to Elrond's son, Elrohir.\n* Talk to Elrohir",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Coldfells",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Your education continues with a trip far to the east to Tirith Rhaw, a tower in lands controlled by the enemy.",category="Ettenmoors",id=2668,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={2766},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="To Tirith Rhaw",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Nartul",repeatable="No",faction="Mon",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTirith Rhaw lay far to the east beyond the Hoardale River.\nSoldier Nartul directed you to scout out Tirith Rhaw in the Coldfells.\n* Find Tirith Rhaw\nObj 2:\nSoldier Nartul awaits your return at Gramsfoot.\nYou discovered and scouted the area surrounding Tirith Rhaw.\n* Return to Soldier Nartul at Gramsfoot ( )"},
{area="Hoardale",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="You have been ushered out on a simple scouting mission to find the central keep called Tol Ascarnen.",category="Ettenmoors",id=2669,scope="n/a",t="Raid",prev={2766},destinypoints={{val=125}},name="To Tol Ascarnen",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Soldier Nartul",repeatable="No",faction="Mon",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTol Ascarnen is on an island in the Hoardale River, east of Gramsfoot.\nYou were ordered to find and scout out Tol Ascarnen.\n* Find Tol Ascarnen\nObj 2:\nSoldier Nartul awaits your return at Gramsfoot.\nYou discovered and scouted the area around Tol Ascarnen.\n* Return to Soldier Nartul at Gramsfoot ( )"},
{area="Meluinen",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="16s"}},d="The Orcs of Gurzlum in the Kingsfell use spider venom to coat their blades and arrows.",mobs={{locations={"13.70S, 44.73W"},name="Gandelin"}},category="North Downs",id=2670,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1905},name="Touch of Corruption",receive={{val="Aegor",id="700069D9"}},level=28,minlevel=23,b="Gandelin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Ongbúrz Orcs can be found in their fortification at Gurzlum, on the rise beside the waterfall north-west of Lin Giliath.\nGandelin asked you to slay the Ongbúrz-defiler and return with the Ongbúrz venom-pouches.\n* Turn in Skirmisher's Venom-pouch\n* Kill 1 Ongbúrz Defiler\nObj 2:\nGandelin is back at Lin Giliath.\nGandelin asked you to slay the Ongbúrz-defiler and return with the Ongbúrz venom-pouches.\n* Talk to Gandelin\n* Turn in Skirmisher's Venom-pouch"},
{area="Low Lands",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Gailthin has identified the giants who have mastery over the mammoths of the Misty Mountains and has asked that you put an end to this dangerous alliance.",mobs={{locations={"20.44S, 97.20W"},name="Gailthin"},{locations={"26.85S, 5.37W"},name="Golhador"}},selectoneof={{val="Madfurr's End",id=70003262},{val="Avornechor",id=70003266},{val="Kulgurz's Punishment",id=70003264},{val="Sukdyr's Fall",id=70003263},{val="Golhador's Spear",id=70016196}},category="Misty Mountains",id=2671,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={873},name="Towering Champions",arcs="Mighty Giants Indeed",receive={{val="Giant Ward",id=70003265}},level=43,minlevel=38,b="Gailthin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Giant's Needle is in the heart of the Giant Halls of the Misty Mountains, southeast of the Dwarf stronghold of Gabilazan.\nMadfurr is east of the Giant's Needle, in a cleft of the rock. Sukdyr is north-east of the Giant's Needle, among the stony paths. Kulgurz is on the high slopes above the Giant's Needle.\nGailthin the Elf, once emissary to the giants of the Misty Mountains, has told you the locations of the powerful giant-champions responsible for taming the ferocious mammoths.\n* Kill 1 Madfurr\n* Kill 1 Sukdyr\n* Kill 1 Kulgurz\nObj 2:\nGolhador is in the pass north of Rivendell that winds into the Misty Mountains.\nGolhador will be pleased to hear that you have defeated the mighty champions responsible for taming the ferocious mammoths.\n* Talk to Golhador"},
{["next"]={179},zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="27s 65c"}},d="Celofa has sent you out to the Western Deeps in search of ancient dwarf-style riddles.  Apparently clues can be found on the bookshelves there, but Celofa warns that making too much noise may attract the nearby Orcs.",category="Burglar",id=2672,scope="n/a",prev={5},name="Tracking Treasure",arcs="The Path of the Mischief Maker",level=58,pois={{locations={"9.20S, 107.15W","8.67S, 107.64W","9.03S, 106.91W","9.20S, 107.20W","9.15S, 107.44W"},name="Dwarf-scroll"}},minlevel=58,b="Celofa",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Western Deeps are north-west from the Redhorn Lodes.  Celofa suggested that you start your search between Gabil-mamach and the Hall of Flowing Water.\nCelofa has asked you to search through any stacks of scrolls you may find in the Western Deeps between Gabil-mamach and the Hall of Flowing Water, but she warned that your search may alert the Orcs of that area to your presence if you are not careful.\n* Use Dwarf-scroll\n* Use Dwarf-scroll\nObj 2:\nCelofa is at the Foundations of Stone, south-east of the Western Deeps and the Redhorn Lodes.\nYou should return to Celofa with the scroll you found.\n* Return to Celofa with the scroll\n*",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="7s 98c"}},d="You have been encouraged to learn the lay of the lands around Lake Nenuial, so you may better find your way around its shores.",mobs={{locations={"12.71S, 67.00W"},name="Cúlith"},{locations={"20.05S, 96.98W"},name="Dagfinn"},{locations={"18.84N, 72.37W"},name="Okko"},{locations={"29.91S, 5.90W"},name="Mallenhadh"},{locations={"31.86S, 51.28W"},name="Flambard Took"},{locations={"34.15S, 75.05W"},name="Bolo Boffin"},{locations={"9.52S, 41.07W"},name="Gaellant"},{locations={"12.48S, 67.31W"},name="Horace Roxhythe"},{locations={"28.14S, 92.17W"},name="Erydhriel"},{locations={"28.74S, 49.31W","28.75S, 49.31W"},name="Juniper Smith"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Improved Strong Trap",id="7000A6A2"},{q="(x3)",val="Polished Quick Trap",id="7000A69F"}},category="Hunter",id=2673,scope="n/a",requiredclasses="Hunter",name="Tracks Through Evendim",receive={{val="Guide to Evendim",id="7000A6DC"}},level=36,c={"* The arrow head is located in the bushes beside the High King's Crossing [13.7S, 64.8W]."},pois={{locations={"12.17S, 66.33W","13.10S, 65.21W","13.75S, 64.78W","12.46S, 65.82W","13.36S, 64.49W","12.80S, 64.90W"},name="Subtle Tracks"}},minlevel=36,b="Flambard Took",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHorace Roxhythe is at the Ranger-camp on the island of Tinnudir, in Evendim.\nYou have been told to speak with Horace Roxhythe, a skilled hunter who can teach you the secrets of finding your way throughout Evendim.\n* Talk to Horace Roxhythe\nObj 2:\nHorace Roxhythe hid one of his arrow-heads somewhere in Evendim. He crossed from the island of Tinnudir to the mainland on the stone bridge.\nYou have been challenged to follow Horace's trail and recover the arrow-head he hid somewhere in Evendim to prove you are ready for his teachings.\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\n* Find/Use Subtle Tracks\nObj 3:\nHorace Roxhythe is at the Ranger-camp on the island of Tinnudir.\nYou have found the arrow-head that Horace hid in Evendim and should return it to him so he will recognize your skill as a hunter.\n* Talk to Horace Roxhythe\n* Turn in Scratched Arrow-head"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="55s 30c"}},d="How they found their way into Moria is unclear, but the forces of the White Hand are now entrenched in the Orc communities of Khazad-dûm. However, it appears to Thithrand that they wish to claim leadership over Moria for themselves.",mobs={{locations={"10.99S, 106.77W"},name="Thithrand"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2674,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Traitors in the Midst",arcs="Traitors in the Midst",level=58,minlevel=57,b="Thithrand",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nIlzkâl and Nardur can be found in the Grand Stair, north-east of the Orc-watch.\nThithrand believes that the Uruk-hai Nardur and Ilzkâl may be planning to revolt against Igash and steal the tribute kept within his throne for themselves.\n* Defeat Ilzkâl\n* Defeat Nardur\nObj 2:\nThithrand is at the Orc-watch, south-west of the Grand Stair.\nYou should return to Thithrand with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Thithrand at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2751},area="South Trollshaws",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="The Elf Barachen and his friends have been told to scout the South Trollshaws for signs of evil and have learned that a company of dwarves bound for the area may have fallen to misfortune.",mobs={{locations={"34.04S, 20.16W"},name="Barachen"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2675,scope="n/a",name="Trampling Hooves",arcs="A Gift from the Dwarves",receive={{val="Longham",id="70002E1C"}},level=33,minlevel=28,b="Barachen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBoars can be found in the South Trollshaws, west of Barachen's camp.\nBarachen asked you to search for the missing dwarves among the boars to the west of his camp. If the dwarves fell afoul of the creatures, some sign may still remain.\n* Defeat boars in the South Trollshaws (10)\nObj 2:\nBarachen is at his camp in the South Trollshaws, south of the road and in the shadow of tall cliffs.\nBarachen is waiting to hear whether you found any sign of the missing dwarves among the boars of the Trollshaws.\n* Talk to Barachen"},
{["next"]={1293},area="Ashenslades",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+300 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="To the south of Dol Goldur, Danfennas seeks out information regarding the pale quality of the trees around the Ashenslades. He has joined several others in Helethir, a small camp to the south of Dol Guldur, to investigate the area.",mobs={{locations={"16.08S, 44.59W"},name="Danfennas"},{locations={"17.71S, 48.28W"},name="Perindúr"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2676,scope="n/a",prev={728,2456,1949},name="Travel to Helethir",receive={{val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=65,minlevel=60,b="Perindúr",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDanfennas is at Helethir, north-east of Mithechad.\nPerindúr has asked you to speak with his friend Danfennas regarding the plague upon the trees of the Ashenslades.\n* Talk to Danfennas at Helethir"},
{["next"]={2475},area="Fasach-larran",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Tasgall has come up with a plan by which the threat of the hill-beasts may be greatly lessened.",category="Angmar",id=2677,scope="n/a",prev={2092},name="Treacherous Hunger",arcs="Strange Beasts",level=43,minlevel=38,b="Tasgall",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCrawlers can be found throughout Fasach-larran.\nTasgall has asked you collect remains from the crawlers of Fasach-larran so he may create bait to lure out Bangrath and Murragrath.\n* Turn in Crawler Remains\nObj 2:\nTasgall's campsite is north of Aughaire and southeast of Nád Nathair.\nYou have collected the remains of several crawlers from Fasach-larran, and should bring them now to Tasgall.\n* Turn in Crawler Remains"},
{["next"]={1506},area="Men Erain",zone="Evendim",money={{val="33s 60c"}},d="Helechír is worried that other Dùnedain ruins in Men Erain may also come under attack.",mobs={{locations={"15.31S, 66.16W"},name="Helechír"},{locations={"15.34S, 66.15W"},name="Sid Waring"}},category="Evendim",id=2678,scope="n/a",t="Small Fellowship",prev={424},name="Treasure in the Ruins",arcs="Breakfast in the Ruins",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=39,c={"* Sid Waring can be found in a small island in Men Erain [15.3S, 66.2W]\n* Chests One and Two can be found at [15.7S, 66.3W]\n* Chests Three and Four can be found at [16.7S, 66.6W]"},pois={{locations={"16.73S, 66.57W","16.65S, 66.64W","15.66S, 66.26W","15.72S, 66.32W"},name="Stolen Relics"}},minlevel=34,b="Helechír",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSid Waring's camp is in Men Erain, on a small island a short distance south of the steps leading up to Alfred Whitley's camp. Helechír is a little north-west of the Ranger camp on the island of Tinnudir, north-east of Men Erain.\nHelechír has asked you to warn a man named Sid Waring of the possibility of attack by tomb-robbers.\n* Talk to Sid Waring\nObj 2:\nSome of the stolen relics are on an island next to Sid Waring's camp; others were carried to another island camp  to the south in Men Erain. Helechír is a little north-west of the Ranger camp on the island of Tinnudir, north-east of Men Erain.\nSid Waring has been wounded, but he remains hale enough to tell you he was attacked by men he knew out of Ost Forod. He mentioned a leader called Brychan the Bold and asked you to recover the relics that were stolen from the ruin he was hired to protect.\n* Bring stolen relics to Helechír\n* Collect stolen relics (4 Stolen Relics )"},
{area="Itä-mâ",zone="Forochel",reputation={{val="+1200 with Lossoth of Forochel"}},money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="Long ago, lost in an unknown battle, the Jewel of Ice was the most revered treasure of the Lossoth. Unbeknownst to all, it has been held in Angmar and was used to ransom the obediance of the tribe who was once entrusted with its protection and eternally shamed by its loss.",mobs={{locations={"19.54N, 71.99W"},name="Rikitsa"},{locations={"11.45N, 69.70W"},name="Esko"}},selectoneof={{val="Forochel's Splendour",id="7000E5D1"},{val="Forochel's Majesty",id="7000E5CF"},{val="Forochel's Glory",id="7000E5CC"}},category="Forochel",id=2679,scope="n/a",prev={558},name="Treasure of the Lossoth",level=49,c={"* Rikitsa is at Sûri-kylä"},minlevel=44,b="Esko",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRikitsa is at Sûri-kylä, well north of Pynti-peldot.\nEsko has asked you to bring the Jewel of Ice to Rikitsa at the Council.\n* Talk to Rikitsa\n* Turn in Jewel of Ice"},
{["next"]={1790},area="High Hollin",zone="Eregion",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="You recovered several of the memorial statues left in Barad Morlas by the Elves of Rivendell, but many more treasures remain lost there...or had until the half-orcs came.",mobs={{locations={"46.94S, 12.50W"},name="Ladenthir"}},category="Eregion",id=2680,scope="n/a",prev={1115},name="Treasures from Barad Morlas",arcs="The Ruins of Barad Morlas",level=49,c={"* Barad Morlas is at [48.1S, 13.7W]"},minlevel=44,b="Ladenthir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalf-orcs can be found in Barad Morlas, south-west of Echad Eregion. Ladenthir is at Echad Eregion, north-east of Barad Morlas.\nLadenthir believes that the half-orcs have uncovered many Elf-relics at Barad Morlas and asks that you defeat them and recover the relics.\n* Bring the relics to Ladenthir at Echad Eregion\n* Turn in Elf-relic"},
{["next"]={2312},area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="11s 50c"}},d="Many old treasures from before the days of Fornost's downfall still remain in the Fields of Fornost.",mobs={{locations={"13.04S, 55.28W"},name="Colbert the Mad"}},category="North Downs",id=2681,scope="n/a",prev={2353},name="Treasures from the Fields",arcs="Mincham's Dream",level=25,pois={{locations={"10.34S, 52.66W"},name="Old Chest"}},minlevel=20,b="Colbert the Mad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe chest your key opens is supposed to be in some ghost-infested ruins to the north-east of Mincham's camp.\nColbert has given you a key which he says will open a treasure in the Fields of Fornost.\n* Use Old Chest\nObj 2:\nColbert is at Mincham's camp.\nYou retrieved a bracelet from the chest, which Colbert might have a use for.\n* Talk to Colbert the Mad\n* Turn in Golden Bracelet\n* Turn in Colbert's Key"},
{["next"]={2698},reputation={{val="+1200 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Barandalf",money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="Barad Tharsír was once an important shipping port that linked Evendim with the south along the Baranduin.",category="Evendim",id=2682,scope="n/a",name="Treasures of Barad Tharsír",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Silver Arnorian Coin",id="7002663E"}},level=33,pois={{locations={"15.03S, 60.52W"},name="Loaded Cart"}},minlevel=28,b="Daerol",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarad Tharsír is across the Baranduin, south-east of the colossus.\nDaerol asked you to return to Barad Tharsír, enter the storeroom, and discover what the robbers are doing there.\n* Use Loaded Cart\nObj 2:\nDaerol is at the colossus, north-west of Barad Tharsír.\nDaerol will want to know that the robbers were excavating the ruins, and the carts were full of nothing but dirt and rubble.\n* Talk to Daerol",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={576},area="Northern Barrow-downs",zone="Bree-land",reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},money={{val="3s 75c"}},d="Strewn throughout the lore you discovered in previous efforts for Tobold Leafcutter were stories of a great Cardolan treasure. He believes that two brothers, warriors of Arnor, fought and recovered the treasure and brought it to the Northern Barrow.",mobs={{locations={"31.74S, 56.24W"},name="Tobold Leafcutter"}},selectoneof={{val="Skunkwood's Shield",id="7000340F"},{val="Dagorcham (Level 19)",id=70003410}},category="Bree-land",id=2683,scope="n/a",prev={718},name="Treasures of Cardolan",arcs="History in the Barrow-downs",level=19,minlevel=14,b="Tobold Leafcutter",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou may find a chest resting at the Northern Barrow, the northernmost barrow of the Barrow-downs. Tobold Leafcutter waits for you between the Old Forest and Barrow-downs.\nTobold Leafcutter has asked you to search the Northern Barrow for more lore. He hopes that lore from the Men of Cardolan may have survived the long years since the Great Plague in a chest. If you find such lore, you should bring it to Tobold.\n* Bring the ancient journal to Tobold Leafcutter\n* Turn in Ancient Journal"},
{area="Trestlebridge",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="4s"}},d="Frideric the Elder tribesman of the Eglain is under threat of attack by the Orc hordes.",mobs={{locations={"31.49S, 29.50W"},name="Frideric the Elder"},{locations={"17.44S, 53.87W"},name="Guardsman Otley"}},category="North Downs",id=2684,scope="n/a",name="Trestlebridge to Ost Guruth",level=20,minlevel=18,b="Guardsman Otley",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nHead down the Greenway from Trestlebridge and then east along the east-west road.\nGo to Ost Guruth and talk to Frideric the Elder.\n* Talk to Frideric the Elder",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+700 with Algraig, Men of Enedwaith"}},zone="Enedwaith",area="Thrór's Coomb",money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Near Pruv Cadlus, you have discovered a strange area filled with food and other supplies.",mobs={{locations={"67.43S, 13.92W"},name="Gronu"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2685,scope="n/a",name="Tribute to the Masters",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Tribute Pile",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGronu is at his camp, north of Harndirion.\nYou should return to Gronu and tell him that the Draig-lûth have been gathering supplies near Amon Mîn.\n* Talk to Gronu at his camp",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tol Ascarnen",zone="Ettenmoors",d="Tyrant Trintrû at Tol Ascarnen is deserving of praise and tribute. The tribute which the tyrant desires most is the flesh of Men.",category="Tol Ascarnen",id=2686,scope="n/a",destinypoints={{val=250}},name="Tribute to the Tyrant",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Quartermaster Apsduf",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nMen can be found throughout the Ettenmoors.\nQuartermaster Apsduf ordered you to gather Man-flesh as tribute to the Tyrant at Tol Ascarnen.\n* Return to Quartermaster Apsduf at Tol Ascarnen ()\n* Turn in Leg of Men",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2022},d="Pada has tasked you with recovering an ancient instrument from an Orc within the Foundations of Stone. He wishes to see your skill so that he can assess how best to teach you what is left to be taught.",category="Minstrel",id=2687,scope="n/a",prev={2},name="Triumphant Spirit",arcs="The Path of the Watcher of Resolve",level=58,minlevel=58,b="Pada",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orc Shîk can be found in the Foundations of Stone. Pada mentioned looking for Shîk in the pools of water with waterfalls along the northern edges of the Foundations of Stone.\nPada has requested that you venture forth to recover an excellent and famous instrument from the unworthy Orcs to help further your final education as a Minstrel.\n* Bring the instrument to Pada\n* Turn in Old Bagpipes",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Moria",area="Zelem-melek",money={{val="44s 24c"}},d="Trolls are a formidable opponent and in Moria, the trolls have had much time to develop thicker hides and worse tempers. It falls to Ossur to watch the comings and goings of the trolls and their handlers at the Grand Stair. In the time since he began watching, he has seen one troll that seemed more frightening and deadly than the others and a throng of handlers who kept the savage trolls at bay.",mobs={{locations={"11.20S, 106.74W"},name="Ossur"}},category="Moria Central Halls",id=2688,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",name="Troll-handlers",arcs="Drummers of the Deep",receive={{val="Plain Heritage Rune of Legend",id="7001F259"}},level=58,minlevel=57,b="Ossur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Grand Stair is north-east of the Orc-watch.\nThe Uruk troll-handlers should be slain for the safety of the dwarves who have come to reclaim Khazad-dûm.\n* Defeat Gazathrûg Handlers\nObj 2:\nOssur the dwarf can be found at the Orc-watch.\nYou defeated a good number of the Uruk troll-handlers, but the trolls were unmoved and did not begin attacking other tribes of Orcs within the Grand Stair.\n* Talk to Ossur at the Orc-watch",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Mirk-eaves",zone="Mirkwood",reputation={{val="+700 with Malledhrim"}},money={{val="45s 36c"}},d="The Elves of the Golden Host seek a way to cripple the Orcs of Durbúrz-stazg.",mobs={{locations={"15.11S, 61.35W"},name="Tethafnel"}},category="Mirkwood",id=2689,scope="n/a",prev={802},destinypoints={{val=500}},name="Trolling the Hills",receive={{q="(x4)",val="Malledhrim Bronze Feather",id="7001F099"}},level=61,minlevel=56,b="Tethafnel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe eastern gate of Durbúrz-stazg lies to the north of Echad Sirion.\nTethafnel has asked you to defeat the Olog-hai warrior Skûm at Durbúrz-stazg. You will need to enter the encampment through the eastern gate.\n* Defeat Skûm at Durbúrz-stazg\nObj 2:\nEchad Sirion lies to the south of Durbúrz-stazg.\nYou should return to Tethafnel with news of your victory against the olog-hai Skûm.\n* Talk to Tethafnel at Echad Sirion"},
{area="Gramsfoot",zone="The Ettenmoors",d="Patrol the Ettenmoors in search of the enemy. You must patrol for 60 minutes. After 60 minutes you will be returned to your post.",category="Ettenmoors",id=2690,scope="n/a",name="Trolls in the Ettenmoors",level=50,minlevel=45,repeatable="No",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nPatrol the Ettenmoors.\n* Patrol the Ettenmoors\nQuest: Trolls in the Ettenmoors\nCategory: Ettenmoors\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 45\nDescription\nPatrol the Ettenmoors in search of the enemy. You must patrol for 60 minutes. After 60 minutes you will be returned to your post.\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nPatrol the Ettenmoors.\n* Patrol the Ettenmoors\nQuest: Trolls in the Ettenmoors\nCategory: Ettenmoors\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 45\nDescription\nPatrol the Ettenmoors in search of the enemy. You must patrol for 60 minutes. After 60 minutes you will be returned to your post.\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nPatrol the Ettenmoors.\n* Patrol the Ettenmoors\nQuest: Trolls in the Ettenmoors\nCategory: Ettenmoors\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 45\nDescription\nPatrol the Ettenmoors in search of the enemy. You must patrol for 60 minutes. After 60 minutes you will be returned to your post.\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nPatrol the Ettenmoors.\n* Patrol the Ettenmoors\nQuest: Trolls in the Ettenmoors\nCategory: Ettenmoors\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 45\nDescription\nPatrol the Ettenmoors in search of the enemy. You must patrol for 60 minutes. After 60 minutes you will be returned to your post.\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nPatrol the Ettenmoors.\n* Patrol the Ettenmoors\nQuest: Trolls in the Ettenmoors\nCategory: Ettenmoors\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 45\nDescription\nPatrol the Ettenmoors in search of the enemy. You must patrol for 60 minutes. After 60 minutes you will be returned to your post.\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nPatrol the Ettenmoors.\n* Patrol the Ettenmoors"},
{["next"]={1971},area="Buckland",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Ted Reedy has asked you to collect some trophies to place upon the walls of Adso's inn. He is willing to pay you for your assistance.",mobs={{locations={"31.57S, 62.54W"},name="Ted Reedy"}},category="Bree-land",id=2691,scope="n/a",name="Trophies for the Walls",arcs="A Right Proper Place",receive={{val="Adso's Axe",id=70009107}},level=15,minlevel=11,b="Ted Reedy",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBears, boars, and wolves roam the Bree-fields north of Buckland, between the Brandy Hills and the border of the Old Forest.\nTed Reedy has requested that you collect materials that will help to give Adso's Inn a rustic feel.\n* Return trophies to Ted Reedy in Buckland\n* Turn in Pristine Bear Carcass\n* Turn in Pristine Boar-head\n* Turn in Pristine Wolf Carcass\n* Turn in Coarse Bear-hide"},
{area="Aughaire",zone="Angmar",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Raith has petitioned the chieftain of Aughaire for greater action against the Trév Duvárdain, and Crannog has recommended that you prove yourself by facing the dangers of Tór Gailvin.",mobs={{locations={"0.09S, 40.13W"},name="Raith"}},selectoneof={{q="(x2)",val="Refined Celebrant Ointment",id="70008D08"},{q="(x2)",val="Refined Athelas Extract",id="70008CF7"}},category="Angmar",id=2692,scope="n/a",name="Trophies of War",receive={{val="Gem of Búth Sánkhas",id="7000EAE1"}},level=43,c={"* Duvárdain Berserkers and Duvárdain Sentries are at Tor Gailvin"},minlevel=38,b="Raith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe fortress of Tór Gailvin is north-east of Aughaire, and its defenders carry the skull-amulets and bloodstone-pendants that Raith wants.\nRaith of Aughaire has asked you to wrest signs of the loyalty of the Trév Duvárdain to Angmar from the defenders of Tór Gailvin.\n* Bring skull-amulets and bloodstone-pendants to Raith\n* Turn in Skull-amulet\n* Turn in Bloodstone-pendant"},
{["next"]={698},area="Trestlebridge",zone="The North Downs",reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},d="Reynard Trotter is concerned about recent developments in the area. The guards reported hearing a terrible noise during the night. Aggy Digweed, one of the guards, wanted to speak to someone about the event.\nTravel to the far side of the Trestlespan and speak with Aggy. Captain Trotter said she'd have more information for you.",mobs={{locations={"16.15S, 53.49W"},name="Aggy Digweed"},{locations={"17.67S, 53.89W"},name="Captain Trotter"}},category="North Downs",id=2693,scope="n/a",name="Trotter's Task",arcs="The Black Fire",level=24,minlevel=19,b="Captain Trotter",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAggy Digweed is to the north of the Trestlespan.\nCaptain Trotter suggests that Aggy Digweed can shed more light on recent events.\n* Find and speak with Aggy Digweed",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Tyrn Fornech",money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="Spring Standish is concerned about the lack of trade with the Snowmen of Forochel ever since tomb-robbers seized the gate at Cirith Rhîw.",mobs={{locations={"7.75S, 64.27W"},name="Spring Standish"}},category="Evendim",id=2694,scope="n/a",name="Trouble at Cirith Rhîw",receive={{q="(x2)",val="Bronze Arnorian Coin",id="7002663D"}},level=37,minlevel=32,b="Spring Standish",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe captain of a robber-band maintains control of the road leading to the gate at Cirith Rhîw, north of Ost Forod.\nSpring Standish has asked you to defeat a tomb-robber captain at Cirith Rhîw, in hopes that the rest of his band will disperse.\n* Defeat tomb-robber captain at Cirith Rhîw\nObj 2:\nSpring Standish is at Ost Forod, the old watch-post in the hills of Tyrn Fornech, south of Cirith Rhîw.\nYou have defeated the tomb-robber captain at Cirith Rhîw and should return to Spring with news of your victory.\n* Talk to Spring Standish",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="",zone="Ered Luin",money={{val="90c"}},d="Trouble arose at Nen Hilith when wolves made their way into the valley. Workers gathering the fallen wood of the vale were driven out, and the sickle-flies, mostly a nuisance, fled the vale and infested the nearby wood. Glade-wardens have come to the vale of Nen Hilith to attempt to discern the cause of the disturbance.",selectoneof={{val="Ovorlas's Guard",id="70019C2A"},{val="Ovorlas's Helm",id="70019C20"}},category="Ered Luin",id=2695,scope="n/a",name="Trouble at Nen Hilith",arcs="Trouble at Nen Hilith",level=6,minlevel=2,b="Ovorlas",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlavrolnen and Helhathel are at the Elf-camp in Nen Hilith.\nOvorlas is pleased at your arrival and has set you to earning the favour of his assistants, Glavrolnen and Helhathel, in the vale of Nen Hilith.\n* Earn Helhathel's favour\n* Earn Glavrolnen's favour\nObj 2:\nOvorlas is at the Elf-camp in Nen Hilith.\nNow that you have earned the favour of Glavrolnen and Helhathel, you should return to Ovorlas.\n* Talk to Ovorlas at Nen Hilith"},
{area="Nain Enidh",zone="The Lone-lands",d="Frideric the Elder has recieved an urgent request from an old companion of his -- Captain Trotter of Trestlebridge -- requesting any aid that he might muster from Ost Guruth in staving off a threatened Orkish incursion upon the town.\nSpeak with Captain Trotter and see what aid you can offer him!",mobs={{locations={"31.49S, 29.50W"},name="Frideric the Elder"}},category="Lone-lands",id=2696,scope="n/a",name="Trouble at Trestlebridge",c={"*"},level=22,minlevel=17,b="Frideric the Elder",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpeak with Friderick in Ost Guruth to arrange a fast mount to Trestlebridge.\nWARNING: Completing this quest will immediately send you to Trestlebridge in the North-downs - getting back is another matter...\n* Talk to Frideric the Elder",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2568},area="South Trollshaws",zone="The Trollshaws",money={{val="18s 90c"}},d="Heithur Ironfist is concerned about his missing dwarves, but he is especially worried about their cargo of historically-significant stones from Thorin's Hall bound for Glóin, and he wants them recovered.",mobs={{locations={"34.03S, 20.19W"},name="Heithur Ironfist"},{locations={"34.04S, 20.16W"},name="Barachen"}},category="Trollshaws",id=2697,scope="n/a",prev={2729},name="Trouble by the Last Bridge",arcs="A Gift from the Dwarves",level=33,minlevel=28,b="Barachen",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAlphlanc is at the Last Bridge on the western edge of the Trollshaws, where the road passes into the Lone-lands.\nBarachen has asked you to speak with Alphlanc at the Last Bridge to see if she has seen sign of the missing dwarves.\n* Talk to Alphlanc\nObj 2:\nThe Last Bridge supports the road as it winds west out of the Trollshaws and passes into the Lone-lands.\nAlphlanc has asked you to search the area immediately around the Last Bridge closely for some sign of the missing dwarves.\n* Search the area around the Last Bridge\nObj 3:\nA smashed crate lies at the foot of the Last Bridge, on the water's edge.\nYou have located a smashed crate by the Last Bridge that appears to be of dwarf-make. You should investigate further.\n* Search the shattered dwarf-crate\nObj 4:\nHeithur Ironfist is at Barachen's camp, east of the Last Bridge, on a sloping hill in the shadow of the southern cliffs. The Elf Rochwen stands on the road north of the camp, ready to aid travellers.\nHeithur will want to hear about your discovery of a shattered dwarf-crate at the base of the Last Bridge, emptied of its contents.\n* Talk to Heithur Ironfist"},
{area="Bree",zone="Bree-land",money={{val="60c"}},d="According to Barliman Butterbur, there is trouble in Buckland that could use your talents.",mobs={{locations={"31.72S, 62.63W"},name="Celandine Brandybuck"},{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Barliman Butterbur"}},category="Bree-land",id=2698,scope="n/a",name="Trouble in Buckland",level=14,minlevel=10,b="Barliman Butterbur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe propery of Newbury is in Buckland. Follow the road west from Bree until you see the Brandywine Bridge, then turn south into Buckland.\nTalk to Celandine Brandybuck at Newbury in Buckland.\n* Speak with Celandine Brandybuck at Newbury in Buckland",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={66},area="Bullroarer's Sward",zone="Evendim",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="Big Folk have bought a large amount of land in the Shire on behalf of a hobbit from the Westfarthing, and it is troubling Hob Hillbrow.",category="Evendim",id=2699,scope="n/a",prev={757},name="Trouble in Dwaling",arcs="Dwaling's Plight",level=31,minlevel=26,b="Hob Hillbrow",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nPearlina Gamgee's residence is located in Dwaling, east of Hob Hillbrow's home.\nHob Hillbrow asked you to check on the home of one his friends, Pearlina Gamgee.\n* Ensure Pearlina Gamgee's home is safe\nObj 2:\nRemove the ruffians living on Pearlina Gamgee's property.\nHob Hillbrow asked you to check on the home of one his friends, Pearlina Gamgee.\n* Defeat Chief's Watcher\nObj 3:\nHob Hillbrow is at his home at the Bullroarer's Sward in Dwaling, west of Pearlina Gamgee's property.\nYou were attacked by ruffians outside Pearlina Gamgee's residence. You should inform Hob Hillbrow.\n* Talk to Hob Hillbrow"},
{area="Thrór's Coomb",zone="Enedwaith",reputation={{val="+300 with The Grey Company"}},money={{val="11s 34c"}},d="A shadow has fallen upon the Lich Bluffs, the ancient burial grounds of the Algraig clans of Dunland and Enedwaith. The Rangers of the Grey Company have sent one of their number to investigate.",mobs={{locations={"69.39S, 13.75W"},name="Culang"},{locations={"70.57S, 15.46W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Enedwaith",id=2700,scope="n/a",name="Trouble in the Bluffs",receive={{val="Silver Token of the Wilds",id="70020A7C"}},level=65,minlevel=65,b="Culang",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMincham is located south and slightly east of Harndirion in the Lich Bluffs.\nReturn to Mincham and let him know that you have been sent to assist him.\n* Talk to Mincham in the Lich Bluffs",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Tookland",zone="The Shire",d="Tuckborough is the chief village of Tookland and home to the Thain of the Shire. Goblins and half-orcs seek to capture it in the name of Sharkey, the brigand chieftain troubling Bree-land and the Shire.",category="Skirmish",id=2701,scope="n/a",name="Trouble in Tuckborough",level=20,minlevel=15,repeatable="Yes",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe first step to breaking the siege on the Great Smials is to reclaim the south and west sides of the hill.\n* Free the southern hillside\n* Free the western hillside\n* Free Hyacinth's entranceway\nObj 2:\nWith the south and west sides in your control, it is now time to break the enemy's hold on the eastern hillside.\n* Free the eastern hillside\n* Free Edilina's entranceway\nObj 3:\nThe hillsides have been claimed for the Free Peoples. Now the courtyard has opened and may be assaulted.\n* Free the courtyard of the Great Smials\nObj 4:\nThe courtyard has fallen. Now all that remains is to defeat the leader of the assault and break the siege.\n* Defeat the half-orc at the doorway to the Great Smials and claim the Great Smials"},
{area="Global",zone="Middle-earth",reputation={{val="+700 with The Mathom Society"}},d="The Great Smials is the home of the Thain of the Shire, the figurative leader of the hobbits. Half-orcs and goblins in the service of Sharkey, the brigand leader troubling Bree-land and the Shire, seek to conquer it.",category="Skirmish",id=2702,scope="n/a",name="Trouble in Tuckborough -- Daily",level=65,minlevel=60,repeatable="Yes",instanced="No",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nFood-supplies are running low, and the hobbits holding out within the Great Smials are in need of aid.\n* Complete the Trouble in Tuckborough Skirmish"},
{area="The Horsefields",zone="Bree-land",d="Troves and Trickery is a festival tradition among many cultures, where participants try to please a number of celebrants with their tricks in order to receive a prize.",mobs={{locations={"24.62S, 51.54W"},name="Bryony Elmwood"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Fall Festival Token",id="7000C3A0"},{val="Man Mask Token",id="700108FF"}},category="Festival",id=2703,scope="n/a",name="Troves and Trickery -- Bree",level=1,minlevel=1,b="Bryony Elmwood",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThere are many folks in Bree-town who might be interested in participating in your game of Troves and Trickery.\nBryony Elmwood has challenged you to a game of Troves and Trickery. You should speak to several townspeople and perform tricks for their amusement.\n* Perform /whippitydo\n* Perform /no\n* Perform /scold\n* Perform /crazy\nObj 2:\nBryony Elmwood is just south of the Market-gate in Bree.\nYou should return to Bryony Elmwood with word of your successes at Troves and Trickery.\n* Talk to Bryony Elmwood at the Bree Festival Grounds",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Falathlorn",zone="Ered Luin",d="Troves and Trickery is a festival tradition among many cultures, where participants try to please a number of celebrants with their tricks in order to receive a prize.",mobs={{locations={"24.51S, 93.08W"},name="Gloreniel"}},selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Fall Festival Token",id="7000C3A0"},{val="Elf Mask Token",id=70010903}},category="Festival",id=2704,scope="n/a",name="Troves and Trickery -- Duillond",c={"* Emote: /look\n* Emote: /hail\n* Emote: /eat\n* Emote: /dance\n* Note: You cannot be mounted while performing this emote.\n* Emote: /handstand\n* Emote: /roar\n* Emote: /cower\n* Emote: /whippitydo"},level=1,minlevel=1,b="Gloreniel",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThere are many Elves in Duillond who might like to participate in your game of Troves and Trickery.\nGloreniel has challenged you to a game of Troves and Trickery. You should speak to several Elves and perform tricks for their amusement.\n* Perform /look\n* Perform /dance\n* Perform /eat\n* Perform /hail\nObj 2:\nGloreniel is just south of Duillond in Falathlorn.\nYou should return to Gloreniel with word of your successes in Troves and Trickery.\n* Talk to Gloreniel",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="The Hill",zone="The Shire",d="Troves and Trickery is a festival tradition among many cultures, where participants try to please a number of celebrants with their tricks in order to receive a prize.",mobs={{locations={"29.89S, 71.35W"},name="Egbert Took"}},selectoneof={{val="Hobbit Mask Token",id=70010907},{q="(x3)",val="Fall Festival Token",id="7000C3A0"}},category="Festival",id=2705,scope="n/a",name="Troves and Trickery -- the Shire",level=1,minlevel=1,b="Egbert Took",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThere are many hobbits throughout the Hobbiton-Bywater area who enjoy the challenge of Troves and Trickery.\nEgbert Took has challenged you to a game of troves and trickery. You should speak to several hobbits and perform tricks for their amusement.\n* Perform /pick\n* Perform /shiver\n* Perform /burp\n* Perform /tantrum\nObj 2:\nEgbert Took is at the Party Tree.\nYou should return to Egbert Took with word of your successes at Troves and Trickery.\n* Talk to Egbert Took",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{area="Thorin's Gate",zone="Ered Luin",d="Troves and Trickery is a festival tradition among many cultures, where participants try to please a number of celebrants with their tricks in order to receive a prize.",selectoneof={{q="(x3)",val="Fall Festival Token",id="7000C3A0"},{val="Dwarf Mask Token",id="7001090B"}},category="Festival",id=2706,scope="n/a",name="Troves and Trickery -- Thorin's Hall",level=1,minlevel=1,b="Guthlág",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThere are many dwarves throughout Thorin's Hall who might enjoy a game of Troves and Trickery.\nGuthlág has challenged you to participate in a game of Troves and Trickery. You should speak to several dwarves and perform tricks for their amusement.\n* Perform /mock\n* Perform /drink\n* Perform /flex\n* Perform /whistle\nObj 2:\nGuthlág is just east of the large statue in the Great Hall.\nYou should return to Guthlág with word of your successes in Troves and trickery.\n* Talk to Guthlág in Thorin's Hall",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2088},area="Fields of Fornost",zone="The North Downs",money={{val="30s 80c"}},d="The Orcs which inhabit the ruins of Fornost are drawn from the Blogmal tribe, more cruel and cunning than their completely brutish cousins of the Tarkrîp. Gareth Copp is convinced they are devising a vicious reprisal for the recent loss of their brethren, whom you slew.",mobs={{locations={"8.00S, 55.99W"},name="Gareth Copp"}},category="North Downs",id=2707,scope="n/a",t="Fellowship",prev={1665},name="True Intentions",arcs="Stopping the Siege",level=34,minlevel=29,b="Gareth Copp",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBlogmal-warlords can be found within the Orc camp near the base of the keep within Fornost.\nGareth Copp has asked you to gather your allies and search for some evidence of the Orcs' plans, most likely to be found upon the person of a Blogmal-warlord.\n* Bring the orders back to Gareth Copp\n* Turn in Blogmal-orders"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},zone="Moria",area="Redhorn Lodes",money={{val="27s 65c"}},d="The Redhorn Lodes have become a haven for beasts and Orc-kind alike since the fall of Moria. A variety of different tribes of Orcs fight for control over the precious ore found within the rock while also competing with insect and beast alike for territory to call their own. The Iron Garrison, seeking to reclaim the mine of Tumun-ghâr, has sent Alwar to the Redhorn Lodes to establish an effort to clear the intruders from the old dwarf-delving.",mobs={{locations={"13.11S, 105.65W"},name="Alwar"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2708,scope="n/a",name="Tumun-ghâr: Incursion in the Quarry",receive={{val="Iron Garrison Resource Token",id="70018DED"}},level=58,minlevel=53,b="Alwar",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance to Tumun-ghâr lies within Gharâaf-fehem.\nAlwar has asked you to assist him in clearing Tumun-ghâr of the vermin within.\nObj 2:\nAlwar can be found at Gharâf-fehem in the Redhorn Lodes.\nYou should return to Alwar to receive a reward for your efforts.\n* Talk to Alwar at Gharâf-fehem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Iron Garrison Guards"}},zone="Moria",area="Redhorn Lodes",money={{val="27s 65c"}},d="The Redhorn Lodes have become a haven for beasts and Orc-kind alike since the fall of Moria. A variety of different tribes of Orcs fight for control over the precious ore found within the rock, while also competing with insect and beast alike for territory to call their own. The Iron Garrison has sent a small expedition into the Redhorn Lodes to recover a little known mine called Tumun-ghâr.",mobs={{locations={"13.11S, 105.65W"},name="Alwar"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2709,scope="n/a",name="Tumun-ghâr: Taking Back What is Ours",receive={{val="Iron Garrison Resource Token",id="70018DED"}},level=58,minlevel=53,b="Alwar",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance to Tumun-ghâr lies within Gharâf-fehem.\nAlwar has asked you to defeat the leader of the intruders within Tumun-ghâr.\nObj 2:\nAlwar is at Gharâf-fehem.\nYou should return to Alwar with news of your success.\n* Talk to Alwar at Gharâf-fehem",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{reputation={{val="+900 with Iron Garrison Miners"}},zone="Moria",area="Redhorn Lodes",money={{val="27s 65c"}},d="Though well-stocked initially, the efforts to reclaim Moria have spread the Iron Garrison thin. To supplement their ambition, the Iron Garrison seeks to repurpose tools and equipment scavenged from the ruins. Within Tumun-ghâr, the Iron Garrison works to collect the tools needed to support additional prospecting efforts across the entirety of Moria.",mobs={{locations={"13.11S, 105.65W"},name="Alwar"}},category="Moria Lower Deeps",id=2710,scope="n/a",name="Tumun-ghâr: Things Left Behind",receive={{val="Iron Garrison Resource Token",id="70018DED"}},level=58,minlevel=53,b="Alwar",repeatable="Yes",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance to Tumun-ghâr lies within Gharâf-fehem.\nAlwar has asked you to collect Miner's Tool-kits from within Tumun-ghâr.\n* Bring the miner's tool-kits to Alwar at Gharâf-fehem in the Redhorn Lodes\n* Turn in Miner's Tool-kit",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2711,1749,989,1747,1275,1660,1748,1751,1750,1752,1827,1826,2710},zone="The Ettenmoors",area="Gramsfoot",d="Uglash has implored you to return to your trainers and learn how better to equip yourself for the battles to come.  He has sent you to your trainers to learn more.",mobs={{locations={"12.30S, 20.89W"},name="Uglash"}},category="Ettenmoors",id=2711,scope="n/a",prev={2768},name="Tutorial: A Warg at the Door",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Uglash",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nUglash has asked you to return to your trainers and learn more about what it takes to become a true soldier in the war against the Free Peoples.\nThe trainers are back where you started your life as a Warg.  Speak with Gruglok.\nObj 2:\nHaving spoken to Gruglok, your traits trainer, you should now purchase some traits and then talk to the Corruptor to equip your traits.\nObj 3:\nNow that you have (presumably) equipped some traits, speak with the Corruptions Trainer to learn more about Corruptions in Monster Play.\nObj 4:\nNow that you've learned how to best equip yourself in Monster Play, speak with Uglash again for final instructions.",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2711,1749,989,1747,1275,1660,1748,1751,1750,1752,1827,1826,2710},zone="The Ettenmoors",area="Gramsfoot",d="Uglash has implored you to return to your trainers and learn how better to equip yourself for the battles to come.  He has sent you to your trainers to learn more.",mobs={{locations={"12.30S, 20.89W"},name="Uglash"}},category="Ettenmoors",id=2712,scope="n/a",prev={2769},name="Tutorial: Learning the Tools",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Uglash",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nUglash has asked you to return to your trainers and learn more about what it takes to become a true soldier in the war against the Free Peoples.\nThe trainers are back where you started your life as an orc.\nObj 2:\nHaving spoken to Dagalúr, your traits trainer, you should now purchase some traits and then talk to the Corruptor to equip your traits.\nObj 3:\nNow that you have (presumably) equipped some traits, speak with the Corruptions Trainer to learn more about Corruptions in Monster Play.\nObj 4:\nNow that you've learned how to best equip yourself in Monster Play, speak with Uglash again for final instructions.",faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2770},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Having entered the Ettenmoors as a Spider, you need to learn your way around.  Follow your orders and don't get yourself killed by the Free People who lurk around every corner.",category="Ettenmoors",id=2713,scope="n/a",name="Tutorial: Spinning the Web",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Tolothdal",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTolothdal has ordered you to get into the fight already.  He wants you to go speak with Chief Guard Duthúrz outside the gate to the south.  Leave the camp and speak with him immediately.\n* Get your orders from Chief Guard Duthúrz ( )\nObj 2:\nYou are deemed unworthy by the Chief Guard.  Speak with Uglash inside the base to learn more about what you need to survive the Moors.\n//compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap3321777677);\n//]]>\nQuest: Tutorial: Spinning the Web\nMonster Play Quest\nCategory: Ettenmoors\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 60\nNext Quests:Tutorial: When Spiders Unite\nRewards\nTraits:\nDamage for Health (Rank 1)Money:\n28 35\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nHaving entered the Ettenmoors as a Spider, you need to learn your way around.  Follow your orders and don't get yourself killed by the Free People who lurk around every corner.\nBestower\nTolothdal (Spider)\n'You have just been hatched, broodling, but already you must play an important role.  Mordirith has sent you here to aid in the war against the Free Peoples.  We have no time to waste.  You must go get your feet wet now, all of them.\n'Head down the hill and out the front gate and speak with Chief Guard Duthúrz.  He will have orders for you.  We must share our web with interesting allies to be victorious.  Now go!'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nTolothdal has ordered you to get into the fight already.  He wants you to go speak with Chief Guard Duthúrz outside the gate to the south.  Leave the camp and speak with him immediately.\n* Get your orders from Chief Guard Duthúrz ( )\nObj 2:\nYou are deemed unworthy by the Chief Guard.  Speak with Uglash inside the base to learn more about what you need to survive the Moors.",traits={{val="Damage for Health (Rank 1)"}},faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2765},money={{val="28s 35c"}},d="Having entered the Ettenmoors as a Warg, you need to learn your way around.  Follow your orders and don't get yourself killed by the Free People who lurk around every corner.",category="Ettenmoors",id=2714,scope="n/a",name="Tutorial: Thrown to the Wargs",level=65,minlevel=60,b="Morsûm",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nMorsûm has ordered you to get into the fight already.  He wants you to go speak with Chief Guard Duthúrz outside the gate to the south.  Leave the camp and speak with him immediately.\n* Get your orders from Chief Guard Duthúrz ( )\nObj 2:\nYou are deemed unworthy by the Chief Guard.  Speak with Uglash inside the base to learn more about what you need to survive the Moors.\n//compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap1339784109);\n//]]>\nQuest: Tutorial: Thrown to the Wargs\nMonster Play Quest\nCategory: Ettenmoors\nScope: n/a\nMin Level: 60\nNext Quests:Tutorial: A Warg at the Door\nRewards\nTraits:\nDamage for Health (Rank 1)Money:\n28 35\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nHaving entered the Ettenmoors as a Warg, you need to learn your way around.  Follow your orders and don't get yourself killed by the Free People who lurk around every corner.\nBestower\nMorsûm (Warg)\n'Pay attention, pup!  You are nothing, a speck.  I don't know why Mordirith sent you here but perhaps you can help.  Head out the front gate to the South and get in the fray.  Speak to Chief Guard Duthúrz out at the first campsite.  He will have work for you.\nGet out of my face.  You sicken me.'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nMorsûm has ordered you to get into the fight already.  He wants you to go speak with Chief Guard Duthúrz outside the gate to the south.  Leave the camp and speak with him immediately.\n* Get your orders from Chief Guard Duthúrz ( )\nObj 2:\nYou are deemed unworthy by the Chief Guard.  Speak with Uglash inside the base to learn more about what you need to survive the Moors.",traits={{val="Damage for Health (Rank 1)"}},faction="Mon",instanced="No"},
