 = 'Failloth (The Last Homely House)Location: 29.60S, 3.10W\nThe Trollshaws >> Rivendell Valley';markerList['1879140446_0x041FBF5000000071_99.8880.941432944'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879140446_0x041FBF5000000071_100.0281.051432944', new GLatLng(-6.6750732421875, 72.59783203125), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879140446_0x041FBF5000000071_100.0281.051432944'; markers['1879140446_0x041FBF5000000071_100.0281.051432944'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Failloth (The Last Homely House)Location: 29.59S, 3.10W\nThe Trollshaws >> Rivendell Valley';markerList['1879140446_0x041FBF5000000071_100.0281.051432944'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879140446_0x041FBF5000000071_44.2845.921432944', new GLatLng(-6.829453125, 72.1079296875), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879140446_0x041FBF5000000071_44.2845.921432944'; markers['1879140446_0x041FBF5000000071_44.2845.921432944'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Failloth (The Last Homely House)Location: 29.77S, 3.38W\nThe Trollshaws >> Rivendell Valley';markerList['1879140446_0x041FBF5000000071_44.2845.921432944'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker); GME_DEFAULT_ICON = G_DEFAULT_ICON;      } else {        document.getElementById(\"map1827834718\").innerHTML = \"In order to see the map that would go in this space, you will need to use a compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap1827834718);\n//]]>\nQuest: Vol. I, Book 15, Volume I, Epilogue -- Laerdan's Parcel\nCategory: Epic - Vol. I, Book 15: Daughter of Strife\nScope: Epic\nMin Level: 47\nRequired Races: Elf\nPrerequisite Quests:Vol. I, Book 15, Chapter 12: One Hope Remains\nRewards\nTitles:\nChampion of EriadorMoney:\n10 22\nReceive:\nLaerdan's Parcel\nRusted Dwarf Tools\nGrey Steed\nCloak of Mordirith's Bane\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nA parcel has been found addressed to you in Laerdan's old room.\nBestower\nFailloth (NPC)\n'While performing the sombre task of cleaning Laerdan's chambers once and for all, I uncovered a note from Laerdan made out to you, (your name), along with a parcel that he left behind. Master Elrond bade me hold these items in my keeping in hopes that you would return.'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nYou should read Laerdan's note before opening the parcel he left for you.\nYou spoke to Failloth in Rivendell and learned that Laerdan had left a note and a parcel behind for you in his room.\n* Use Laerdan's Note (Level 1)\nObj 2:\nFailloth is in the courtyard of the Last Homely House, in Rivendell.\nYou have read Laerdan's note and should speak now to Failloth.\n* Talk to Failloth"},
{["next"]={2821},reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Old Forest",money={{val="3s 75c"}},d="Tom Bombadil was pleased with the lilies you found for Goldberry and has told you where the crebain you were searching for can be found. He also told you that a woman was there waiting.",mobs={{locations={"32.66S, 57.32W","33.84S, 55.81W","32.65S, 57.33W"},name="Tom Bombadil"}},selectoneof={{val="Tallang",id="7000343A"},{val="Taronn",id="7000343B"},{val="Bombadil's Rune-stone",id="7001618F"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2852,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2819},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 10: Into the Barrow-downs",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=19,c={"* Go northeast into the Barrow-downs\n* Defeat Andraste and the crebain\n* Return to Tom Bombadil"},minlevel=14,b="Tom Bombadil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Barrow-downs are reached by going north and east along the Old Barrows Road. The crebain stopped to roost in the trees within the Barrow-downs, south along the ridge, above the eaves of the forest.\nTom Bombadil found the crebain within the Barrow-downs, but also mentioned the presence of a woman. You should stay on your guard.\n* Find and defeat the Crebain and their Master\nObj 2:\nThe Old Barrows Road is north of Andraste's grove. The house of Tom Bombadil is west and south along the Old Barrows Road.\nAndraste revealed that the Lord of the Nazgûl had gone to someplace called Othrongroth, but you could learn nothing more before her death. Tom Bombadil is the Master of the Wood and of the Barrow-downs. He might know where Othrongroth lies.\n* Talk to Tom Bombadil at his house"},
{["next"]={2822},reputation={{val="+900 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Old Forest",money={{val="5s 50c"}},d="You learned from the woman Andraste that the Lord of the Nazgûl was travelling to a place called Othrongroth. If you could spy on the Witch-king at this place, you might learn more of his plans.",mobs={{locations={"32.66S, 57.32W","33.84S, 55.81W","32.65S, 57.33W"},name="Tom Bombadil"}},selectoneof={{val="Froth-fótar",id=70003228},{val="Gollos",id="7000343F"},{val="Defender of Cardolan",id=70003440},{val="Golfadanir",id=70003052},{val="Toranc",id="7000343E"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2853,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2820},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 11: Othrongroth",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=21,minlevel=16,b="Tom Bombadil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTom Bombadil has agreed to show you the way to Othrongroth, a barrow in the Barrow-downs.\n* Speak to Tom Bombadil\nObj 2:\nReturn to Tom Bombadil and claim your reward.\nYou and your allies braved the dark depths of Othrongroth and emerged victorious.\n* Talk to Tom Bombadil"},
{["next"]={2841},reputation={{val="+500 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Old Forest",d="You were rescued from the clutches of the Wight-lord by Tom Bombadil, but you learned much that may help Strider and his people.",mobs={{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Barliman Butterbur"},{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Gandalf"},{locations={"32.66S, 57.32W","33.84S, 55.81W","32.65S, 57.33W"},name="Tom Bombadil"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2854,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2821},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 12: The Black Rider's Designs",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",receive={{val="Malbellas",id=70000677}},level=21,minlevel=16,b="Tom Bombadil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nStrider awaits your return in his room at The Prancing Pony in Bree. The entrance leading from the Barrow-downs to the Great East Road is to the north.\nTravel back to Bree and tell Strider what you learned of the Witch-king's plans.\n* Talk to Strider\nObj 2:\nBarliman Butterbur serves his guests in the common room of The Prancing Pony.\nYou travelled back to The Prancing Pony, but you found the door to Strider's room locked. You should speak to Barliman Butterbur to learn if he can tell you where Strider has gone.\n* Talk to Barliman Butterbur\nObj 3:\nGandalf's room in The Prancing Pony Inn in Bree is found by taking a left out of the common room, until you can only bear right. The room is at the top of the stairs at the end of the hall.\nBarliman Butterbur told you that Strider has left The Prancing Pony, but that Gandalf, a Wizard by reputation, arrived and asked to speak to any who were looking for the Ranger. You should speak to Gandalf and tell him what you have learned.\n* Talk to Gandalf"},
{["next"]={2812},reputation={{val="+900 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Bree",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="Strider has asked you to help him end Amdir's murderous rampage once and for all.",mobs={{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Strider"}},selectoneof={{val="Cloak of Cardolan",id=70000412},{val="Hengaim",id=70000411},{val="Menedgaim",id="700090FE"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2855,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 1: Unravelling the Thread",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Strider",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nStrider is in his room at The Prancing Pony Inn in Bree, which is found by taking a left down the hall out of the common room until you can only bear right. The room is at the end of the hall to the right of the stairs.\nAt night-fall, Strider will lead you against Amdir and the Blackwolds.\n* Talk to Strider\nObj 2:\nStrider is in his room at The Prancing Pony Inn in Bree, which is found by taking a left down the hall out of the common room until you can only bear right. The room is at the end of the hall to the right of the stairs.\nWith the threat of Amdir ended, you should report back to Strider and see if there is anything else he would have you do.\n* Talk to Strider"},
{["next"]={2813},reputation={{val="+500 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Bree",d="While Strider sees to some important travellers he is awaiting, he has asked you to travel to Combe and aid Constable Underhill in making sure the threat of the Blackwolds is at its end.",mobs={{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Strider"},{locations={"28.73S, 49.28W"},name="Constable Underhill"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2856,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2811},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 2: To a Constable's Aid",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Strider",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nConstable Underhill often loiters about Combe town centre, east and north of Bree.\nStrider has informed you that he has an important matter to attend to, but has asked you to go to Combe and encourage Constable Underhill to investigate the brigands' old hideout.\n* Talk to Constable Underhill"},
{["next"]={2814},reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Combe",money={{val="1s 80c"}},d="At Strider's request, you have travelled to Combe to help Constable Underhill investigate if the Blackwold brigands are truly no longer a threat to the people of the Chetwood.",mobs={{locations={"28.73S, 49.28W"},name="Constable Underhill"}},selectoneof={{val="Resilient Trousers",id="7001B595"},{val="Constable's Hammer",id=70000421},{val="Constable's Jacket",id=70000420}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2857,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2812},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 3: Blackwolds Broken",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Constable Underhill",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Blackwolds' old hideout is found south of the Combe guard-house, near Staddle Falls at the north-east end of Staddle pond.\nConstable Underhill has decided that it is probably a good idea to take a look in the Blackwolds' old hideout, to make sure they aren't mustering there again. He has asked, however, that you accompany him.\n* Speak to Constable Underhill\nObj 2:\nSpeak to Constable Underhill.\nYou infiltrated the Blackwolds' hideout and defeated several of them, at the request of Constable Underhill.\n* Talk to Constable Underhill"},
{["next"]={2815},reputation={{val="+500 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Combe",d="From a dying brigand at Skunkwood's old hideout, you learned that the strange Pale Dwarf was trying to bully the Blackwolds into continuing their alliance with the Witch-realm of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Strider"},{locations={"28.73S, 49.28W"},name="Constable Underhill"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2858,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2813},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 4: Dark Designs",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Constable Underhill",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nStrider is in his room at The Prancing Pony Inn in Bree, which is found by taking a left down the hall out of the common room until you can only bear right. The room is at the end of the hall to the right of the stairs.\nYou should return to Strider and tell him what you learned about the Blackwolds and the Pale Dwarf.\n* Talk to Strider"},
{["next"]={2816},reputation={{val="+500 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Bree",d="While you were away investigating the Blackwold brigands, five Nazgûl attacked The Prancing Pony in search of four travellers from the Shire, which Strider had under his protection. Strider has told you that there are a total of nine Riders, and that he must know the location of the other four.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 61.30W"},name="Lenglinn"},{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Strider"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2859,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2814},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 5: The Other Riders",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Strider",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLenglinn's camp sits on a rise north of the Buckland Gate, along the Great East Road, west of Bree.\nStrider has asked that you speak with Lenglinn, another Ranger, and learn if he has seen any other Nazgûl passing out of the Shire.\n* Talk to Lenglinn"},
{["next"]={2817},reputation={{val="+300 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Buckland",money={{val="86c"}},d="Desiring news about the other Nazgûl, Strider sent you west to the borders of the Shire and Buckland to speak to Lenglinn, whom he had sent to look after a hobbit.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 61.30W"},name="Lenglinn"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2860,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2815},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 6: In the Black Riders' Wake",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=16,c={"* Go down the hill from Lenglinn, there are Crebain there. Defeat them and return to Lenglinn"},minlevel=11,b="Lenglinn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe crebain have taken roost south-west, just beyond his camp.\nLenglinn told you that crebain followed in the wake of the Nazgûl and have taken roost outside his camp. He is sure the birds are the Enemy's spies and will report on movements in the west. He has asked you to dispose of them to prevent them from doing harm.\n* Defeat crebain (4)\nObj 2:\nLenglinn's camp is to the north-east of the crebain roost.\nWith the crebain dead, the Enemy has fewer eyes watching Buckland and the Shire. Speak again with Lenglinn and learn what else he would have you do.\n* Talk to Lenglinn"},
{["next"]={222,2818},reputation={{val="+500 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Buckland",d="The Horn-call of Buckland had alerted Lenglinn to the Nazgûl's presence there.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 61.30W"},name="Lenglinn"},{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Strider"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2861,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2816},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 7: Horn-call of Buckland",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",receive={{val="Daerechor",id="7000041A"}},level=16,minlevel=11,b="Lenglinn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBaggins' home is at Crickhollow, almost due south-east of the Buckland Gate, south of Lenglinn's camp.\nIn order to determine the movements of the Nazgûl, Lenglinn has asked you to investigate the home of a hobbit named Baggins.\n* Investigate Crickhollow\nObj 2:\nLenglinn's camp is north of the Buckland Gate, north-west of Crickhollow.\nWhen you spoke to Fredegar Bolger, he told you that the Black Riders had not caught him and so learned nothing from him, but he let slip to you something about a Ring belonging to the Enemy. As Fredegar was speaking, crebain flew out of the sky and attacked him, and though you defeated the crebain, two retreated into the Old Forest. You should bring this news to Lenglinn.\n* Talk to Lenglinn\nObj 3:\nStrider is in his room at The Prancing Pony Inn in Bree, which is found by taking a left down the hall out of the common room until you can only bear right. The room is at the end of the hall to the right of the stairs.\nLenglinn asked you to seek Strider's counsel on how to find the crebain that had overheard Fredegar Bolger's words and escaped into the Old Forest. He fears that if the Enemy learns that this Ring they seek is no longer in the Shire, all may be lost.\n* Talk to Strider"},
{["next"]={2819},reputation={{val="+500 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Bree",d="When you were in Buckland investigating the Nazgûl's incursion, you spoke with Fredegar Bolger, who revealed information about Frodo Baggins and the Enemy's Ring. Crebain attacked and may have overheard the hobbit's words.",mobs={{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Strider"},{locations={"32.66S, 57.32W","33.84S, 55.81W","32.65S, 57.33W"},name="Tom Bombadil"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2862,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2817},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 8: Master of the Wood",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=18,minlevel=13,b="Strider",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTom Bombadil's house is at the far eastern end of the River Withywindle in the Old Forest.\nStrider told you to seek out someone named Tom Bombadil and ask for his aid finding the crebain who flew into the Old Forest.\n* Talk to Tom Bombadil"},
{["next"]={2820},reputation={{val="+700 with Men of Bree"}},zone="Bree-land",area="Old Forest",money={{val="3s 20c"}},d="Strider directed you to speak to Tom Bombadil, the master of the Old Forest, to ask for his aid in tracking the crebain who fled into woods.",mobs={{locations={"32.66S, 57.32W","33.84S, 55.81W","32.65S, 57.33W"},name="Tom Bombadil"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2863,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2818},name="Vol. I, Book 1, Chapter 9: Lilies for the River-daughter",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=18,c={"* Go down the hill into the river\n* Collect 4 large lilies\n* Return to Tom Bombadil"},pois={{locations={"33.01S, 58.24W","33.06S, 58.25W","32.84S, 58.16W","32.96S, 58.16W","32.93S, 58.17W","33.00S, 58.20W","32.91S, 58.13W","32.95S, 58.15W","32.90S, 58.14W","32.81S, 58.18W","33.02S, 58.26W","33.04S, 58.28W","32.90S, 58.16W","32.88S, 58.15W","32.95S, 58.16W","33.07S, 58.30W","32.93S, 58.14W","33.03S, 58.24W"},name="Large Lily"}},minlevel=13,b="Tom Bombadil",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe river flows westward from the house of Tom Bombadil.\nYou found Tom Bombadil and spoke with the strange creature. While he was not at first willing to find the crebain he did at last relent, if you would perform a task he considered far more important. He wishes you to gather lilies from the river, near someone called Old Man Willow.\n* Bring the lilies to Tom Bombadil\n* Collect large lilies (4 Large Lily )"},
{["next"]={2811},zone="Bree-land",area="Bree",money={{val="72c"}},d="Barliman confided that a recent arrival to the Prancing Pony is one he would rather do without. He suggested that speaking with him, as he may be the sort of individual for whom you are looking.",mobs={{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Barliman Butterbur"},{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Strider"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2864,scope="n/a",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 1, Foreword: An Unwanted Guest",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=15,minlevel=11,b="Barliman Butterbur",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nStrider's room in The Prancing Pony Inn in Bree can be found by heading left down the hall out of the common room, until you can only bear right. Strider's room is to the right of the stairs at the end of the hall.\nBarliman explained that a Ranger, Strider, was in a room in the Prancing Pony. He directed from the main bar to follow the hall left to the top of the stair, look for a short hall and door on the right and you should find Strider.\n* Talk to Strider",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{d="You have travelled with Constable Underhill of Combe into the cave that the Blackwolds once used as a hideout.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2865,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 1, Instance: Blackwolds Broken",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=15,minlevel=11,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nConstable Underhill travelled with you to the cave hideout of William Skunkwood, the former leader of the Blackwolds in the area of Combe. Skunkwood is dead, as well as a good many other brigands, but you must be certain they have not begun to muster their strength again.\n* Speak to Constable Underhill\nObj 2:\nIn one of the deeper chambers of the Blackwolds' hideout, you encountered the mysterious dwarf threatening a brigand. The dwarf gravely wounded the brigand, then fled, commanding his dwarves to attack you.\nConstable Underhill has asked you to speak to the wounded brigand.\n* Speak to the brigand\nObj 3:\nThe dying brigand revealed that the Blackwolds were being paid by both someone from the south and agents of Angmar. When he tried to reform the band without allegiance to either, the Pale Dwarf struck him down. You should speak with Constable Underhill about this.\n* Speak to Constable Underhill"},
{d="Tom Bombadil has brought you to the barrow named Othrongroth. A servant of the Nazgûl, Andraste, said that the Lord of the Nazgûl would be found here.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2866,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 1, Instance: Othrongroth",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=21,minlevel=16,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nThe entrance to Othrongroth is nearby to the west.\nTom Bombadil led you safely to the entrance of Othrongroth, the Great Barrow, in the Barrow-downs. Your search for the Witch-king will lead you into the barrow.\n* Go to the entrance of the Great Barrow, Othrongroth\nObj 2:\nThe Witch-king and the dwarf Skorgrím have entered Othrongroth. You should follow them into the barrow and search for them there.\n* Follow the Witch-king\nObj 3:\nYour path through the Great Barrow led you to the Black Rider, who took notice of your presence and called the Dead to attack you. Defeat these creatures and continue on through Othrongroth!\n* Pursue the Witch-king\nObj 4:\nYour pursuit of the Witch-king has led you to a room with a wight seated upon a great throne. The creature bid you welcome and said that if you sought an audience, you could approach.\n* Speak to the Wight-lord\nObj 5:\nThanks to the arrival of Tom Bombadil, the Wight-lord has been defeated! Tom waits to speak with you.\n* Talk to Tom Bombadil"},
{zone="Bree-land",area="Chetwood",d="Strider has asked you to help him end Amdir's murderous rampage once and for all.",mobs={{locations={"33.51S, 47.76W","34.35S, 48.86W"},name="Strider"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",id=2867,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 1, Instance: Unravelling the Thread",arcs="Volume I, Book 1: Stirrings in the Darkness",level=15,minlevel=11,repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nStrider and his kinsmen, Torthann and Lenglinn, have led you to the outskirts of the brigand camp. Strider beckons to you.\n* Talk to Strider\nObj 2:\nStrider told you to speak with Torthann when you are ready to begin your search for Amdir. Strider and Lenglinn will find a back way in.\n* Talk to Torthann\nObj 3:\nTorthann sensed the source of the brigands' fear in the southern corner of the camp. You should investigate.\n* Speak with Torthann\nObj 4:\nTorthann is not convinced that the evil ends with the wight and thinks that Amdir is somewhere near by. Perhaps there is more to the camp.\n* Speak with Torthann\nObj 5:\nTorthann beckons to you.",faction="FrP",instanced="Yes"},
{["next"]={2569,2834},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Nain Enidh",money={{val="16s"}},d="Radagast is concerned with the cause of the corruption in the swamps. He feels that the wights are a symptom of a greater evil.",mobs={{locations={"30.97S, 29.51W"},name="Radagast the Brown"}},selectoneof={{val="Boots of the Ruin-hold",id=70000692},{val="Greataxe of the Brown Wizard",id=70000693}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2868,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2832},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 10: Breeders of the Dead",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",receive={{val="Red Stone",id=70000691}},level=28,c={"* The Gaunt-Men will usually generate several adds, so this quest is a bit more difficult than the preceding one."},minlevel=23,b="Radagast the Brown",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe gaunt-men dwell in the ruins to the far east of Haragmar.\nRadagast told you of the gaunt-men, necromancers in the service of Sauron, who are responsible for the emergence of these wights. He asked you to defeat the war-singers and bring him their sigils. He can then determine which of the Gaunt-lords they serve.\n* Bring the sigils back to Radagast the Brown at Ost Guruth\n* Turn in Gaunt-man Sigil"},
{["next"]={2569,2835},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Nain Enidh",money={{val="17s 50c"}},d="Radagast wants to learn what drew a creature such as Ivar to the Red Swamp. He thinks that something could be learned from one of the Eglain.",mobs={{locations={"37.54S, 28.10W"},name="Aric the Stone-speaker"},{locations={"30.97S, 29.51W"},name="Radagast the Brown"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2869,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2833},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 11: The Stone-speaker",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=29,c={"* Aric the Stone-speaker is in south Harloeg in Ost Haer"},minlevel=24,b="Radagast the Brown",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAric is south of Ost Guruth, beyond Talath Gaun, down in Harloeg.\nRadagast spoke of a man named Aric the Stone-speaker. Aric may be able to tell you the history of the Red Swamp.\n* Talk to Aric the Stone-speaker in Harloeg"},
{["next"]={2836,2701},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Harloeg",money={{val="7s"}},d="While investigating the source of the wights of the Red Swamp, Radagast sent you to a man named Aric the Stone-speaker. Aric hinted that the dead might hold the answers you seek.",mobs={{locations={"37.54S, 28.10W"},name="Aric the Stone-speaker"},{locations={"37.71S, 28.02W"},name="Emelin"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2870,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2834},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 12: A Dead Man's Challenge",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=29,c={"* Emelin is in the same part of the ruins as Alric. After talking to him you must defeat 3 shades summoned by him."},minlevel=24,b="Aric the Stone-speaker",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nEmelin haunts the area called Ost Haer.\nAric spoke of a shade called Emelin. If you can prove your worth to the shade, he might give you the information you desire.\n* Talk to Emelin\nObj 2:\nEmelin haunts the area called Ost Haer.\nEmelin has tasked you with defeating the apparitions of his dead warriors. Succeed, and he will help you. Fail, and you may perish.\n* Talk to Emelin at Ost Haer"},
{["next"]={2837},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Harloeg",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="Emelin told you about his failure to protect one of the River-maidens and the curse it brought down upon him and his men. He agreed to help you if you accomplish a task for him.",mobs={{locations={"37.71S, 28.02W"},name="Emelin"}},selectoneof={{val="Emelin's Spear",id="7001618E"},{val="Brudhraw's Fall",id="700092E0"},{val="Shimmering Ring",id="700069FE"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2871,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2835},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 13: In the Gaunt-lord's Grasp",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=30,c={"* Brudhraw is up the steps past the Bog-lord in Nindor"},minlevel=25,b="Emelin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe wights and their Wight-lord may be found west of Ost Haer in Nindor.\nEmelin told you that the Gaunt-lord Ivar the Blood-hand raises the wights as his soldiers. You must destroy them and their lord, a wight called Brudhraw.\n* Defeat Brudhraw\nObj 2:\nEmelin is at Ost Haer, to the north.\nYou defeated the wight-lord Brudhraw. Now you should return to the shade called Emelin.\n* Talk to Emelin at Ost Haer"},
{["next"]={2838},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Harloeg",money={{val="17s 85c"}},d="You defeated the wight-lord and brought some semblance of peace to Emelin and his men, the fallen warriors of Arthedain.",mobs={{locations={"30.97S, 29.51W"},name="Radagast the Brown"},{locations={"37.71S, 28.02W"},name="Emelin"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2872,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2836},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 14: History of the Red Maid",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=30,c={"* Talk to Radagast the Brown in his tower in the back of Ost Guruth"},minlevel=25,b="Emelin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRadagast the Brown is in the tower at the end of the main avenue in Ost Guruth.\nEmelin told you his sad tale, then instructed you to return to Radagast the Brown.\n* Talk to Radagast the Brown at Ost Guruth"},
{["next"]={1301,1842,1040,2798,2804,1462,2584,2839,1852,835},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Nain Enidh",money={{val="35s 70c"}},d="Radagast told you that members of the Eglain, led by Elsa and Eriac, had entered Agamaur, the northern marshes of the Red Swamp.",mobs={{locations={"30.97S, 29.51W","29.79S, 27.39W","29.78S, 27.39W"},name="Radagast the Brown"},{locations={"29.66S, 27.37W"},name="Elsa the Bold"}},selectoneof={{val="Ring of the Eglain",id="700006A0"},{val="The Scavenger's Lot",id="7000069E"},{val="Bracelet of the Eglain",id="700006A1"},{val="Celeglang",id="700092DD"},{val="Scale Boots of the Eglain",id="7000069F"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2873,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2837},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 15:  (Fellowship)The Red-pass",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=30,minlevel=25,b="Radagast the Brown",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRadagast the Brown is in the tower at the end of the main avenue in Ost Guruth.\nRadagast the Brown waits to lead you into the passage to Agamaur. When you are prepared to leave, you should speak with Radagast again.\n* Talk to Radagast the Brown at Ost Guruth\nObj 2:\nElsa is in the camp within the ruins.\nYou should speak with Elsa about your victory within Agamaur.\n* Talk to Elsa in Agamaur\nObj 3:\nThe Eglain and the shades of Arthedain have established a small encampment within the ruins. Elsa of the Eglain waits to speak with you.\nYour battle against Ivar's dark-water was a victory, or so it appears. The Gaunt-lord retreated into the north, pursued by Radagast the Brown, and has not been seen since.\n* Talk to Radagast the Brown in Agamaur"},
{["next"]={2857},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Agamaur",money={{val="18s 20c"}},d="With the aid of the shades of Arthedain, the Eglain held fast against against Ivar's forces.",mobs={{locations={"29.79S, 27.39W","29.78S, 27.39W"},name="Radagast the Brown"},{locations={"29.66S, 27.37W"},name="Elsa the Bold"},{locations={"31.49S, 29.50W"},name="Frideric the Elder"},{locations={"30.99S, 29.55W"},name="Hana the Young"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2874,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2838},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 16: Agamaur Secured",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",receive={{val="Frideric's Thanks",id="700092E1"}},level=31,c={"* Talk to Radagast the Brown in his tower in the back of Ost Guruth"},minlevel=26,b="Radagast the Brown",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElsa is in the Agamaur camp.\nRadagast thanked you for your help and asked you to speak with the Eglain woman named Elsa.\n* Speak with Elsa the Bold\nObj 2:\nThe passage to Haragmar lies to the south. Ost Guruth is west of Haragmar.\nElsa gave you a letter to deliver to Frideric requesting supplies for her encampment. She also asked you to deliver a pack to her sister, Hana. Both can be found in Ost Guruth.\n* Talk to Hana the Young\n* Turn in Light Pack\nObj 3:\nFrideric abides in the courtyard of Ost Guruth.\nHana was pleased to receive the pack from Elsa, knowing that her sister is watching out for both her and all of the Eglain.\n* Talk to Frideric the Elder\n* Turn in A Letter to Frideric"},
{["next"]={2827},zone="The Lone-lands",area="The Weather Hills",money={{val="7s"}},d="Candaith, the Ranger who watches the Great East Road as it passes through the Lone-lands, has learned of an Orkish presence in the Weather Hills.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 37.88W"},name="Candaith"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2875,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 1: Rise of the Orcs",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=22,c={"* The Orcs to kill are just southwest of Candaith's camp at Glumhallow"},minlevel=17,b="Candaith",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nWhite Hand Orcs infest the Weather Hills, west of Candaith's camp.\nThe Ranger Candaith offered you assistance in finding Radagast the Brown in exchange for aid against the Orcs in the Weather Hills.\n* Defeat melee White Hand Orcs (8 Tarkrîp Battler, Scouting Orc-warrior, Toughened Orc-warrior)\n* Defeat ranged White Hand Orcs (6 Tarkrîp Outrider, White Hand Sniper)\nObj 2:\nCandaith is at his camp near the foot of Weathertop, among the Weather Hills.\nWhile you were fighting the Orcs, Candaith began his search for Radagast the Brown.\n* Talk to Candaith at his camp",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2828,1601},zone="The Lone-lands",area="The Weather Hills",money={{val="7s"}},d="In his search for signs of Radagast, Candaith tracked a messenger from the Orc-encampment in the Midgewater Pass, but was unable to learn what message the Orc carried before his hunt was interrupted by winged crebain.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 37.88W"},name="Candaith"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2876,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2826},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 2: An Orc-messenger",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=22,minlevel=17,b="Candaith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Orc-messenger is surely at one of the enemy camps in Glumhallow, west of Candaith's own encampment at the foot of Weathertop.\nAn Orc-messenger made his way from the Midgewater Pass to the outlying Orc-camps located throughout the Weather Hills. Candaith asked you to intercept the Orc-messenger and return with the orders he must bear.\n* Bring the Orc-orders to Candaith\n* Turn in Orc-orders"},
{["next"]={2829},zone="The Lone-lands",area="The Weather Hills",money={{val="7s"}},d="Candaith has learned of the existence of a War-master among the Orcs named Uzorr. His defeat would be a powerful blow against them.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 37.88W"},name="Candaith"}},selectoneof={{val="Uzorr's Foe",id=70000729},{val="Uzorr's Vanquisher",id=70000728}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2877,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2827},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 3: War-master Uzorr",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=22,pois={{locations={"28.15S, 38.06W"},name="Orc-letter"}},minlevel=17,b="Candaith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWar-master Uzorr can be found in Bleakrift, north-west of Candaith's camp at the foot of Weathertop.\nCandaith asked you to find and slay War-master Uzorr and search the camp for a letter containing his orders.\n* Defeat War-master Uzorr\n* Use Orc-letter\nObj 2:\nCandaith is at his camp at the foot of Weathertop, among the Weather Hills.\nYou were victorious over War-master Uzorr and have obtained a letter that surely contains his orders from whatever power commands the orcs that have ventured into the Lone-lands.\n* Talk to Candaith\n* Turn in Orc-letter"},
{["next"]={2840},zone="The Lone-lands",area="The Weather Hills",money={{val="7s"}},d="As Candaith returned from his journey in the lands to the east, he saw flashes atop Weathertop of white light, akin to lightning, though there was no storm.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 37.88W"},name="Candaith"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2878,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2828},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 4: Light in the Darkness",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=22,c={"* Go to the top of Weathertop for the stone"},pois={{locations={"31.21S, 36.88W"},name="Rune-covered Rock"}},minlevel=17,b="Candaith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWeathertop towers above Candaith's camp.\nCandaith asked you to search Weathertop for anything out of the ordinary and to bring any news or evidence that you may find back to him.\n* Use Rune-covered Rock\nObj 2:\nCandaith's camp is at the foot of Weathertop.\nYou found a rune-covered rock and took a rubbing of the markings. You should return to Candaith and learn if he knows what the runes might mean.\n* Talk to Candaith\n* Turn in Rock-rubbing"},
{zone="The Lone-lands",area="The Weather Hills",money={{val="13s 60c"}},d="While you climbed to the peak of Weathertop, Candaith busily worked to translate the letter you recovered from Bleakrift. His translation is complete and the news he uncovered is grave.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 37.88W"},name="Candaith"}},selectoneof={{val="Baingarab",id=70000710},{val="Rigul's Bane",id="7000070F"},{val="Candaith's Scale Leggings",id="7000070E"},{val="Candaith's Leather Leggings",id="7000070D"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2879,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2829},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 5 (Fellowship): Retake Weathertop",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",receive={{val="Collúr",id="7000070C"}},level=23,minlevel=18,b="Candaith",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCandaith is at his camp at the foot of Weathertop.\nThe Ranger Candaith asked you to assist him in driving a company of Orcs from Weathertop. He told you to gather allies and return to him when you are prepared.\n* Talk to Candaith and retake Weathertop with a fellowship\nObj 2:\nCandaith is at his camp at the foot of Weathertop.\nCandaith is waiting to discuss with you the strange events that occurred atop Amon Sûl.\n* Talk to Candaith"},
{["next"]={2831},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Annunlos",money={{val="14s 50c"}},d="After earning the trust of the Eglain, they confessed that Radagast the Brown, another of Gandalf's order, currently resides in a tower within their homestead of Ost Guruth.",mobs={{locations={"30.97S, 29.51W"},name="Radagast the Brown"},{locations={"34.38S, 36.91W"},name="Hunulf Munce"},{locations={"34.02S, 40.67W","34.02S, 40.66W","34.03S, 40.68W"},name="Gadaric Munce"}},selectoneof={{val="Ranger's Light Gloves",id="7001BEBF"},{val="Dorthann",id="7000068A"},{val="Radagast's Rune-stone",id="700161C9"},{val="Túranc (Level 27)",id="7000068B"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2880,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 7: Radagast the Brown",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=27,minlevel=22,b="Gadaric Munce",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRadagast the Brown dwells in seclusion within a tower in the ruins of Ost Guruth, the place the Eglain call home. Seek out his counsel.\nGadaric and Hunulf Munce believe that your intentions are good and have provided you with the whereabouts of their most esteemed guest.\n* Talk to Radagast the Brown"},
{["next"]={2832},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Nain Enidh",money={{val="14s 50c"}},d="An aura of corruption drew Radagast the Brown to the Red Swamp. He needs help to uncover the source of this corruption.",mobs={{locations={"30.97S, 29.51W"},name="Radagast the Brown"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2881,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2830},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 8: The Red Swamp",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=27,c={"* The bog-lurker nests are in the Circle of Blood at Haragmar, east of Ost Guruth"},pois={{locations={"31.45S, 26.96W","31.17S, 27.40W","30.97S, 27.47W","31.55S, 27.11W","31.27S, 27.25W","31.44S, 27.32W","31.74S, 27.94W","31.26S, 27.04W","31.46S, 27.74W","31.43S, 27.50W"},name="Bog-prowler Nest"}},minlevel=22,b="Radagast the Brown",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe bog-prowlers wander in Haragmar, east of Ost Guruth.\nIn order to learn what might be causing the corruption of the swamp, Radagast needs bits of moss from the nests of the bog-prowlers.\n* Use Bog-prowler Nest\nObj 2:\nRadagast waits in Ost Guruth, west of Haragmar.\nYou should return to Radagast the Brown with the moss you collected.\n* Talk to Radagast the Brown\n* Turn in Bog-moss"},
{["next"]={2833},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Nain Enidh",money={{val="16s"}},d="Your discovery of wights in Haragmar, the southern reaches of the Red Swamp,  alarms Radagast the Brown. He suspects the involvement of powers from Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"30.97S, 29.51W"},name="Radagast the Brown"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2882,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2831},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Chapter 9: The Bloated Dead",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=28,c={"* Several wights are in the Circle of Blood but there are more wights in east Haragmar"},minlevel=23,b="Radagast the Brown",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWights can be found deeper in Haragmar, the southern reaches of the Red Swamp, east of Ost Guruth.\nRadagast sent you back into the swamp to defeat the wights that are fouling the land with their evil.\n* Defeat wights in Haragmar (15)\nObj 2:\nRadagast the Brown waits at the tower at the northern end of the main thoroughfare in Ost Guruth.\nYou should return to Radagast the Brown with news of your battle with the wights of Haragmar.\n* Talk to Radagast the Brown in Ost Guruth"},
{["next"]={2826},zone="Bree-land",area="Bree",money={{val="2s 80c"}},d="Gandalf learned from one of the Great Eagles, Gwaihir the Windlord, that another wizard, Radagast the Brown, discovered a source of corruption within the Lone-lands. Radagast has gone missing and you must enlist the aid of the Rangers to find his whereabouts.",mobs={{locations={"30.14S, 37.88W"},name="Candaith"},{locations={"25.55S, 52.88W"},name="Saeradan"},{locations={"29.60S, 51.25W","29.64S, 51.28W","29.61S, 51.26W","29.53S, 51.29W"},name="Gandalf"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2883,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2822},name="Vol. I, Book 2, Foreword: Aiding the Order",level=22,minlevel=17,b="Gandalf",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSaeradan is at his cabin north along the Greenway in Bree-land.\nGandalf is concerned about the shadow spreading out of Angmar. He asked you to consult with the Rangers to search for Radagast the Brown, another of his order.\n* Talk to Saeradan at his cabin along the Greenway\nObj 2:\nCandaith is at his camp in the Lone-lands.\nSaeradan does not know where Radagast can be found. He suspects that Candaith, the Ranger who watches the Lone-lands, may have information on the wizard's whereabouts.\n* Talk to Candaith",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="The Lone-lands",area="Agamaur",d="Ruins of the ancient kingdom of Rhudaur, twisted by time and the touch of a dark evil, lay before you. Alongside Radagast the Brown, you must find Elsa and Eriac and assist them against the Gaunt-lord, Ivar the Blood-hand, and his undead minions.",mobs={{locations={"28.95S, 26.53W"},name="Elsa the Bold"},{locations={"29.01S, 26.53W","29.68S, 27.35W","29.26S, 23.17W"},name="Dannasen"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2884,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 2, Instance: Red-pass",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",c={"* Kill all the mobs in the way. Radagast will not aggro or hit the mobs."},level=30,minlevel=25,repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou have travelled with Radagast into the corrupted swamp of Agamaur. Aid him as he travels to the Eglain-encampment to the west.\n* Talk to Radagast\nObj 2:\nThe leader of the shades resides at the seemingly abandoned Eglain-encampment.\nThe defeat of Dour-root has opened the way into the western ruins, where the shades Radagast spoke of dwell. Radagast asked that you entreat with Dannasen, their leader, for their aid.\n* Talk to Dannasen\nObj 3:\nNeven's throne is further northward into the ruins.\nNeven holds some sway over the shade-captain, Dannasen. Perhaps if you speak with him you may find a way to alter Dannasen's orders.\n* Kill 1 Neven\nObj 4:\nDannasen lingers at the Eglain-encampment to the south of Neven's throne.\nNeven, the shades' commander, was actually a wight summoned by Ivar to contain the shades. With his destruction, Dannasen may now be willing to aid you.\n* Speak to Dannasen\nObj 5:\nFollow Radagast as he moves deeper into Agamaur.\nDannasen, renewed, called forth his men to battle and opened the way westward. It may be that now you will be able to reach Elsa and Eriac.\n* Follow Radagast deeper into Agamaur\nObj 6:\nSpeak to Elsa to learn more about her battles in Agamaur.\nThanks to Dannasen and his men, the way westward into Agamaur was opened, and you were able to reach Elsa and Eriac.\n* Talk to Elsa the Bold\nObj 7:\nThe gate into Garth Agarwen lies to the north.\nElsa has sent you to seek Ivar at Garth Agarwen and put an end to him.\n* Speak to Radagast\nObj 8:\nSpeak to Radagast to see if there is something else he would have you do.\nRadagast has driven the Gaunt-lord Ivar from Agamaur and stopped his nefarious plans...for now.\n* Speak to Radagast",faction="FrP",instanced="Yes"},
{d="The Ranger Candaith has enlisted your aid in a quest to remove the threat of Orcs from the Weather Hills. Candaith believes that the presence of Orcs from the South upon Weathertop is a precursor to an invasion of Eriador.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 2: The Red Maid",id=2885,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 2, Instance: Retake Weathertop",arcs="Volume I, Book 2: The Red Maid",level=23,minlevel=18,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nYou have arrived at the foot of Weathertop to discover that Orcs from the South have made their way to the crest. Candaith awaits your assistance in driving the war-band from the ruins of Amon Sûl.\n* Speak with Candaith\nObj 2:\nA small force of goblins greeted you at the foot of Weathertop. Candaith has sent you upon the path to the left, while he will clear the path to the right, meeting once again upon the crest of Weathertop.\n* Speak with Candaith\nObj 3:\nCandaith sent you up one branch of the path up Weathertop, while he took the other, in search of the leaders of the Orc war-band.\n* Kill 1 Bûb-hosh\n* Kill 1 Muz\nObj 4:\nSomewhere above you on the path, Candaith waits to speak with you again.\nYou have defeated two of the leaders of the Orc war-band.\n* Speak with Candaith at Weathertop's peak\nObj 5:\nYou have found the leader of Saruman's expedition, the Uruk Rigûl. You must defeat Rigûl and his minions to break their will and drive them from the Weather Hills.\n* Defeat Rigûl\n* Defeat Rigûl's minions\nObj 6:\nThe Uruk-hai expedition lies in ruins. You have won the day. You should speak with Candaith.\n* Speak with Candaith"},
{["next"]={2845},reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="From the reports coming from the west and south of the North Downs, Halbarad believes the Enemy is moving on many fronts. The strength of Esteldín is nearly tapped, and Halbarad feels a council of the Free Peoples must be called. Before doing so, he desires more knowledge on the Enemy's movements.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"13.06S, 55.30W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2886,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 1: Ranger of the Fields",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=34,minlevel=29,b="Halbarad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMincham can be found in his camp on the southern edge of the Fields of Fornost.\nHalbarad has asked you to speak with Mincham to learn if the Enemy has retaken the ruins of Fornost, the ancient capital of Arnor.\n* Talk to Mincham"},
{["next"]={2846},reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Fields of Fornost",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="Mincham believes that the Enemy has indeed returned to Fornost, but cannot tell the strength of the forces there as they approached the city from the north.",mobs={{locations={"13.06S, 55.30W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2887,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2844},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 2: The Gates of Fornost",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",receive={{val="Luth-feld",id="700017A8"}},level=34,minlevel=29,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Norbury Gates lie to the north of Mincham's camp.\nMincham believes the only way to determine the strength of the forces of Angmar within Fornost is to test the defences erected at its gates. He has asked you to slay Orcs and Wargs and bring him a report of the resistance there.\n* Defeat Ongbúrz Orcs at Norbury Gates (10)\n* Defeat Wargs at Norbury Gates (6)\nObj 2:\nMincham can be found at his camp in the southern Fields of Fornost.\nThe Ranger Mincham will need to hear your report regarding the defences at the gates of Fornost.\n* Talk to Mincham"},
{["next"]={2848,2851,2854},reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Fields of Fornost",money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="After reporting to him of your battles against the Orcs and Wargs that guard the gates of Fornost, Mincham surmised that it was as Halbarad feared: Angmar has sent a large force to reclaim and fortify Fornost.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"13.06S, 55.30W"},name="Mincham"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2888,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2845},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 3: Fallen Once More",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Mincham",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalbarad can be found in Esteldín.\nMincham beseeches you take the knowledge of Angmar's presence at Fornost to Halbarad.\n* Talk to Halbarad"},
{["next"]={2849},reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",d="To deal with the threat from Angmar, Halbarad has decided that he must call a council of the Free Peoples of the North Downs -- the Council of Esteldín.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"7.21S, 44.92W"},name="Hannar"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2889,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2846},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 4, Part I: A Call to Dwarves",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Halbarad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBoth Dori and Hannar should be found in Othrikar, which lies north of Esteldín.\nHalbarad told you that the Dwarves of Othrikar are good Longbeards who were put to task by the Dourhands for many years, though they have recently thrown off their yoke. Although they are still pressed by the Dourhands, Halbarad has asked you to bring them word of the Council of Esteldín.\n* Talk to Dori or Hannar"},
{["next"]={2850},zone="The North Downs",area="Nan Amlug West",money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="When you arrived at Othrikar, bringing word of the Council of Esteldín, Hannar told you that Dori, the emissary of the Longbeards of Erebor, had been captured by the Dourhands.",mobs={{locations={"7.21S, 44.92W"},name="Hannar"}},selectoneof={{val="Dori's Saviour",id="7000182E"},{val="Dori's Defenders",id="7000182D"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2890,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2848},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 4, Part II: Freeing Dori",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=35,c={"* Dori is imprisoned at [7.7S, 47.0W]"},minlevel=30,b="Hannar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Dourhands' camp where Dori is being held is west of Othrikar. Search the ruins for where Dori is being held.\nHannar told you that the dwarves could not even consider coming to the Council of Esteldín, unless Dori was freed from the Dourhands. As an envoy of the Rangers, he told you that you must free him if you hope to have the support of the dwarves at the Council.\nThis quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great.\n* Find Dori\nObj 2:\nHannar can be found at the mines of Othrikar.\nAfter escorting Dori to safety, he told you to return to Othrikar and speak to Hannar.\n* Talk to Hannar"},
{["next"]={2847},reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Nan Amlug West",d="After rescuing Dori from the clutches of the Dourhands, both Dori and Hannar agreed that the Dwarves of Othrikar shall come to the Council of Esteldín.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"7.21S, 44.92W"},name="Hannar"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2891,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2849},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 4, Part III: The Dwarves Shall Come",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=36,minlevel=31,b="Hannar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalbarad can be found in Esteldín.\nHannar told you to bring word to Halbarad that the Dwarves of Othrikar agreed to come to the Council.\n* Talk to Halbarad"},
{["next"]={2852},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",d="To deal with the threat from Angmar, Halbarad has decided that he must call a council of the Free Peoples of the North Downs -- the Council of Esteldín.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"13.68S, 44.95W","13.68S, 44.94W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Gildor Inglorion"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2892,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2846},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 5, Part I: A Call to Elves",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Halbarad",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nGildor Inglorion can be found in the Elf-glade of Lin Giliath, south of Esteldín.\nHalbarad told you that the Elf-glade was recently attacked by Stone-trolls. He expressed his concern that the Elves of Lin Giliath will be too overwhelmed dealing with the aftermath of this attack to come to the Council.\n* Talk to Gildor Inglorion",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2847},reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",d="After defeating the Uruk Drukordh, Gildor told you that the Elves of Lin Giliath shall come to the Council of Esteldín.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"13.68S, 44.95W","13.68S, 44.94W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Gildor Inglorion"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2893,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2852},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 5, Part III: Might of the Elves",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=36,minlevel=31,b="Gildor Inglorion",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalbarad can be found in Esteldín.\nGildor told you to bring word to Halbarad that the Elves have agreed to come to the Council of Esteldín.\n* Talk to Halbarad"},
{["next"]={2853},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="When you arrived at Lin Giliath, Gildor told you that the Orcs to the west are planning to move against the Elf-glade.",mobs={{locations={"13.68S, 44.95W","13.68S, 44.94W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Gildor Inglorion"}},selectoneof={{val="Othigil",id=70001810},{val="Thenidmaib",id="7000180F"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2894,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2851},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 5, Part II: Tending the Glade",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=35,c={"* You can wait for Drukordh to walk away from the other mobs before engaging in battle so that no adds participate"},minlevel=30,b="Gildor Inglorion",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDrukordh can be found in the deepest, most southern recesses of Nan Wathren.\nGildor told you that if the Uruk Drukordh were slain, then Lin Giliath would remain safe enough for him to come to the Council of Esteldín. You were warned not to confront the Uruk without the help of allies.\nUsing the Elf-stone allows you to access the inspiration buff while solo or in a smaller fellowship.\n* Kill 1 Drukordh\n* Use Shimmering Elf-stone\nObj 2:\nGildor can be found in Lin Giliath.\nWith the Uruk Drukordh slain, you should make your way back to Gildor and bring him this good news.\n* Return to Gildor at Lin Giliath\n* Turn in Shimmering Elf-stone"},
{["next"]={2855},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",d="To deal with the threat from Angmar, Halbarad has decided that he must call a council of the Free Peoples of the North Downs -- the Council of Esteldín.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2895,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2846},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 6, Part I: A Call to Men",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=35,minlevel=30,b="Halbarad",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nNellie Boskins can be found in Trestlebridge.\nHalbarad warned you that Nellie may be so consumed with the defence of Trestlebridge that she will not see the importance of coming to the Council of Esteldín.\n* Talk to Nellie Boskins\nObj 2:\nHalbarad can be found in Esteldín.\nUpon hearing your message regarding the Council of Esteldín, Nellie Boskins ardently refused to come, saying that the defence of her town was above all other concerns. You should return to Halbarad with her answer.\n* Talk to Halbarad",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2847},reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",d="After you and Halbarad came to the aid of her town, Nellie Boskins swore to lend what strength the people of Trestlebridge have to his endeavour. They will come to the Council of Esteldín.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2896,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2855},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 6, Part III: The Free Peoples of Trestlebridge",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=36,minlevel=31,b="Nellie Boskins",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHalbarad can be found in Esteldín.\nNellie Boksins has asked you to inform Halbarad that she will come to the Council of Esteldín.\n* Talk to Halbarad"},
{["next"]={2856},reputation={{val="+900 with Men of Bree"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="19s 60c"}},d="Upon returning from Trestlebridge with Nellie Boskin's refusal to join the Council, Halbarad informed you that a large force of Orcs was moving on Trestlebridge.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"}},selectoneof={{val="Defender of Trestlebridge",id="7000180A"},{val="Cerygaim",id=70001809}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2897,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2854},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 6, Part II: The Defence of Trestlebridge",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=35,c={"* Talk to Halbarad and complete the instance [35] The Defence of Trestlebridge\n* Talk to Nellie Boskins when done"},minlevel=30,b="Halbarad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTravel with Halbarad to Trestlebridge and aid in its defence.\nHalbarad told you that the Orcs moving on Trestlebridge are from the more powerful Ongbúrz tribe. The townsfolk will not be able to defend against them alone. Halbarad instructed you to gather allies and return to him.\nThis quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great.\n* Talk to Halbarad\nObj 2:\nNellie Boskins can be found in Trestlebridge.\nAt Halbarad's side, you helped defend Trestlebridge from the Orcs that sought to destroy it. At the conclusion of the battle, Nellie Boskins asked to speak with you.\n* Talk to Nellie Boskins"},
{["next"]={2867},reputation={{val="+700 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="The Elves, Men, and dwarves of the North Downs have all agreed to come to the Council of Esteldín, but Halbarad's chieftain has yet to be informed of the events that have transpired there.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},selectoneof={{val="Snake-skin Locket",id=70001198},{val="Rendail",id="7000119B"},{val="Derdail",id="7000119A"},{val="Thinker's Shoes",id=70001199}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2898,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2856,2853,2850},name="Vol. I, Book 3, Chapter 7: The Council Assembled",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=37,minlevel=32,b="Halbarad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAragorn can be found in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris, which lies in the Trollshaws.\nHalbarad has asked you to take word of the invasion of the North Downs to his chieftain, Aragorn, and to obtain his advice.\n* Talk to Aragorn in Rivendell"},
{["next"]={2844},reputation={{val="+500 with Rangers of Esteldín"}},zone="The Lone-lands",area="Nain Enidh",money={{val="19s 25c"}},d="Orcs from the north are sweeping across the North Downs and setting fires to everything in their path.",mobs={{locations={"9.39S, 41.16W","9.40S, 41.16W","9.60S, 41.05W"},name="Halbarad"},{locations={"30.14S, 37.88W"},name="Candaith"},{locations={"31.49S, 29.50W"},name="Frideric the Elder"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 3: The Council of the North",id=2899,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 3, Foreword: Fires in the North",arcs="Volume I, Book 3: The Council of the North",level=34,minlevel=29,b="Frideric the Elder",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTravel along the road to the west until you reach The Forsaken Inn. Candaith is at a camp north of The Forsaken Inn, north-west of Weathertop.\nFrideric told you that a Ranger desires to speak with you about urgent matters.\n* Talk to Candaith\nObj 2:\nHalbarad is in the North Downs, north of Meluinen.\nCandaith's fellow Ranger is in urgent need of assistance.\n* Talk to Halbarad"},
{["next"]={2859},reputation={{val="+500 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="20s 30c"}},d="Servants of the Enemy pursued Frodo Baggins to the Bruinen, and though the hobbit and his friends were saved and the fell creatures defeated by the power of Elrond, not all of the Nazgûl have been accounted for.",mobs={{locations={"31.65S, 15.18W"},name="Elladan"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2900,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 4, Chapter 1: Where is the Horse and the Rider?",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=37,minlevel=32,b="Elrond",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElladan is at his camp of Thorenhad on the north-western slope of the Bruinen Gorges, north of the bear-dens.\nLord Elrond has asked you to lend your assistance to his sons Elladan and Elrohir, currently seeking the missing Nazgûl.\n* Talk to Elladan"},
{["next"]={2860},reputation={{val="+900 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Bruinen Gorges",money={{val="20s 65c"}},d="Elladan and Elrohir have had an unfruitful search for the missing Rider, but the brothers have finally uncovered some traces of his passing.",mobs={{locations={"31.65S, 15.18W"},name="Elladan"}},selectoneof={{val="Elladan's Shield",id="700161C4"},{val="Brognam",id="7000110A"},{val="Elladan's Leggings",id=70001109}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2901,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2858},name="Vol. I, Book 4, Chapter 2: The Missing Rider",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=38,pois={{locations={"36.60S, 18.37W"},name="Black Horse Corpse"}},minlevel=33,b="Elladan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe hoofprints were discovered far south of the road, and the sons of Elrond believe that the missing Rider might be hiding in the ruins of Minas Agor, located within the narrow channels of the South Trollshaws.\nElladan has asked you to follow the Nazgûl into the South Trollshaws.\nThe Elf-stone can be used to allow for you to access the inspiration buff while solo or in a smaller fellowship.\n* Find some sign of the missing Nazgûl\n* Use Shimmering Elf-stone\n* If you find yourself without a full fellowship you may draw upon inspiration\nObj 2:\nThe corpse of a black horse lies in the ruins of Minas Agor, located among the narrow channels of the South Trollshaws.\nYou should remove the bridle from the horse's corpse and return with it to Elladan.\nThe elf-stone can be used to allow for you to access the inpiration buff while solo or in a smaller fellowship.\n* Use Black Horse Corpse\n* Use Shimmering Elf-stone\n* If you find yourself without a full fellowship you may draw upon inspiration\nObj 3:\nElladan is at Thorenhad, located among the Bruinen Gorges, north of a bear-den.\nElladan will be both pleased and troubled to see the bridle of the black horse, for it means that the missing Rider is still somewhere within the Trollshaws.\n* Talk to Elladan\n* Turn in Bridle of a Black Steed\n* Turn in Shimmering Elf-stone"},
{["next"]={2861},reputation={{val="+700 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Bruinen Gorges",d="Elladan was pleased that you found the horse of the missing Rider, but will not be satisfied until he knows its master's fate.",mobs={{locations={"31.65S, 15.18W"},name="Elladan"},{locations={"30.14S, 3.06W"},name="Glorfindel"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2902,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2859},name="Vol. I, Book 4, Chapter 3: The Wisdom of Lord Glorfindel",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=38,minlevel=33,b="Elladan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLord Glorfindel can be found in Imladris, far to the east of Thorenhad, contemplating the waterfalls by the Last Homely House.\nElladan has asked you to consult with the Elf-lord Glorfindel about the missing Rider.\n* Talk to Glorfindel\nObj 2:\nThe Ford of Bruinen is to the west of Imladris, at the bottom of the steeply-climbing slopes.\nLord Glorfindel has given you an Elf-stone and has asked you to test its powers by holding it aloft on the banks of the Bruinen.\n* Use Glorfindel's Elf-stone (Level 1)\nObj 3:\nLord Glorfindel is in Imladris, high above the Bruinen and to the east, by the waterfall outside the Last Homely House.\nGlorfindel is waiting to speak with you upon your return from the Ford of Bruinen.\n* Talk to Glorfindel\n* Turn in Glorfindel's Elf-stone (Level 1)"},
{["next"]={2862},reputation={{val="+500 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",d="Lord Glorfindel gave you a beryl which glows when it is brought into places where great evil has left its mark.",mobs={{locations={"31.65S, 15.18W"},name="Elladan"},{locations={"30.14S, 3.06W"},name="Glorfindel"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2903,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2860},name="Vol. I, Book 4, Chapter 4: Regaining the Trail",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=38,minlevel=33,b="Glorfindel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElladan is at Thorenhad, his camp among the Bruinen Gorges, north of the bear-dens.\nLord Glorfindel has sent you back to Elladan with a beryl, an Elf-stone that glows when it comes near places on which great evil has left its mark.\n* Talk to Elladan\n* Turn in Glorfindel's Elf-stone (Level 1)"},
{["next"]={2863},reputation={{val="+900 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Bruinen Gorges",money={{val="33s 60c"}},d="Elladan has determined that the missing Rider may be hiding in one of the many caves that dot the crags of the Trollshaws and wants you to search several of them with Glorfindel's beryl.",mobs={{locations={"31.65S, 15.18W"},name="Elladan"}},selectoneof={{val="Eluil",id=70001115},{val="Ladgris",id=70001113},{val="Luthrand",id=70001114}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2904,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2861},name="Vol. I, Book 4, Chapter 5: Hiding in the Dark",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=39,minlevel=34,b="Elladan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElladan gave you his notes containing the locations of the troll-caves.\nElladan wants you to search three troll-caves with Glorfindel's beryl.\nUsing the Elf-stone allows you to access the inspiration buff while solo or in a smaller fellowship.\n* Use Glorfindel's Elf-stone\n* Find the deepest chamber of Torogrod\n* Use Glorfindel's Elf-stone\n* Find the deepest chamber of Nurath\n* Use Glorfindel's Elf-stone\n* Find the deepest chamber of Thingroth\n* Use Shimmering Elf-stone\n* If not in a fellowship you can use the shimmering elf-stone to invoke inspiration\nObj 2:\nElladan is at Thorenhad, his camp among the Bruinen Gorges, north of the bear-dens.\nElladan is waiting to hear what Glorfindel's beryl revealed: that the missing Nazgûl was never in any of the caves you searched.\n* Talk to Elladan\n* Turn in Glorfindel's Elf-stone\n* Turn in Elladan's Notes\n* Turn in Shimmering Elf-stone"},
{["next"]={2864},reputation={{val="+900 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Bruinen Gorges",money={{val="21s"}},d="While you were searching the caves of the Trollshaws for some sign of the missing Nazgûl, Elladan heard tell of one of the Onodrim in the wilderness that might know the Rider's whereabouts.",mobs={{locations={"31.65S, 15.18W"},name="Elladan"},{locations={"34.04S, 20.16W"},name="Barachen"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2905,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2862},name="Vol. I, Book 4, Chapter 6: The Knowledge of the Onodrim",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=39,minlevel=34,b="Elladan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBarachen is at his camp south of the Great East Road that runs through the South Trollshaws. Scouts along the road can direct you to him.\nElladan told you that Barachen reported seeing one of the Onodrim somewhere in the wild and wants you to talk to him about it.\n* Talk to Barachen\nObj 2:\nOne of the Onodrim, a creature of ancient days, was seen in the valley of the giants south of the High Moor, high above the Bruinen. Barachen reportedly saw the Onod standing next to some mighty trees as he came south into the valley.\nBarachen reported seeing one of the Onodrim somewhere in the Trollshaws, and Elladan thinks it possible that this Onod might know something of the missing Nazgûl's whereabouts.\n* Find the Onod\nObj 3:\nElladan is at Thorenhad, his camp among the Bruinen Gorges, north of the bear-dens.\nElladan will be troubled to learn the fate of the Onod that Barachen saw in the valley of the giants.\n* Talk to Elladan"},
{["next"]={2865},reputation={{val="+500 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Bruinen Gorges",d="Elladan is greatly concerned about the evil that seems to grow from deep within the Trollshaws and knows that you cannot face it alone.",mobs={{locations={"31.65S, 15.18W"},name="Elladan"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Legolas"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2906,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2863},name="Vol. I, Book 4, Chapter 7: The Aid of Mirkwood",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=40,minlevel=35,b="Elladan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMaster Elrond is at Imladris, far east of Elladan's camp of Thorenhad and above the Bruinen.\nElladan has asked that you speak with his father about arranging an audience with the visiting Elves from Mirkwood, who might have some experience with creatures of the manner which you encountered.\n* Talk to Elrond\nObj 2:\nLegolas is in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nMaster Elrond has told you of an Elf-prince named Legolas, currently staying in Imladris for a time. He hails from Mirkwood and may have some knowledge of the creature you faced in the Trollshaws.\n* Talk to Legolas in Rivendell"},
{["next"]={2866,1138},reputation={{val="+1200 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="34s 16c"}},d="Legolas recognized the creature you described as one of Wood-trolls and has agreed to help you track the rest down.",mobs={{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Legolas"}},selectoneof={{val="Cuneldor",id="700010FB"},{q="(x5)",val="Brilliant Edhelharn Token",id="70001BC4"},{val="Himhar",id="700010FD"},{val="Taushakh's Doom",id="700010FE"},{val="Tracker's Trousers",id="700010FC"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2907,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2864},name="Vol. I, Book 4, Chapter 8: The Unmarked Trail",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=40,minlevel=35,b="Legolas",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLegolas is in Rivendell, in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nThe Elf-prince from Mirkwood, Legolas, is waiting to help you track down the Wood-trolls in the Trollshaws and defeat them.\nThis quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great.\n* Talk to Legolas in Rivendell and track down the Wood-trolls\nObj 2:\nLegolas is in Rivendell, in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nThe Elf-prince from Mirkwood, Legolas, is waiting to speak with you about what the two of you saw in the lair of the Wood-trolls.\n* Talk to Legolas in Rivendell"},
{["next"]={2869},reputation={{val="+300 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="8s 82c"}},d="Legolas has been dismayed by the events in the lair of the Wood-trolls and thinks Elrond should be told of them at once.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Legolas"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2908,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2865},name="Vol. I, Book 4, Chapter 9: Hasten Their Departure",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",receive={{val="Dorlos",id="70000FC8"}},level=42,minlevel=37,b="Legolas",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMaster Elrond is within the Last Homely House.\nLegolas has asked you to go to Elrond at once and tell him what transpired in the lair of Taushakh, king of the Wood-trolls.\n* Talk to Elrond"},
{["next"]={2858},reputation={{val="+500 with Elves of Rivendell"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="8s 12c"}},d="Aragorn has asked that you speak with Elrond concerning a matter of gravest import for Rivendell.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2909,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 4, Foreword: The Troubles of Rivendell",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=37,minlevel=32,b="Aragorn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElrond waits in the library on the upper floor of his house.\nAragorn asked that you present yourself to Elrond, the master of the Last Homely House.\n* Talk to Elrond"},
{d="Legolas has led the way deep into the Gladdalf, a remote corner of the Trollshaws, on the trail of the Wood-trolls.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 4: Chasing Shadows",id=2910,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 4, Instance: The Unmarked Trail",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: Chasing Shadows",level=40,c={"* Enter the instance.\n* Protect Legolas as he hunts for the evil.\n* Defeat Taushakh."},minlevel=35,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nLegolas is following a mysterious trail into the Gladdalf.\nYou and Legolas of Mirkwood have followed the signs of the Wood-trolls through the wilderness of the Trollshaws.\n* Talk to Legolas\nObj 2:\nLegolas is threatened by attacking wood-trolls in the Gladdalf.\nYou and Legolas of Mirkwood have followed the signs of the Wood-trolls through the wilderness of the Trollshaws.\n* Talk to Legolas\nObj 3:\nLegolas is following a mysterious trail into the Gladdalf.\nYou and Legolas of Mirkwood have followed the signs of the Wood-trolls through the wilderness of the Trollshaws.\n* Talk to Legolas\nObj 4:\nLegolas is threatened by droves of corrupted fen-crawlers in the Gladdalf.\nYou and Legolas of Mirkwood have followed the signs of the Wood-trolls through the wilderness of the Trollshaws.\n* Aid Legolas\nObj 5:\nLegolas has followed a mysterious trail onto an earthen rise surrounded by water in the centre of the Gladdalf.\nYou and Legolas the Elf have followed the signs of the Wood-trolls through the wilderness of the Trollshaws.\n* Talk to Legolas\nObj 6:\nLegolas is waiting to speak with you.\nYou and Legolas of Mirkwood have followed the signs of the Wood-trolls through the wilderness of the Trollshaws.\n* Talk to Legolas"},
{["next"]={2870},reputation={{val="+500 with Thorin's Hall"}},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="22s 5c"}},d="Elrond feels that the Nazgûl you drove off from the Trollshaws has fled into the Misty Mountains. He has asked you to continue your pursuit of the Nazgûl with the aid of Glóin.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2911,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2866},name="Vol. I, Book 5, Chapter 1: Into the Misty Mountains",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",receive={{val="Inscribed Horn",id="70000FCE"}},level=42,minlevel=37,b="Elrond",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGlóin can be found at the camp at the top of the pass that leads from Rivendell into the Misty Mountains.\nElrond suggested that you seek Glóin's aid in the hunt for the Nazgûl.\n* Talk to Glóin"},
{["next"]={2871},reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},zone="The Misty Mountains",area="Bruinen Source West",money={{val="22s 5c"}},d="Glóin told you that the goblins seem very active of late, and that he would not be surprised if the Nazgûl you are pursuing were the cause.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"}},selectoneof={{val="Congronn",id=70001146},{val="Threk-fótar",id=70001145},{val="Doom of Gurzmat",id=70001147}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2912,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2869},name="Vol. I, Book 5, Chapter 2: Troublesome Goblins",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",level=42,c={"* Head east and a bit north to Pinnath Fenui\n* Defeat Gurzmat who is at the top of the hill and calls 1 add\n* Return to Glóin"},minlevel=37,b="Glóin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe goblins have many camps among the ridges of Pinnath Fenui, far to the east and north of Glóin's camp.\nGlóin told you that if you search for the goblins' camps in the Misty Mountains, you should find a goblin named Gurzmat. He appears to be their leader, and by defeating him, you should throw the goblins into disarray and perhaps find the trail of the Nazgûl.\n* Find the goblin-camp\nObj 2:\nGurzmat is somewhere deep within the goblin-camp that sprawls along the ridges of the Pinnath Fenui.\nGlóin told you that by defeating the goblin Gurzmat, you would throw the goblins into disarray and perhaps find the trail of the Nazgûl you seek.\n* Kill 1 Gurzmat\nObj 3:\nGlóin is at his camp north of Rivendell.\nIn defeating Gurzmat, you find him accompanied by hostile Dourhand dwarves. Glóin should be made known of this development immediately.\n* Talk to Glóin"},
{["next"]={2872},reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},zone="The Misty Mountains",area="Bruinen Source West",money={{val="35s 84c"}},d="Glóin told you that the Nazgûl you are pursuing can be found in the old dwarf-fortress of Gabilazan, in the company of Skorgrím Dourhand. The two entered the nearly impregnable inner keep of the fortress. Glóin believes the only way to enter the inner keep is to learn its secret entrance.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2913,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2870},name="Vol. I, Book 5, Chapter 3: The High Fortress",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",level=43,c={"* Head east then south to Gabilazan [28.0S, 0.8E]\n* The vault is on the right/west a short way inside\n* Defeat the mobs inside then inspect the cornerstone\n* Return to Glóin"},pois={{locations={"27.32S, 0.00E"},name="Gabilazan Cornerstone"}},minlevel=38,b="Glóin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe cornerstone containing the plans is located inside Gabilazan's Vault, located in one of the two passes east of Glóin's camp. Glóin's camp is north of Rivendell.\nGlóin told you that to learn how to access the secret entrance to Gabilazan's inner keep, you will need to take the plans for the fortress placed in its cornerstone.\n* Use Gabilazan Cornerstone\nObj 2:\nBring the Gabilazan plans to Glóin.\n* Bring the Gabilazan plans to Glóin\n* Turn in Gabilazan-plans"},
{["next"]={2873},reputation={{val="+700 with Thorin's Hall"}},zone="The Misty Mountains",area="Bruinen Source West",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Glóin discovered the secret entrance to the inner keep of Gabilazan, but the way is locked and will require an artifact of the old days.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2914,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2871},name="Vol. I, Book 5, Chapter 4: The Key-stone",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",level=43,c={"* Head north into Bruinen Source West\n* Collect the key from a chest at Iskeld's Lookout [21.5S, 4.6W]\n* Return to Glóin"},pois={{locations={"21.60S, 4.54W"},name="Key-stone"}},minlevel=38,b="Glóin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe dwarf-vault that contains the key-stone is at Iskeld's Lookout, near the source of the Bruinen. Glóin is at his camp north of Rivendell.\nGlóin has asked you to retrieve a key-stone from an old dwarf-vault. The key-stone will allow you entry into the Dourhand-occupied dwarf-keep.\n* Bring the key-stone to Glóin\n* Collect the key-stone"},
{["next"]={1139,2874},reputation={{val="+1200 with Thorin's Hall"}},zone="The Misty Mountains",area="Bruinen Source West",money={{val="44s 80c"}},d="With the Key-stone in hand, you can now enter the dwarf-keep in Gabilazan, the last refuge of the Dourhands and confront both the Nazgûl and Skorgrím.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"}},selectoneof={{val="Gloín's Halberd",id=70001153},{val="The Climber's Hands",id=70001152},{val="Crawler-hide Coat",id=70001151},{val="Glóin's Gold Ring",id=70001154},{val="The Stone-cutter's Arms",id=70001150}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2915,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2872},name="Vol. I, Book 5, Chapter 5: The Last Refuge",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",level=43,c={"* Talk to Gimli to start the instance\n* Defeat enemies (Dourhands and Frost Giants) & protect Gimli\n* Defeat Skorgrím Dourhand\n* Talk to Glóin"},minlevel=38,b="Glóin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGimli is in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nWhen you have gathered a fellowship, seek out Gimli, and he will accompany you to the dwarf-keep where the Nazgûl and Skorgrím may be hiding.\nThis quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great.\n* Speak to Gimli in Rivendell\nObj 2:\nGlóin is at his camp north of Rivendell.\nThe Nazgûl left the dwarf-keep, commanding Skorgrím to slay you. Fortunately, you were able to defeat Skorgrím, but a fell spirit emerged from his corpse and cursed the Longbeards before vanishing. You should tell Glóin all that has transpired.\n* Talk to Glóin"},
{["next"]={2875},reputation={{val="+500 with Thorin's Hall"}},zone="The Misty Mountains",area="Bruinen Source West",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Upon hearing that the Nazgûl fled to Helegrod, Glóin told you some of the tale of that ancient fortress.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2916,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2873},name="Vol. I, Book 5, Chapter 6: In the Steps of Evil",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",level=43,c={"* Head north-east to some steps and a door on the east side of Northern Bruinen Source, some way below Helegrod itself. Do not enter the door.\n* Defeat & search the wights that appear on the steps.\n* Return to Glóin"},minlevel=38,b="Glóin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHelegrod is north of Glóin's camp. The outer treasury is near Nan Gongarag.\nGlóin thinks you may be able to learn what the Nazgûl's plan for Helegrod is by scouting the borders of that abandoned hall for the entrance to the treasury. He warned you not to enter Helegrod itself, for it is guarded too strongly by dark things.\n* Scout the borders of Helegrod\nObj 2:\nHelegrod is north of Glóin's camp.\nAt the entrance to Helegrod's treasury you encountered wights. You should defeat one and search its remains for some clue as to what brought it here.\n* Bring the Sigil of Drugoth to Glóin\n* Turn in Sigil of Drugoth"},
{["next"]={2876},reputation={{val="+500 with Thorin's Hall"}},zone="The Misty Mountains",area="Bruinen Source West",money={{val="22s 40c"}},d="Troubled by the wights you discovered at the entrance to Helegrod's treasury and the sigil you found on one of the wight's bodies, Glóin suggested it was time to speak with Master Elrond.",mobs={{locations={"24.88S, 4.12W"},name="Glóin"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2917,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2874},name="Vol. I, Book 5, Chapter 7: Evil Tidings",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",level=43,c={"* Walk back to Rivendell and speak with Elrond."},minlevel=38,b="Glóin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElrond is in the library of Imladris.\nGlóin has asked you to speak with Elrond about what you have discovered outside of Helegrod's treasury.\n* Talk to Elrond\n* Turn in Sigil of Drugoth"},
{["next"]={1140,2886},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="44s 80c"}},d="Elrond told you that after the dwarf-king Durin defeated Thorog the dragon, the body of the dragon was left to moulder in the empty treasury of Helegrod. He fears that the ice and cold of Orod Lostol will have preserved the body to such an extent that the arts of the Gaunt-lord, Drugoth, may be able to instill it with a fell spirit and raise it as a wight.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},selectoneof={{val="Manatham",id="70000FD6"},{val="Gilloch",id="70000FD8"},{val="Estelham",id="70000FD5"},{val="Arassechor",id="70000FD9"},{val="Luth-klath",id="70000FD7"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2918,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2875},name="Vol. I, Book 5, Chapter 8: Fire and Ice",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",level=43,minlevel=38,b="Elrond",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nHelegrod is north of Rivendell and Glóin's camp.\nElrond has asked you to enter the treasury of Helegrod and put a stop to the Nazgûl's schemes. He warned you to gather allies.\nThis quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great.\n* Enter the Helegrod treasury and end the Nazgûl's schemes\nObj 2:\nElrond can be found in the library of Imladris.\nIn the treasury, you encountered the Nazgûl and were able to defeat him. You also interrupted the ritual being performed by the Gaunt-lord to restore the dragon Thorog, although part of the process was completed, and the dragon flew off. Elrond should be made aware of what happened.\n* Talk to Elrond"},
{zone="The Misty Mountains",area="Helegrod",d="At the behest of Master Elrond of Imladris, you have entered the abandoned treasury of Helegrod to end the Nazgûl's scheme to restore the dragon Thorog.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2919,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 5, Instance: Fire and Ice",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",pois={{locations={"17.72S, 0.86E","17.45S, 0.80E","17.53S, 0.82E"},name="Obelisk"}},level=43,minlevel=38,repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nSeek out the Nazgûl and end his schemes.\n* End the Nazgûl's plans\nObj 2:\nExamine the obelisk.\nYou have encountered an obelisk that was glowing faintly.\n* Examine the obelisk\nObj 3:\nSeek out the obelisks and open the way to the centre of the treasury.\nExamination of the obelisk found at the entrance to the treasury revealed that the only way to enter the centre treasury is to invoke the name of Elbereth at obelisks found scattered through out the treasury.\n* Use Obelisk\nObj 4:\nSeek out the Nazgûl and end his schemes.\nNow that you have invoked the name of the Elbereth at three of the obelisks in the treasury, the way to the centre of the treasury is open.\n* End the Nazgûl's plans",faction="FrP",instanced="Yes"},
{d="With your help, Glóin was able to obtain the key-stone to the secret entrance leading to the inner keep of the dwarf fortress located in the pass of Gabilazan. Alongside his son, Gimli, he has asked you to go into this keep and put a stop to the Nazgûl and Skogrím.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",id=2920,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 5, Instance: The Last Refuge",arcs="Volume I, Book 5: The Last Refuge",level=43,minlevel=38,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nSpeak with Gimli to begin your foray into the dwarf-keep.\nThe dwarf-keep in the pass of Gabilazan might be both the last hiding-place of the Dourhands led by Skorgrím and the Nazgûl you have pursued through the Trollshaws and into the Misty Mountains.\n* Talk to Gimli\nObj 2:\nSpeak with Gimli to continue your foray into the dwarf-keep.\nThe dwarf-keep in the pass of Gabilazan might be both the last hiding-place of the Dourhands led by Skorgrím and the Nazgûl you have pursued through the Trollshaws and into the Misty Mountains.\n* Talk to Gimli\nObj 3:\nSpeak with Gimli to continue your foray into the dwarf-keep.\nThe dwarf-keep in the pass of Gabilazan might be both the last hiding-place of the Dourhands led by Skorgrím and the Nazgûl you have pursued through the Trollshaws and into the Misty Mountains.\n* Talk to Gimli\nObj 4:\nYou have made your way deep into the dwarf-keep. It is nearly time to confront the Nazgûl and Skorgrím. Speak with Gimli to begin the final battle.\nThe dwarf-keep in the pass of Gabilazan might be both the last hiding-place of the Dourhands led by Skorgrím and the Nazgûl you have pursued through the Trollshaws and into the Misty Mountains.\n* Confront the Nazgûl and Skorgrím\nObj 5:\nGimli is standing in the courtyard of the keep of Gabilazan.\nYou have successfully defeated Skorgrím Dourhand, but the significance of his death is still uncertain.\n* Talk to Gimli"},
{["next"]={2880},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="A trained falcon arrived at Rivendell, bearing a troubling message from the hidden Ranger-camp at Esteldín for Aragorn, Chieftain of the Rangers.",mobs={{locations={"9.44S, 41.27W"},name="Daervunn"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 6: Fires in the North",id=2921,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 6, Chapter 1: Of Golodir and Angmar",arcs="Volume I, Book 6: Fires in the North",level=44,c={"* Go to Daervunn at Esteldín in the North Downs"},minlevel=39,b="Aragorn",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nEsteldín lies in the North Downs, far to the north and west of Rivendell.\nAragorn has asked you to travel to Esteldín in his stead to speak with Daervunn, whom he hopes can shed light on the troubling message.\n* Talk to Daervunn",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2881},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="Daervunn told you of how a wounded falcon arrived, bearing a message from Corunir, a Ranger from the company of Golodir, who defied Aragorn's commands and passed into Angmar, believing that a shadow had come again unto Carn Dûm.",mobs={{locations={"9.44S, 41.27W"},name="Daervunn"},{locations={"0.69N, 39.90W"},name="Corunir"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 6: Fires in the North",id=2922,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2879},name="Vol. I, Book 6, Chapter 2: Against His Lord",arcs="Volume I, Book 6: Fires in the North",level=45,minlevel=40,b="Daervunn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCorunir is at Aughaire, a Hillman-village in Angmar, somewhere north of Ram Dúath.\nDaervunn besought you to pass north through Ram Dúath and seek out the Ranger Corunir, who dwells now among the Hillmen of Angmar.\n* Talk to Corunir"},
{["next"]={2882},zone="Angmar",area="Aughaire",money={{val="22s 75c"}},d="Corunir told you of how Golodir raised up an army from among the Hillmen to assail Carn Dûm. The expedition failed, and Corunir was left alone, unable to pass Rammas Deluon -- now possessed of a terrible power -- to learn the fate of his captain and companions.",mobs={{locations={"0.69N, 39.90W"},name="Corunir"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 6: Fires in the North",id=2923,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2880},name="Vol. I, Book 6, Chapter 3: Secrets of the Stones",arcs="Volume I, Book 6: Fires in the North",level=44,c={"* Find the watching stone at [3.1N, 35.7W]\n* Return to Corunir in Aughaire"},pois={{locations={"3.08N, 30.62W","0.33N, 34.25W","4.85N, 37.15W","3.10N, 35.74W","5.61N, 38.72W","3.41N, 30.77W","6.10N, 38.66W","2.92N, 32.12W","4.68N, 36.78W","0.24S, 34.39W","5.26N, 38.18W"},name="Lesser Watching Stone"}},minlevel=39,b="Corunir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLesser watching-stones litter the landscape of western Angmar, especially near Angmarim and Hillman encampments.\nCorunir believes that the secret of Rammas Deluon can be revealed by investigating one of the lesser watching-stones. He has instructed you to find one of the lesser stones and take a rubbing of the runes upon it. He warned you to avoid fell and deadly watching-stones.\n* Use Lesser Watching Stone\n* Turn in Charcoal\n* Turn in Blank Parchment\nObj 2:\nCorunir is at the Hillman-village of Aughaire.\nWith the rubbings Corunir required in hand, you should return to the Ranger with your report.\n* Talk to Corunir\n* Turn in Watching-stone Rubbing"},
{["next"]={2883},zone="Angmar",area="Aughaire",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="The rubbing you made showed runes of a foul nature, written in the Black Speech, which Corunir is not well-versed in; however, he was able to make out something about the \\qheart\\q of the stone.",mobs={{locations={"0.69N, 39.90W"},name="Corunir"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 6: Fires in the North",id=2924,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2881},name="Vol. I, Book 6, Chapter 4: Heart of Stone",arcs="Volume I, Book 6: Fires in the North",receive={{val="Ithilchol",id="7000119E"}},level=45,c={"* Head north out of Aughaire then west into Western Malenhad. Do not try and cross the line of standing statues in the middle - you will be defeated instantly. Displays the prompt \"The will of the Silent Watchers has overpowered you.  You do not yet have the strength to overcome their malice.  You succumb to your wounds.\"  Fallen statues can be found in various pools in Malenhad. There is one available at [0.4N, 31.2W].\n* After successfully collecting a heart return to Corunir."},pois={{locations={"0.24S, 30.12W","1.00N, 31.34W","0.56S, 30.23W","0.88S, 30.11W","0.21S, 30.50W","0.08S, 30.41W","0.80S, 30.55W","0.30S, 30.40W","0.56N, 31.10W","0.43N, 31.18W","0.70S, 30.75W","0.20N, 30.16W","0.12S, 30.22W","0.47S, 30.74W","0.84N, 31.26W","0.67N, 31.17W","0.85N, 31.10W","0.52S, 30.67W"},name="Lifeless Watching-stone"}},minlevel=40,b="Corunir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLifeless watching-stones can be found in Western Malenhad, far to the east of Aughaire.\nCorunir has asked you to find one of the stone-hearts the runes spoke of by searching lifeless watching-stones.\n* Find/Use Lifeless Watching-stone\n* Find/Use Lifeless Watching-stone\nObj 2:\nCorunir is at the Hillman-village of Aughaire.\nYou should return to Corunir with the stone-heart that you discovered.\n* Talk to Corunir\n* Turn in Cracked Heart-stone"},
{["next"]={2884},zone="Angmar",area="Aughaire",money={{val="23s 10c"}},d="While the stone-heart you found was cracked and useless, another path still remains open. Corunir has learned of a ritual taking place at the fortress of Tór Gailvin, which may yield a whole heart if interrupted.",mobs={{locations={"0.69N, 39.90W"},name="Corunir"}},selectoneof={{val="Fist of Gundabad",id=70001723},{val="Eruis",id=70001722},{val="Edhelharloch",id=70001724}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 6: Fires in the North",id=2925,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2882},name="Vol. I, Book 6, Chapter 5: The Sorcerer's Doom",arcs="Volume I, Book 6: Fires in the North",level=45,c={"* Enter Tór Gailvin and defeat Sorcerer Tath. The spirit will aggro after Tath is dead but does not need to be defeated.\n* Loot Tath's body and return to Corunir in Aughaire."},minlevel=40,b="Corunir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTath is at Tór Gailvin, north-east of Aughaire, east of the Fail-á-Khro.\nCorunir has sent you to Tór Gailvin to wrest a stone-heart from a sorcerer of Angmar named Tath.\n* Bring the stone-heart to Corunir\n* Turn in Stone-heart"},
{["next"]={1903,2352,2720,2464,1357,2064,2334,2885,405,631,2284,3238,3188,962,1730,933,1144,632,2370,710,427,1742,982,193,2551,408,2044,2601,2432,45,2646},zone="Angmar",area="Aughaire",money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="Corunir reacted strangely to the presence and touch of the stone-heart, recoiling from it in terror. He told you that the heart had been prepared to receive a fell spirit from an elder Age, similar to those that inhabit the wights which serve Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"1.03S, 35.63W","6.31S, 33.12W","3.78S, 35.95W"},name="Ancient Watching-stone"},{locations={"0.69N, 39.90W"},name="Corunir"}},selectoneof={{val="Corunir's Robe",id="70006B32"},{val="Corunir's Axe",id=70001729},{val="Thalronn",id="7000172B"},{val="Eiliangor",id=70001728}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 6: Fires in the North",id=2926,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2883},name="Vol. I, Book 6, Chapter 6: Challenging the Stone",arcs="Volume I, Book 6: Fires in the North",level=46,c={"* Find one of the Watching-stones in the Ram Dúath. There at least 2 possible locations\nBetween Duvairë (Morroval) and Frith-vailë among the seige-engines (easiest to reach).\n* Between Bail Róva and Frith-vailë.\n* Use the stone & fight its spirit.\n* Return to Corunir in Aughaire."},minlevel=41,b="Corunir",repeatable="No",traits={{val="Conqueror of the Watching-stones"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe ancient watching-stone is near the eastern pass of Ram Dúath, near Bail Róva, east of Aughaire.\nCorunir believes that the stone-heart may be able to draw forth the fell spirit from another watching-stone and has asked you to test his theory upon an ancient watching-stone which guards the passes of Ram Dúath.\n* Kill 1 Enraged Fell-spirit\n* Present Heart-stone to Ancient Watching-stone\nObj 2:\nCorunir is at the Hillman-village of Aughaire, west of Bail Róva.\nWith the spirit of the ancient watching-stone defeated, you should return to Corunir with the news of hope.\n* Talk to Corunir\n* Turn in Stone-heart"},
{["next"]={2887,3212},zone="Angmar",area="Aughaire",money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="Your defeat of the ancient watching-stone of Ram Dúath has proven that the stones can be defied.",mobs={{locations={"0.69N, 39.90W"},name="Corunir"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 6: Fires in the North",id=2927,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2884},name="Vol. I, Book 6, Chapter 7: Beyond Rammas Deluon",arcs="Volume I, Book 6: Fires in the North",level=46,c={"* Talk to Braigiar at Gabilshathûr."},minlevel=41,b="Corunir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRammas Deluon lies far to the east of Aughaire in Malenhad. Corunir suggested you look for a dwarf encampment in the south past the Rammas Deluon.\nCorunir bade you pass through Rammas Deluon, for you no longer have cause to fear the deadly stones. He hopes that you may find a remnant of the force Golodir led through the stones somewhere on the other side.\n* Search for survivors from Golodir's band"},
{["next"]={2879},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="9s 10c"}},d="The shadow of Angmar -- Sauron's hand in the North -- grows steadily, threatening the peace and security of Eriador.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 6: Fires in the North",id=2928,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 6, Foreword: Turning to the North",arcs="Volume I, Book 6: Fires in the North",level=44,minlevel=39,b="Elrond",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nAragorn waits in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nElrond warned you of a growing evil within Angmar and asked you to speak with Aragorn.\n* Talk to Aragorn in Rivendell",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2888},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="After discovering the secret of the watching-stones of Rammas Deluon, Corunir sent you into the eastern reaches of Angmar, seeking the Rangers and Hillmen of Aughaire who had marched forth to throw down the rising power of Angmar. You found the Ranger Braigiar at the dwarf-outpost of Gabilshathûr in Malenhad.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Lorniel"},{locations={"10.87N, 23.93W"},name="Areneth"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2929,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2885},name="Vol. I, Book 7, Chapter 1: Hidden in Shadow",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",level=46,c={"* Head north from Gabilshathûr to the hidden refuge of Gath Forthnír\n* Talk to Areneth, then to Lorniel who is in a room inside."},minlevel=41,b="Braigiar",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGath Forthnír lies somewhere far to the north of Gabilshathûr.\nBraigiar has sent you to find and lend aid to the survivors of Golodir's company at the encampment of Gath Forthnír.\n* Find the Rangers of Gath Forthnír\nObj 2:\nLorniel is inside the building at Gath Forthnír.\nAreneth told you to speak with Lorniel, daughter of Golodir.\n* Talk to Lorniel"},
{["next"]={2889},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="23s 45c"}},d="Lorniel told you that she believes her father still lives, held captive in the dungeons of Carn Dûm. She hopes to find a way inside the terrible city and rescue him.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Lorniel"},{locations={"9.79N, 27.36W"},name="Raghnall"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2930,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2887},name="Vol. I, Book 7, Chapter 2: Crossing the Shadow",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",level=46,c={"* Head West from Gath Forthnír to find Raghnall\n* When you've spoke to him, 1 Hunting Morroval will show up but it will disappear after a minute so you don't have to kill them\n* Return to Lorniel"},minlevel=41,b="Lorniel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMeet with Raghnall south of Bail Cátharnakh, west of Gath Forthnír.\nLorniel told you that she had heard from a Hillman named Raghnall who was seeking to leave the service of Angmar and might have information that will allow her to gain access to Carn Dûm.\n* Talk to Raghnall\nObj 2:\nLorniel can be found within Gath Forthnír, east of Bail Cátharnakh.\nYou met with Raghnall and he gave you a scroll that explains how to forge a key for the Gates of Carn Dûm.\n* Talk to Lorniel\n* Turn in Tattered Scroll"},
{["next"]={2890},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="You retrieved the scroll from Raghnall, but it was written in Black Speech, which Lorniel is unable to translate.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Lorniel"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Laerdan"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2931,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2888},name="Vol. I, Book 7, Chapter 3: Opening the Way",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",level=47,minlevel=42,b="Lorniel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLaerdan is in Gath Forthnír.\nLorniel suggested you seek out an Elf named Laerdan in hopes of learning what Raghnall's scroll would reveal.\n* Talk to Laerdan\nObj 2:\nElrond Halfelven is at Rivendell in the Trollshaws.\nLaerdan, also unable to translate the scroll, sent you to Rivendell to speak with Elrond Halfelven.\n* Talk to Elrond\n* Turn in Tattered Scroll"},
{["next"]={2891},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="23s 80c"}},d="You journeyed to Rivendell to seek the aid of Elrond Halfelven in translating Raghnall's scroll. The Master of the Last Homely House gave you a mysterious welcome, but did offer to assist you.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2932,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2889},name="Vol. I, Book 7, Chapter 4: Dwarf Mastery",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",level=47,c={"* Go to Dwalin in Thorin's Hall"},minlevel=42,b="Elrond",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDwalin is at Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin.\nElrond transcribed the scroll into Westron, but told you to seek the aid of Dwalin and the dwarves of Ered Luin in forging the pass-key to Carn Dûm.\n* Talk to Dwalin\n* Turn in Elven Scroll"},
{["next"]={2892},zone="The Shire",area="The Delving Fields",money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="Dwalin, Master of Thorin's Hall, has agreed to help you forge the key, but there are some vital components missing.",mobs={{locations={"33.41S, 75.57W"},name="Keeper Brombard Foxtail"},{locations={"25.08S, 48.86W"},name="Jon Brackenbrook"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2933,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2890},name="Vol. I, Book 7, Chapter 5: What Is Needed",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",receive={{val="Balanin",id="7000056B"}},level=48,minlevel=43,b="Dwalin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nKeeper Brombard Foxtail is at the Mathom-house in Michel Delving in the western part of the Shire. Jon Brackenbrook is in the town of Archet, north-east of Bree-town.\nDwalin informed you that he needs a mithril nugget, which might be in the keeping of the Mathom-house in the Shire, and a key to cast a mould from, which might be obtained from Jon Brackenbrook, the new Captain of Archet.\n* Talk to Keeper Brombard Foxtail\n* Talk to Jon Brackenbrook\nObj 2:\nDwalin can be found in Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin.\nDwalin sent you to get a mithril nugget from the Mathom-house in the Shire and a key to help in casting a mould from Jon Brackenbrook in Archet.\n* Talk to Dwalin\n* Turn in Mithril-nugget\n* Turn in Ruined Key\nObj 3:\nLitli can be found by the forge near the throne of Thorin's Hall.\nNow that you have recovered the mithril and Éogan's key, Litli, one of Dwalin's smiths, can begin work on the key.\n* Talk to Litli\n* Turn in Mithril-nugget\n* Turn in Ruined Key\nObj 4:\nDwalin can be found in Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin.\nLitli took the mithril from you and began heating it. However, he mentioned that shaping the mithril will be a problem, one that perhaps Dwalin can solve.\n* Talk to Dwalin"},
{["next"]={2893},money={{val="24s 15c"}},d="You obtained the mithril nugget and the ruined key as Dwalin asked, but his smith, Litli, informed you that there was still one more thing needed to work the mithril.",selectoneof={{val="Litli's Shield",id="7001618A"},{val="Goluamath",id="70000E19"},{val="Dwalin's Shield",id="70000E18"},{val="Faerdamil's Bane",id="70000E17"},{val="Drake-biter",id="70000E16"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2934,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2891},name="Vol. I, Book 7, Chapter 6: Thrór's Hammer",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",level=48,c={"* Head to the NE corner of Thorin's Gate and enter Skorgrím's Tomb.\n* The first two groups of Wights will have powerful disease effects, so be prepared.\n* Defeat the two groups of two L49-50 Wights per group.\n* Watch out for the trap spikes.  They are easy to recognize and can be timed without difficulty.\n* Head due west until you reach Faerdami, a signature mob with about 4.4K Morale.\n* Defeat Faerdami and loot the hammer.  He restricts the area you can move about in, so it is a close up fight.\n* Return to Litli at Thorin's Hall"},minlevel=43,b="Dwalin",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThrór's Hammer lies within the tomb of Skorgrím Dourhand. The tomb lies south of Thorin's Hall, in the Berghold.\nDwalin told you he needed a hammer that Thrór, Thorin's grandfather and last King Under the Mountain before the coming of Smaug, took with him into exile and which Thráin his son brought to the Blue Mountains.\n* Bring Thrór's Hammer to Dwalin\n* Turn in Thrór's Hammer\nObj 2:\nLitli can be found by the forges near the throne of Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin.\nYou should take the hammer you found to Litli so that he can forge the key you need.\n* Talk to Litli\n* Turn in Thrór's Hammer"},
{["next"]={2894},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="After retrieving Thrór's Hammer and the necessary materials, Dwalin's smith, Litli, forged for you a mithril key that should allow you to pass the gates of Carn Dûm.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Lorniel"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2935,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2892},name="Vol. I, Book 7, Chapter 7: The Key Forged",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",level=49,c={"* Return to Lorniel in Gath Forthnír."},minlevel=44,b="Litli",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLorniel awaits your return at Gath Forthnír in eastern Angmar.\nYou should return with the key to Lorniel.\n* Talk to Lorniel\n* Turn in Key to the Gates of Carn Dûm"},
{["next"]={2897,1141},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="49s"}},d="With the key to Carn Dûm in hand, the time has come to move against the forces of the False King and try to rescue Golodir.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Lorniel"}},selectoneof={{val="Gaelnin",id="700011AF"},{val="Faerthol",id="700011AD"},{val="Faercharab",id="700011AC"},{val="Faerchar",id="700011AE"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2936,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2893},name="Vol. I, Book 7, Chapter 8: The Gates of Carn Dûm",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",receive={{val="Gates of Carn Dûm Key",id="700011AB"}},level=49,c={"* Talk to Lorniel to enter the instance\n* Protect Lorniel as you fight through several groups of Angamarin, trolls, little people, and others. AOE skills will be very helpful.\n* Fight round to the opposite side of the gate and pull the lever\n* Protect Lorniel through several more groups.\n* Defeat Mordirith, who has about 49K morale. Persistence is the key!"},minlevel=44,b="Lorniel",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLorniel awaits you at Gath Forthnír in eastern Angmar.\nLorniel told you to speak with her again when you were ready to begin your raid on Carn Dûm.\nThis quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great.\n* Talk to Lorniel\nObj 2:\nGolodir is at Gath Forthnír.\nYou have rescued Golodir, but at a terrible cost. The False King, Mordirith, appeared and slew her. You were able to weaken Mordirith and escape with Golodir back to Gath Forthnír.\n* Talk to Golodir"},
{d="You have travelled to Rhunendin with Lorniel. Using the key you helped forge, she is going to search for her father.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2937,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 7, Instance: The Gates of Carn Dûm",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",level=49,c={"* Follow Lorniel\n* Push the lever using the path on the right side\n* Follow Lorniel until the East Gate of Carn Dûm\n* Defeat Mordirith\n* Talk to Golodir"},minlevel=44,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nProtect Lorniel as she searches for her father, Golodir.\n* Talk to Lorniel\nObj 2:\nUse the lever on the other side of the gate.\nAs you progressed deeper into Rhunendin, you encountered a gate the key to Carn Dûm would not open. You should make your way to the lever and open the gate for Lorniel.\n* Open the gate for Lorniel\nObj 3:\nProtect Lorniel as she searches for her father, Golodir.\n* Talk to Lorniel\nObj 4:\nProtect Lorniel as she searches for her father, Golodir.\n* Talk to Lorniel\nObj 5:\nAfter you found Golodir, Lorniel was slain.  Now the False King stands before you, far from his source of power. Now is the time to defeat Mordirith.\n* Defeat Mordirith, the False King\nObj 6:\nGolodir is waiting to talk to you.\nYou have found Golodir and driven off Mordirith, but at a terrible cost.\n* Talk to Golodir"},
{d="At Dwalin's direction, you have travelled to the abandoned tomb of Skorgrím Dourhand to search for mithril-shaping hammer of Thorin's grandfather, Thrór.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",id=2938,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 7, Instance: Thrór's Hammer",arcs="Volume I, Book 7: The Hidden Hope",level=48,minlevel=43,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nSearch Skorgrím's tomb for Thrór's Hammer.\n* Search for Thrór's Hammer\nObj 2:\nDefeat Faerdami, a fell-spirit who has taken possession of Thrór's Hammer.\n* Kill 1 Faerdamil"},
{["next"]={2898},reputation={{val="+1200 with Council of the North"}},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="39s 20c"}},d="The assault on Carn Dûm saw the freedom of the Ranger Golodir, but proved fruitless as Lorniel perished, and Mordirith, the Steward of Angmar, withdrew into the fastness of the city.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Laerdan"}},selectoneof={{val="Cúrain",id="700011B6"},{val="Laerdan's Earring",id="700011B5"},{val="Rochbenaith",id="700011B4"},{val="Laerdan's Axe",id="700011B3"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",id=2939,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2894},name="Vol. I, Book 8, Chapter 1: The Flickering Flame",arcs="Volume I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",level=49,c={"* This quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great."},minlevel=44,b="Golodir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLaerdan is at Gath Forthnír.\nGolodir, crushed by his daughter's death, told you to leave him be and to go speak with the Elf Laerdan.\nThis quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great.\n* Talk to Laerdan\nObj 2:\nGolodir's gear was given to emissaries from the goblins, dwarves and nomads of Angmar. These emissaries can be found in the spires surrounding Barad Gúlaran to the south of Gath Forthnír.\nAs a first step in his plan to renew Golodir's spirit, Laerdan has asked you to retrieve the Ranger's weapons and gear from the emissaries within the towers of Barad Gúlaran.\nThis quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great.\n* Bring Golodir's gear to Laerdan\n* Turn in Golodir's Sword\n* Turn in Golodir's Mail-shirt\n* Turn in Gondorian Shield"},
{["next"]={2899},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="You managed to recover Golodir's equipment, but as Laerdan pointed out to you, the gear was corroded and decayed beyond use.",mobs={{locations={"9.46S, 41.95W"},name="Toram"},{locations={"9.44S, 41.27W"},name="Daervunn"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Laerdan"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",id=2940,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2897},name="Vol. I, Book 8, Chapter 2: Rekindling the Flame",arcs="Volume I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",level=49,minlevel=44,b="Laerdan",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDaervunn is at Esteldín in the North Downs, far to the south and west of Angmar.\nLaerdan instructed you to take Golodir's equipment to the Ranger Daervunn to be repaired.\n* Talk to Daervunn\n* Turn in Golodir's Mail-shirt\nObj 2:\nToram is in Esteldín.\nDaervunn felt he could repair Golodir's shirt, but the sword and shield were beyond his ability. He asked you to speak to Toram in Esteldín to have those items repaired.\n* Talk to Toram\n* Turn in Golodir's Sword\n* Turn in Gondorian Shield\nObj 3:\nReclaim Golodir's sword and shield from Toram in Esteldín.\nDaervunn asked you to take Golodir's sword and shield to Toram, an armoursmith in Esteldín, for repair.\n* Talk to Toram\nObj 4:\nDaervunn is at Esteldín.\nYou should return to Daervunn to collect Golodir's shirt and to see if he has any thoughts on how to repair Golodir's sword.\n* Talk to Daervunn\n* Turn in Gondorian Shield\n* Turn in Golodir's Sword"},
{["next"]={2900},zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="The Rangers of Esteldín were able to repair Golodir's shield and mail shirt, but the sword was of Elf-craft beyond their skill.",mobs={{locations={"9.44S, 41.27W"},name="Daervunn"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"},{locations={"28.53S, 6.22W"},name="Hemeldir"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",id=2941,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2898},name="Vol. I, Book 8, Chapter 3: Forging the Sword",arcs="Volume I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",level=49,c={"* Elrond is at Rivendell in the Trollshaws.\n* Hemeldir can be found near Rivendell's forges [28.5S, 6.2W]"},minlevel=44,b="Daervunn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nElrond is at Rivendell in the Trollshaws.\nDaervunn suggested you take Golodir's sword to Elrond of Rivendell to be reforged.\n* Bring Golodir's gear to Elrond\nObj 2:\nHemeldir can be found near Rivendell's forges.\nElrond instructed you to take Golodir's sword to his chief smith, Hemeldir, to be reforged.\n* Talk to Hemeldir\n* Turn in Golodir's Sword\nObj 3:\nHemeldir can be found near Rivendell's forges.\nYou should check with Hemeldir to learn if he has finished reforging Golodir's sword.\n* Collect Golodir's sword from Hemeldir\nObj 4:\nElrond is in Rivendell.\nHemeldir returned Golodir's reforged sword to you and told you to bring it to Elrond for approval.\n* Talk to Elrond\n* Turn in Forged Sword\n* Turn in Golodir's Mail-shirt\n* Turn in Gondorian Shield"},
{["next"]={2901},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="24s 50c"}},d="Elrond renamed Golodir's sword Dúnachar, Avenger of the West, and prophesied that it would one day avenge the death of Lorniel, Golodir's daughter.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Elrond"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Laerdan"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",id=2942,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2899},name="Vol. I, Book 8, Chapter 4: A Beacon of Hope",arcs="Volume I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",level=49,c={"* Laerdann and Golodir are in Gath Forthnír in Angmar"},minlevel=44,b="Elrond",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLaerdan is at Gath Forthnír in the eastern reaches of Himbar.\nElrond gave you the sword Dúnachar and told you to take it and the rest of Golodir's gear to Laerdan.\n* Talk to Laerdan\n* Turn in Dúnachar\n* Turn in Gondorian Shield\n* Turn in Golodir's Mail-shirt\nObj 2:\nGolodir is at Gath Forthnír in the eastern reaches of Himbar.\nLaerdan instructed you to return Golodir's gear to him.\n* Talk to Golodir\n* Turn in Golodir's Mail-shirt\n* Turn in Gondorian Shield\n* Turn in Dúnachar"},
{["next"]={2902,1142},reputation={{val="+1200 with Council of the North"}},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="49s 70c"}},d="Laerdan's hopes of using the sword and armour of Golodir to renew the Ranger's spirit were not in vain. The sight of the shining shield of Gondor and of his bright-burning sword, Dúnachar, kindled within Golodir a new fire...perhaps a dangerous one.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"}},selectoneof={{val="Aranham",id="700011B9"},{val="Ríanham",id="700011BB"},{val="Bane of Mordirith",id="700011BD"},{val="Heronham",id="700011BA"},{val="Foe of Mordirith",id="700011BC"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",id=2943,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2900},name="Vol. I, Book 8, Chapter 5: Mordirith's Fall",arcs="Volume I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",receive={{val="Phial of the Swirling Waters",id="700011B8"}},level=50,c={"* This quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great."},minlevel=45,b="Golodir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nMordirith can be found within the throne room of Carn Dûm.\nGolodir has asked you to join him as he returns to Carn Dûm to face Mordirith, the False King, Steward of Angmar.\nThis quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great.\n* Speak to Golodir\nObj 2:\nGolodir is at Gath Forthnír.\nAfter defeating Mordirith and encountering the mysterious Sara Oakheart, you and Golodir travelled back to Gath Forthnír. You should speak with Golodir again.\n* Talk to Golodir in Gath Forthnír"},
{["next"]={2905,2914},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="With Golodir's aid, you have greatly weakened Mordirith, the Steward of Angmar, and avenged the death of Lorniel.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},selectoneof={{val="Thaliongron",id="700011A2"},{val="Idhrinn",id="700011A0"},{val="Anghigil",id="700011A1"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",id=2944,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2901},name="Vol. I, Book 8, Chapter 6: A Watchful Eye",arcs="Volume I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",level=50,c={"* Aragorn in Rivendell in one of the guest rooms [30.7S, 6.2W]"},minlevel=45,b="Golodir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nAragorn is at Rivendell in the Trollshaws, in one of the guest rooms along the road that winds up the southern slope of the Vale of Imladris.\nGolodir instructed you to take word of Mordirith's fall to his chieftain, Aragorn.\n* Talk to Aragorn in Rivendell"},
{d="You have travelled deep into Carn Dûm with Golodir, into the very fortress of the Witch-king himself. Here Golodir hopes to confront Mordirith and shatter the Iron Crown forever.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",id=2945,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 8, Instance: Mordirith's Fall",arcs="Volume I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",level=50,c={"* This quest is meant for a fellowship. If you choose to undertake this quest solo you will receive an inspiration bonus, but the challenge will be great."},minlevel=45,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nAid Golodir as you make your way deeper into the Castle of the Witch-king.\n* Speak to Golodir\nObj 2:\nWith the light of Dúnachar, Golodir has defeated Mordirith, although the villain escaped before he could be completely defeated. You should speak with Golodir to see what he would wish you to do.\n* Talk to Golodir\nObj 3:\nYou should speak with Golodir at once.\n* Talk to Golodir"},
{d="You have entered Minas Maur in search of Prakhum, the emissary of Goblin-town.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North",id=2946,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 8, Instance: The Flickering Flame",level=50,minlevel=45,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nYou must defeat Prakhum, the emissary of Goblin-town, in order to retrieve some of Golodir's equipment.\n* Defeat Prakhum\nQuest: Vol. I, Book 8, Instance: The Flickering Flame\nCategory: Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North\nScope: Epic\nMin Level: 45\nDescription\nYou have entered Minas Angos in search of Laugi Goldentongue, the emissary of the Dourhands.\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nYou must defeat Laugi Goldentongue, the emissary of the Dourhands from the Blue Mountains, in order to retrieve some of Golodir's equipment.\n* Defeat Laugi Goldentongue\nQuest: Vol. I, Book 8, Instance: The Flickering Flame\nCategory: Epic - Vol. I, Book 8: The Scourge of the North\nScope: Epic\nMin Level: 45\nDescription\nYou have entered Minas Agar in search of Karstíona, the emissary of the Trév Duvárdain.\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nYou must defeat Karstíona, the emissary of the Trév Duvárdain from western Angmar, in order to retrieve some of Golodir's equipment.\n* Defeat Karstíona"},
{["next"]={2906},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="Mordirith, the False King, has been defeated and sent back to Mordor houseless, but the mysterious Sara Oakheart stole the palantír Mordirith had in his possession. This greatly concerns Gandalf the Grey.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"},{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Gandalf"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2947,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2902},name="Vol. I, Book 9, Chapter 1: Oakheart Unhidden",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Gandalf",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGolodir is at Gath Forthnír in Angmar, far to the north of Rivendell.\nGandalf the Grey has instructed you to return to Gath Forthnír and help Golodir to search for Sara Oakheart and the missing palantír.\n* Talk to Golodir\nObj 2:\nSara Oakheart is at Barad Gúlaran in Nan Gurth in Angmar. Barad Gúlaran is located in the centre of a series of bridges that surround it like the spokes of a waggon-wheel. Sara Oakheart was seen by the tower located at the most south-easterly of these bridges.\nSara Oakheart has been found outside Barad Gúlaran. Golodir has told you to be careful.\n* Talk to Sara Oakheart"},
{["next"]={2024,1429,308,1979,2907},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="You have found Sara Oakheart at Barad Gúlaran, the ancient retreat of the Witch-king of Angmar.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2948,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2905},name="Vol. I, Book 9, Chapter 2: Oakheart's Might",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Sara Oakheart",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSara Oakheart has asked you to escort her into Barad Gúlaran.\n* Help Sara Oakheart get to the heart of Barad Gúlaran\nObj 2:\nGolodir is at Gath Forthnír.\nYou should return to Golodir and tell him what happened at Barad Gúlaran.\n* Talk to Golodir"},
{["next"]={2912},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Golodir is concerned that Mordirith's Knights will be taken into Amarthiel's service.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"}},selectoneof={{val="Parthranc",id="7000A240"},{val="Tatharanc",id="7000A246"},{val="Rododhranc",id="7000A24C"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2949,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2906},name="Vol. I, Book 9, Chapter 3: Golodir's Request",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Golodir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nYour allies may be found in Ost Guruth in the Lone-lands, Esteldín in the North Downs, and in your homelands -- Combe for hobbits and the race of Men and Gondamon for dwarf and Elf-kind.\nGolodir has asked you to return to three places where Sara Oakheart has been encountered in the past and speak with allies in those places.\nObj 2:\nGolodir is at Gath Forthnír in Angmar.\nYou should return to Golodir and tell him the task is completed.\n* Talk to Golodir"},
{requiredraces="Hobbit",zone="Bree-land",area="Combe",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Constable Underhill mentioned that there is a new threat in the Chetwood and that maybe it is the Knight whom you seek.",mobs={{locations={"28.73S, 49.28W"},name="Constable Underhill"}},selectoneof={{val="Angronn",id="7000A26F"},{val="Purger of Chetwood",id="7000A26C"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2950,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 9, Chapter 3: Journey to Combe",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Constable Underhill",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Knight of Mordirith can be found near an evil idol in the Chetwood, north-east of Combe.\nConstable Underhill told you how to find the threat in the Chetwood, which might be the Knight you seek.\n* Find the Knight of Mordirith\nObj 2:\nConstable Underhill is outside The Comb and Wattle in Combe, south-west of the Knight's camp.\nHaving defeated the Knight of Mordirith, you return to Constable Underhill and let him know that the threat is ended.\n* Talk to Constable Underhill"},
{zone="The North Downs",area="Esteldín",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Daervunn has warned you of a new threat to the north near the entrance to Ram Dúath and that maybe it is the Knight you seek.",mobs={{locations={"9.44S, 41.27W"},name="Daervunn"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2951,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 9, Chapter 3: Journey to Esteldín",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Daervunn",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Knight of Mordirith may be found near Ost Crithlanc, north-east of Esteldín.\nDaervunn told you of a new threat in the north, which may be the Knight you seek.\n* Find the Knight of Mordirith\nObj 2:\nDaervunn is at Esteldín, south of the mouth of Ram Dúath.\nHaving defeated the Knight of Mordirith, You should return to Daervunn and let him know of your success.\n* Speak with Daervunn at Esteldin",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{requiredraces="Dwarf",zone="Ered Luin",area="Low Lands",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Mathi Stouthand has warned you of a new threat to the north of Gondamon and that maybe it is the Knight you seek.",mobs={{locations={"20.29S, 96.69W"},name="Mathi"}},selectoneof={{val="Mathi's Master Axe",id="7000A271"},{val="Arangrist",id="7000A26A"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2952,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 9, Chapter 3: Journey to Gondamon",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,c={"* The Knight of Mordirith in Ered Luin is Kevoca (lvl 50 Signature with 4,428 morale) and can be found near Ringdale [18.4S, 96.1W]"},minlevel=45,b="Mathi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Knight of Mordirith might be found north of Gondamon.\nMathi Stouthand suggested that the threat to the north of Gondamon may be the Knight you seek.\n* Find the Knight of Mordirith\nObj 2:\nMathi Stouthand is at Gondamon, south of the Knight's camp.\nHaving defeated the Knight of Mordirith, you should return to Mathi Stouthand and let him know that you were successful.\n* Talk to Mathi"},
{zone="The Lone-lands",area="Nain Enidh",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Frideric the Elder has warned you of a new threat in the southern bogs and that maybe it is the Knight you seek.",mobs={{locations={"31.49S, 29.50W"},name="Frideric the Elder"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2953,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 9, Chapter 3: Journey to the Lone-lands",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",c={"* The Knight of Mordirith in the Lone-lands is Neacal (lvl 50 Signature with 4,428 morale) and can be found in Harloeg [39.2S, 25.1W]"},level=50,minlevel=45,b="Frideric the Elder",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe Knight of Mordirith may be found somewhere within Harloeg, south and east of Ost Guruth.\nFrideric the Elder suggested that you might find the Knight of Mordirith in the southern bog.\n* Find the Knight of Mordirith\nObj 2:\nFrideric the Elder is at Ost Guruth, north and west of Harloeg.\nHaving defeated the Knight of Mordirith, you should return to Frideric the Elder and let him know of your success.\n* Talk to Frideric the Elder",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={2913},reputation={{val="+300 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Angmar",area="Himbar",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="Golodir was pleased with your success in the south, but is still concerned with Amarthiel and her possession of a palantír.",mobs={{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Golodir"},{locations={"10.90N, 23.93W","10.89N, 23.93W"},name="Laerdan"},{locations={"12.72S, 67.18W"},name="Calenglad"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2954,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2907},name="Vol. I, Book 9, Chapter 4: Amarthiel's Trail",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Golodir",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nLaerdan is on the other side of the cave at Gath Forthnír.\nGolodir instructed you to speak with Laerdan to learn how you can help him track down Amarthiel.\n* Talk to Laerdan\nObj 2:\nCalenglad is at the Ranger-camp at Tinnudir on the eastern shore of Lake Evendim.\nLaerdan instructed you to go to the Ranger-camp in Evendim to speak with the Ranger Calenglad.\n* Talk to Calenglad"},
{["next"]={2917},reputation={{val="+900 with The Wardens of Annúminas"}},zone="Evendim",area="Parth Aduial",money={{val="39s 76c"}},d="Calenglad has informed you that there has been a recent growth in the number of Angmarim outside of Annúminas.",mobs={{locations={"12.72S, 67.18W"},name="Calenglad"}},selectoneof={{val="Calenglad's Rune-stone",id=70016189},{val="Jormund's Uncut Diamond",id="7000A260"},{val="Calenglad's Ring",id="7000B3FF"},{val="Mirechor",id="7000A258"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2955,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2912},name="Vol. I, Book 9, Chapter 5: Amarthiel's Hope",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Calenglad",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nCalenglad is at the Ranger-camp at Tinnudir on the eastern shore of Lake Evendim.\nSpeak with Calenglad when you are ready to leave for Annúminas.\n* Discover Amarthiel's plans at Annúminas\nObj 2:\nCalenglad is at the Ranger-camp at Tinnudir on the eastern shore of Lake Evendim.\nYou should speak with Calenglad again, now that you have discovered Amarthiel's plans.\n* Talk to Calenglad"},
{["next"]={2905},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="Aragorn believes that Gandalf should be informed of the mysterious Sara Oakheart's theft of the palantír.",mobs={{locations={"29.77S, 3.38W","29.59S, 3.10W","29.60S, 3.10W"},name="Gandalf"},{locations={"30.70S, 6.20W"},name="Aragorn"}},category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2956,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={2902},name="Vol. I, Book 9, Foreword: News of the Palantír",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,c={"* Gandalf is in Bilbo's room on the ground floor of the Last Homely House, in Rivendell."},minlevel=45,b="Aragorn",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nGandalf is in Bilbo's room on the first floor of the Last Homely House, in Rivendell.\nAragorn has sent you to speak with Gandalf.\n* Talk to Gandalf in Rivendell"},
{d="Calenglad has asked you to find Amarthiel and discover her plans. He has sent you to Annúminas with five Rangers to help fight off the Angmarim.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2957,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 9, Instance: Amarthiel's Hope",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,minlevel=45,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nSpeak with the Ranger Protector before you search for Amarthiel.\n* Talk to the Ranger Protector standing before you\nObj 2:\nFind Amarthiel and discover her plans.\n* Find and stop Amarthiel\nObj 3:\nYou must defeat the Black Númenórean.\n* Kill 1 Morguldur"},
{d="Sara Oakheart has asked you to speak with her and would like you to follow her as she tells you her story.",category="Epic - Vol. I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",id=2958,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. I, Book 9, Instance: Oakheart's Might",arcs="Volume I, Book 9: The Shores of Evendim",level=50,c={"* Sara Oakheart is a lvl 50 Avenger with 44,284 morale. Just let her get the aggro of the spirits and help her beating on one of them.\n* Then just relax and watch the movie unwind.\n* You cannot avoid being defeated at the end of the instance."},minlevel=45,repeatable="No",instanced="Yes",faction="FrP",o="Obj 1:\nFollow Sara Oakheart into the heart of Barad Gúlaran.\n* Talk to Sara Oakheart\nObj 2:\nFollow Sara Oakheart into the heart of Barad Gúlaran.\n* Follow Sara Oakheart deeper into Barad Gúlaran"},
{requiredraces="Elf",["next"]={3029},zone="Eregion",area="Nan Sirannon",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="You have received a weapon from the Elder Days, discovered by the dwarves in a hidden cache, and you must now delve for its secrets.",mobs={{locations={"50.48S, 8.09W"},name="Hundi"}},selectoneof={{val="Scion of the Drowned Kingdom",id="70017D81"},{val="Guardian of the Deep Halls",id="70017D83"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2959,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3027},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 10: Forgotten Lineage",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",receive={{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Celebrant Salve",id="70000F40"},{q="(x3)",val="Distilled Athelas Essence",id="70000F31"}},level=50,c={"* Dithalion [28.5S, 6.2W] is by The Forges of Rivendell and Wafi [28.5S, 6.2W] is by The Forging Hall in Thorin's Hall\n* There is a dwarf Forge-master right at his side."},minlevel=45,b="Hundi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nWafi is in the Forging Hall of Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin.\nHundi has told you to show your new weapon to Wafi in Thorin's Hall. Wafi will be able to help determine the intrinsic characteristics of the weapon.\n* Talk to Wafi\nObj 2:\nRósar the Forge-master is in the Forging Hall in Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin. He has the skill to identify the mysterious weapon you have acquired.\nWafi has instructed you to have Rósar the Forge-master identify your weapon so that you may understand its strength and potential.\n* Bring the weapon to the Forge-master to be identified\nObj 3:\nNow that your weapon has been identified, you must equip it if you wish it to enhance its worth.\n* Equip your new weapon\nObj 4:\nWafi is in the Forging Hall of Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin.\nRósar the Forge-master has identified your weapon, and you should now show it to Wafi.\n* Talk to Wafi\nObj 5:\nWafi is in the Forging Hall of Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin.\nWafi has asked you to slot one of the Relics to your weapon in order to further customise its abilities.\n* Slot a Setting Relic in your weapon\nObj 6:\nWafi is in the Forging Hall of Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin.\nWafi has asked you to slot one of the Relics you have to your weapon in order to further customise its abilities, and is now waiting to speak with you.\n* Talk to Wafi\n//Hundi Location: 50.48S, 8.09W\nEregion >> Nan Sirannon';markerList['1879127503_0x041AD5C00000001C_61.1163.451384736'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952', new GLatLng(-5.7549462890625, 67.237734375), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952'; markers['1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Dithalion Location: 28.55S, 6.15W\nThe Trollshaws >> Rivendell Valley';markerList['1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952', new GLatLng(-5.7549462890625, 67.237734375), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952'; markers['1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Dithalion Location: 28.55S, 6.15W\nThe Trollshaws >> Rivendell Valley';markerList['1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker);  marker = createMarker( '1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952', new GLatLng(-5.7549462890625, 67.237734375), { 'icon':OTHERNPC_ICON }); marker.id = '1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952'; markers['1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952'] = marker; marker.caption = 'Dithalion Location: 28.55S, 6.15W\nThe Trollshaws >> Rivendell Valley';markerList['1879127504_0x041AF77000000058_130.16130.431400952'] = marker; map.addOverlay(marker); GME_DEFAULT_ICON = G_DEFAULT_ICON;      } else {        document.getElementById(\"map2708887658\").innerHTML = \"In order to see the map that would go in this space, you will need to use a compatible web browser.\";            }        if(firstMap == null) {          firstMap = map;        }      }      addLoadEvent(makeMap2708887658);\n//]]>\nQuest: Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 10: Forgotten Lineage\nCategory: Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria\nScope: Epic\nArc(s): Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria\nMin Level: 45\nRequired Races: Elf\nPrerequisite Quests:Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 9: A Weapon of the Elder Days OR Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 9: A Weapon of the Elder Days OR Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 9: A Weapon of the Elder Days OR Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 9: A Weapon of the Elder Days OR Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 9: A Weapon of the Elder Days OR Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 9: A Weapon of the Elder Days OR Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 9: A Weapon of the Elder Days OR Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 9: A Weapon of the Elder Days OR Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 9: A Weapon of the Elder Days\nNext Quests:Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 11: Worth Beyond Measure\nRewards\nMoney:\n9 94\nReceive:\nDistilled Celebrant Salve (x3)Select one of:\nScion of the Drowned Kingdom\nGuardian of the Deep Halls\nsetTooltips();\nDescription\nYou have received a weapon from the Elder Days that the dwarves discovered in a hidden cache, and you must now delve for its secrets.\nBestower\nHundi (NPC)\n'Weapons of this make may have a long and storied history, (your name). Its tale grows ever with the felling of evil foes -- the more servants of evil this weapon cuts down, the more deadly it becomes.\n'Only a skilful few can read the tale of a weapon from its craftsmanship. I refer you to one who can further aid you: the Elf Dithalion by the forges in Rivendell. He is wise and learned in many things, including the study of ancient weapons.\n'If Dithalion cannot help you, he will surely know another who can descry the lineage and powers in a weapon of this artistry.'\nObjectives\nObj 1:\nDithalion is by the forges in Rivendell.\nHundi bid you to show your new weapon to Dithalion, an Elf of Rivendell who will be able to help determine the intrinsic strengths of the weapon.\n* Talk to Dithalion\nObj 2:\nSnár the Forge-master is at the Forges of Rivendell, right next to Dithalion. He has the skill to identify the mysterious weapon you have acquired.\nDithalion has referred you to Snár the Forge-master, who will be able to identify your weapon. From him you may learn of its strengths and potential for growth.\n* Bring the weapon to the Forge-master to be identified\nObj 3:\nNow that your weapon has been identified, you must equip it if you wish it to increase in worth.\n* Equip your new weapon\nObj 4:\nDithalion is at the Forges of Rivendell.\nSnár the Forge-master has identified your new weapon, and you should speak now with Dithalion.\n* Talk to Dithalion\nObj 5:\nDithalion is at the Forges of Rivendell.\nDithalion has asked you to slot one of your Relics into your weapon in order to further customise its abilities.\n* Slot a Setting Relic into your weapon to further customise its abilities\nObj 6:\nDithalion is at the Forges of Rivendell.\nYou have slotted a Relic into your weapon and should now speak with Dithalion.\n* Talk to Dithalion"},
{["next"]={3030},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="Your new weapon has the potential for worth beyond measure, but you must yet wield it in battle.",mobs={{locations={"28.55S, 6.15W"},name="Dithalion"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2960,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3028},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 11: Worth Beyond Measure",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,c={"* Dithalion [28.5S, 6.2W] is by The Forges of Rivendell and Wafi [28.5S, 6.2W] is by The Forging Hall in Thorin's Hall\n* There is a dwarf Forge-master right at his side."},minlevel=45,b="Dithalion",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nYou must fight foes with the weapon you received from Sigthorn and Hundi until it reaches the tenth level of advancement.\nFighting enemies that grant you experience will also grant experience to certain weapons if you have them equipped.\n* Achieve the tenth level of advancement with your new weapon\nObj 2:\nWafi is in the Forging Hall of Thorin's Hall, in Ered Luin, and Dithalion is by the Forges of Rivendell.\nNow that you have fought many foes with your new weapon, you should return to either Wafi or Dithalion to demonstrate your progress.\n* Talk to Wafi\n* Talk to Dithalion"},
{["next"]={3031},zone="The Trollshaws",area="Rivendell Valley",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="You have advanced your weapon to an admirable level, and should now see what hidden strengths you have revealed.",mobs={{locations={"28.55S, 6.15W"},name="Dithalion"},{locations={"50.63S, 7.62W"},name="Ráthwald"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2961,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3029},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 12: Forged Anew",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,c={"* Once an Item Advancement weapon receives enough experience, it can be brought to a Forge-master to be reforged. Reforging such a weapon reveals its hidden potential."},minlevel=45,b="Dithalion",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nForge-masters can be found in the Forging Hall of Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin, and by the Forges of Rivendell.\nNow that your weapon has reached a high level of advancement, it can be reforged by a Forge-master. This process reveals a weapon's hidden potential.\n* Bring the weapon to the Forge-master to be reforged\nObj 2:\nWafi is in the Forging Hall of Thorin's Hall in Ered Luin, and Dithalion is by the Forges of Rivendell.\nNow that you have reforged the weapon, you should return to either Wafi or Dithalion to demonstrate its development.\n* Talk to Wafi\n* Talk to Dithalion\nObj 3:\nRáthwald is at the crumbling arch near the camp of Echad Dúnann in Eregion.\nYour weapon has become powerful indeed, perhaps powerful enough to use in battle with the Watcher before the Doors of Durin.\n* Talk to Ráthwald"},
{["next"]={3032},zone="Eregion",area="Nan Sirannon",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="You have become proficient with a lost weapon of the Elder Days, and the dwarves of Bósi's expedition are confident that you can now stand against the Watcher in the Water.",mobs={{locations={"50.63S, 7.62W"},name="Ráthwald"}},titles={{val="Seeker of Deep Places"}},selectoneof={{val="Studier of the Watcher",id="70017CA1"},{val="Survivor of the Watcher",id="70017C9F"},{val="Dodger of the Watcher",id="70017CA3"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2962,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3030},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 13: The Watcher in the Water",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,c={"* Talk to Ráthwald and finish the instance"},minlevel=45,b="Ráthwald",repeatable="No",traits={{val="Seeker of Deep Places"}},faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nRáthwald is at the ruined arch near Echad Dúnann, in Eregion.\nNow that you have a weapon strong enough to harm the Watcher in the Water, Ráthwald is waiting to bring you to Bósi.\n* Talk to Ráthwald and travel to face the Watcher\nObj 2:\nRáthwald is at the ruined arch near Echad Dúnann, in Eregion.\nYou have driven away the Watcher in the Water and the dwarves have entered Moria at last.\n* Talk to Ráthwald"},
{["next"]={3035,3043},zone="Eregion",area="Nan Sirannon",money={{val="10s 8c"}},d="The dwarves have entered Moria at last, but their work has just begun. You will need to assist them in their struggle if they are to find any success in the forgotten halls of Khazad-dûm.",mobs={{locations={"8.04S, 116.12W"},name="Tulk"},{locations={"50.63S, 7.62W"},name="Ráthwald"}},selectoneof={{val="Rune-keeper's Rune-bag",id="70017D7E"},{val="Hunter's Axe of the Third Age (Level 51)",id="70017E50"},{val="Burglar's Tools",id="70017D80"},{val="Warden's Spear of the Third Age (Level 51)",id="70017E4F"},{val="Captain's Emblem",id="70017D82"},{val="Guardian's Belt",id="70017D7F"},{val="Minstrel's Songbook",id="70017D7B"},{val="Lore-master's Book",id="70017D7A"},{val="Champion's Rune",id="70017D7D"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2963,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3031},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 14: Khazad-dûm At Last!",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=51,c={"* Go into Moria, if it is too dark, turn up the Gamma in the Graphics in the Options Menu."},minlevel=46,b="Ráthwald",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nTulk is just inside the Doors of Durin that stand by the still pool where you did battle with the Watcher in the Water.\nYou have been told to speak with Tulk about the dwarves that have entered Moria.\n* Talk to Tulk"},
{["next"]={3018},zone="Eregion",area="Nan Sirannon",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="An expedition of dwarves has come to Hollin intending to reclaim the lost halls of Khazad-dûm.",mobs={{locations={"50.73S, 7.19W"},name="Tulk"},{locations={"50.63S, 7.62W"},name="Ráthwald"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2964,scope="Epic",t="Epic",name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 1:  Strangers in Hollin",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Ráthwald",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nTulk is east of the ruined gate near the Walls of Moria, in the south-east of Eregion.\nRáthwald has told you that an expedition of dwarves has come to Hollin to seek out Balin within the halls of Khazad-dûm. He has told you to offer your aid to Tulk just beyond the ruined gate where he keeps watch.\n* Talk to Tulk",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={3019},zone="Eregion",area="Walls of Moria",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="You have offered your services to the expedition of dwarves that has come to Hollin to reclaim the halls of Khazad-dûm beneath the mountains.",mobs={{locations={"50.73S, 7.19W"},name="Tulk"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2965,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3017},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 2: Along the Sirannon",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Tulk",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nSpying crebain can be found along the banks of the dried-up Sirannon, south-east of the ruined gate in the area near the Walls of Moria.\nTulk has asked you to defeat the spying crebain along the banks of the Sirannon and to bring him their talons, which can be put to various uses.\n* Defeat spying crebain (4)\n* Turn in Jagged Talon\nObj 2:\nTulk can be found east of the ruined gate in the area near the Walls of Moria.\nThe dwarf Tulk awaits your return with the talons you collected from the spying crebain along the Sirannon.\n* Talk to Tulk\n* Turn in Jagged Talon"},
{["next"]={3020},zone="Eregion",area="Walls of Moria",d="Tulk has asked you to bring a report to Bósi, the leader of the expedition of dwarves. Bósi's kin have come to Hollin purposing to enter Moria.",mobs={{locations={"50.73S, 7.19W"},name="Tulk"},{locations={"51.37S, 5.89W"},name="Bósi"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2966,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3018},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 3: Bósi the Dwarf",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Tulk",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBósi is overseeing some of the waggons along the road through Hollin, south-east from the Hollin Gate and then bending to the north-east.\nTulk has given you a report to bring to Bósi, one of the dwarves leading the expedition to Hollin.\n* Talk to Bósi\n* Turn in Tulk's Report",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={3022,3021},zone="Eregion",area="Walls of Moria",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="Bósi has asked you to help re-supply the workers attempting to unearth the Hollin Gate with lunches in order to keep their spirits high.",mobs={{locations={"51.76S, 3.52W"},name="Wárr"},{locations={"51.37S, 5.89W"},name="Bósi"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2967,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3019},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 4: Outside the Gate",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Bósi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nDwarf-workers can be found north of Bósi's encampment, all along the winding road that runs up to the Hollin Gate.\nBósi has asked you to deliver lunches to the dwarves charged with unearthing the rubble in front of the Hollin Gate, and to then report to Wárr.\n* Turn in Prepared Lunch\n* Turn in Prepared Lunch\n* Turn in Prepared Lunch\n* Turn in Prepared Lunch\n* Turn in Prepared Lunch\n* Turn in Prepared Lunch\n* Turn in Prepared Lunch\nObj 2:\nThe dwarf Wárr is at the Hollin Gate, supervising the workers there.\nNow that you have delivered the lunches to the dwarf-workers along the road to the Hollin Gate, you should speak with Wárr for further engagement.\n* Talk to Wárr\nObj 3:\nBósi is overseeing some of the waggons near the banks of the dried-up Sirannon, south of the road that winds up to the Hollin Gate.\nWárr has asked you to deliver a supply of broken pickaxes to Bósi and to request replacements.\n* Talk to Bósi\n* Turn in Broken Pick-axe"},
{["next"]={3023},zone="Eregion",area="Walls of Moria",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Bósi has tasked you with collecting the materials necessary for producing new pickaxes to replace the ones broken by the dwarves at the Hollin Gate.",mobs={{locations={"51.37S, 5.89W"},name="Bósi"}},selectoneof={{val="Bósi's Necklace",id="70017CBE"},{val="Elnaith",id="70017CD3"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2968,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3020},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 5: Handling the Situation",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,pois={{locations={"50.85S, 6.63W","51.02S, 5.89W","50.52S, 5.36W","50.18S, 6.16W","52.25S, 5.36W","50.71S, 6.63W","50.81S, 5.52W","52.97S, 7.09W","51.46S, 6.65W","50.22S, 5.71W","50.66S, 6.03W","50.30S, 5.49W","50.93S, 6.12W","50.90S, 5.41W","52.37S, 5.63W","51.90S, 5.65W","50.86S, 6.15W","51.35S, 6.03W","52.60S, 7.13W","50.56S, 6.27W","50.22S, 5.84W","50.67S, 5.34W","51.03S, 6.57W","50.61S, 6.37W","52.75S, 7.34W","52.20S, 5.48W","51.02S, 5.65W","51.27S, 6.10W","51.91S, 5.46W","52.77S, 7.31W","50.30S, 6.13W","51.47S, 6.30W","50.74S, 6.62W","52.19S, 5.74W","52.61S, 7.17W","50.35S, 6.27W"},name="Thick Branch"}},minlevel=45,b="Bósi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThick branches can be found at the base of trees in the area around the Hollin Gate. Bori is likely talking to his friend Bróin at the stairs east of Bósi.\nBósi has asked you to collect thick branches with which to make sturdy pick-handles and to help his son Bori with the task of gathering sharpening stones.\n* Help Bori with the task Bósi gave him\n* Bring thick branches to Bósi\n* Collect thick branches (6 Thick Branch )\nObj 2:\nBósi is west of the stairs leading up to the fetid lake in front of the Hollin Gate.\nBósi is waiting to speak with you now that sufficient materials for new pickaxes have been gathered.\n* Talk to Bósi"},
{zone="Eregion",area="Walls of Moria",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Bori was charged with gathering suitable stones upon which to sharpen the pickaxes for workers at the Hollin Gate.",mobs={{locations={"51.20S, 5.11W"},name="Bori"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2969,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3020},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 5: Keeping Sharp",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,pois={{locations={"52.07S, 6.49W","52.08S, 6.89W","51.63S, 7.13W","51.65S, 5.84W","51.31S, 5.31W","51.52S, 5.58W","51.48S, 7.28W","52.03S, 6.26W","52.07S, 6.66W","51.02S, 7.46W","51.57S, 5.65W","51.82S, 6.18W","51.36S, 5.36W","51.88S, 7.19W","51.55S, 5.70W","51.37S, 5.39W","51.93S, 7.15W","51.92S, 6.28W","51.18S, 7.42W","51.13S, 7.36W","51.43S, 7.32W","51.72S, 5.86W","51.93S, 5.97W"},name="Eregion Stone (Level 1)"}},minlevel=45,b="Bori",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nStones can be found along the dry bed of the Sirannon, but not every stone is suitably sharp.\nBori is waiting for you to bring him enough stones to sharpen the pickaxes needed by the workers unearthing the Hollin Gate.\n* Collect sharp Eregion stones (6 Eregion Stone (Level 1) )\nObj 2:\nBori is at the base of the stairs that lead up to the fetid lake in front of the Hollin Gate. Stones can be found along the dry bed of the Sirannon, but not every stone is suitably sharp.\nBori is waiting for you to bring him enough stones to sharpen the pickaxes required by the workers unearthing the Hollin Gate.\n* Talk to Bori\n* Turn in Eregion Stone (Level 1)",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={3024,3025},zone="Eregion",area="Walls of Moria",d="Bósi thanked you for your part in gathering materials for the crafting of new pickaxes, and sent you to Brogur so you may lend your aid to his cousin.",mobs={{locations={"50.34S, 5.59W"},name="Brogur"},{locations={"51.37S, 5.89W"},name="Bósi"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2970,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3021},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 6: Cousin Brogur",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Bósi",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nBósi's cousin Brogur is somewhere along the road that winds up to the Hollin Gate, north of Bósi's position.\nBósi has asked you to lend your aid to his cousin Brogur while the pickaxes are being crafted.\n* Talk to Brogur",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{zone="Eregion",area="Walls of Moria",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="Brogur's son Bróin has asked for your help fighting off the dangerous Shadow-wargs that lurk beyond the Sirannon's banks.",mobs={{locations={"51.20S, 5.10W"},name="Bróin"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2971,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3023},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 7: The Glorious Tale of Bróin the Mighty",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Bróin",repeatable="No",o="Obj 1:\nShadow-wargs can be found south of the stairs that lead up to the pool in front of the Hollin Gate, on the other side of the Sirannon's dry river-bed.\nBróin has somehow managed to foist his task off on you, and now you have to face the Shadow-wargs in his stead.\n* Defeat Shadow-wargs (3)\nObj 2:\nBróin is at the base of the stairs that climb up to the fetid pool in front of the Hollin Gate, east of Bósi's location.\nYou have defeated many Shadow-wargs and should return now to Bróin.\n* Talk to Bróin",faction="FrP",instanced="No"},
{["next"]={3026},zone="Eregion",area="Walls of Moria",money={{val="9s 94c"}},d="Brogur is concerned about the unusually aggressive behaviour of the wolves in the area and wants them dealt with.",mobs={{locations={"50.34S, 5.59W"},name="Brogur"},{locations={"51.37S, 5.89W"},name="Bósi"}},selectoneof={{val="Bróin's Ring",id="70017CBF"},{val="Brogur's Cloak",id="70017C9D"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2972,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3023},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 7: Wolf-voices on the Wind",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,pois={{locations={"52.53S, 6.88W","52.66S, 7.31W","52.98S, 7.27W","52.56S, 7.08W"},name="Burned Wolf-corpse"}},minlevel=45,b="Brogur",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nThe cause of the wolves' fearsome behaviour may be found among their lairs, south of Brogur's location and across the Sirannon's dry river-bed. Brogur believes the cave Filgogân may hold some clue to the wolves' madness, in the far southwestern corner of the area. Bróin can be seen talking to Bori at the base of the stairs that climb to the pool in front of the Hollin Gate.\nBrogur has asked you to search for the cause of the shadow-wolves growing madness, and to help his son Bróin with a task. When you have done each of these things, he told you to speak with his cousin Bósi.\n* Use Burned Wolf-corpse\n* Help Bróin with the task Brogur gave him\nObj 2:\nBósi is south of Brogur's location, in view of the stairs that lead up to the pool in front of the Hollin Gate.\nYou have learned something of the Shadow-wargs' madness and aided Bróin with his task, and have been asked to speak now with Bósi.\n* Talk to Bósi"},
{["next"]={3027},zone="Eregion",area="Walls of Moria",money={{val="24s 85c"}},d="The dwarves of Bósi and Brogur's expedition await the opening of the Doors of Durin.",mobs={{locations={"50.63S, 7.62W"},name="Ráthwald"},{locations={"51.37S, 5.89W"},name="Bósi"}},selectoneof={{val="Survivor's Blade",id="70017CD1"},{val="Survivor's Bracelet",id="70017CBB"},{val="Survivor's Vest",id="70017CA2"},{val="Survivor's Robe",id="70017CA0"},{val="Survivor's Armour",id="70017C9E"}},category="Epic - Vol. II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",id=2973,scope="Epic",t="Epic",prev={3025},name="Vol. II, Book 1, Chapter 8: Before the Doors of Durin",arcs="Volume II, Book 1: The Walls of Moria",level=50,minlevel=45,b="Bósi",repeatable="No",faction="FrP",instanced="No",o="Obj 1:\nBósi is waiting at his small camp to travel with you to the Doors of Durin.\nBósi's dwarves have repaired the pickaxes, and now he wants you to bring them to the workers with him.\n* Talk to Bósi and travel to the Doors of Durin\nObj 2:\nRáthwald is outside the arch near the camp of Echad Dúnan, in Eregion.\nThe dwarves have retreated in disarray from the Doors of Durin, and must now plan for the uncertain future.\n* Talk to Ráthwald"},
